WEBVTT

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:16.859
Scholastic Audio presents Wings of Fire

00:00:16.859 --> 00:00:20.940
Book 3, The Hidden Kingdom, by 2 E T

00:00:20.940 --> 00:00:23.760
Sutherland, read by Shannon McManus.

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:46.679
The Dragonette Prophecy.

00:00:46.740 --> 00:00:50.820
When the war has lasted 20 years, the

00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:53.880
dragonettes will come, when the land is

00:00:53.880 --> 00:00:56.579
soaked in blood and tears, the

00:00:56.579 --> 00:00:57.780
dragonettes will come.

00:00:57.899 --> 00:01:01.799
Find the sea wing egg of deepest blue

00:01:01.799 --> 00:01:04.379
wings of night shall come to you.

00:01:04.439 --> 00:01:08.400
The largest egg in mountain high will

00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:10.019
give to you the wings of sky.

00:01:10.079 --> 00:01:13.620
For wings of earth, search through the

00:01:13.620 --> 00:01:16.980
mud, for an egg the color of dragon blood

00:01:16.980 --> 00:01:20.579
and hidden alone from the rival queens.

00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:23.760
The sand wing egg awaits unseen.

00:01:23.819 --> 00:01:28.379
Of 3 queens who blister and blaze and

00:01:28.379 --> 00:01:28.859
burn.

00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:33.299
Two shall die, and one shall learn, If

00:01:33.299 --> 00:01:35.579
she bows to a fate that is stronger and

00:01:35.579 --> 00:01:38.700
higher, Shall have the power of wings of

00:01:38.700 --> 00:01:39.060
fire.

00:01:39.120 --> 00:01:43.739
Five eggs to hatch on brightest night

00:01:43.739 --> 00:01:46.560
five dragons born to end the fight.

00:01:46.620 --> 00:01:50.159
Darkness will rise to bring the light.

00:01:50.219 --> 00:01:53.340
The dragonettes are coming.

00:02:05.400 --> 00:02:10.020
Prologue.

00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:13.139
The five Dragonettes were fighting.

00:02:13.199 --> 00:02:17.280
Again, bright scales in green and red and

00:02:17.280 --> 00:02:19.740
gold caught the rising sun as the young

00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:22.379
dragons darted between the rocks, claws

00:02:22.379 --> 00:02:23.099
and teeth flashing.

00:02:23.219 --> 00:02:26.759
Five forked tongues hissed with fury.

00:02:26.819 --> 00:02:30.000
Beyond them, below the cliff, the sea

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:31.979
crashed against the sand with a muffled

00:02:31.979 --> 00:02:34.139
rushing sound, as if it didn't want to

00:02:34.139 --> 00:02:35.639
compete with the shouts of the dragons.

00:02:35.699 --> 00:02:38.639
It was embarrassing, was what it was.

00:02:38.699 --> 00:02:41.819
Nautilus glanced up uneasily at the

00:02:41.819 --> 00:02:43.379
massive black dragon beside him.

00:02:43.439 --> 00:02:45.840
The dragonettes were so busy yelling at

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:47.639
one another that they hadn't even noticed

00:02:47.639 --> 00:02:48.060
him yet.

00:02:48.120 --> 00:02:51.000
Nautilus wished he could read Morrow

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:53.639
Seer's mind, the way Morrow Seer was

00:02:53.639 --> 00:02:54.659
undoubtedly reading his.

00:02:54.719 --> 00:02:57.780
He also wished there were more talons of

00:02:57.780 --> 00:03:00.240
peace around, but when word spread that

00:03:00.240 --> 00:03:02.460
the night wing was coming, most of them

00:03:02.460 --> 00:03:03.840
suddenly found urgent missions

00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:04.500
elsewhere.

00:03:04.560 --> 00:03:06.900
The peace movements hideout in the

00:03:06.900 --> 00:03:09.240
seaside cliffs, was virtually deserted

00:03:09.240 --> 00:03:09.599
this morning.

00:03:09.659 --> 00:03:12.960
Occasionally a dragon snout would emerge

00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:16.139
from one of the caves, spot Morosier, and

00:03:16.139 --> 00:03:17.099
instantly vanish again.

00:03:17.159 --> 00:03:20.759
The 5 dragonettes were the only ones on

00:03:20.759 --> 00:03:22.860
top of the cliffs, although there were

00:03:22.860 --> 00:03:24.539
several other young dragons living with

00:03:24.539 --> 00:03:26.460
the talents of peace, they'd all been

00:03:26.460 --> 00:03:27.539
whisked out of sight.

00:03:27.599 --> 00:03:30.120
But apparently no one had seen fit to

00:03:30.120 --> 00:03:32.400
warn the objects of Morrow Seers' scrutiny

00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:34.379
that he was coming, or that they were

00:03:34.379 --> 00:03:35.340
going to be inspected.

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:39.000
Well, Maro Seer said.

00:03:39.060 --> 00:03:40.500
They are.

00:03:40.500 --> 00:03:42.360
Energetic.

00:03:42.419 --> 00:03:45.419
They were just a backup plan.

00:03:45.479 --> 00:03:47.520
Nautilus said defensively.

00:03:47.580 --> 00:03:50.580
Nobody thought we'd need them, especially

00:03:50.580 --> 00:03:51.180
not all of them.

00:03:51.240 --> 00:03:54.599
We thought maybe one or two if something

00:03:54.599 --> 00:03:55.740
went wrong with the originals.

00:03:55.800 --> 00:03:58.379
We haven't spent a lot of time training

00:03:58.379 --> 00:03:58.740
them.

00:03:58.860 --> 00:04:01.139
I can see that.

00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:05.099
Moro Seer's dark eyes narrowed as Viper.

00:04:05.159 --> 00:04:07.919
The sand wing fell into a crevice, and

00:04:07.919 --> 00:04:09.840
the mud wing promptly tripped and landed

00:04:09.840 --> 00:04:10.259
on top of her.

00:04:10.379 --> 00:04:13.500
With a hiss, Viper whipped around and bit

00:04:13.500 --> 00:04:16.139
Ocher's tail, setting off a yowling

00:04:16.139 --> 00:04:16.620
whine.

00:04:16.680 --> 00:04:20.339
Excuse me, Nautilus said.

00:04:20.399 --> 00:04:21.959
He could see where this was going.

00:04:22.019 --> 00:04:25.139
He stepped forward, cuffed Viper's ears

00:04:25.139 --> 00:04:27.599
and snatched Squid, the little green sea

00:04:27.599 --> 00:04:29.159
wing out of the way before the others

00:04:29.159 --> 00:04:30.539
could set his tail on fire.

00:04:30.600 --> 00:04:33.540
Stop this. he hissed.

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:35.040
You are being watched.

00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:38.939
Flame, the red Sky Wing Dragonette

00:04:38.939 --> 00:04:41.040
snapped his mouth shut and whipped his

00:04:41.040 --> 00:04:43.259
head around, scanning the twisted rocks

00:04:43.259 --> 00:04:44.220
of the sea cliff.

00:04:44.339 --> 00:04:47.160
Maro Seer stepped into the light of the

00:04:47.160 --> 00:04:49.019
sunrise. and look down his snout

00:04:49.019 --> 00:04:49.620
majestically.

00:04:49.680 --> 00:04:54.000
I knew it, crowed the little Nightwing

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:54.660
Dragonette.

00:04:54.779 --> 00:04:57.360
Fate speaker leaped off a stone pillar

00:04:57.360 --> 00:04:58.800
flapping her wings proudly.

00:04:58.860 --> 00:05:00.959
I knew a nightwing was coming to see us.

00:05:01.019 --> 00:05:02.160
Didn't I tell you guys this would

00:05:02.160 --> 00:05:02.339
happen?

00:05:02.459 --> 00:05:04.379
Did you?

00:05:04.500 --> 00:05:07.379
Ogre scratched his large brown head.

00:05:07.439 --> 00:05:09.779
No, said Viper.

00:05:09.839 --> 00:05:13.019
Don't think so, piped up Squid from

00:05:13.019 --> 00:05:14.339
behind Nautilus's back.

00:05:14.399 --> 00:05:17.160
Even if you did, you also predicted an

00:05:17.160 --> 00:05:19.259
earthquake, a new talent of peace and

00:05:19.259 --> 00:05:21.540
that we'd have something besides seagulls

00:05:21.540 --> 00:05:23.939
for breakfast this week, said Flame.

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:25.740
And since none of those things have

00:05:25.740 --> 00:05:27.540
happened, you can see why we might have

00:05:27.540 --> 00:05:28.259
stopped listening.

00:05:28.379 --> 00:05:32.279
Well, I knew, fate speaker said

00:05:32.279 --> 00:05:32.939
blithely.

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:36.839
I thought with my powers, and I foresee

00:05:36.839 --> 00:05:39.000
that he brought us something great for

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:40.560
breakfast, didn't you?

00:05:40.620 --> 00:05:43.259
She beamed up at Maro Seer.

00:05:43.319 --> 00:05:44.639
He blinked slowly.

00:05:44.699 --> 00:05:46.560
Hmm.

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:48.360
Nautilus.

00:05:48.420 --> 00:05:50.459
A word, please.

00:05:50.519 --> 00:05:52.259
Can I come too?

00:05:52.319 --> 00:05:55.139
The black dragonette asked, bouncing

00:05:55.139 --> 00:05:56.339
closer tomorrow's seer.

00:05:56.399 --> 00:05:57.899
I've never met another night wing

00:05:57.899 --> 00:05:58.139
before.

00:05:58.199 --> 00:06:01.439
Although, of course, I feel a very strong

00:06:01.439 --> 00:06:03.779
psychic connection with our whole tribe.

00:06:03.899 --> 00:06:06.540
Stay here.

00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:09.899
Marosi pressed one claw into her chest

00:06:09.899 --> 00:06:11.579
and moved her back to the other

00:06:11.579 --> 00:06:12.540
dragonettes.

00:06:12.600 --> 00:06:15.000
She sat down and curled her tail around

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:16.680
her talons with a huffing snort.

00:06:16.740 --> 00:06:20.040
Morosier stepped down the rocks, out of

00:06:20.040 --> 00:06:20.459
earshot.

00:06:20.519 --> 00:06:23.339
When he turned, he found Nautilus right

00:06:23.339 --> 00:06:24.060
behind him.

00:06:24.120 --> 00:06:26.759
The clinging to his tail was the sea wing

00:06:26.759 --> 00:06:27.899
dragonette.

00:06:27.959 --> 00:06:30.420
Maro seer gazed at Squid disapprovingly.

00:06:30.480 --> 00:06:33.300
I can't leave him alone with them

00:06:33.300 --> 00:06:35.699
Nautilus said apologetically.

00:06:35.759 --> 00:06:38.160
Whenever I'm not watching, one of them

00:06:38.160 --> 00:06:38.699
bites him.

00:06:38.759 --> 00:06:43.680
Or, they all do, sniffed the small green

00:06:43.680 --> 00:06:44.220
dragon.

00:06:44.279 --> 00:06:47.579
Maro Seer flicked his tongue out and in

00:06:47.579 --> 00:06:48.420
considering.

00:06:48.540 --> 00:06:53.160
It is clear to me, said the enormous

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:54.060
night wing after a moment.

00:06:54.120 --> 00:06:56.699
That leaving the dragonettes of the

00:06:56.699 --> 00:06:58.560
prophecy and the care of the talons of

00:06:58.560 --> 00:07:00.540
peace was a mistake.

00:07:00.600 --> 00:07:04.860
Both the real ones and the false ones.

00:07:04.920 --> 00:07:06.600
Who?

00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:08.579
asked the dragonette.

00:07:08.639 --> 00:07:12.240
Hush, said Nautilus, covering the

00:07:12.240 --> 00:07:14.100
dragonette's snout with one talent.

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:16.560
He saw the look on Maru Seer's face and

00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:20.220
added hastily, You remember, Squid, we

00:07:20.220 --> 00:07:21.779
taught you about the prophecy?

00:07:21.839 --> 00:07:24.000
You know the war that all the dragon

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:25.139
tribes are fighting?

00:07:25.199 --> 00:07:28.860
The one you want to stop, Squid said.

00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:30.660
Because we're the good guys.

00:07:30.720 --> 00:07:31.860
We want peace.

00:07:31.920 --> 00:07:34.800
Right, said Nautilus.

00:07:34.860 --> 00:07:36.540
Basically, right.

00:07:36.600 --> 00:07:39.600
So the prophecy says that 5 dragonettes

00:07:39.600 --> 00:07:42.180
were hatched about 6 years ago, a sea

00:07:42.180 --> 00:07:46.319
wing, a sky wing, a mud wing, a sand wing

00:07:46.319 --> 00:07:48.899
and a night wing, who are going to end

00:07:48.899 --> 00:07:49.439
the war.

00:07:49.500 --> 00:07:52.920
They get to choose which sister should be

00:07:52.920 --> 00:07:54.600
the new sandwing queen.

00:07:54.660 --> 00:07:58.500
Burn, blister, or blaze.

00:07:58.620 --> 00:08:01.800
Oh, said Squid.

00:08:01.860 --> 00:08:05.040
Hey, I hatched about 6 years ago.

00:08:05.100 --> 00:08:07.800
Really?

00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:09.240
said Morrow Seer.

00:08:09.300 --> 00:08:12.779
You're barely in the size of a 3 year old

00:08:12.779 --> 00:08:13.680
dragonette.

00:08:13.740 --> 00:08:18.000
I have a big personality, Squid informed

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:19.980
him, as if he had been told this enough

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:21.839
times that he was certain everyone knew

00:08:21.839 --> 00:08:22.019
it.

00:08:22.139 --> 00:08:25.500
And your friends are about 6 years old

00:08:25.500 --> 00:08:25.920
too.

00:08:25.980 --> 00:08:27.899
Nautilus said quickly.

00:08:27.959 --> 00:08:30.600
They're not my friends.

00:08:30.660 --> 00:08:31.680
Squid grumbled.

00:08:31.740 --> 00:08:34.679
They're all bullies, except for Fate

00:08:34.679 --> 00:08:36.899
Speaker, who is plain crazy.

00:08:36.960 --> 00:08:40.440
Maro Sierr glanced back at fate speaker

00:08:40.440 --> 00:08:42.299
the Nightwing Dragonette.

00:08:42.360 --> 00:08:43.980
She was sitting on top of a twisted stone

00:08:43.980 --> 00:08:46.620
column, leaning so far toward them that

00:08:46.620 --> 00:08:48.000
she looked in imminent danger of

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:49.980
overbalancing and toppling off.

00:08:50.039 --> 00:08:53.460
Well, squid, Nautilus said.

00:08:53.519 --> 00:08:55.679
What if you were one of the dragonettes

00:08:55.679 --> 00:08:56.279
in the prophecy?

00:08:56.340 --> 00:08:58.379
What would you think about that?

00:08:58.440 --> 00:09:02.220
The Sea Wing gave Marosir a canny look?

00:09:02.279 --> 00:09:04.919
Would I get treasure?

00:09:04.980 --> 00:09:10.620
You'd get fame, and power, said Morris

00:09:10.620 --> 00:09:11.039
Seer.

00:09:11.100 --> 00:09:14.220
If you did what you were told, that is.

00:09:14.399 --> 00:09:17.220
How about treasure?

00:09:17.279 --> 00:09:18.360
Squid insisted.

00:09:18.480 --> 00:09:21.240
Maru Seer gave Nautilus an incredulous

00:09:21.240 --> 00:09:21.419
look.

00:09:21.539 --> 00:09:24.480
Is this dragonette?

00:09:24.539 --> 00:09:25.919
Bargaining with me?

00:09:25.980 --> 00:09:29.940
I like treasure, Squid pointed out.

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:33.480
A talented peace are so lame because none

00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:34.320
of them have any treasure.

00:09:34.440 --> 00:09:39.539
We gave up worldly things to fight for a

00:09:39.539 --> 00:09:41.759
higher cause, Nautilus said.

00:09:41.820 --> 00:09:44.399
Peace is more important than jewels or

00:09:44.399 --> 00:09:44.639
gold.

00:09:44.759 --> 00:09:48.059
Nah, said Squid.

00:09:48.120 --> 00:09:49.559
I'd rather have gold.

00:09:49.620 --> 00:09:54.179
Would you be willing to choose whichever

00:09:54.179 --> 00:09:58.200
sandwing queen we told you to, Marosir

00:09:58.200 --> 00:09:58.559
asked.

00:09:58.620 --> 00:10:03.600
If so, we could perhaps talk about gold.

00:10:03.659 --> 00:10:08.700
All right, Squid said, with a gleam in

00:10:08.700 --> 00:10:09.000
his eye.

00:10:09.059 --> 00:10:11.519
But I don't want Flame to be part of it.

00:10:11.580 --> 00:10:12.899
He has to stay here.

00:10:12.960 --> 00:10:15.000
Why?

00:10:15.120 --> 00:10:18.059
What's wrong with your Sky Wing?

00:10:18.120 --> 00:10:20.639
Maro Sierr asked Nautilus.

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:21.960
Nothing.

00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:23.100
Nautilus said.

00:10:23.159 --> 00:10:25.500
They are just having a fight today.

00:10:25.559 --> 00:10:29.820
And every day, Squid said, because he's

00:10:29.820 --> 00:10:30.059
mean.

00:10:30.120 --> 00:10:35.580
The Sky Wing is non-negotiable, said Maro

00:10:35.580 --> 00:10:35.940
Seer.

00:10:36.059 --> 00:10:39.960
You're non-negotiable, Squid said.

00:10:40.019 --> 00:10:44.100
Squid, be polite, said Nautilus tiredly.

00:10:44.159 --> 00:10:48.899
I foresee that I am going to regret this

00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:51.779
said Maru Seer, frowning down at the sea

00:10:51.779 --> 00:10:52.320
wings.

00:10:52.320 --> 00:10:55.500
But I will be taking over the training of

00:10:55.500 --> 00:10:56.820
the prophecy dragonette.

00:10:56.879 --> 00:11:00.899
They have been mishandled for too long.

00:11:01.019 --> 00:11:04.440
Obviously they need clearer guidance.

00:11:04.500 --> 00:11:06.480
What does that mean?

00:11:06.539 --> 00:11:07.980
Nautilus asked.

00:11:08.039 --> 00:11:10.200
A sense of dread was starting to creep

00:11:10.200 --> 00:11:11.100
across his scales.

00:11:11.159 --> 00:11:12.840
He glanced at Squid.

00:11:12.899 --> 00:11:14.820
Perhaps they should have chosen a

00:11:14.820 --> 00:11:16.440
different sea wing to be the fake

00:11:16.440 --> 00:11:17.639
dragonette of the prophecy.

00:11:17.700 --> 00:11:20.700
If Maru seer hurts squid.

00:11:20.759 --> 00:11:24.899
If anything happens to him, his mother is

00:11:24.899 --> 00:11:27.600
going to kill me, Nautilus thought.

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:30.720
It means they're coming with me.

00:11:30.779 --> 00:11:33.899
Maro Seer said, with a flick of his

00:11:33.899 --> 00:11:34.139
tail.

00:11:34.259 --> 00:11:35.820
Where?

00:11:35.940 --> 00:11:37.019
Squid demanded.

00:11:37.080 --> 00:11:41.759
You'll find out when we get there, said

00:11:41.759 --> 00:11:42.659
Marusir.

00:11:42.720 --> 00:11:44.519
And if you know what's good for you

00:11:44.519 --> 00:11:47.940
you'll stop asking nosy questions and do

00:11:47.940 --> 00:11:48.659
what you're told.

00:11:48.720 --> 00:11:53.340
I can do that, Squid said, but good luck

00:11:53.340 --> 00:11:54.480
with Flame and Viper.

00:11:54.600 --> 00:11:55.860
He thought for a moment.

00:11:55.919 --> 00:11:58.559
And fate speaker. for that matter.

00:11:58.620 --> 00:12:02.340
Wait, no, said Nautilus.

00:12:02.399 --> 00:12:04.679
He tried to fill his mind with noise, so

00:12:04.679 --> 00:12:05.879
the Nightwing couldn't read his

00:12:05.879 --> 00:12:06.120
thoughts.

00:12:06.179 --> 00:12:10.799
You can't take them, except for fate

00:12:10.799 --> 00:12:12.059
speaker who came from you.

00:12:12.120 --> 00:12:14.279
All their parents are talents.

00:12:14.340 --> 00:12:16.500
That's how we got their eggs in the 1st

00:12:16.500 --> 00:12:16.860
place.

00:12:16.980 --> 00:12:19.320
They won't want them to leave.

00:12:19.440 --> 00:12:23.220
Except ogre, Squid offered.

00:12:23.279 --> 00:12:24.899
His mom won't care.

00:12:24.960 --> 00:12:26.279
It's a mud wing thing.

00:12:26.340 --> 00:12:28.259
Shut up.

00:12:28.320 --> 00:12:30.059
Said Morrow Seer.

00:12:30.120 --> 00:12:32.460
He studied Nautilus with narrow black

00:12:32.460 --> 00:12:32.820
eyes.

00:12:32.940 --> 00:12:34.679
Don't think it.

00:12:34.740 --> 00:12:35.759
Don't think it.

00:12:35.879 --> 00:12:37.080
Don't think it.

00:12:37.139 --> 00:12:39.299
Nautilus repeated to himself.

00:12:39.360 --> 00:12:44.100
Three moons, Maro Seer said with

00:12:44.100 --> 00:12:44.519
disgust.

00:12:44.580 --> 00:12:48.240
This dragonet, is your son?

00:12:48.360 --> 00:12:52.919
Nautilus stared down at his claws, and it

00:12:52.919 --> 00:12:54.659
seems like a good idea when the talons

00:12:54.659 --> 00:12:56.820
1st decided to have backup dragonettes.

00:12:56.940 --> 00:13:00.720
Squid hatched around the right time, if

00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:03.779
not exactly on the brightest night, and

00:13:03.779 --> 00:13:05.100
it meant that everyone in the movement

00:13:05.100 --> 00:13:07.019
treated the dragonette like the precious

00:13:07.019 --> 00:13:08.460
creature Nautilus knew he was.

00:13:08.580 --> 00:13:11.940
Of course I am. said Squid.

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:13.799
Isn't that a funny coincidence?

00:13:13.860 --> 00:13:15.240
Wow.

00:13:15.299 --> 00:13:17.879
I'm the son of the leader of the talons

00:13:17.879 --> 00:13:20.879
of peace, and a dragonette of destiny.

00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:23.039
He puffed out his chest.

00:13:23.100 --> 00:13:25.379
I'm even more important than I thought I

00:13:25.379 --> 00:13:25.679
was.

00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:28.080
He strutted off toward the other

00:13:28.080 --> 00:13:30.659
Dragonettes, having forgotten. as he

00:13:30.659 --> 00:13:32.940
often did that none of them liked hearing

00:13:32.940 --> 00:13:35.100
about how important he was, and that he

00:13:35.100 --> 00:13:36.720
would almost certainly end up with a

00:13:36.720 --> 00:13:38.159
singed snout before long.

00:13:38.220 --> 00:13:41.700
Nautilus watched him go, wondering how

00:13:41.700 --> 00:13:43.019
everything had gone so wrong.

00:13:43.080 --> 00:13:45.899
Why had the talons agreed to work with

00:13:45.899 --> 00:13:46.679
Maru Seer?

00:13:46.740 --> 00:13:48.840
Why had they decided to get involved with

00:13:48.840 --> 00:13:50.100
a prophecy in the 1st place?

00:13:50.159 --> 00:13:52.500
And how had they lost the real

00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:53.580
Dragonettes?

00:13:53.639 --> 00:13:55.440
That was the question that drove him

00:13:55.440 --> 00:13:55.799
crazy.

00:13:55.860 --> 00:13:59.279
Kestrel Dune and Webbs should have been

00:13:59.279 --> 00:14:01.740
able to keep a handle on 5 dragonettes

00:14:01.740 --> 00:14:03.720
especially when they were conveniently

00:14:03.720 --> 00:14:05.039
trapped in a secret cave.

00:14:05.100 --> 00:14:08.039
Instead, the 5 had escaped.

00:14:08.100 --> 00:14:11.519
Then possibly killed Queen Scarlet of the

00:14:11.519 --> 00:14:13.919
Sky Wings, thrown the Sky Kingdom into

00:14:13.919 --> 00:14:16.679
upheaval, turned Queen Coral against her

00:14:16.679 --> 00:14:19.740
allies, wrecked the Sea Wing Palace, and

00:14:19.740 --> 00:14:21.360
disappeared once more into the wild

00:14:21.360 --> 00:14:22.320
Zapira.

00:14:22.379 --> 00:14:25.980
Worse yet, there was no one to punish.

00:14:26.039 --> 00:14:29.340
Kestrel and June were dead, while Webbs

00:14:29.340 --> 00:14:30.960
had wriggled away from the talons and

00:14:30.960 --> 00:14:32.940
vanished, and who knew where the

00:14:32.940 --> 00:14:35.159
dragonets were, or when they'd turn up

00:14:35.159 --> 00:14:37.080
again with their spectacular talent for

00:14:37.080 --> 00:14:38.039
trouble and chaos.

00:14:38.100 --> 00:14:42.240
Quite a coincidence.

00:14:42.299 --> 00:14:46.019
Maro Seer echoed Squid's remark, sounding

00:14:46.019 --> 00:14:47.340
rather unimpressed.

00:14:47.399 --> 00:14:50.460
Well, said Nautilus.

00:14:50.519 --> 00:14:51.720
I thought why not?

00:14:51.840 --> 00:14:54.000
Of course, none of these 5 actually

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:56.639
hatched on the brightest night, or else

00:14:56.639 --> 00:14:58.980
they'd be the real dragonets of the

00:14:58.980 --> 00:14:59.940
prophecy, wouldn't they?

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:02.639
But they are about the right age, and

00:15:02.639 --> 00:15:04.379
nobody has to know the rest.

00:15:04.440 --> 00:15:09.120
Except anyone who was at their hatching.

00:15:09.240 --> 00:15:10.799
Marosia mused.

00:15:10.860 --> 00:15:13.500
It would be tidier if we could kill any

00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:14.159
witnesses.

00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:16.320
Nautilus blanched.

00:15:16.440 --> 00:15:20.159
Do their parents count as witnesses?

00:15:20.220 --> 00:15:22.919
He wondered, before he could squelch the

00:15:22.919 --> 00:15:23.159
thought.

00:15:23.220 --> 00:15:26.820
We'll cross that bridge when we come to

00:15:26.820 --> 00:15:29.159
it, Marosier said briskly.

00:15:29.220 --> 00:15:31.980
Since we can't be sure yet which of these

00:15:31.980 --> 00:15:34.019
we'll use and which we'll discard.

00:15:34.139 --> 00:15:37.500
He frowned at fate speaker, who was

00:15:37.500 --> 00:15:39.000
eagerly interrogating squid.

00:15:39.059 --> 00:15:41.519
Nautilus felt properly faint now.

00:15:41.580 --> 00:15:43.620
Discard?

00:15:43.679 --> 00:15:44.759
He echoed.

00:15:44.879 --> 00:15:46.740
Moro Seer snorted.

00:15:46.799 --> 00:15:48.539
Very well.

00:15:48.600 --> 00:15:51.720
I'll try to bring yours back in one

00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:52.500
piece.

00:15:52.559 --> 00:15:55.500
He wrinkled his snout, looking as close

00:15:55.500 --> 00:15:57.840
to amused as Nautilus had ever seen him.

00:15:57.960 --> 00:16:02.279
But isn't peace, the most important thing

00:16:02.279 --> 00:16:03.000
Seawing?

00:16:03.120 --> 00:16:06.059
Don't you tell your talons all the time

00:16:06.059 --> 00:16:09.240
that any sacrifice must be made to end

00:16:09.240 --> 00:16:09.779
this war.

00:16:09.840 --> 00:16:14.879
Yes, but the alternate dragonets were

00:16:14.879 --> 00:16:16.259
your idea in the 1st place.

00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:20.279
A good idea, as it turns out, since the

00:16:20.279 --> 00:16:21.899
real ones have proven to be so

00:16:21.899 --> 00:16:24.480
unsatisfactory.

00:16:24.600 --> 00:16:27.299
Marasir hissed softly.

00:16:27.360 --> 00:16:30.779
So we get rid of the most dangerous

00:16:30.779 --> 00:16:31.019
ones.

00:16:31.080 --> 00:16:33.899
I train their replacements myself.

00:16:33.960 --> 00:16:37.320
He smiled in a way that made Nautilus

00:16:37.320 --> 00:16:39.840
feel queasy. right down to his claws.

00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:44.700
And then, We make sure the prophecy is

00:16:44.700 --> 00:16:45.539
fulfilled.

00:16:45.600 --> 00:16:47.580
The way it was supposed to be.

00:16:47.639 --> 00:16:52.080
Chapter one.

00:16:52.139 --> 00:16:55.440
It had been raining for 5 days.

00:16:55.500 --> 00:16:58.259
Glory officially hated it.

00:16:58.320 --> 00:17:01.679
She also was not enjoying the comments

00:17:01.679 --> 00:17:04.380
from the other dragonettes about how as a

00:17:04.380 --> 00:17:05.339
rain wing.

00:17:05.400 --> 00:17:06.480
She should love this weather.

00:17:06.539 --> 00:17:09.660
She most certainly did not love this

00:17:09.660 --> 00:17:09.900
weather.

00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:12.480
In the caves under the mountain.

00:17:12.599 --> 00:17:15.059
The dragoness had never, ever been rained

00:17:15.059 --> 00:17:15.299
on.

00:17:15.359 --> 00:17:18.119
This downpour felt unnatural and

00:17:18.119 --> 00:17:21.179
unstoppable and horribly, unpleasantly

00:17:21.179 --> 00:17:22.199
wet.

00:17:22.259 --> 00:17:26.279
I don't care if a real rain wing is

00:17:26.279 --> 00:17:28.799
supposed to like this, she thought, as

00:17:28.799 --> 00:17:31.319
droplets rolled off her snout, seeped

00:17:31.319 --> 00:17:33.420
through her scales, and soaked her wings

00:17:33.420 --> 00:17:35.220
until they dragged heavily behind her.

00:17:35.339 --> 00:17:38.579
If they do, there's something wrong with

00:17:38.579 --> 00:17:38.759
them.

00:17:38.880 --> 00:17:41.819
No sensible dragon should enjoy weather

00:17:41.819 --> 00:17:43.740
that makes it so hard to fly.

00:17:43.799 --> 00:17:45.660
Three moons.

00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:48.180
Please let them be sensible dragons.

00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:50.279
Let them be nothing like the stories.

00:17:50.400 --> 00:17:54.359
Everyone said rain wings were useless and

00:17:54.359 --> 00:17:55.140
lazy.

00:17:55.200 --> 00:17:57.359
But the tribe lived off by themselves in

00:17:57.359 --> 00:17:59.279
the rainforest, where no one ever saw

00:17:59.279 --> 00:17:59.519
them.

00:17:59.579 --> 00:18:01.440
So everyone might be wrong.

00:18:01.500 --> 00:18:04.440
Glory was really hoping they were wrong.

00:18:04.500 --> 00:18:07.920
She shook her whole body and glared at

00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:09.359
the fog shrouded sky.

00:18:09.420 --> 00:18:11.940
What she wanted was more sun.

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:15.180
She'd missed the sun her whole life and

00:18:15.180 --> 00:18:17.700
had known it until it hit her scales the

00:18:17.700 --> 00:18:18.720
day they left the caves.

00:18:18.779 --> 00:18:21.779
More long sunny days would be fine by

00:18:21.779 --> 00:18:22.140
her.

00:18:22.200 --> 00:18:24.539
Instead, there was this.

00:18:24.599 --> 00:18:30.900
Rain, mud, more rain, more mud, plus one

00:18:30.900 --> 00:18:33.720
moaning, groaning, dripping, slow poke of

00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:34.799
a wounded sea wing.

00:18:34.859 --> 00:18:37.319
Can we stop?

00:18:37.559 --> 00:18:38.460
Webbs gasped.

00:18:38.519 --> 00:18:39.779
I need to rest.

00:18:39.900 --> 00:18:42.599
He floundered through the mud to a

00:18:42.599 --> 00:18:44.160
slightly drier spot under a tree.

00:18:44.220 --> 00:18:46.799
Glory narrowed her eyes at him as the

00:18:46.799 --> 00:18:49.019
blue green dragon flopped to the ground.

00:18:49.079 --> 00:18:51.059
The other dragonettes stopped too

00:18:51.059 --> 00:18:52.859
exchanging glances.

00:18:52.920 --> 00:18:54.960
They were walking today instead of flying

00:18:54.960 --> 00:18:57.000
because Webbs said it was easier on his

00:18:57.000 --> 00:18:59.519
injury, and yet he still asked to stop

00:18:59.519 --> 00:19:00.779
nearly every 10 steps.

00:19:00.839 --> 00:19:03.779
Glory was starting to suspect he didn't

00:19:03.779 --> 00:19:05.220
really want them to get to the

00:19:05.220 --> 00:19:05.819
rainforest.

00:19:05.940 --> 00:19:07.619
But why?

00:19:07.680 --> 00:19:08.819
She wondered.

00:19:08.880 --> 00:19:10.740
Is he hiding something?

00:19:10.799 --> 00:19:13.140
Does it have to do with my parents?

00:19:13.200 --> 00:19:16.619
As the guardian who had stolen her from

00:19:16.619 --> 00:19:18.539
the rain wing tribe in the 1st place

00:19:18.539 --> 00:19:20.940
Webbs should have been a helpful fount of

00:19:20.940 --> 00:19:22.319
knowledge about where she came from.

00:19:22.380 --> 00:19:25.859
Instead, he got all mumbly and forgetful

00:19:25.859 --> 00:19:27.720
whenever they asked about the rainforest

00:19:27.720 --> 00:19:28.200
dragons.

00:19:28.259 --> 00:19:31.799
Clay paced over to Webbs and peered down

00:19:31.799 --> 00:19:32.400
at his wound.

00:19:32.519 --> 00:19:35.160
They'd wrapped it with seaweed soaked in

00:19:35.160 --> 00:19:37.319
ocean water for as long as they could, but

00:19:37.319 --> 00:19:39.119
now they were too far inland to get any

00:19:39.119 --> 00:19:39.240
more.

00:19:39.299 --> 00:19:43.079
The poisoned scratch near Webb's tail had

00:19:43.079 --> 00:19:45.299
become an ugly gash, surrounded by

00:19:45.299 --> 00:19:48.000
blackened scales, and the black seemed to

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:49.140
spread a bit more each day.

00:19:49.200 --> 00:19:51.960
None of them had any idea what to do to

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:53.640
combat sandwing poison.

00:19:53.700 --> 00:19:57.599
Not to mention, we have no idea why

00:19:57.599 --> 00:19:59.940
blister wanted webs dead so badly.

00:20:00.059 --> 00:20:04.259
I mean, I think he's awful, but she

00:20:04.259 --> 00:20:05.099
doesn't even know him.

00:20:05.160 --> 00:20:08.880
Glory glanced at Starflight, the Black

00:20:08.880 --> 00:20:10.200
Knight Wing, who was the smartest

00:20:10.200 --> 00:20:12.720
dragonette she knew, and probably still

00:20:12.720 --> 00:20:14.400
would be, even if she knew more than 4

00:20:14.400 --> 00:20:15.000
dragons.

00:20:15.059 --> 00:20:17.460
She wondered if he had any theories about

00:20:17.460 --> 00:20:18.299
blister and webs.

00:20:18.359 --> 00:20:21.420
Clay swept his tail through the mud

00:20:21.420 --> 00:20:22.200
looking worried.

00:20:22.259 --> 00:20:25.920
I hope the rain wings can help him, he

00:20:25.920 --> 00:20:26.160
said.

00:20:26.220 --> 00:20:28.920
This isn't exactly like their venom.

00:20:28.980 --> 00:20:31.440
But maybe they'll have more ideas than we

00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:31.680
do.

00:20:31.740 --> 00:20:34.380
Glory shook out her wings and looked

00:20:34.380 --> 00:20:34.740
away.

00:20:34.799 --> 00:20:36.299
She didn't care.

00:20:36.359 --> 00:20:38.640
The other Dragonettes felt some kind of

00:20:38.640 --> 00:20:40.859
misguided loyalty to their old guardian

00:20:40.859 --> 00:20:43.079
as if it was their responsibility to save

00:20:43.079 --> 00:20:43.380
him.

00:20:43.440 --> 00:20:46.259
She was the only one who seemed to

00:20:46.259 --> 00:20:48.119
remember how he'd been willing to stand

00:20:48.119 --> 00:20:49.799
by and let someone kill her.

00:20:49.859 --> 00:20:52.920
Stealing her egg had been his idea too.

00:20:53.039 --> 00:20:56.460
The prophecy called for a sky wing, but

00:20:56.460 --> 00:20:58.559
when the talons lost their sky wing egg

00:20:58.559 --> 00:21:00.900
before it hatched, Webbs had decided to

00:21:00.900 --> 00:21:02.220
replace it with a rain wing.

00:21:02.279 --> 00:21:05.279
It was his fault Glory had been forced to

00:21:05.279 --> 00:21:07.619
grow up under the mountain, far from her

00:21:07.619 --> 00:21:09.599
home and family, learning about a

00:21:09.599 --> 00:21:11.160
prophecy that didn't even have a place

00:21:11.160 --> 00:21:11.759
for her in it.

00:21:11.819 --> 00:21:14.220
It was easy for the others.

00:21:14.279 --> 00:21:16.440
There was no question about their

00:21:16.440 --> 00:21:17.039
destiny.

00:21:17.099 --> 00:21:18.839
But glory.

00:21:18.900 --> 00:21:21.119
If she was meant to help save the world

00:21:21.119 --> 00:21:23.400
then why hadn't the prophecy called for a

00:21:23.400 --> 00:21:24.000
rain wing?

00:21:24.059 --> 00:21:27.000
And if she wasn't necessary for this big

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:29.940
grand destiny, then what was the point of

00:21:29.940 --> 00:21:30.660
her life at all?

00:21:30.720 --> 00:21:34.140
Maybe it was all one big mistake?

00:21:34.200 --> 00:21:36.960
But when she thought like that, she ended

00:21:36.960 --> 00:21:38.759
up having violent dreams about ripping

00:21:38.759 --> 00:21:39.420
webs apart.

00:21:39.480 --> 00:21:41.940
So, better not to think about it.

00:21:42.059 --> 00:21:44.519
Destiny would have to sort itself out.

00:21:44.579 --> 00:21:47.160
Right now, she was going home.

00:21:47.220 --> 00:21:50.579
The branch above glory suddenly dipped

00:21:50.579 --> 00:21:52.380
and dumped a lake's worth of water onto

00:21:52.380 --> 00:21:55.200
her head, she leaped back with a hiss and

00:21:55.200 --> 00:21:56.160
glared up into the tree.

00:21:56.220 --> 00:21:59.279
Shh, tsunami said from above.

00:21:59.339 --> 00:22:01.740
She dropped down to the ground and peered

00:22:01.740 --> 00:22:02.819
around at the gloomy swamp.

00:22:02.880 --> 00:22:05.579
There's a pair of mud wings headed this

00:22:05.579 --> 00:22:07.200
way, but they'll never see us in this

00:22:07.200 --> 00:22:07.440
weather.

00:22:07.500 --> 00:22:11.220
Rolls of thick gray fog hung over the mud

00:22:11.220 --> 00:22:13.500
wreathing the stunted trees like smoke

00:22:13.500 --> 00:22:16.019
around a dragon's horns, it was hard to

00:22:16.019 --> 00:22:17.220
tell what time of day it was.

00:22:17.279 --> 00:22:20.400
The sky was gray in every direction. and

00:22:20.400 --> 00:22:22.559
the rain drizzled down unrelentingly.

00:22:22.619 --> 00:22:25.140
Glory agreed with tsunami.

00:22:25.200 --> 00:22:26.940
A dragon could barely see her own

00:22:26.940 --> 00:22:28.980
wingtips in this, let alone another

00:22:28.980 --> 00:22:29.460
dragon.

00:22:29.519 --> 00:22:33.539
We should still hide, Starflight said

00:22:33.539 --> 00:22:34.019
anxiously.

00:22:34.079 --> 00:22:36.599
We're only a day's flight from Queen

00:22:36.599 --> 00:22:37.920
Warren's palace right now.

00:22:37.980 --> 00:22:43.140
If we get caught, more prison, Clay said

00:22:43.140 --> 00:22:45.960
with a sigh, every queen they'd met so

00:22:45.960 --> 00:22:47.940
far seemed determined to keep the

00:22:47.940 --> 00:22:49.859
dragonettes trapped under her claws.

00:22:49.920 --> 00:22:52.740
They'd escaped Queen Scarlet's prison in

00:22:52.740 --> 00:22:55.019
the Sky Kingdom only because of Glory's

00:22:55.019 --> 00:22:57.779
venom, a secret weapon even she had known

00:22:57.779 --> 00:22:58.980
about until she'd needed it.

00:22:59.039 --> 00:23:01.619
She touched her forked tongue to her

00:23:01.619 --> 00:23:03.299
fangs. and glanced at the sky.

00:23:03.420 --> 00:23:07.019
They still had no idea if Queen Scarlet

00:23:07.019 --> 00:23:08.519
had survived Glory's attack.

00:23:08.579 --> 00:23:11.460
Given their luck, Glory was pretty sure

00:23:11.460 --> 00:23:13.680
Scarlet was alive and planning some

00:23:13.680 --> 00:23:14.519
horrible revenge.

00:23:14.640 --> 00:23:17.700
After that escape, they'd gone looking

00:23:17.700 --> 00:23:19.859
for safety with Tsunami's mother, Queen

00:23:19.859 --> 00:23:21.660
Coral of the Sea Wings.

00:23:21.720 --> 00:23:23.700
Of course, Coral had decided to lock them

00:23:23.700 --> 00:23:24.119
up as well.

00:23:24.240 --> 00:23:26.460
Glory hadn't been surprised.

00:23:26.519 --> 00:23:29.039
Not even family could be trusted when it

00:23:29.039 --> 00:23:29.880
came to the prophecy.

00:23:29.940 --> 00:23:32.640
Everyone had their own plans for how this

00:23:32.640 --> 00:23:33.420
war should end.

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:36.839
So if Queen Mohen of the Mudwings found

00:23:36.839 --> 00:23:39.180
them in her territory, She probably

00:23:39.180 --> 00:23:41.220
wasn't going to give them tea and send

00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:41.700
them on their way.

00:23:41.759 --> 00:23:45.059
The mudwing queen held court beside a

00:23:45.059 --> 00:23:47.099
large lake on the southern edge of the

00:23:47.099 --> 00:23:47.759
mud kingdom.

00:23:47.819 --> 00:23:51.000
Glory remembered the map of Pyria, and a

00:23:51.000 --> 00:23:52.500
shiver of realization ran down her

00:23:52.500 --> 00:23:52.799
spine.

00:23:52.859 --> 00:23:55.680
If Starflight was right, and they were

00:23:55.680 --> 00:23:56.940
only a day's flight from there.

00:23:57.000 --> 00:23:59.099
Then they must be only a day's flight

00:23:59.099 --> 00:24:00.299
from the rainforest as well.

00:24:00.359 --> 00:24:02.220
From the rainforest.

00:24:02.279 --> 00:24:04.799
And Glory's tribe.

00:24:04.920 --> 00:24:08.640
And then, I'll belong somewhere.

00:24:08.700 --> 00:24:11.579
The rain wings won't care that I'm not in

00:24:11.579 --> 00:24:12.299
some prophecy.

00:24:12.359 --> 00:24:15.660
Glory, tsunami scolded.

00:24:15.779 --> 00:24:17.759
Bright yellow scales are the one thing

00:24:17.759 --> 00:24:18.599
they might see.

00:24:18.720 --> 00:24:20.220
Go back to camouflage.

00:24:20.279 --> 00:24:23.099
Glory glanced down and saw the star

00:24:23.099 --> 00:24:24.660
bursts of gold that had appeared all

00:24:24.660 --> 00:24:25.500
across her scales.

00:24:25.559 --> 00:24:28.799
Those meant happiness or excitement, as

00:24:28.799 --> 00:24:31.200
far as she knew, since she'd seen them

00:24:31.200 --> 00:24:33.720
pretty rarely in her life, it drove her

00:24:33.720 --> 00:24:35.640
crazy when her scales changed color

00:24:35.640 --> 00:24:37.859
without her telling them to, they did

00:24:37.859 --> 00:24:38.759
that way too often.

00:24:38.819 --> 00:24:41.400
She had to squash every big emotion

00:24:41.400 --> 00:24:42.960
before it splashed all over her.

00:24:43.019 --> 00:24:46.319
She concentrated on the steady drip drip

00:24:46.319 --> 00:24:48.720
of the swamp around them, staring down at

00:24:48.720 --> 00:24:50.880
the thick brown mud oozing through her

00:24:50.880 --> 00:24:51.240
claws.

00:24:51.299 --> 00:24:54.299
She imagined the fog winding around her

00:24:54.299 --> 00:24:56.460
wings, slipping into the cracks in her

00:24:56.460 --> 00:24:59.160
scales and spreading like gray clouds

00:24:59.160 --> 00:25:00.299
rolling across the sky.

00:25:00.359 --> 00:25:05.339
And she's gone, Tsunami said.

00:25:05.460 --> 00:25:07.019
She's still there?

00:25:07.079 --> 00:25:08.339
Sonny piped up.

00:25:08.460 --> 00:25:11.220
She edged closer to glory and bumped into

00:25:11.220 --> 00:25:11.940
one of her wings.

00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:13.740
See, right there.

00:25:13.859 --> 00:25:16.920
She stretched out a talent, but glory

00:25:16.920 --> 00:25:17.640
moved out of reach.

00:25:17.700 --> 00:25:20.220
Sonny felt around in the air for a moment

00:25:20.220 --> 00:25:21.059
and then gave up.

00:25:21.119 --> 00:25:23.880
The little sand wing had been unusually

00:25:23.880 --> 00:25:25.259
quiet for the last few days.

00:25:25.319 --> 00:25:28.500
Glory guest Sonny hated the rain too.

00:25:28.559 --> 00:25:30.720
The desert dragons were designed for

00:25:30.720 --> 00:25:33.900
steering heat, blazing sun, and endless

00:25:33.900 --> 00:25:34.980
clear sky days.

00:25:35.039 --> 00:25:38.099
Even an odd looking sandwing like Sonny

00:25:38.099 --> 00:25:40.079
still had the instincts of her tribe.

00:25:40.140 --> 00:25:43.200
Really, Clay was the only one happy about

00:25:43.200 --> 00:25:43.740
the weather.

00:25:43.799 --> 00:25:46.619
Only a mud wing could appreciate the

00:25:46.619 --> 00:25:48.480
squishing and squashing under their claws

00:25:48.480 --> 00:25:49.980
as they traveled through the swamp.

00:25:50.039 --> 00:25:52.619
Starflight swiveled his head suddenly.

00:25:52.680 --> 00:25:56.279
I think I smell someone coming, he

00:25:56.279 --> 00:25:56.700
whispered.

00:25:56.759 --> 00:25:59.279
He shuddered from horns to claws.

00:25:59.339 --> 00:26:02.940
Don't panic, tsunami whispered back.

00:26:03.000 --> 00:26:04.920
Clay, you hide me in Sonny.

00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:07.440
Starflight, find a shadow and do your

00:26:07.440 --> 00:26:09.539
invisible petrified night wing thing.

00:26:09.599 --> 00:26:11.759
Glory, you can shield webs.

00:26:11.819 --> 00:26:13.619
No, thanks.

00:26:13.740 --> 00:26:15.420
Glory said immediately.

00:26:15.480 --> 00:26:17.819
She wasn't going anywhere near Webbs

00:26:17.880 --> 00:26:19.200
certainly not to save his life.

00:26:19.259 --> 00:26:20.940
I'll take Sonny.

00:26:21.000 --> 00:26:23.640
She didn't like touching other dragons

00:26:23.640 --> 00:26:25.799
but Sonny was better than webs.

00:26:25.859 --> 00:26:29.339
But tsunami started, stamping her foot.

00:26:29.400 --> 00:26:31.140
Glory ignored her.

00:26:31.200 --> 00:26:33.720
She lifted one wing and tugged the little

00:26:33.720 --> 00:26:35.279
gold dragon in close to her side.

00:26:35.279 --> 00:26:37.980
When she lowered her wing again, Sonny

00:26:37.980 --> 00:26:39.420
was hidden by Glory's gray brown

00:26:39.420 --> 00:26:40.200
camouflage.

00:26:40.259 --> 00:26:42.960
Yikes, Clay said.

00:26:43.019 --> 00:26:45.000
That was so weird.

00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:47.460
Like Sonny just got eaten by the fog.

00:26:47.519 --> 00:26:50.640
His stomach grumbled woefully at the word

00:26:50.640 --> 00:26:53.099
eaten, and the mud wing shuffled his big

00:26:53.099 --> 00:26:54.059
feet in embarrassment.

00:26:54.119 --> 00:26:56.940
Starflight peered at the spot where Sonny

00:26:56.940 --> 00:26:59.039
had just been twisting his claws in the

00:26:59.039 --> 00:26:59.279
mud.

00:26:59.339 --> 00:27:02.099
She's fine, Glory said.

00:27:02.160 --> 00:27:04.019
They'll follow orders like a good

00:27:04.019 --> 00:27:06.420
dragonette, or tsunami might fling you to

00:27:06.420 --> 00:27:06.900
the eels.

00:27:06.960 --> 00:27:09.839
Tsunami frowned in her direction, but

00:27:09.839 --> 00:27:12.180
Starflight slunk away and found a dark

00:27:12.180 --> 00:27:14.519
tree hollow where his black scales melted

00:27:14.519 --> 00:27:15.900
into the shadows.

00:27:15.960 --> 00:27:17.400
Now Glory could hear it too.

00:27:17.460 --> 00:27:21.359
The tramp squelch, tramp squelch, of

00:27:21.359 --> 00:27:23.579
enormous claws, marching through the

00:27:23.579 --> 00:27:24.180
swamp toward them.

00:27:24.240 --> 00:27:26.640
The heat from Sunny's scales was

00:27:26.640 --> 00:27:28.200
uncomfortably warm against her side.

00:27:28.259 --> 00:27:31.380
Webbs hadn't moved while they talked.

00:27:31.440 --> 00:27:33.539
He lay curled against the tree roots

00:27:33.539 --> 00:27:35.759
snout resting on his tail, looking

00:27:35.759 --> 00:27:36.299
miserable.

00:27:36.420 --> 00:27:40.619
Clay shepherded tsunami up next to webs

00:27:40.619 --> 00:27:42.839
and spread his mud colored wings to hide

00:27:42.839 --> 00:27:43.140
them both.

00:27:43.200 --> 00:27:46.680
It wasn't a perfect solution, a blue tail

00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:48.839
stuck out on one side, the edge of blue

00:27:48.839 --> 00:27:51.299
green wings on the other, but in this fog

00:27:51.299 --> 00:27:53.519
they looked mostly like a blobby mound of

00:27:53.519 --> 00:27:55.140
mud, which should be good enough.

00:27:55.200 --> 00:27:58.799
Tramp squelch, tramp, squelch.

00:27:58.859 --> 00:28:01.019
I don't like this patrol.

00:28:01.140 --> 00:28:03.000
A deep voice grumbled.

00:28:03.059 --> 00:28:04.559
Glory nearly jumped.

00:28:04.619 --> 00:28:06.599
It sounded like it was coming from 2

00:28:06.599 --> 00:28:07.200
trees away.

00:28:07.259 --> 00:28:10.920
Too close to that creepy rainforest if

00:28:10.920 --> 00:28:11.400
you ask me.

00:28:11.460 --> 00:28:15.599
It's not really haunted, said a 2nd

00:28:15.599 --> 00:28:15.839
voice.

00:28:15.900 --> 00:28:18.180
You know, the only things that live there

00:28:18.180 --> 00:28:20.400
are birds and lazy rain wings.

00:28:20.460 --> 00:28:23.640
Years of learning self-control kept glory

00:28:23.640 --> 00:28:25.019
from glinching.

00:28:25.079 --> 00:28:28.019
She'd heard lazy rain wings thrown around

00:28:28.019 --> 00:28:29.940
often enough by the guardians under the

00:28:29.940 --> 00:28:32.579
mountain, but it felt like an extra stab

00:28:32.579 --> 00:28:33.720
in the eye to hear it from a total

00:28:33.720 --> 00:28:34.200
stranger.

00:28:34.259 --> 00:28:38.579
If that were true, said the 1st voice

00:28:38.579 --> 00:28:40.859
then her majesty would let us hunt in

00:28:40.859 --> 00:28:43.619
there, but she knows it's not safe, and

00:28:43.619 --> 00:28:44.819
you've heard the noises at night.

00:28:44.880 --> 00:28:47.759
Are you telling me it's the rain wings

00:28:47.759 --> 00:28:48.900
screaming like that?

00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:51.180
Screaming.

00:28:51.240 --> 00:28:54.599
Under Glory's wing, Sunny turned her head

00:28:54.599 --> 00:28:56.160
a little, as if she were trying to hear

00:28:56.160 --> 00:28:56.400
better.

00:28:56.460 --> 00:28:59.880
Not to mention the dead bodies.

00:28:59.940 --> 00:29:01.680
The 1st voice muttered.

00:29:01.799 --> 00:29:05.160
That's not some kind of rainforest

00:29:05.160 --> 00:29:08.279
monster, said the 2nd guard, but there

00:29:08.279 --> 00:29:09.839
was a tilt in her tone that sounded

00:29:09.839 --> 00:29:10.440
unsure.

00:29:10.440 --> 00:29:12.240
That's the war.

00:29:12.299 --> 00:29:15.000
Some kind of gorilla attacks to scare

00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:15.180
us.

00:29:15.240 --> 00:29:17.700
All the way down here.

00:29:17.759 --> 00:29:20.880
Why would the sea wings or the ice wings

00:29:20.880 --> 00:29:23.099
come all this way to kill one or 2 mud

00:29:23.099 --> 00:29:23.759
wings here and there?

00:29:23.880 --> 00:29:25.980
There are bigger battles going on

00:29:25.980 --> 00:29:26.640
everywhere else.

00:29:26.700 --> 00:29:30.839
Let's go a bit faster, said the 2nd voice

00:29:30.839 --> 00:29:31.440
uneasily.

00:29:31.500 --> 00:29:34.200
They should really let us patrol in

00:29:34.200 --> 00:29:35.880
threes or 4s instead of in pairs.

00:29:35.940 --> 00:29:38.160
Tell me about it.

00:29:38.220 --> 00:29:41.579
Tramp, squelch, tramp, squelch.

00:29:41.640 --> 00:29:44.460
So what do you think about the Sky Wing

00:29:44.460 --> 00:29:44.940
situation?

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:47.759
Are you for Ruby, or do you think?

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:51.299
Glory strained her ears, but their voices

00:29:51.299 --> 00:29:54.000
faded into the mist as the 2 mud winged

00:29:54.000 --> 00:29:55.140
soldiers splashed away.

00:29:55.200 --> 00:29:57.960
She badly wanted to know what the sky

00:29:57.960 --> 00:29:59.099
wing situation was.

00:29:59.220 --> 00:30:01.680
Maybe her friends wouldn't notice if she

00:30:01.680 --> 00:30:02.519
slipped away for a moment.

00:30:02.579 --> 00:30:06.240
Be right back, she whispered to Sonny

00:30:06.240 --> 00:30:08.640
lifting her wing and stepping away.

00:30:08.700 --> 00:30:10.619
Sonny caught her tail, wide eyed.

00:30:10.680 --> 00:30:11.819
Don't go.

00:30:11.880 --> 00:30:13.019
She whispered.

00:30:13.079 --> 00:30:13.859
It's not safe.

00:30:13.920 --> 00:30:15.299
You heard what they said.

00:30:15.359 --> 00:30:18.240
About rainforest monsters?

00:30:18.299 --> 00:30:20.339
Glory rolled her eyes.

00:30:20.400 --> 00:30:22.380
Can't say I'm terribly worried about

00:30:22.380 --> 00:30:22.559
that.

00:30:22.619 --> 00:30:24.000
I won't go far.

00:30:24.059 --> 00:30:26.579
She shook Sonny off and slipped after the

00:30:26.579 --> 00:30:27.119
soldiers.

00:30:27.180 --> 00:30:29.279
Carefully stepping only on the dry

00:30:29.279 --> 00:30:31.440
patches so her claws wouldn't splash in

00:30:31.440 --> 00:30:31.859
the mud.

00:30:31.920 --> 00:30:34.440
It was weirdly quiet in the swamp

00:30:34.440 --> 00:30:36.900
especially with the fog muffling most

00:30:36.900 --> 00:30:37.319
sounds.

00:30:37.380 --> 00:30:39.960
She tried to follow the distant rumble of

00:30:39.960 --> 00:30:41.940
voices, and what she thought might be the

00:30:41.940 --> 00:30:43.920
sound of marching mud wing talons.

00:30:43.980 --> 00:30:46.680
But after a few moments, even those

00:30:46.680 --> 00:30:47.819
became impossible to hear.

00:30:47.940 --> 00:30:50.160
She stopped, listening.

00:30:50.220 --> 00:30:51.900
The trees dripped.

00:30:51.960 --> 00:30:54.539
Rain drizzled moodily through the

00:30:54.539 --> 00:30:54.960
branches.

00:30:55.079 --> 00:30:57.900
Small gurgles burbled out of the mud here

00:30:57.900 --> 00:30:59.640
and there, as if the swamp were

00:30:59.640 --> 00:31:00.240
hiccuping.

00:31:00.299 --> 00:31:03.240
And then a scream tore through the air.

00:31:03.299 --> 00:31:07.259
Glory's rough flared in fear, and pale

00:31:07.259 --> 00:31:09.240
green stripes zigzagged through her

00:31:09.240 --> 00:31:10.140
scales.

00:31:10.200 --> 00:31:12.660
She fought back her terror, focusing her

00:31:12.660 --> 00:31:14.160
colors back to gray and brown.

00:31:14.220 --> 00:31:15.480
Glory!

00:31:15.539 --> 00:31:17.880
Sonny yelled, behind her somewhere.

00:31:17.940 --> 00:31:18.900
Shut up.

00:31:19.019 --> 00:31:20.700
Glory thought furiously.

00:31:20.759 --> 00:31:22.380
Don't draw attention.

00:31:22.440 --> 00:31:24.180
Don't let anything know we're here.

00:31:24.240 --> 00:31:26.940
The other dragonettes must have had the

00:31:26.940 --> 00:31:28.799
same thought and stopped her, because

00:31:28.799 --> 00:31:30.000
Sonny didn't call out again.

00:31:30.059 --> 00:31:33.720
Unless it was one of them who screamed.

00:31:33.779 --> 00:31:35.640
But it couldn't have been.

00:31:35.759 --> 00:31:37.980
The scream had come from somewhere up

00:31:37.980 --> 00:31:38.339
ahead.

00:31:38.400 --> 00:31:41.519
Glory checked her scales again to make

00:31:41.519 --> 00:31:43.740
sure she was well hidden and then sped up

00:31:43.740 --> 00:31:45.660
hurrying through the trees toward the

00:31:45.660 --> 00:31:45.900
screen.

00:31:45.960 --> 00:31:48.539
The fog was so dense.

00:31:48.599 --> 00:31:51.059
She nearly missed the 2 dark lumps that

00:31:51.059 --> 00:31:53.700
looked like fallen logs, but her claws

00:31:53.700 --> 00:31:55.559
came down on something that was decidedly

00:31:55.559 --> 00:31:57.599
a dragon tail, and she leaped back.

00:31:57.660 --> 00:32:00.599
Two brown dragons were sprawled in the

00:32:00.599 --> 00:32:03.240
mud, surrounded by pools of blood that

00:32:03.240 --> 00:32:04.680
were already being washed away by the

00:32:04.680 --> 00:32:04.920
rain.

00:32:04.980 --> 00:32:07.380
Their throats had been ripped out so

00:32:07.380 --> 00:32:09.420
viciously that their heads were nearly

00:32:09.420 --> 00:32:10.500
severed from their bodies.

00:32:10.559 --> 00:32:14.339
Glory stared into the rolling gray fog.

00:32:14.400 --> 00:32:17.400
But nothing moved out there, except the

00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:17.700
rain.

00:32:17.759 --> 00:32:21.480
The mud winged soldiers were dead, and

00:32:21.480 --> 00:32:23.099
there was no sign of what had killed

00:32:23.099 --> 00:32:23.279
them.

00:32:23.339 --> 00:32:27.359
Chapter 2.

00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:32.039
Remind me why we're walking toward the

00:32:32.039 --> 00:32:34.140
place where the monster and the screaming

00:32:34.140 --> 00:32:37.019
and the something that kills dragons, Clay

00:32:37.019 --> 00:32:37.319
asked.

00:32:37.380 --> 00:32:40.740
We could go somewhere else, Starflight

00:32:40.740 --> 00:32:41.099
said.

00:32:41.160 --> 00:32:42.900
Maybe to the ice wings?

00:32:42.960 --> 00:32:45.960
Ice wings, yes.

00:32:46.019 --> 00:32:47.039
Clay said.

00:32:47.099 --> 00:32:49.440
That sounds like a great plan.

00:32:49.500 --> 00:32:50.519
Let's do that.

00:32:50.579 --> 00:32:53.339
No mysterious dragon killing things in

00:32:53.339 --> 00:32:54.599
the ice kingdom, right?

00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:57.000
What are those animals they have up

00:32:57.000 --> 00:32:57.240
there?

00:32:57.299 --> 00:32:58.920
Penguins?

00:32:58.980 --> 00:33:01.440
I bet I could beat a penguin or 2 in

00:33:01.440 --> 00:33:01.799
battle?

00:33:01.859 --> 00:33:02.579
couldn't I?

00:33:02.700 --> 00:33:04.140
How big are they?

00:33:04.200 --> 00:33:06.480
Maybe just one penguin.

00:33:06.539 --> 00:33:09.420
So we can freeze to death instead?

00:33:09.539 --> 00:33:10.500
Glory said.

00:33:10.559 --> 00:33:13.799
A rumor, and a couple of dead soldiers

00:33:13.799 --> 00:33:15.839
were not going to scare her away from her

00:33:15.839 --> 00:33:17.519
home when she was finally this close.

00:33:17.640 --> 00:33:20.640
Fantastic plans, Starflight.

00:33:20.700 --> 00:33:22.920
Not to mention that Ice Kingdom is half a

00:33:22.920 --> 00:33:25.079
continent away, while the rainforest is

00:33:25.079 --> 00:33:25.440
right here.

00:33:25.500 --> 00:33:29.700
Besides, webs will never make it all the

00:33:29.700 --> 00:33:30.660
way to the ice kingdom.

00:33:30.660 --> 00:33:32.400
Sunny chimed in.

00:33:32.460 --> 00:33:34.920
She glanced nervously up at the trees

00:33:34.920 --> 00:33:36.779
which seemed to be getting taller and

00:33:36.779 --> 00:33:37.680
taller as they walked.

00:33:37.799 --> 00:33:40.799
It was also warmer the farther they went

00:33:40.799 --> 00:33:42.839
and up in the vines overhead.

00:33:42.900 --> 00:33:44.640
Glory could see flashes of color.

00:33:44.700 --> 00:33:47.279
The bright summer yellows and purples and

00:33:47.279 --> 00:33:49.500
blues might have been birds or flowers

00:33:49.500 --> 00:33:51.539
but they were definitely not typical of

00:33:51.539 --> 00:33:54.299
the brown, brown, brown, mud kingdom.

00:33:54.359 --> 00:33:57.180
Glory wasn't sure, but she guessed the

00:33:57.180 --> 00:33:58.859
dragonettes were in the rainforest for

00:33:58.859 --> 00:33:59.339
real now.

00:33:59.460 --> 00:34:02.700
The gnarled claw shapes of the marsh

00:34:02.700 --> 00:34:05.339
trees were half a day behind them, and so

00:34:05.339 --> 00:34:06.779
were the mud wing bodies.

00:34:06.839 --> 00:34:09.239
Tsunami had wanted to stop and search the

00:34:09.239 --> 00:34:10.199
area for clues.

00:34:10.260 --> 00:34:12.000
But she'd been outvoted by the other

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:14.519
dragonettes when Starflight pointed out

00:34:14.519 --> 00:34:16.920
that now they'd really be in trouble, if

00:34:16.920 --> 00:34:18.360
they were caught right next to a double

00:34:18.360 --> 00:34:18.719
murder.

00:34:18.780 --> 00:34:21.119
Not to mention whatever had killed the

00:34:21.119 --> 00:34:22.860
soldiers couldn't have gone far.

00:34:22.920 --> 00:34:26.039
That was enough to get everyone, even

00:34:26.039 --> 00:34:27.780
Webbs, to fly through the night.

00:34:27.840 --> 00:34:30.539
And they'd circle down to walk again only

00:34:30.539 --> 00:34:32.340
once the sun was up, and they were

00:34:32.340 --> 00:34:33.000
looking for food.

00:34:33.059 --> 00:34:36.840
See, Gloria said to Clay and Starflight.

00:34:36.900 --> 00:34:39.420
Even Sonny is acting braver than you

00:34:39.420 --> 00:34:40.500
scaredy scavengers.

00:34:40.559 --> 00:34:43.079
Even sunny?

00:34:43.139 --> 00:34:44.579
The Sandwing flared.

00:34:44.699 --> 00:34:46.079
What's that supposed to mean?

00:34:46.139 --> 00:34:47.279
I'm brave.

00:34:47.340 --> 00:34:49.019
I'm brave all the time.

00:34:49.139 --> 00:34:51.839
She lashed her tail and ducked away when

00:34:51.839 --> 00:34:53.219
clay reached to patter on the head.

00:34:53.280 --> 00:34:56.519
Warm bursts of sunlight, nudged through

00:34:56.519 --> 00:34:58.679
the leafy canopy, making all their scales

00:34:58.679 --> 00:34:59.159
glow.

00:34:59.219 --> 00:35:01.739
Glory letter scales turn whatever color

00:35:01.739 --> 00:35:02.340
they wanted.

00:35:02.400 --> 00:35:05.219
A shimmery beetle green spread all over

00:35:05.219 --> 00:35:07.559
her, touched here and there with curls of

00:35:07.559 --> 00:35:08.099
amber.

00:35:08.219 --> 00:35:10.199
She liked the feeling of matching the

00:35:10.199 --> 00:35:11.340
trees and sunbeams.

00:35:11.400 --> 00:35:15.719
We'll be there soon, she thought, with a

00:35:15.719 --> 00:35:16.679
shiver of anticipation.

00:35:16.739 --> 00:35:19.739
But I mustn't get my hopes up.

00:35:19.800 --> 00:35:21.659
Maybe it won't be what I imagined.

00:35:21.719 --> 00:35:24.239
It just has to be better than life under

00:35:24.239 --> 00:35:26.820
the mountain, trapped in a cave by

00:35:26.820 --> 00:35:27.900
guardians who hate me.

00:35:27.960 --> 00:35:30.360
I'm not setting the bar too high here, I

00:35:30.360 --> 00:35:30.539
think.

00:35:30.599 --> 00:35:34.019
Something crackled off to their left, but

00:35:34.019 --> 00:35:36.179
when Glory whipped around, all she saw

00:35:36.179 --> 00:35:39.000
was a shaggy gray sloth, hanging from a

00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:41.039
tree and blinking sleepily at her.

00:35:41.099 --> 00:35:45.119
Have I mentioned this place makes me

00:35:45.119 --> 00:35:45.780
nervous?

00:35:45.840 --> 00:35:46.980
Clay asked.

00:35:47.099 --> 00:35:50.460
Only about a 1000 times, Glory said.

00:35:50.519 --> 00:35:53.159
I wish we knew what the mudwings were

00:35:53.159 --> 00:35:54.840
talking about, Sunny said.

00:35:54.900 --> 00:35:57.059
How can they live right next to the

00:35:57.059 --> 00:35:58.679
rainforest and not know why it's

00:35:58.679 --> 00:35:58.980
dangerous?

00:35:59.039 --> 00:36:02.519
How can the rain wings live in the

00:36:02.519 --> 00:36:04.440
rainforest if it's all that dangerous?

00:36:04.559 --> 00:36:06.119
Glory countered.

00:36:06.179 --> 00:36:08.159
Webbs sniffed faintly.

00:36:08.219 --> 00:36:10.860
The 1st sound he'd made in a while, he

00:36:10.860 --> 00:36:13.679
muttered, Because they're rain wings.

00:36:13.739 --> 00:36:15.420
They probably haven't even noticed.

00:36:15.480 --> 00:36:17.820
Glory glared at him.

00:36:17.940 --> 00:36:20.639
Maybe you'd like a matching venomous

00:36:20.639 --> 00:36:23.519
wound on your other side, she snarled.

00:36:23.579 --> 00:36:26.400
Tsunami whirled and grabbed Webb's

00:36:26.400 --> 00:36:26.820
snout.

00:36:26.880 --> 00:36:29.340
The bigger Sea Wing snorted with surprise

00:36:29.340 --> 00:36:31.500
and tried to jerk back, but she held him

00:36:31.500 --> 00:36:33.300
firmly so she could glare into his face.

00:36:33.360 --> 00:36:35.699
All right, enough.

00:36:35.760 --> 00:36:37.260
What do you know about this?

00:36:37.320 --> 00:36:38.519
She demanded.

00:36:38.579 --> 00:36:40.619
You're the only one who's been to the

00:36:40.619 --> 00:36:41.159
rainforest.

00:36:41.219 --> 00:36:43.019
Does it have some kind of monster?

00:36:43.079 --> 00:36:46.260
She shook his snout, none too gently.

00:36:46.320 --> 00:36:49.199
Stop drooping like a wet fern and tell us

00:36:49.199 --> 00:36:49.619
what you know.

00:36:49.679 --> 00:36:53.760
Nothing, Webbs mumbled through tsunami's

00:36:53.760 --> 00:36:54.059
grip.

00:36:54.119 --> 00:36:57.840
Stand on his tail, Glory suggested, or

00:36:57.840 --> 00:36:58.860
poke that scratch.

00:36:58.920 --> 00:37:00.119
That'll get him talking.

00:37:00.179 --> 00:37:03.059
Don't be horrible, Sonny said.

00:37:03.119 --> 00:37:05.219
She nudged their guardian's shoulder with

00:37:05.219 --> 00:37:05.699
her snout.

00:37:05.820 --> 00:37:08.579
Webbs, please warn us if you know

00:37:08.579 --> 00:37:08.940
something.

00:37:09.000 --> 00:37:11.099
It's not safe for you either.

00:37:11.159 --> 00:37:14.639
Webb's side, and tsunami let go of him.

00:37:14.699 --> 00:37:18.059
I swear, I don't know anything about a

00:37:18.059 --> 00:37:18.539
monster.

00:37:18.599 --> 00:37:19.619
He said.

00:37:19.679 --> 00:37:22.019
I didn't see anything dangerous when I

00:37:22.019 --> 00:37:23.579
snuck in to steal Glory's egg.

00:37:23.639 --> 00:37:25.800
Honestly, it was really easy.

00:37:25.860 --> 00:37:28.260
It was the night before the brightest

00:37:28.260 --> 00:37:30.480
night, so you could tell which eggs were

00:37:30.480 --> 00:37:32.820
about to hatch, and I just took one and

00:37:32.820 --> 00:37:34.139
flew back to the mountains.

00:37:34.199 --> 00:37:36.900
I didn't even run into any rain wings, let

00:37:36.900 --> 00:37:37.559
alone a monster.

00:37:37.679 --> 00:37:41.460
My parents weren't guarding their nest.

00:37:41.519 --> 00:37:42.719
Glory asked.

00:37:42.780 --> 00:37:46.019
Webbs looked down at his talons and shook

00:37:46.019 --> 00:37:46.260
his head.

00:37:46.380 --> 00:37:48.599
That doesn't mean anything.

00:37:48.719 --> 00:37:50.159
Glory thought.

00:37:50.219 --> 00:37:52.739
But she remembered the mudwing village

00:37:52.739 --> 00:37:55.320
and Clay's mother, who had sold one of

00:37:55.320 --> 00:37:57.300
her eggs to the talons of peace for a

00:37:57.300 --> 00:37:57.960
couple of cows.

00:37:58.019 --> 00:38:01.079
She hadn't missed clay at all, and she

00:38:01.079 --> 00:38:01.980
certainly didn't want him back.

00:38:02.039 --> 00:38:04.619
Glory hoped her parents wouldn't be like

00:38:04.619 --> 00:38:04.920
that.

00:38:04.980 --> 00:38:07.679
Both Clay and tsunami had been

00:38:07.679 --> 00:38:08.699
disappointed.

00:38:08.760 --> 00:38:10.739
Maybe parent dragons were always

00:38:10.739 --> 00:38:13.260
disappointing. especially when you'd

00:38:13.260 --> 00:38:14.699
spent years dreaming about what they

00:38:14.699 --> 00:38:15.239
might be like.

00:38:15.300 --> 00:38:18.719
Well, Glory didn't particularly care

00:38:18.719 --> 00:38:20.400
whether her parents were the most amazing

00:38:20.400 --> 00:38:21.599
dragons in the world.

00:38:21.659 --> 00:38:24.239
She just wanted to meet other rain wings

00:38:24.239 --> 00:38:26.519
and show her friends that they weren't

00:38:26.519 --> 00:38:28.500
all lazy fruit eaters, like the other

00:38:28.500 --> 00:38:29.219
tribes thought.

00:38:29.280 --> 00:38:32.159
With their camouflage scales and secret

00:38:32.159 --> 00:38:34.739
venom, surely they had to be tougher and

00:38:34.739 --> 00:38:36.179
stronger than anyone suspected.

00:38:36.239 --> 00:38:40.380
Maybe it's a new monster, Clay

00:38:40.380 --> 00:38:40.800
suggested.

00:38:40.920 --> 00:38:43.500
Something that's come to the rainforest

00:38:43.500 --> 00:38:44.880
since you were here 6 years ago.

00:38:44.940 --> 00:38:48.300
Maybe, Webb said.

00:38:48.360 --> 00:38:50.519
The talons never sent anyone down this

00:38:50.519 --> 00:38:50.699
way.

00:38:50.760 --> 00:38:53.820
I can't tell you much about this place

00:38:53.820 --> 00:38:54.179
either.

00:38:54.300 --> 00:38:57.000
Starflet said, wearing at one of his

00:38:57.000 --> 00:38:57.360
claws.

00:38:57.420 --> 00:39:00.119
There were almost no scrolls about the

00:39:00.119 --> 00:39:02.099
rainforest or the dragons who live here.

00:39:02.159 --> 00:39:04.260
Glory knew that.

00:39:04.320 --> 00:39:07.079
She'd memorized every reference she could

00:39:07.079 --> 00:39:09.659
find anywhere to the rain wings, and all

00:39:09.659 --> 00:39:11.639
put together, they told her essentially

00:39:11.639 --> 00:39:12.119
nothing.

00:39:12.179 --> 00:39:15.780
There had been one scroll called Dangers

00:39:15.780 --> 00:39:18.000
of the Rainforest, so she knew a fair

00:39:18.000 --> 00:39:20.519
amount about quicksand, poisonous snakes

00:39:20.519 --> 00:39:23.159
and deadly bugs, but even that one barely

00:39:23.159 --> 00:39:25.860
mentioned the rain wings themselves, and

00:39:25.860 --> 00:39:27.360
certainly nothing about creatures big

00:39:27.360 --> 00:39:29.039
enough to massacre the mud winged

00:39:29.039 --> 00:39:29.519
soldiers.

00:39:29.579 --> 00:39:32.280
Something chattered loudly in the

00:39:32.280 --> 00:39:34.019
branches overhead, and they all jumped.

00:39:34.139 --> 00:39:38.340
It was just a monkey, Glory said fiercely

00:39:38.340 --> 00:39:40.920
clamping down on her nerves, so her

00:39:40.920 --> 00:39:42.000
scales wouldn't change color.

00:39:42.059 --> 00:39:45.179
Or a, a toucan or something.

00:39:45.239 --> 00:39:48.539
Can we eat toucans?

00:39:48.599 --> 00:39:49.380
Clay asked hopefully.

00:39:49.440 --> 00:39:51.840
Only if we can catch them.

00:39:51.900 --> 00:39:52.980
Tsunami said.

00:39:53.039 --> 00:39:55.380
She flexed her wings and glanced up the

00:39:55.380 --> 00:39:56.579
branches and vines overhead.

00:39:56.639 --> 00:39:58.920
Glory wasn't hungry anymore.

00:39:58.980 --> 00:40:01.260
Now that the sun had finally come out.

00:40:01.320 --> 00:40:04.139
Each touch of sunlight felt as if it

00:40:04.139 --> 00:40:05.519
filled her up better than any cow.

00:40:05.639 --> 00:40:08.460
With a twinge of guilt, she remembered

00:40:08.460 --> 00:40:10.860
the Skywing Palace, and the sculptured

00:40:10.860 --> 00:40:13.139
tree Queen Scarlet had set up to display

00:40:13.139 --> 00:40:15.420
glory on, like a piece of treasure.

00:40:15.480 --> 00:40:18.659
There had been so much sun there.

00:40:18.719 --> 00:40:21.059
Nothing like she'd ever had in her whole

00:40:21.059 --> 00:40:22.079
life under the mountain.

00:40:22.139 --> 00:40:25.019
Queen Scarlet would roll glory into the

00:40:25.019 --> 00:40:27.000
sunlight and let her change colors

00:40:27.000 --> 00:40:28.800
however she wanted all day long.

00:40:28.920 --> 00:40:31.199
She didn't try to talk to her.

00:40:31.260 --> 00:40:34.619
She never touched her or yelled at her, or

00:40:34.619 --> 00:40:36.960
insulted her, or compared her to anyone.

00:40:37.019 --> 00:40:40.139
Scarlet's only wish had been for glory to

00:40:40.139 --> 00:40:41.340
sleep and be beautiful.

00:40:41.400 --> 00:40:44.039
But I didn't love it.

00:40:44.099 --> 00:40:46.440
Glory told her self fiercely.

00:40:46.500 --> 00:40:48.599
It was just new and different.

00:40:48.659 --> 00:40:51.840
A new, different way to be a prisoner and

00:40:51.840 --> 00:40:53.639
have my life chosen for me.

00:40:53.880 --> 00:40:55.739
I more than a lump of treasure.

00:40:55.800 --> 00:40:58.800
I guess Scarlet found that out the hard

00:40:58.800 --> 00:40:59.099
way.

00:40:59.159 --> 00:41:02.039
Caw, caw.

00:41:02.099 --> 00:41:05.340
Tsunami leaped into battle pose, her

00:41:05.340 --> 00:41:07.139
teeth bared, with Clay a step behind

00:41:07.139 --> 00:41:07.380
her.

00:41:07.440 --> 00:41:10.019
The others stopped as she glared around

00:41:10.019 --> 00:41:11.699
looking for the source of the noise.

00:41:11.760 --> 00:41:15.179
I'm telling you, Glory said.

00:41:15.239 --> 00:41:16.920
It's only 2 cans.

00:41:16.980 --> 00:41:18.360
There's nothing to be scared of.

00:41:18.420 --> 00:41:19.860
You're just jumpy.

00:41:19.920 --> 00:41:23.099
Now, why would we be jumpy?

00:41:23.219 --> 00:41:24.360
Tsunami said.

00:41:24.420 --> 00:41:27.360
Oh, right, the dead bodies.

00:41:27.420 --> 00:41:30.960
At least I told you about them, Glory

00:41:30.960 --> 00:41:32.699
said, her rough flaring.

00:41:32.760 --> 00:41:36.539
You saw a dead body of someone we knew on

00:41:36.539 --> 00:41:38.460
day one in the kingdom of the sea and

00:41:38.460 --> 00:41:39.719
decided not to tell us.

00:41:39.900 --> 00:41:43.079
Guys, Starflight said.

00:41:43.139 --> 00:41:44.699
That was different.

00:41:44.760 --> 00:41:47.760
That was Kestrel, tsunami cried.

00:41:47.820 --> 00:41:49.380
I had to find a way to tell you

00:41:49.380 --> 00:41:49.860
properly.

00:41:49.980 --> 00:41:53.880
Super job you did there, Lori said.

00:41:53.940 --> 00:41:55.380
Guys!

00:41:55.440 --> 00:41:56.820
Starfight yelled.

00:41:56.880 --> 00:41:58.800
They stopped and looked back at him.

00:41:58.920 --> 00:42:01.559
He was turning in frantic circles, staring

00:42:01.559 --> 00:42:02.940
out at the trees.

00:42:03.000 --> 00:42:05.219
It took Lori a moment, but she realized

00:42:05.219 --> 00:42:06.900
what he was looking for right before he

00:42:06.900 --> 00:42:08.760
said, we're Sunny.

00:42:08.820 --> 00:42:10.800
They all fell silent.

00:42:10.860 --> 00:42:13.619
Sonny had vanished into thin air.

00:42:13.679 --> 00:42:17.820
Chapter 3.

00:42:18.059 --> 00:42:19.980
Sonny!

00:42:20.039 --> 00:42:22.380
Clay bellowed at the top of his lungs.

00:42:22.440 --> 00:42:24.000
She was mad.

00:42:24.059 --> 00:42:25.559
Starflight fretted.

00:42:25.679 --> 00:42:27.840
Maybe she ran off because she was mad at

00:42:27.840 --> 00:42:28.079
us.

00:42:28.139 --> 00:42:30.059
She was?

00:42:30.119 --> 00:42:31.199
Clay asked.

00:42:31.260 --> 00:42:32.400
Why was she mad?

00:42:32.460 --> 00:42:34.739
Glory couldn't remember either.

00:42:34.800 --> 00:42:38.159
Run off into a strange rainforest on her

00:42:38.159 --> 00:42:38.400
own?

00:42:38.460 --> 00:42:39.840
Tsunami said.

00:42:39.900 --> 00:42:41.340
That's not like her.

00:42:41.400 --> 00:42:43.980
Glory closed her eyes and ransacked her

00:42:43.980 --> 00:42:44.340
brain.

00:42:44.400 --> 00:42:48.000
Poisonous snakes, deadly swarms of ants.

00:42:48.059 --> 00:42:50.099
What were the other dangers of the

00:42:50.099 --> 00:42:50.699
rainforest?

00:42:50.760 --> 00:42:51.900
Quicksand?

00:42:52.019 --> 00:42:54.420
She opened her eyes and peered the ground

00:42:54.420 --> 00:42:56.820
around them, but it was all plain dirt

00:42:56.820 --> 00:42:58.980
tree debris, and tangled roots.

00:42:59.039 --> 00:43:00.780
Nothing looked like quicksand.

00:43:00.900 --> 00:43:02.280
Sunny.

00:43:02.340 --> 00:43:03.539
Sunny.

00:43:03.599 --> 00:43:05.039
Clay yelled again.

00:43:05.099 --> 00:43:06.659
Tsunami growled.

00:43:06.719 --> 00:43:09.360
We made it through the sky kingdom and

00:43:09.360 --> 00:43:10.980
the kingdom of the sea without losing

00:43:10.980 --> 00:43:13.320
anyone, and now we're 2 minutes into the

00:43:13.320 --> 00:43:14.760
rainforest and one of us is gone.

00:43:14.820 --> 00:43:18.599
She's not gone, Starflight said.

00:43:18.659 --> 00:43:20.760
His voice vibrating with panic.

00:43:20.820 --> 00:43:22.079
She can't be.

00:43:22.139 --> 00:43:23.699
She has to be here somewhere.

00:43:23.820 --> 00:43:25.500
I was looking at her only a few moments

00:43:25.500 --> 00:43:25.739
ago.

00:43:25.800 --> 00:43:29.099
Glory turned her gaze up to the trees.

00:43:29.159 --> 00:43:31.679
Another gray sloth hung from a nearby

00:43:31.679 --> 00:43:32.940
branch, yawning.

00:43:33.000 --> 00:43:34.860
It looked like perhaps the least

00:43:34.860 --> 00:43:36.420
threatening creature she'd ever seen.

00:43:36.539 --> 00:43:37.920
She frowned at it.

00:43:37.980 --> 00:43:40.800
Webbs, what do you think happened?

00:43:40.860 --> 00:43:43.619
Tsunami demanded, following Glory's

00:43:43.619 --> 00:43:43.920
gaze.

00:43:44.039 --> 00:43:45.480
There was no response.

00:43:45.539 --> 00:43:47.099
They all turned around.

00:43:47.159 --> 00:43:49.019
Webbs was gone too.

00:43:49.139 --> 00:43:53.820
No way, Clay said, flaring his wings.

00:43:53.880 --> 00:43:55.440
He was just here.

00:43:55.500 --> 00:43:58.500
I saw his face when we realized Sonny was

00:43:58.500 --> 00:43:58.679
gone.

00:43:58.739 --> 00:44:00.599
Maybe 10 seconds ago.

00:44:00.659 --> 00:44:02.639
He couldn't have disappeared in 10

00:44:02.639 --> 00:44:03.300
seconds.

00:44:03.360 --> 00:44:05.219
But he did.

00:44:05.280 --> 00:44:06.780
Starfly cried.

00:44:06.840 --> 00:44:09.900
He did, and Sonny did, into thin air.

00:44:09.960 --> 00:44:12.780
Ouch, tsunami said.

00:44:12.900 --> 00:44:14.579
Clapping a talon to her neck.

00:44:14.639 --> 00:44:16.380
Something just stung me.

00:44:16.440 --> 00:44:19.019
Clay jumped and clawed at his neck as

00:44:19.019 --> 00:44:19.199
well.

00:44:19.320 --> 00:44:22.320
Starflight's eyes went wide, and then he

00:44:22.320 --> 00:44:24.179
threw himself to the ground and rolled

00:44:24.179 --> 00:44:25.980
under the nearest low hanging bush with

00:44:25.980 --> 00:44:26.880
his wings over his head.

00:44:26.940 --> 00:44:29.340
What in the world are you?

00:44:29.460 --> 00:44:30.539
Glory started.

00:44:30.599 --> 00:44:31.920
Ducking to look at him?

00:44:31.980 --> 00:44:34.199
She heard a soft buzz as something

00:44:34.199 --> 00:44:36.780
whizzed by her ear, followed by a tiny

00:44:36.780 --> 00:44:38.579
thunk, as it hit the tree behind her.

00:44:38.639 --> 00:44:41.519
She spun around, and saw Clay literally

00:44:41.519 --> 00:44:43.019
disappear right in front of her.

00:44:43.079 --> 00:44:46.559
It was as if the forest reached out leafy

00:44:46.559 --> 00:44:49.139
arms, quietly wrapped him up, and bundled

00:44:49.139 --> 00:44:49.500
him away.

00:44:49.559 --> 00:44:52.860
One moment he was there, blinking dizzily

00:44:52.860 --> 00:44:53.699
and then he was gone.

00:44:53.760 --> 00:44:57.000
A heartbeat later, so was tsunami.

00:44:57.059 --> 00:44:58.679
Aha.

00:44:58.739 --> 00:44:59.940
Glory thought.

00:45:00.000 --> 00:45:02.699
She planted herself next to Starfly's

00:45:02.699 --> 00:45:04.440
hiding spot, and flared her rough.

00:45:04.500 --> 00:45:06.900
She could sense the waves of pale orange

00:45:06.900 --> 00:45:09.119
and dark red rippling across her scales

00:45:09.119 --> 00:45:11.099
but she didn't try to hide them.

00:45:11.159 --> 00:45:12.780
She didn't care if her audience knew she

00:45:12.780 --> 00:45:13.079
was angry.

00:45:13.139 --> 00:45:15.780
That's enough, she called.

00:45:15.840 --> 00:45:17.579
Come out here right now.

00:45:17.639 --> 00:45:20.519
There was a pause, and then the air

00:45:20.519 --> 00:45:22.679
seemed to shimmer for a moment, and

00:45:22.679 --> 00:45:24.059
suddenly a drag in the color of

00:45:24.059 --> 00:45:26.460
raspberries stood in front of her

00:45:26.460 --> 00:45:26.880
grinning.

00:45:26.940 --> 00:45:29.460
Glory had never seen anyone else use

00:45:29.460 --> 00:45:31.260
camouflage scales like hers.

00:45:31.320 --> 00:45:34.739
It was startling, and unsettling, and

00:45:34.739 --> 00:45:36.360
kind of the coolest thing she'd ever

00:45:36.360 --> 00:45:36.599
seen.

00:45:36.719 --> 00:45:39.599
Holy moons, she thought.

00:45:39.659 --> 00:45:41.760
That is awesome.

00:45:41.820 --> 00:45:42.900
We do that.

00:45:42.960 --> 00:45:45.119
Rain wings, like me.

00:45:45.179 --> 00:45:48.840
Another dragon, dark blue dappled with

00:45:48.840 --> 00:45:50.280
gold appeared beside the first.

00:45:50.340 --> 00:45:51.840
She was grinning too.

00:45:51.900 --> 00:45:54.480
Wrestling overhead made glory look up.

00:45:54.539 --> 00:45:57.539
Suddenly, the trees were full of

00:45:57.539 --> 00:45:58.139
dragons.

00:45:58.260 --> 00:46:01.980
Rain wings curled around the trunks or

00:46:01.980 --> 00:46:03.539
hung from the branches by their tails.

00:46:03.659 --> 00:46:06.239
Several of them were colors she'd never

00:46:06.239 --> 00:46:07.079
even imagined.

00:46:07.199 --> 00:46:10.500
She saw deep shades of violet, iridescent

00:46:10.500 --> 00:46:13.739
peach, pale jade, and a yellow so

00:46:13.739 --> 00:46:14.159
bright.

00:46:14.219 --> 00:46:15.960
It was like being stabbed in the eyes

00:46:15.960 --> 00:46:16.619
with the sun.

00:46:16.679 --> 00:46:19.260
We are beautiful.

00:46:19.320 --> 00:46:23.579
Aw, look, said the raspberry dragon.

00:46:23.639 --> 00:46:24.900
She's happy to see us.

00:46:24.960 --> 00:46:28.260
He beamed at her, and Glory realized that

00:46:28.260 --> 00:46:30.480
small bubbles of rose pink were rising up

00:46:30.480 --> 00:46:31.980
from her talons to her wings.

00:46:32.039 --> 00:46:35.579
Poor little dragonette, murmured the dark

00:46:35.579 --> 00:46:36.360
blue rain wing.

00:46:36.420 --> 00:46:38.340
Why are her scales so dull?

00:46:38.400 --> 00:46:40.079
Glory blinked.

00:46:40.139 --> 00:46:42.059
Is she talking about me?

00:46:42.179 --> 00:46:46.440
Shh, don't be rude, said the 1st rain

00:46:46.440 --> 00:46:46.980
wing.

00:46:47.039 --> 00:46:48.599
Hello, tiny one.

00:46:48.659 --> 00:46:51.719
I'm John Boo, and this is Liana.

00:46:51.840 --> 00:46:52.980
What's your name?

00:46:53.039 --> 00:46:54.840
And why don't we know you already?

00:46:54.900 --> 00:46:57.059
Glory.

00:46:57.179 --> 00:46:59.820
And they easily terrified black one is

00:46:59.820 --> 00:47:01.380
Starflight, she said.

00:47:01.440 --> 00:47:04.260
She glanced behind her and saw Starflight

00:47:04.260 --> 00:47:05.699
peering out from under the bush.

00:47:05.760 --> 00:47:07.559
Where are my friends?

00:47:07.619 --> 00:47:11.699
The dark blue dragon, Liana, tilted one

00:47:11.699 --> 00:47:12.719
of her wings up at the trees.

00:47:12.840 --> 00:47:16.260
Amid the dragons clustered overhead were

00:47:16.260 --> 00:47:20.159
4 hanging nets woven of vines, sunny, webs

00:47:20.159 --> 00:47:21.840
clay, and tsunami were inside.

00:47:21.960 --> 00:47:24.300
They all had their eyes closed and hung

00:47:24.300 --> 00:47:25.860
limply like sacks of fish.

00:47:25.920 --> 00:47:27.599
Are they okay?

00:47:27.659 --> 00:47:29.460
Starfly cried.

00:47:29.519 --> 00:47:33.059
Sleeping darts, said the raspberry dragon

00:47:33.119 --> 00:47:35.159
producing a tiny blowgun from a pouch

00:47:35.159 --> 00:47:35.820
around his neck.

00:47:35.820 --> 00:47:39.000
Let's just say we have some tree frogs

00:47:39.000 --> 00:47:41.159
around here, you wouldn't want to lick.

00:47:41.219 --> 00:47:43.260
Your friends will wake up fine in a few

00:47:43.260 --> 00:47:43.500
hours.

00:47:43.559 --> 00:47:47.099
It's easier to meet new dragons this way

00:47:47.099 --> 00:47:48.179
said Liana.

00:47:48.239 --> 00:47:50.280
We've had a couple of grumpy brown ones

00:47:50.280 --> 00:47:52.320
stumble in here, and for some reason they

00:47:52.320 --> 00:47:53.880
start biting us before we can even say

00:47:53.880 --> 00:47:54.360
hello.

00:47:54.420 --> 00:47:56.579
This way we get to chat first.

00:47:56.639 --> 00:47:58.260
Well, they're still a bit groggy.

00:47:58.320 --> 00:48:02.159
Plus, it's more fun, said John Boo.

00:48:02.219 --> 00:48:04.320
Practicing dart shooting on ourselves

00:48:04.320 --> 00:48:05.219
isn't the same.

00:48:05.340 --> 00:48:09.239
They probably won't think it's so fun

00:48:09.239 --> 00:48:12.300
Gloria said, especially the blue one.

00:48:12.360 --> 00:48:14.760
She can be a little cranky, just to warn

00:48:14.760 --> 00:48:15.000
you.

00:48:15.119 --> 00:48:19.260
So, are we your prisoners now?

00:48:19.320 --> 00:48:21.119
Starflight asked glumly.

00:48:21.179 --> 00:48:23.820
The Dark Blue Dragon burst into gales of

00:48:23.820 --> 00:48:26.159
laughter, and amused noise is swept

00:48:26.159 --> 00:48:27.599
through all the dragons in the trees.

00:48:27.659 --> 00:48:30.360
Rain wings don't take prisoners.

00:48:30.480 --> 00:48:33.659
Funny little black dragon, Liana said

00:48:33.659 --> 00:48:34.739
when she could speak again.

00:48:34.800 --> 00:48:36.480
Whatever would we do with them?

00:48:36.539 --> 00:48:39.960
Interrogate them for information?

00:48:40.019 --> 00:48:41.460
Glory suggested.

00:48:41.519 --> 00:48:43.920
Trade them for hostages or weaponry?

00:48:43.980 --> 00:48:46.139
Contain them to minimize any threats.

00:48:46.260 --> 00:48:49.260
The rain wings blinked at her, as if

00:48:49.260 --> 00:48:51.179
she'd suddenly started speaking toucan.

00:48:51.239 --> 00:48:55.019
Just a few ideas, she said with a shrug.

00:48:55.079 --> 00:48:58.800
If we're not prisoners, Starflight said

00:48:58.800 --> 00:49:00.539
then what are you going to do with us?

00:49:00.599 --> 00:49:04.920
Well, said the raspberry dragon, glancing

00:49:04.920 --> 00:49:06.420
up at the position of the sun over the

00:49:06.420 --> 00:49:07.019
canopy.

00:49:07.079 --> 00:49:09.179
Was anyone hungry?

00:49:09.239 --> 00:49:12.119
And then the trees began to scream.

00:49:12.179 --> 00:49:16.559
Chapter 4.

00:49:16.920 --> 00:49:20.159
Starflight nearly leaped out of his

00:49:20.159 --> 00:49:20.760
scales.

00:49:20.820 --> 00:49:23.519
Glory felt her talons dig into the leafy

00:49:23.519 --> 00:49:25.739
dirt as she tried not to bolt into the

00:49:25.739 --> 00:49:26.099
jungle.

00:49:26.159 --> 00:49:29.699
The screams faded, and she realized that

00:49:29.699 --> 00:49:31.320
all the rain wings were staring at her

00:49:31.320 --> 00:49:32.219
quizzically.

00:49:32.280 --> 00:49:33.420
Are you all right?

00:49:33.539 --> 00:49:34.980
John Boo asked.

00:49:35.039 --> 00:49:37.320
Wow, that's a spooked color.

00:49:37.380 --> 00:49:39.900
You weren't freak like that by us.

00:49:39.960 --> 00:49:41.039
We clearly need to work on our

00:49:41.039 --> 00:49:41.579
scariness.

00:49:41.639 --> 00:49:46.260
I'm not spooked, Glory said.

00:49:46.320 --> 00:49:48.420
Gritting her teeth and regaining control

00:49:48.420 --> 00:49:49.260
of her scales.

00:49:49.320 --> 00:49:52.440
I am, Starflight stammered.

00:49:52.500 --> 00:49:54.900
What, what was that noise?

00:49:54.960 --> 00:49:57.420
Oh, Liana said.

00:49:57.480 --> 00:49:58.860
The screamer monkeys.

00:49:58.980 --> 00:50:01.920
She pointed up, and Glory spotted a pair

00:50:01.920 --> 00:50:03.780
of large brown monkeys lounging on a

00:50:03.780 --> 00:50:04.380
branch overhead.

00:50:04.440 --> 00:50:06.780
They started doing that a few years ago.

00:50:06.840 --> 00:50:09.179
It startled us at 1st too.

00:50:09.239 --> 00:50:11.340
John Boo said sympathetically.

00:50:11.400 --> 00:50:13.559
They used to make these deeper grunty

00:50:13.559 --> 00:50:16.019
noises, but now it's all shrieking and

00:50:16.019 --> 00:50:17.760
gibbering like dragons being murdered.

00:50:17.880 --> 00:50:19.139
You get used to it.

00:50:19.199 --> 00:50:20.880
Do you?

00:50:20.940 --> 00:50:22.440
Gloria asked.

00:50:22.500 --> 00:50:25.139
On the one talon, that explained what the

00:50:25.139 --> 00:50:26.699
mudwing patrols were hearing from the

00:50:26.699 --> 00:50:27.239
rainforest.

00:50:27.300 --> 00:50:30.059
On the other, it definitely did not

00:50:30.059 --> 00:50:32.940
explain the dead soldiers, and on the 3rd

00:50:32.940 --> 00:50:35.280
talon, why would monkeys suddenly start

00:50:35.280 --> 00:50:36.960
making different noises than they had

00:50:36.960 --> 00:50:37.500
before?

00:50:37.559 --> 00:50:41.039
And on the 4th, why didn't the rain wings

00:50:41.039 --> 00:50:41.760
think that was weird?

00:50:41.820 --> 00:50:44.400
Come on back to our village.

00:50:44.460 --> 00:50:45.840
John Boo said.

00:50:45.900 --> 00:50:47.340
We could knock you out for the flight

00:50:47.340 --> 00:50:48.420
there if you want.

00:50:48.480 --> 00:50:49.800
You might be more comfortable.

00:50:49.920 --> 00:50:52.079
There are a lot of branches in the way.

00:50:52.139 --> 00:50:56.400
No, thank you, Starflight said.

00:50:56.460 --> 00:50:59.820
Absolutely not, Glory said at the same

00:50:59.820 --> 00:51:00.539
time.

00:51:00.599 --> 00:51:01.980
Jambu shrugged.

00:51:02.039 --> 00:51:04.380
All right, then follow us.

00:51:04.440 --> 00:51:06.960
He leaped gracefully into the air and

00:51:06.960 --> 00:51:08.699
spiraled up toward the treetops.

00:51:08.760 --> 00:51:10.559
The rest of the dragons did the same.

00:51:10.619 --> 00:51:13.679
It looked a bit like a rainbow exploding

00:51:13.679 --> 00:51:15.900
and spattering color all over the trees.

00:51:15.960 --> 00:51:18.300
Glory and Starflight followed them into

00:51:18.300 --> 00:51:21.000
the canopy, high above the forest floor

00:51:21.000 --> 00:51:23.039
where they were surrounded by sunlit

00:51:23.039 --> 00:51:25.380
emerald green, and the whirring whisper

00:51:25.380 --> 00:51:26.280
of tiny wings.

00:51:26.340 --> 00:51:29.159
Birds darted and hopped all around them

00:51:29.159 --> 00:51:31.500
as brightly colored as the rain wings.

00:51:31.559 --> 00:51:33.659
Whenever glory paused for more than a

00:51:33.659 --> 00:51:36.119
moment, purple and gold butterflies

00:51:36.119 --> 00:51:37.739
landed on her talons or head.

00:51:37.800 --> 00:51:40.019
Perhaps they thought she was a flower.

00:51:40.079 --> 00:51:42.900
They stayed away from Starflight's darker

00:51:42.900 --> 00:51:43.260
scales.

00:51:43.320 --> 00:51:46.199
The rain wings moved through the treetops

00:51:46.199 --> 00:51:48.900
with a weird grace, using their tails or

00:51:48.900 --> 00:51:50.639
spreading their wings to glide between

00:51:50.639 --> 00:51:51.059
the trees.

00:51:51.119 --> 00:51:53.519
It looked more like swimming in the air

00:51:53.519 --> 00:51:54.420
than flying.

00:51:54.480 --> 00:51:56.639
Glory wasn't sure she'd ever get the hang

00:51:56.639 --> 00:51:56.940
of it.

00:51:57.000 --> 00:52:00.119
But it made sense, since straight flying

00:52:00.119 --> 00:52:02.159
between the densely packed trees would be

00:52:02.159 --> 00:52:03.539
difficult for creatures the size of

00:52:03.539 --> 00:52:04.079
dragons.

00:52:04.139 --> 00:52:07.440
Starflight kept smacking into vines as he

00:52:07.440 --> 00:52:08.280
tried to keep up with them.

00:52:08.340 --> 00:52:10.800
Glory wondered if he was wishing he'd

00:52:10.800 --> 00:52:12.659
accepted the offer to be knocked out in a

00:52:12.659 --> 00:52:13.559
net like the others.

00:52:13.679 --> 00:52:18.179
She saw Sonny's net soar past them, handed

00:52:18.179 --> 00:52:20.760
smoothly from talon to talon, from rain

00:52:20.760 --> 00:52:21.840
wing to rain wing.

00:52:21.900 --> 00:52:24.239
With a quick glance to make sure no one

00:52:24.239 --> 00:52:26.340
was watching her, Glory tried wrapping

00:52:26.340 --> 00:52:28.260
her tail around a branch and swinging in

00:52:28.260 --> 00:52:30.300
a full circle, like the other rain wings

00:52:30.300 --> 00:52:30.539
did.

00:52:30.599 --> 00:52:34.800
Almost there, Jambu said, landing beside

00:52:34.800 --> 00:52:35.039
her.

00:52:35.099 --> 00:52:37.559
His weight on the branch threw off her

00:52:37.559 --> 00:52:39.780
swing, and she ended up hanging upside

00:52:39.780 --> 00:52:41.639
down by her tail for an awkward moment.

00:52:41.699 --> 00:52:44.099
With a grin, he reached down and helped

00:52:44.099 --> 00:52:44.940
haul her back upright.

00:52:45.059 --> 00:52:47.820
Her back talons gripped the rough bark of

00:52:47.820 --> 00:52:48.239
the branch.

00:52:48.300 --> 00:52:51.059
It felt like ancient dragon scales under

00:52:51.059 --> 00:52:51.900
her claws.

00:52:51.960 --> 00:52:55.019
You really aren't from around here, he

00:52:55.019 --> 00:52:55.320
said.

00:52:55.380 --> 00:52:59.880
No, Glory said, a Starflight thudded down

00:52:59.880 --> 00:53:01.019
clumsily on the branch as well.

00:53:01.079 --> 00:53:04.320
My egg was stolen from the rain wings 6

00:53:04.320 --> 00:53:04.739
years ago.

00:53:04.800 --> 00:53:08.159
Well, I can take you out tree gliding

00:53:08.159 --> 00:53:10.199
anytime you want to practice, he said.

00:53:10.260 --> 00:53:12.000
I bet you'll figure it out pretty

00:53:12.000 --> 00:53:12.300
quickly.

00:53:12.360 --> 00:53:14.940
He spread his wings and leaped off

00:53:14.940 --> 00:53:15.119
again.

00:53:15.179 --> 00:53:17.579
Glory frowned at his departing pink

00:53:17.579 --> 00:53:18.000
tail.

00:53:18.059 --> 00:53:22.260
Yeah, that was weird, Starflight said

00:53:22.320 --> 00:53:25.500
answering her unspoken thought. wasn't

00:53:25.500 --> 00:53:25.619
it?

00:53:25.679 --> 00:53:28.679
As if he didn't care at all, Glory said.

00:53:28.739 --> 00:53:31.860
He didn't ask who stole me, or where I

00:53:31.860 --> 00:53:33.780
was raised, or even act like he

00:53:33.780 --> 00:53:36.239
remembered an egg getting stolen, as if

00:53:36.239 --> 00:53:38.460
eggs just vanish all the time, no big

00:53:38.460 --> 00:53:38.699
deal.

00:53:38.760 --> 00:53:41.280
She scratched her rough thoughtfully.

00:53:41.340 --> 00:53:43.079
Well, whatever.

00:53:43.139 --> 00:53:44.280
Maybe they do.

00:53:44.340 --> 00:53:47.579
Maybe there is a rainforest monster, and

00:53:47.579 --> 00:53:49.199
the dragons are used to losing eggs to

00:53:49.199 --> 00:53:49.500
it.

00:53:49.559 --> 00:53:53.159
That is really, really not comforting.

00:53:53.219 --> 00:53:54.599
Starflight said.

00:53:54.659 --> 00:53:56.940
He wrapped his black wings closer to

00:53:56.940 --> 00:53:59.219
himself, peering down at the forest floor

00:53:59.219 --> 00:54:01.440
as if he expected something toothy to pop

00:54:01.440 --> 00:54:02.519
up and try to grab him.

00:54:02.639 --> 00:54:04.139
Comforting.

00:54:04.199 --> 00:54:07.139
Glory couldn't think of any particularly

00:54:07.139 --> 00:54:09.360
comforting explanations for John Boo's

00:54:09.360 --> 00:54:10.500
lack of interest in her abduction.

00:54:10.559 --> 00:54:14.460
Perhaps he's just a weird dragon, who

00:54:14.460 --> 00:54:16.380
doesn't pay attention to dragonets or

00:54:16.380 --> 00:54:16.679
eggs.

00:54:16.739 --> 00:54:19.079
Surely the rest of my tribal care.

00:54:19.139 --> 00:54:23.099
Come on, let's keep up, she said to

00:54:23.099 --> 00:54:23.820
Starflight.

00:54:23.880 --> 00:54:26.280
A few swings and glides later.

00:54:26.340 --> 00:54:28.619
Suddenly all the rain wings around them

00:54:28.619 --> 00:54:31.380
veered up, spiraling even higher into the

00:54:31.380 --> 00:54:32.099
treetops.

00:54:32.159 --> 00:54:35.039
Starflight made an anxious noise as the

00:54:35.039 --> 00:54:36.840
nets whooshed by with their unconscious

00:54:36.840 --> 00:54:37.440
friends in them.

00:54:37.500 --> 00:54:40.980
And then the dragons started to land, and

00:54:40.980 --> 00:54:42.840
glory began to see the home of the rain

00:54:42.840 --> 00:54:43.440
wings.

00:54:43.500 --> 00:54:46.079
Oh, she breathed.

00:54:46.199 --> 00:54:48.480
She stopped to hover in the air so she

00:54:48.480 --> 00:54:49.019
could look at everything.

00:54:49.079 --> 00:54:51.840
The iridescent colors of the dragons

00:54:51.840 --> 00:54:53.280
brought the hidden world forward.

00:54:53.340 --> 00:54:55.920
Otherwise, the village was camouflaged as

00:54:55.920 --> 00:54:56.940
well as any rain wing.

00:54:57.000 --> 00:55:00.599
Wide vine walkways, shimmering with talon

00:55:00.599 --> 00:55:03.360
sized orange orchids hung between leafy

00:55:03.360 --> 00:55:03.840
platforms.

00:55:03.900 --> 00:55:07.019
A few of the tree houses had low walls or

00:55:07.019 --> 00:55:07.980
woven ceilings.

00:55:08.039 --> 00:55:11.400
Others were open to the sky, and carpeted

00:55:11.400 --> 00:55:14.039
with soft white flowers, like fallen

00:55:14.039 --> 00:55:14.400
clouds.

00:55:14.460 --> 00:55:17.159
Glory spotted a few of the sleepy gray

00:55:17.159 --> 00:55:19.500
sloths, ambling or swinging between the

00:55:19.500 --> 00:55:19.980
walkways.

00:55:20.039 --> 00:55:22.320
She wondered if they weren't smart enough

00:55:22.320 --> 00:55:24.480
to know they were surrounded by dragons

00:55:24.480 --> 00:55:25.980
who could eat them at any moment.

00:55:26.039 --> 00:55:29.820
This is the coolest place I've ever

00:55:29.820 --> 00:55:30.119
seen.

00:55:30.179 --> 00:55:32.400
Glory thought triumphantly.

00:55:32.460 --> 00:55:34.500
And it's my place.

00:55:34.559 --> 00:55:37.860
Visitors, Liana called.

00:55:37.920 --> 00:55:40.500
She had one corner of Clay's net and her

00:55:40.500 --> 00:55:42.719
claws, carefully she and the other rain

00:55:42.719 --> 00:55:45.059
wings lowered him onto a platform wide

00:55:45.059 --> 00:55:46.260
enough for 20 dragons.

00:55:46.320 --> 00:55:49.380
Glory swept up to land beside him, and

00:55:49.380 --> 00:55:51.119
watched her tribe gently set down her

00:55:51.119 --> 00:55:51.780
other friends.

00:55:51.840 --> 00:55:54.239
Dragon heads popped up all around the

00:55:54.239 --> 00:55:54.539
village.

00:55:54.599 --> 00:55:57.539
Glory realized that most of them were in

00:55:57.539 --> 00:55:59.340
hanging contraptions like hammocks.

00:55:59.400 --> 00:56:01.019
She studied the closest one.

00:56:01.079 --> 00:56:04.320
It was strung between 2 trees, sturdily

00:56:04.320 --> 00:56:06.239
woven of vines and lined with violet

00:56:06.239 --> 00:56:07.739
feathers and blue petals.

00:56:07.800 --> 00:56:09.960
The dragon inside was impossible to see

00:56:09.960 --> 00:56:11.579
until he poked his head out.

00:56:11.639 --> 00:56:13.619
His scales match the green and purple

00:56:13.619 --> 00:56:14.519
around him perfectly.

00:56:14.579 --> 00:56:18.719
Clever, Starflight said, tilting his head

00:56:18.719 --> 00:56:20.699
at the hammock, he glanced to the ground

00:56:20.699 --> 00:56:22.320
miles below them and shivered.

00:56:22.440 --> 00:56:24.960
I certainly wouldn't want to sleep up

00:56:24.960 --> 00:56:26.340
this high without something like that.

00:56:26.400 --> 00:56:28.380
Look at that hammock design.

00:56:28.440 --> 00:56:31.199
You can't fall out, and with rain wing

00:56:31.199 --> 00:56:33.300
camouflage, enemies aren't likely to spot

00:56:33.300 --> 00:56:33.780
you either.

00:56:33.900 --> 00:56:37.440
Glory glanced down at her scales, and saw

00:56:37.440 --> 00:56:39.239
a color rolling through them that she'd

00:56:39.239 --> 00:56:41.820
never seen on herself before, a vibrant

00:56:41.820 --> 00:56:43.980
blue purple she guessed meant pride.

00:56:44.039 --> 00:56:46.320
She was proud of her tribe.

00:56:46.380 --> 00:56:49.079
She'd barely met them, and already they

00:56:49.079 --> 00:56:50.699
were as impressive as she'd hoped.

00:56:50.760 --> 00:56:52.860
So their guardians.

00:56:52.920 --> 00:56:53.940
She thought.

00:56:54.000 --> 00:56:56.400
All those years of making me sleep on

00:56:56.400 --> 00:56:58.920
uncomfortable rock ledges in the dark, and

00:56:58.920 --> 00:57:00.599
who are the backward dragons exactly?

00:57:00.659 --> 00:57:02.940
I know.

00:57:03.000 --> 00:57:03.719
Isn't it pretty?

00:57:03.780 --> 00:57:06.599
We quite like our village too, Leanna

00:57:06.599 --> 00:57:09.179
said, practically in glory's ear.

00:57:09.239 --> 00:57:11.039
Glory jumped back, flicking her tail.

00:57:11.159 --> 00:57:13.920
All right, there was one thing that made

00:57:13.920 --> 00:57:14.639
her uncomfortable.

00:57:14.760 --> 00:57:17.099
The way the other rain wings looked at

00:57:17.099 --> 00:57:18.480
her as if they expected to understand

00:57:18.480 --> 00:57:21.119
every thought she had, just by reading

00:57:21.119 --> 00:57:21.719
her scales.

00:57:21.780 --> 00:57:25.139
She clamped down on her emotions, turning

00:57:25.139 --> 00:57:27.119
our scales back to a treetop green that

00:57:27.119 --> 00:57:28.380
matched the background.

00:57:28.440 --> 00:57:30.719
Liana didn't seem ruffled by Glory's

00:57:30.719 --> 00:57:30.960
reaction.

00:57:31.019 --> 00:57:33.960
The rain wing scanned the leaves overhead

00:57:33.960 --> 00:57:37.260
then smiled as 5 small dragons in shades

00:57:37.260 --> 00:57:39.659
of sky blue and copper dropped through

00:57:39.659 --> 00:57:40.500
the canopy toward them.

00:57:40.559 --> 00:57:44.219
Hope you're hungry, Leanna said. as the

00:57:44.219 --> 00:57:45.539
dragons opened their talons.

00:57:45.599 --> 00:57:48.360
Strange shapes bounced and rolled across

00:57:48.360 --> 00:57:50.820
the platform, bumping against Glory's

00:57:50.820 --> 00:57:51.539
sleeping friends.

00:57:51.659 --> 00:57:54.179
Glory picked up the one closest tour.

00:57:54.239 --> 00:57:56.820
Lime green and star shaped.

00:57:56.880 --> 00:57:59.159
It smelled like pineapple and basil.

00:57:59.219 --> 00:58:01.920
She poked it with one claw, wondering if

00:58:01.920 --> 00:58:02.639
she had to peel it.

00:58:02.699 --> 00:58:05.639
Under the mountain, the dragonettes had

00:58:05.639 --> 00:58:06.900
almost never eaten fruit.

00:58:06.960 --> 00:58:09.179
She knew more from reading about it in

00:58:09.179 --> 00:58:11.760
scrolls than from the few berries Webbs

00:58:11.760 --> 00:58:12.599
had sometimes brought back.

00:58:12.659 --> 00:58:15.480
Queen Scarlet was the one who'd given her

00:58:15.480 --> 00:58:16.079
pineapple.

00:58:16.139 --> 00:58:19.199
Don't think about Queen Scarlet.

00:58:19.260 --> 00:58:22.619
Starflight scanned the platform with a

00:58:22.619 --> 00:58:23.460
disappointed expression.

00:58:23.519 --> 00:58:26.280
Is all of this fruit?

00:58:26.280 --> 00:58:27.000
he asked.

00:58:27.119 --> 00:58:28.860
Isn't there any meat?

00:58:28.980 --> 00:58:31.260
Liana wrinkled her nose.

00:58:31.320 --> 00:58:34.440
You can hunt if you want. she said, but

00:58:34.440 --> 00:58:35.760
really, it's a waste of energy.

00:58:35.820 --> 00:58:39.420
She glanced up at the sky again, and it's

00:58:39.420 --> 00:58:41.940
almost our suntime, so if you must, then

00:58:41.940 --> 00:58:42.599
do it quietly.

00:58:42.659 --> 00:58:44.820
Suntime?

00:58:44.880 --> 00:58:45.840
Glory asked.

00:58:45.900 --> 00:58:49.019
Oh, sweetheart, Liana shook her head.

00:58:49.079 --> 00:58:50.280
Is that what's wrong with you?

00:58:50.340 --> 00:58:53.579
I was not aware that anything was wrong

00:58:53.579 --> 00:58:56.820
with me, Glory said, firmly keeping her

00:58:56.820 --> 00:58:58.079
scales from changing color.

00:58:58.199 --> 00:59:00.719
Not from a rain wing point of view

00:59:00.719 --> 00:59:00.960
anyway.

00:59:01.019 --> 00:59:04.440
It's just your scales, Liana said.

00:59:04.500 --> 00:59:06.900
They're so... mousey.

00:59:06.960 --> 00:59:09.000
Glory stared at her.

00:59:09.059 --> 00:59:10.559
Mousey?

00:59:10.619 --> 00:59:14.579
You know, Liana said apologetically, a

00:59:14.579 --> 00:59:16.679
little dull, not like ours.

00:59:16.739 --> 00:59:19.860
She stretched out one wing, and let a

00:59:19.860 --> 00:59:21.539
waterfall of rainbows ripple through it.

00:59:21.599 --> 00:59:25.019
Is she saying I'm not as beautiful as

00:59:25.019 --> 00:59:25.980
other rain wings?

00:59:26.039 --> 00:59:28.679
Certainly, they were all very bright and

00:59:28.679 --> 00:59:29.159
shiny.

00:59:29.219 --> 00:59:31.440
Maybe her own skills weren't quite as

00:59:31.440 --> 00:59:31.860
vibrant.

00:59:31.920 --> 00:59:34.559
Glory wasn't sure what to think of that.

00:59:34.619 --> 00:59:37.679
In fact, she was pretty sure she didn't

00:59:37.679 --> 00:59:37.860
care.

00:59:37.920 --> 00:59:41.519
She'd always been the pretty one, and it

00:59:41.519 --> 00:59:43.860
had never gotten her anywhere, other than

00:59:43.860 --> 00:59:45.659
chained to a decorative tree in the

00:59:45.659 --> 00:59:46.739
Skywing Palace.

00:59:46.800 --> 00:59:49.800
So tell me about suntime.

00:59:49.860 --> 00:59:51.239
She said with a shrug.

00:59:51.300 --> 00:59:54.059
A few streaks of orange and emerald

00:59:54.059 --> 00:59:56.579
flashed through Liana's scales, and then

00:59:56.579 --> 00:59:58.139
vanished into dark blue again.

00:59:58.199 --> 01:00:00.119
Orange and emerald.

01:00:00.179 --> 01:00:03.659
If their scales worked the same way, then

01:00:03.659 --> 01:00:05.400
that meant Liana was feeling a little

01:00:05.400 --> 01:00:08.400
surprised and a little irritated, as if

01:00:08.400 --> 01:00:10.019
she'd hoped to prod more of a reaction

01:00:10.019 --> 01:00:10.619
out of glory.

01:00:10.679 --> 01:00:14.579
This scale reading business can go both

01:00:14.579 --> 01:00:15.780
ways, my new friends.

01:00:15.840 --> 01:00:20.460
Sometime, Liana said smoothly, as if her

01:00:20.460 --> 01:00:21.599
scales hadn't changed at all.

01:00:21.659 --> 01:00:24.239
It's the hours when the sun is highest, so

01:00:24.239 --> 01:00:26.699
we climb up as close to it as we can and

01:00:26.699 --> 01:00:26.940
sleep.

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:31.559
Oh, Starflight interjected in his

01:00:31.559 --> 01:00:34.260
figuring things out voice, glory.

01:00:34.320 --> 01:00:36.300
It's like those naps you always take

01:00:36.300 --> 01:00:38.940
after lunch, I knew that must be a rain

01:00:38.940 --> 01:00:41.280
wing thing, but I could never figure out

01:00:41.280 --> 01:00:41.820
the point.

01:00:41.880 --> 01:00:44.340
Why sleep in the middle of the day?

01:00:44.400 --> 01:00:46.260
Don't you all have anything more

01:00:46.260 --> 01:00:46.980
important to do?

01:00:47.039 --> 01:00:49.920
Glory flicked her tail and narrowed her

01:00:49.920 --> 01:00:50.460
eyes at him.

01:00:50.519 --> 01:00:52.139
But Leana didn't seem offended.

01:00:52.260 --> 01:00:55.079
The sun recharges our scales while we

01:00:55.079 --> 01:00:56.460
sleep, she explained.

01:00:56.519 --> 01:00:58.800
It makes us prettier, better at

01:00:58.800 --> 01:01:00.900
camouflage, smarter, and happier.

01:01:00.960 --> 01:01:02.880
What could be more important than that?

01:01:02.940 --> 01:01:06.300
Oh, Starflight said again.

01:01:06.360 --> 01:01:08.940
He studied glory like a scroll that

01:01:08.940 --> 01:01:10.019
finally made sense.

01:01:10.079 --> 01:01:13.139
Oh, happier?

01:01:13.199 --> 01:01:16.380
Like, less grouchy?

01:01:16.440 --> 01:01:21.000
Shut up, Glory said, giving him a shove.

01:01:21.059 --> 01:01:22.980
She'd already put some of these pieces

01:01:22.980 --> 01:01:24.000
together in her own mind.

01:01:24.059 --> 01:01:27.000
She knew that what the guardians had done

01:01:27.000 --> 01:01:29.579
keeping her trapped underground, away

01:01:29.579 --> 01:01:31.860
from the sun her whole life, had probably

01:01:31.860 --> 01:01:34.199
made her into a grumpier, less powerful

01:01:34.199 --> 01:01:35.340
dragon than she could have been.

01:01:35.400 --> 01:01:37.559
But she didn't need the others figuring

01:01:37.559 --> 01:01:39.480
that out, because she didn't need their

01:01:39.480 --> 01:01:39.780
pity.

01:01:39.900 --> 01:01:42.539
And who knew what she would have been

01:01:42.539 --> 01:01:43.079
like otherwise?

01:01:43.139 --> 01:01:45.840
Being prickly was kind of an essential

01:01:45.840 --> 01:01:47.760
part of being glory, if you asked her.

01:01:47.820 --> 01:01:51.599
The truth was, in the Sky Kingdom, where

01:01:51.599 --> 01:01:53.880
Queen Scarlet left her in the sun all day

01:01:53.880 --> 01:01:56.880
glory had never felt happier or more at

01:01:56.880 --> 01:01:59.460
peace, or less like herself.

01:01:59.519 --> 01:02:02.400
She knew it was the effect of the sun and

01:02:02.400 --> 01:02:02.880
nothing else.

01:02:03.000 --> 01:02:05.519
She knew that what she'd experienced was

01:02:05.519 --> 01:02:07.380
like finally getting to eat as much as

01:02:07.380 --> 01:02:09.420
she needed after a lifetime of

01:02:09.420 --> 01:02:10.019
starvation.

01:02:10.079 --> 01:02:13.860
She knew that Queen Scarlet was evil, and

01:02:13.860 --> 01:02:15.840
that glory was only another sparkly piece

01:02:15.840 --> 01:02:16.679
of treasure to her.

01:02:16.739 --> 01:02:20.519
Part of her had hated it, hated the weird

01:02:20.519 --> 01:02:22.679
sleepiness, and the unmotivated

01:02:22.679 --> 01:02:24.239
contentment that made her feel like a

01:02:24.239 --> 01:02:25.139
puddle of slugs.

01:02:25.199 --> 01:02:27.539
And yet, there was a part of her that

01:02:27.539 --> 01:02:28.800
could have stayed that way forever.

01:02:28.860 --> 01:02:31.440
She shook herself fiercely.

01:02:31.500 --> 01:02:34.860
So go sleep, she said to Liana.

01:02:34.920 --> 01:02:36.179
We're not going anywhere.

01:02:36.239 --> 01:02:38.880
The other rain wings who'd carried the

01:02:38.880 --> 01:02:40.860
nets, had already flown off to higher

01:02:40.860 --> 01:02:43.500
platforms in the treetops, some were

01:02:43.500 --> 01:02:46.260
sprawled out in open patches of sun, while

01:02:46.260 --> 01:02:48.000
others were stretched inside the clever

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:49.260
hammocks, snoring.

01:02:49.320 --> 01:02:52.679
True, said Liana, we'll wake up before

01:02:52.679 --> 01:02:53.280
your friends do.

01:02:53.340 --> 01:02:56.280
Don't you want to ask all your questions

01:02:56.280 --> 01:02:56.940
first?

01:02:57.000 --> 01:02:58.800
Starflight said to Glory.

01:02:58.860 --> 01:03:00.780
Don't you want to find your family and

01:03:00.780 --> 01:03:04.320
there's no rush, Lori said, cutting him

01:03:04.320 --> 01:03:04.500
off.

01:03:04.559 --> 01:03:06.480
They're asleep now anyway.

01:03:06.539 --> 01:03:08.460
The answers will be the same in a few

01:03:08.460 --> 01:03:08.699
hours.

01:03:08.820 --> 01:03:12.119
She knew she was good at looking like she

01:03:12.119 --> 01:03:12.659
didn't care.

01:03:12.719 --> 01:03:15.780
She particularly wanted Liana to think

01:03:15.780 --> 01:03:16.380
she didn't care.

01:03:16.440 --> 01:03:19.440
It was lucky that questions couldn't

01:03:19.440 --> 01:03:21.179
parade across her scales, like her

01:03:21.179 --> 01:03:23.340
emotions, or she'd have been covered in

01:03:23.340 --> 01:03:25.500
them, but she wasn't about to look

01:03:25.500 --> 01:03:27.480
desperate in her 1st moments with her new

01:03:27.480 --> 01:03:27.840
tribe.

01:03:27.900 --> 01:03:29.940
They certainly didn't seem to have a

01:03:29.940 --> 01:03:30.960
1000000 questions for her.

01:03:31.019 --> 01:03:32.460
So fine.

01:03:32.519 --> 01:03:34.619
She could act like this reunion was no

01:03:34.619 --> 01:03:35.519
big deal to her either.

01:03:35.579 --> 01:03:39.659
Maybe acting cool and unconcerned was a

01:03:39.659 --> 01:03:40.860
natural rain wing thing.

01:03:40.980 --> 01:03:42.960
Starflight scratched his head.

01:03:43.019 --> 01:03:46.079
Can you at least ask about the monster?

01:03:46.139 --> 01:03:48.000
Monster?

01:03:48.059 --> 01:03:49.199
Liana laughed.

01:03:49.260 --> 01:03:51.000
There's no such thing as monsters.

01:03:51.119 --> 01:03:52.679
Really?

01:03:52.739 --> 01:03:54.000
Starflight asked.

01:03:54.059 --> 01:03:56.460
Then what's killing mudwing soldiers on

01:03:56.460 --> 01:03:56.880
your borders?

01:03:56.940 --> 01:03:59.880
Oh, Leanna said.

01:03:59.940 --> 01:04:01.260
That monster.

01:04:01.320 --> 01:04:04.619
Starflight's wings flared, and his eyes

01:04:04.619 --> 01:04:06.000
went wide as the moon's.

01:04:06.059 --> 01:04:07.980
Liana burst out laughing.

01:04:08.039 --> 01:04:09.300
Your face.

01:04:09.360 --> 01:04:10.500
She cried.

01:04:10.559 --> 01:04:11.820
That was so worth it.

01:04:11.880 --> 01:04:14.039
I'm just kidding little black dragon.

01:04:14.099 --> 01:04:16.079
I don't know anything about any dead mud

01:04:16.079 --> 01:04:18.360
wings, but I do know we don't have any

01:04:18.360 --> 01:04:19.320
monsters here.

01:04:19.380 --> 01:04:22.199
Just relax, Starflight.

01:04:22.260 --> 01:04:23.400
Glory said.

01:04:23.460 --> 01:04:25.079
Think about libraries or something.

01:04:25.139 --> 01:04:27.719
Little Dragon!

01:04:27.780 --> 01:04:29.880
Jambu called from a perch high above

01:04:29.880 --> 01:04:32.159
glory's head, she squinted up at him

01:04:32.159 --> 01:04:34.380
dazzled by the bright light reflecting

01:04:34.380 --> 01:04:35.639
off his magenta scales.

01:04:35.699 --> 01:04:37.800
Are you joining us for suntime?

01:04:37.860 --> 01:04:39.300
Want a hammock?

01:04:39.300 --> 01:04:39.900
he offered.

01:04:39.900 --> 01:04:41.099
Or a platform?

01:04:41.159 --> 01:04:43.860
Glory blinked at her friends.

01:04:43.920 --> 01:04:46.320
Clay was snoring louder than all the rain

01:04:46.320 --> 01:04:47.159
wings combined.

01:04:47.219 --> 01:04:50.519
Tsunami frowned even in her sleep, her

01:04:50.519 --> 01:04:52.559
claws twitching, as if she dreamed about

01:04:52.559 --> 01:04:52.920
fighting.

01:04:53.039 --> 01:04:55.920
Sonny was curled up in a peaceful ball

01:04:55.920 --> 01:04:58.980
like a snoozing chinchilla, and Webbs

01:04:58.980 --> 01:05:01.619
with his shallow breathing, looked and

01:05:01.619 --> 01:05:02.820
sounded halfway dead.

01:05:02.880 --> 01:05:05.639
If they weren't going to wake up soon

01:05:05.639 --> 01:05:06.179
anyway.

01:05:06.300 --> 01:05:10.679
Go ahead, Starflight said, it's okay.

01:05:10.739 --> 01:05:11.579
I'll watch them.

01:05:11.639 --> 01:05:14.099
He shook his wings and puffed out his

01:05:14.099 --> 01:05:16.619
chest imposingly, which came across a bit

01:05:16.619 --> 01:05:18.000
like a tree frog trying to look

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:18.480
menacing.

01:05:18.599 --> 01:05:22.019
Wake me if you need to, Glory said.

01:05:22.079 --> 01:05:24.300
If I hear someone shrieking like a tiny

01:05:24.300 --> 01:05:25.980
scavenger, I'll assume it's you.

01:05:26.039 --> 01:05:29.400
Starflight huffed an outrage as Glory

01:05:29.400 --> 01:05:31.260
scooped up a couple of mysterious fruits

01:05:31.260 --> 01:05:33.119
and flew to Jamboo's branch.

01:05:33.239 --> 01:05:35.159
I'll take a platform.

01:05:35.219 --> 01:05:37.860
She said, landing beside the pink rain

01:05:37.860 --> 01:05:38.280
wing.

01:05:38.340 --> 01:05:39.360
You sure?

01:05:39.420 --> 01:05:40.260
He asked.

01:05:40.320 --> 01:05:42.539
Usually dragonettes stick to the

01:05:42.539 --> 01:05:43.079
hammocks.

01:05:43.139 --> 01:05:44.639
In case they roll off in their sleep.

01:05:44.699 --> 01:05:46.860
You'd wake up before hitting the ground

01:05:46.860 --> 01:05:48.539
but you'd probably hit a few other things

01:05:48.539 --> 01:05:49.019
first.

01:05:49.079 --> 01:05:52.019
So, you know, we're not talking death or

01:05:52.019 --> 01:05:54.179
anything, but some serious ouch.

01:05:54.239 --> 01:05:57.420
I'll be fine, Glory said.

01:05:57.539 --> 01:06:00.059
She'd never fallen off the ghastly rock

01:06:00.059 --> 01:06:01.860
ledge where she'd been forced to sleep

01:06:01.860 --> 01:06:04.860
for 6 years, and even in her Sky Kingdom

01:06:04.860 --> 01:06:07.739
sun overdose almost coma, she'd always

01:06:07.739 --> 01:06:09.480
stayed perfectly balanced on the marble

01:06:09.480 --> 01:06:09.780
tree.

01:06:09.840 --> 01:06:12.360
A calm sleeper, huh?

01:06:12.360 --> 01:06:13.320
said Jambu.

01:06:13.380 --> 01:06:15.780
Clear conscience, peaceful dreams.

01:06:15.900 --> 01:06:17.579
Sure.

01:06:17.639 --> 01:06:18.840
Glory said.

01:06:18.900 --> 01:06:22.199
As if I would tell my dreams to a dragon

01:06:22.199 --> 01:06:24.960
I just met, or my crimes, for that

01:06:24.960 --> 01:06:25.199
matter.

01:06:25.260 --> 01:06:28.739
Then you can join ours, he said.

01:06:28.800 --> 01:06:31.019
Hopping from the branch to a platform

01:06:31.019 --> 01:06:33.480
covered in overlapping leaves, laid out

01:06:33.480 --> 01:06:35.039
to look like one gigantic leaf.

01:06:35.099 --> 01:06:38.039
The other 2 dragons on it nodded sleepily

01:06:38.039 --> 01:06:38.340
at her.

01:06:38.460 --> 01:06:41.039
Glory turned in a circle and lay down

01:06:41.039 --> 01:06:43.559
with her wings spread wide, to catch as

01:06:43.559 --> 01:06:45.179
much sunshine as possible.

01:06:45.239 --> 01:06:48.360
Warmth flooded through her, as if she

01:06:48.360 --> 01:06:49.619
were rolling in molten gold.

01:06:49.679 --> 01:06:54.599
This, she thought, as her eyes closed, and

01:06:54.599 --> 01:06:55.860
all her muscles relaxed.

01:06:55.920 --> 01:06:58.679
I could have slept in the sun like this

01:06:58.679 --> 01:07:00.599
every day of my life.

01:07:00.659 --> 01:07:02.820
Forget this stupid prophecy.

01:07:02.880 --> 01:07:05.820
This is the destiny I was supposed to

01:07:05.820 --> 01:07:06.119
have.

01:07:06.179 --> 01:07:10.619
Chapter 5.

01:07:10.920 --> 01:07:14.699
Glory woke up refreshed and relaxed.

01:07:14.760 --> 01:07:17.159
But as she lay there with her eyes closed

01:07:17.159 --> 01:07:19.739
she felt a wave of strange anger at

01:07:19.739 --> 01:07:20.039
herself.

01:07:20.099 --> 01:07:22.440
All right, sure.

01:07:22.500 --> 01:07:25.559
I'm not in the great magnificent wondrous

01:07:25.559 --> 01:07:26.760
dragonette prophecy.

01:07:26.820 --> 01:07:29.460
Maybe no one would ever write a prophecy

01:07:29.460 --> 01:07:30.420
about a rain wing.

01:07:30.480 --> 01:07:33.719
Maybe no dragon Empire expects any of us

01:07:33.719 --> 01:07:35.940
to have any important destiny or do

01:07:35.940 --> 01:07:36.900
anything worthwhile.

01:07:37.019 --> 01:07:40.440
But this, sleeping all day in a patch of

01:07:40.440 --> 01:07:40.800
sun?

01:07:40.920 --> 01:07:42.960
Is that all I'm good for?

01:07:43.019 --> 01:07:45.539
All any rain wing is good for?

01:07:45.599 --> 01:07:48.300
There must be more to us than this.

01:07:48.360 --> 01:07:50.760
There must be more to me.

01:07:50.820 --> 01:07:53.639
She wanted to kick herself.

01:07:54.000 --> 01:07:56.639
Falling asleep almost the moment she

01:07:56.639 --> 01:07:57.360
found her home.

01:07:57.420 --> 01:08:00.119
This was exactly what she didn't want her

01:08:00.119 --> 01:08:02.280
friends to think about her or her tribe.

01:08:02.340 --> 01:08:04.679
She'd have to show them that there was a

01:08:04.679 --> 01:08:06.420
good reason for rain wings to have

01:08:06.420 --> 01:08:06.780
suntime.

01:08:06.840 --> 01:08:10.320
It must make them smarter, and fiercer, or

01:08:10.320 --> 01:08:10.619
something.

01:08:10.679 --> 01:08:13.800
She shifted her wings, and froze.

01:08:13.920 --> 01:08:17.100
Something was curled in the gap between

01:08:17.100 --> 01:08:18.840
her shoulder and her wing.

01:08:18.960 --> 01:08:21.779
Some part of it was also draped across

01:08:21.779 --> 01:08:22.199
her neck.

01:08:22.260 --> 01:08:26.640
It was warm, warmer than the sunbeams, and

01:08:26.640 --> 01:08:28.859
it was breathing deeply and evenly.

01:08:28.920 --> 01:08:31.739
She inched her head around, and peered

01:08:31.739 --> 01:08:32.760
sideways at it.

01:08:32.819 --> 01:08:36.779
There was a sloth, sleeping on her.

01:08:36.840 --> 01:08:39.119
It had crept into the curve of her

01:08:39.119 --> 01:08:40.920
shoulder, and fitted itself there

01:08:40.920 --> 01:08:43.500
perfectly, slipping one arm over her neck

01:08:43.500 --> 01:08:44.579
to pillow its head.

01:08:44.640 --> 01:08:47.640
Long, silvery gray fur draped over her

01:08:47.640 --> 01:08:48.479
green scales.

01:08:48.539 --> 01:08:51.539
Its eyes were shut, and it had a peaceful

01:08:51.539 --> 01:08:52.859
smile on its sleeping face.

01:08:52.920 --> 01:08:56.039
What ridiculous creatures?

01:08:56.100 --> 01:08:57.479
Fearless?

01:08:57.539 --> 01:08:58.859
Or stupid.

01:08:58.920 --> 01:09:03.060
Or maybe this is a diabolically clever

01:09:03.060 --> 01:09:03.479
plan.

01:09:03.600 --> 01:09:07.260
After all, she couldn't eat it now.

01:09:07.319 --> 01:09:09.599
She couldn't possibly eat something that

01:09:09.599 --> 01:09:11.099
smiled like that.

01:09:11.159 --> 01:09:13.500
It reminded her a bit of Sonny, who

01:09:13.500 --> 01:09:15.119
probably would also have no trouble

01:09:15.119 --> 01:09:16.979
falling asleep on something big enough to

01:09:16.979 --> 01:09:17.279
eat her.

01:09:17.340 --> 01:09:20.520
She twisted her head up, moving as little

01:09:20.520 --> 01:09:22.380
as possible so she wouldn't disturb the

01:09:22.380 --> 01:09:22.859
sloth.

01:09:22.920 --> 01:09:25.319
The other rain wings on her platform were

01:09:25.319 --> 01:09:25.920
still asleep.

01:09:25.979 --> 01:09:29.279
The sun had drifted down the sky, but she

01:09:29.279 --> 01:09:30.659
guessed there were several hours yet

01:09:30.659 --> 01:09:31.439
until nightfall.

01:09:31.500 --> 01:09:34.439
A soft breeze tossed homeless leaves

01:09:34.439 --> 01:09:37.560
across the canopy, and 2 fat blue frogs

01:09:37.560 --> 01:09:40.380
on a nearby branch, were having a drowsy

01:09:40.380 --> 01:09:41.819
rivety conversation.

01:09:41.880 --> 01:09:45.060
The sloth chirruped.

01:09:45.119 --> 01:09:48.119
It opened its enormous dark eyes, looked

01:09:48.119 --> 01:09:51.060
into hers, and yawned a wide, oddly

01:09:51.060 --> 01:09:52.079
elegant yawn.

01:09:54.060 --> 01:09:56.640
I'm awake, Glory said.

01:09:56.760 --> 01:09:58.859
So you should probably flee in terror

01:09:58.859 --> 01:09:59.159
now?

01:09:59.220 --> 01:10:03.180
Rumble, rumble.

01:10:03.300 --> 01:10:04.979
The sloth said agreeably.

01:10:05.039 --> 01:10:07.380
It snuggled closer to her scales and

01:10:07.380 --> 01:10:08.279
yawned again.

01:10:08.340 --> 01:10:11.340
I'm not like these other dragons.

01:10:11.460 --> 01:10:12.840
I have things to do.

01:10:12.960 --> 01:10:14.220
Glory told it.

01:10:14.279 --> 01:10:16.260
You can't keep sleeping there.

01:10:16.319 --> 01:10:19.380
Mmm, um, boom, boom.

01:10:19.439 --> 01:10:22.260
The sloth concurred, closing its eyes.

01:10:22.319 --> 01:10:25.380
The platform vibrated underneath her as

01:10:25.380 --> 01:10:26.340
John Boo chuckled.

01:10:26.460 --> 01:10:28.500
He rolled over and nodded at the sloth.

01:10:28.560 --> 01:10:31.020
You've been chosen, he said.

01:10:31.079 --> 01:10:32.520
That happened fast.

01:10:32.579 --> 01:10:34.920
No, thank you.

01:10:34.979 --> 01:10:36.060
Glory said.

01:10:36.119 --> 01:10:38.760
I don't want to be chosen, especially by

01:10:38.760 --> 01:10:39.539
a sloth.

01:10:39.600 --> 01:10:42.479
She pushed herself up to sitting, but the

01:10:42.479 --> 01:10:44.279
sloth somehow got both arms around her

01:10:44.279 --> 01:10:46.979
neck and hung on, nestling against her

01:10:46.979 --> 01:10:47.279
wing.

01:10:47.340 --> 01:10:50.159
She likes you, Jambu said.

01:10:50.220 --> 01:10:52.140
Now you have to pick a name for her.

01:10:52.199 --> 01:10:54.420
The queen calls hers Shaggy.

01:10:54.479 --> 01:10:57.060
First of all, what?

01:10:57.060 --> 01:10:58.439
and no.

01:10:58.500 --> 01:11:01.859
It is seriously undignified for a dragon

01:11:01.859 --> 01:11:03.000
queen to have a sloth.

01:11:03.119 --> 01:11:06.300
Also, this sloth is much too pretty for a

01:11:06.300 --> 01:11:09.359
dopey name like Shaggy, Glory said, then

01:11:09.359 --> 01:11:10.199
caught herself.

01:11:10.260 --> 01:11:13.140
And I'm not naming her because I'm not

01:11:13.140 --> 01:11:13.979
keeping her.

01:11:14.039 --> 01:11:16.199
She'll wander away if I ignore her long

01:11:16.199 --> 01:11:16.439
enough.

01:11:16.500 --> 01:11:19.079
John Boo snorted with amusement.

01:11:19.140 --> 01:11:21.239
Or maybe I'll eat her.

01:11:21.300 --> 01:11:22.199
Glory said.

01:11:22.260 --> 01:11:23.939
Why don't you eat them?

01:11:24.000 --> 01:11:26.819
She shot a glance at the sloth, who

01:11:26.819 --> 01:11:28.500
looked serenely unconcerned.

01:11:28.560 --> 01:11:29.939
He shrugged.

01:11:30.060 --> 01:11:33.060
Because they're cute, and too hairy.

01:11:33.119 --> 01:11:34.500
They're all fur.

01:11:34.560 --> 01:11:37.020
You'd have indigestion for days.

01:11:37.079 --> 01:11:39.899
Glory reached up and poked the sloth with

01:11:39.899 --> 01:11:40.380
her claw.

01:11:40.500 --> 01:11:42.300
It did seem to be mostly fur.

01:11:42.420 --> 01:11:46.500
The sloth wriggled, as if it was being

01:11:46.500 --> 01:11:46.979
tickled.

01:11:47.039 --> 01:11:50.159
I'm not playing with you, Glory said.

01:11:50.220 --> 01:11:51.359
You have to go away.

01:11:51.420 --> 01:11:53.340
I have important things to do, like

01:11:53.340 --> 01:11:54.720
finding my parents.

01:11:54.779 --> 01:11:57.539
Jambu tilted his head at her.

01:11:57.600 --> 01:12:00.420
His raspberry pink scales had drifts of

01:12:00.420 --> 01:12:01.739
light pink whorls in them.

01:12:01.800 --> 01:12:04.500
Glory was pretty sure she'd never been

01:12:04.500 --> 01:12:06.539
that color, and she had no idea if it

01:12:06.539 --> 01:12:07.739
meant anything.

01:12:07.800 --> 01:12:09.960
Sometimes pink popped into her scales

01:12:09.960 --> 01:12:12.420
when she was happy, but Jambu was pink

01:12:12.420 --> 01:12:13.439
from head to toe.

01:12:13.500 --> 01:12:15.479
Nobody could be that happy.

01:12:15.539 --> 01:12:17.699
Finding your parents?

01:12:17.699 --> 01:12:18.539
he echoed.

01:12:18.600 --> 01:12:19.500
How?

01:12:19.560 --> 01:12:22.380
You tell me, Glory said.

01:12:22.439 --> 01:12:25.500
I can tell you when I was stolen, and one

01:12:25.500 --> 01:12:27.180
of those sea wings down there can tell

01:12:27.180 --> 01:12:27.720
you from where.

01:12:27.779 --> 01:12:29.100
Isn't that enough?

01:12:29.159 --> 01:12:33.539
Jambu laughed, as if he genuinely thought

01:12:33.539 --> 01:12:34.500
she was joking.

01:12:34.560 --> 01:12:36.420
Then smothered his giggles when he

01:12:36.420 --> 01:12:37.500
realized she wasn't.

01:12:37.619 --> 01:12:39.539
What are you talking about?

01:12:39.600 --> 01:12:42.479
Rain wings don't do parents.

01:12:42.600 --> 01:12:45.180
Glory tried to ignore the twist of

01:12:45.180 --> 01:12:46.500
disappointment in her stomach.

01:12:46.560 --> 01:12:48.779
You knew that might happen.

01:12:48.840 --> 01:12:50.880
Remember the mudwings?

01:12:50.939 --> 01:12:53.220
Maybe the rain wings are the same.

01:12:53.279 --> 01:12:55.500
Raised by their siblings instead.

01:12:55.560 --> 01:13:00.300
So she started, why would you want to

01:13:00.300 --> 01:13:01.020
find them anyway?

01:13:01.079 --> 01:13:02.460
Jambu asked.

01:13:02.520 --> 01:13:05.340
Glory stamped down her temper, so it

01:13:05.340 --> 01:13:06.300
wouldn't show up in her scales.

01:13:06.359 --> 01:13:09.000
Two reasons, she said.

01:13:09.239 --> 01:13:11.520
One, I want to know where I came from and

01:13:11.520 --> 01:13:12.600
what I've missed.

01:13:12.659 --> 01:13:15.479
And two, I want my family to know I'm

01:13:15.479 --> 01:13:15.779
right.

01:13:15.840 --> 01:13:18.300
They must have worried a lot when my egg

01:13:18.300 --> 01:13:18.840
went missing.

01:13:18.899 --> 01:13:21.180
She studied him for reaction.

01:13:21.239 --> 01:13:23.939
Jambu pulled on his snout and looked

01:13:23.939 --> 01:13:24.600
confused.

01:13:24.659 --> 01:13:27.300
But they wouldn't know, he said.

01:13:27.420 --> 01:13:28.979
I guess you don't.

01:13:29.100 --> 01:13:30.600
I mean.

01:13:31.079 --> 01:13:33.420
He stopped and glanced around at the

01:13:33.420 --> 01:13:34.619
sleeping dragons everywhere.

01:13:34.680 --> 01:13:36.659
A few were up and moving through the

01:13:36.659 --> 01:13:38.460
village already, but most were still

01:13:38.460 --> 01:13:38.939
snoozing.

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:43.079
I'll just show you, he said, spreading

01:13:43.079 --> 01:13:43.739
his wings.

01:13:43.800 --> 01:13:45.479
Glory spread hers as well.

01:13:45.539 --> 01:13:49.319
Time to get off, Sloth, she said, unless

01:13:49.319 --> 01:13:50.460
you're prepared for some flying.

01:13:52.439 --> 01:13:54.659
The sloth wrapped its arms more firmly

01:13:54.659 --> 01:13:55.380
around her neck.

01:13:55.439 --> 01:13:57.239
Do they understand us?

01:13:57.300 --> 01:13:58.380
Glory asked.

01:13:58.439 --> 01:14:01.020
Doubtful, John Boo said.

01:14:01.079 --> 01:14:02.699
They're just reading our body language

01:14:02.699 --> 01:14:03.600
and responding.

01:14:03.659 --> 01:14:06.779
He shook off a winding vine and dove off

01:14:06.779 --> 01:14:07.260
the platform.

01:14:07.319 --> 01:14:10.619
Glory checked the sloth again.

01:14:10.680 --> 01:14:12.000
She was pretty sure it was smiling at

01:14:12.000 --> 01:14:12.239
her.

01:14:12.300 --> 01:14:15.180
Maybe her sloth could understand her.

01:14:15.239 --> 01:14:17.939
Maybe it was smarter than all the other

01:14:17.939 --> 01:14:19.319
sloths in the rainforest.

01:14:19.380 --> 01:14:22.859
She followed Jambu, gliding carefully

01:14:22.859 --> 01:14:24.539
between the trees and hanging vines.

01:14:24.659 --> 01:14:26.880
She tried not to care about the furry

01:14:26.880 --> 01:14:28.859
creature clinging to her, but she found

01:14:28.859 --> 01:14:31.380
herself lying more slowly than usual, and

01:14:31.380 --> 01:14:32.880
avoiding things that might knock it off.

01:14:32.939 --> 01:14:35.579
You ridiculous dragon.

01:14:35.640 --> 01:14:36.840
It's only prey.

01:14:36.899 --> 01:14:38.340
No matter how cute.

01:14:38.399 --> 01:14:41.340
Wherever Jamboo was leading her.

01:14:41.399 --> 01:14:43.199
It was some distance from the center of

01:14:43.199 --> 01:14:43.619
the village.

01:14:43.680 --> 01:14:46.859
They passed more platforms, covered with

01:14:46.859 --> 01:14:49.140
sleeping dragons, and something like a

01:14:49.140 --> 01:14:51.600
trampoline of enormous interwoven leaves

01:14:51.600 --> 01:14:54.659
stretched between 4 trees, where a few

01:14:54.659 --> 01:14:56.279
little dragonettes were bouncing and

01:14:56.279 --> 01:14:58.140
flapping their wings furiously as they

01:14:58.140 --> 01:14:58.739
learned to fly.

01:14:58.859 --> 01:15:00.899
Everyone looked happy.

01:15:00.960 --> 01:15:03.300
There were none of the horrible war

01:15:03.300 --> 01:15:05.880
wounds and scars glory had seen in the

01:15:05.880 --> 01:15:06.479
other kingdoms.

01:15:06.539 --> 01:15:09.300
Nobody seemed tense or terrified.

01:15:09.359 --> 01:15:11.819
Nobody was being forced to fight to the

01:15:11.819 --> 01:15:14.279
death or punished for failing at guard

01:15:14.279 --> 01:15:14.579
duty.

01:15:14.640 --> 01:15:19.439
No fighting, no worrying about the war, no

01:15:19.439 --> 01:15:22.500
starving, or bowing to an insane queen.

01:15:22.500 --> 01:15:25.260
Well, as far as I know anyway.

01:15:25.380 --> 01:15:28.020
Who needs a prophecy when they could have

01:15:28.020 --> 01:15:28.619
a home like this?

01:15:28.680 --> 01:15:32.340
Jambu angled down toward a structure

01:15:32.340 --> 01:15:35.100
shaped like a gigantic green egg.

01:15:35.159 --> 01:15:37.199
Holes all over the roof allowed sunlight

01:15:37.199 --> 01:15:39.420
through the overlapping leaves, but the

01:15:39.420 --> 01:15:41.819
bottom was reinforced with tightly woven

01:15:41.819 --> 01:15:44.640
vines and branches, so it looked sturdier

01:15:44.640 --> 01:15:46.260
than anything else glory had seen so

01:15:46.260 --> 01:15:46.680
far.

01:15:46.739 --> 01:15:49.020
She wondered for a moment if this was the

01:15:49.020 --> 01:15:51.359
palace, but surely it wasn't big enough

01:15:51.359 --> 01:15:51.659
for that.

01:15:51.720 --> 01:15:54.720
She hadn't seen anything large or regal

01:15:54.720 --> 01:15:56.640
enough to be the Rainwing Queen's palace

01:15:56.640 --> 01:15:56.819
yet.

01:15:56.880 --> 01:15:59.640
They landed on a branch next to one of

01:15:59.640 --> 01:16:02.159
the window holes, and John Boo gestured

01:16:02.159 --> 01:16:02.760
for her to look inside.

01:16:02.880 --> 01:16:06.659
Pale eggs lined the entire floor, packed

01:16:06.659 --> 01:16:07.319
closely together.

01:16:07.380 --> 01:16:10.619
In the sunlight from above, shimmering

01:16:10.619 --> 01:16:13.199
colors glowed under the thin shells as

01:16:13.199 --> 01:16:15.420
the unhatched dragonettes wriggled and

01:16:15.420 --> 01:16:15.899
squirmed.

01:16:15.960 --> 01:16:18.359
Glory guessed that the eggs around the

01:16:18.359 --> 01:16:21.180
outer edges were the closest to hatching

01:16:21.180 --> 01:16:22.500
since she could see more movement inside

01:16:22.500 --> 01:16:22.859
them.

01:16:22.920 --> 01:16:25.739
A few even had tiny cracks along the top

01:16:25.739 --> 01:16:26.039
already.

01:16:26.159 --> 01:16:30.479
So, she said, so you have a hatchery.

01:16:30.539 --> 01:16:33.840
All the queens do, I mean, sure, this is

01:16:33.840 --> 01:16:37.079
a lot of eggs for one queen, but, Wait.

01:16:37.140 --> 01:16:40.020
Are you saying this is the hatchery I was

01:16:40.020 --> 01:16:40.619
stolen from?

01:16:40.680 --> 01:16:43.800
Am I the daughter of a queen too?

01:16:43.859 --> 01:16:46.680
Not that it made much difference to her

01:16:46.680 --> 01:16:49.020
but it would be pretty funny to see the

01:16:49.020 --> 01:16:50.880
look on tsunami's face if that was true.

01:16:50.939 --> 01:16:54.600
I have no idea, Jambu said.

01:16:54.659 --> 01:16:57.119
There are 3 hatcheries, so it could have

01:16:57.119 --> 01:16:59.100
been any of them, but you're missing the

01:16:59.100 --> 01:16:59.579
point.

01:16:59.640 --> 01:17:02.640
These eggs aren't all from one queen or

01:17:02.640 --> 01:17:03.659
any one dragon.

01:17:03.720 --> 01:17:06.239
We keep all our eggs together like this.

01:17:06.300 --> 01:17:09.420
Glory blinked at the array of smooth

01:17:09.420 --> 01:17:11.100
white shapes in front of her.

01:17:11.159 --> 01:17:14.399
So these are a 3rd of the eggs in the

01:17:14.399 --> 01:17:18.119
village right now, all stuffed in

01:17:18.119 --> 01:17:18.600
together.

01:17:18.600 --> 01:17:21.420
Exactly, said Jambu.

01:17:21.479 --> 01:17:23.699
They keep each other warm and hatch

01:17:23.699 --> 01:17:24.420
whenever they need to.

01:17:24.479 --> 01:17:27.119
We stop by every couple of days to check

01:17:27.119 --> 01:17:28.920
for newly hatched dragonettes.

01:17:28.979 --> 01:17:31.199
Otherwise, we don't have to worry about

01:17:31.199 --> 01:17:31.800
our eggs.

01:17:31.859 --> 01:17:33.420
They're all safe in here.

01:17:33.479 --> 01:17:38.939
Except for mine, Glory pointed out, which

01:17:38.939 --> 01:17:39.539
was stolen.

01:17:39.600 --> 01:17:42.899
She paused, realization dawning.

01:17:42.960 --> 01:17:45.180
It felt as though the wind had just been

01:17:45.180 --> 01:17:47.279
sucked out from under her, and she was

01:17:47.279 --> 01:17:48.720
falling with useless wings.

01:17:48.779 --> 01:17:51.539
And nobody noticed.

01:17:51.600 --> 01:17:53.699
She said slowly.

01:17:53.760 --> 01:17:56.039
That's what you're telling me.

01:17:56.159 --> 01:17:59.220
You had no idea my egg was missing at

01:17:59.220 --> 01:17:59.399
all.

01:17:59.460 --> 01:18:01.859
Jambu shrugged.

01:18:01.920 --> 01:18:03.539
He didn't even look embarrassed.

01:18:03.600 --> 01:18:05.279
Why would we?

01:18:05.279 --> 01:18:06.000
he said.

01:18:06.060 --> 01:18:08.699
As you can see, we have plenty of eggs.

01:18:08.760 --> 01:18:10.260
New ones rolling every week.

01:18:10.319 --> 01:18:12.659
So why go to the trouble of counting

01:18:12.659 --> 01:18:12.779
them?

01:18:12.899 --> 01:18:17.520
Because I wasn't just an egg rolling in

01:18:17.520 --> 01:18:19.079
and out of your hatchery.

01:18:19.140 --> 01:18:21.539
Glory said, flaring her rough.

01:18:21.600 --> 01:18:24.779
There was a real live dragon in there, a

01:18:24.779 --> 01:18:27.180
dragonette who had to grow up for 6 years

01:18:27.180 --> 01:18:30.239
with no family, no rainforest, and no

01:18:30.239 --> 01:18:30.539
sun.

01:18:30.600 --> 01:18:36.359
The sloth said sympathetically, hugging

01:18:36.359 --> 01:18:36.659
her neck.

01:18:36.720 --> 01:18:38.819
Glory had forgotten it was there.

01:18:38.880 --> 01:18:41.880
A cloudy blue gray began to march up

01:18:41.880 --> 01:18:43.800
Jamboo's scales from his talons.

01:18:43.859 --> 01:18:47.159
He made an almost comically sad face at

01:18:47.159 --> 01:18:47.340
her.

01:18:47.460 --> 01:18:49.260
No son?

01:18:49.260 --> 01:18:50.220
he said.

01:18:50.279 --> 01:18:53.699
Hey, I survived just fine.

01:18:53.760 --> 01:18:55.140
Glory said.

01:18:55.199 --> 01:18:57.720
She stepped away from Jambu's wing as he

01:18:57.720 --> 01:18:58.260
reached for her.

01:18:58.319 --> 01:19:01.260
This isn't a tragic pity me situation.

01:19:01.319 --> 01:19:04.079
I'm just saying, maybe you should care a

01:19:04.079 --> 01:19:05.520
little more about your eggs and the

01:19:05.520 --> 01:19:06.539
dragons inside them.

01:19:06.600 --> 01:19:09.840
When we do care, he said.

01:19:09.899 --> 01:19:12.539
Dark green distress flickering in his

01:19:12.539 --> 01:19:12.779
rough.

01:19:12.840 --> 01:19:14.760
We take very good care of our

01:19:14.760 --> 01:19:15.539
dragonettes.

01:19:15.600 --> 01:19:17.579
We just don't worry about the edge

01:19:17.579 --> 01:19:20.100
because we've never lost any before.

01:19:20.159 --> 01:19:22.500
How do you know?

01:19:22.560 --> 01:19:23.520
she cried.

01:19:23.579 --> 01:19:26.579
If I was stolen so easily, you might have

01:19:26.579 --> 01:19:27.300
lost others too.

01:19:27.359 --> 01:19:30.180
He opened and closed his mouth a few

01:19:30.180 --> 01:19:32.640
times, looking so stupid that she wanted

01:19:32.640 --> 01:19:33.899
to punch him in his snout.

01:19:33.960 --> 01:19:36.420
This went beyond parents who didn't love

01:19:36.420 --> 01:19:37.140
their eggs.

01:19:37.199 --> 01:19:39.300
Nobody had missed her.

01:19:39.359 --> 01:19:42.119
She had no family wondering what had

01:19:42.119 --> 01:19:42.840
happened to her.

01:19:42.899 --> 01:19:45.119
Nobody had cared that she was gone.

01:19:45.180 --> 01:19:48.180
Webbs must have known their rain wings

01:19:48.180 --> 01:19:48.779
were like this.

01:19:48.840 --> 01:19:51.479
That's why he came to the rainforest to

01:19:51.479 --> 01:19:52.380
steal an egg.

01:19:52.439 --> 01:19:54.600
That was what he hadn't wanted to admit

01:19:54.600 --> 01:19:55.439
to her on the way here.

01:19:55.500 --> 01:19:58.380
The rain wings weren't a secretly

01:19:58.380 --> 01:20:00.180
wonderful, perfect tribe.

01:20:00.239 --> 01:20:01.859
It was worse than she'd feared.

01:20:01.920 --> 01:20:04.500
Her tribe was too lazy to even count

01:20:04.500 --> 01:20:05.100
their own eggs.

01:20:05.159 --> 01:20:10.380
Oh, now you're mad, John Boo said

01:20:10.380 --> 01:20:10.920
woefully.

01:20:10.979 --> 01:20:13.739
Glory couldn't stop the dark red streaks

01:20:13.739 --> 01:20:15.060
appearing along her wings.

01:20:15.119 --> 01:20:16.319
She scowled at him.

01:20:16.439 --> 01:20:19.319
So how do you know which dragonette

01:20:19.319 --> 01:20:20.399
belonged to which parents?

01:20:20.399 --> 01:20:21.060
she asked.

01:20:21.119 --> 01:20:23.640
We don't, he said.

01:20:23.699 --> 01:20:26.100
We raised them all together, the whole

01:20:26.100 --> 01:20:26.939
village.

01:20:27.000 --> 01:20:27.960
Everybody helps.

01:20:28.020 --> 01:20:30.000
I teach tree gliding.

01:20:30.060 --> 01:20:31.380
He said proudly.

01:20:31.439 --> 01:20:33.779
The blue grave of scales was already

01:20:33.779 --> 01:20:35.039
fading back into pink again.

01:20:35.159 --> 01:20:39.180
But then, Glory said slowly.

01:20:39.239 --> 01:20:42.359
Doesn't that mean you don't even know who

01:20:42.359 --> 01:20:43.319
you're related to?

01:20:43.380 --> 01:20:47.699
Oh, I know what you're thinking, John Boo

01:20:47.699 --> 01:20:47.939
said.

01:20:48.060 --> 01:20:50.399
Don't worry, we have a way to tell.

01:20:50.460 --> 01:20:52.920
Before 2 dragons decide to have eggs

01:20:52.920 --> 01:20:53.819
together.

01:20:53.880 --> 01:20:54.779
They do the venom test.

01:20:54.840 --> 01:20:57.779
He pivoted in a circle and plucked a

01:20:57.779 --> 01:20:59.579
floppy oval leaf from one of the trees

01:20:59.579 --> 01:21:01.680
then laid it on the branch between them.

01:21:01.739 --> 01:21:02.819
Watch.

01:21:02.939 --> 01:21:05.880
He opened his mouth wide, nearly

01:21:05.880 --> 01:21:08.760
unhinging his lower jaw, and spat a small

01:21:08.760 --> 01:21:10.319
amount of black venom on the leaf.

01:21:10.439 --> 01:21:13.380
Glory had imagined herself looking cool

01:21:13.380 --> 01:21:15.239
and menacing when she shot her venom.

01:21:15.300 --> 01:21:17.340
But the other rain wing mostly looked

01:21:17.340 --> 01:21:19.680
creepy, like a mentally unbalanced

01:21:19.680 --> 01:21:20.220
snake.

01:21:20.279 --> 01:21:23.279
The leaf immediately began to sizzle and

01:21:23.279 --> 01:21:23.640
melt.

01:21:23.760 --> 01:21:27.060
Now you shoot your venom at it, he said

01:21:27.060 --> 01:21:28.380
just a little.

01:21:28.439 --> 01:21:29.579
Try to hit the same spot.

01:21:29.699 --> 01:21:32.939
Glory hadn't exactly ever practiced

01:21:32.939 --> 01:21:35.760
aiming her venom, or controlling how much

01:21:35.760 --> 01:21:36.539
she shot out.

01:21:36.600 --> 01:21:40.319
She bared her fangs of the leaf and ended

01:21:40.319 --> 01:21:42.119
up nearly drenching it in black poison.

01:21:42.180 --> 01:21:45.119
The branch below and around the leaf

01:21:45.119 --> 01:21:48.119
started smoking and fizzing as well, but

01:21:48.119 --> 01:21:50.399
strangely, where glory's venom hit

01:21:50.399 --> 01:21:53.100
jamboos, those spots stopped melting

01:21:53.100 --> 01:21:53.520
instantly.

01:21:53.579 --> 01:21:56.760
Whoa, Jambu said.

01:21:56.880 --> 01:21:58.979
He sprayed a little more of his venom

01:21:58.979 --> 01:22:01.500
carefully on the rest of the leaf and the

01:22:01.500 --> 01:22:03.239
branch where glories had splashed.

01:22:03.300 --> 01:22:05.579
All of the smoking and sizzling stopped.

01:22:05.640 --> 01:22:08.340
The leaf sat peacefully in a puddle of

01:22:08.340 --> 01:22:10.619
what appeared to be harmless black goop.

01:22:10.680 --> 01:22:12.000
Glory blinked at it.

01:22:12.060 --> 01:22:14.340
Hmm, she said.

01:22:14.399 --> 01:22:15.659
Unexpected.

01:22:15.720 --> 01:22:18.420
John Booth whacked one of her wings with

01:22:18.420 --> 01:22:20.760
his, radiating delight in every pink

01:22:20.760 --> 01:22:21.300
scale.

01:22:21.420 --> 01:22:23.340
Don't you see what just happened?

01:22:23.399 --> 01:22:26.039
Your venom counteracted mine.

01:22:26.100 --> 01:22:27.300
Isn't that awesome?

01:22:27.359 --> 01:22:28.680
That's so awesome.

01:22:28.739 --> 01:22:30.659
Is it?

01:22:30.720 --> 01:22:31.800
Glory asked.

01:22:31.859 --> 01:22:33.600
That means we're related.

01:22:33.779 --> 01:22:35.100
Jambu cried.

01:22:35.159 --> 01:22:36.659
You're my little sister.

01:22:36.720 --> 01:22:39.779
Gloria flexed her claus and thought about

01:22:39.779 --> 01:22:40.020
that.

01:22:40.079 --> 01:22:42.600
She'd come to the rainforest looking for

01:22:42.600 --> 01:22:45.239
some family after all, but it figured

01:22:45.239 --> 01:22:46.979
that she'd find out Jambu was her brother

01:22:46.979 --> 01:22:49.800
right after deciding he was the dizziest

01:22:49.800 --> 01:22:51.659
most useless dragon she'd ever met.

01:22:51.720 --> 01:22:54.060
And what good was a family who'd never

01:22:54.060 --> 01:22:56.460
been there for you, who'd never known or

01:22:56.460 --> 01:22:59.279
cared you were alive, and lost, and in

01:22:59.279 --> 01:22:59.640
danger?

01:22:59.699 --> 01:23:02.279
Oh, she said.

01:23:02.340 --> 01:23:03.779
Wow.

01:23:03.840 --> 01:23:05.220
Related.

01:23:05.279 --> 01:23:08.399
She reached up and scratched the sloth's

01:23:08.399 --> 01:23:08.640
chin.

01:23:08.699 --> 01:23:10.739
It snuggled in closer to her with another

01:23:10.739 --> 01:23:11.939
burbling sound.

01:23:12.119 --> 01:23:16.079
That's how we know, Jambu said, waving a

01:23:16.079 --> 01:23:17.460
talon at the half melted leaf.

01:23:17.520 --> 01:23:20.399
If your venom made it melt faster, then

01:23:20.399 --> 01:23:22.619
we'd know we're not related, so we could

01:23:22.619 --> 01:23:23.279
have eggs together.

01:23:23.340 --> 01:23:25.500
But when your venom cancels out the other

01:23:25.500 --> 01:23:27.720
dragons, you come from the same family.

01:23:27.779 --> 01:23:30.119
Can you believe her brother and sister?

01:23:30.180 --> 01:23:32.819
Well, okay, we're probably only half

01:23:32.819 --> 01:23:35.399
brother and sister, but still, it's

01:23:35.399 --> 01:23:35.880
pretty cool.

01:23:35.939 --> 01:23:40.380
You're definitely not my dad though, Glory

01:23:40.380 --> 01:23:41.399
said, right?

01:23:41.460 --> 01:23:43.979
Jumbo let out a shot of laughter.

01:23:44.039 --> 01:23:46.800
I'm only 9 years old, he said.

01:23:46.859 --> 01:23:49.319
I promise I haven't fathered any eggs yet

01:23:49.319 --> 01:23:51.180
and I especially didn't have any when I

01:23:51.180 --> 01:23:51.600
was three.

01:23:51.659 --> 01:23:56.340
Well, that's a relief, Glory thought.

01:23:56.399 --> 01:24:00.000
That must be how the tribe cures dragons

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:02.220
who've been hit by Venom too, right?

01:24:02.279 --> 01:24:03.060
She said.

01:24:03.119 --> 01:24:05.520
Find a family member to stop the spread

01:24:05.520 --> 01:24:06.060
of the poison?

01:24:06.180 --> 01:24:08.819
Her newfound brother looked horrified.

01:24:08.880 --> 01:24:12.539
We don't use our venom on other dragons.

01:24:12.600 --> 01:24:13.859
He said.

01:24:13.920 --> 01:24:16.319
Bright green flaring across is rough.

01:24:16.380 --> 01:24:18.119
Who would do that?

01:24:18.180 --> 01:24:22.560
Um, no one, Glory said.

01:24:22.619 --> 01:24:26.340
Maybe not in your perfect world, but talk

01:24:26.340 --> 01:24:28.079
to me again when you're held prisoner by

01:24:28.079 --> 01:24:29.819
a queen who's forcing your friends to

01:24:29.819 --> 01:24:30.539
fight to the death.

01:24:30.600 --> 01:24:34.140
I meant if someone hit someone else by

01:24:34.140 --> 01:24:36.899
accident, that's not impossible, right?

01:24:36.960 --> 01:24:40.380
Our Venom Trainers would never let that

01:24:40.380 --> 01:24:40.680
happen.

01:24:40.739 --> 01:24:42.359
Jambu protested.

01:24:42.420 --> 01:24:44.819
He glanced down at the mess she'd made on

01:24:44.819 --> 01:24:45.180
the branch.

01:24:45.239 --> 01:24:48.119
I bet you could get a few sessions with

01:24:48.119 --> 01:24:48.899
one of them if you want.

01:24:48.960 --> 01:24:51.420
We only ever use it for this kind of test

01:24:51.420 --> 01:24:54.840
and very rarely, for prey if we need it

01:24:54.840 --> 01:24:57.060
or, you know, things that attack us

01:24:57.060 --> 01:24:58.199
hypothetically.

01:24:58.260 --> 01:25:01.199
Things that attack you?

01:25:01.260 --> 01:25:03.840
Gloria asked, perking up her ears.

01:25:03.899 --> 01:25:08.640
Like mysterious rainforest monsters?

01:25:08.699 --> 01:25:09.899
She wondered.

01:25:09.960 --> 01:25:12.720
We should get back to your friends, he

01:25:12.720 --> 01:25:13.079
said.

01:25:13.140 --> 01:25:15.420
They'll be waking up any minute, and we

01:25:15.420 --> 01:25:16.800
can tell them our good news about being

01:25:16.800 --> 01:25:17.399
related.

01:25:17.460 --> 01:25:19.020
So awesome.

01:25:19.079 --> 01:25:21.960
All right, she said.

01:25:22.020 --> 01:25:23.579
I've seen enough here.

01:25:23.699 --> 01:25:26.880
And I'm pretty sure I've gotten all the

01:25:26.880 --> 01:25:28.739
answers about my family that I'm ever

01:25:28.739 --> 01:25:29.460
going to get.

01:25:29.520 --> 01:25:34.140
A long lost sister, Jambu yammered

01:25:34.140 --> 01:25:35.520
curling his tail around the branch.

01:25:35.579 --> 01:25:36.779
So cool.

01:25:36.840 --> 01:25:39.239
I can teach you tree gliding and show you

01:25:39.239 --> 01:25:40.439
all the different fruits in the

01:25:40.439 --> 01:25:42.600
rainforest, and how to take care of your

01:25:42.600 --> 01:25:45.899
sloth, and He swung around the branch and

01:25:45.899 --> 01:25:47.399
glided off, still talking.

01:25:47.460 --> 01:25:49.859
Glory took one more look at the village

01:25:49.859 --> 01:25:50.939
hatchery and followed him.

01:25:51.000 --> 01:25:53.279
She couldn't help but notice that he had

01:25:53.279 --> 01:25:54.119
no questions for her.

01:25:54.180 --> 01:25:57.720
He didn't care where she'd been or who'd

01:25:57.720 --> 01:25:58.859
stolen her or why.

01:25:58.920 --> 01:26:01.439
He didn't ask about the world beyond the

01:26:01.439 --> 01:26:01.979
rainforest.

01:26:02.039 --> 01:26:04.319
He had lots of ideas for what he could

01:26:04.319 --> 01:26:06.479
show her, but didn't seem interested in

01:26:06.479 --> 01:26:07.859
what she might be able to teach him.

01:26:07.920 --> 01:26:10.920
She shook her head and navigated around a

01:26:10.920 --> 01:26:11.939
mossy tree trunk.

01:26:12.000 --> 01:26:14.100
Who cares anyway?

01:26:14.220 --> 01:26:17.579
Even if it's all true, everything the

01:26:17.579 --> 01:26:20.760
guardians said about rain wings, even if

01:26:20.760 --> 01:26:22.560
they are all useless and don't care about

01:26:22.560 --> 01:26:25.140
the right things, I'm still me.

01:26:25.199 --> 01:26:28.140
And I am not going to be like them.

01:26:28.199 --> 01:26:31.140
Not ever, no way.

01:26:31.199 --> 01:26:35.880
Chapter 6.

01:26:35.939 --> 01:26:39.659
Glory was not surprised to find tsunami

01:26:39.659 --> 01:26:41.399
twitching violently in her sleep when she

01:26:41.399 --> 01:26:42.359
and Jambu landed.

01:26:42.420 --> 01:26:44.880
The sea wing would probably be ready to

01:26:44.880 --> 01:26:46.319
fight someone the moment her eyes

01:26:46.319 --> 01:26:47.100
opened.

01:26:47.159 --> 01:26:49.500
What was surprising, though, was

01:26:49.500 --> 01:26:51.539
discovering what Starfly got up to when

01:26:51.539 --> 01:26:51.960
he was bored.

01:26:52.079 --> 01:26:55.739
Hey, glory, he called the moment he

01:26:55.739 --> 01:26:56.340
spotted her.

01:26:56.399 --> 01:26:57.479
Watch this.

01:26:57.539 --> 01:27:00.119
The Nightwing rolled one of the larger

01:27:00.119 --> 01:27:03.000
pieces of fruit, around light pinkish

01:27:03.000 --> 01:27:05.399
melon looking thing, in front of Clay's

01:27:05.399 --> 01:27:06.420
nose, and jumped back.

01:27:06.479 --> 01:27:09.779
Although he was still knocked out, Clay's

01:27:09.779 --> 01:27:10.859
nose started twitching.

01:27:10.920 --> 01:27:14.039
His snout trembled and sniffed, and

01:27:14.039 --> 01:27:16.260
inched closer and closer to the melon.

01:27:16.319 --> 01:27:18.420
His stomach growled loudly.

01:27:18.479 --> 01:27:20.579
His tongue flicked in and out.

01:27:20.640 --> 01:27:24.180
Starflight took the melon away again, and

01:27:24.180 --> 01:27:26.340
Clay stopped moving with a long, tragic

01:27:26.340 --> 01:27:26.699
sigh.

01:27:26.760 --> 01:27:29.340
Isn't that hilarious?

01:27:29.399 --> 01:27:31.199
Starflight asked Glory.

01:27:31.260 --> 01:27:33.239
She gave him an amused look.

01:27:33.300 --> 01:27:36.060
I've always figured torturing our

01:27:36.060 --> 01:27:37.260
sleeping friends would be funny.

01:27:37.319 --> 01:27:40.199
He sat back and flung his tail over his

01:27:40.199 --> 01:27:41.520
talons, frowning.

01:27:41.579 --> 01:27:43.739
I didn't have anything else to do.

01:27:43.800 --> 01:27:46.199
It's been unbearably quiet with everyone

01:27:46.199 --> 01:27:46.680
sleeping.

01:27:46.739 --> 01:27:49.380
His eyes flicked to Jambu.

01:27:49.439 --> 01:27:54.060
Have you asked him about your, Yep, glory

01:27:54.060 --> 01:27:56.220
interjected, dead end.

01:27:56.279 --> 01:27:59.880
We're brother and sister, Jambu announced

01:27:59.880 --> 01:28:00.420
gleefully.

01:28:00.479 --> 01:28:03.060
Starflight tilted his head slowly to one

01:28:03.060 --> 01:28:06.359
side. and gave Glory Ann, is he joking?

01:28:06.420 --> 01:28:07.020
Look.

01:28:07.020 --> 01:28:11.279
You don't seem... much alike.

01:28:11.340 --> 01:28:13.439
He politely understated.

01:28:13.500 --> 01:28:16.079
She shrugged, and the sloth on her back

01:28:16.079 --> 01:28:17.640
said, squirrible.

01:28:17.699 --> 01:28:20.279
Starflight's eyes nearly popped out of

01:28:20.279 --> 01:28:20.579
his head.

01:28:20.699 --> 01:28:24.239
Glory, he said, there's a sloth on you.

01:28:24.300 --> 01:28:27.359
You've got sloth, a sloth.

01:28:27.420 --> 01:28:28.619
It's sitting right on your neck.

01:28:28.739 --> 01:28:30.420
I know.

01:28:30.479 --> 01:28:31.500
Glory said.

01:28:31.560 --> 01:28:33.779
Apparently they're like pets to the rain

01:28:33.779 --> 01:28:34.619
wings.

01:28:34.680 --> 01:28:36.840
This one likes me, even though I've

01:28:36.840 --> 01:28:37.979
explained to it that I'm pretty

01:28:37.979 --> 01:28:38.819
disagreeable.

01:28:38.880 --> 01:28:40.439
Oh.

01:28:40.500 --> 01:28:43.859
Fascinating, Starflight said.

01:28:43.920 --> 01:28:46.859
His talons twitched as if he were dying

01:28:46.859 --> 01:28:48.960
for a scroll to check or somewhere to

01:28:48.960 --> 01:28:49.979
write notes.

01:28:50.039 --> 01:28:53.100
If I remember right, pets don't tend to

01:28:53.100 --> 01:28:54.479
do well in dragon communities.

01:28:54.539 --> 01:28:56.760
They usually get eaten by forgetful

01:28:56.760 --> 01:28:58.739
relatives, or sometimes by the owner

01:28:58.739 --> 01:28:59.220
herself.

01:28:59.279 --> 01:29:01.859
Scavengers, on the other talent

01:29:01.859 --> 01:29:04.260
apparently keep all kinds of odd prey

01:29:04.260 --> 01:29:07.380
animals as pets, like cows and goats and

01:29:07.380 --> 01:29:07.680
fish.

01:29:07.739 --> 01:29:10.859
That's according to a longitudinal study

01:29:10.859 --> 01:29:13.260
of peculiar scavenger behavior, anyway.

01:29:13.319 --> 01:29:16.560
Glory remembered that scroll, but she

01:29:16.560 --> 01:29:17.640
hadn't taken it very seriously.

01:29:17.760 --> 01:29:20.939
Some of the things scavengers supposedly

01:29:20.939 --> 01:29:22.739
did were too absurd to be real.

01:29:22.859 --> 01:29:26.819
We would never eat our pets, Jambu

01:29:26.819 --> 01:29:27.359
interjected.

01:29:27.420 --> 01:29:28.680
Why bother?

01:29:28.739 --> 01:29:31.380
There's enough fruit in the rainforest to

01:29:31.380 --> 01:29:33.479
be sure no rain wing will ever go hungry

01:29:33.479 --> 01:29:35.579
and the sun gives us more than half the

01:29:35.579 --> 01:29:36.960
energy we need to survive anyway.

01:29:37.020 --> 01:29:40.979
So you really don't eat meat?

01:29:41.100 --> 01:29:44.039
Starflight asked, given Gloria a sideways

01:29:44.039 --> 01:29:48.960
glance, you're all vegetarians, vegetarian

01:29:48.960 --> 01:29:49.800
dragons.

01:29:49.859 --> 01:29:52.739
Jambu waved his front talons airily.

01:29:52.800 --> 01:29:54.300
We're not strict about it.

01:29:54.359 --> 01:29:55.979
We eat what we feel like eating.

01:29:56.039 --> 01:29:58.859
Bananas are easier to catch and peel than

01:29:58.859 --> 01:29:59.460
monkeys are.

01:29:59.579 --> 01:30:00.060
That's all.

01:30:00.119 --> 01:30:03.000
Lazy fruit eaters.

01:30:03.060 --> 01:30:05.640
Glory thought, just like everyone says

01:30:05.640 --> 01:30:06.060
they are.

01:30:06.119 --> 01:30:09.960
But they also have tranquilizer blow guns

01:30:09.960 --> 01:30:12.239
and a cleverly designed hidden village.

01:30:12.300 --> 01:30:15.300
She reminded herself, It didn't help.

01:30:15.359 --> 01:30:18.600
They didn't even notice my egg was gone.

01:30:18.659 --> 01:30:22.560
Ouch, said a small voice behind them.

01:30:22.619 --> 01:30:24.420
I think something.

01:30:24.600 --> 01:30:26.340
Bit me.

01:30:26.399 --> 01:30:27.239
What?

01:30:27.359 --> 01:30:29.279
Where are we?

01:30:29.340 --> 01:30:32.819
Starflight bounded over to Sonny's side.

01:30:32.880 --> 01:30:34.079
Are you all right?

01:30:34.140 --> 01:30:36.359
he asked, helping her stand up.

01:30:36.420 --> 01:30:38.579
The little sand wing blinked several

01:30:38.579 --> 01:30:41.100
times and stared around at the rain wing

01:30:41.100 --> 01:30:41.460
village.

01:30:41.520 --> 01:30:43.199
How did we get here?

01:30:43.260 --> 01:30:45.899
She shook out her wings and peeked over

01:30:45.899 --> 01:30:46.260
the edge.

01:30:46.319 --> 01:30:49.380
Oh my gosh, that's a long way down.

01:30:49.439 --> 01:30:52.260
Glory, you have a cute furry thing.

01:30:52.319 --> 01:30:53.520
Can I hold it?

01:30:53.640 --> 01:30:54.300
Please, please?

01:30:54.420 --> 01:30:56.220
Why not?

01:30:56.279 --> 01:30:59.220
Glory said, disentangling the sloth from

01:30:59.220 --> 01:30:59.880
around her neck.

01:30:59.939 --> 01:31:01.739
Just don't eat it.

01:31:01.800 --> 01:31:04.979
She passed it over to Sonny, who cradled

01:31:04.979 --> 01:31:06.539
it gently between her front talons.

01:31:06.600 --> 01:31:09.899
The soft poked Sonny's snout in a curious

01:31:09.899 --> 01:31:12.720
exploratory way, then climbed up it onto

01:31:12.720 --> 01:31:14.699
her head and sat down with a yawn.

01:31:14.760 --> 01:31:17.760
It's not afraid of dragons at all

01:31:17.760 --> 01:31:19.439
Starflight mused.

01:31:19.560 --> 01:31:20.939
Fascinating.

01:31:21.000 --> 01:31:25.199
Webbs moaned.

01:31:25.260 --> 01:31:27.479
He clutched his head with his eyes still

01:31:27.479 --> 01:31:27.779
closed.

01:31:27.840 --> 01:31:29.880
Everything hurts.

01:31:29.939 --> 01:31:32.939
Sonny crawled over to him and checked his

01:31:32.939 --> 01:31:35.819
wound, even from where she was, Glory

01:31:35.819 --> 01:31:36.840
could tell that it looked worse.

01:31:36.960 --> 01:31:39.720
The blackness was spreading, and the

01:31:39.720 --> 01:31:41.760
scratch looked angrily twisted and raw.

01:31:41.819 --> 01:31:46.020
Nothing's going to get me. tsunami yelled

01:31:46.020 --> 01:31:46.979
leaping to her feet.

01:31:47.039 --> 01:31:49.380
I'll fight off any poisonous bugs.

01:31:49.439 --> 01:31:51.899
Where are we?

01:31:52.020 --> 01:31:55.020
She wobbled on her talons and tipped over

01:31:55.020 --> 01:31:55.560
with a thud.

01:31:55.619 --> 01:31:57.899
Don't move too fast.

01:31:57.960 --> 01:31:59.760
Jeambu suggested helpfully.

01:31:59.819 --> 01:32:02.159
The tranquilizer takes a little while to

01:32:02.159 --> 01:32:02.760
completely wear off.

01:32:02.819 --> 01:32:05.159
Tranquilizer?

01:32:05.279 --> 01:32:06.840
Tsunami shouted.

01:32:06.899 --> 01:32:08.279
How dare you?

01:32:08.340 --> 01:32:12.539
Tsunami, stop yelling, Glory said, or

01:32:12.539 --> 01:32:13.859
I'll ask him to knock you out again.

01:32:13.920 --> 01:32:16.140
I'd like to see him try.

01:32:16.199 --> 01:32:17.760
Tsunami cried.

01:32:17.819 --> 01:32:20.760
Please do, Glory said to Jambu.

01:32:20.880 --> 01:32:23.039
Do you have any darts that last for, say

01:32:23.039 --> 01:32:24.119
days?

01:32:24.180 --> 01:32:26.939
We don't do multiple darts in one day.

01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:30.180
Jambu explained, taking glory seriously

01:32:30.180 --> 01:32:31.500
just to be safe.

01:32:31.560 --> 01:32:34.500
Tsunami flared her wings and glowered

01:32:34.500 --> 01:32:36.539
fiercely at Jambu and the other rain

01:32:36.539 --> 01:32:38.220
wings, who were beginning to gather on

01:32:38.220 --> 01:32:39.119
the platform around them.

01:32:39.180 --> 01:32:41.699
Suddenly, Glory thought the bright

01:32:41.699 --> 01:32:45.239
purples, deep oranges, turquoise blues

01:32:45.239 --> 01:32:48.060
and lemon yellows, looked somehow too

01:32:48.060 --> 01:32:49.680
shiny and too vivid now.

01:32:49.739 --> 01:32:51.960
She'd guessed that they were showing off

01:32:51.960 --> 01:32:54.000
for her friends, except she got the

01:32:54.000 --> 01:32:56.100
feeling all rain wings woke up every day

01:32:56.100 --> 01:32:58.199
and spent hours trying to look more

01:32:58.199 --> 01:32:59.699
colorful than everyone else.

01:32:59.760 --> 01:33:01.500
Clay?

01:33:01.560 --> 01:33:02.340
Sunny said.

01:33:02.460 --> 01:33:04.859
She nudged the slumbering mud wing.

01:33:04.920 --> 01:33:06.779
Clay, wake up.

01:33:06.840 --> 01:33:07.739
Are you all right?

01:33:07.800 --> 01:33:08.819
Is he all right?

01:33:08.939 --> 01:33:12.600
He should be fine. said Liana, swooping

01:33:12.600 --> 01:33:13.560
up behind Jambu.

01:33:13.619 --> 01:33:15.600
His dose wasn't any different than the

01:33:15.600 --> 01:33:15.960
rest of yours.

01:33:16.020 --> 01:33:18.420
I'm awake.

01:33:18.479 --> 01:33:20.039
Clay muttered.

01:33:20.100 --> 01:33:22.319
He buried his head under his talons.

01:33:22.380 --> 01:33:25.380
I'm just waiting until glory and tsunami

01:33:25.380 --> 01:33:26.039
stopped fighting.

01:33:26.100 --> 01:33:30.119
I was dreaming about sheep, and buffalo

01:33:30.119 --> 01:33:31.020
and bears.

01:33:31.079 --> 01:33:33.479
They were all on the table in front of

01:33:33.479 --> 01:33:33.720
me.

01:33:33.779 --> 01:33:36.180
And I had to decide which to eat first.

01:33:36.239 --> 01:33:39.779
Oh, and they all smelled like melons.

01:33:39.840 --> 01:33:41.819
That part was kind of weird.

01:33:41.880 --> 01:33:46.140
Sunny, tsunami cried, making the sand

01:33:46.140 --> 01:33:46.739
wing jump.

01:33:46.800 --> 01:33:48.300
Stay very still.

01:33:48.359 --> 01:33:50.159
There's a sloth on your head.

01:33:50.220 --> 01:33:52.979
If I hit it just right, we can share it

01:33:52.979 --> 01:33:53.399
for dinner.

01:33:53.520 --> 01:33:56.340
She stepped forward, flexing her talons.

01:33:56.399 --> 01:33:58.739
There was a murmur of disapproval from

01:33:58.739 --> 01:34:00.060
the watching rain wings.

01:34:00.119 --> 01:34:02.939
Oh no, you don't, Lori said.

01:34:03.000 --> 01:34:06.119
She brushed past tsunami and snatched the

01:34:06.119 --> 01:34:07.199
sloth away from Sonny.

01:34:07.260 --> 01:34:09.420
It cheerfully wrapped its arms around her

01:34:09.420 --> 01:34:11.819
neck and reburied its nose in her ruff.

01:34:11.880 --> 01:34:15.060
It's mine, Glory said to tsunami.

01:34:15.119 --> 01:34:16.319
Yours?

01:34:16.439 --> 01:34:17.819
Tsunami echoed.

01:34:17.880 --> 01:34:20.279
Yours as in, you're saving it for a

01:34:20.279 --> 01:34:20.880
midnight snack?

01:34:21.000 --> 01:34:25.079
Mine as in don't touch, Glory answered

01:34:25.079 --> 01:34:27.300
and don't make snide comments either.

01:34:27.359 --> 01:34:29.100
Me?

01:34:29.159 --> 01:34:30.300
Tsunami said.

01:34:30.359 --> 01:34:32.760
You're telling me not to make snide

01:34:32.760 --> 01:34:33.239
comments?

01:34:33.300 --> 01:34:35.100
Clay?

01:34:35.159 --> 01:34:37.680
Come on, Sonny said, tugging on his

01:34:37.680 --> 01:34:37.920
ears.

01:34:38.039 --> 01:34:40.560
Make them stop so somebody will help

01:34:40.560 --> 01:34:41.220
webs.

01:34:41.279 --> 01:34:44.100
Glory had more or less forgotten they'd

01:34:44.100 --> 01:34:45.720
come to find a cure for the poisoned

01:34:45.720 --> 01:34:47.819
sandwing scratch near Webb's tail.

01:34:47.880 --> 01:34:50.159
She glanced around at the watching rain

01:34:50.159 --> 01:34:50.819
wings.

01:34:50.939 --> 01:34:53.819
Their eyes were wide as full moons, and

01:34:53.819 --> 01:34:55.500
their scales glowed with pink and blue

01:34:55.500 --> 01:34:57.600
bubbles of curiosity and enthrallment.

01:34:57.659 --> 01:35:00.479
They looked as entertained by Glory's

01:35:00.479 --> 01:35:03.239
spat with tsunami as the Skywings were by

01:35:03.239 --> 01:35:04.920
actual Gladiator Arena battles.

01:35:05.039 --> 01:35:08.520
Maybe they resolve all their arguments by

01:35:08.520 --> 01:35:09.359
taking naps.

01:35:09.479 --> 01:35:10.979
She thought grouchily.

01:35:11.039 --> 01:35:14.220
Clay heaved himself upright and stretched

01:35:14.220 --> 01:35:15.359
his muscles rippling.

01:35:15.420 --> 01:35:18.840
A few of the younger rain wings went, ooh

01:35:18.840 --> 01:35:21.239
and tried to change their scales to match

01:35:21.239 --> 01:35:24.060
his, muddy brown with undertones of

01:35:24.060 --> 01:35:25.619
glowing amber in the sunlight.

01:35:25.680 --> 01:35:27.000
That's right.

01:35:27.060 --> 01:35:29.039
Starflight said to Sonny.

01:35:29.100 --> 01:35:30.720
We should focus on webs.

01:35:30.779 --> 01:35:32.039
Of course you're right.

01:35:32.100 --> 01:35:33.420
I'll take care of this.

01:35:33.539 --> 01:35:35.699
He turned to Jambu and Liana.

01:35:35.760 --> 01:35:38.520
We urgently request an audience with

01:35:38.520 --> 01:35:39.539
Queen Dazzling.

01:35:39.600 --> 01:35:42.359
The 2 rain wings wrinkled their snouts

01:35:42.359 --> 01:35:42.840
thoughtfully.

01:35:42.899 --> 01:35:44.699
Queen Dazzling?

01:35:44.760 --> 01:35:45.600
Liana said.

01:35:45.659 --> 01:35:46.739
You don't mean that.

01:35:46.859 --> 01:35:49.979
I do, Starflight insisted.

01:35:50.039 --> 01:35:51.840
It's of the utmost importance.

01:35:51.899 --> 01:35:53.520
We must see her at once.

01:35:53.640 --> 01:35:58.920
Dazzling, Jambu said to Liana, it's not

01:35:58.920 --> 01:35:59.699
her month, is it?

01:35:59.760 --> 01:36:02.760
I don't think so, Yana agreed.

01:36:02.819 --> 01:36:04.619
I guess they could see her anyway.

01:36:04.680 --> 01:36:08.220
We must, Starflight said firmly.

01:36:08.279 --> 01:36:09.840
Take us to her at once.

01:36:09.899 --> 01:36:13.079
Wait, Glory jumped in.

01:36:13.199 --> 01:36:15.479
What do you mean not her month?

01:36:15.539 --> 01:36:18.539
Well, Jambu said.

01:36:18.600 --> 01:36:20.220
Wouldn't you rather see the current

01:36:20.220 --> 01:36:20.699
queen?

01:36:20.760 --> 01:36:22.020
If it's so important?

01:36:22.079 --> 01:36:25.319
Starflight's pompous attitude fizzled out

01:36:25.319 --> 01:36:27.060
like someone had dumped a pile of snow on

01:36:27.060 --> 01:36:27.239
it.

01:36:27.300 --> 01:36:31.800
But, he said, But the Nightwing guide to

01:36:31.800 --> 01:36:34.859
the tribes said, I'm sure it said Queen

01:36:34.859 --> 01:36:35.460
Dazzling.

01:36:35.520 --> 01:36:38.760
It also said we have no natural weapons

01:36:38.760 --> 01:36:40.199
Lori pointed out.

01:36:40.260 --> 01:36:42.600
So perhaps it's not the most reliable

01:36:42.600 --> 01:36:44.520
source, at least about rain wings.

01:36:44.579 --> 01:36:46.319
Who's the current queen?

01:36:46.439 --> 01:36:47.760
She asked Liana.

01:36:47.819 --> 01:36:50.159
I'm pretty sure it's magnificent right

01:36:50.159 --> 01:36:51.420
now, Liana said.

01:36:51.479 --> 01:36:54.060
Unless she handed it over to grandeur a

01:36:54.060 --> 01:36:54.300
bit early.

01:36:54.359 --> 01:36:57.659
Oh no, Glory thought.

01:36:57.720 --> 01:36:58.859
Don't say it.

01:36:58.920 --> 01:37:00.300
Don't say it.

01:37:00.359 --> 01:37:04.079
You take turns, being queen.

01:37:04.140 --> 01:37:05.699
Tsunami burst out.

01:37:05.760 --> 01:37:07.020
Are you serious?

01:37:07.140 --> 01:37:11.039
Only the ones who want to, Liana said.

01:37:11.100 --> 01:37:13.619
Most of us find it way too much work, you

01:37:13.619 --> 01:37:13.920
know?

01:37:13.979 --> 01:37:17.579
Yeah, so boring.

01:37:17.640 --> 01:37:20.699
Dragons bother you all day long.

01:37:20.760 --> 01:37:22.020
Jambu agreed.

01:37:22.140 --> 01:37:24.720
Makes me glad I can't be queen.

01:37:24.779 --> 01:37:30.000
So who can, Gloria asked. anyone?

01:37:30.060 --> 01:37:32.100
Or only the royal family.

01:37:32.159 --> 01:37:34.500
Royal family.

01:37:34.560 --> 01:37:36.960
Jambu echoed with great amusement.

01:37:37.020 --> 01:37:39.899
Oh, right, Glory said.

01:37:39.960 --> 01:37:42.300
Rain wings don't do families.

01:37:42.359 --> 01:37:44.340
She informed her friends.

01:37:44.399 --> 01:37:47.220
Sonny tilted her head, but luckily the

01:37:47.220 --> 01:37:48.960
rain wings kept talking before she could

01:37:48.960 --> 01:37:50.039
say anything sympathetic.

01:37:50.100 --> 01:37:52.920
Pretty much any female in the tribe can

01:37:52.920 --> 01:37:55.260
be queen if she wants to, said Liana.

01:37:55.319 --> 01:37:56.520
Really?

01:37:56.640 --> 01:37:58.260
Tsunami said curiously.

01:37:58.319 --> 01:37:59.699
How about me?

01:37:59.760 --> 01:38:00.659
Can I be queen?

01:38:00.720 --> 01:38:03.119
I'm originally a princess, you know, and

01:38:03.119 --> 01:38:04.800
I'm really good at telling dragons what

01:38:04.800 --> 01:38:05.039
to do.

01:38:05.100 --> 01:38:08.340
Liana and Jambu looked at her dubiously.

01:38:08.399 --> 01:38:11.579
Tsunami shifted her sea blue wings, raised

01:38:11.579 --> 01:38:14.159
her snout in a queenly way, and flashed

01:38:14.159 --> 01:38:15.720
the royal glowing patterns in her

01:38:15.720 --> 01:38:16.079
scales.

01:38:16.140 --> 01:38:20.760
Well, Jambu said, I guess you could ask.

01:38:20.880 --> 01:38:24.300
Absolutely not, Glory said.

01:38:24.359 --> 01:38:26.939
Have a little tribe dignity for Moon's

01:38:26.939 --> 01:38:27.239
sake.

01:38:27.300 --> 01:38:29.460
You cannot have a sea wing as queen of

01:38:29.460 --> 01:38:30.300
the rain wings.

01:38:30.359 --> 01:38:31.800
Tsunami, quit that.

01:38:31.859 --> 01:38:34.920
When you say it like that, it does sound

01:38:34.920 --> 01:38:38.100
weird, Ayana agreed, scratching her ruff

01:38:38.100 --> 01:38:38.819
with one talon.

01:38:38.880 --> 01:38:41.100
Glory didn't want to know what tsunami

01:38:41.100 --> 01:38:43.140
was thinking right then, something about

01:38:43.140 --> 01:38:45.420
what a useless, ridiculous tribe this was

01:38:45.420 --> 01:38:45.659
probably.

01:38:45.720 --> 01:38:48.060
So fine.

01:38:48.119 --> 01:38:51.000
Take us to Queen Magnificent, she said.

01:38:51.060 --> 01:38:53.039
How far is the palace?

01:38:53.100 --> 01:38:55.800
Most of the rain wings politely tried to

01:38:55.800 --> 01:38:56.880
muffle their laughter.

01:38:56.939 --> 01:39:01.439
We don't really do palaces, Liana said.

01:39:01.500 --> 01:39:02.939
Come on, follow me.

01:39:03.000 --> 01:39:06.180
Jambu and the other rain wings stayed

01:39:06.180 --> 01:39:08.760
behind, waving, like a bowl full of

01:39:08.760 --> 01:39:11.279
butterflies, as Glory settled the salt on

01:39:11.279 --> 01:39:12.960
her shoulder again, and she and her

01:39:12.960 --> 01:39:14.520
friends followed Liana up into the

01:39:14.520 --> 01:39:15.060
treetops.

01:39:15.119 --> 01:39:17.460
The tree house she led them to was not

01:39:17.460 --> 01:39:18.659
much different from all the others

01:39:18.659 --> 01:39:21.180
although it was a bit higher and closer

01:39:21.180 --> 01:39:24.239
to the sun, with an open roof and 5 giant

01:39:24.239 --> 01:39:26.579
open windows in the curved outside walls

01:39:26.579 --> 01:39:29.399
a short hanging walkway, glowing with

01:39:29.399 --> 01:39:31.439
fuchsia flowers shaped like dragon

01:39:31.439 --> 01:39:33.539
tongues, led from the doorway to another

01:39:33.539 --> 01:39:34.319
large platform.

01:39:34.439 --> 01:39:37.140
Seven dragons were standing in a line on

01:39:37.140 --> 01:39:37.680
the platform.

01:39:37.739 --> 01:39:40.439
Most of them looked bored or sleepy

01:39:40.439 --> 01:39:43.020
although one or 2 had angry red flickers

01:39:43.020 --> 01:39:44.039
sparking through their scales.

01:39:44.100 --> 01:39:48.119
Here you are, Liana said, landing and

01:39:48.119 --> 01:39:49.199
nodding at the end of the line.

01:39:49.260 --> 01:39:51.600
Magnificent we'll get to eventually.

01:39:51.659 --> 01:39:53.520
She squinted up at the sky.

01:39:53.640 --> 01:39:57.060
Probably before dark, depending on what

01:39:57.060 --> 01:39:58.439
these others you hear to complain about.

01:39:58.500 --> 01:40:01.020
We have to wait?

01:40:01.140 --> 01:40:02.699
Tsunami barked.

01:40:02.760 --> 01:40:04.020
In a line?

01:40:04.079 --> 01:40:06.420
Shouldn't visitors to the rainforest

01:40:06.420 --> 01:40:07.800
automatically go to the front?

01:40:07.859 --> 01:40:10.920
The waiting rain wings all shimmered

01:40:10.920 --> 01:40:13.500
green with displeasure, and shot tsunami

01:40:13.500 --> 01:40:14.399
unfriendly looks.

01:40:14.460 --> 01:40:17.340
We can wait, Glory said.

01:40:17.399 --> 01:40:18.180
No big deal.

01:40:18.239 --> 01:40:21.239
The sloth flopped out on her back, and

01:40:21.239 --> 01:40:22.140
made a snoozy sound.

01:40:22.199 --> 01:40:25.920
It's a big deal to Webbs, Sonny pointed

01:40:25.920 --> 01:40:26.159
out.

01:40:26.220 --> 01:40:28.079
Look how much pain he's in.

01:40:28.199 --> 01:40:30.779
Webbs contrived to look even more

01:40:30.779 --> 01:40:32.699
pathetic than he had a moment earlier.

01:40:32.760 --> 01:40:35.039
He flopped down on the platform and

01:40:35.039 --> 01:40:36.000
groaned softly.

01:40:36.060 --> 01:40:38.520
Sorry, Liana said.

01:40:38.579 --> 01:40:40.439
This is how we do it, to be fair.

01:40:40.500 --> 01:40:42.300
Nobody gets to go ahead of anyone else.

01:40:42.359 --> 01:40:45.479
Tsunami drew herself up as tall as she

01:40:45.479 --> 01:40:47.039
could, and glared at her.

01:40:47.159 --> 01:40:49.800
Didn't I mention that I'm the royal

01:40:49.800 --> 01:40:51.899
daughter of the queen of the sea wings?

01:40:51.960 --> 01:40:55.079
That sounds lovely for you, Liana said.

01:40:55.140 --> 01:40:57.779
I am on a gathering patrol now, but I'll

01:40:57.779 --> 01:40:59.100
come back to check on you all afterward.

01:40:59.159 --> 01:41:02.039
She took a step back, made a cheeky

01:41:02.039 --> 01:41:03.960
little bow to tsunami, and flew away.

01:41:04.020 --> 01:41:06.180
Well, I never.

01:41:06.239 --> 01:41:07.680
Tsunami sputtered.

01:41:07.739 --> 01:41:09.300
Maybe we should tell them who we really

01:41:09.300 --> 01:41:09.539
are.

01:41:09.600 --> 01:41:12.539
Glory hissed at her.

01:41:12.600 --> 01:41:14.939
We agree to stop doing that.

01:41:15.000 --> 01:41:17.699
You don't think Queen Magnificent would

01:41:17.699 --> 01:41:19.260
lock us up, do you?

01:41:19.260 --> 01:41:20.340
said Sonny.

01:41:20.399 --> 01:41:22.260
Doubtful.

01:41:22.319 --> 01:41:23.640
Starflight agreed.

01:41:23.699 --> 01:41:26.159
I bet these dragons haven't even heard of

01:41:26.159 --> 01:41:26.760
our prophecy.

01:41:26.819 --> 01:41:29.460
I'm not sure they'd particularly care.

01:41:29.520 --> 01:41:32.579
True, said Glory.

01:41:32.640 --> 01:41:34.260
They don't care about much.

01:41:34.319 --> 01:41:38.520
Better safe than sorry, don't you think?

01:41:38.579 --> 01:41:39.659
Clay said.

01:41:39.720 --> 01:41:41.939
I vote we keep it quiet.

01:41:42.000 --> 01:41:44.939
I mean, you never know how dragons will

01:41:44.939 --> 01:41:45.779
react, right?

01:41:45.840 --> 01:41:47.699
Sorry, tsunami.

01:41:47.760 --> 01:41:51.420
No, you're right, she grumbled.

01:41:51.479 --> 01:41:53.520
She stretched her wings and neck.

01:41:53.640 --> 01:41:55.859
I just can't believe they knocked us out

01:41:55.859 --> 01:41:57.779
and now they're making us wait around to

01:41:57.779 --> 01:41:58.260
see the queen.

01:41:58.319 --> 01:42:00.180
Yeah.

01:42:00.239 --> 01:42:01.500
Glory said.

01:42:01.560 --> 01:42:03.899
It would make so much more sense if

01:42:03.899 --> 01:42:06.300
they'd chain you all up in a cave and

01:42:06.300 --> 01:42:08.460
starve you and ignore you for a day or 2

01:42:08.460 --> 01:42:11.039
and then throw you in prison after you

01:42:11.039 --> 01:42:12.720
save one of their princesses.

01:42:12.840 --> 01:42:14.579
Oh no, wait.

01:42:14.699 --> 01:42:16.920
That's what your mom did.

01:42:16.979 --> 01:42:21.779
At least there's food here, Clay said

01:42:21.779 --> 01:42:23.399
over tsunamis sputtering.

01:42:23.460 --> 01:42:25.439
He had scooped up a pile of the fruit

01:42:25.439 --> 01:42:27.359
from the 1st platform and brought it with

01:42:27.359 --> 01:42:29.279
him. looking pleased with himself.

01:42:29.340 --> 01:42:31.739
He started arranging the choices in front

01:42:31.739 --> 01:42:31.979
of him.

01:42:32.039 --> 01:42:34.439
What do you think these are?

01:42:34.500 --> 01:42:37.199
He poked a branch covered in what looked

01:42:37.199 --> 01:42:38.760
like bright yellow sundrops.

01:42:38.880 --> 01:42:42.119
The dragonette shared the fruit, even

01:42:42.119 --> 01:42:44.699
webs perked up enough to eat, but glory

01:42:44.699 --> 01:42:45.180
wasn't hungry.

01:42:45.239 --> 01:42:48.060
She passed a small orange fruit up to the

01:42:48.060 --> 01:42:50.939
sloth, but didn't eat anything herself.

01:42:51.000 --> 01:42:53.279
Like Jambu had said, the sun had filled

01:42:53.279 --> 01:42:55.920
her up more than any food ever had, which

01:42:55.920 --> 01:42:58.079
was weird, and she didn't want to think

01:42:58.079 --> 01:43:00.239
about it, or about what it meant that

01:43:00.239 --> 01:43:01.979
she'd been kept away from something so

01:43:01.979 --> 01:43:03.840
important for practically all her

01:43:03.840 --> 01:43:04.739
Dragonette years.

01:43:04.800 --> 01:43:08.279
Instead, she wandered toward the walkway

01:43:08.279 --> 01:43:10.439
and back, trying to peek across to the

01:43:10.439 --> 01:43:11.340
queen's tree house.

01:43:11.460 --> 01:43:13.560
Through the windows, she could see

01:43:13.560 --> 01:43:16.079
rainbow scales, bright blue and

01:43:16.079 --> 01:43:18.180
shimmering yellow and emerald green.

01:43:18.239 --> 01:43:20.760
She also spotted garlands of white

01:43:20.760 --> 01:43:23.399
flowers, with petals like dragonfly

01:43:23.399 --> 01:43:23.760
wings.

01:43:23.819 --> 01:43:26.279
The rain wings seem to use flowers for

01:43:26.279 --> 01:43:28.560
decoration, the way the other tribes used

01:43:28.560 --> 01:43:30.000
jewels and precious stones.

01:43:30.060 --> 01:43:32.340
Glory glanced at tsunami.

01:43:32.399 --> 01:43:34.800
The sea wing was still wearing the

01:43:34.800 --> 01:43:36.479
strands of pearls her mother had given

01:43:36.479 --> 01:43:37.619
her in the kingdom of the sea.

01:43:37.739 --> 01:43:40.260
She acted like she'd forgotten they were

01:43:40.260 --> 01:43:42.539
there, but occasionally Glory saw her

01:43:42.539 --> 01:43:43.680
running them through her claws.

01:43:43.739 --> 01:43:47.579
But her mother was a little bit crazy and

01:43:47.579 --> 01:43:48.840
a smidgen evil.

01:43:48.899 --> 01:43:50.399
Glory thought to herself.

01:43:50.460 --> 01:43:53.220
Wouldn't I rather have no mother than one

01:43:53.220 --> 01:43:54.300
like Queen Coral?

01:43:54.359 --> 01:43:56.579
Even if she did come with pearls?

01:43:56.640 --> 01:43:59.520
What are you seeing the queen about?

01:43:59.579 --> 01:44:01.920
She asked the 1st dragon in line.

01:44:01.979 --> 01:44:04.500
He jumped, startled to be spoken to.

01:44:04.560 --> 01:44:09.000
Oh, oh, he said slowly.

01:44:09.060 --> 01:44:11.579
I'm just wondering if I can get my

01:44:11.579 --> 01:44:12.539
assignment changed.

01:44:12.600 --> 01:44:16.199
Like, right now I teach Dragonettes about

01:44:16.199 --> 01:44:18.659
fruit gathering, but I really think I'd

01:44:18.659 --> 01:44:21.539
be better at, like, advanced napping

01:44:21.539 --> 01:44:22.140
techniques.

01:44:22.199 --> 01:44:25.859
Glory only barely managed not to laugh

01:44:25.859 --> 01:44:26.460
out loud.

01:44:26.579 --> 01:44:30.420
He was clearly not joking, was advanced

01:44:30.420 --> 01:44:32.520
napping techniques an actual subject.

01:44:32.579 --> 01:44:34.859
She decided it would be rude to ask.

01:44:34.920 --> 01:44:36.720
What about you?

01:44:36.779 --> 01:44:39.840
she asked, turning to the next dragon in

01:44:39.840 --> 01:44:40.140
line.

01:44:40.199 --> 01:44:43.260
This one was tall and pale orange, and a

01:44:43.260 --> 01:44:45.300
small gray blue dragonette sat in the

01:44:45.300 --> 01:44:47.399
curl of her tail, frowning grumpily.

01:44:47.460 --> 01:44:49.979
I'm bringing this dragonette in for

01:44:49.979 --> 01:44:51.899
punishment, said the tall dragon.

01:44:51.960 --> 01:44:53.939
He seems to think it's funny to stuff

01:44:53.939 --> 01:44:56.039
berries up the noses of sleeping dragons

01:44:56.039 --> 01:44:56.939
during suntime.

01:44:57.000 --> 01:44:59.880
The little gray blue dragon huffed a

01:44:59.880 --> 01:45:01.979
noise that was somewhere between amused

01:45:01.979 --> 01:45:04.859
and outraged and made a gruesome vase of

01:45:04.859 --> 01:45:05.220
glory.

01:45:05.279 --> 01:45:08.159
She made one right back, and he gaped in

01:45:08.159 --> 01:45:08.640
surprise.

01:45:08.699 --> 01:45:11.819
I'll tell you why I'm here.

01:45:11.939 --> 01:45:14.340
Snarled the 3rd dragon in line.

01:45:14.460 --> 01:45:16.920
He was one of the 2 with the furious red

01:45:16.920 --> 01:45:18.000
flickers along his ruff.

01:45:18.060 --> 01:45:20.039
The other was at the back of the line.

01:45:20.100 --> 01:45:22.020
Glory thought they might be the only

01:45:22.020 --> 01:45:24.539
angry rain wings she'd seen so far.

01:45:24.600 --> 01:45:29.100
Uh-oh, said the napping techniques dragon

01:45:29.100 --> 01:45:29.939
with a sleepy smile.

01:45:30.060 --> 01:45:32.880
Mangrove is complaining about something

01:45:32.880 --> 01:45:33.239
again.

01:45:33.300 --> 01:45:36.359
The tall orange dragon chuckled

01:45:36.359 --> 01:45:36.960
appreciatively.

01:45:37.020 --> 01:45:39.960
Complaining about something.

01:45:40.020 --> 01:45:41.520
Mangrove yelped.

01:45:41.579 --> 01:45:42.779
I'll say.

01:45:42.899 --> 01:45:45.420
Something we should all be complaining

01:45:45.420 --> 01:45:45.960
about.

01:45:46.020 --> 01:45:48.779
My orchid isn't the only one who's

01:45:48.779 --> 01:45:49.500
missing, you know.

01:45:49.560 --> 01:45:51.779
Glory tilted her head.

01:45:51.840 --> 01:45:53.399
Your orchid?

01:45:53.520 --> 01:45:54.180
she asked.

01:45:54.300 --> 01:45:57.180
Was this another weird rain wing thing

01:45:57.180 --> 01:45:58.979
where it would turn out they were

01:45:58.979 --> 01:46:00.779
bizarrely attached to their flowers?

01:46:00.840 --> 01:46:04.739
My pardner, Mangrove growled.

01:46:04.800 --> 01:46:05.880
Orchid.

01:46:05.939 --> 01:46:08.100
She's been missing for 3 weeks.

01:46:08.159 --> 01:46:11.100
I've asked the queen every day since then

01:46:11.100 --> 01:46:12.359
to send out a search party.

01:46:12.420 --> 01:46:17.100
Sometimes dragons need a break, said the

01:46:17.100 --> 01:46:18.479
1st dragon with a shrug.

01:46:18.539 --> 01:46:21.479
Maybe she's taking a really long nap

01:46:21.479 --> 01:46:23.819
somewhere, agreed the tall orange

01:46:23.819 --> 01:46:24.300
dragon.

01:46:24.359 --> 01:46:27.659
Three weeks.

01:46:27.720 --> 01:46:29.340
Mangrove hissed.

01:46:29.399 --> 01:46:32.039
And other dragons are missing too?

01:46:32.100 --> 01:46:34.079
Glory asked Mangrove.

01:46:34.140 --> 01:46:38.159
At least 12 in the last year, including

01:46:38.159 --> 01:46:40.140
Orchid, he said grimly.

01:46:40.199 --> 01:46:42.899
A chill crawl down glory's spine.

01:46:42.960 --> 01:46:45.479
So the mudwing soldiers weren't the only

01:46:45.479 --> 01:46:47.579
ones encountering something malevolent in

01:46:47.579 --> 01:46:48.239
the rainforest.

01:46:48.300 --> 01:46:52.199
There was something out there. lurking

01:46:52.199 --> 01:46:54.359
behind the colorful birds and exuberant

01:46:54.359 --> 01:46:56.819
flowers and tall whispering trees

01:46:56.819 --> 01:46:59.760
something that could take out 2 mud wings

01:46:59.760 --> 01:47:03.539
at once, and also make 12 rain wings

01:47:03.539 --> 01:47:04.680
disappear without a trace.

01:47:04.800 --> 01:47:09.539
Chapter 7.

01:47:09.600 --> 01:47:14.039
Next. boomed a voice from the Queen's

01:47:14.039 --> 01:47:14.640
Treehouse.

01:47:14.699 --> 01:47:17.460
The 1st dragon ambled across the bridge

01:47:17.460 --> 01:47:20.039
yawning, and slid through the curtain of

01:47:20.039 --> 01:47:21.539
silvery yellow flowers that hung in the

01:47:21.539 --> 01:47:21.840
doorway.

01:47:21.960 --> 01:47:24.899
Can I come in for your audience?

01:47:24.960 --> 01:47:26.939
Glory asked Mangrove.

01:47:27.000 --> 01:47:29.460
She wanted to know how Queen Magnificent

01:47:29.460 --> 01:47:31.260
would handle the problem of missing rain

01:47:31.260 --> 01:47:31.619
wings.

01:47:31.680 --> 01:47:33.239
Why?

01:47:33.300 --> 01:47:35.699
Mangrove asked suspiciously.

01:47:35.760 --> 01:47:38.039
I'm not letting you have my turn.

01:47:38.100 --> 01:47:41.699
I'll just listen, Lori promised.

01:47:41.819 --> 01:47:44.220
Hmm, he said.

01:47:44.279 --> 01:47:46.500
All right, I suppose.

01:47:46.560 --> 01:47:49.199
She turned to the last rain wing in line

01:47:49.199 --> 01:47:49.859
and took a guess.

01:47:49.920 --> 01:47:52.319
Are you here about a missing dragon too?

01:47:52.380 --> 01:47:54.239
A dragonette.

01:47:54.359 --> 01:47:55.619
The rain wing answered.

01:47:55.680 --> 01:47:58.560
The scarlet flickers in her ruff were

01:47:58.560 --> 01:48:00.300
reflected in the dark burgundy of her

01:48:00.300 --> 01:48:00.659
scales.

01:48:00.720 --> 01:48:03.420
Everyone thinks I lost her while we were

01:48:03.420 --> 01:48:06.000
venom training, but I know it wasn't my

01:48:06.000 --> 01:48:06.180
fault.

01:48:06.300 --> 01:48:08.819
She stamped her talons on the wood

01:48:08.819 --> 01:48:11.460
platform and hissed the skeptical look on

01:48:11.460 --> 01:48:12.960
the nearest dragon's face.

01:48:13.020 --> 01:48:14.939
So what happened to her?

01:48:15.000 --> 01:48:16.140
Glory asked.

01:48:16.199 --> 01:48:18.600
The burgundy dragon flung her wings up.

01:48:18.659 --> 01:48:19.979
I don't know.

01:48:20.039 --> 01:48:21.420
Maybe she ran off.

01:48:21.539 --> 01:48:23.819
She's a terrible student and a pain in

01:48:23.819 --> 01:48:24.180
the tail.

01:48:24.239 --> 01:48:26.640
I just want to be cleared so I can have

01:48:26.640 --> 01:48:27.479
my assignment back.

01:48:27.539 --> 01:48:30.239
Poor Bromeliad.

01:48:30.300 --> 01:48:32.399
If you have no assignment, that means

01:48:32.399 --> 01:48:35.220
last choice of suntime spots, and only

01:48:35.220 --> 01:48:36.720
leftovers at feeding time.

01:48:36.779 --> 01:48:39.359
The pale orange dragon explained to

01:48:39.359 --> 01:48:39.720
Glory.

01:48:39.779 --> 01:48:41.399
It's not a lot of fun.

01:48:41.460 --> 01:48:45.960
You must also want to find her, Glory

01:48:45.960 --> 01:48:46.979
said to Bermeliad.

01:48:47.039 --> 01:48:48.239
Aren't you worried?

01:48:48.359 --> 01:48:52.380
She'll show up eventually, said Brumeliad

01:48:52.380 --> 01:48:54.119
flipping her burgundy tail back and

01:48:54.119 --> 01:48:54.420
forth.

01:48:54.539 --> 01:48:57.659
Assuming she's still alive.

01:48:57.720 --> 01:48:58.979
Glory thought.

01:48:59.039 --> 01:49:01.920
If you're both here about missing dragons

01:49:01.920 --> 01:49:04.079
she said, wouldn't it make sense to see

01:49:04.079 --> 01:49:04.800
the queen together?

01:49:04.859 --> 01:49:07.800
Brameliad and mangrove blinked at each

01:49:07.800 --> 01:49:08.640
other, considering.

01:49:08.640 --> 01:49:11.579
Next, called the voice again.

01:49:11.640 --> 01:49:14.939
The 1st dragon emerged and flew away, and

01:49:14.939 --> 01:49:16.859
the orange dragon hauled her dragonette

01:49:16.859 --> 01:49:18.779
across the bridge into the tree house.

01:49:18.840 --> 01:49:20.880
There could be totally different

01:49:20.880 --> 01:49:21.720
explanations.

01:49:21.840 --> 01:49:23.460
Mangrove said.

01:49:23.520 --> 01:49:25.979
I'm sure something terrible happened to

01:49:25.979 --> 01:49:26.699
Orchid.

01:49:26.760 --> 01:49:30.000
And I'm pretty sure Kingaju ran off

01:49:30.000 --> 01:49:32.340
despite me, said Bromeliad.

01:49:32.399 --> 01:49:34.859
Still, Glory said.

01:49:34.920 --> 01:49:38.819
I mean, it makes no difference to me, but

01:49:38.819 --> 01:49:41.399
maybe she'd listen to 2 dragons more than

01:49:41.399 --> 01:49:42.420
she'd listen to one.

01:49:42.479 --> 01:49:45.960
Promiliad glanced to the 3 dragons in the

01:49:45.960 --> 01:49:47.220
line between her and Mangrove.

01:49:47.279 --> 01:49:49.920
One was fast asleep, and the other 2

01:49:49.920 --> 01:49:51.600
seemed to be half listening, half

01:49:51.600 --> 01:49:52.619
watching butterflies.

01:49:52.680 --> 01:49:54.180
Next.

01:49:54.300 --> 01:49:58.680
Come on, Mangrove said, reaching back and

01:49:58.680 --> 01:50:00.239
hauling Bromeliad up with him.

01:50:00.300 --> 01:50:03.180
And you too, he said to Glory.

01:50:03.239 --> 01:50:06.600
Wait here, Glory called to her friends.

01:50:06.659 --> 01:50:09.180
Clay looked up with melons stuffed in

01:50:09.180 --> 01:50:11.159
each cheek as she hurried over the

01:50:11.159 --> 01:50:12.779
walkway after the rain wings.

01:50:12.840 --> 01:50:15.300
Glory heard tsunami starting to protest

01:50:15.300 --> 01:50:17.340
and then the voices of Starflight and

01:50:17.340 --> 01:50:18.119
Sonny hushing her.

01:50:18.180 --> 01:50:20.699
The hanging vines of yellow flowers

01:50:20.699 --> 01:50:22.199
smelled like honey and vanilla.

01:50:22.260 --> 01:50:25.560
They swished against Glory's snout as she

01:50:25.560 --> 01:50:27.000
pushed through into the sunlit room

01:50:27.000 --> 01:50:27.899
beyond.

01:50:27.960 --> 01:50:30.300
To her surprise, there were no guards.

01:50:30.359 --> 01:50:33.539
No soldiers protecting the queen, no

01:50:33.539 --> 01:50:35.399
heralds announcing each arrival.

01:50:35.640 --> 01:50:37.500
The only dragon in the room was Queen

01:50:37.500 --> 01:50:40.380
Magnificent herself, curled on a sort of

01:50:40.380 --> 01:50:43.319
nest, made from lacy scarlet flowers and

01:50:43.319 --> 01:50:44.760
scraps of russet monkey fur.

01:50:44.819 --> 01:50:48.000
The queen was as large as coral, but

01:50:48.000 --> 01:50:49.500
personally, Glory thought she was a lot

01:50:49.500 --> 01:50:50.159
more impressive.

01:50:50.220 --> 01:50:52.920
Instead of gaudy ropes of pearls

01:50:52.920 --> 01:50:55.260
magnificent wore only a few garlands of

01:50:55.260 --> 01:50:58.020
the white dragonfly wing flowers, which

01:50:58.020 --> 01:50:59.939
set off the iridescent brightness of her

01:50:59.939 --> 01:51:00.720
shifting scales.

01:51:00.779 --> 01:51:03.960
Settled under one of her wings, was a

01:51:03.960 --> 01:51:06.420
silvery gray sloth, much like the one on

01:51:06.420 --> 01:51:07.079
glory's back.

01:51:07.079 --> 01:51:10.619
It made a welcoming yurp, noise, and

01:51:10.619 --> 01:51:12.539
glorious sloth burbled in response.

01:51:12.659 --> 01:51:15.119
The queen flicked the point of her tail

01:51:15.119 --> 01:51:17.819
and leaned forward to sniff at glory.

01:51:17.880 --> 01:51:20.159
Her green eyes were friendly, and a

01:51:20.159 --> 01:51:21.060
little sleepy looking.

01:51:21.119 --> 01:51:24.899
You're new, she said cheerfully.

01:51:24.960 --> 01:51:26.159
Aren't you?

01:51:26.220 --> 01:51:27.479
How exciting.

01:51:27.539 --> 01:51:29.340
I like new things.

01:51:29.399 --> 01:51:31.380
It's my turn.

01:51:31.439 --> 01:51:33.359
Mangrove insisted.

01:51:33.420 --> 01:51:35.880
This dragonette just wanted to watch.

01:51:35.939 --> 01:51:40.859
All right, said Queen Magnificent, as if

01:51:40.859 --> 01:51:42.239
she wasn't that curious anyway.

01:51:42.300 --> 01:51:45.359
She turned to mangrove and Bromeliad, and

01:51:45.359 --> 01:51:46.979
wrinkled her snout to look like she was

01:51:46.979 --> 01:51:47.279
listening.

01:51:47.340 --> 01:51:49.020
Go ahead.

01:51:49.079 --> 01:51:53.279
You know why I'm here. said Mangrove.

01:51:53.340 --> 01:51:55.199
Orchid is still missing.

01:51:55.260 --> 01:51:57.359
It's been 3 weeks.

01:51:57.420 --> 01:51:59.399
We have to go looking for her.

01:51:59.460 --> 01:52:03.420
Orchid, said the queen.

01:52:03.479 --> 01:52:05.399
Tapping her chin thoughtfully.

01:52:05.460 --> 01:52:08.399
Of course, still missing.

01:52:08.460 --> 01:52:10.739
Or kid.

01:52:10.859 --> 01:52:14.039
I come to about this every day.

01:52:14.100 --> 01:52:15.779
Mangrove said.

01:52:15.840 --> 01:52:18.659
Remember, we were fruit gathering and she

01:52:18.659 --> 01:52:19.260
disappeared.

01:52:19.380 --> 01:52:22.319
Mm-hmm, said the queen.

01:52:22.380 --> 01:52:23.760
What about you?

01:52:23.819 --> 01:52:26.939
From Iliad shook out her wings.

01:52:27.000 --> 01:52:29.760
My student, Kingaju, ran off during a

01:52:29.760 --> 01:52:32.159
venom training session, and hasn't come

01:52:32.159 --> 01:52:32.399
back.

01:52:32.460 --> 01:52:36.000
I want the blame lifted from me so I can

01:52:36.000 --> 01:52:37.680
go back to my regular life.

01:52:37.739 --> 01:52:40.680
How long ago was this?

01:52:40.739 --> 01:52:42.359
The queen asked.

01:52:42.420 --> 01:52:46.199
About 18 days, said Bromeliad.

01:52:46.260 --> 01:52:49.380
She's no one's favorite dragonette.

01:52:49.439 --> 01:52:50.159
I might add.

01:52:50.279 --> 01:52:53.279
All right then, said the queen.

01:52:53.340 --> 01:52:55.199
You may start training again.

01:52:55.260 --> 01:52:59.279
Thank you. said Bromeliad with a bow

01:52:59.279 --> 01:53:00.420
backing toward the door.

01:53:00.479 --> 01:53:03.479
Hang on, Glory said.

01:53:03.539 --> 01:53:06.060
Not that it means anything to me, but

01:53:06.060 --> 01:53:08.640
isn't anyone worried that 2 dragons

01:53:08.640 --> 01:53:10.140
disappeared within a few days of each

01:53:10.140 --> 01:53:10.319
other?

01:53:10.439 --> 01:53:12.359
Did they?

01:53:12.420 --> 01:53:13.619
Said the queen.

01:53:13.680 --> 01:53:16.079
She curled her front talons around her

01:53:16.079 --> 01:53:17.760
sloth and stroked its head.

01:53:17.880 --> 01:53:20.699
They'll probably turn up.

01:53:20.760 --> 01:53:22.199
Dragons usually do.

01:53:22.260 --> 01:53:26.100
Not lately, Mangrove said.

01:53:26.159 --> 01:53:29.220
We have 12 dragons missing from our

01:53:29.220 --> 01:53:32.520
village right now, including Orchid and

01:53:32.520 --> 01:53:33.239
Kinkachu.

01:53:33.300 --> 01:53:36.960
12. murmured the queen.

01:53:37.020 --> 01:53:38.939
Someone's been counting.

01:53:39.000 --> 01:53:41.520
Who has that kind of energy?

01:53:41.579 --> 01:53:44.460
She yawned and looked at her claws.

01:53:44.520 --> 01:53:46.319
There was an awkward pause.

01:53:46.380 --> 01:53:49.140
Familiad shuffled a few steps closer to

01:53:49.140 --> 01:53:49.439
the door.

01:53:49.500 --> 01:53:52.199
Mangrove coiled his tail tightly around

01:53:52.199 --> 01:53:54.539
his talons and glared at the queen.

01:53:54.600 --> 01:54:00.119
Um, Glory said, look, again, this is none

01:54:00.119 --> 01:54:02.460
of my business, but maybe someone should

01:54:02.460 --> 01:54:03.180
investigate.

01:54:03.239 --> 01:54:06.000
Like, find out if they all disappeared

01:54:06.000 --> 01:54:08.520
from the same general area, or if they

01:54:08.520 --> 01:54:10.859
have anything in common, or if they left

01:54:10.859 --> 01:54:11.819
any clues behind?

01:54:11.880 --> 01:54:16.020
All right, the queen said genially.

01:54:16.079 --> 01:54:17.699
Sounds tiring.

01:54:17.760 --> 01:54:19.560
Who wants to do that?

01:54:19.680 --> 01:54:22.800
Glory looked at mangrove, but he was

01:54:22.800 --> 01:54:23.579
already pointing at her.

01:54:23.640 --> 01:54:25.500
She should do it.

01:54:25.560 --> 01:54:26.520
He said.

01:54:26.579 --> 01:54:29.819
She seems like she has useful questions.

01:54:29.880 --> 01:54:33.119
Splendid, said the Queen.

01:54:33.180 --> 01:54:34.199
Let's do that.

01:54:34.260 --> 01:54:35.399
Problem solved.

01:54:35.460 --> 01:54:36.180
Next.

01:54:36.239 --> 01:54:38.939
Wait, Gloria said.

01:54:39.000 --> 01:54:42.060
I don't do stuff like this, and I'm kind

01:54:42.060 --> 01:54:43.439
of busy with other things.

01:54:43.500 --> 01:54:46.680
Well, I guess that depends.

01:54:46.739 --> 01:54:49.800
Saving the world and stopping the war is

01:54:49.800 --> 01:54:51.840
what the dragonettes and the prophecy are

01:54:51.840 --> 01:54:54.119
supposed to do and I'm not actually in

01:54:54.119 --> 01:54:54.899
the prophecy.

01:54:54.960 --> 01:54:57.960
But I guess if I accept my regular rain

01:54:57.960 --> 01:55:00.060
wing destiny, then there's absolutely

01:55:00.060 --> 01:55:01.319
nothing I have to do.

01:55:01.439 --> 01:55:05.159
Tag along on someone else's destiny, or

01:55:05.159 --> 01:55:06.960
settle for a future as a snoozing

01:55:06.960 --> 01:55:07.680
dingbat.

01:55:07.739 --> 01:55:10.439
Fantastic choices you've left me with

01:55:10.439 --> 01:55:12.060
talons of peace.

01:55:12.119 --> 01:55:14.880
Mangrove and Bromeliad had already swept

01:55:14.880 --> 01:55:15.539
out the door.

01:55:15.600 --> 01:55:18.060
Glory started to follow them, and then

01:55:18.060 --> 01:55:20.699
jumped back as tsunami burst in, followed

01:55:20.699 --> 01:55:21.840
by the other dragonettes.

01:55:21.899 --> 01:55:24.060
Clay and Starflight had their shoulders

01:55:24.060 --> 01:55:26.399
under Webb's wings, and their guardian

01:55:26.399 --> 01:55:28.199
was staggering, like his tail was about

01:55:28.199 --> 01:55:28.739
to fall off.

01:55:28.800 --> 01:55:32.520
Ooh, said the queen perking up.

01:55:32.579 --> 01:55:34.439
You're all new.

01:55:34.500 --> 01:55:36.659
What about?

01:55:36.659 --> 01:55:39.180
Glory glanced out of the waiting platform

01:55:39.180 --> 01:55:41.279
and saw that the other 3 dragons were

01:55:41.279 --> 01:55:41.460
gone.

01:55:41.520 --> 01:55:45.180
We convinced them that our situation was

01:55:45.180 --> 01:55:46.020
an emergency.

01:55:46.140 --> 01:55:47.279
Starflight said.

01:55:47.399 --> 01:55:49.199
Well, Sonny did.

01:55:49.260 --> 01:55:51.000
Sunny beamed.

01:55:51.060 --> 01:55:54.600
Greetings, queen of the rain wings.

01:55:54.659 --> 01:55:56.399
Starflight said grandly.

01:55:56.460 --> 01:55:59.159
He swept his wings out and bowed low.

01:55:59.220 --> 01:56:01.079
Ooh.

01:56:01.140 --> 01:56:02.640
The queen said again.

01:56:02.699 --> 01:56:06.060
We have come to you despite great peril

01:56:06.060 --> 01:56:08.760
in a time of crisis, to throw ourselves

01:56:08.760 --> 01:56:11.579
upon your merciful, we need your help

01:56:11.579 --> 01:56:12.960
Tsunami said.

01:56:13.020 --> 01:56:15.659
Magnificent wings drooped a little.

01:56:15.720 --> 01:56:19.500
Oh dear, she said, do I have to do

01:56:19.500 --> 01:56:19.979
something?

01:56:20.100 --> 01:56:24.899
This is Webbs, Sonny said, tugging on his

01:56:24.899 --> 01:56:25.859
talon to lead him forward.

01:56:25.979 --> 01:56:28.319
She pointed to the venomous gash near his

01:56:28.319 --> 01:56:30.779
tail, and Queen Magnificent made a

01:56:30.779 --> 01:56:32.699
disapproving tisk noise.

01:56:32.760 --> 01:56:35.279
That is very ugly.

01:56:35.399 --> 01:56:37.140
The queen observed.

01:56:37.199 --> 01:56:40.380
It sure is, said Glory.

01:56:40.439 --> 01:56:41.640
Also, it's killing him.

01:56:41.699 --> 01:56:42.840
Minor detail.

01:56:42.899 --> 01:56:46.560
Your dragons know about poison, tsunami

01:56:46.560 --> 01:56:46.920
said.

01:56:46.979 --> 01:56:49.020
We need someone who can help us cure

01:56:49.020 --> 01:56:49.260
him.

01:56:49.319 --> 01:56:52.680
That doesn't look like something one of

01:56:52.680 --> 01:56:54.600
us did, said the queen.

01:56:54.659 --> 01:56:58.079
We never use our venom on other dragons.

01:56:58.199 --> 01:57:01.739
All of the dragonette shot sideways looks

01:57:01.739 --> 01:57:02.340
at glory.

01:57:02.399 --> 01:57:04.199
She narrowed her eyes back at them.

01:57:04.260 --> 01:57:07.800
I dare you to tell her what I've done to

01:57:07.800 --> 01:57:09.180
save your stupid scales.

01:57:09.239 --> 01:57:13.920
It's not rain wing venom, Starflight said

01:57:13.920 --> 01:57:14.520
hastily.

01:57:14.579 --> 01:57:17.159
He was scratched by a sand wings tail

01:57:17.159 --> 01:57:17.520
barb.

01:57:17.579 --> 01:57:20.340
Oh, said the queen.

01:57:20.399 --> 01:57:22.619
I don't know anything about those.

01:57:22.680 --> 01:57:25.079
She took a deep breath to yell.

01:57:25.140 --> 01:57:26.039
Next.

01:57:26.100 --> 01:57:28.140
But Sonny interrupted before she could.

01:57:28.199 --> 01:57:32.460
Oh, please, you must have healers, she

01:57:32.460 --> 01:57:32.939
pleaded.

01:57:33.000 --> 01:57:34.560
Someone who could look at it?

01:57:34.619 --> 01:57:35.340
Please?

01:57:35.460 --> 01:57:36.960
We don't want him to die.

01:57:37.020 --> 01:57:41.579
Well, some of us don't, Glory muttered.

01:57:41.640 --> 01:57:44.220
Queen Magnificent tapped her claws on the

01:57:44.220 --> 01:57:45.600
tree house floor.

01:57:45.659 --> 01:57:47.579
Her sloth seized one of her talons and

01:57:47.579 --> 01:57:48.479
tried to gnaw on it.

01:57:48.539 --> 01:57:52.739
We do have healers, said the queen.

01:57:52.800 --> 01:57:54.840
Rolling her sloth playfully onto its

01:57:54.840 --> 01:57:55.020
back.

01:57:55.140 --> 01:57:57.539
I guess you could talk to them.

01:57:57.600 --> 01:58:00.119
There are about 12 tree lodges down from

01:58:00.119 --> 01:58:00.300
here.

01:58:00.420 --> 01:58:02.579
In the one with the red berries growing

01:58:02.579 --> 01:58:03.180
on the balcony.

01:58:03.300 --> 01:58:05.520
She pointed out one of the windows.

01:58:05.579 --> 01:58:09.359
They might not be able to do anything, but

01:58:09.359 --> 01:58:10.020
you may ask.

01:58:10.140 --> 01:58:14.159
Thank you, Sunny said, backing toward the

01:58:14.159 --> 01:58:14.340
door.

01:58:14.399 --> 01:58:17.340
And don't forget to report back to me on

01:58:17.340 --> 01:58:18.300
that investigation.

01:58:18.359 --> 01:58:20.760
Magnificent said to Glory.

01:58:20.819 --> 01:58:22.979
It'll be nice to have something to make

01:58:22.979 --> 01:58:24.119
mangrove go away.

01:58:24.180 --> 01:58:26.039
What's your name, anyhow?

01:58:26.100 --> 01:58:28.680
Glory, she answered.

01:58:28.739 --> 01:58:31.500
I was stolen from the rain wings by this

01:58:31.500 --> 01:58:33.840
dragon 6 years ago, when I was still an

01:58:33.840 --> 01:58:34.140
egg.

01:58:34.260 --> 01:58:36.420
Glory pointed at Webbs.

01:58:36.479 --> 01:58:39.180
Oh my, said the queen.

01:58:39.239 --> 01:58:40.560
That is rude.

01:58:40.619 --> 01:58:43.439
Well, I'm glad he finally brought you

01:58:43.439 --> 01:58:43.859
back, dear.

01:58:43.920 --> 01:58:46.380
He did nothing of the sort.

01:58:46.439 --> 01:58:47.819
Glory flared.

01:58:47.939 --> 01:58:49.199
I brought myself back.

01:58:49.260 --> 01:58:51.000
He was going to let me die.

01:58:51.060 --> 01:58:52.739
Glory?

01:58:52.800 --> 01:58:54.840
Tsunami interrupted with a frown.

01:58:54.899 --> 01:58:55.979
What are you doing?

01:58:56.039 --> 01:58:58.020
I don't know.

01:58:58.140 --> 01:58:59.460
Glory thought.

01:58:59.520 --> 01:59:02.699
Maybe I just want someone to be punished

01:59:02.699 --> 01:59:03.779
for everything I've been through.

01:59:03.840 --> 01:59:06.479
And the fact that nobody here even

01:59:06.479 --> 01:59:07.380
noticed I was gone.

01:59:07.439 --> 01:59:11.279
She took a deep breath, and forced all

01:59:11.279 --> 01:59:13.319
the dark, rolling red and billowing

01:59:13.319 --> 01:59:15.659
orange out of her scales until she was a

01:59:15.659 --> 01:59:18.060
calm white, like the blossoms around the

01:59:18.060 --> 01:59:18.720
queen's neck.

01:59:18.779 --> 01:59:22.079
Nothing, she said to tsunami.

01:59:22.140 --> 01:59:22.979
Whatever.

01:59:23.039 --> 01:59:25.560
I just figured Magnificent would want to

01:59:25.560 --> 01:59:27.600
know what happened to me, but she doesn't

01:59:27.600 --> 01:59:29.460
and who really cares anyway?

01:59:29.520 --> 01:59:32.279
Glory bowed to the queen and stepped over

01:59:32.279 --> 01:59:32.760
to the door.

01:59:32.819 --> 01:59:34.800
You all go see the healers.

01:59:34.859 --> 01:59:36.659
I'm going to start looking for the

01:59:36.659 --> 01:59:37.380
missing dragons.

01:59:37.439 --> 01:59:39.659
She pushed through the yellow flower

01:59:39.659 --> 01:59:40.079
curtain.

01:59:40.140 --> 01:59:43.199
Because someone should care when a dragon

01:59:43.199 --> 01:59:43.800
disappears.

01:59:43.920 --> 01:59:48.300
Chapter 8.

01:59:48.359 --> 01:59:52.020
Halfway across the bridge, Glory heard

01:59:52.020 --> 01:59:53.220
Clay's voice behind her.

01:59:53.279 --> 01:59:55.560
Wait, he called.

01:59:55.619 --> 01:59:58.140
His heavy talons thumped on the walkway

01:59:58.140 --> 02:00:00.180
making it shake and jump underneath her.

02:00:00.239 --> 02:00:02.220
What missing dragons?

02:00:02.279 --> 02:00:05.579
Some big scary thing is prowling the

02:00:05.579 --> 02:00:08.699
rainforest, Glory said, she resettled her

02:00:08.699 --> 02:00:11.880
wings, or at least something is making

02:00:11.880 --> 02:00:14.579
rain wings disappear, probably the same

02:00:14.579 --> 02:00:16.380
something that killed those mud wings.

02:00:16.439 --> 02:00:17.699
I'll figure out what.

02:00:17.760 --> 02:00:18.899
No big deal.

02:00:18.960 --> 02:00:20.520
I'll catch up with you all afterward.

02:00:20.579 --> 02:00:23.699
We don't all have to escort webs

02:00:23.699 --> 02:00:25.859
everywhere, Clay said with a smile.

02:00:25.920 --> 02:00:28.560
I'll come with you, and we'll bring

02:00:28.560 --> 02:00:29.399
Starfight too.

02:00:29.460 --> 02:00:30.899
Maybe we can help.

02:00:30.960 --> 02:00:33.060
Starflight, he called.

02:00:33.119 --> 02:00:35.220
The night wing poked his nose out through

02:00:35.220 --> 02:00:36.060
the hanging flowers.

02:00:36.119 --> 02:00:38.880
Let tsunami and Sonny take webs.

02:00:38.939 --> 02:00:39.720
You come with us.

02:00:39.779 --> 02:00:43.199
Glory shrugged, but her wing tips turned

02:00:43.199 --> 02:00:44.579
rose pink against her will.

02:00:44.640 --> 02:00:46.920
At least there were a couple of dragons

02:00:46.920 --> 02:00:48.060
who cared if she existed.

02:00:48.119 --> 02:00:50.939
After all, the only reason she was still

02:00:50.939 --> 02:00:53.159
alive was because Clay had been willing

02:00:53.159 --> 02:00:54.840
to risk his life in the underground river

02:00:54.840 --> 02:00:55.380
to save her.

02:00:55.439 --> 02:00:59.520
The golden sunlight was slanting sideways

02:00:59.520 --> 02:01:01.500
through the tall green trees.

02:01:01.560 --> 02:01:04.079
As glory, clay, and starflight glided

02:01:04.079 --> 02:01:06.720
between the branches, small whirlwinds of

02:01:06.720 --> 02:01:08.640
orange and blue butterflies lifted off

02:01:08.640 --> 02:01:09.779
and landed again behind them.

02:01:09.840 --> 02:01:12.479
Funny faced little monkeys with long

02:01:12.479 --> 02:01:14.460
tails chattered indignantly when the

02:01:14.460 --> 02:01:15.479
dragons swooped by.

02:01:15.539 --> 02:01:18.239
They found mangrove on a small platform

02:01:18.239 --> 02:01:20.699
by himself, sorting fruit.

02:01:20.760 --> 02:01:22.859
Glory landed lightly in the middle, while

02:01:22.859 --> 02:01:24.779
clay perched on the edge, and tried to

02:01:24.779 --> 02:01:26.819
keep his feet and tail from squashing any

02:01:26.819 --> 02:01:27.479
of the berries.

02:01:27.479 --> 02:01:30.479
Starflight found a nearby branch, and

02:01:30.479 --> 02:01:32.760
studied the fruit as if he were trying to

02:01:32.760 --> 02:01:34.560
match it with pictures from the scrolls

02:01:34.560 --> 02:01:35.460
he'd memorized.

02:01:35.520 --> 02:01:38.399
The red streaks in mangroves rough had

02:01:38.399 --> 02:01:40.439
been replaced by whorls of dark purple.

02:01:40.500 --> 02:01:43.260
He looked up and nodded brusquely at

02:01:43.260 --> 02:01:43.739
glory.

02:01:43.800 --> 02:01:47.220
You got me into this, Glory said, so I'm

02:01:47.220 --> 02:01:47.760
starting with you.

02:01:47.819 --> 02:01:50.039
Since you might be the only dragon who

02:01:50.039 --> 02:01:51.479
even knows about all the missing rain

02:01:51.479 --> 02:01:51.840
wings.

02:01:51.899 --> 02:01:53.939
Who was the 1st to disappear?

02:01:54.060 --> 02:01:57.359
Mangrove put down a banana and looked up

02:01:57.359 --> 02:02:00.479
at the sky, thinking, It must have been

02:02:00.479 --> 02:02:02.340
splendor, he said.

02:02:02.460 --> 02:02:06.060
She'd just finished her turn as queen, and

02:02:06.060 --> 02:02:07.199
passed it to dazzling.

02:02:07.260 --> 02:02:10.079
Whoa, Clay said.

02:02:10.140 --> 02:02:11.819
There's a queen missing?

02:02:11.880 --> 02:02:15.420
Well, she wasn't queen that month.

02:02:15.539 --> 02:02:17.340
Mangrove pointed out.

02:02:17.460 --> 02:02:20.640
And when she didn't come back, they just

02:02:20.640 --> 02:02:22.199
started skipping her turn.

02:02:22.319 --> 02:02:25.560
If she wanted it, they figured she'd show

02:02:25.560 --> 02:02:26.100
up for it.

02:02:26.159 --> 02:02:29.520
Was anyone with her when she went

02:02:29.520 --> 02:02:29.939
missing?

02:02:30.060 --> 02:02:31.140
Gloria asked.

02:02:31.199 --> 02:02:33.899
She felt the sloth circle and settle

02:02:33.899 --> 02:02:34.500
around her neck again.

02:02:34.560 --> 02:02:36.539
She kept forgetting it was there.

02:02:36.600 --> 02:02:39.239
It felt like a warm, floppy necklace when

02:02:39.239 --> 02:02:39.779
it wasn't moving.

02:02:39.840 --> 02:02:41.880
Mangrove shook his head.

02:02:41.939 --> 02:02:44.100
Not as far as I know.

02:02:44.220 --> 02:02:47.460
I noticed she was gone only when her turn

02:02:47.460 --> 02:02:48.539
came back around.

02:02:48.600 --> 02:02:49.920
And she wasn't there.

02:02:49.979 --> 02:02:52.979
But I can guess when she went missing

02:02:52.979 --> 02:02:55.199
because her sloth found someone else to

02:02:55.199 --> 02:02:56.699
live with right around then.

02:02:56.760 --> 02:03:00.600
Glory tapped her claws on a platform, and

02:03:00.600 --> 02:03:02.579
thought about the sea wing court, where

02:03:02.579 --> 02:03:04.920
politics and intrigue and betrayal all

02:03:04.920 --> 02:03:06.060
simmered below the surface.

02:03:06.119 --> 02:03:09.359
Not to mention the sand wings, where 3

02:03:09.359 --> 02:03:11.039
sisters were tearing apart the entire

02:03:11.039 --> 02:03:13.079
dragon world in their fight for power.

02:03:13.140 --> 02:03:16.619
Maybe one of the other queens took her

02:03:16.619 --> 02:03:18.060
out, she suggested.

02:03:18.119 --> 02:03:21.000
Maybe dazzling or someone wanted a longer

02:03:21.000 --> 02:03:23.579
turn, or less competition.

02:03:23.640 --> 02:03:26.100
Starflight nodded, as if he'd had the

02:03:26.100 --> 02:03:26.520
same thought.

02:03:26.579 --> 02:03:30.239
Mangrove's ears popped faintly yellow, and

02:03:30.239 --> 02:03:31.380
then back to purple again.

02:03:31.439 --> 02:03:35.100
Nothing like that changed, he said.

02:03:35.159 --> 02:03:38.159
The turns are the same length, one month

02:03:38.159 --> 02:03:38.579
each.

02:03:38.640 --> 02:03:41.279
And there were only 6 dragons in the

02:03:41.279 --> 02:03:43.319
tribe willing to be queen in any case.

02:03:43.380 --> 02:03:44.939
Now five.

02:03:45.000 --> 02:03:47.340
So none of them have to wait very long in

02:03:47.340 --> 02:03:47.699
between.

02:03:47.760 --> 02:03:51.420
Besides, nobody enjoys being queen.

02:03:51.479 --> 02:03:54.180
Can I eat this?

02:03:54.239 --> 02:03:57.180
Clay asked, poking a rubbery red sphere

02:03:57.180 --> 02:03:58.199
near his claws.

02:03:58.260 --> 02:04:01.199
If you must, said Mangrove.

02:04:01.260 --> 02:04:03.300
Clay scooped it into his mouth and

02:04:03.300 --> 02:04:05.100
started chewing with a startled

02:04:05.100 --> 02:04:05.880
expression.

02:04:05.939 --> 02:04:08.460
Who disappeared after splendor?

02:04:08.520 --> 02:04:09.779
Gloria asked.

02:04:09.840 --> 02:04:13.319
Two dragons who were out venom training

02:04:13.380 --> 02:04:14.579
said Mangrove.

02:04:14.699 --> 02:04:17.159
One of them was having trouble aiming his

02:04:17.159 --> 02:04:19.560
venom properly, so the other took him

02:04:19.560 --> 02:04:22.079
away from the village to practice, and

02:04:22.079 --> 02:04:23.340
neither of them came back.

02:04:23.399 --> 02:04:28.380
Kinkaju was working on her venom too, Lori

02:04:28.380 --> 02:04:28.739
said.

02:04:28.800 --> 02:04:31.380
Is there a particular spot where rain

02:04:31.380 --> 02:04:32.399
wings go to do that?

02:04:32.460 --> 02:04:34.380
Mangrove shook his head.

02:04:34.439 --> 02:04:37.140
Wherever the Venom Trainers choose.

02:04:37.199 --> 02:04:42.899
Clay mumbled around the fruit in his

02:04:42.899 --> 02:04:43.319
jaws.

02:04:43.380 --> 02:04:47.640
Yes, those fruits are, said mangrove.

02:04:47.699 --> 02:04:49.800
It'll probably take you an hour to

02:04:49.800 --> 02:04:52.560
swallow it, and then several days to pick

02:04:52.560 --> 02:04:53.939
the bits out of your teeth.

02:04:54.000 --> 02:04:57.119
Ah, Starflight said.

02:04:57.180 --> 02:04:59.520
Let's take a few back for tsunami.

02:04:59.579 --> 02:05:02.340
Glory hit our smile, trying to look

02:05:02.340 --> 02:05:03.840
responsible and investigative.

02:05:03.899 --> 02:05:06.239
What else can you tell me about the

02:05:06.239 --> 02:05:07.319
missing dragons?

02:05:07.319 --> 02:05:08.760
she asked Mangrove.

02:05:08.819 --> 02:05:10.260
How many females?

02:05:10.319 --> 02:05:11.640
How many dragonettes?

02:05:11.699 --> 02:05:12.239
Stuff like that.

02:05:12.300 --> 02:05:15.060
Mangrove counted on his claws.

02:05:15.119 --> 02:05:21.000
Seven females, 5 males, 4 dragonettes

02:05:21.000 --> 02:05:22.380
under the age of seven.

02:05:22.439 --> 02:05:26.520
Kinkaju is 3, so she'd be the youngest

02:05:26.520 --> 02:05:28.199
and Taper is the oldest.

02:05:28.319 --> 02:05:30.659
He's around 110.

02:05:30.779 --> 02:05:34.319
Do any of them have enemies in the

02:05:34.319 --> 02:05:34.680
tribe?

02:05:34.739 --> 02:05:35.819
Glory asked.

02:05:35.880 --> 02:05:37.979
Anyone who'd wish them harm?

02:05:38.039 --> 02:05:41.279
Mangrove drew himself up, and bolts of

02:05:41.279 --> 02:05:42.960
orange flashed along the underside of his

02:05:42.960 --> 02:05:43.260
wings.

02:05:43.380 --> 02:05:47.340
Rain wings don't ever fight each other, he

02:05:47.340 --> 02:05:47.579
said.

02:05:47.640 --> 02:05:50.220
There's no such thing as enemies within

02:05:50.220 --> 02:05:50.819
the tribe.

02:05:50.880 --> 02:05:53.520
Haven't you noticed how peaceful and

02:05:53.520 --> 02:05:54.659
harmonious everyone is?

02:05:54.779 --> 02:05:57.960
Well, sure, Glory said.

02:05:58.020 --> 02:05:59.460
Everyone but you.

02:05:59.520 --> 02:06:01.500
You seem a little grumpy.

02:06:01.560 --> 02:06:03.960
So apparently it's at least possible to

02:06:03.960 --> 02:06:05.159
be a grumpy rain wing.

02:06:05.279 --> 02:06:07.500
He stared at her for a moment with his

02:06:07.500 --> 02:06:08.039
mouth open.

02:06:08.100 --> 02:06:10.859
Whoops, Glory thought.

02:06:10.920 --> 02:06:13.739
I hope I didn't just lose my best source

02:06:13.739 --> 02:06:14.279
of information.

02:06:14.340 --> 02:06:18.359
I mean, she added, there's nothing wrong

02:06:18.359 --> 02:06:18.720
with that.

02:06:18.840 --> 02:06:21.239
I'm pretty grumpy most of the time.

02:06:21.300 --> 02:06:24.960
Most of the time. said Starflight.

02:06:25.020 --> 02:06:27.180
Moom voomph.

02:06:27.239 --> 02:06:28.619
Clay Mumble agreed.

02:06:28.739 --> 02:06:32.399
Some things just deserve being grumpy at

02:06:32.399 --> 02:06:35.340
Glory said, frowning at her friends.

02:06:35.340 --> 02:06:37.380
Mangrove let out a bark of laughter.

02:06:37.439 --> 02:06:38.819
All right.

02:06:38.880 --> 02:06:39.779
You're right.

02:06:39.840 --> 02:06:42.899
I guess I've been neglecting my sun time

02:06:42.899 --> 02:06:45.420
since Orchid went missing, he said.

02:06:45.479 --> 02:06:48.239
I used to be as cheerful as everyone else

02:06:48.239 --> 02:06:50.220
but I'm worried about her.

02:06:50.279 --> 02:06:53.279
He rubbed one talon over his roughened

02:06:53.279 --> 02:06:53.520
ears.

02:06:53.579 --> 02:06:57.659
Trust me, Orchid was perfection in every

02:06:57.659 --> 02:06:58.439
scale.

02:06:58.500 --> 02:07:01.140
No one could possibly want to hurt her.

02:07:01.199 --> 02:07:04.319
That's what I was afraid of.

02:07:04.439 --> 02:07:05.699
Glory thought.

02:07:05.760 --> 02:07:08.699
If another rain wing wasn't behind the

02:07:08.699 --> 02:07:10.680
abductions, then it had to be something

02:07:10.680 --> 02:07:13.800
more mysterious, and more dangerous.

02:07:13.979 --> 02:07:15.659
She couldn't help thinking of the dead

02:07:15.659 --> 02:07:16.859
mud wing soldiers.

02:07:16.920 --> 02:07:20.279
But what was dangerous, and strong enough

02:07:20.279 --> 02:07:22.800
to kill dragons, and why didn't anyone

02:07:22.800 --> 02:07:23.579
know it was out there?

02:07:23.640 --> 02:07:26.939
She glanced at Starflight, but he looked

02:07:26.939 --> 02:07:28.079
as puzzled as she was.

02:07:28.140 --> 02:07:31.319
I don't really want to talk about this

02:07:31.319 --> 02:07:35.039
anymore right now. said Mangrove, hunching

02:07:35.039 --> 02:07:35.520
his shoulders.

02:07:35.579 --> 02:07:38.819
Then do something else for us, Glory

02:07:38.819 --> 02:07:39.119
said.

02:07:39.180 --> 02:07:41.520
Take me to the last place you saw

02:07:41.520 --> 02:07:42.180
Orchid.

02:07:42.300 --> 02:07:45.600
Mangrove bowed his head, shoveled the

02:07:45.600 --> 02:07:48.239
unsorted fruit into a lopsided pile, and

02:07:48.239 --> 02:07:48.960
spread his wings.

02:07:49.079 --> 02:07:51.479
Glory and the others followed him over

02:07:51.479 --> 02:07:54.420
the edge, and rapidly down in giant loops

02:07:54.420 --> 02:07:55.739
toward the rainforest floor.

02:07:56.279 --> 02:07:58.920
It grew darker the farther down they

02:07:58.920 --> 02:07:59.220
went.

02:07:59.279 --> 02:08:01.439
With the sunlight caught in the treetops

02:08:01.439 --> 02:08:02.460
far above their heads.

02:08:02.520 --> 02:08:06.000
Glory watched the forest for signs they

02:08:06.000 --> 02:08:08.399
could use to follow the trail back, a top

02:08:08.399 --> 02:08:09.359
old banana tree here.

02:08:09.420 --> 02:08:12.000
A spider web as large as one of her wings

02:08:12.000 --> 02:08:12.300
there.

02:08:12.359 --> 02:08:15.000
She caught glimpses of other creatures in

02:08:15.000 --> 02:08:15.779
the undergrowth.

02:08:15.840 --> 02:08:18.300
A large furry ant eater had its nose

02:08:18.300 --> 02:08:20.279
buried in a hole, rummaging around.

02:08:20.340 --> 02:08:23.460
A pair of long legged, lavender colored

02:08:23.460 --> 02:08:25.680
birds paused in their stroll through the

02:08:25.680 --> 02:08:27.720
forest to shoot suspicious looks at the

02:08:27.720 --> 02:08:28.800
dragons whisking by.

02:08:28.859 --> 02:08:31.560
Glory was surprised at how far they flew

02:08:31.560 --> 02:08:31.979
from the village.

02:08:32.039 --> 02:08:35.159
Isn't there a fruit to gather closer to

02:08:35.159 --> 02:08:35.399
home?

02:08:35.460 --> 02:08:36.300
She called.

02:08:36.420 --> 02:08:39.060
Mangrove nodded, and twisted his head

02:08:39.060 --> 02:08:40.140
around to glance back at her.

02:08:40.199 --> 02:08:43.500
Or get and I like to search farther out

02:08:43.500 --> 02:08:45.300
in case we find something new.

02:08:45.359 --> 02:08:47.939
The rainforest is full of surprises.

02:08:48.000 --> 02:08:50.399
We find a new kind of fruit at least once

02:08:50.399 --> 02:08:50.760
a year.

02:08:50.819 --> 02:08:54.180
He landed beside a giant fallen tree

02:08:54.180 --> 02:08:56.159
overgrown with moss and vines.

02:08:56.220 --> 02:08:59.340
The undergrowth around his talons erupted

02:08:59.340 --> 02:09:01.859
as lizards and insects scurried busily

02:09:01.859 --> 02:09:02.039
away.

02:09:02.159 --> 02:09:05.819
Several bug eyed, sky blue frogs peeked

02:09:05.819 --> 02:09:07.739
out from the branches of the fallen tree

02:09:07.739 --> 02:09:10.319
flicking their tongues in and out, just

02:09:10.319 --> 02:09:11.100
like dragons.

02:09:11.159 --> 02:09:15.000
Don't eat any of those, Mangrove warned

02:09:15.000 --> 02:09:17.340
clay, sing the mud wings gaze following

02:09:17.340 --> 02:09:18.060
the frogs.

02:09:18.119 --> 02:09:20.460
Zoom, zoom, voom.

02:09:20.520 --> 02:09:23.520
Clay mumbled, pointing to his jaws, where

02:09:23.520 --> 02:09:24.960
the red fruit appeared to be stuck.

02:09:25.020 --> 02:09:27.359
Are they poisonous?

02:09:27.420 --> 02:09:28.680
Starflight asked.

02:09:28.739 --> 02:09:31.199
He poked the branches, but the frogs

02:09:31.199 --> 02:09:33.060
stared at him like, oh yeah?

02:09:33.119 --> 02:09:34.560
Bring it, you big lizard.

02:09:34.619 --> 02:09:38.939
No, Mangrove said, but they will give you

02:09:38.939 --> 02:09:41.699
the weirdest hallucinations about insects

02:09:41.699 --> 02:09:42.539
for about a week.

02:09:42.600 --> 02:09:44.340
Really not worth it.

02:09:44.399 --> 02:09:48.600
So Orchid disappeared around here, Gloria

02:09:48.600 --> 02:09:48.899
asked.

02:09:48.960 --> 02:09:51.420
Do you know if Kinkaju was in this area

02:09:51.420 --> 02:09:51.720
as well?

02:09:51.779 --> 02:09:53.640
Mangrove shrugged.

02:09:53.699 --> 02:09:55.260
Possibly.

02:09:55.319 --> 02:09:58.140
Romeliad likes as much privacy as

02:09:58.140 --> 02:09:59.939
possible for training her more difficult

02:09:59.939 --> 02:10:02.939
pupils, so no one else will see her

02:10:02.939 --> 02:10:03.600
yelling at them.

02:10:03.659 --> 02:10:06.300
Glory turned slowly.

02:10:06.359 --> 02:10:07.979
Studying the forest around them.

02:10:08.100 --> 02:10:10.739
She could hear monkeys, and birds

02:10:10.739 --> 02:10:12.000
chittering in the trees overhead.

02:10:12.119 --> 02:10:13.739
Wings flapped.

02:10:13.800 --> 02:10:17.159
Twigs snapped, and claws rustled in the

02:10:17.159 --> 02:10:17.520
bushes.

02:10:17.579 --> 02:10:20.579
The air smelled like mangoes and wet

02:10:20.579 --> 02:10:22.979
leaves, as if there were a pond or

02:10:22.979 --> 02:10:24.000
waterfall nearby.

02:10:24.060 --> 02:10:27.359
And there was another scent too, a

02:10:27.359 --> 02:10:29.819
horrible one underneath the others.

02:10:29.880 --> 02:10:31.380
Starflight?

02:10:31.380 --> 02:10:32.039
she said.

02:10:32.100 --> 02:10:33.779
What do you smell?

02:10:33.840 --> 02:10:36.779
She'd noticed that his nose seemed

02:10:36.779 --> 02:10:38.640
stronger than the other dragonettes.

02:10:38.699 --> 02:10:41.399
He'd been the 1st to smell fire when the

02:10:41.399 --> 02:10:43.140
Sky Wings attacked the Sea Wing Summer

02:10:43.140 --> 02:10:43.619
Palace?

02:10:43.680 --> 02:10:45.899
Maybe it was a night wing skill.

02:10:45.960 --> 02:10:49.260
The black dragon inhaled slowly. then

02:10:49.260 --> 02:10:50.159
wrinkled its snout.

02:10:50.220 --> 02:10:54.420
Something decaying. he said, like a dying

02:10:54.420 --> 02:10:54.720
animal.

02:10:54.779 --> 02:10:58.199
Mangrove blanched from horns to tail

02:10:58.199 --> 02:11:00.539
turning a pale, sickly green.

02:11:00.600 --> 02:11:03.060
Don't panic, Glory said quickly.

02:11:03.119 --> 02:11:04.560
I'm sure it's not her.

02:11:04.619 --> 02:11:07.800
It's not a dragon, right, Starflight?

02:11:07.859 --> 02:11:12.119
I'm not sure, he said, lifting a snout

02:11:12.119 --> 02:11:12.840
and sniffing again.

02:11:12.899 --> 02:11:15.119
She stamped on his foot, and he jumped

02:11:15.119 --> 02:11:16.199
with a yowl of pain.

02:11:16.260 --> 02:11:17.220
What?

02:11:17.279 --> 02:11:18.060
I can't tell.

02:11:18.119 --> 02:11:21.960
We'll go find it, Glory said to Mangrove

02:11:21.960 --> 02:11:22.800
you stay here.

02:11:22.859 --> 02:11:25.500
The rain wing leaned against the fallen

02:11:25.500 --> 02:11:27.180
tree with a stricken expression.

02:11:27.239 --> 02:11:29.819
Couldn't you be a little reassuring?

02:11:29.880 --> 02:11:32.640
Glory hissed at Starflight once they were

02:11:32.640 --> 02:11:33.359
out of earshot.

02:11:33.420 --> 02:11:35.279
Didn't you see his scales?

02:11:35.340 --> 02:11:38.520
Since when do you care how other dragons

02:11:38.520 --> 02:11:39.060
feel?

02:11:39.119 --> 02:11:39.840
He asked.

02:11:39.899 --> 02:11:41.819
I care better than you do.

02:11:41.880 --> 02:11:43.020
She countered.

02:11:43.079 --> 02:11:45.479
Maybe if you had actual nightwing powers

02:11:45.479 --> 02:11:47.579
and could read minds, you'd notice what's

02:11:47.579 --> 02:11:48.180
going on around you.

02:11:48.239 --> 02:11:50.220
Womph.

02:11:50.340 --> 02:11:51.659
Wom, wom, wom.

02:11:51.779 --> 02:11:53.220
Clay ordered from behind them.

02:11:53.279 --> 02:11:56.100
Starflight folded his wings close to his

02:11:56.100 --> 02:11:57.359
body and glared at her.

02:11:57.420 --> 02:11:59.760
Well, glory demanded.

02:11:59.819 --> 02:12:01.979
Can you follow the smell or not?

02:12:02.039 --> 02:12:04.380
He turned and stamped off through the

02:12:04.380 --> 02:12:04.739
trees.

02:12:04.800 --> 02:12:07.560
Moom, moom, moom.

02:12:07.619 --> 02:12:09.539
Clay said to Glory sternly.

02:12:09.600 --> 02:12:12.479
Ah, your lectures are even cuter when I

02:12:12.479 --> 02:12:14.279
can't understand a word of them, she

02:12:14.279 --> 02:12:14.640
teased.

02:12:14.760 --> 02:12:18.300
He gave her shoulder a playful shove that

02:12:18.300 --> 02:12:19.500
nearly sent her through the nearest

02:12:19.500 --> 02:12:19.979
tree.

02:12:20.039 --> 02:12:22.859
When they caught up to Starflight, the

02:12:22.859 --> 02:12:24.420
night wing was standing next to a small

02:12:24.420 --> 02:12:26.880
waterfall, as high as Clay's shoulder

02:12:26.880 --> 02:12:29.159
that splashed into a tiny pond.

02:12:29.220 --> 02:12:31.920
A stream no wider than a dragon tail

02:12:31.920 --> 02:12:34.020
burbled at the top of the waterfall and

02:12:34.020 --> 02:12:35.220
away from the pond at the bottom.

02:12:35.279 --> 02:12:38.460
Thick brownish weeds choked the slimy

02:12:38.460 --> 02:12:40.800
surface of the pond, and a dead fish

02:12:40.800 --> 02:12:42.060
floated in the shallows.

02:12:42.119 --> 02:12:44.819
The top of the waterfall was flanked by a

02:12:44.819 --> 02:12:47.640
pair of tall, dark trees, as fat around

02:12:47.640 --> 02:12:49.800
as the columns where sky wing prisoners

02:12:49.800 --> 02:12:50.220
were kept.

02:12:50.279 --> 02:12:53.100
Their trunks were so brown that they were

02:12:53.100 --> 02:12:55.319
nearly black, and their branches began

02:12:55.319 --> 02:12:57.779
far overhead, so they looked more like

02:12:57.779 --> 02:12:59.579
black pillars than trees.

02:12:59.640 --> 02:13:02.159
The closest one had a boulder leaning up

02:13:02.159 --> 02:13:04.380
against it, that was twice the size of

02:13:04.380 --> 02:13:05.220
Marosir.

02:13:05.279 --> 02:13:07.920
On the same side of the waterfall, at the

02:13:07.920 --> 02:13:11.279
base, halfway into the pond lay a furry

02:13:11.279 --> 02:13:12.420
wheezing sloth.

02:13:12.479 --> 02:13:15.180
Although it took glory a moment to figure

02:13:15.180 --> 02:13:17.220
out what it was through the cloud of

02:13:17.220 --> 02:13:18.779
flies around it.

02:13:18.840 --> 02:13:20.460
The terrible smell was thick in the air.

02:13:20.520 --> 02:13:25.680
Said Glory Sloth, leaning around her neck

02:13:25.680 --> 02:13:26.880
to peer at the one on the ground.

02:13:26.939 --> 02:13:29.220
Glory lifted her wing to block the

02:13:29.220 --> 02:13:30.600
gruesome site from her new pet.

02:13:30.659 --> 02:13:32.760
What's wrong with it?

02:13:32.819 --> 02:13:34.260
Gloria asked.

02:13:34.319 --> 02:13:37.319
She inched toward the gasping sloth, and

02:13:37.319 --> 02:13:39.720
realized that it had a serious bite on

02:13:39.720 --> 02:13:40.199
one leg.

02:13:40.260 --> 02:13:42.659
The wound was black and crawling with

02:13:42.659 --> 02:13:43.140
insects.

02:13:43.199 --> 02:13:45.840
It looked even worse than Webb's injury.

02:13:45.899 --> 02:13:49.920
I'm not entirely sure, said Starflight.

02:13:49.979 --> 02:13:52.319
I mean, that bite shouldn't have been

02:13:52.319 --> 02:13:52.859
enough to kill it.

02:13:52.920 --> 02:13:54.420
But it's clearly dying.

02:13:54.479 --> 02:13:57.539
Could it be Rainwing Venom?

02:13:57.659 --> 02:13:58.500
Glory asked.

02:13:58.560 --> 02:14:00.659
It looks about the size of a dragon

02:14:00.659 --> 02:14:01.199
bite.

02:14:01.260 --> 02:14:04.619
Her sloth started chirruping in a tragic

02:14:04.619 --> 02:14:05.279
distressed way.

02:14:05.340 --> 02:14:07.920
She slid it off her neck and held it to

02:14:07.920 --> 02:14:10.199
her chest, facing away from the sloth on

02:14:10.199 --> 02:14:10.500
the ground.

02:14:10.560 --> 02:14:13.680
It was comforting to feel its silky fur

02:14:13.680 --> 02:14:14.579
under her talons.

02:14:14.640 --> 02:14:19.500
Maybe, Starflight said doubtfully, but it

02:14:19.500 --> 02:14:21.000
looks like something slower acting to

02:14:21.000 --> 02:14:21.180
me.

02:14:21.239 --> 02:14:23.520
I guess it's been dying for several

02:14:23.520 --> 02:14:24.119
days.

02:14:24.180 --> 02:14:27.899
It does smell awful, Glory said.

02:14:27.960 --> 02:14:29.039
Poor thing.

02:14:29.100 --> 02:14:32.579
Clay crouched beside the sloth and lifted

02:14:32.579 --> 02:14:34.380
its leg carefully in his talons

02:14:34.380 --> 02:14:36.899
inspecting it as if he were hoping to

02:14:36.899 --> 02:14:37.739
find a way to fix it.

02:14:37.800 --> 02:14:40.800
The flies zipped angrily around his snout

02:14:40.800 --> 02:14:43.079
with loud buzzes of outrage.

02:14:43.260 --> 02:14:45.300
The dying sloth whimpered softly.

02:14:45.359 --> 02:14:48.479
Glory stepped around them and ventured up

02:14:48.479 --> 02:14:49.800
the slope to the pillar tree.

02:14:49.859 --> 02:14:52.079
Something about the boulder looked weird

02:14:52.079 --> 02:14:52.439
to her.

02:14:52.500 --> 02:14:55.560
It leaned almost too casually against the

02:14:55.560 --> 02:14:58.020
tree, as if it had been set there on

02:14:58.020 --> 02:14:58.680
purpose.

02:14:58.739 --> 02:15:01.500
She circled around to the other side and

02:15:01.500 --> 02:15:02.880
stopped. staring.

02:15:02.939 --> 02:15:05.760
There was a hole in the boulder.

02:15:05.819 --> 02:15:08.939
More than a hole, a doorway.

02:15:09.000 --> 02:15:13.260
Chapter 9.

02:15:13.380 --> 02:15:17.279
Glory wasn't quite sure how she knew this

02:15:17.279 --> 02:15:19.079
was not an ordinary hole in a rock.

02:15:19.140 --> 02:15:23.159
It looked like a hole, dark, with smooth

02:15:23.159 --> 02:15:26.159
stone edges, and just big enough for a

02:15:26.159 --> 02:15:27.720
full grown dragon to pass through.

02:15:27.840 --> 02:15:30.779
A moss curtain partly covered it in a way

02:15:30.779 --> 02:15:32.220
that didn't look quite accidental

02:15:32.220 --> 02:15:32.819
enough.

02:15:32.880 --> 02:15:36.180
But looking into it, made her head spin

02:15:36.180 --> 02:15:38.279
as if she were standing on the edge of a

02:15:38.279 --> 02:15:39.479
cliff and high winds.

02:15:39.539 --> 02:15:42.659
A faint sound whistled out of the hole

02:15:42.659 --> 02:15:45.239
like a storm howling on the far side of

02:15:45.239 --> 02:15:45.539
the world.

02:15:45.600 --> 02:15:48.720
She could sense that this hole opened

02:15:48.720 --> 02:15:50.880
into a tunnel, and that tunnel went

02:15:50.880 --> 02:15:51.420
somewhere.

02:15:51.479 --> 02:15:55.020
It was impossible She could walk all the

02:15:55.020 --> 02:15:56.760
way around the boulder. and there was

02:15:56.760 --> 02:15:59.100
nowhere for a tunnel to go, but she was

02:15:59.100 --> 02:15:59.520
sure of it.

02:15:59.579 --> 02:16:03.659
Starflight, she said, as calmly as she

02:16:03.659 --> 02:16:03.899
could.

02:16:03.960 --> 02:16:05.640
What do you think of this?

02:16:05.760 --> 02:16:08.460
The night wing climbed up beside her

02:16:08.460 --> 02:16:10.979
heard around the boulder, and jumped back

02:16:10.979 --> 02:16:11.880
when he saw the hole.

02:16:12.000 --> 02:16:14.039
A tremor shivered through his wings.

02:16:14.159 --> 02:16:17.279
I think it's horrible, he said.

02:16:17.340 --> 02:16:18.659
Can't you feel it?

02:16:18.720 --> 02:16:20.460
There's something horribly wrong with

02:16:20.460 --> 02:16:20.640
it.

02:16:20.699 --> 02:16:23.159
Like someone ripped a hole where there

02:16:23.159 --> 02:16:23.579
shouldn't be one.

02:16:23.699 --> 02:16:25.079
Don't go near it.

02:16:25.199 --> 02:16:28.979
I think I have to go into it, Glory

02:16:28.979 --> 02:16:29.220
said.

02:16:29.279 --> 02:16:32.280
You say that like you're not terrified

02:16:32.280 --> 02:16:33.600
Starfight said.

02:16:33.719 --> 02:16:36.359
But I can see your scales turning the

02:16:36.359 --> 02:16:38.399
same pale green that mangroves just

02:16:38.399 --> 02:16:38.639
were.

02:16:38.700 --> 02:16:40.920
That means frightened, doesn't it?

02:16:40.979 --> 02:16:44.459
Don't try to read my scales, Glory

02:16:44.459 --> 02:16:44.940
snapped.

02:16:45.000 --> 02:16:47.340
She deliberately turned herself as black

02:16:47.340 --> 02:16:48.000
as he was.

02:16:48.059 --> 02:16:50.999
It's not a coincidence that this hole is

02:16:50.999 --> 02:16:51.239
here.

02:16:51.299 --> 02:16:53.399
Close to where at least one dragon

02:16:53.399 --> 02:16:54.059
disappeared.

02:16:54.120 --> 02:16:55.979
Maybe Orchid went through.

02:16:56.040 --> 02:16:58.739
Or maybe something came out and got her.

02:16:58.860 --> 02:17:04.020
Um, exactly, Starflight said, and she was

02:17:04.020 --> 02:17:04.680
never seen again.

02:17:04.739 --> 02:17:07.139
I'm pretty sure you just made my point

02:17:07.139 --> 02:17:07.559
for me.

02:17:07.620 --> 02:17:11.579
I promised I'd figure this out, Gloria

02:17:11.579 --> 02:17:12.120
insisted.

02:17:12.180 --> 02:17:14.340
Not run and hide the moment we found a

02:17:14.340 --> 02:17:14.639
clue.

02:17:14.700 --> 02:17:17.940
Clay joined them, his wings drooping.

02:17:18.000 --> 02:17:20.520
His jaws were finally free of the rubbery

02:17:20.520 --> 02:17:21.000
red fruit.

02:17:21.059 --> 02:17:23.699
There was nothing I could do for the

02:17:23.699 --> 02:17:24.119
sloth.

02:17:24.180 --> 02:17:25.139
He said.

02:17:25.200 --> 02:17:26.819
It was too far gone.

02:17:26.879 --> 02:17:32.039
Said Glorious Sloth mournfully.

02:17:32.100 --> 02:17:34.739
Glory looked over Clay's shoulder at the

02:17:34.739 --> 02:17:36.780
still, silvery gray figure flopped on the

02:17:36.780 --> 02:17:36.959
ground.

02:17:37.020 --> 02:17:38.579
Is it dead?

02:17:38.639 --> 02:17:39.899
She whispered.

02:17:39.959 --> 02:17:40.979
He nodded.

02:17:41.040 --> 02:17:43.799
I didn't want to leave it in pain like

02:17:43.799 --> 02:17:43.979
that.

02:17:44.040 --> 02:17:46.559
But you're not going to eat it?

02:17:46.620 --> 02:17:48.600
She tilted her head at him.

02:17:48.659 --> 02:17:52.440
Seems a little heartless, you know?

02:17:52.440 --> 02:17:53.579
he said.

02:17:53.639 --> 02:17:56.519
And from the smell of it, it would

02:17:56.519 --> 02:17:57.479
probably make you sick.

02:17:57.540 --> 02:17:59.340
Starflight pointed out.

02:17:59.399 --> 02:18:02.219
I wonder what bit it, and whether it has

02:18:02.219 --> 02:18:03.360
any connection to this hole.

02:18:03.479 --> 02:18:06.360
Clay noticed the hole for the 1st time

02:18:06.360 --> 02:18:08.459
and flared his wings in surprise.

02:18:08.579 --> 02:18:09.959
Creepy.

02:18:10.020 --> 02:18:11.040
He yelped.

02:18:11.100 --> 02:18:13.020
Why is it so creepy?

02:18:13.079 --> 02:18:17.159
Glory wants to go in there, Starflight

02:18:17.159 --> 02:18:18.540
said, rolling his eyes.

02:18:18.600 --> 02:18:21.540
Clay stalked up to the hole, sniffed it

02:18:21.540 --> 02:18:22.680
and nodded thoughtfully.

02:18:22.739 --> 02:18:26.159
Yeah, we probably have to.

02:18:26.219 --> 02:18:28.079
No, we don't?

02:18:28.200 --> 02:18:29.579
Starfly cried.

02:18:29.700 --> 02:18:31.559
He curled his wings in toward his body.

02:18:31.620 --> 02:18:33.059
That's insane.

02:18:33.120 --> 02:18:35.100
There could be anything lurking in

02:18:35.100 --> 02:18:35.280
there.

02:18:35.340 --> 02:18:38.159
Including the answer to what is attacking

02:18:38.159 --> 02:18:40.020
the rain wings, Glory said.

02:18:40.079 --> 02:18:41.399
I'm going in.

02:18:41.459 --> 02:18:42.359
You 2 wait here.

02:18:42.420 --> 02:18:45.540
Clay pounced on her tail and sat on it.

02:18:45.600 --> 02:18:46.860
Ow!

02:18:46.920 --> 02:18:49.559
Glory yelped, trying to wriggle free.

02:18:49.620 --> 02:18:51.600
Get off, you giant lump.

02:18:51.659 --> 02:18:55.200
We might be doing this, but we're doing

02:18:55.200 --> 02:18:56.100
it sensibly.

02:18:56.159 --> 02:18:59.579
Clay said, as in tomorrow morning.

02:18:59.639 --> 02:19:03.299
When it's not almost dark, with backup

02:19:03.299 --> 02:19:05.159
and a rope and a plan.

02:19:05.219 --> 02:19:07.499
Tomorrow morning?

02:19:07.559 --> 02:19:10.439
Glory shoved him as hard as she could, but

02:19:10.439 --> 02:19:11.279
he didn't budge.

02:19:11.340 --> 02:19:12.959
I want answers now.

02:19:13.020 --> 02:19:16.440
Sounds like something tsunami would say

02:19:16.440 --> 02:19:19.799
Starflight said, with a smug face that

02:19:19.799 --> 02:19:21.000
meant he knew she wouldn't like that

02:19:21.000 --> 02:19:21.600
comparison.

02:19:21.659 --> 02:19:24.780
You are so asking to get bitten.

02:19:24.899 --> 02:19:26.280
Glory growled.

02:19:26.340 --> 02:19:28.620
She stared at the boulder for a moment

02:19:28.620 --> 02:19:29.399
thinking.

02:19:29.459 --> 02:19:32.819
Rushing in was the tsunami thing to do.

02:19:32.879 --> 02:19:35.519
Glory could be sensible and patient

02:19:35.519 --> 02:19:35.939
instead.

02:19:36.000 --> 02:19:37.799
All right.

02:19:37.860 --> 02:19:40.379
We can wait until morning, but I'm

02:19:40.379 --> 02:19:41.819
staying right here to watch this hole.

02:19:41.879 --> 02:19:44.819
I don't think it's going anywhere.

02:19:44.879 --> 02:19:47.099
Starflight said patronizingly.

02:19:47.159 --> 02:19:49.979
Yeah, but maybe I'll see something go

02:19:49.979 --> 02:19:52.799
into it, Glory said, or come out.

02:19:52.920 --> 02:19:55.860
Starflight backed away from the hole in a

02:19:55.860 --> 02:19:58.319
hurry, his wings twitching nervously.

02:19:58.379 --> 02:20:01.440
I'll stay with you, Clay said.

02:20:01.500 --> 02:20:04.500
Starflight, bring the others back here in

02:20:04.500 --> 02:20:06.780
the morning. along with the longest

02:20:06.780 --> 02:20:08.760
strongest vines you can find.

02:20:08.879 --> 02:20:11.879
And tell Mangrove will be here all night

02:20:11.879 --> 02:20:14.280
so he can go home, Glory said.

02:20:14.340 --> 02:20:17.219
Try to be a little sympathetic if you can

02:20:17.219 --> 02:20:17.700
muster that.

02:20:17.819 --> 02:20:20.579
Like, please point out that we haven't

02:20:20.579 --> 02:20:22.379
found orchids dead body or anything.

02:20:22.440 --> 02:20:24.479
All right.

02:20:24.540 --> 02:20:27.059
Starflight said, taking several more

02:20:27.059 --> 02:20:27.600
steps back.

02:20:27.719 --> 02:20:30.540
Don't do anything stupid while I'm gone.

02:20:30.600 --> 02:20:34.139
We'll try to contain ourselves said

02:20:34.139 --> 02:20:34.620
Glory.

02:20:34.680 --> 02:20:38.280
He flew off into the trees, and as the

02:20:38.280 --> 02:20:40.440
shadows quickly swallowed him up, She

02:20:40.440 --> 02:20:41.639
noticed how dark it was already

02:20:41.639 --> 02:20:44.040
especially down at the bottom of the

02:20:44.040 --> 02:20:44.399
forest.

02:20:44.459 --> 02:20:46.500
There was probably still a bit of

02:20:46.500 --> 02:20:48.899
sunshine up in the treetops, but night

02:20:48.899 --> 02:20:49.680
was coming on fast.

02:20:49.739 --> 02:20:52.799
She realized she was a bit relieved that

02:20:52.799 --> 02:20:54.360
Clay had stopped her from going into the

02:20:54.360 --> 02:20:54.600
hole.

02:20:54.659 --> 02:20:57.479
She needed to be able to see in the dark

02:20:57.479 --> 02:21:00.059
like tsunami, or breathe fire like the

02:21:00.059 --> 02:21:02.159
others, if she wanted to explore with no

02:21:02.159 --> 02:21:02.459
light.

02:21:02.520 --> 02:21:06.180
You can get off my tail now, she said to

02:21:06.180 --> 02:21:06.540
Clay.

02:21:06.600 --> 02:21:10.559
Let's find a place to hide, he suggested

02:21:10.559 --> 02:21:11.399
standing up.

02:21:11.520 --> 02:21:14.219
Ooh, and maybe something to eat.

02:21:14.340 --> 02:21:15.420
Are you hungry?

02:21:15.479 --> 02:21:16.920
I'm hungry.

02:21:17.040 --> 02:21:20.340
Shocking, Gloria said with a laugh.

02:21:20.399 --> 02:21:22.979
You know there's still enough of that

02:21:22.979 --> 02:21:24.959
fruit left stuck to your teeth to make a

02:21:24.959 --> 02:21:26.159
whole other meal.

02:21:26.219 --> 02:21:29.760
I know, Clay said ruefully.

02:21:29.819 --> 02:21:32.040
He ran his tongue across the gummy red

02:21:32.040 --> 02:21:34.139
bits stuck between his white teeth.

02:21:34.200 --> 02:21:37.079
But I kind of wish I had a sheep or a cow

02:21:37.079 --> 02:21:37.979
instead.

02:21:38.040 --> 02:21:40.739
Sorry, Glory said.

02:21:40.799 --> 02:21:42.600
You probably won't find any of those

02:21:42.600 --> 02:21:42.840
here.

02:21:42.959 --> 02:21:45.840
She spread her wings and leaped into the

02:21:45.840 --> 02:21:47.459
low branches of a fat gray tree.

02:21:47.520 --> 02:21:51.180
Vines covered in purple blossoms hung in

02:21:51.180 --> 02:21:53.940
long loops all over the tree, and another

02:21:53.940 --> 02:21:55.920
skinnier tree seemed to be growing up

02:21:55.920 --> 02:21:58.440
around the fat one, winding its trunk

02:21:58.440 --> 02:22:00.299
around and around it like a monkey's

02:22:00.299 --> 02:22:00.659
tail.

02:22:00.659 --> 02:22:03.299
They found a spot where the branches wove

02:22:03.299 --> 02:22:05.280
together thickly enough that they could

02:22:05.280 --> 02:22:06.659
both lie down without worrying about

02:22:06.659 --> 02:22:07.200
falling off.

02:22:07.260 --> 02:22:10.379
Through the vines, glory could watch the

02:22:10.379 --> 02:22:13.139
hole in the boulder, although it too was

02:22:13.139 --> 02:22:14.639
rapidly disappearing into the growing

02:22:14.639 --> 02:22:15.180
shadows.

02:22:15.299 --> 02:22:18.180
Clay curled up close to her, but not

02:22:18.180 --> 02:22:20.280
touching her, which she appreciated.

02:22:20.340 --> 02:22:22.559
She wondered if other rain wings

02:22:22.559 --> 02:22:24.840
preferred not to be touched or if that

02:22:24.840 --> 02:22:27.180
was a special thing of her own, picked up

02:22:27.180 --> 02:22:29.040
from living with 3 guardians who hit her

02:22:29.040 --> 02:22:30.780
almost as often as they looked at her.

02:22:30.840 --> 02:22:34.260
Let's be fair, she thought to herself.

02:22:34.319 --> 02:22:36.600
Webbs never hurt me himself.

02:22:36.659 --> 02:22:39.479
He just let the other 2 do whatever they

02:22:39.479 --> 02:22:39.719
wanted.

02:22:39.780 --> 02:22:42.899
So whenever Kestrel or Dune felt

02:22:42.899 --> 02:22:45.059
frustrated, whenever the war was going

02:22:45.059 --> 02:22:47.579
badly, or someone screwed up in battle

02:22:47.579 --> 02:22:48.059
training.

02:22:48.120 --> 02:22:50.340
Or there wasn't enough dinner for

02:22:50.340 --> 02:22:50.940
everyone.

02:22:51.000 --> 02:22:53.879
Or they just remembered they had a rain

02:22:53.879 --> 02:22:56.040
wing instead of the sky wing who was

02:22:56.040 --> 02:22:57.120
supposed to be in the prophecy.

02:22:57.180 --> 02:23:00.479
Glory was an easy target for an angry

02:23:00.479 --> 02:23:02.940
claw swipe, or vicious tail thump.

02:23:03.000 --> 02:23:06.299
Well, whatever, she thought.

02:23:06.360 --> 02:23:09.659
I'm free now, and Kestrel and Dune are

02:23:09.659 --> 02:23:10.200
both dead.

02:23:10.260 --> 02:23:13.260
She reached up and stroked the sloth

02:23:13.260 --> 02:23:14.280
curled around her neck.

02:23:14.340 --> 02:23:16.680
It snuggled into a talon with a soft

02:23:16.680 --> 02:23:17.219
warble.

02:23:17.280 --> 02:23:20.399
How does it feel to be home?

02:23:20.459 --> 02:23:22.440
Clay whispered after a while.

02:23:22.500 --> 02:23:25.559
His shape was just a blacker outline in

02:23:25.559 --> 02:23:26.219
the dark beside her.

02:23:26.340 --> 02:23:29.340
Glory coiled her tail around the branch.

02:23:29.399 --> 02:23:31.559
She'd been avoiding thinking about this

02:23:31.559 --> 02:23:33.540
ever since visiting the hatchery.

02:23:33.600 --> 02:23:36.899
I did exactly what I told myself not to.

02:23:36.959 --> 02:23:40.139
Got my hopes up, so they could be smacked

02:23:40.139 --> 02:23:40.860
down.

02:23:40.920 --> 02:23:46.139
It doesn't really feel like I am home, she

02:23:46.139 --> 02:23:46.739
said slowly.

02:23:46.860 --> 02:23:50.700
The suntime was great, and I like all the

02:23:50.700 --> 02:23:52.920
fruit, but the other dragons?

02:23:52.979 --> 02:23:54.299
I don't know.

02:23:54.360 --> 02:23:55.860
It's weird.

02:23:55.920 --> 02:23:58.079
I thought they'd be more like me.

02:23:58.139 --> 02:24:00.299
They're nothing like me at all.

02:24:00.360 --> 02:24:02.940
Clay's wings rustled.

02:24:03.000 --> 02:24:06.659
I thought the same thing, he said.

02:24:06.719 --> 02:24:09.600
I thought the guardians and the scrolls

02:24:09.600 --> 02:24:12.299
must be wrong about rain wings, because

02:24:12.299 --> 02:24:14.100
you're never lazy or boring.

02:24:14.159 --> 02:24:16.860
But I guess you're just different from

02:24:16.860 --> 02:24:17.280
the others.

02:24:17.340 --> 02:24:21.719
Maybe I'm not really, Glory said.

02:24:21.840 --> 02:24:25.200
Maybe more suntime would make me as lazy

02:24:25.200 --> 02:24:25.739
as they are.

02:24:25.799 --> 02:24:29.819
She remembered the sky kingdom again, and

02:24:29.819 --> 02:24:31.680
the warm, hypnotizing feeling of sleeping

02:24:31.680 --> 02:24:33.299
in the sun all day long.

02:24:33.360 --> 02:24:36.899
I doubt that, Clay said.

02:24:36.959 --> 02:24:39.120
Not all rain wings are the same.

02:24:39.239 --> 02:24:41.639
You'd be different no matter where you

02:24:41.639 --> 02:24:42.120
grew up.

02:24:42.239 --> 02:24:45.180
I wonder, Glory thought.

02:24:45.239 --> 02:24:48.540
And even if I am, what good does that do

02:24:48.540 --> 02:24:48.780
me?

02:24:48.840 --> 02:24:51.959
Not different enough to be part of a

02:24:51.959 --> 02:24:53.520
prophecy, she said.

02:24:53.639 --> 02:24:55.920
I'm still not a sky wing.

02:24:55.979 --> 02:25:00.000
We don't want a sky wing, Clay said

02:25:00.000 --> 02:25:00.479
firmly.

02:25:00.540 --> 02:25:02.760
Have you thought about what to do next?

02:25:02.879 --> 02:25:06.540
Like, if we all go look for Blaze.

02:25:06.600 --> 02:25:09.239
You don't want to stay here, do you?

02:25:09.299 --> 02:25:10.799
With your tribe?

02:25:10.860 --> 02:25:13.680
I have no idea.

02:25:13.739 --> 02:25:16.860
Glory said suddenly.

02:25:16.920 --> 02:25:17.940
Listen.

02:25:18.059 --> 02:25:20.219
They both fell silent.

02:25:20.280 --> 02:25:23.579
The rainforest was full of strange noises

02:25:23.579 --> 02:25:24.059
at night.

02:25:24.120 --> 02:25:26.819
Hidden birds hooted and squawked.

02:25:26.879 --> 02:25:30.180
The branches shook and rustled, as if

02:25:30.180 --> 02:25:32.100
animals made of wind were rushing through

02:25:32.100 --> 02:25:32.340
them.

02:25:32.399 --> 02:25:35.040
A chorus of burps and gurgles came from

02:25:35.040 --> 02:25:35.579
the stream.

02:25:35.639 --> 02:25:37.680
Which glory guessed was a gathering of

02:25:37.680 --> 02:25:38.100
frogs.

02:25:38.159 --> 02:25:40.200
Now there was something else.

02:25:40.260 --> 02:25:43.739
Something stamping slowly on enormous

02:25:43.739 --> 02:25:43.979
feet.

02:25:44.040 --> 02:25:47.280
Stamp, slither.

02:25:47.340 --> 02:25:50.159
Stamp, slither.

02:25:50.280 --> 02:25:53.520
The sloth had a stranglehold on Glory's

02:25:53.520 --> 02:25:53.819
neck.

02:25:53.879 --> 02:25:55.440
She could feel it shaking.

02:25:55.500 --> 02:25:58.079
She was sure her own scales were turning

02:25:58.079 --> 02:26:00.479
green with fear, and she had to force all

02:26:00.479 --> 02:26:01.920
her energy into staying black.

02:26:01.979 --> 02:26:05.219
The something made a sniffing, snorting

02:26:05.219 --> 02:26:05.520
sound.

02:26:05.579 --> 02:26:08.639
Slither, slither.

02:26:08.700 --> 02:26:10.979
It was near the pond now.

02:26:11.040 --> 02:26:13.319
It stopped moving for a long moment.

02:26:13.379 --> 02:26:16.079
Glory wasn't sure whether she was

02:26:16.079 --> 02:26:18.180
imagining the great hulking shape she

02:26:18.180 --> 02:26:20.340
thought she could see, like shadows

02:26:20.340 --> 02:26:21.120
within shadows.

02:26:21.180 --> 02:26:24.959
Crunch, crunch, slurp.

02:26:25.079 --> 02:26:27.840
Slurp, crunch.

02:26:27.899 --> 02:26:31.379
Gulping and smacking sounds followed, and

02:26:31.379 --> 02:26:32.579
then abruptly stopped again.

02:26:32.639 --> 02:26:37.680
Stamp, slither, stamp, slither.

02:26:37.739 --> 02:26:40.739
And as suddenly as it had arrived, the

02:26:40.739 --> 02:26:41.700
creature vanished again.

02:26:41.760 --> 02:26:45.299
Glory strained her ears, but she couldn't

02:26:45.299 --> 02:26:46.860
hear any footsteps retreating into the

02:26:46.860 --> 02:26:49.139
forest or the crackling of branches

02:26:49.139 --> 02:26:49.559
underfoot.

02:26:49.620 --> 02:26:52.979
Whatever it was, had disappeared very

02:26:52.979 --> 02:26:53.579
close by.

02:26:53.639 --> 02:26:57.299
As if it had gone back into its hole.

02:26:57.360 --> 02:27:01.079
Neither she nor Clay said anything for a

02:27:01.079 --> 02:27:01.500
long time.

02:27:01.559 --> 02:27:04.020
She wasn't sure enough that the

02:27:04.020 --> 02:27:05.819
slithering thing was gone to risk making

02:27:05.819 --> 02:27:06.360
any noise.

02:27:06.420 --> 02:27:09.840
She held as still as she could, even when

02:27:09.840 --> 02:27:11.280
her legs started to cramp.

02:27:11.340 --> 02:27:15.360
After what seemed like hours, she heard

02:27:15.360 --> 02:27:17.639
soft snoring coming from Clay's perch.

02:27:17.700 --> 02:27:20.219
She adjusted her wings and tried to sleep

02:27:20.219 --> 02:27:20.520
too.

02:27:20.579 --> 02:27:22.979
But every noise made her heart thump

02:27:22.979 --> 02:27:25.379
fiercely, and all she could do was swim

02:27:25.379 --> 02:27:27.600
in and out of a drowsy haze for the rest

02:27:27.600 --> 02:27:27.959
of the night.

02:27:28.020 --> 02:27:31.379
It was a relief when the sun finally

02:27:31.379 --> 02:27:33.299
started to drift down through the leaves

02:27:33.299 --> 02:27:33.540
again.

02:27:33.659 --> 02:27:37.260
She sat up, rubbed her tired eyes, and

02:27:37.260 --> 02:27:39.120
glanced toward the pond in the boulder.

02:27:39.180 --> 02:27:41.040
The dead sloth was gone.

02:27:41.100 --> 02:27:44.340
All that remained were a few tufts of

02:27:44.340 --> 02:27:47.219
gray fur and some blood spattered leaves

02:27:47.219 --> 02:27:50.280
soaking into the wet, wet ground.

02:27:50.340 --> 02:27:54.360
Chapter 10.

02:27:54.600 --> 02:27:58.200
By the time the other dragonettes arrived

02:27:58.200 --> 02:28:00.180
Glory had wiped out any trace of green

02:28:00.180 --> 02:28:01.979
fear from her scales.

02:28:02.040 --> 02:28:04.260
She waited by the boulder, her wings

02:28:04.260 --> 02:28:06.600
speckled gray like the stone, as they

02:28:06.600 --> 02:28:07.620
swooped down to join her.

02:28:07.680 --> 02:28:10.920
Sunny jumped up to hug Clay's neck as

02:28:10.920 --> 02:28:11.520
soon as she saw him.

02:28:11.579 --> 02:28:14.940
Hal's webs, Clay asked.

02:28:15.000 --> 02:28:16.440
Tsunami snorted.

02:28:16.500 --> 02:28:19.200
I don't think these healers have seen

02:28:19.200 --> 02:28:21.360
anything worse than a sprained wing or a

02:28:21.360 --> 02:28:23.219
stubbed claw before, she said.

02:28:23.280 --> 02:28:25.020
They're doing a lot of peering at the

02:28:25.020 --> 02:28:25.860
scratch and muttering.

02:28:25.920 --> 02:28:29.399
But I'm sure he'll be fine, Sonny said.

02:28:29.459 --> 02:28:31.319
The rain wings are trying their best.

02:28:31.379 --> 02:28:34.379
She turned and caught tsunami rolling her

02:28:34.379 --> 02:28:35.219
eyes behind her back.

02:28:35.280 --> 02:28:36.719
Sonny frowned.

02:28:36.780 --> 02:28:37.739
They are.

02:28:37.799 --> 02:28:41.100
Sonny, you think everyone's always trying

02:28:41.100 --> 02:28:41.700
their best.

02:28:41.760 --> 02:28:43.319
Tsunami pointed out.

02:28:43.379 --> 02:28:46.020
Little Sandwing huffed a small snort of

02:28:46.020 --> 02:28:46.440
flame.

02:28:46.500 --> 02:28:48.719
So, everyone is.

02:28:48.780 --> 02:28:50.219
Why wouldn't they be?

02:28:50.280 --> 02:28:54.719
Yes, dear, tsunami said, not unkindly.

02:28:54.780 --> 02:28:58.799
Hello, a voice interrupted.

02:28:58.860 --> 02:29:01.379
A pink comet streaked through the trees

02:29:01.379 --> 02:29:03.479
and thudded down beside the dragonettes.

02:29:03.540 --> 02:29:06.120
Glory jumped back and flared her rough at

02:29:06.120 --> 02:29:08.040
Jambu as he bowed to all of them

02:29:08.040 --> 02:29:08.579
grinning.

02:29:08.700 --> 02:29:10.559
What are you doing here?

02:29:10.620 --> 02:29:11.459
she asked.

02:29:11.579 --> 02:29:13.440
I heard what you were up to.

02:29:13.500 --> 02:29:15.600
And it sounded like fun, he said

02:29:15.600 --> 02:29:16.139
brightly.

02:29:16.200 --> 02:29:18.180
So I took the day off to see if I could

02:29:18.180 --> 02:29:18.420
help.

02:29:18.479 --> 02:29:21.059
Brother and sister working as a team.

02:29:21.120 --> 02:29:22.739
Awesome, right?

02:29:22.799 --> 02:29:25.319
He craned his neck to see the hole in the

02:29:25.319 --> 02:29:26.040
boulder behind her.

02:29:26.100 --> 02:29:28.979
Oh, freaky thing.

02:29:29.100 --> 02:29:31.680
No wonder it feels so weird in this part

02:29:31.680 --> 02:29:32.219
of the forest.

02:29:32.280 --> 02:29:34.799
Most of the rain wings avoid coming

02:29:34.799 --> 02:29:37.559
anywhere near this pond, but no one's

02:29:37.559 --> 02:29:39.180
ever reported a mystery hole before.

02:29:39.239 --> 02:29:40.500
I don't think.

02:29:40.559 --> 02:29:42.180
So what's the plan?

02:29:42.239 --> 02:29:45.360
The plan is I go in.

02:29:45.420 --> 02:29:47.879
Glory said, and everyone else waits

02:29:47.879 --> 02:29:48.120
here.

02:29:48.180 --> 02:29:51.120
Well, nobody liked that plan.

02:29:51.180 --> 02:29:53.340
Tsunami wanted to go first.

02:29:53.399 --> 02:29:54.840
Clay wanted to go together.

02:29:54.899 --> 02:29:57.180
Starflight was still in favor of not

02:29:57.180 --> 02:29:57.840
going in at all.

02:29:57.899 --> 02:30:00.479
Even Jambu started whining about not

02:30:00.479 --> 02:30:01.379
wanting to be left behind.

02:30:01.440 --> 02:30:05.399
Glory folded her tail over her talons and

02:30:05.399 --> 02:30:06.420
waited for them to shut up.

02:30:06.540 --> 02:30:08.819
Sonny sidled up to her.

02:30:08.879 --> 02:30:11.280
Maybe we could compromise.

02:30:11.340 --> 02:30:14.819
Sonny suggested quietly, Maybe you could

02:30:14.819 --> 02:30:16.379
take someone with you.

02:30:16.440 --> 02:30:17.879
Someone with fire, maybe?

02:30:17.940 --> 02:30:19.860
Who could help you with a darkness in

02:30:19.860 --> 02:30:20.219
there?

02:30:20.280 --> 02:30:22.920
Unfortunately, that was a good point.

02:30:22.979 --> 02:30:25.860
Glory didn't love the idea of blundering

02:30:25.860 --> 02:30:28.379
into total darkness alone, and if she was

02:30:28.379 --> 02:30:31.200
right, and it was a tunnel, there was no

02:30:31.200 --> 02:30:33.479
way to know how long it was, or how lost

02:30:33.479 --> 02:30:34.260
she could get.

02:30:34.319 --> 02:30:38.700
Like maybe Sonny started to say.

02:30:38.760 --> 02:30:42.780
All right, Glory shouted, silencing the

02:30:42.780 --> 02:30:43.260
others.

02:30:43.319 --> 02:30:44.940
All right, fine.

02:30:45.000 --> 02:30:45.899
Different plan.

02:30:45.959 --> 02:30:48.360
Clay and I go in 1st and see what's in

02:30:48.360 --> 02:30:48.540
there.

02:30:48.600 --> 02:30:51.120
Sonny looked disappointed.

02:30:51.239 --> 02:30:52.799
Glory wasn't sure why.

02:30:52.860 --> 02:30:55.319
She was doing exactly what the Sandwang

02:30:55.319 --> 02:30:55.799
had suggested.

02:30:55.860 --> 02:30:57.659
What about me?

02:30:57.719 --> 02:31:00.000
Tsunami said, bristling.

02:31:00.059 --> 02:31:03.540
You hold the other end of the vines, Clay

02:31:03.540 --> 02:31:03.840
said.

02:31:03.899 --> 02:31:06.360
If we yank on them 3 times.

02:31:06.420 --> 02:31:07.739
It means we're in trouble.

02:31:07.799 --> 02:31:11.520
So either pull us out, or if you can't

02:31:11.520 --> 02:31:12.780
come in and get us.

02:31:12.899 --> 02:31:16.379
Glory didn't love the idea of having a

02:31:16.379 --> 02:31:18.600
vine tied around your shoulders, but she

02:31:18.600 --> 02:31:19.200
was outvoted.

02:31:19.319 --> 02:31:22.500
As Starflight tightened the knots, she

02:31:22.500 --> 02:31:24.239
untangled her sloth and passed it to

02:31:24.239 --> 02:31:24.600
Sonny.

02:31:24.659 --> 02:31:26.700
Here, she said.

02:31:26.760 --> 02:31:29.159
Watch silver for me while I'm gone?

02:31:29.219 --> 02:31:33.000
Aw, Sonny said, brightening.

02:31:33.059 --> 02:31:34.200
Pretty name.

02:31:34.260 --> 02:31:37.020
Glory hadn't meant to say it out loud.

02:31:37.079 --> 02:31:39.059
She didn't want the others to notice that

02:31:39.059 --> 02:31:40.559
she was starting to like the weird little

02:31:40.559 --> 02:31:41.100
mammal.

02:31:41.159 --> 02:31:43.559
Well, you can call it whatever you want

02:31:43.559 --> 02:31:44.700
she said.

02:31:44.760 --> 02:31:48.059
The soft disagreed.

02:31:48.180 --> 02:31:50.219
But it flopped across Sonny's back with a

02:31:50.219 --> 02:31:51.000
blissful expression.

02:31:51.059 --> 02:31:54.659
It must like the sand wing warmth of her

02:31:54.659 --> 02:31:55.200
scales.

02:31:55.260 --> 02:31:56.579
Glory realized.

02:31:56.639 --> 02:31:58.680
What if it doesn't want to come back to

02:31:58.680 --> 02:31:58.920
me?

02:31:58.979 --> 02:32:01.139
She shook out her wings.

02:32:01.200 --> 02:32:03.899
Then it'll be Sonny's problem, I guess.

02:32:03.959 --> 02:32:07.440
Let's go catch a monster, she said to

02:32:07.440 --> 02:32:07.920
Clay.

02:32:07.979 --> 02:32:11.159
Remember, 3 togs.

02:32:11.219 --> 02:32:13.079
Clay said to tsunami.

02:32:13.139 --> 02:32:15.479
He squared his shoulders and marched up

02:32:15.479 --> 02:32:16.799
to the boulder alongside Glory.

02:32:16.860 --> 02:32:19.680
She knew he must be remembering the awful

02:32:19.680 --> 02:32:21.659
noises and dark creature from the night

02:32:21.659 --> 02:32:22.260
before too.

02:32:22.319 --> 02:32:25.260
She was glad he'd followed her lead of

02:32:25.260 --> 02:32:26.700
not telling the others about it.

02:32:26.760 --> 02:32:29.100
Starflight didn't need another reason to

02:32:29.100 --> 02:32:30.600
try to stop her from going into the

02:32:30.600 --> 02:32:30.899
hole.

02:32:30.959 --> 02:32:33.479
Let me go in first.

02:32:33.540 --> 02:32:36.540
Clay whispered, so I can light the way.

02:32:36.600 --> 02:32:40.260
Glory nodded reluctantly, and he stepped

02:32:40.260 --> 02:32:41.340
forward into the darkness.

02:32:41.399 --> 02:32:44.399
She followed right away, nearly stepping

02:32:44.399 --> 02:32:44.879
on his tail.

02:32:44.940 --> 02:32:48.180
He breathed out a plume of flame, and

02:32:48.180 --> 02:32:50.219
they saw a stone tunnel stretching ahead

02:32:50.219 --> 02:32:52.200
of them, then turning abruptly to the

02:32:52.200 --> 02:32:52.319
right.

02:32:52.379 --> 02:32:56.159
That's impossible, Clay whispered.

02:32:56.219 --> 02:32:58.739
This tunnel is much longer than the

02:32:58.739 --> 02:33:01.440
boulder, and it's not going down into the

02:33:01.440 --> 02:33:01.620
ground.

02:33:01.739 --> 02:33:04.139
Some kind of magic.

02:33:04.200 --> 02:33:05.760
Glory guessed.

02:33:05.819 --> 02:33:08.159
Maybe animus magic.

02:33:08.219 --> 02:33:10.500
Glory couldn't think of anything else

02:33:10.500 --> 02:33:11.879
that could have made a tunnel like this.

02:33:11.940 --> 02:33:14.399
Unless there were mystery creatures with

02:33:14.399 --> 02:33:16.860
powers similar to animus dragons.

02:33:16.920 --> 02:33:19.440
When she was 4 years old, she'd gone

02:33:19.440 --> 02:33:21.299
through a phase of reading all the animus

02:33:21.299 --> 02:33:24.239
dragon stories and hoping she was one, so

02:33:24.239 --> 02:33:26.100
that she could enchant Dune's dinner to

02:33:26.100 --> 02:33:26.459
eat him.

02:33:26.579 --> 02:33:29.879
Of course, no powers had ever manifested

02:33:29.879 --> 02:33:32.219
and it was probably lucky they hadn't.

02:33:32.280 --> 02:33:34.200
Given what they'd learned about that kind

02:33:34.200 --> 02:33:36.959
of magic from tsunami's sister anemone in

02:33:36.959 --> 02:33:37.620
the kingdom of the sea.

02:33:37.739 --> 02:33:41.399
On the one talon, the ability to

02:33:41.399 --> 02:33:43.260
manipulate and enchant any physical

02:33:43.260 --> 02:33:45.059
object, Glory thought.

02:33:45.120 --> 02:33:48.299
On the other, say goodbye to your soul.

02:33:48.360 --> 02:33:51.479
She squeezed past clay and set off down

02:33:51.479 --> 02:33:51.840
the tunnel.

02:33:51.899 --> 02:33:54.360
He stayed close enough to brush her wings

02:33:54.360 --> 02:33:55.260
with his snout.

02:33:55.319 --> 02:33:59.340
I thought the scroll said, there hasn't

02:33:59.340 --> 02:34:01.979
been an animus dragon in generations, Clay

02:34:01.979 --> 02:34:03.420
said, scratching his head.

02:34:03.540 --> 02:34:06.899
But between Queen Coral's daughters, and

02:34:06.899 --> 02:34:07.379
this being here?

02:34:07.500 --> 02:34:09.479
I guess I remembered wrong.

02:34:09.540 --> 02:34:13.680
No, that is what the scrolls said.

02:34:13.739 --> 02:34:14.940
Remember?

02:34:15.000 --> 02:34:16.680
That was in the histories written by

02:34:16.680 --> 02:34:18.600
Nightwings, Glory said.

02:34:18.659 --> 02:34:22.139
Nightwings can't stand animus dragons

02:34:22.139 --> 02:34:24.000
because animus power is much cooler than

02:34:24.000 --> 02:34:24.600
what they can do.

02:34:24.659 --> 02:34:26.940
And Nightwings would rather be the only

02:34:26.940 --> 02:34:28.739
magically powerful dragons out there.

02:34:28.799 --> 02:34:30.659
So maybe they lied.

02:34:30.719 --> 02:34:34.079
Or they didn't know that it runs in the

02:34:34.079 --> 02:34:36.360
sea wing royal family, Clay said.

02:34:36.420 --> 02:34:39.420
Or perhaps any dragons who do have animus

02:34:39.420 --> 02:34:39.840
power.

02:34:39.899 --> 02:34:42.360
Make sure to keep it hidden, so they

02:34:42.360 --> 02:34:45.479
won't be forced to use it, like, for the

02:34:45.479 --> 02:34:46.020
war or something.

02:34:46.079 --> 02:34:49.620
He breathed out another spurt of fire, and

02:34:49.620 --> 02:34:51.120
they saw the turn a few steps ahead of

02:34:51.120 --> 02:34:51.299
them.

02:34:51.360 --> 02:34:54.899
This tunnel might not be an animus thing

02:34:54.899 --> 02:34:56.100
either, Glory said.

02:34:56.159 --> 02:34:58.979
Maybe there's some other kind of creature

02:34:58.979 --> 02:35:00.659
who can do this type of magic.

02:35:00.719 --> 02:35:03.780
Clay didn't answer, but she felt the

02:35:03.780 --> 02:35:05.040
shiver that ran through his wings.

02:35:05.100 --> 02:35:06.780
At the turn.

02:35:06.840 --> 02:35:08.940
Glory leaned forward to glance around the

02:35:08.940 --> 02:35:09.180
corner.

02:35:09.239 --> 02:35:12.059
Even before Clay could use his fire.

02:35:12.120 --> 02:35:13.139
She saw light.

02:35:13.200 --> 02:35:15.899
Enough light to realize, the tunnel

02:35:15.899 --> 02:35:17.879
turned again to the left, and that was

02:35:17.879 --> 02:35:18.959
where the light was coming from.

02:35:19.020 --> 02:35:22.559
They crept to the next corner and peered

02:35:22.559 --> 02:35:23.040
around it.

02:35:23.159 --> 02:35:25.799
Another long tunnel stretched ahead of

02:35:25.799 --> 02:35:28.319
them, and at the end of it waited an

02:35:28.319 --> 02:35:30.840
outline of bright sunlight, much too

02:35:30.840 --> 02:35:32.340
bright for the floor of the rainforest.

02:35:32.399 --> 02:35:35.280
Clay and glory exchanged glances.

02:35:35.340 --> 02:35:37.200
Did we miss something?

02:35:37.260 --> 02:35:38.219
she whispered.

02:35:38.280 --> 02:35:40.260
I thought this tunnel would be much

02:35:40.260 --> 02:35:40.620
longer.

02:35:40.680 --> 02:35:44.280
Also that it would have, you know, a

02:35:44.280 --> 02:35:44.940
monster in it.

02:35:45.059 --> 02:35:49.139
It must have come from out there, Clay

02:35:49.139 --> 02:35:51.299
said, nodding at the circle of sunshine.

02:35:51.360 --> 02:35:54.719
They slid along the tunnel. keeping an

02:35:54.719 --> 02:35:57.239
eye out for hidden entrances, but as far

02:35:57.239 --> 02:35:58.979
as glory could tell, there were none.

02:35:59.100 --> 02:36:01.979
There were only the long, smooth stone

02:36:01.979 --> 02:36:04.620
walls leading to that brightness, which

02:36:04.620 --> 02:36:06.540
got more and more blinding the closer

02:36:06.540 --> 02:36:06.840
they came.

02:36:06.899 --> 02:36:10.799
She paused the doorway. blinking, and

02:36:10.799 --> 02:36:13.500
realized that sand was piled up outside

02:36:13.500 --> 02:36:16.020
as high as her shoulders, nearly blocking

02:36:16.020 --> 02:36:16.500
the exit.

02:36:16.559 --> 02:36:19.979
She dug into it, shoving sand aside until

02:36:19.979 --> 02:36:21.420
there was a hole big enough to crawl

02:36:21.420 --> 02:36:23.040
through, then poked her head out.

02:36:23.100 --> 02:36:27.239
The sun beat down on her scales, but not

02:36:27.239 --> 02:36:28.559
in the same way that it did in the

02:36:28.559 --> 02:36:31.079
rainforest treetops or in the claws of

02:36:31.079 --> 02:36:32.700
the clouds mountains.

02:36:32.760 --> 02:36:35.100
Here the heat was dry as ancient bones

02:36:35.100 --> 02:36:37.559
sucking all the moisture out of her

02:36:37.559 --> 02:36:40.200
scales, and there was no breeze that she

02:36:40.200 --> 02:36:40.559
could feel.

02:36:40.620 --> 02:36:43.379
Grains of sand trickled between her

02:36:43.379 --> 02:36:44.219
talons.

02:36:44.280 --> 02:36:47.159
As her eyes adjusted, she realized that

02:36:47.159 --> 02:36:50.159
the sand stretched, endless and pale to

02:36:50.159 --> 02:36:51.180
the horizon ahead of her.

02:36:51.239 --> 02:36:52.799
There were no trees.

02:36:52.860 --> 02:36:55.379
The sky was aggressively blue and

02:36:55.379 --> 02:36:55.979
cloudless.

02:36:56.040 --> 02:36:59.219
A sickly stench of death hung faintly in

02:36:59.219 --> 02:36:59.579
the air.

02:36:59.700 --> 02:37:02.639
There was nothing but desert as far as

02:37:02.639 --> 02:37:03.479
the eye could see.

02:37:03.540 --> 02:37:07.319
Clay squished himself up beside her, and

02:37:07.319 --> 02:37:09.000
stuck his nose out into the blazing

02:37:09.000 --> 02:37:09.180
heat.

02:37:09.239 --> 02:37:12.180
Yowch, he said.

02:37:12.239 --> 02:37:14.219
Glory's ears twitched.

02:37:14.280 --> 02:37:17.100
Out in the sky, a pair of tiny dark

02:37:17.100 --> 02:37:19.260
shapes appeared, approaching fast.

02:37:19.319 --> 02:37:20.879
Hide.

02:37:20.940 --> 02:37:23.520
Glory ordered, shoving clay back into the

02:37:23.520 --> 02:37:25.799
tunnel. throwing off the vine rope.

02:37:25.860 --> 02:37:27.299
She wriggled out of the hole.

02:37:27.360 --> 02:37:30.120
She stretched her talons across the sand

02:37:30.120 --> 02:37:32.520
and focused on her scales, watching them

02:37:32.520 --> 02:37:34.620
blur quickly into the pale brown gold

02:37:34.620 --> 02:37:35.280
white colors.

02:37:35.340 --> 02:37:37.139
Camouflaged.

02:37:37.200 --> 02:37:38.700
She stared up at the approaching

02:37:38.700 --> 02:37:39.180
dragons.

02:37:39.239 --> 02:37:42.540
There were 2 sand wings. swooping lower

02:37:42.540 --> 02:37:43.379
as they got closer.

02:37:43.500 --> 02:37:46.680
For an uneasy moment, Glory thought they

02:37:46.680 --> 02:37:48.780
must have seen her, but they whooshed

02:37:48.780 --> 02:37:51.299
past without even glancing down, and she

02:37:51.299 --> 02:37:53.100
realized they were aiming at something

02:37:53.100 --> 02:37:55.739
beyond and behind her. moving

02:37:55.739 --> 02:37:56.459
cautiously.

02:37:56.520 --> 02:37:59.399
Lori crept out another few steps and

02:37:59.399 --> 02:37:59.940
turned around.

02:38:00.000 --> 02:38:03.659
On this side, the hole was hidden in a

02:38:03.659 --> 02:38:06.000
dune, surrounded by a semicircle of dull

02:38:06.000 --> 02:38:06.959
green cacti.

02:38:07.020 --> 02:38:10.200
Each cactus was half as tall as a full

02:38:10.200 --> 02:38:13.139
grown dragon, with tiny thorns as sharp

02:38:13.139 --> 02:38:13.739
as fangs.

02:38:13.799 --> 02:38:16.680
A few dusty white flowers bloomed between

02:38:16.680 --> 02:38:17.219
the prickles.

02:38:17.340 --> 02:38:20.760
Beyond the cactus sentries, the dunes

02:38:20.760 --> 02:38:22.979
slanted down to an enormous structure in

02:38:22.979 --> 02:38:25.620
the distance, the 2 sandwings spiraled

02:38:25.620 --> 02:38:28.020
into it, vanishing behind the thick

02:38:28.020 --> 02:38:29.159
sandstone walls.

02:38:29.219 --> 02:38:31.559
There were no windows that glory could

02:38:31.559 --> 02:38:31.860
see.

02:38:31.920 --> 02:38:34.979
There was only the solid block shape, like

02:38:34.979 --> 02:38:36.840
a monstrous brick dropped on the sand.

02:38:36.899 --> 02:38:39.479
Wait, she thought.

02:38:39.540 --> 02:38:42.959
There was something dotting the top of

02:38:42.959 --> 02:38:43.440
the walls.

02:38:43.500 --> 02:38:46.799
Small dark shapes at regular intervals

02:38:46.799 --> 02:38:48.780
fluttering now and then in the very

02:38:48.780 --> 02:38:50.399
slight breaths of wind.

02:38:51.000 --> 02:38:53.760
She squinted, trying to process what she

02:38:53.760 --> 02:38:54.780
could see.

02:38:54.840 --> 02:38:57.360
It looked like, but it couldn't be.

02:38:57.479 --> 02:39:00.959
She closed her eyes abruptly and clutched

02:39:00.959 --> 02:39:01.440
her stomach.

02:39:01.500 --> 02:39:03.120
It was.

02:39:03.180 --> 02:39:06.540
She remembered the scroll now where she'd

02:39:06.540 --> 02:39:07.799
read a description of this place.

02:39:07.860 --> 02:39:11.159
The dark shapes were dragon heads.

02:39:11.219 --> 02:39:13.500
The heads of dragons who had been

02:39:13.500 --> 02:39:15.600
executed, and mounted where everyone

02:39:15.600 --> 02:39:18.239
could see them, to remind others of the

02:39:18.239 --> 02:39:19.500
dangers of disobedience.

02:39:19.559 --> 02:39:22.559
According to the scroll, you could smell

02:39:22.559 --> 02:39:24.420
them from miles in all directions.

02:39:24.479 --> 02:39:27.000
Glory knew where she was now.

02:39:27.120 --> 02:39:30.239
She was standing in a kingdom of sand

02:39:30.239 --> 02:39:33.239
within sight of Burns stronghold.

02:39:33.299 --> 02:39:37.440
Chapter 11.

02:39:37.799 --> 02:39:41.280
Burns stronghold had once been the

02:39:41.280 --> 02:39:42.600
original Sandwing Palace.

02:39:42.719 --> 02:39:44.879
That was where all the trouble had

02:39:44.879 --> 02:39:45.120
started.

02:39:45.180 --> 02:39:48.059
Glory flattened herself against the sand

02:39:48.059 --> 02:39:50.579
and stared at it, remembering the history

02:39:50.579 --> 02:39:54.299
webs had taught them. 18 years ago, Queen

02:39:54.299 --> 02:39:56.340
Oasis had rolled the sand wings from

02:39:56.340 --> 02:39:56.459
here.

02:39:56.520 --> 02:40:00.959
Her 3 daughters, burn, blister, and blaze

02:40:00.959 --> 02:40:03.719
had been minor dragons, footnotes in the

02:40:03.719 --> 02:40:04.500
scrolls of the time.

02:40:04.559 --> 02:40:09.239
Oasis was old, fierce, and canny, with a

02:40:09.239 --> 02:40:10.680
vast and impressive treasury.

02:40:10.680 --> 02:40:13.260
No one expected her to be challenged for

02:40:13.260 --> 02:40:14.040
many years yet.

02:40:14.100 --> 02:40:16.979
And certainly no one would ever have

02:40:16.979 --> 02:40:18.959
expected a puny treasure hunting

02:40:18.959 --> 02:40:21.180
scavenger to kill her, but that was

02:40:21.180 --> 02:40:22.139
exactly what had happened.

02:40:22.200 --> 02:40:25.799
Now the treasure was gone, and the 3

02:40:25.799 --> 02:40:27.659
sisters had drawn all the other tribes

02:40:27.659 --> 02:40:30.959
into their struggle for power. 18 years

02:40:30.959 --> 02:40:31.860
of bloodshed.

02:40:31.920 --> 02:40:35.399
Glory flicked her tail, concentrating on

02:40:35.399 --> 02:40:36.840
keeping her scales the color of the

02:40:36.840 --> 02:40:37.079
sand.

02:40:37.200 --> 02:40:40.559
Byrne had driven out the other 2 and kept

02:40:40.559 --> 02:40:41.639
the palace for herself.

02:40:41.700 --> 02:40:44.940
Or depending on which scrolls you read

02:40:44.940 --> 02:40:47.280
blister and blaze had escaped before she

02:40:47.280 --> 02:40:48.180
could kill either of them.

02:40:48.239 --> 02:40:51.719
They'd gone in search of allies, knowing

02:40:51.719 --> 02:40:53.819
that neither one could beat Bern on her

02:40:53.819 --> 02:40:53.940
own.

02:40:54.000 --> 02:40:56.520
This wasn't how the palace had looked

02:40:56.520 --> 02:40:58.200
during the reign of Queen Oasis.

02:40:58.260 --> 02:41:02.219
Byrne had added the thick walls, and, of

02:41:02.219 --> 02:41:04.319
course, the dragon heads on top of them.

02:41:04.379 --> 02:41:07.260
Glory wondered if Burne was down there in

02:41:07.260 --> 02:41:08.340
her stronghold right now.

02:41:08.399 --> 02:41:11.879
Or was she in the Sky Kingdom, trying to

02:41:11.879 --> 02:41:13.620
hold on to her alliance after what glory

02:41:13.620 --> 02:41:14.819
had done to Queen Scarlet.

02:41:14.879 --> 02:41:18.600
The real questions were, did she know

02:41:18.600 --> 02:41:19.559
about this passageway?

02:41:19.680 --> 02:41:21.959
And did she have anything to do with the

02:41:21.959 --> 02:41:22.920
missing rain wings?

02:41:22.979 --> 02:41:24.899
Glory!

02:41:24.959 --> 02:41:27.239
Clay hissed from the dark hole in the

02:41:27.239 --> 02:41:28.260
dune.

02:41:28.260 --> 02:41:29.040
What's going on?

02:41:29.100 --> 02:41:32.219
Gloria slid back down the hill to face

02:41:32.219 --> 02:41:32.459
him.

02:41:32.520 --> 02:41:35.819
We're in the kingdom of sand, she said.

02:41:35.879 --> 02:41:38.159
I have no idea how or why.

02:41:38.219 --> 02:41:40.680
What's that over there?

02:41:40.739 --> 02:41:43.139
Clay asked, pointing north.

02:41:43.200 --> 02:41:45.959
Glory turned and saw a wing of dragons

02:41:45.959 --> 02:41:47.579
flying high up in the sky.

02:41:47.639 --> 02:41:50.760
Their scales sparkled in the sunlight, so

02:41:50.760 --> 02:41:52.440
that even from here she could guess that

02:41:52.440 --> 02:41:55.260
they were ice wings, white and pale blue

02:41:55.260 --> 02:41:55.860
as diamonds.

02:41:55.920 --> 02:41:58.379
From their angle of flight, they seem to

02:41:58.379 --> 02:42:00.120
be returning from the Sky Kingdom to

02:42:00.120 --> 02:42:02.280
their own home on the frozen peninsula to

02:42:02.280 --> 02:42:02.940
the north.

02:42:03.000 --> 02:42:05.639
Ice Wings, Glory said.

02:42:05.700 --> 02:42:07.979
We're not too far from the ice kingdom

02:42:07.979 --> 02:42:08.219
here.

02:42:08.280 --> 02:42:10.860
That was hard to imagine in this

02:42:10.860 --> 02:42:13.020
blistering heat, but she remembered it

02:42:13.020 --> 02:42:14.219
from the map on the wall of their

02:42:14.219 --> 02:42:15.059
underground cave.

02:42:15.120 --> 02:42:18.239
Oh, Clay said brightly.

02:42:18.299 --> 02:42:20.399
So we could go find Blaze.

02:42:20.459 --> 02:42:23.520
Hooray, said Glory.

02:42:23.639 --> 02:42:25.500
She knew the others were hoping that

02:42:25.500 --> 02:42:27.420
Blaze would be a good candidate for Queen

02:42:27.420 --> 02:42:29.459
so they could choose her instead of burn

02:42:29.459 --> 02:42:32.100
or blister, but Glory's hopes weren't

02:42:32.100 --> 02:42:34.200
very high, based on what she'd read about

02:42:34.200 --> 02:42:34.739
Blaze.

02:42:34.799 --> 02:42:37.020
Could Blaze or the ice wings have

02:42:37.020 --> 02:42:38.700
anything to do with this passageway to

02:42:38.700 --> 02:42:39.299
the rainforest?

02:42:39.360 --> 02:42:41.879
But what had they heard in the middle of

02:42:41.879 --> 02:42:42.239
the night?

02:42:42.239 --> 02:42:44.040
And where had it gone?

02:42:44.100 --> 02:42:48.299
All right, let's go tell the others, she

02:42:48.299 --> 02:42:48.600
said.

02:42:48.659 --> 02:42:53.159
But that is completely impossible

02:42:53.159 --> 02:42:55.920
Starflight said, for the 1000000th time.

02:42:55.979 --> 02:42:59.100
The kingdom of sand is literally half a

02:42:59.100 --> 02:43:01.260
world away, on the other side of the

02:43:01.260 --> 02:43:02.700
mountains for moon's sake.

02:43:02.760 --> 02:43:05.040
You couldn't have walked there down a

02:43:05.040 --> 02:43:06.239
tunnel in the rainforest.

02:43:06.299 --> 02:43:09.540
Go look for yourself, Glory snapped.

02:43:09.600 --> 02:43:10.559
It's for real.

02:43:10.620 --> 02:43:13.079
Someone built a secret passage between

02:43:13.079 --> 02:43:14.700
here and Sandwing territory.

02:43:14.760 --> 02:43:18.059
She dipped her tail in the stream, glad

02:43:18.059 --> 02:43:19.440
to be back in the coolness of the

02:43:19.440 --> 02:43:20.100
rainforest.

02:43:20.159 --> 02:43:22.379
Her scales felt as if she'd run through a

02:43:22.379 --> 02:43:22.620
fire.

02:43:22.680 --> 02:43:25.799
Silver sat on one of glory's talons

02:43:25.799 --> 02:43:28.139
dipped her paw in the water, and patted

02:43:28.139 --> 02:43:29.280
it against glory's leg.

02:43:29.340 --> 02:43:31.079
But why?

02:43:31.139 --> 02:43:32.280
Tsunami said.

02:43:32.340 --> 02:43:33.420
What is the point?

02:43:33.479 --> 02:43:36.360
That, glory couldn't answer.

02:43:36.420 --> 02:43:38.760
So they could sneak through and eat a

02:43:38.760 --> 02:43:39.600
sloth here or there?

02:43:39.659 --> 02:43:40.799
That made no sense.

02:43:40.860 --> 02:43:43.200
And what made even less sense was

02:43:43.200 --> 02:43:44.459
kidnapping rain wings.

02:43:44.520 --> 02:43:47.879
Do you think sand wings are coming

02:43:47.879 --> 02:43:50.459
through here to attack the mud wings?

02:43:50.520 --> 02:43:52.319
Sonny asked hesitantly.

02:43:52.379 --> 02:43:55.260
Maybe it was a sandwing who killed those

02:43:55.260 --> 02:43:55.799
soldiers.

02:43:55.860 --> 02:43:58.860
Seems like a roundabout way of doing

02:43:58.860 --> 02:44:00.659
things, tsunami said.

02:44:00.719 --> 02:44:03.360
If the sand wings have an animus, they

02:44:03.360 --> 02:44:05.399
could create a passage straight into mud

02:44:05.399 --> 02:44:07.559
wing territory or something more useful.

02:44:07.680 --> 02:44:10.979
I still think this passage has something

02:44:10.979 --> 02:44:12.600
to do with the missing rain wings.

02:44:12.659 --> 02:44:15.540
Lori said, but I don't understand what.

02:44:15.600 --> 02:44:18.299
If they wandered into it by accident

02:44:18.299 --> 02:44:21.540
they'd just come back, the way we did, if

02:44:21.540 --> 02:44:24.719
they were taken, what would sand wings or

02:44:24.719 --> 02:44:26.940
ice wings want with a few rain wings?

02:44:27.000 --> 02:44:31.559
Burn likes collecting things, Starflight

02:44:31.559 --> 02:44:32.040
remembered.

02:44:32.159 --> 02:44:35.219
But you saw her face when Queen Scarlet

02:44:35.219 --> 02:44:36.840
was showing me off in the sky kingdom

02:44:36.840 --> 02:44:37.739
Glory said.

02:44:37.799 --> 02:44:40.500
Burn looked like she'd never seen a rain

02:44:40.500 --> 02:44:42.840
wing before, and she doesn't like pretty

02:44:42.840 --> 02:44:43.319
things.

02:44:43.379 --> 02:44:45.780
She likes horribly weird things.

02:44:45.840 --> 02:44:48.540
You're all so lucky you didn't see the

02:44:48.540 --> 02:44:50.760
creepy gift Queen Scarlet got for her

02:44:50.760 --> 02:44:51.899
when she came to visit.

02:44:51.959 --> 02:44:54.840
It was this dead stuffed crocodile with

02:44:54.840 --> 02:44:57.540
bat wings sewn on its back, so it looked

02:44:57.540 --> 02:44:58.680
sort of like a dragon.

02:44:58.739 --> 02:45:02.100
She shuddered. totally hideous.

02:45:02.159 --> 02:45:04.020
But Burne loved it.

02:45:04.079 --> 02:45:07.139
And you don't know anything about this

02:45:07.139 --> 02:45:09.719
passage, tsunami said to Jambu.

02:45:09.780 --> 02:45:12.059
Glory's brother lifted his brightly

02:45:12.059 --> 02:45:13.860
colored wings, looking baffled.

02:45:13.920 --> 02:45:16.319
I know that rain wings didn't put it

02:45:16.319 --> 02:45:17.459
there, he said.

02:45:17.520 --> 02:45:19.620
Why would we want a way out of the

02:45:19.620 --> 02:45:20.219
rainforest?

02:45:20.340 --> 02:45:22.139
Life is perfect here?

02:45:22.200 --> 02:45:24.780
Unless you make the mistake of going

02:45:24.780 --> 02:45:27.299
missing, and then good luck because no

02:45:27.299 --> 02:45:28.200
one's going to look for you.

02:45:28.260 --> 02:45:30.000
Glory pointed out.

02:45:30.000 --> 02:45:34.559
Well, maybe, John Boo said, as if that

02:45:34.559 --> 02:45:36.000
were a perfectly normal problem for a

02:45:36.000 --> 02:45:37.020
dragon tribe to have.

02:45:37.079 --> 02:45:39.059
But it's great for the rest of us.

02:45:39.180 --> 02:45:42.000
Glory wondered what color his scales

02:45:42.000 --> 02:45:43.079
would turn if she bit him.

02:45:43.139 --> 02:45:46.799
Do you even have an animus dragon?

02:45:46.920 --> 02:45:47.940
Starflight asked.

02:45:48.000 --> 02:45:49.680
What's that?

02:45:49.799 --> 02:45:51.120
Jambu answered.

02:45:51.180 --> 02:45:53.760
Never mind, Glory said.

02:45:53.819 --> 02:45:55.860
Do Sandwings ever visit you?

02:45:55.920 --> 02:45:57.780
Or have you ever seen one in the forest?

02:45:57.840 --> 02:45:59.819
Jambu shook his head.

02:45:59.879 --> 02:46:01.559
Don't think so.

02:46:01.620 --> 02:46:04.079
I don't even know what a sand wing looks

02:46:04.079 --> 02:46:05.399
like. he said.

02:46:05.459 --> 02:46:07.920
Me, Sonny said.

02:46:07.979 --> 02:46:09.120
Sort of.

02:46:09.180 --> 02:46:12.659
But you've seen them in scrolls, right?

02:46:12.719 --> 02:46:13.920
Starflight said.

02:46:14.040 --> 02:46:17.520
Scrolls, John Boo said.

02:46:17.579 --> 02:46:22.139
Um, those are Starflight looked as if

02:46:22.139 --> 02:46:23.639
someone had just asked him whether

02:46:23.639 --> 02:46:24.840
breathing was really necessary.

02:46:24.899 --> 02:46:28.379
You don't have any scrolls?

02:46:28.440 --> 02:46:29.760
He gasped.

02:46:29.819 --> 02:46:31.559
Don't you read?

02:46:31.620 --> 02:46:32.760
Do you really not read?

02:46:32.819 --> 02:46:33.780
Not anything?

02:46:33.840 --> 02:46:36.540
John Boo shrugged apologetically.

02:46:36.600 --> 02:46:39.600
I'm not sure what you're talking about. he

02:46:39.600 --> 02:46:39.780
said.

02:46:39.840 --> 02:46:42.659
Starflight had to sit down and fold his

02:46:42.659 --> 02:46:43.799
wings over his head for a minute.

02:46:43.860 --> 02:46:46.979
Glory coiled her tail as Clay described

02:46:46.979 --> 02:46:48.239
Sandwings for Jambu.

02:46:48.299 --> 02:46:50.340
Every new thing she learned about rain

02:46:50.340 --> 02:46:53.639
wings made them sound worse, a tribe

02:46:53.639 --> 02:46:56.159
without scrolls, who didn't care what was

02:46:56.159 --> 02:46:57.180
beyond their own borders.

02:46:57.239 --> 02:46:59.579
Why weren't they at least curious about

02:46:59.579 --> 02:47:00.360
the rest of the world?

02:47:00.420 --> 02:47:02.819
It made her want to shake all of them.

02:47:02.879 --> 02:47:04.559
Nope.

02:47:04.620 --> 02:47:06.059
Doesn't sound familiar.

02:47:06.120 --> 02:47:07.379
John Biz said.

02:47:07.440 --> 02:47:10.200
I'm pretty sure the only other tribe

02:47:10.200 --> 02:47:12.540
visitors we've ever had looked like him.

02:47:12.600 --> 02:47:15.899
He pointed at Clay, and they're usually

02:47:15.899 --> 02:47:17.639
lost and want to get out of the

02:47:17.639 --> 02:47:19.020
rainforest as fast as possible.

02:47:19.079 --> 02:47:23.879
Maybe we should destroy it, Sonny said

02:47:23.879 --> 02:47:24.659
unexpectedly.

02:47:24.719 --> 02:47:26.520
They all turned to look at her.

02:47:26.579 --> 02:47:28.920
She shuffled her talons on the damp

02:47:28.920 --> 02:47:29.639
forest floor.

02:47:29.700 --> 02:47:31.799
The passageway, I mean.

02:47:31.979 --> 02:47:33.840
It can't be here for anything good

02:47:33.840 --> 02:47:34.020
right?

02:47:34.139 --> 02:47:37.079
I know I don't like the idea that burn

02:47:37.079 --> 02:47:39.540
could pop out of there any minute, and if

02:47:39.540 --> 02:47:42.659
it's making rain wings disappear, Well

02:47:42.659 --> 02:47:43.620
who cares why?

02:47:43.680 --> 02:47:46.860
Let's just smash the boulder or stuff the

02:47:46.860 --> 02:47:48.659
tunnel full of trees and set them on fire

02:47:48.659 --> 02:47:49.079
or something.

02:47:49.200 --> 02:47:51.239
Glory blinked.

02:47:51.299 --> 02:47:53.159
It did sort of make sense.

02:47:53.219 --> 02:47:55.620
There was definitely something not right

02:47:55.620 --> 02:47:57.600
about this hole someone had ripped

02:47:57.600 --> 02:47:58.500
through normal space.

02:47:58.559 --> 02:48:01.020
Maybe destroying it would solve the

02:48:01.020 --> 02:48:03.120
problem, but Glory wanted to know the

02:48:03.120 --> 02:48:03.899
answer too.

02:48:03.959 --> 02:48:05.399
There had to be a why.

02:48:05.459 --> 02:48:07.739
Tsunami spoke first.

02:48:07.799 --> 02:48:09.479
I don't think that'll work.

02:48:09.540 --> 02:48:12.600
If there's someone or something behind

02:48:12.600 --> 02:48:14.819
this, then wrecking their secret passage

02:48:14.819 --> 02:48:15.659
won't stop them.

02:48:15.719 --> 02:48:18.059
At least this way we have an advantage

02:48:18.059 --> 02:48:19.260
because we know about it.

02:48:19.319 --> 02:48:22.920
And what if the missing rain wings are

02:48:22.920 --> 02:48:24.059
alive on the other side?

02:48:24.180 --> 02:48:25.620
Clay said.

02:48:25.680 --> 02:48:27.840
What if there's a chance to save them?

02:48:27.899 --> 02:48:31.319
Oh, Sonny said.

02:48:31.379 --> 02:48:32.280
That's true.

02:48:32.340 --> 02:48:35.940
I'm not going into Burns Palace

02:48:35.940 --> 02:48:38.459
Starflight said immediately.

02:48:38.520 --> 02:48:39.239
No way.

02:48:39.299 --> 02:48:42.360
A monkey in the trees overhead dropped a

02:48:42.360 --> 02:48:44.399
nut, and Starflight jumped nervously

02:48:44.399 --> 02:48:46.200
aside as it tumbled down beside him.

02:48:46.260 --> 02:48:49.319
I will if I have to, Glory said.

02:48:49.379 --> 02:48:51.360
She should have been the one to think

02:48:51.360 --> 02:48:53.100
about saving the missing rain wings.

02:48:53.159 --> 02:48:54.719
If they were still alive.

02:48:54.780 --> 02:48:56.819
Of course, she had to help bring them

02:48:56.819 --> 02:48:57.360
home.

02:48:57.420 --> 02:48:59.340
Even if she did think the whole tribe was

02:48:59.340 --> 02:49:00.000
empty headed.

02:49:00.059 --> 02:49:03.600
But we don't know for sure that Burne is

02:49:03.600 --> 02:49:04.079
involved.

02:49:04.139 --> 02:49:05.700
Starflight pointed out.

02:49:05.760 --> 02:49:08.219
It could certainly be the ice wings

02:49:08.219 --> 02:49:08.819
instead.

02:49:08.879 --> 02:49:10.680
We need to spend a lot more time

02:49:10.680 --> 02:49:11.760
gathering information.

02:49:11.819 --> 02:49:14.819
Maybe spying on the stronghold and on the

02:49:14.819 --> 02:49:16.979
ice kingdom, charting their movements

02:49:16.979 --> 02:49:18.000
studying the tunnel.

02:49:18.059 --> 02:49:21.059
Suddenly something much larger than a nut

02:49:21.059 --> 02:49:23.159
thudded out of the tree behind Starflight

02:49:23.159 --> 02:49:25.500
the Nightwing yelped and leaped out of

02:49:25.500 --> 02:49:27.479
the way, as a bright green dragon

02:49:27.479 --> 02:49:29.459
galloped past him and dashed into the

02:49:29.459 --> 02:49:30.360
hole in the boulder.

02:49:30.420 --> 02:49:32.819
Hey, Glory shouted.

02:49:32.879 --> 02:49:34.680
That was mangrove.

02:49:34.799 --> 02:49:36.000
Jambu cried.

02:49:36.059 --> 02:49:36.959
What is he doing?

02:49:37.020 --> 02:49:39.719
He's going to look for orchid.

02:49:39.780 --> 02:49:41.940
Glory tucked silver into the nearest

02:49:41.940 --> 02:49:42.420
tree.

02:49:42.479 --> 02:49:45.659
Wait here, she ordered the sloth.

02:49:45.780 --> 02:49:47.940
She folded her wings and ran into the

02:49:47.940 --> 02:49:48.959
tunnel after mangrove.

02:49:49.079 --> 02:49:50.819
Mangrove.

02:49:50.879 --> 02:49:53.219
She called, as his tail whisked around

02:49:53.219 --> 02:49:53.639
the corner.

02:49:53.700 --> 02:49:55.260
Come back.

02:49:55.319 --> 02:49:56.159
We're making a plan.

02:49:56.280 --> 02:49:58.139
Don't be freaking dragon.

02:49:58.260 --> 02:49:59.879
She added under her breath.

02:49:59.940 --> 02:50:02.639
Even the one rain wing she liked was a

02:50:02.639 --> 02:50:03.239
nimrod.

02:50:03.299 --> 02:50:05.819
She shot around the last corner just in

02:50:05.819 --> 02:50:07.559
time to see him disappear out into the

02:50:07.559 --> 02:50:08.819
bright desert sunshine.

02:50:08.879 --> 02:50:11.459
By the time she burst out behind him and

02:50:11.459 --> 02:50:13.739
her eyes adjusted to the light, he was a

02:50:13.739 --> 02:50:16.139
green claw mark in the sky, flying away

02:50:16.139 --> 02:50:17.100
as fast as he could.

02:50:17.159 --> 02:50:20.579
A moment later, his scales shifted color

02:50:20.579 --> 02:50:22.260
and he vanished against the blue.

02:50:22.319 --> 02:50:25.020
Glory flapped her wings in frustration

02:50:25.020 --> 02:50:26.520
and sat down with a sigh.

02:50:26.579 --> 02:50:30.000
One by one, her friends emerged from the

02:50:30.000 --> 02:50:30.299
tunnel.

02:50:30.360 --> 02:50:36.000
Oh, 3 moons, tsunami said as the heat hit

02:50:36.000 --> 02:50:36.540
her scales.

02:50:36.600 --> 02:50:38.219
It's horrible here.

02:50:38.340 --> 02:50:41.819
Sunny stretched her wings wide and tilted

02:50:41.819 --> 02:50:42.659
her face up to the sun.

02:50:42.719 --> 02:50:44.280
Wow.

02:50:44.340 --> 02:50:45.780
She whispered.

02:50:45.840 --> 02:50:48.180
Starflight blinked and gazed around.

02:50:48.239 --> 02:50:51.600
You're right, he said to Glory.

02:50:51.659 --> 02:50:53.399
I can't believe it.

02:50:53.459 --> 02:50:56.340
This is really the kingdom of sand.

02:50:56.459 --> 02:50:58.920
Jambu tumbled out behind them.

02:50:58.979 --> 02:51:00.959
Where's Mangrove?

02:51:01.079 --> 02:51:01.739
He asked.

02:51:01.799 --> 02:51:04.739
Did he head for burned stronghold?

02:51:04.799 --> 02:51:07.139
Starflight guest, shading his eyes to

02:51:07.139 --> 02:51:08.520
look in the direction of the faraway

02:51:08.520 --> 02:51:08.940
palace.

02:51:09.000 --> 02:51:11.219
Glory shook her head and pointed north.

02:51:11.280 --> 02:51:13.379
Nope, she said.

02:51:13.440 --> 02:51:15.360
I don't think he even noticed it.

02:51:15.420 --> 02:51:17.879
Looks like we're off to the ice kingdom.

02:51:17.940 --> 02:51:22.260
Chapter 12.

02:51:22.620 --> 02:51:26.280
This isn't safe at all.

02:51:26.340 --> 02:51:27.959
Starfly called.

02:51:28.020 --> 02:51:29.760
This is the opposite of safe.

02:51:29.819 --> 02:51:32.040
We might as well just hand ourselves over

02:51:32.040 --> 02:51:33.059
to Queen Glacier.

02:51:33.120 --> 02:51:37.260
I'm right next to you, Glory said, and

02:51:37.260 --> 02:51:39.180
grinned when Starflight lost to Beat and

02:51:39.180 --> 02:51:40.379
had to flap harder to keep up.

02:51:40.440 --> 02:51:42.959
Not only was it funny, but it was also

02:51:42.959 --> 02:51:44.639
nice to know that her camouflage was

02:51:44.639 --> 02:51:45.120
working so well.

02:51:45.180 --> 02:51:47.700
Her brother certainly seemed to have no

02:51:47.700 --> 02:51:48.000
problem.

02:51:48.059 --> 02:51:50.760
She glanced around the endless empty blue

02:51:50.760 --> 02:51:52.379
that surrounded them as they flew north.

02:51:52.440 --> 02:51:54.299
Jambu?

02:51:54.299 --> 02:51:54.659
she said.

02:51:54.719 --> 02:51:58.319
Still here, answered a patch of sky from

02:51:58.319 --> 02:51:58.920
off to her left.

02:51:58.979 --> 02:52:02.159
You really don't have to come with us. she

02:52:02.159 --> 02:52:02.459
said again.

02:52:02.579 --> 02:52:05.579
The semicircle of cacti was now half a

02:52:05.579 --> 02:52:07.620
day's flight behind them, but John Boo

02:52:07.620 --> 02:52:08.940
could still make it back before dark.

02:52:08.940 --> 02:52:12.420
Nah, he said, this is better than

02:52:12.420 --> 02:52:13.020
suntime.

02:52:13.079 --> 02:52:15.540
I feel like I've been rolled in sunlight

02:52:15.540 --> 02:52:17.040
and stuffed with bananas.

02:52:17.100 --> 02:52:19.440
I bet the rest of the tribe would love to

02:52:19.440 --> 02:52:21.180
come through that tunnel and have their

02:52:21.180 --> 02:52:22.200
sun time here on the sand.

02:52:22.260 --> 02:52:27.180
Glory pictured a 100 rain wings suddenly

02:52:27.180 --> 02:52:30.120
sprawled in the desert, snoring away, only

02:52:30.120 --> 02:52:32.700
a few miles from Burns stronghold.

02:52:32.760 --> 02:52:33.420
She shuddered.

02:52:33.479 --> 02:52:37.200
That would be a really, really terrible

02:52:37.200 --> 02:52:38.760
plan, she said.

02:52:38.819 --> 02:52:41.219
It's not safe here for basically any

02:52:41.219 --> 02:52:41.760
dragon.

02:52:41.879 --> 02:52:44.639
That's what I'm trying to say.

02:52:44.700 --> 02:52:46.979
Starflight yelped from her other side.

02:52:47.040 --> 02:52:49.379
Even rain wings?

02:52:49.379 --> 02:52:50.940
said Jambu cheerfully.

02:52:51.000 --> 02:52:52.680
Nobody cares what we do.

02:52:52.739 --> 02:52:56.520
The world is still at war, Glory said.

02:52:56.639 --> 02:52:59.340
And some of the queens are really not to

02:52:59.340 --> 02:52:59.819
be trusted.

02:52:59.879 --> 02:53:02.399
I don't know what they do with you, but

02:53:02.399 --> 02:53:03.420
it wouldn't be friendly.

02:53:03.479 --> 02:53:04.799
Why not?

02:53:04.860 --> 02:53:06.180
asked Jamboo.

02:53:06.239 --> 02:53:09.120
Because you're so dopey, you're just

02:53:09.120 --> 02:53:10.020
asking for it.

02:53:10.139 --> 02:53:13.079
Because most dragons are naturally

02:53:13.079 --> 02:53:16.139
unfriendly, she said, biting and fighting

02:53:16.139 --> 02:53:17.040
is what we're built for.

02:53:17.100 --> 02:53:19.020
Really?

02:53:19.020 --> 02:53:20.399
said Jambu.

02:53:20.459 --> 02:53:21.719
We're not.

02:53:21.840 --> 02:53:23.879
There was a ripple in the air as he

02:53:23.879 --> 02:53:24.540
flicked his tail.

02:53:24.659 --> 02:53:27.479
Well, you should be, said Glory.

02:53:27.540 --> 02:53:29.879
One day, some other tribe might come to

02:53:29.879 --> 02:53:31.739
you, and you'll have to be able to defend

02:53:31.739 --> 02:53:32.280
yourselves.

02:53:32.340 --> 02:53:34.979
Promise me you'll be careful when we get

02:53:34.979 --> 02:53:35.760
to the ice wings.

02:53:35.819 --> 02:53:37.440
Don't let them know what you are.

02:53:37.500 --> 02:53:40.500
All right, all right, he said.

02:53:40.620 --> 02:53:42.360
Well, I think it's pretty cute.

02:53:42.479 --> 02:53:44.219
My little sister getting all worried

02:53:44.219 --> 02:53:45.540
about me over nothing.

02:53:45.719 --> 02:53:47.280
Glory rolled her eyes.

02:53:47.340 --> 02:53:48.780
Why did she care?

02:53:48.899 --> 02:53:51.899
If her tribe wanted to do idiotic things

02:53:51.899 --> 02:53:53.399
did it really affect her?

02:53:53.459 --> 02:53:56.520
Well, it did if she planned to stay in

02:53:56.520 --> 02:53:57.360
the rainforest.

02:53:57.420 --> 02:53:59.040
But was that her plan?

02:53:59.100 --> 02:54:01.799
The rain wings were far from the family

02:54:01.799 --> 02:54:02.819
she'd hoped for.

02:54:02.879 --> 02:54:04.979
But if she didn't stay with the rain

02:54:04.979 --> 02:54:06.360
wings, where would she go?

02:54:06.420 --> 02:54:09.780
With the other dragonettes, to fulfill a

02:54:09.780 --> 02:54:11.579
prophecy she wasn't supposed to be in?

02:54:11.639 --> 02:54:14.340
What about after the prophecy was

02:54:14.340 --> 02:54:14.819
fulfilled?

02:54:14.879 --> 02:54:17.579
Clay had brothers and sisters in the mud

02:54:17.579 --> 02:54:18.059
wings.

02:54:18.120 --> 02:54:20.819
Tsunami had loved the kingdom of the sea

02:54:20.819 --> 02:54:22.440
apart from her crazy mother.

02:54:22.500 --> 02:54:25.079
Maybe she'd still go back and challenge

02:54:25.079 --> 02:54:26.159
her for the throne one day.

02:54:26.219 --> 02:54:28.799
The night wings, of course, would welcome

02:54:28.799 --> 02:54:30.959
Starflight with open wings anytime.

02:54:31.020 --> 02:54:33.299
Glory glanced over at Sonny.

02:54:33.420 --> 02:54:36.059
The little sandwing flew in a tired

02:54:36.059 --> 02:54:38.639
flappy way, but her jaw was set and

02:54:38.639 --> 02:54:39.420
determined.

02:54:39.479 --> 02:54:41.280
Would she ever fit in somewhere?

02:54:41.340 --> 02:54:44.340
She was such an odd looking sandwing

02:54:44.340 --> 02:54:46.680
without the poison tipped tail all the

02:54:46.680 --> 02:54:47.639
rest of her tribe had.

02:54:47.700 --> 02:54:49.260
Would anyone want her?

02:54:49.319 --> 02:54:51.659
If the dragonettes did fulfill the

02:54:51.659 --> 02:54:52.979
prophecy and end the war?

02:54:53.100 --> 02:54:56.159
Well, presumably, whichever queen they

02:54:56.159 --> 02:54:57.959
chose for the sand wings would be pretty

02:54:57.959 --> 02:54:58.620
grateful.

02:54:58.680 --> 02:55:00.719
Surely she'd take Sonny in.

02:55:00.840 --> 02:55:03.780
Besides, everyone liked Sonny.

02:55:03.899 --> 02:55:06.420
Glory shook her head and stretched her

02:55:06.420 --> 02:55:06.840
talons.

02:55:06.899 --> 02:55:09.299
She was getting way ahead of herself.

02:55:09.360 --> 02:55:12.479
First, we find mangrove and get him

02:55:12.479 --> 02:55:12.659
home.

02:55:12.719 --> 02:55:15.719
Then I find the missing rain wings and

02:55:15.719 --> 02:55:18.959
whoever, or whatever is taking, or

02:55:18.959 --> 02:55:19.500
killing them.

02:55:19.559 --> 02:55:22.379
Then the great dragonettes of destiny

02:55:22.379 --> 02:55:24.719
figure out how to stop the war, and maybe

02:55:24.719 --> 02:55:25.799
I tag along for that.

02:55:25.860 --> 02:55:27.780
And then we'll see what happens.

02:55:27.899 --> 02:55:31.200
I wouldn't mind stopping for a nab

02:55:31.200 --> 02:55:31.440
though.

02:55:31.500 --> 02:55:33.959
Jamba's voice said, out of the blue.

02:55:34.079 --> 02:55:36.239
We won't have time for that.

02:55:36.299 --> 02:55:37.379
Glory said.

02:55:37.440 --> 02:55:40.440
Then again, Mangrove was a rain wing.

02:55:40.500 --> 02:55:43.200
So maybe he would stop mid idiotically

02:55:43.200 --> 02:55:45.540
foolish rescue for a nap, but they

02:55:45.540 --> 02:55:46.139
couldn't count on it.

02:55:46.200 --> 02:55:49.680
Also, Jambu, it's not going to be like

02:55:49.680 --> 02:55:50.399
this the whole way.

02:55:50.520 --> 02:55:53.040
It's going to get really cold by tonight

02:55:53.040 --> 02:55:56.219
and tomorrow we'll be in the Ice Kingdom

02:55:56.219 --> 02:55:57.959
where it will be seriously freezing.

02:55:58.079 --> 02:56:02.040
I'm sure it'll be fine, John Boo said

02:56:02.040 --> 02:56:02.520
breezily.

02:56:02.579 --> 02:56:05.159
It was already colder than it had been

02:56:05.159 --> 02:56:06.959
back at the tunnel entrance, and the

02:56:06.959 --> 02:56:09.120
desert sand below had changed to rocky

02:56:09.120 --> 02:56:11.760
treeless hills, gradually sloping up as

02:56:11.760 --> 02:56:12.719
they flew farther north.

02:56:12.780 --> 02:56:15.840
Glory saw Sunny casting a wistful glance

02:56:15.840 --> 02:56:16.979
back at the desert behind them.

02:56:17.040 --> 02:56:18.959
Starflight was right.

02:56:19.020 --> 02:56:20.879
This wasn't particularly safe.

02:56:20.940 --> 02:56:24.479
Glory and Jambu were camouflaged, but

02:56:24.479 --> 02:56:25.979
there wasn't much of a way to explain a

02:56:25.979 --> 02:56:29.100
mud wing, a sea wing, a night wing, and a

02:56:29.100 --> 02:56:31.799
sand wing all flying together, especially

02:56:31.799 --> 02:56:33.540
right into ice wing territory.

02:56:33.600 --> 02:56:36.059
They'd agreed to stop telling everyone

02:56:36.059 --> 02:56:38.459
they were the dragonettes of the prophecy

02:56:38.459 --> 02:56:40.680
but arriving like this, they might as

02:56:40.680 --> 02:56:42.840
well be carrying, here we are, please

02:56:42.840 --> 02:56:44.700
imprison us, banners.

02:56:44.819 --> 02:56:47.100
Glory wished again that her friends had

02:56:47.100 --> 02:56:48.360
just let her come on her own.

02:56:48.420 --> 02:56:51.120
She was sure she could retrieve mangrove

02:56:51.120 --> 02:56:51.600
by herself.

02:56:51.659 --> 02:56:54.659
They were lucky to avoid any ice wing

02:56:54.659 --> 02:56:55.139
patrols.

02:56:55.200 --> 02:56:57.959
Sunny heard one coming, which gave them

02:56:57.959 --> 02:57:00.059
time to hide down in the rocky landscape

02:57:00.059 --> 02:57:02.700
and they landed sometime after dark on

02:57:02.700 --> 02:57:05.040
ground that crunched ominously under

02:57:05.040 --> 02:57:06.059
glory's claws.

02:57:06.120 --> 02:57:08.340
Is this snow?

02:57:08.340 --> 02:57:10.559
Clay asked, poking the dirt.

02:57:10.620 --> 02:57:12.540
No.

02:57:12.600 --> 02:57:15.299
Starflight said, in his know it all voice

02:57:15.299 --> 02:57:17.280
it's just frozen dirt.

02:57:17.340 --> 02:57:19.500
We're going to be really cold tonight.

02:57:19.559 --> 02:57:22.379
They'd chosen a spot at the base of a

02:57:22.379 --> 02:57:24.659
short cliff, which would help block the

02:57:24.659 --> 02:57:26.940
wind, but glory could already feel the

02:57:26.940 --> 02:57:28.799
cold seeping up from the ground through

02:57:28.799 --> 02:57:30.239
her claws and underscales.

02:57:30.360 --> 02:57:33.840
And we shouldn't use fire, tsunami said

02:57:33.840 --> 02:57:34.500
bossily.

02:57:34.559 --> 02:57:36.120
We can't risk being seen.

02:57:36.180 --> 02:57:40.079
Dibs, I get to sleep next to Sunny. said

02:57:40.079 --> 02:57:40.620
Clay.

02:57:40.680 --> 02:57:42.959
He grinned at her, and she beamed back.

02:57:43.020 --> 02:57:45.540
Her warm scales would be the only source

02:57:45.540 --> 02:57:46.319
of heat they had.

02:57:46.379 --> 02:57:48.780
Even glory would have to put up with

02:57:48.780 --> 02:57:50.579
close contact if she wanted to get

02:57:50.579 --> 02:57:51.719
through the night without freezing.

02:57:51.780 --> 02:57:54.420
Glory knew Clay was joking.

02:57:54.479 --> 02:57:57.000
He was more likely to use his own body as

02:57:57.000 --> 02:57:58.620
a shield to keep the wind away from the

02:57:58.620 --> 02:57:59.219
rest of them.

02:57:59.280 --> 02:58:01.860
But she glanced over at Starflight and

02:58:01.860 --> 02:58:03.540
caught the crustfallen look on his face.

02:58:03.600 --> 02:58:05.819
Oh, Starfight.

02:58:05.879 --> 02:58:07.860
Maybe you should actually do something

02:58:07.860 --> 02:58:09.059
about that crush of yours.

02:58:09.120 --> 02:58:12.899
He'd never admitted it out loud, but Lori

02:58:12.899 --> 02:58:14.639
was pretty sure he'd been hopelessly in

02:58:14.639 --> 02:58:15.840
love with Sonny his whole life.

02:58:15.899 --> 02:58:18.659
She was also pretty sure Sonny had no

02:58:18.659 --> 02:58:20.940
idea, and that she might never find out

02:58:20.940 --> 02:58:21.780
at this rate.

02:58:22.200 --> 02:58:23.760
Not my problem.

02:58:23.819 --> 02:58:25.920
Glory reminded herself.

02:58:26.040 --> 02:58:28.680
But as they huddled up to sleep, she

02:58:28.680 --> 02:58:30.780
edged around so Starflight ended up

02:58:30.780 --> 02:58:33.299
curled next to Sonny's wings, with Clay

02:58:33.299 --> 02:58:34.079
behind both of them.

02:58:34.139 --> 02:58:36.659
She coiled herself as tightly as she

02:58:36.659 --> 02:58:38.879
could, and found a spot along Clay's

02:58:38.879 --> 02:58:39.120
tail.

02:58:39.180 --> 02:58:42.059
Jambu immediately lay down practically on

02:58:42.059 --> 02:58:42.600
top of her.

02:58:42.659 --> 02:58:44.040
Oof.

02:58:44.100 --> 02:58:46.620
Glory whispered, a little more personal

02:58:46.620 --> 02:58:47.520
space, please.

02:58:47.579 --> 02:58:51.360
I don't know what that is, Jambu

02:58:51.360 --> 02:58:53.940
whispered back, but I'm really freaking

02:58:53.940 --> 02:58:55.260
cold, aren't you?

02:58:55.319 --> 02:58:57.299
Glory sighed.

02:58:57.360 --> 02:59:00.180
She was, and John Boo was warm.

02:59:00.239 --> 02:59:01.920
And he was her brother.

02:59:01.979 --> 02:59:05.399
She curled up for a 2nd night in a row of

02:59:05.399 --> 02:59:06.239
uncomfortable sleep.

02:59:06.299 --> 02:59:10.620
Glory woke up shortly before dawn.

02:59:10.680 --> 02:59:13.739
The sun was a thin, pale line of light on

02:59:13.739 --> 02:59:16.200
the horizon, and the dark purple sky

02:59:16.200 --> 02:59:17.459
still glittered with stars.

02:59:17.520 --> 02:59:19.860
She could see her breath in the air

02:59:19.860 --> 02:59:22.500
trails of smoke, as if she could breathe

02:59:22.500 --> 02:59:23.579
fire like the others.

02:59:23.639 --> 02:59:26.579
She wriggled out from under Jambu, who

02:59:26.579 --> 02:59:28.559
slept with his mouth open and his wings

02:59:28.559 --> 02:59:29.399
flopped wide.

02:59:29.459 --> 02:59:31.620
At least he wasn't pink today.

02:59:31.680 --> 02:59:34.079
She found it a little easier to take him

02:59:34.079 --> 02:59:35.940
seriously when he was the gray and brown

02:59:35.940 --> 02:59:37.379
colors of the rocks below them.

02:59:37.440 --> 02:59:40.799
She glanced down at her scales to make

02:59:40.799 --> 02:59:42.420
sure they match the landscape as well.

02:59:42.540 --> 02:59:44.819
She liked how there was even a subtle

02:59:44.819 --> 02:59:47.100
sparkle to them, just like the frost that

02:59:47.100 --> 02:59:47.700
covered the ground.

02:59:47.760 --> 02:59:51.540
Tsunami shifted in her sleep, growling

02:59:51.540 --> 02:59:51.959
softly.

02:59:52.020 --> 02:59:54.719
Glory realized that Starflight was

02:59:54.719 --> 02:59:55.139
already awake.

02:59:55.200 --> 02:59:58.139
He blinked at her over Sunny's back

02:59:58.139 --> 02:59:58.860
looking exhausted.

02:59:58.920 --> 03:00:01.620
She flicked her tail and signaled that he

03:00:01.620 --> 03:00:02.340
should go back to sleep.

03:00:02.399 --> 03:00:04.979
Then she spread her wings and hopped up

03:00:04.979 --> 03:00:06.600
to the top of the small cliff to see what

03:00:06.600 --> 03:00:07.799
the land ahead looked like.

03:00:07.860 --> 03:00:10.860
A lot like the land they'd left behind

03:00:10.860 --> 03:00:13.139
and the land they were on, apparently.

03:00:13.200 --> 03:00:16.979
Except, was that snow in the distance?

03:00:16.979 --> 03:00:19.620
Glory gave her scales a moment to shift

03:00:19.620 --> 03:00:21.420
and then she lifted into the sky.

03:00:21.540 --> 03:00:24.059
They hadn't been able to see it in the

03:00:24.059 --> 03:00:25.860
dark the night before, but there was

03:00:25.860 --> 03:00:27.659
definitely snow on the taller hills ahead

03:00:27.659 --> 03:00:29.940
of them, and more snow beyond that.

03:00:30.000 --> 03:00:31.620
Lori shivered.

03:00:31.680 --> 03:00:34.680
It would get colder from here, and it was

03:00:34.680 --> 03:00:35.940
already close to unbearable.

03:00:36.000 --> 03:00:38.700
This had to be tough on Sonny and Clay as

03:00:38.700 --> 03:00:38.879
well.

03:00:38.940 --> 03:00:41.280
Maybe the others could stay here while

03:00:41.280 --> 03:00:42.120
she went on ahead.

03:00:42.180 --> 03:00:45.600
In fact, maybe she should go ahead right

03:00:45.600 --> 03:00:48.360
now, without them, so no one else would

03:00:48.360 --> 03:00:48.840
be at risk.

03:00:48.899 --> 03:00:51.899
Except she knew perfectly well that her

03:00:51.899 --> 03:00:54.059
idiot friends would follow her and just

03:00:54.059 --> 03:00:55.799
get in worse trouble without her there to

03:00:55.799 --> 03:00:55.979
help.

03:00:56.040 --> 03:00:58.979
If she wanted to go on without them, she'd

03:00:58.979 --> 03:01:01.020
have to convince them to be smart, listen

03:01:01.020 --> 03:01:02.280
to her, and stay behind.

03:01:02.340 --> 03:01:05.459
There was something large up ahead in the

03:01:05.459 --> 03:01:07.680
snow covered hills, some kind of

03:01:07.680 --> 03:01:08.040
building.

03:01:08.100 --> 03:01:11.040
It couldn't be Glacier's palace, though.

03:01:11.159 --> 03:01:14.040
Glory knew that was far to the north, on

03:01:14.040 --> 03:01:16.260
the coldest tip of the peninsula, where

03:01:16.260 --> 03:01:18.780
no other dragons would ever want to go.

03:01:18.840 --> 03:01:20.879
This building was almost too far south

03:01:20.879 --> 03:01:21.780
for ice wings.

03:01:21.840 --> 03:01:24.899
Glory flew a bit closer and saw smoke

03:01:24.899 --> 03:01:26.700
rising from a few of its chimneys.

03:01:26.760 --> 03:01:31.139
Smoke means fire, she thought, which

03:01:31.139 --> 03:01:32.760
means not ice wings.

03:01:32.819 --> 03:01:35.639
She circled in the air and studied it a

03:01:35.639 --> 03:01:35.879
bit more.

03:01:35.940 --> 03:01:38.879
It had to be blaze and her sand wings.

03:01:38.940 --> 03:01:41.100
Glory had been wondering how they

03:01:41.100 --> 03:01:42.420
survived in the ice kingdom.

03:01:42.479 --> 03:01:45.420
Apparently the answer was, by not going

03:01:45.420 --> 03:01:46.260
very far into it.

03:01:46.379 --> 03:01:50.219
Suddenly, a movement below caught her

03:01:50.219 --> 03:01:50.459
eye.

03:01:50.520 --> 03:01:53.579
She froze, hovering in the air and hoping

03:01:53.579 --> 03:01:54.719
her camouflage was perfect.

03:01:54.780 --> 03:01:58.079
There was a dragon among the rocks, not

03:01:58.079 --> 03:01:59.760
far from where her friends were sleeping

03:01:59.760 --> 03:02:01.559
but not close enough to see them either.

03:02:01.620 --> 03:02:04.559
He was stamping his feet, and slapping

03:02:04.559 --> 03:02:06.239
his wings together, as if he was trying

03:02:06.239 --> 03:02:06.840
to warm up.

03:02:06.899 --> 03:02:08.520
Mangrove?

03:02:08.520 --> 03:02:11.579
Glory thought, hopefully, gliding a bit

03:02:11.579 --> 03:02:12.000
closer.

03:02:12.059 --> 03:02:15.600
He wasn't camouflaged exactly, but he was

03:02:15.600 --> 03:02:16.979
black, like a night wing.

03:02:17.040 --> 03:02:19.020
Maybe he thought that would hide him well

03:02:19.020 --> 03:02:19.260
enough.

03:02:19.319 --> 03:02:22.379
And then the dragon below let out a small

03:02:22.379 --> 03:02:23.399
plume of fire.

03:02:23.459 --> 03:02:25.379
Heating the ground below him before

03:02:25.379 --> 03:02:26.280
curling up on it.

03:02:26.340 --> 03:02:28.799
So it wasn't a rain wing.

03:02:28.860 --> 03:02:32.100
It was an actual night wing, on his own

03:02:32.100 --> 03:02:33.479
in ice wing territory.

03:02:33.540 --> 03:02:37.379
Well, that can't be good news.

03:02:37.440 --> 03:02:42.059
Chapter 13.

03:02:42.299 --> 03:02:46.260
Why was there a night wing here, of all

03:02:46.260 --> 03:02:46.920
places.

03:02:46.979 --> 03:02:50.100
Glory glided quietly away and landed

03:02:50.100 --> 03:02:51.299
softly out of his sight.

03:02:51.360 --> 03:02:54.780
Her curiosity was too strong to resist, so

03:02:54.780 --> 03:02:55.680
she needed a disguise.

03:02:55.739 --> 03:02:58.799
The only logical dragons that should be

03:02:58.799 --> 03:03:01.379
wandering around here were ice wings, and

03:03:01.379 --> 03:03:03.180
maybe some of their sand wing allies.

03:03:03.239 --> 03:03:05.639
She closed her eyes and remember the ice

03:03:05.639 --> 03:03:07.440
wing who had fought clay in the arena

03:03:07.440 --> 03:03:08.520
Fjord.

03:03:08.579 --> 03:03:10.920
The 1st dragon she'd killed with her

03:03:10.920 --> 03:03:11.399
venom.

03:03:11.459 --> 03:03:12.959
She'd had no choice.

03:03:13.020 --> 03:03:15.180
He'd been moments away from killing

03:03:15.180 --> 03:03:15.719
clay.

03:03:15.840 --> 03:03:18.719
Plus, she'd had no idea what her venom

03:03:18.719 --> 03:03:19.079
would do.

03:03:19.139 --> 03:03:21.959
She'd just known instinctively that she

03:03:21.959 --> 03:03:24.000
could do something, that she had to do

03:03:24.000 --> 03:03:24.299
something.

03:03:24.420 --> 03:03:27.120
That she had a weapon she'd never known

03:03:27.120 --> 03:03:27.360
about.

03:03:27.420 --> 03:03:30.420
Starflight thought that perhaps she

03:03:30.420 --> 03:03:31.979
couldn't have used her venom under the

03:03:31.979 --> 03:03:32.879
mountain anyway.

03:03:32.940 --> 03:03:35.280
He said it might have been activated by

03:03:35.280 --> 03:03:37.319
finally exposing her scales to full

03:03:37.319 --> 03:03:39.719
sunlight, the way Clay's fireproof

03:03:39.719 --> 03:03:41.819
abilities had come to full strength once

03:03:41.819 --> 03:03:43.440
he'd encountered mud for the 1st time.

03:03:43.500 --> 03:03:46.319
Glory could now but wonder how different

03:03:46.319 --> 03:03:48.299
life might have been if she could have

03:03:48.299 --> 03:03:49.799
threatened the guardians the way they

03:03:49.799 --> 03:03:50.399
threatened her.

03:03:50.459 --> 03:03:53.399
Focus, Fjord.

03:03:53.459 --> 03:03:57.000
His pale blue scales, the color of sky

03:03:57.000 --> 03:03:59.940
filled snow, his darker blue eyes.

03:04:00.120 --> 03:04:02.340
She felt the changes shimmer across her

03:04:02.340 --> 03:04:02.700
scales.

03:04:02.760 --> 03:04:05.819
The hardest part was the extra horns Ice

03:04:05.819 --> 03:04:07.739
Wings had around their heads.

03:04:07.799 --> 03:04:09.540
She concentrated on making her rough look

03:04:09.540 --> 03:04:11.700
like it was made of icicles, and hoped

03:04:11.700 --> 03:04:12.120
that would do.

03:04:12.180 --> 03:04:15.059
She also could make her claws ridged like

03:04:15.059 --> 03:04:17.639
ice wing claws, and her tail wasn't as

03:04:17.639 --> 03:04:19.500
whipped thin at the end as an ice wings

03:04:19.500 --> 03:04:19.799
would be.

03:04:19.860 --> 03:04:22.260
Maybe this is a bad idea.

03:04:22.379 --> 03:04:24.959
Maybe there's no way I'll get away with

03:04:24.959 --> 03:04:25.139
it.

03:04:25.260 --> 03:04:29.040
But it was still pretty dark out, and she

03:04:29.040 --> 03:04:31.319
really, really wanted to know what a

03:04:31.319 --> 03:04:32.520
night wing was doing out here.

03:04:32.579 --> 03:04:36.959
Well, she thought ruefully, if he figures

03:04:36.959 --> 03:04:38.879
me out, I guess I'll just kill him.

03:04:38.940 --> 03:04:42.059
Somehow, it didn't sound as funny as

03:04:42.059 --> 03:04:42.719
she'd hoped.

03:04:42.780 --> 03:04:45.180
She leaped into the air and flew back to

03:04:45.180 --> 03:04:46.620
the spot where she'd seen this strange

03:04:46.620 --> 03:04:47.159
dragon.

03:04:47.219 --> 03:04:49.500
For a moment, she was afraid she'd lost

03:04:49.500 --> 03:04:52.079
him, before she realized that he was

03:04:52.079 --> 03:04:52.559
lying down.

03:04:52.620 --> 03:04:55.020
His black scales half hidden in the long

03:04:55.020 --> 03:04:55.559
shadows.

03:04:55.620 --> 03:04:58.620
Confidence, she told herself.

03:04:58.680 --> 03:05:00.959
It's all about attitude.

03:05:01.020 --> 03:05:04.860
Hey, she barked, landing with a thump

03:05:04.860 --> 03:05:05.520
beside him.

03:05:05.579 --> 03:05:06.659
Who are you?

03:05:06.719 --> 03:05:08.459
And what are you doing in our territory?

03:05:08.579 --> 03:05:11.399
The Night Wing leaped up in surprise and

03:05:11.399 --> 03:05:12.120
stared at her.

03:05:12.180 --> 03:05:14.760
He was a lot younger and smaller than

03:05:14.760 --> 03:05:17.459
Morrow Seer, wiry and graceful in his

03:05:17.459 --> 03:05:19.379
movements, even when he was startled.

03:05:19.440 --> 03:05:22.020
The silver scales sparkling under his

03:05:22.020 --> 03:05:23.940
wings caught the morning light, like

03:05:23.940 --> 03:05:24.959
trapped stars.

03:05:25.020 --> 03:05:27.120
Great moons.

03:05:27.239 --> 03:05:28.500
Where did you come from?

03:05:28.559 --> 03:05:29.520
he asked.

03:05:29.579 --> 03:05:31.680
He looked up at the sky with a puzzled

03:05:31.680 --> 03:05:32.280
expression.

03:05:32.340 --> 03:05:33.840
Where do you think?

03:05:33.840 --> 03:05:34.620
she said.

03:05:34.680 --> 03:05:36.719
And I am asking the questions here.

03:05:36.840 --> 03:05:38.940
What are you doing in the ice kingdom?

03:05:39.000 --> 03:05:42.420
Technically, this isn't the Ice Kingdom

03:05:42.420 --> 03:05:43.739
yet, he said.

03:05:43.799 --> 03:05:45.059
Oh, didn't you know that?

03:05:45.120 --> 03:05:46.799
It isn't?

03:05:46.860 --> 03:05:47.700
She thought.

03:05:47.760 --> 03:05:50.219
The map she'd memorized didn't exactly

03:05:50.219 --> 03:05:51.719
have borders drawn on it.

03:05:51.780 --> 03:05:53.340
Not that those would have helped her out

03:05:53.340 --> 03:05:53.760
here anyway.

03:05:53.819 --> 03:05:57.120
You're close enough, she growled.

03:05:57.180 --> 03:05:58.620
Explain yourself.

03:05:58.680 --> 03:06:01.319
She wished she had a spear or something

03:06:01.319 --> 03:06:02.940
she could poke at him.

03:06:03.000 --> 03:06:06.180
It will be Ice Kingdom territory one day

03:06:06.299 --> 03:06:07.620
said the Nightwing.

03:06:07.739 --> 03:06:10.079
If Blaze wins the war, that is.

03:06:10.079 --> 03:06:12.719
She's promised Queen Glacier all the land

03:06:12.719 --> 03:06:14.040
you can see from here to the southern

03:06:14.040 --> 03:06:14.579
horizon.

03:06:14.639 --> 03:06:16.920
Basically, where the desert starts.

03:06:16.979 --> 03:06:19.799
He pointed, but Glory stopped herself

03:06:19.799 --> 03:06:21.479
from looking and kept her eyes on him.

03:06:21.540 --> 03:06:23.040
The night wing smiled.

03:06:23.100 --> 03:06:25.079
I suppose you know all that.

03:06:25.139 --> 03:06:26.159
He said.

03:06:26.219 --> 03:06:28.379
But it's interesting, isn't it?

03:06:28.440 --> 03:06:31.200
That's a lot of land Blaze is willing to

03:06:31.200 --> 03:06:33.659
hand over, but not exactly useful land to

03:06:33.659 --> 03:06:34.260
either tribe.

03:06:34.319 --> 03:06:37.020
So what would Queen Glacier want with

03:06:37.020 --> 03:06:37.200
it?

03:06:37.260 --> 03:06:39.239
Do you think there's treasure under these

03:06:39.239 --> 03:06:39.540
rocks?

03:06:39.659 --> 03:06:40.979
That would be my guess.

03:06:41.040 --> 03:06:42.840
A diamond mine perhaps?

03:06:42.899 --> 03:06:44.639
Maybe you know.

03:06:44.700 --> 03:06:47.819
Maybe all the ice wings know, and are

03:06:47.819 --> 03:06:50.280
wisely keeping it a secret from Blaze and

03:06:50.280 --> 03:06:51.120
her sand wings.

03:06:51.180 --> 03:06:54.540
He gave her a wry, clever look, as if

03:06:54.540 --> 03:06:56.819
he'd just opened up her mind and spread

03:06:56.819 --> 03:06:58.260
it out on the rocks for them to admire

03:06:58.260 --> 03:06:58.559
together.

03:06:58.620 --> 03:07:01.739
A horrible sinking feeling shot through

03:07:01.739 --> 03:07:02.159
glory.

03:07:02.219 --> 03:07:04.620
She'd forgotten that Nightwings could

03:07:04.620 --> 03:07:05.280
read minds.

03:07:05.340 --> 03:07:07.559
Some Nightwings.

03:07:07.620 --> 03:07:10.139
She reminded herself, certainly not

03:07:10.139 --> 03:07:13.379
Starflight, and she thought not Marosier

03:07:13.379 --> 03:07:15.479
judging from his lack of reaction to all

03:07:15.479 --> 03:07:16.799
the thoughts she'd had about him.

03:07:16.860 --> 03:07:19.379
Maybe this dragon was one who could see

03:07:19.379 --> 03:07:20.159
the future instead.

03:07:20.219 --> 03:07:23.639
Still, she forced every thought out of

03:07:23.639 --> 03:07:25.920
her mind except, what are you doing

03:07:25.920 --> 03:07:26.219
here?

03:07:26.280 --> 03:07:30.420
Answer my questions, Nightwing, she said

03:07:30.420 --> 03:07:32.700
or I'll take you to Queen Glacier, and

03:07:32.700 --> 03:07:33.840
you can explain yourself to her.

03:07:33.899 --> 03:07:37.139
That wouldn't be a good idea, he said.

03:07:37.200 --> 03:07:39.000
You really don't want the rest of my

03:07:39.000 --> 03:07:40.260
tribe to come looking for me.

03:07:40.319 --> 03:07:43.440
And you really don't want to sit in a

03:07:43.440 --> 03:07:45.239
dungeon made of ice until they show up

03:07:45.239 --> 03:07:47.940
which would most likely be sometime after

03:07:47.940 --> 03:07:49.200
you froze to death.

03:07:49.260 --> 03:07:50.700
She pointed out.

03:07:50.760 --> 03:07:53.280
So tell me what you're doing here, and

03:07:53.280 --> 03:07:54.780
perhaps I'll let you go.

03:07:54.840 --> 03:07:56.100
Win-win.

03:07:56.219 --> 03:07:58.979
He tilted his head. looking amused.

03:07:59.040 --> 03:08:01.979
All right, he said after a moment.

03:08:02.040 --> 03:08:03.600
I'm waiting for someone.

03:08:03.659 --> 03:08:06.299
Well, a view someone's.

03:08:06.360 --> 03:08:07.739
Who?

03:08:07.799 --> 03:08:08.459
She asked.

03:08:08.520 --> 03:08:11.219
I can't tell you that, he said.

03:08:11.280 --> 03:08:13.079
Nightwing business, I'm afraid.

03:08:13.139 --> 03:08:14.579
I'm on an assignment.

03:08:14.639 --> 03:08:18.180
I didn't know Nightwings had business

03:08:18.180 --> 03:08:19.200
Glory said.

03:08:19.260 --> 03:08:21.659
I thought you just sculked around in your

03:08:21.659 --> 03:08:22.559
secret location.

03:08:22.620 --> 03:08:24.479
Congratulating one another on knowing

03:08:24.479 --> 03:08:25.559
everything and doing nothing.

03:08:25.680 --> 03:08:28.319
The Nightwing started laughing.

03:08:28.379 --> 03:08:31.319
Nobody talks to us like that, he said.

03:08:31.379 --> 03:08:33.180
Where's your sense of awe?

03:08:33.239 --> 03:08:34.860
Your terror of our powers?

03:08:34.979 --> 03:08:38.100
He spread his wings majestically, but his

03:08:38.100 --> 03:08:38.819
eyes were teasing.

03:08:38.940 --> 03:08:42.180
If your powers were that impressive, you'd

03:08:42.180 --> 03:08:44.399
do something to stop this war, she said.

03:08:44.459 --> 03:08:48.420
Also, I'm the one with the, uh, the

03:08:48.420 --> 03:08:49.680
freezing death breath here.

03:08:49.739 --> 03:08:52.920
She nearly slipped and said venom, but

03:08:52.920 --> 03:08:54.000
either way, it was true.

03:08:54.059 --> 03:08:56.819
Nightwing powers weren't that spectacular

03:08:56.819 --> 03:08:58.319
when it came to an actual battle.

03:08:58.379 --> 03:09:00.600
Starflights were downright pathetic.

03:09:00.659 --> 03:09:03.959
Maybe we'll help stop the war someday, he

03:09:03.959 --> 03:09:04.260
said.

03:09:04.319 --> 03:09:06.420
Maybe we haven't picked a side yet.

03:09:06.540 --> 03:09:08.700
Like the dragonettes or the prophecy.

03:09:08.760 --> 03:09:11.520
Glory kept her face calm and bored.

03:09:11.579 --> 03:09:13.979
That old thing, she said.

03:09:14.040 --> 03:09:16.020
I don't believe in prophecies.

03:09:16.139 --> 03:09:18.420
Sorry, I know they're a Nightwing

03:09:18.420 --> 03:09:19.979
specialty, but seriously?

03:09:20.040 --> 03:09:21.719
If you can actually see the future.

03:09:21.780 --> 03:09:24.059
Why be all cryptic and vague about it?

03:09:24.120 --> 03:09:27.120
Why not give us a prophecy that's like, oh

03:09:27.120 --> 03:09:29.520
by the way, Blaze is going to win the war

03:09:29.520 --> 03:09:31.440
so give her the crown now and don't even

03:09:31.440 --> 03:09:32.459
bother fighting about it.

03:09:32.520 --> 03:09:35.579
Skip all the death and bloodshed, and

03:09:35.579 --> 03:09:37.200
leave a bunch of poor dragonettes out of

03:09:37.200 --> 03:09:37.379
it.

03:09:37.440 --> 03:09:39.540
The Nightwing laughed again.

03:09:39.600 --> 03:09:42.420
You feel sorry for the dragonettes, he

03:09:42.420 --> 03:09:42.600
said.

03:09:42.719 --> 03:09:43.799
That's interesting.

03:09:43.860 --> 03:09:46.500
I've seen a lot of that around pyrea

03:09:46.500 --> 03:09:46.680
actually.

03:09:46.739 --> 03:09:49.979
Everyone expects so much of them, but

03:09:49.979 --> 03:09:51.600
they also think it's a heavy burden for 5

03:09:51.600 --> 03:09:52.440
young dragons.

03:09:52.500 --> 03:09:54.719
I wonder if the dragonettes would be

03:09:54.719 --> 03:09:56.340
surprised by all this sympathy for them.

03:09:56.399 --> 03:09:59.040
He looked thoughtful for a moment, then

03:09:59.040 --> 03:09:59.579
yawned.

03:09:59.700 --> 03:10:02.219
You haven't seen any sign of them here

03:10:02.219 --> 03:10:02.879
have you?

03:10:03.000 --> 03:10:05.639
Rumor has it they were headed for the Ice

03:10:05.639 --> 03:10:06.180
Kingdom next.

03:10:06.239 --> 03:10:07.920
Really?

03:10:07.979 --> 03:10:09.719
Glory said impassively.

03:10:09.780 --> 03:10:10.680
Why?

03:10:10.739 --> 03:10:14.100
To me, Blaze, I suppose, he said.

03:10:14.159 --> 03:10:16.739
So, are they here?

03:10:16.799 --> 03:10:19.139
In Queen Glacier's dungeon already

03:10:19.139 --> 03:10:19.440
perhaps.

03:10:19.500 --> 03:10:21.959
Nope, Glory said.

03:10:22.020 --> 03:10:23.219
No sign of them.

03:10:23.280 --> 03:10:24.239
None at all.

03:10:24.299 --> 03:10:26.879
She thought of snowstorms and sheets of

03:10:26.879 --> 03:10:27.239
ice.

03:10:27.299 --> 03:10:28.979
Blocking the way to all her other

03:10:28.979 --> 03:10:29.340
thoughts.

03:10:29.399 --> 03:10:31.620
He studied her for a moment.

03:10:31.739 --> 03:10:33.600
Right, he said.

03:10:33.659 --> 03:10:36.239
Well, they couldn't have gotten here that

03:10:36.239 --> 03:10:36.719
fast anyway.

03:10:36.840 --> 03:10:38.819
It's a long way from the kingdom of the

03:10:38.819 --> 03:10:39.120
sea.

03:10:39.180 --> 03:10:41.159
How do you know they were there?

03:10:41.219 --> 03:10:42.239
Glory asked.

03:10:42.299 --> 03:10:44.639
Oh, wait, I forgot.

03:10:44.700 --> 03:10:47.280
Nightwings are all knowing, all seeing

03:10:47.280 --> 03:10:48.840
and all brilliant, right?

03:10:48.899 --> 03:10:51.959
Don't forget all wonderful and all

03:10:51.959 --> 03:10:53.399
handsome, he said.

03:10:53.459 --> 03:10:55.440
She snorted to cover her laugh.

03:10:55.500 --> 03:10:58.200
How would anyone know that, when you all

03:10:58.200 --> 03:11:00.420
stay hidden away like turtles, she said.

03:11:00.479 --> 03:11:03.659
Seriously, come hang out with dragons in

03:11:03.659 --> 03:11:04.680
the real world sometime.

03:11:04.739 --> 03:11:07.079
Is that an invitation?

03:11:07.200 --> 03:11:08.040
He asked.

03:11:08.100 --> 03:11:10.379
I probably have a day or 2 before the

03:11:10.379 --> 03:11:11.879
before my work can begin.

03:11:11.940 --> 03:11:14.040
I wouldn't mind seeing the inside of an

03:11:14.040 --> 03:11:15.479
ice wing tavern if you'll be there.

03:11:15.540 --> 03:11:18.659
Glory felt a shiver of danger slip along

03:11:18.659 --> 03:11:19.079
her spine.

03:11:19.200 --> 03:11:22.620
So let me get this straight, she said.

03:11:22.680 --> 03:11:24.659
You're telling me nothing about why

03:11:24.659 --> 03:11:25.139
you're here.

03:11:25.200 --> 03:11:27.479
But you expect me to bring you into our

03:11:27.479 --> 03:11:29.340
kingdom and buy you a drink?

03:11:29.399 --> 03:11:31.799
Nightwings really do think highly of

03:11:31.799 --> 03:11:32.639
themselves, don't they?

03:11:32.700 --> 03:11:35.579
What if I bought you that drink?

03:11:35.579 --> 03:11:36.540
he offered.

03:11:36.600 --> 03:11:39.899
Oh, then I'm sure Queen Glacier would

03:11:39.899 --> 03:11:40.440
understand.

03:11:40.500 --> 03:11:42.180
No problem, Glory said.

03:11:42.299 --> 03:11:44.579
She loves strange dragons in her

03:11:44.579 --> 03:11:45.180
territory.

03:11:45.239 --> 03:11:46.379
It's her very favorite thing.

03:11:46.440 --> 03:11:49.500
The Nightwing smiled a little wistfully.

03:11:49.559 --> 03:11:51.540
All right, he said.

03:11:51.600 --> 03:11:52.979
Never mind.

03:11:53.100 --> 03:11:55.319
But maybe you could come back and see me

03:11:55.319 --> 03:11:55.620
sometime.

03:11:55.680 --> 03:11:57.780
I'll be here for a few more days at least

03:11:57.780 --> 03:12:00.120
probably, and it's pretty boring just

03:12:00.120 --> 03:12:00.479
sitting here.

03:12:00.540 --> 03:12:04.139
Waiting for your mysterious someone's

03:12:04.139 --> 03:12:06.420
Glory said, which you're not going to

03:12:06.420 --> 03:12:07.739
tell me anything more about.

03:12:07.799 --> 03:12:09.420
He spread his wings.

03:12:09.479 --> 03:12:10.440
Sorry.

03:12:10.500 --> 03:12:11.639
I wish I could.

03:12:11.700 --> 03:12:13.500
I bet my job would impress you.

03:12:13.559 --> 03:12:18.000
I'm not easily impressed, Glory said, and

03:12:18.000 --> 03:12:19.500
was surprised when he laughed again.

03:12:19.559 --> 03:12:22.799
Well, good luck with your assignment, I

03:12:22.799 --> 03:12:23.219
suppose.

03:12:23.280 --> 03:12:24.959
What's your name?

03:12:25.020 --> 03:12:27.420
He asked, as she took a step back.

03:12:27.479 --> 03:12:29.760
Sorry, I can't tell you that.

03:12:29.819 --> 03:12:32.520
She said mockingly, Ice wing business.

03:12:32.579 --> 03:12:35.819
Who knew sarcasm could grow in a place

03:12:35.819 --> 03:12:36.420
this cold?

03:12:36.540 --> 03:12:38.219
He said with a smile.

03:12:38.280 --> 03:12:40.440
Will you tell me your name, if I tell you

03:12:40.440 --> 03:12:40.680
mine?

03:12:40.739 --> 03:12:42.959
Nope, she said.

03:12:43.020 --> 03:12:45.180
Frankly, I'm not that interested.

03:12:45.299 --> 03:12:47.399
She turned her back and spread her

03:12:47.399 --> 03:12:47.760
wings.

03:12:47.819 --> 03:12:51.000
I'll tell you anyway. he said, as she

03:12:51.000 --> 03:12:51.780
lifted into the sky.

03:12:51.840 --> 03:12:53.819
If you'll come see me again.

03:12:53.879 --> 03:12:54.899
Will you?

03:12:54.959 --> 03:12:57.600
Maybe, she called back.

03:12:57.659 --> 03:12:58.620
I'm pretty busy.

03:12:58.680 --> 03:13:01.559
My name, he called.

03:13:01.620 --> 03:13:03.899
She slowed down to listen, but didn't

03:13:03.899 --> 03:13:04.139
look back.

03:13:04.200 --> 03:13:07.500
My name is Death Bringer.

03:13:07.559 --> 03:13:11.760
Chapter 14.

03:13:12.000 --> 03:13:14.579
Death bringer.

03:13:14.639 --> 03:13:17.940
Waiting for someone, a few someone's.

03:13:18.000 --> 03:13:20.219
You haven't seen any sign of the

03:13:20.219 --> 03:13:21.479
dragonettes, have you?

03:13:21.540 --> 03:13:24.239
Gloria's head was spinning as she flew

03:13:24.239 --> 03:13:24.479
away.

03:13:24.540 --> 03:13:26.819
Was the Nightwing here waiting for them?

03:13:26.940 --> 03:13:29.100
Death bringer.

03:13:29.159 --> 03:13:30.479
Seriously?

03:13:30.540 --> 03:13:33.239
The only dragon she knew of who the Night

03:13:33.239 --> 03:13:34.620
Wings wanted dead was her.

03:13:34.680 --> 03:13:37.500
As soon as Morrow Seer had laid eyes on

03:13:37.500 --> 03:13:39.899
her, back under the mountain, he decided

03:13:39.899 --> 03:13:42.600
she was going to mess up the prophecy, so

03:13:42.600 --> 03:13:44.280
he'd ordered the guardians to kill her

03:13:44.280 --> 03:13:46.260
which was why she and the others had

03:13:46.260 --> 03:13:46.680
escaped.

03:13:46.739 --> 03:13:49.379
Had he sent Deathbringer to finish the

03:13:49.379 --> 03:13:49.620
job?

03:13:49.680 --> 03:13:52.319
Why waste all that energy hunting her

03:13:52.319 --> 03:13:52.620
down?

03:13:52.680 --> 03:13:55.620
The Death Bringer had sounded as if he

03:13:55.620 --> 03:13:56.879
was waiting for more than just her.

03:13:56.940 --> 03:13:59.280
She wondered if that meant the other

03:13:59.280 --> 03:14:00.600
dragonettes were in danger too.

03:14:00.659 --> 03:14:03.239
Surely the Night Wings wouldn't kill off

03:14:03.239 --> 03:14:03.659
any of them.

03:14:03.719 --> 03:14:06.420
That had to mess up the prophecy much

03:14:06.420 --> 03:14:07.799
more dramatically than glory could.

03:14:07.860 --> 03:14:10.860
She landed next to her friends, and

03:14:10.860 --> 03:14:12.420
nearly gave Starfly a heart attack.

03:14:12.479 --> 03:14:14.760
Ice Wing!

03:14:14.819 --> 03:14:16.979
he yelped, flailing over backward.

03:14:17.040 --> 03:14:19.979
Tsunami leaped to her feet, teeth bared.

03:14:20.040 --> 03:14:21.360
Look out.

03:14:21.420 --> 03:14:22.739
It's...

03:14:22.739 --> 03:14:23.280
Oh.

03:14:23.399 --> 03:14:25.559
Starfly took a deep breath.

03:14:25.620 --> 03:14:27.479
This glory's scales shifted back to brown

03:14:27.479 --> 03:14:28.020
and gray.

03:14:28.079 --> 03:14:29.280
Glory.

03:14:29.399 --> 03:14:31.440
Why would you do that to me?

03:14:31.559 --> 03:14:35.040
Because it's hilarious, she said.

03:14:35.100 --> 03:14:36.600
And shh.

03:14:36.659 --> 03:14:38.399
She thought they were far enough away

03:14:38.399 --> 03:14:40.200
from Death Bringer, but she wasn't

03:14:40.200 --> 03:14:42.000
completely sure how far sound would carry

03:14:42.000 --> 03:14:43.319
in the cold, crisp air.

03:14:43.379 --> 03:14:47.520
You looked very sparkly, Sonny said

03:14:47.520 --> 03:14:48.180
sleepily.

03:14:48.239 --> 03:14:50.700
I nearly clobbered you with my tail

03:14:50.700 --> 03:14:53.040
tsunami said in a severe voice.

03:14:53.159 --> 03:14:55.979
And I nearly bit your snout when you were

03:14:55.979 --> 03:14:57.959
snoring last night, Glory said.

03:14:58.020 --> 03:15:00.659
So I guess we're both models of self

03:14:59.819 --> 03:15:00.659
restraint.

03:15:00.719 --> 03:15:02.159
Jambu wake up.

03:15:02.219 --> 03:15:04.739
She poked her brother, who was the only

03:15:04.739 --> 03:15:06.299
one who'd slept through Starflight's

03:15:06.299 --> 03:15:06.540
alarm.

03:15:06.600 --> 03:15:11.459
Too cold, he mumbled, flopping one wing

03:15:11.459 --> 03:15:12.239
over his head.

03:15:12.299 --> 03:15:16.260
Too bad, she said, and poked him again.

03:15:16.319 --> 03:15:18.780
Besides, if you get up and move you'll

03:15:18.780 --> 03:15:19.319
feel warmer.

03:15:19.379 --> 03:15:24.059
More sleeping, he insisted. folding the

03:15:24.059 --> 03:15:25.200
other wing over his head as well.

03:15:25.260 --> 03:15:27.479
Glory sighed and left him alone.

03:15:27.600 --> 03:15:29.639
Starflight, she asked.

03:15:29.700 --> 03:15:32.159
Do you have any idea how literal a

03:15:32.159 --> 03:15:33.180
Nightwing's name is?

03:15:33.239 --> 03:15:35.760
Like, does it always signals something

03:15:35.760 --> 03:15:36.600
about what they do?

03:15:36.659 --> 03:15:39.600
The other dragonettes started getting up

03:15:39.600 --> 03:15:40.200
and stretching.

03:15:40.260 --> 03:15:42.780
Starflight scratched his head.

03:15:42.840 --> 03:15:46.020
Well, there's Moros here, he said.

03:15:46.079 --> 03:15:48.059
He can see the future and deliver

03:15:48.059 --> 03:15:48.840
prophecies.

03:15:48.899 --> 03:15:51.479
So that's what seeing the morrow is

03:15:51.479 --> 03:15:51.719
about.

03:15:51.780 --> 03:15:54.659
Yes, thank you, Glory said.

03:15:54.719 --> 03:15:55.739
I figured that one out.

03:15:55.799 --> 03:15:58.920
But did they know he'd be a prophet when

03:15:58.920 --> 03:15:59.579
they named him?

03:15:59.639 --> 03:16:01.680
Sonny asked curiously.

03:16:01.739 --> 03:16:03.719
Not all night wings are.

03:16:03.780 --> 03:16:05.700
So how would they know that?

03:16:05.760 --> 03:16:08.940
Maybe another prophet foresaw it?

03:16:09.000 --> 03:16:10.260
Tsunami joked.

03:16:10.319 --> 03:16:12.360
Starflight poked at the frozen ground

03:16:12.360 --> 03:16:13.379
with one claw.

03:16:13.440 --> 03:16:16.260
I don't know any more than that, he

03:16:16.260 --> 03:16:16.500
said.

03:16:16.559 --> 03:16:19.559
Maru seer hasn't told me any night wing

03:16:19.559 --> 03:16:20.459
tribe secrets.

03:16:20.520 --> 03:16:23.040
And you've read all the same scrolls I

03:16:23.040 --> 03:16:23.280
have.

03:16:23.340 --> 03:16:26.219
True, Glory said.

03:16:26.280 --> 03:16:28.440
Lots of epic nonsense about wonderful

03:16:28.440 --> 03:16:29.399
night wings.

03:16:29.459 --> 03:16:31.500
They all have these awkward mouthful

03:16:31.500 --> 03:16:32.700
names.

03:16:32.760 --> 03:16:34.139
I think in the stories their names do

03:16:34.139 --> 03:16:36.239
usually match their skills, if I remember

03:16:36.239 --> 03:16:36.659
right.

03:16:36.719 --> 03:16:38.760
Why are you asking?

03:16:38.819 --> 03:16:41.159
Starflight tilted his head at her.

03:16:41.219 --> 03:16:45.420
Because I just met one, Glory said.

03:16:45.479 --> 03:16:48.540
And I think he's here to kill us.

03:16:48.600 --> 03:16:50.520
Well, me, at least.

03:16:50.579 --> 03:16:53.159
That got their attention in a hurry.

03:16:53.219 --> 03:16:55.860
She told them about Death Bringer, and

03:16:55.860 --> 03:16:58.620
everything he'd said, almost everything

03:16:58.620 --> 03:16:59.159
anyhow.

03:16:59.159 --> 03:17:01.200
She didn't want them to figure out that

03:17:01.200 --> 03:17:02.520
she thought he was kind of cute.

03:17:02.579 --> 03:17:05.159
That is, before she realized he was there

03:17:05.159 --> 03:17:05.579
to kill her.

03:17:05.639 --> 03:17:09.120
Let's get out of here, Starflight said

03:17:09.120 --> 03:17:09.840
when she finished.

03:17:09.899 --> 03:17:13.020
Let's fly south right now and get back to

03:17:13.020 --> 03:17:14.940
the rainforest as fast as possible.

03:17:15.000 --> 03:17:17.399
Jambu poked his nose out, hopefully.

03:17:17.459 --> 03:17:20.280
I like that plan, he offered.

03:17:20.399 --> 03:17:23.579
It does sound like the warmest plan.

03:17:23.700 --> 03:17:25.799
But what about mangrove?

03:17:25.860 --> 03:17:27.840
Clay asked with a shiver.

03:17:27.899 --> 03:17:30.059
I saw something else.

03:17:30.120 --> 03:17:30.840
Glory said.

03:17:30.899 --> 03:17:33.180
I think it's where Blaze and her army

03:17:33.180 --> 03:17:34.200
must be camping out.

03:17:34.260 --> 03:17:36.840
She described the buildings she'd seen.

03:17:36.959 --> 03:17:39.360
Starflight and tsunami both nodded.

03:17:39.420 --> 03:17:42.360
Make sense to me, said tsunami.

03:17:42.420 --> 03:17:44.340
Blaze would need a place of her own.

03:17:44.399 --> 03:17:46.739
She couldn't survive a day in Glacier's

03:17:46.739 --> 03:17:47.040
palace.

03:17:47.100 --> 03:17:48.600
Right.

03:17:48.659 --> 03:17:51.239
It's mostly built of ice, so she wouldn't

03:17:51.239 --> 03:17:52.680
even be able to use her fire there.

03:17:52.799 --> 03:17:54.360
Starflight mused.

03:17:54.479 --> 03:17:57.000
So here's what I'm thinking.

03:17:57.059 --> 03:17:57.840
Glory said.

03:17:57.899 --> 03:18:01.020
I'm sure a mangrove saw this place too

03:18:01.079 --> 03:18:01.799
hell head right for it.

03:18:01.920 --> 03:18:04.620
Probably camouflage himself and sneak in

03:18:04.620 --> 03:18:05.520
looking for orchid.

03:18:05.579 --> 03:18:07.739
So I'll go after him and bring him back.

03:18:07.799 --> 03:18:10.079
While you guys hide somewhere, Death

03:18:10.079 --> 03:18:11.100
Bringer won't find you.

03:18:11.159 --> 03:18:13.559
And then we all fly south as fast as

03:18:13.559 --> 03:18:13.860
possible.

03:18:13.920 --> 03:18:15.899
Wait.

03:18:15.959 --> 03:18:17.340
By yourself?

03:18:17.459 --> 03:18:18.479
Clay said.

03:18:18.540 --> 03:18:20.459
Can't one of us go with you?

03:18:20.520 --> 03:18:22.079
Who?

03:18:22.139 --> 03:18:22.979
Glory said.

03:18:23.040 --> 03:18:25.139
Who else can disguise herself as an ice

03:18:25.139 --> 03:18:25.500
wing?

03:18:25.620 --> 03:18:28.319
Her friends all looked at Jambu, who

03:18:28.319 --> 03:18:29.219
blinked sleepily.

03:18:29.280 --> 03:18:31.739
And be helpful.

03:18:31.799 --> 03:18:33.000
Glory added.

03:18:33.059 --> 03:18:36.420
I can be helpful, Jambu said with a

03:18:36.420 --> 03:18:36.719
yawn.

03:18:36.780 --> 03:18:39.540
I bet I'm better at spotting camouflaged

03:18:39.540 --> 03:18:40.559
rain wings than you are.

03:18:40.620 --> 03:18:43.260
Glory hesitated.

03:18:43.319 --> 03:18:44.280
That actually did sound useful.

03:18:44.340 --> 03:18:46.680
She wasn't really sure how she intended

03:18:46.680 --> 03:18:48.000
to find a mangrove on her own.

03:18:48.059 --> 03:18:50.940
You can do that, she said.

03:18:51.000 --> 03:18:53.399
It's a game we play starting when we're

03:18:53.399 --> 03:18:54.180
dragonettes.

03:18:54.239 --> 03:18:55.319
Jambu said.

03:18:55.379 --> 03:18:58.680
One dragonette camouflages herself, and

03:18:58.680 --> 03:19:00.120
whoever sees her 1st wins.

03:19:00.180 --> 03:19:03.540
So no guarantees, but it's probably more

03:19:03.540 --> 03:19:04.620
practice than you've had.

03:19:04.680 --> 03:19:07.139
She thought for a moment and shook her

03:19:07.139 --> 03:19:07.379
head.

03:19:07.440 --> 03:19:09.180
It's too dangerous.

03:19:09.239 --> 03:19:11.579
I can take care of myself, and I don't

03:19:11.579 --> 03:19:12.059
need any help.

03:19:12.120 --> 03:19:17.340
Glory, Clay said, in a sort of amiably

03:19:17.340 --> 03:19:21.120
threatening voice, you take him or we're

03:19:21.120 --> 03:19:21.959
all coming with you.

03:19:22.020 --> 03:19:24.659
Glory could tell by the looks on their

03:19:24.659 --> 03:19:26.100
faces, that this was true.

03:19:26.219 --> 03:19:29.100
Stupid heroic, we're a team idiots.

03:19:29.159 --> 03:19:31.079
All right, fine.

03:19:31.139 --> 03:19:33.059
We'll go in camouflaged.

03:19:33.120 --> 03:19:34.799
But I want to make sure you can look like

03:19:34.799 --> 03:19:35.579
an ice wing too.

03:19:35.639 --> 03:19:37.680
Try matching what I'm doing.

03:19:37.799 --> 03:19:40.500
She let her scales shimmer back into our

03:19:40.500 --> 03:19:41.520
ice wing disguise.

03:19:41.639 --> 03:19:44.219
Clay winced, and she guessed he'd

03:19:44.219 --> 03:19:46.319
recognized which dragon she'd used as a

03:19:46.319 --> 03:19:46.559
model.

03:19:46.620 --> 03:19:49.139
Watching Fjor die in front of him

03:19:49.139 --> 03:19:50.760
couldn't have been any easier for him

03:19:50.760 --> 03:19:51.479
than for her.

03:19:51.540 --> 03:19:54.540
Now make your scales a bit whiter.

03:19:54.659 --> 03:19:57.299
Glory said to John Boo, so we're not

03:19:57.299 --> 03:19:59.700
exactly the same, and shift around the

03:19:59.700 --> 03:20:00.659
fake icicle horns.

03:20:00.719 --> 03:20:02.879
She stepped back and studied him.

03:20:02.940 --> 03:20:04.620
I think that'll do.

03:20:04.680 --> 03:20:06.840
Can you remember that if we need to

03:20:06.840 --> 03:20:07.739
become ice wings?

03:20:07.799 --> 03:20:10.020
Sure, he said.

03:20:10.079 --> 03:20:11.819
He held out his wings and looked at

03:20:11.819 --> 03:20:12.059
them.

03:20:12.120 --> 03:20:14.219
This is a pretty cool color.

03:20:14.280 --> 03:20:16.139
I'll have to remember it once we're

03:20:16.139 --> 03:20:16.260
home.

03:20:16.319 --> 03:20:19.319
We also need ice wing names.

03:20:19.379 --> 03:20:21.120
UB Penguin.

03:20:21.180 --> 03:20:22.319
I'll be Storm.

03:20:22.379 --> 03:20:23.700
That should be easy to remember.

03:20:23.760 --> 03:20:26.399
I still think one of us should go with

03:20:26.399 --> 03:20:26.579
you.

03:20:26.639 --> 03:20:28.200
Tsunami interjected.

03:20:28.260 --> 03:20:31.020
Mudwings and Seawings are the enemy

03:20:31.020 --> 03:20:31.260
here.

03:20:31.319 --> 03:20:34.920
Glory pointed out, and no events, guys

03:20:34.920 --> 03:20:36.719
but it's not like Starfight or Sunny

03:20:36.719 --> 03:20:37.440
would be much help.

03:20:37.500 --> 03:20:39.780
No offense?

03:20:39.840 --> 03:20:41.219
Sonny squeaked.

03:20:41.280 --> 03:20:43.620
How am I not supposed to be offended by

03:20:43.620 --> 03:20:43.799
that?

03:20:43.860 --> 03:20:46.559
She lashed her tail and scowled.

03:20:46.620 --> 03:20:49.200
We'll get in and out faster if we just

03:20:49.200 --> 03:20:51.360
keep our scales hidden, Glory said.

03:20:51.420 --> 03:20:53.819
Don't worry, we'll be back by tonight.

03:20:53.879 --> 03:20:56.879
What if you find the missing rain wings

03:20:56.879 --> 03:20:57.239
in there?

03:20:57.299 --> 03:20:58.559
Clay asked.

03:20:58.620 --> 03:21:01.260
Glory flicked her tail, letting her

03:21:01.260 --> 03:21:03.000
scales shift back into the color of the

03:21:03.000 --> 03:21:06.180
rocks, will free them, and come storming

03:21:06.180 --> 03:21:07.799
out in a big, invisible herd.

03:21:07.860 --> 03:21:08.639
All right?

03:21:08.700 --> 03:21:11.520
Clay and tsunami nodded reluctantly.

03:21:11.579 --> 03:21:14.159
Come on, Jambu, Glory said.

03:21:14.219 --> 03:21:15.899
The rest of you stay hidden.

03:21:15.959 --> 03:21:16.920
I mean it.

03:21:16.979 --> 03:21:19.200
She sprang into the air with her brother

03:21:19.200 --> 03:21:21.899
beside her, and let her scales adjust to

03:21:21.899 --> 03:21:22.620
the sky around them.

03:21:22.620 --> 03:21:25.680
As they beat their way north, she glanced

03:21:25.680 --> 03:21:28.020
back once, and saw Sonny staring after

03:21:28.020 --> 03:21:30.299
them, while tsunami waved her talons

03:21:30.299 --> 03:21:30.899
bossily.

03:21:30.959 --> 03:21:35.340
It's still cold, John Boo moaned.

03:21:35.399 --> 03:21:37.260
Even with my wings beating.

03:21:37.319 --> 03:21:39.360
I think it's even colder.

03:21:39.420 --> 03:21:43.079
Well, we're up in the air, Glory pointed

03:21:43.079 --> 03:21:45.000
out. and the wind probably isn't

03:21:45.000 --> 03:21:45.299
helping.

03:21:45.360 --> 03:21:47.579
But this will be over soon.

03:21:47.639 --> 03:21:48.180
Don't worry.

03:21:48.239 --> 03:21:50.459
She pointed to the building ahead of

03:21:50.459 --> 03:21:50.639
them.

03:21:50.700 --> 03:21:54.239
Just to warn you, there will be snow, but

03:21:54.239 --> 03:21:55.920
hopefully the sand wings keep the inside

03:21:55.920 --> 03:21:56.819
warm with their fires.

03:21:56.940 --> 03:22:00.059
Snow, Jambu said.

03:22:00.120 --> 03:22:01.319
And fire?

03:22:01.379 --> 03:22:03.420
You know, I've never seen either of

03:22:03.420 --> 03:22:03.600
those.

03:22:03.659 --> 03:22:07.200
I've never seen snow up close either.

03:22:07.260 --> 03:22:08.280
Glory admitted.

03:22:08.399 --> 03:22:11.579
It looks fluffy. said Jambu.

03:22:11.639 --> 03:22:15.239
It wasn't fluffy.

03:22:15.299 --> 03:22:18.600
It was wet and piercingly freezing

03:22:18.600 --> 03:22:20.459
against their talons as they landed

03:22:20.459 --> 03:22:21.239
outside the walls.

03:22:21.299 --> 03:22:24.120
John Boo let out a yelp of pain, and

03:22:24.120 --> 03:22:26.040
glory nearly tackled him to shut him up.

03:22:26.100 --> 03:22:27.540
Who's there?

03:22:27.600 --> 03:22:29.639
called a voice from above.

03:22:29.879 --> 03:22:30.780
They both froze.

03:22:30.840 --> 03:22:32.700
There scales the color of the white

03:22:32.700 --> 03:22:33.719
ground below them.

03:22:33.780 --> 03:22:36.299
A sandwing head poked out a window.

03:22:36.360 --> 03:22:37.739
Did you hear that?

03:22:37.739 --> 03:22:38.700
he asked.

03:22:38.760 --> 03:22:41.219
Another sandwing head wriggled out beside

03:22:41.219 --> 03:22:41.579
his.

03:22:41.639 --> 03:22:43.979
No, and I don't see anything.

03:22:44.040 --> 03:22:45.780
You're imagining things again.

03:22:45.840 --> 03:22:49.200
When Burns army shows up to crush us

03:22:49.200 --> 03:22:50.940
growled the 1st dragon.

03:22:51.000 --> 03:22:53.819
We'll see them coming from miles away

03:22:53.819 --> 03:22:57.000
said the 2nd, and they'll be frozen and

03:22:57.000 --> 03:22:58.920
weak from the cold, and we'll have ice

03:22:58.920 --> 03:23:00.719
wing back up by the time they get here.

03:23:00.780 --> 03:23:02.280
Stop interrupting our game.

03:23:02.340 --> 03:23:04.979
The 2nd guard withdrew into the room.

03:23:05.040 --> 03:23:08.340
The 1st glanced around suspiciously, his

03:23:08.340 --> 03:23:10.440
gaze trailing across the snow where Glory

03:23:10.440 --> 03:23:12.059
and John Boo crouched.

03:23:12.120 --> 03:23:14.159
Finally, he huffed out a snort and

03:23:14.159 --> 03:23:15.000
retreated back inside.

03:23:15.120 --> 03:23:17.879
Gloria flipped her tail into her

03:23:17.879 --> 03:23:20.819
brother's talons and led the way, slipping

03:23:20.819 --> 03:23:22.680
around the thick stone walls until she

03:23:22.680 --> 03:23:25.440
found a dragon sized door, locked, of

03:23:25.440 --> 03:23:25.680
course.

03:23:25.739 --> 03:23:27.420
She glanced up.

03:23:27.479 --> 03:23:29.760
But she'd already seen from above that

03:23:29.760 --> 03:23:32.280
there was no inner courtyard, or openings

03:23:32.280 --> 03:23:34.379
anywhere on the roof, other than the

03:23:34.379 --> 03:23:35.760
chimneys, which were too small.

03:23:35.819 --> 03:23:38.159
The windows were all too narrow for a

03:23:38.159 --> 03:23:39.479
dragon to squeeze through as well.

03:23:39.540 --> 03:23:41.879
This was a proper fortress.

03:23:42.000 --> 03:23:44.340
She wondered if it had been built early

03:23:44.340 --> 03:23:44.879
in the war.

03:23:44.940 --> 03:23:48.059
When Blaise 1st came to Queen Glacier for

03:23:48.059 --> 03:23:49.260
protection and an alliance.

03:23:49.319 --> 03:23:51.840
This was a pretty generous gift for

03:23:51.840 --> 03:23:54.360
Glacier to give to her ally, a whole

03:23:54.360 --> 03:23:56.280
fortress ride in ice wing territory.

03:23:56.340 --> 03:23:58.860
Death bringer's words came back to her.

03:23:58.920 --> 03:24:02.040
Blaise had promised Glacier all this land

03:24:02.040 --> 03:24:03.000
if she won the war.

03:24:03.059 --> 03:24:06.180
Glory thought of the other 2 sandwing

03:24:06.180 --> 03:24:06.540
sisters.

03:24:06.600 --> 03:24:09.120
She wondered what Byrne had promised the

03:24:09.120 --> 03:24:11.399
sky wings and mud wings, and whether

03:24:11.399 --> 03:24:13.200
blister had promised the sea wings

03:24:13.200 --> 03:24:15.659
anything, or if she'd just manipulated

03:24:15.659 --> 03:24:17.340
Queen Coral into supporting her.

03:24:17.399 --> 03:24:20.219
I'm not seeing a way to sneak in here.

03:24:20.280 --> 03:24:21.780
Glory whispered.

03:24:21.840 --> 03:24:22.860
Do you have any ideas?

03:24:22.920 --> 03:24:25.260
She felt Jambu shrug.

03:24:25.319 --> 03:24:27.000
Sorry, he said.

03:24:27.059 --> 03:24:28.979
I've never done anything like this.

03:24:29.100 --> 03:24:31.799
They tried circling the walls one more

03:24:31.799 --> 03:24:33.719
time, but there was only the one door.

03:24:33.780 --> 03:24:36.360
Glory couldn't see any gaps in the

03:24:36.360 --> 03:24:37.680
fortress's defenses anywhere.

03:24:37.739 --> 03:24:40.200
Their only choice was to wait for that

03:24:40.200 --> 03:24:42.180
door to open and hope they could slip

03:24:42.180 --> 03:24:42.420
inside.

03:24:42.540 --> 03:24:44.520
But who knew how long that would take?

03:24:44.579 --> 03:24:47.639
The sun was finally drifting up the pale

03:24:47.639 --> 03:24:49.979
blue sky, reflecting off the glittering

03:24:49.979 --> 03:24:50.280
snow.

03:24:50.340 --> 03:24:52.620
Glory did not want to stand out here all

03:24:52.620 --> 03:24:52.920
day.

03:24:52.979 --> 03:24:55.739
For one thing, Jambu would probably

03:24:55.739 --> 03:24:56.520
freeze to death.

03:24:56.579 --> 03:24:59.639
She didn't like the cold either, but he'd

03:24:59.639 --> 03:25:01.139
never been out of a tropical environment

03:25:01.139 --> 03:25:01.440
before.

03:25:01.500 --> 03:25:05.459
Same goes for mangrove, she realized.

03:25:05.579 --> 03:25:08.579
In fact, how would he have gotten inside

03:25:08.579 --> 03:25:09.360
the fortress?

03:25:09.420 --> 03:25:11.579
Maybe he wasn't there at all.

03:25:11.639 --> 03:25:13.559
Maybe he was lying in a snowbank

03:25:13.559 --> 03:25:15.780
somewhere, slowly disappearing into the

03:25:15.780 --> 03:25:16.079
ice.

03:25:16.139 --> 03:25:17.879
Glory shook her head.

03:25:17.940 --> 03:25:20.760
Mangrove wasn't the type to give up if

03:25:20.760 --> 03:25:21.479
she read him right.

03:25:21.540 --> 03:25:23.520
And neither was she.

03:25:23.579 --> 03:25:26.940
We'll have to go in as Ice Wings, she

03:25:26.940 --> 03:25:27.239
said.

03:25:27.299 --> 03:25:28.799
Just follow my lead.

03:25:28.860 --> 03:25:31.979
John Boo's head appeared, nodding

03:25:31.979 --> 03:25:34.440
agreeably, as his scales shifted color.

03:25:34.500 --> 03:25:37.979
Glory let her scales change as well, then

03:25:37.979 --> 03:25:39.540
turned in a circle to check herself as

03:25:39.540 --> 03:25:40.139
best she could.

03:25:40.200 --> 03:25:43.139
It wasn't a perfect disguise by any means

03:25:43.139 --> 03:25:45.780
but hopefully these sand wings wouldn't

03:25:45.780 --> 03:25:46.260
look too closely.

03:25:46.319 --> 03:25:48.959
And between her camouflage scales and

03:25:48.959 --> 03:25:50.940
venom, She felt like she had a pretty

03:25:50.940 --> 03:25:52.860
good chance of escaping, even if they did

03:25:52.860 --> 03:25:53.459
catch her.

03:25:53.520 --> 03:25:55.860
She marched up to the door and rapped

03:25:55.860 --> 03:25:56.280
smartly.

03:25:56.399 --> 03:25:58.739
Try to look like a soldier?

03:25:58.799 --> 03:26:01.559
She hissed to Jambu, who was slouching

03:26:01.559 --> 03:26:02.520
and rubbing his neck behind her.

03:26:02.579 --> 03:26:05.760
I don't know what that looks like, he

03:26:05.760 --> 03:26:07.620
whispered back, just before the door

03:26:07.620 --> 03:26:08.459
swung open.

03:26:08.520 --> 03:26:11.459
A heavyset sandwing with broken claws on

03:26:11.459 --> 03:26:12.899
one talon peered out at them.

03:26:12.959 --> 03:26:14.219
Eh?

03:26:14.219 --> 03:26:15.059
he muttered.

03:26:15.120 --> 03:26:17.639
We have an important message for Queen

03:26:17.639 --> 03:26:19.440
Blaze, Gloria announced.

03:26:19.500 --> 03:26:22.260
Take us somewhere we can wait until she

03:26:22.260 --> 03:26:22.739
returns.

03:26:22.799 --> 03:26:26.639
Surely, like her sisters, Blaze would be

03:26:26.639 --> 03:26:28.020
off leading a battle somewhere.

03:26:28.079 --> 03:26:30.120
Once they were shown into a waiting room

03:26:30.120 --> 03:26:32.340
they could change back to camouflage and

03:26:32.340 --> 03:26:34.020
search the fortress for mangrove without

03:26:34.020 --> 03:26:34.379
being seen.

03:26:34.440 --> 03:26:36.299
Eh?

03:26:36.360 --> 03:26:38.340
Until she returns.

03:26:38.399 --> 03:26:40.920
The Sandwing looked at her as if she were

03:26:40.920 --> 03:26:41.159
mad.

03:26:41.219 --> 03:26:42.959
Blaze is here.

03:26:43.020 --> 03:26:44.100
She's always here.

03:26:44.159 --> 03:26:46.200
I can take you right to her.

03:26:46.260 --> 03:26:50.520
Chapter 15.

03:26:50.940 --> 03:26:54.420
Uh-oh, glory thought.

03:26:54.479 --> 03:26:57.780
But it better be good news, said the

03:26:57.780 --> 03:26:59.760
Sandwang. stomping around and heading

03:26:59.760 --> 03:27:00.659
into the fortress.

03:27:00.719 --> 03:27:03.959
She doesn't like hearing bad news, and we

03:27:03.959 --> 03:27:05.159
don't like her hearing it either.

03:27:05.219 --> 03:27:07.559
Queen Glacier needs to figure that out

03:27:07.559 --> 03:27:09.840
and stop sending all these gloomy

03:27:09.840 --> 03:27:10.319
reports.

03:27:10.440 --> 03:27:13.860
Gloria and Jambu exchanged glances and

03:27:13.860 --> 03:27:14.459
hurried after him.

03:27:14.520 --> 03:27:17.399
The door thudded, shut behind them, and

03:27:17.399 --> 03:27:19.559
another sand wing guard followed close on

03:27:19.559 --> 03:27:21.959
their tails, slipping away was not going

03:27:21.959 --> 03:27:22.379
to be easy.

03:27:22.440 --> 03:27:25.680
Blaze's fortress was not much like the

03:27:25.680 --> 03:27:28.260
glorious extravagant palaces of Queen

03:27:28.260 --> 03:27:30.120
Scarlet, or Queen Coral.

03:27:30.180 --> 03:27:32.760
The halls here were narrow, and nothing

03:27:32.760 --> 03:27:33.719
was open to the sky.

03:27:33.780 --> 03:27:36.719
A fireplace held a roaring fire in every

03:27:36.719 --> 03:27:38.940
room they passed, so the heat was almost

03:27:38.940 --> 03:27:41.879
stifling, and yet cold winds still

03:27:41.879 --> 03:27:43.200
rattled through the small windows.

03:27:43.260 --> 03:27:45.840
There was no treasure adorning the walls

03:27:45.840 --> 03:27:48.540
no gold or pearls embedded in the floor.

03:27:48.600 --> 03:27:51.600
Instead, the stone walls were hung with

03:27:51.600 --> 03:27:53.100
thick, woven tapestries.

03:27:53.159 --> 03:27:55.860
Each tapestry had a bright yellow sun

03:27:55.860 --> 03:27:58.319
blazing at the center of it, surrounded

03:27:58.319 --> 03:28:00.239
by patterns of images from the desert

03:28:00.239 --> 03:28:04.139
sinuous lizards, prickly cacti, palm

03:28:04.139 --> 03:28:05.219
trees, camels.

03:28:05.280 --> 03:28:07.979
White and green and blue cover the dull

03:28:07.979 --> 03:28:10.319
gray walls almost from corner to corner.

03:28:10.379 --> 03:28:15.239
They miss their home, Glory realized, and

03:28:15.239 --> 03:28:17.100
was shocked to find herself feeling sorry

03:28:17.100 --> 03:28:18.239
for these sand wings.

03:28:18.299 --> 03:28:20.459
They'd come here to support Blaze.

03:28:20.579 --> 03:28:23.219
Probably they'd fled alongside her when

03:28:23.219 --> 03:28:25.739
Bern tried to claim the throne, and now

03:28:25.739 --> 03:28:27.600
they were trapped in this icy world that

03:28:27.600 --> 03:28:28.440
was nothing like their own.

03:28:28.559 --> 03:28:32.100
Kind of like growing up in a cave instead

03:28:32.100 --> 03:28:32.940
of a rainforest.

03:28:33.000 --> 03:28:36.299
Cool, Jambu said.

03:28:36.360 --> 03:28:38.520
He pointed at a tapestry covered in

03:28:38.520 --> 03:28:39.600
rioting green lizards.

03:28:39.659 --> 03:28:42.299
That one's really wild.

03:28:42.360 --> 03:28:42.719
I like it.

03:28:42.840 --> 03:28:45.659
The sand wing soldiers stared at him.

03:28:45.719 --> 03:28:47.040
Really?

03:28:47.040 --> 03:28:48.360
said the one in the lead.

03:28:48.420 --> 03:28:50.700
Our ice wing visitors usually make it

03:28:50.700 --> 03:28:52.500
pretty clear that they think our hangings

03:28:52.500 --> 03:28:52.860
are.

03:28:52.920 --> 03:28:54.239
How do they put it?

03:28:54.299 --> 03:28:56.100
garish and gaudy.

03:28:56.159 --> 03:29:00.479
Well, they're not our style, Glory said

03:29:00.479 --> 03:29:03.120
stamping on John Boo's foot, but we can

03:29:03.120 --> 03:29:04.500
still appreciate the artistry.

03:29:04.559 --> 03:29:07.799
Huh, said the 1st Sandwang.

03:29:07.860 --> 03:29:09.659
Never heard that from an ice wing

03:29:09.659 --> 03:29:09.899
before.

03:29:09.959 --> 03:29:12.059
He turned and kept walking.

03:29:12.120 --> 03:29:15.360
Glory shot Jambu aglare, and he wrinkled

03:29:15.360 --> 03:29:16.139
his snout at her.

03:29:16.200 --> 03:29:18.479
They reached the center of the fortress

03:29:18.479 --> 03:29:21.059
or so glory guest, since there were no

03:29:21.059 --> 03:29:23.100
windows here, and stopped in a small

03:29:23.100 --> 03:29:25.079
antechamber outside a pair of giant

03:29:25.079 --> 03:29:25.860
wooden doors.

03:29:25.920 --> 03:29:28.500
One of the sand wings knocked twice and

03:29:28.500 --> 03:29:29.040
they all waited.

03:29:29.100 --> 03:29:32.940
As the silence stretched out, Glory

03:29:32.940 --> 03:29:35.100
realized that there was something huddled

03:29:35.100 --> 03:29:36.299
in a corner of the little room.

03:29:36.360 --> 03:29:40.020
It looked like a dirty pile of prey fur

03:29:40.020 --> 03:29:43.379
at first, but when she peered closer, She

03:29:43.379 --> 03:29:45.600
realized there were 2 scavengers in

03:29:45.600 --> 03:29:45.780
there.

03:29:45.840 --> 03:29:48.120
They leaned against the wall with their

03:29:48.120 --> 03:29:49.799
arms around each other, shivering.

03:29:49.920 --> 03:29:51.959
What are those?

03:29:52.079 --> 03:29:55.079
Jambu whispered to her, spotting them at

03:29:55.079 --> 03:29:55.559
the same time.

03:29:55.620 --> 03:29:58.739
You're one of those ice wings who's never

03:29:58.739 --> 03:30:00.420
left the queen's palace, aren't you?

03:30:00.540 --> 03:30:03.239
Guessed the 2nd soldier, overhearing

03:30:03.239 --> 03:30:03.420
him.

03:30:03.479 --> 03:30:06.360
I hear they rarely see scavengers that

03:30:06.360 --> 03:30:06.899
far north.

03:30:06.959 --> 03:30:10.620
He prodded the furs with one sharp claw

03:30:10.620 --> 03:30:12.479
and the 2 scavengers let out tragic

03:30:12.479 --> 03:30:13.139
little whimpers.

03:30:13.200 --> 03:30:16.200
We found one of their hidden dens near

03:30:16.200 --> 03:30:18.360
the mountains, and gathered up whatever

03:30:18.360 --> 03:30:18.899
we could catch.

03:30:18.959 --> 03:30:20.940
They're faster than they look.

03:30:21.000 --> 03:30:23.579
We got only 6 of them, when there must

03:30:23.579 --> 03:30:24.239
have been at least 20.

03:30:24.540 --> 03:30:26.159
He shook his head.

03:30:26.219 --> 03:30:27.959
These 2 are what's left?

03:30:28.079 --> 03:30:30.659
You're going to eat them?

03:30:30.780 --> 03:30:31.920
Jambu said.

03:30:31.979 --> 03:30:35.459
Don't sound so shocked, Glory thought

03:30:35.459 --> 03:30:37.739
lashing her tail, but she could

03:30:37.739 --> 03:30:39.899
understand what he was feeling, with her

03:30:39.899 --> 03:30:42.180
big eyes and strange arms wound around

03:30:42.180 --> 03:30:42.600
each other.

03:30:42.659 --> 03:30:45.899
The 2 scavengers looked like overgrown

03:30:45.899 --> 03:30:47.100
less cute sloths.

03:30:47.159 --> 03:30:49.559
She couldn't imagine eating them either.

03:30:49.620 --> 03:30:51.600
The thought made her feel weirdly

03:30:51.600 --> 03:30:52.319
queasy.

03:30:52.379 --> 03:30:54.420
It didn't help that one of them was

03:30:54.420 --> 03:30:56.760
staring at her in the same plaintive way

03:30:56.760 --> 03:30:58.500
Silver did when she didn't want Glory to

03:30:58.500 --> 03:30:59.159
leave her behind.

03:30:59.219 --> 03:31:02.100
Of course, said the guard.

03:31:02.159 --> 03:31:04.979
We wreck any scavenger dens we can find

03:31:04.979 --> 03:31:06.899
and eat as many of them as we can

03:31:06.899 --> 03:31:08.340
glaciers orders.

03:31:08.459 --> 03:31:10.440
She thinks one day we'll find where they

03:31:10.440 --> 03:31:11.280
bury our treasure.

03:31:11.340 --> 03:31:15.059
If it still exists, who knows what

03:31:15.059 --> 03:31:17.639
scavengers do with treasure, muttered the

03:31:17.639 --> 03:31:18.120
other guard.

03:31:18.180 --> 03:31:20.639
He knocked again, and this time the door

03:31:20.639 --> 03:31:22.020
swung open under his talon.

03:31:22.139 --> 03:31:24.659
The room on the other side was larger

03:31:24.659 --> 03:31:26.159
than any they'd seen so far.

03:31:26.219 --> 03:31:28.799
The smooth stone floor was covered in

03:31:28.799 --> 03:31:31.200
sand, and the tapestries on the walls

03:31:31.200 --> 03:31:33.360
here were more intricate, with images of

03:31:33.360 --> 03:31:36.420
dragons and crowns and jewels surrounding

03:31:36.420 --> 03:31:37.139
the yellow suns.

03:31:37.260 --> 03:31:40.379
Giant wine red pillows and camel hair

03:31:40.379 --> 03:31:43.079
carpets were piled in a loose nest in the

03:31:43.079 --> 03:31:45.120
middle of the room, and sprawled across

03:31:45.120 --> 03:31:47.399
this was a strikingly beautiful sand

03:31:47.399 --> 03:31:47.819
wing.

03:31:47.940 --> 03:31:51.120
She had her chin propped on one talon, and

03:31:51.120 --> 03:31:53.100
was gazing listlessly into a mirror on

03:31:53.100 --> 03:31:54.299
the sand in front of her.

03:31:54.360 --> 03:31:56.579
Her tail coiled gracefully across the

03:31:56.579 --> 03:31:59.100
pillows, with a poisonous barb touching

03:31:59.100 --> 03:31:59.399
the floor.

03:31:59.459 --> 03:32:02.520
Her wings were folded, and her scales

03:32:02.520 --> 03:32:04.860
shimmered like white gold against the red

03:32:04.860 --> 03:32:05.819
backdrop.

03:32:05.879 --> 03:32:09.420
Blaze lifted her dark eyes and saw Glory

03:32:09.420 --> 03:32:10.500
and Jambu in the doorway.

03:32:10.559 --> 03:32:13.260
She forced a smile, and reached her front

03:32:13.260 --> 03:32:14.760
talons toward them in a welcoming

03:32:14.760 --> 03:32:15.120
gesture.

03:32:15.180 --> 03:32:18.059
Oh, wonderful, she said.

03:32:18.120 --> 03:32:20.159
We haven't had visitors in so long.

03:32:20.219 --> 03:32:22.440
I was hoping Queen Glacier would send us

03:32:22.440 --> 03:32:22.680
news.

03:32:22.739 --> 03:32:25.799
Glory bowed and Jambu imitated her.

03:32:25.860 --> 03:32:29.879
If this is a bad time, your majesty, we

03:32:29.879 --> 03:32:30.600
can wait until later.

03:32:30.719 --> 03:32:32.340
No, no.

03:32:32.399 --> 03:32:35.280
Please come in, Blaze cried.

03:32:35.340 --> 03:32:38.100
Okatillo, please bring us some tea.

03:32:38.159 --> 03:32:40.680
Oh, and some of those dried lizards, if

03:32:40.680 --> 03:32:41.159
we have any left.

03:32:41.219 --> 03:32:45.000
Of course, Your Majesty. said the 1st

03:32:45.000 --> 03:32:46.680
guard, with a respectful bow.

03:32:46.799 --> 03:32:49.440
Both sandwing soldiers backed out of the

03:32:49.440 --> 03:32:52.139
room, leaving Glory and Jambu alone with

03:32:52.139 --> 03:32:52.620
Blaze.

03:32:52.680 --> 03:32:55.739
I'm guessing it wouldn't be this easy to

03:32:55.739 --> 03:32:57.299
get a private audience with burn or

03:32:57.299 --> 03:32:58.860
blister, Lori thought.

03:32:58.920 --> 03:33:01.979
Blaze was not as cautious or suspicious

03:33:01.979 --> 03:33:04.559
as her sisters, but then she had no

03:33:04.559 --> 03:33:06.479
reason to suspect a pair of ice wings.

03:33:06.540 --> 03:33:09.000
Is it about Queen Scarlet?

03:33:09.059 --> 03:33:11.219
Blaise asked, leaning forward.

03:33:11.280 --> 03:33:12.899
Did we find out if she's dead?

03:33:12.959 --> 03:33:15.360
Are the Sky Wings still following burn?

03:33:15.420 --> 03:33:17.760
You know, if Glacier would let me go to

03:33:17.760 --> 03:33:18.780
the Sky Kingdom?

03:33:18.840 --> 03:33:21.239
I bet I could convince the Sky Wings to

03:33:21.239 --> 03:33:22.739
switch alliances to us.

03:33:22.799 --> 03:33:24.899
I can be really convincing.

03:33:24.959 --> 03:33:26.579
Everyone likes me.

03:33:26.639 --> 03:33:29.399
Or they could throw you in prison.

03:33:29.459 --> 03:33:32.399
Glory thought, or hand you over to burn.

03:33:32.459 --> 03:33:36.059
I know what you'll say, Blaise said

03:33:36.059 --> 03:33:36.719
restlessly.

03:33:36.780 --> 03:33:40.020
What glacier always says, stay put, and

03:33:40.020 --> 03:33:41.040
let her handle things.

03:33:41.159 --> 03:33:43.920
I know all that military stuff is too

03:33:43.920 --> 03:33:46.260
confusing for me, but I think I could be

03:33:46.260 --> 03:33:47.459
useful with a talking part.

03:33:47.520 --> 03:33:50.040
Other dragons like hearing me talk.

03:33:50.100 --> 03:33:54.959
I'm sure that is true, Your Majesty, said

03:33:54.959 --> 03:33:55.799
Glory politely.

03:33:55.860 --> 03:34:00.600
So, Blaise said, her pitch dark eyes were

03:34:00.600 --> 03:34:02.399
too eerily similar to burns and

03:34:02.399 --> 03:34:03.059
blisters.

03:34:03.120 --> 03:34:05.819
They gave Glory the creeps, even though

03:34:05.819 --> 03:34:07.379
she knew a very different brain was

03:34:07.379 --> 03:34:07.860
behind them.

03:34:07.920 --> 03:34:10.139
What's your important message?

03:34:10.260 --> 03:34:14.219
Option one, make up a lie.

03:34:14.280 --> 03:34:16.379
Option two.

03:34:16.440 --> 03:34:17.340
Run for it.

03:34:17.399 --> 03:34:19.020
Option three.

03:34:19.079 --> 03:34:21.780
Tell a version of the truth.

03:34:21.840 --> 03:34:24.180
Glory took a deep breath.

03:34:24.239 --> 03:34:27.540
The dragonettes of the prophecy want to

03:34:27.540 --> 03:34:27.840
meet you.

03:34:27.959 --> 03:34:30.239
Blaze set up fast.

03:34:30.360 --> 03:34:32.579
The dragonettes?

03:34:32.639 --> 03:34:33.360
she cried.

03:34:33.420 --> 03:34:34.860
Glacier found them?

03:34:34.920 --> 03:34:38.760
They're looking for you, glory hedged.

03:34:38.879 --> 03:34:41.940
Well, bring them here, bring them here

03:34:41.940 --> 03:34:43.500
Blaise said.

03:34:43.559 --> 03:34:46.079
We can have a feast or a party.

03:34:46.139 --> 03:34:47.940
We haven't had one of those in forever

03:34:47.940 --> 03:34:51.360
because, you know, Queen Glacier

03:34:51.360 --> 03:34:53.340
disapproves of that kind of thing, but

03:34:53.340 --> 03:34:55.020
for something like this, I'm sure we

03:34:55.020 --> 03:34:55.260
could.

03:34:55.319 --> 03:34:58.139
Oh, we'll definitely need more dried

03:34:58.139 --> 03:34:58.739
lizards.

03:34:58.799 --> 03:35:00.840
We even have a pair of scavengers we

03:35:00.840 --> 03:35:01.260
could share.

03:35:01.319 --> 03:35:03.600
Maybe we should roast a camel.

03:35:03.659 --> 03:35:05.280
One of them's a mudwing, right?

03:35:05.340 --> 03:35:06.600
He had probably like that.

03:35:06.659 --> 03:35:09.000
We don't have anything for sea wings.

03:35:09.120 --> 03:35:12.299
Maybe Queen Glacier can send us some fish

03:35:12.299 --> 03:35:13.860
or a penguin.

03:35:13.920 --> 03:35:16.440
Or do you think she'd like a walrus?

03:35:16.500 --> 03:35:19.620
Wait, Glory said.

03:35:19.739 --> 03:35:23.040
As tempting as a feast sounded, and she

03:35:23.040 --> 03:35:25.260
knew clay would collapse with joy if you

03:35:25.260 --> 03:35:27.719
were offered a roasted camel, she wasn't

03:35:27.719 --> 03:35:29.100
about to walk her friends back into

03:35:29.100 --> 03:35:30.420
another queen's clutches.

03:35:30.479 --> 03:35:32.100
There's a catch.

03:35:32.159 --> 03:35:34.139
They're not willing to risk coming

03:35:34.139 --> 03:35:34.620
inside.

03:35:34.680 --> 03:35:37.020
They need you to go meet with them.

03:35:37.079 --> 03:35:40.020
Blaise flung herself down on the carpets

03:35:40.020 --> 03:35:41.579
again, looking petulant.

03:35:41.639 --> 03:35:44.280
But what about my party?

03:35:44.340 --> 03:35:47.520
she said, and I don't like going

03:35:47.520 --> 03:35:48.659
outside.

03:35:48.719 --> 03:35:52.620
It's too cold and it makes my scales all

03:35:52.620 --> 03:35:53.520
dry and ugly.

03:35:53.579 --> 03:35:57.299
You won't have to go far, Glory said.

03:35:57.360 --> 03:36:00.180
Jambu was twitching in a weird

03:36:00.180 --> 03:36:00.899
distracting way.

03:36:00.959 --> 03:36:02.520
She poked him with her tail.

03:36:02.639 --> 03:36:05.940
And isn't it worth it if the dragonettes

03:36:05.940 --> 03:36:07.379
end up choosing you to be the next

03:36:07.379 --> 03:36:08.520
sandwing queen?

03:36:08.579 --> 03:36:11.340
Blaise worried one of her claws between

03:36:11.340 --> 03:36:12.840
her teeth, thinking.

03:36:12.899 --> 03:36:16.200
Jamboo poked Glory back and cut his eyes

03:36:16.200 --> 03:36:17.520
toward the far corner of the room.

03:36:17.579 --> 03:36:20.579
Glory squinted, but all she could see was

03:36:20.579 --> 03:36:23.280
sand and stone walls and tapestry

03:36:23.280 --> 03:36:25.020
except...

03:36:25.020 --> 03:36:28.620
Then the sand moved, and for the briefest

03:36:28.620 --> 03:36:31.139
moment, a pair of eyes blinked out of the

03:36:31.139 --> 03:36:32.639
wall, then vanished again.

03:36:32.700 --> 03:36:35.100
Mangrove is here.

03:36:35.159 --> 03:36:39.420
I should wait for Queen Glacier, Blaise

03:36:39.420 --> 03:36:39.719
said.

03:36:39.780 --> 03:36:41.760
She wouldn't like my going off alone.

03:36:41.819 --> 03:36:43.440
I'm sure she wants to meet the

03:36:43.440 --> 03:36:44.280
dragonettes too.

03:36:44.340 --> 03:36:47.399
Glory already did not like the sound of

03:36:47.399 --> 03:36:48.420
the ice wing queen.

03:36:48.540 --> 03:36:51.000
She'd bet that Glacier was exactly the

03:36:51.000 --> 03:36:53.280
kind of dragon who would love to lock up

03:36:53.280 --> 03:36:54.360
5 Dragonettes.

03:36:54.420 --> 03:36:56.760
Actually, Glory said.

03:36:56.819 --> 03:36:58.920
She sent us to tell you that it's a good

03:36:58.920 --> 03:36:59.219
idea.

03:36:59.280 --> 03:37:01.500
You should go ahead and meet with them

03:37:01.500 --> 03:37:03.059
and you can tell her all about it

03:37:03.059 --> 03:37:03.540
afterward.

03:37:03.600 --> 03:37:05.520
There's nothing to fear from the

03:37:05.520 --> 03:37:06.299
dragonettes.

03:37:06.420 --> 03:37:09.360
And besides, Penguin and I will be there

03:37:09.360 --> 03:37:09.840
to protect you.

03:37:09.899 --> 03:37:13.020
Oh, said Blaze.

03:37:13.079 --> 03:37:15.239
That is reassuring.

03:37:15.299 --> 03:37:18.780
She gave Jambu a concerned look, and he

03:37:18.780 --> 03:37:20.700
managed to stop twitching for a moment.

03:37:20.760 --> 03:37:23.700
Do you think they'll really choose me?

03:37:23.760 --> 03:37:26.879
Blaise asked hopefully, turning back to

03:37:26.879 --> 03:37:27.239
glory.

03:37:27.299 --> 03:37:29.340
Oh, who am I kidding?

03:37:29.399 --> 03:37:31.260
I'm sure they will if they meet me.

03:37:31.319 --> 03:37:33.420
All right, I'll do it.

03:37:33.479 --> 03:37:35.340
Great.

03:37:35.399 --> 03:37:36.959
Jambu burst out.

03:37:37.020 --> 03:37:37.680
Let's go.

03:37:37.739 --> 03:37:42.059
Right now, Blaise said.

03:37:42.120 --> 03:37:43.020
Already?

03:37:43.079 --> 03:37:45.360
Glory wasn't sure if that was a good idea

03:37:45.360 --> 03:37:45.899
either.

03:37:45.959 --> 03:37:47.940
Her friends weren't exactly expecting

03:37:47.940 --> 03:37:50.459
Blaze to show up, and it would be hard to

03:37:50.459 --> 03:37:52.260
stay hidden from Deathbringer with a

03:37:52.260 --> 03:37:54.000
sandwing parading along beside them.

03:37:54.059 --> 03:37:57.420
Still, this was what they wanted, a

03:37:57.420 --> 03:37:59.459
chance to meet the 3rd queen candidate

03:37:59.459 --> 03:38:00.420
without risking imprisonment.

03:38:00.479 --> 03:38:04.440
Yep, right now, Glory said.

03:38:04.500 --> 03:38:07.260
She shot a significant look at Mangroves

03:38:07.260 --> 03:38:09.360
Corner, hoping he'd be smart enough to

03:38:09.360 --> 03:38:10.620
follow them out.

03:38:10.680 --> 03:38:12.360
Blaise picked up the mirror and checked

03:38:12.360 --> 03:38:14.459
her scales from several angles.

03:38:14.520 --> 03:38:16.920
Finally, she swept one of the camel hair

03:38:16.920 --> 03:38:18.959
blankets off the floor. and flung it

03:38:18.959 --> 03:38:20.879
around her shoulders like a cape, then

03:38:20.879 --> 03:38:22.139
led the way to the door.

03:38:22.200 --> 03:38:25.139
Jambu darted to the corner, grabbed a

03:38:25.139 --> 03:38:26.819
patch of sand, which turned out to be

03:38:26.819 --> 03:38:29.040
mangrove's elbow, and tugged him along

03:38:29.040 --> 03:38:29.819
after them.

03:38:29.879 --> 03:38:33.059
Blaise started to turn around, but Glory

03:38:33.059 --> 03:38:34.020
was there to distract her.

03:38:34.079 --> 03:38:37.739
Tell me about this tapestry. she said

03:38:37.739 --> 03:38:40.440
pointing to one with 2 large sand wing

03:38:40.440 --> 03:38:42.299
dragons flying across a blue background.

03:38:42.360 --> 03:38:44.399
I don't remember seeing it before.

03:38:44.459 --> 03:38:48.959
Oh, that one was my idea, Blaise said.

03:38:49.020 --> 03:38:52.139
It's the tragic romantic story of how my

03:38:52.139 --> 03:38:54.059
brother fell in love with a dragon he

03:38:54.059 --> 03:38:56.819
knew our mother would never approve of, so

03:38:56.819 --> 03:38:57.840
he kept her hidden from us.

03:38:57.899 --> 03:39:00.540
But then she ran off and broke his

03:39:00.540 --> 03:39:00.719
heart.

03:39:00.780 --> 03:39:04.680
Although we were all thinking, or did

03:39:04.680 --> 03:39:05.040
she?

03:39:05.100 --> 03:39:08.459
Of course, because it is so likely that

03:39:08.459 --> 03:39:10.500
mother just found out and had her killed

03:39:10.500 --> 03:39:12.180
which was something she would totally

03:39:12.180 --> 03:39:12.540
do.

03:39:12.600 --> 03:39:16.139
Blaise chattered on about the tapestry as

03:39:16.139 --> 03:39:17.459
she swept through the antechamber.

03:39:17.520 --> 03:39:20.219
Glory glanced sideways at the 2

03:39:20.219 --> 03:39:20.940
scavengers.

03:39:21.000 --> 03:39:23.520
The one with Silver's eyes had fallen

03:39:23.520 --> 03:39:25.379
asleep, and looked even more pathetic

03:39:25.379 --> 03:39:25.620
now.

03:39:25.680 --> 03:39:28.739
Blaze was several steps ahead, and not

03:39:28.739 --> 03:39:30.180
paying attention to anything but the

03:39:30.180 --> 03:39:32.700
sound of her own voice, Glory scooped up

03:39:32.700 --> 03:39:34.620
the sleeping scavenger, and slid it onto

03:39:34.620 --> 03:39:35.219
her back.

03:39:35.280 --> 03:39:37.799
It did not smell very pleasant at all.

03:39:37.920 --> 03:39:40.920
No wonder the rain wings preferred fruit

03:39:40.979 --> 03:39:43.020
bananas never smelled this bad.

03:39:43.079 --> 03:39:46.079
She folded her wings back over it, hiding

03:39:46.079 --> 03:39:46.920
it as well as she could.

03:39:46.979 --> 03:39:49.680
Jamboo saw what she was doing, and

03:39:49.680 --> 03:39:51.000
grabbed the other scavenger.

03:39:51.120 --> 03:39:53.700
Even though it was awake, it barely

03:39:53.700 --> 03:39:55.860
struggled as Jambu tucked it under one

03:39:55.860 --> 03:39:56.159
wing.

03:39:56.219 --> 03:39:59.280
They hurried after Blaze, following her

03:39:59.280 --> 03:40:00.540
back through the hallways to the main

03:40:00.540 --> 03:40:00.780
door.

03:40:00.840 --> 03:40:03.479
They went by a few sand wing guards.

03:40:03.540 --> 03:40:05.819
Blaise addressed them by name and they

03:40:05.819 --> 03:40:07.500
saluted, but she didn't tell them where

03:40:07.500 --> 03:40:09.299
she was going, and none of them looked

03:40:09.299 --> 03:40:10.920
suspicious, or even curious.

03:40:11.040 --> 03:40:13.680
None of them paid any attention to glory

03:40:13.680 --> 03:40:16.079
and Jambu, or to their poorly hidden

03:40:16.079 --> 03:40:17.340
stolen goods.

03:40:17.399 --> 03:40:19.860
Almost every sand wing they passed was

03:40:19.860 --> 03:40:20.819
injured in some way.

03:40:20.879 --> 03:40:24.120
Blaze was unscathed, but all of her

03:40:24.120 --> 03:40:26.340
soldiers had scars slicing across their

03:40:26.340 --> 03:40:29.399
scales, or missing talons, or wounded

03:40:29.399 --> 03:40:29.819
tails.

03:40:29.879 --> 03:40:31.799
Glory thought of Dune.

03:40:31.860 --> 03:40:34.079
Their sand winged guardian who had been

03:40:34.079 --> 03:40:35.879
so maimed by the war that he could never

03:40:35.879 --> 03:40:36.540
fly again.

03:40:36.600 --> 03:40:38.940
It had never occurred to her to ask him

03:40:38.940 --> 03:40:40.739
which side he had fought on before he

03:40:40.739 --> 03:40:41.819
joined the talons of peace.

03:40:41.879 --> 03:40:45.360
A blast of cold air smacked them in their

03:40:45.360 --> 03:40:47.100
snouts as they stepped outside.

03:40:47.159 --> 03:40:49.680
Blaise wrapped her blanket around herself

03:40:49.680 --> 03:40:52.500
more tightly, lifted her claws gingerly

03:40:52.500 --> 03:40:53.879
out of the snow, and whined.

03:40:53.940 --> 03:40:56.819
Are you sure the dragonettes won't come

03:40:56.819 --> 03:40:57.180
inside?

03:40:57.299 --> 03:41:00.180
Glory glanced back at Jambu.

03:41:00.239 --> 03:41:02.340
A shimmer in the air beside him was all

03:41:02.340 --> 03:41:04.319
she could see of mangrove, but she was

03:41:04.319 --> 03:41:05.219
relieved to know he was there.

03:41:05.280 --> 03:41:09.899
That way, Your Majesty, she said, nodding

03:41:09.899 --> 03:41:10.319
south.

03:41:10.379 --> 03:41:13.319
Blaise heaved a sigh, spread her wings

03:41:13.319 --> 03:41:14.760
and leaped into the air.

03:41:14.760 --> 03:41:17.280
Quickly, Glory twisted around, and

03:41:17.280 --> 03:41:19.020
dragged the scavenger off her back.

03:41:19.079 --> 03:41:21.479
She dumped it on the snowy ground, and it

03:41:21.479 --> 03:41:22.620
woke up with a yelp.

03:41:22.680 --> 03:41:24.719
Jambu dropped the other one next to it.

03:41:24.780 --> 03:41:26.459
Go on.

03:41:26.520 --> 03:41:29.159
Run for your scrawny lives, Glory said.

03:41:29.219 --> 03:41:31.620
Poking her scavenger with her snout.

03:41:31.680 --> 03:41:34.260
The scavenger scrambled backward, then

03:41:34.260 --> 03:41:35.940
grabbed the other one's arm and took off

03:41:35.940 --> 03:41:36.719
running through the snow.

03:41:36.780 --> 03:41:39.180
You think they'll be all right?

03:41:39.239 --> 03:41:42.120
Jambu asked, as he and Glory flew after

03:41:42.120 --> 03:41:42.719
Blaze.

03:41:42.780 --> 03:41:44.459
It's so cold out here.

03:41:44.579 --> 03:41:48.059
I bet that's what all those furs are for

03:41:48.059 --> 03:41:48.959
Glory said.

03:41:49.020 --> 03:41:51.780
Anyway, I'd rather freeze to death than

03:41:51.780 --> 03:41:53.340
be eaten by a sand wing.

03:41:53.399 --> 03:41:54.780
Blech!

03:41:54.840 --> 03:41:55.739
Jambu said.

03:41:55.799 --> 03:41:57.180
Meat eaters.

03:41:57.239 --> 03:41:57.780
I don't get it.

03:41:57.899 --> 03:42:00.420
They caught up to blaze and steered her

03:42:00.420 --> 03:42:01.680
toward the spot where their friends were

03:42:01.680 --> 03:42:01.920
waiting.

03:42:02.040 --> 03:42:03.479
As they flew.

03:42:03.540 --> 03:42:05.760
Glory scanned the ground below them for

03:42:05.760 --> 03:42:07.020
any sign of death bringer.

03:42:07.079 --> 03:42:10.379
The sun was high in the sky, although it

03:42:10.379 --> 03:42:12.540
felt like it was far away, behind a

03:42:12.540 --> 03:42:13.139
ceiling of ice.

03:42:13.200 --> 03:42:16.379
The frost glinted on the ground, and now

03:42:16.379 --> 03:42:18.120
Glory could see scrubby patches of brown

03:42:18.120 --> 03:42:20.219
grass and twisted shrubs.

03:42:20.280 --> 03:42:23.399
A gray wolf trotted across the rocks, but

03:42:23.399 --> 03:42:24.840
he was the only sign of life she saw.

03:42:24.899 --> 03:42:27.899
Wherever death bringer was for the day.

03:42:27.959 --> 03:42:29.219
He'd hidden himself well.

03:42:29.280 --> 03:42:31.920
Her friends had done their best too.

03:42:31.979 --> 03:42:34.620
Several large boulders had been shoved

03:42:34.620 --> 03:42:36.719
together below the cliff to look like a

03:42:36.719 --> 03:42:39.239
fallen rock pile, and glory nearly flew

03:42:39.239 --> 03:42:39.719
right over it.

03:42:39.780 --> 03:42:42.540
She circled back down to land with Jambu

03:42:42.540 --> 03:42:43.440
and Blaze behind her.

03:42:43.500 --> 03:42:45.299
Sonny was the 1st one out.

03:42:45.420 --> 03:42:46.860
You did it!

03:42:46.920 --> 03:42:47.879
she cried.

03:42:47.940 --> 03:42:49.260
You found...

03:42:49.799 --> 03:42:50.760
Him.

03:42:50.879 --> 03:42:52.319
Wait.

03:42:52.379 --> 03:42:54.299
She squinted at Blaze.

03:42:54.360 --> 03:42:55.920
Uh, glory?

03:42:55.979 --> 03:42:58.620
That's an actual sandwing.

03:42:58.680 --> 03:43:00.180
I know.

03:43:00.239 --> 03:43:00.899
Don't worry.

03:43:00.959 --> 03:43:04.079
Mangrove is here too, Glory said, flicking

03:43:04.079 --> 03:43:04.440
her tail.

03:43:04.500 --> 03:43:06.479
It's all right to show yourself now.

03:43:06.540 --> 03:43:09.899
The rain wing slowly materialized in a

03:43:09.899 --> 03:43:11.760
dull, green, unhappy color.

03:43:11.819 --> 03:43:14.399
He ducked his head and wouldn't meet her

03:43:14.399 --> 03:43:14.700
gaze.

03:43:14.760 --> 03:43:16.620
Yikes.

03:43:16.680 --> 03:43:19.020
Blaise yelped, leaping away from him.

03:43:19.079 --> 03:43:20.459
How did that happen?

03:43:20.520 --> 03:43:21.840
Where did he come from?

03:43:21.899 --> 03:43:24.059
She looked around wildly.

03:43:24.180 --> 03:43:26.219
As if she expected more dragons to

03:43:26.219 --> 03:43:27.899
suddenly poof out of the landscape.

03:43:27.959 --> 03:43:31.620
What do you know about rain wings, your

03:43:31.620 --> 03:43:32.219
majesty?

03:43:32.280 --> 03:43:33.659
Glory asked.

03:43:33.719 --> 03:43:36.239
She watched Blaze's face intently

03:43:36.239 --> 03:43:38.219
wondering if the sand wing knew anything

03:43:38.219 --> 03:43:40.559
about the missing rain wings, and if it

03:43:40.559 --> 03:43:41.579
would show in her expression.

03:43:41.639 --> 03:43:44.040
But the potential queen looked as

03:43:44.040 --> 03:43:45.000
mystified as before.

03:43:45.059 --> 03:43:48.360
I've heard they're pretty, she said

03:43:48.360 --> 03:43:50.639
tossing her head, but I've never seen

03:43:50.639 --> 03:43:50.940
one.

03:43:51.000 --> 03:43:55.440
You have now, Glory said.

03:43:55.500 --> 03:43:57.780
She held out her wings and let them shift

03:43:57.780 --> 03:44:00.239
to a light, non-threatening purple.

03:44:00.299 --> 03:44:03.120
At the same time, John Boo's scales

03:44:03.120 --> 03:44:05.700
shivered back to pink, although a paler

03:44:05.700 --> 03:44:06.840
chillier pink than usual.

03:44:06.899 --> 03:44:11.100
Ooh, Blaise said enviously.

03:44:11.159 --> 03:44:13.799
She reached out and took one of Jambu's

03:44:13.799 --> 03:44:16.020
wings in her talons, inspecting the

03:44:16.020 --> 03:44:18.299
scales as if he were an inanimate

03:44:18.299 --> 03:44:20.100
tapestry instead of a living dragon.

03:44:20.159 --> 03:44:22.920
Jambu blinked at glory, but didn't pull

03:44:22.920 --> 03:44:23.159
away.

03:44:23.219 --> 03:44:24.840
Wow.

03:44:24.899 --> 03:44:28.020
I wish I could do that, Blaise said.

03:44:28.079 --> 03:44:30.540
I'd be a different color every minute.

03:44:30.780 --> 03:44:33.600
She turned over the wing, so Jambu had to

03:44:33.600 --> 03:44:35.219
contort himself into an odd position.

03:44:35.280 --> 03:44:38.579
She didn't seem alarmed or angry to been

03:44:38.579 --> 03:44:40.260
tricked by their ice wing disguises.

03:44:40.319 --> 03:44:42.780
Glory wasn't sure whether to admire her

03:44:42.780 --> 03:44:45.719
bravery or roll her eyes ablaze's lack of

03:44:45.719 --> 03:44:46.200
caution.

03:44:46.260 --> 03:44:48.899
Do you think the change in camouflage

03:44:48.899 --> 03:44:51.120
would still work if I had someone make

03:44:51.120 --> 03:44:54.719
like, a coat of rain wing scales for me?

03:44:54.780 --> 03:44:56.159
Blaise asked.

03:44:56.219 --> 03:44:57.959
That could be pretty.

03:44:58.020 --> 03:45:01.319
She eyed Jamboo's scales like she was

03:45:01.319 --> 03:45:02.879
trying to figure out how to take them off

03:45:02.879 --> 03:45:03.180
him.

03:45:03.239 --> 03:45:05.940
Mangrove finally looked up and met

03:45:05.940 --> 03:45:07.680
Glory's eyes with a worried expression.

03:45:07.739 --> 03:45:11.579
By now, clay, tsunami, and Starflight had

03:45:11.579 --> 03:45:13.559
all emerged from the rock pile as well.

03:45:13.620 --> 03:45:16.500
Starflight pointed at Blaze, his eyes

03:45:16.500 --> 03:45:17.100
wide.

03:45:17.159 --> 03:45:19.139
Glory, he cried.

03:45:19.200 --> 03:45:24.780
This, this is, you found, I know, Glory

03:45:24.780 --> 03:45:25.020
said.

03:45:25.079 --> 03:45:28.200
Everyone, this is Blaze.

03:45:28.440 --> 03:45:32.639
Blaze, these are, she hated the phrase

03:45:32.639 --> 03:45:34.680
but it was what everyone called them.

03:45:34.739 --> 03:45:37.799
These are the dragonettes of destiny.

03:45:37.860 --> 03:45:42.239
Chapter 16.

03:45:42.479 --> 03:45:50.100
Oh, wow, it is so, so, so exciting to

03:45:50.100 --> 03:45:52.379
meet you, Blaise said brightly.

03:45:52.440 --> 03:45:53.940
Where's the Sky Wing?

03:45:54.000 --> 03:45:57.840
Glory managed to keep her face and scales

03:45:57.840 --> 03:45:59.280
from showing any reaction.

03:45:59.340 --> 03:46:01.319
The Sky Wing is dead.

03:46:01.379 --> 03:46:02.760
She wanted to yell.

03:46:02.819 --> 03:46:04.500
You're stuck with me instead.

03:46:04.620 --> 03:46:05.700
Deal with it.

03:46:05.760 --> 03:46:10.020
Glory is our 5th dragonette, Clay said.

03:46:10.079 --> 03:46:14.579
He nodded toward her Oh, Blaise said

03:46:14.579 --> 03:46:16.559
regarding glory with skepticism.

03:46:16.620 --> 03:46:18.420
But...

03:46:18.420 --> 03:46:21.059
She's a rain wing.

03:46:21.059 --> 03:46:24.540
And the prophecy calls for a sky wing

03:46:24.540 --> 03:46:25.799
doesn't it?

03:46:25.860 --> 03:46:28.379
What prophecy?

03:46:28.440 --> 03:46:29.879
John Boo asked.

03:46:29.940 --> 03:46:32.100
What's a dragonette of destiny?

03:46:32.159 --> 03:46:34.139
Are you serious?

03:46:34.200 --> 03:46:35.520
Glory said to him.

03:46:35.579 --> 03:46:37.920
Do you know anything about what's going

03:46:37.920 --> 03:46:38.459
on out here?

03:46:38.520 --> 03:46:41.819
It's far too complicated to explain?

03:46:41.940 --> 03:46:44.639
Starflight said, with a flick of his

03:46:44.639 --> 03:46:45.059
tail?

03:46:45.120 --> 03:46:47.760
There's a war going on.

03:46:47.819 --> 03:46:51.719
Clay said kindly, and a prophecy that

03:46:51.719 --> 03:46:55.079
says, 5 dragonettes will stop it, and

03:46:55.079 --> 03:46:55.739
that's us.

03:46:55.860 --> 03:46:58.920
Oh, John Boo said.

03:46:58.979 --> 03:47:00.000
Neat.

03:47:00.059 --> 03:47:05.100
Yes, far too complicated, tsunami said to

03:47:05.100 --> 03:47:05.700
Starflight.

03:47:05.760 --> 03:47:07.979
The black dragonette frowned at her.

03:47:08.040 --> 03:47:11.219
It's a little more specific than that.

03:47:11.280 --> 03:47:12.959
Blaise pointed out.

03:47:13.020 --> 03:47:15.659
It says 2 of the Sandwing sisters will

03:47:15.659 --> 03:47:16.139
die.

03:47:16.200 --> 03:47:19.200
Hopefully not me, and it says the 5

03:47:19.200 --> 03:47:22.319
dragonettes are a mud wing, a sea wing, a

03:47:22.319 --> 03:47:25.680
night wing, a sand wing, and a sky wing.

03:47:25.739 --> 03:47:29.159
We've got a rain wing instead, said

03:47:29.159 --> 03:47:31.260
tsunami, and we're fine with that.

03:47:31.319 --> 03:47:35.100
There's also me, Sonny piped up.

03:47:35.159 --> 03:47:36.959
I'm the sandwing, even though I'm weird

03:47:36.959 --> 03:47:37.319
looking.

03:47:37.379 --> 03:47:39.899
Blaze peered down at Sonny.

03:47:39.959 --> 03:47:43.559
Oh my gosh, you are weird looking.

03:47:43.620 --> 03:47:45.180
What's wrong with your tail?

03:47:45.239 --> 03:47:47.219
Why are your scales the wrong color?

03:47:47.280 --> 03:47:51.059
I don't know, Sonny said. spreading her

03:47:51.059 --> 03:47:53.639
wings, but I am still the sandwing in the

03:47:53.639 --> 03:47:54.180
prophecy.

03:47:54.239 --> 03:47:55.979
Are you sure?

03:47:56.040 --> 03:47:57.299
Blaze asked.

03:47:57.360 --> 03:47:59.819
She circled around Sonny, inspecting

03:47:59.819 --> 03:48:00.000
her.

03:48:00.059 --> 03:48:04.559
Wow, you all are not what I expected.

03:48:04.620 --> 03:48:07.680
For one thing, you're smaller, and I

03:48:07.680 --> 03:48:10.739
thought you'd be, I don't know, prettier.

03:48:10.799 --> 03:48:12.719
She stopped at glory.

03:48:12.780 --> 03:48:15.000
Explain the rain wing again.

03:48:15.059 --> 03:48:17.459
Also, the other 2 rain wings.

03:48:17.520 --> 03:48:18.540
Why are they here?

03:48:18.600 --> 03:48:22.920
You should go, Glory said to Jambu.

03:48:22.979 --> 03:48:25.379
She glanced at Mangrove. who was

03:48:25.379 --> 03:48:27.000
shivering and tugging his wings around

03:48:27.000 --> 03:48:27.479
himself.

03:48:27.479 --> 03:48:29.340
Take him home.

03:48:29.399 --> 03:48:31.200
You're both going to freeze if you stay

03:48:31.200 --> 03:48:31.920
out here any longer.

03:48:31.979 --> 03:48:35.760
I'm sorry, Mangrove said to her.

03:48:35.819 --> 03:48:37.920
I thought, I know.

03:48:38.040 --> 03:48:40.379
We'll find her, but not here.

03:48:40.440 --> 03:48:42.059
Glory pointed south.

03:48:42.120 --> 03:48:43.559
Both of you go.

03:48:43.620 --> 03:48:44.819
We'll catch up soon.

03:48:44.879 --> 03:48:47.040
Jambu didn't argue.

03:48:47.100 --> 03:48:49.620
He was also shivering from wing tip to

03:48:49.620 --> 03:48:51.600
wing tip, and he looked especially glad

03:48:51.600 --> 03:48:53.040
to have an excuse to get away from

03:48:53.040 --> 03:48:53.520
Blaze.

03:48:53.639 --> 03:48:55.799
Where are they going?

03:48:55.860 --> 03:48:58.860
Blaze asked, as the 2 rain wings lifted

03:48:58.860 --> 03:48:59.040
off.

03:48:59.100 --> 03:49:01.620
Isn't a rainforest kind of far from

03:49:01.620 --> 03:49:01.860
here?

03:49:01.920 --> 03:49:05.520
You know, we actually have some questions

03:49:05.520 --> 03:49:06.540
for you.

03:49:06.600 --> 03:49:08.520
Starflight interjected.

03:49:08.579 --> 03:49:11.459
Like, can you tell us why you should be

03:49:11.459 --> 03:49:12.899
queen instead of your sisters?

03:49:12.959 --> 03:49:17.219
Because I'm prettier and nicer and

03:49:17.219 --> 03:49:18.180
friendlier than they are.

03:49:18.239 --> 03:49:19.500
Blaise said.

03:49:19.559 --> 03:49:20.819
Obviously.

03:49:20.879 --> 03:49:23.639
She smiled and whirled in a circle

03:49:23.639 --> 03:49:25.739
holding the blanket out so it flapped

03:49:25.739 --> 03:49:26.459
like a flag.

03:49:26.520 --> 03:49:28.680
I mean, haven't you met them?

03:49:28.739 --> 03:49:30.479
Aren't they both awful?

03:49:30.540 --> 03:49:34.020
Yeah, Clay said ruefully.

03:49:34.079 --> 03:49:38.040
Well, Starflight said, then call the look

03:49:38.040 --> 03:49:39.120
on Tsunami's face.

03:49:39.239 --> 03:49:40.739
I guess they are.

03:49:40.799 --> 03:49:43.979
But could you survive a challenge?

03:49:44.040 --> 03:49:45.239
Tsunami asked.

03:49:45.299 --> 03:49:47.879
If you did become queen, how long would

03:49:47.879 --> 03:49:49.559
you last before someone tried to take the

03:49:49.559 --> 03:49:50.100
throne from you?

03:49:50.159 --> 03:49:52.079
Ouch!

03:49:52.200 --> 03:49:53.399
Blaise said.

03:49:53.459 --> 03:49:55.020
That's kind of rude, isn't it?

03:49:55.079 --> 03:49:58.020
I'm a much older dragon than you.

03:49:58.079 --> 03:50:01.020
I've been in a battle, more or less.

03:50:01.079 --> 03:50:03.360
She flicked her poisonous tail back and

03:50:03.360 --> 03:50:03.780
forth.

03:50:03.840 --> 03:50:06.059
And I do have this deadly tail.

03:50:06.180 --> 03:50:10.319
So do all sandwings, tsunami said

03:50:10.319 --> 03:50:11.159
unimpressed.

03:50:11.280 --> 03:50:14.879
Hey, how do you cure someone who's been

03:50:14.879 --> 03:50:16.739
scratched by Sandwing Tail?

03:50:16.739 --> 03:50:17.639
Sonny asked.

03:50:17.760 --> 03:50:20.639
I mean, say by accident.

03:50:20.700 --> 03:50:23.639
She did a good job of sounding like she

03:50:23.639 --> 03:50:26.159
was just curious, but Glory knew she was

03:50:26.159 --> 03:50:26.940
thinking of webs.

03:50:27.059 --> 03:50:30.420
There's this cactus juice that heals our

03:50:30.420 --> 03:50:32.940
poison, Blaise said, with a dismissive

03:50:32.940 --> 03:50:35.219
wave, grows all over the desert.

03:50:35.219 --> 03:50:39.120
Once again, Glory thought, she's not

03:50:39.120 --> 03:50:41.760
suspicious at all, or worried about

03:50:41.760 --> 03:50:43.739
keeping sand wings secrets, apparently.

03:50:43.799 --> 03:50:48.059
Anyway, Blaze insisted to tsunami.

03:50:48.120 --> 03:50:50.040
I'll have Queen Glacier to help me if

03:50:50.040 --> 03:50:50.940
anything goes wrong.

03:50:51.000 --> 03:50:52.739
Tsunami snorted.

03:50:52.799 --> 03:50:55.260
Glacier can't fight for you in a

03:50:55.260 --> 03:50:57.420
challenge for the throne, Starfight

03:50:57.420 --> 03:50:57.659
said.

03:50:57.780 --> 03:50:59.340
She can't?

03:50:59.459 --> 03:51:02.040
Blaise said, as if this was surprising

03:51:02.040 --> 03:51:02.520
news.

03:51:02.579 --> 03:51:03.659
Huh?

03:51:03.719 --> 03:51:05.940
Well, she can still come down and kill

03:51:05.940 --> 03:51:07.139
whoever's challenging me.

03:51:07.200 --> 03:51:08.219
She wouldn't mind.

03:51:08.280 --> 03:51:11.760
But that wouldn't be fair, Sonny said.

03:51:11.819 --> 03:51:14.040
That would violate all the challenge

03:51:14.040 --> 03:51:14.399
rules.

03:51:14.459 --> 03:51:15.959
Right, Starflight?

03:51:16.079 --> 03:51:18.959
He nodded, but Blaze was already talking

03:51:18.959 --> 03:51:19.440
over them.

03:51:19.500 --> 03:51:21.120
Who cares?

03:51:21.180 --> 03:51:22.139
She said.

03:51:22.200 --> 03:51:23.459
Don't even worry about it.

03:51:23.520 --> 03:51:26.100
I'll be such a great queen that no one

03:51:26.100 --> 03:51:27.299
will want to challenge me.

03:51:27.360 --> 03:51:29.700
There, that's an excellent plan.

03:51:29.760 --> 03:51:32.399
So how does this prophecy thing work?

03:51:32.459 --> 03:51:34.379
Are you guys going to kill my sisters?

03:51:34.440 --> 03:51:36.420
That would make my life much easier.

03:51:36.479 --> 03:51:38.879
Glory lashed your tail.

03:51:38.940 --> 03:51:40.319
She hadn't thought of that.

03:51:40.379 --> 03:51:42.360
Killing off burn and blister.

03:51:42.420 --> 03:51:44.579
It was certainly one way to fulfill the

03:51:44.579 --> 03:51:47.639
prophecy, if they could do it, which

03:51:47.639 --> 03:51:50.040
seemed unlikely, considering armies of

03:51:50.040 --> 03:51:51.959
dragons had been trying to kill all of

03:51:51.959 --> 03:51:53.819
the sisters for 18 years already.

03:51:53.879 --> 03:51:56.700
Sonny looked taken aback as well.

03:51:56.760 --> 03:51:59.159
We are not hired killers.

03:51:59.280 --> 03:52:00.360
She said.

03:52:00.420 --> 03:52:02.819
We were thinking we tell everyone who we

03:52:02.819 --> 03:52:05.159
choose, and they'll all listen to us and

03:52:05.159 --> 03:52:05.760
stop fighting.

03:52:05.879 --> 03:52:09.239
Oh, said Blaise.

03:52:09.299 --> 03:52:12.120
That sounds nice.

03:52:12.180 --> 03:52:15.479
What's the power of wings of fire?

03:52:15.540 --> 03:52:16.079
do I get that?

03:52:16.139 --> 03:52:19.920
These were all questions Glory had had

03:52:19.920 --> 03:52:22.260
about the prophecy her whole life, and

03:52:22.260 --> 03:52:24.239
yet she felt weirdly irritated to hear

03:52:24.239 --> 03:52:26.399
them coming from Blaze, as if the

03:52:26.399 --> 03:52:27.780
dragonettes had all the answers.

03:52:27.840 --> 03:52:30.959
At the same time, it occurred to her to

03:52:30.959 --> 03:52:33.959
wonder why Blister, the smartest sister

03:52:33.959 --> 03:52:35.700
hadn't asked these questions.

03:52:35.760 --> 03:52:38.100
Perhaps she knew the answers already.

03:52:38.100 --> 03:52:40.440
Or perhaps she wanted someone to think

03:52:40.440 --> 03:52:40.920
she did.

03:52:40.979 --> 03:52:45.000
We're figuring it out, Clay said.

03:52:45.120 --> 03:52:48.719
It's not like we chose this, Glory said.

03:52:48.780 --> 03:52:50.879
We were sort of shoved into this whole

03:52:50.879 --> 03:52:51.780
destiny thing.

03:52:51.840 --> 03:52:56.459
You weren't, Blaise said, her voice light

03:52:56.459 --> 03:52:57.659
and puzzled.

03:52:57.719 --> 03:52:59.639
There's no rain wing in the prophecy at

03:52:59.639 --> 03:52:59.819
all.

03:52:59.879 --> 03:53:01.500
Why don't you just go home?

03:53:01.559 --> 03:53:04.260
In the awkward pause that followed?

03:53:04.319 --> 03:53:06.840
Glory imagined all the other dragons

03:53:06.840 --> 03:53:08.340
having the exact same thought.

03:53:08.399 --> 03:53:11.879
Why didn't she just go home, where she

03:53:11.879 --> 03:53:14.040
could sit safely in the rainforest and

03:53:14.040 --> 03:53:16.860
stay out of the war and sleep all day?

03:53:16.920 --> 03:53:19.559
Maybe I should, she thought.

03:53:19.620 --> 03:53:21.959
I mean, is it worth it?

03:53:22.020 --> 03:53:24.659
Fighting for one of these 3 awful

03:53:24.659 --> 03:53:25.260
sandwings?

03:53:25.319 --> 03:53:28.379
Wouldn't it be easier to give in and

03:53:28.379 --> 03:53:30.299
accept that I'm meant to be a lazy rain

03:53:30.299 --> 03:53:30.780
wing?

03:53:30.840 --> 03:53:34.260
It was almost a relief to be distracted

03:53:34.260 --> 03:53:36.659
by a nightwing assassin landing on top of

03:53:36.659 --> 03:53:37.799
the rock pile beside them.

03:53:37.860 --> 03:53:40.319
The others whipped around to stare at him

03:53:40.319 --> 03:53:41.579
their tails lashing.

03:53:41.639 --> 03:53:43.860
Blaise squinted in a puzzled way.

03:53:43.920 --> 03:53:45.659
Oh, hello.

03:53:45.719 --> 03:53:47.219
Is he in the prophecy?

03:53:47.280 --> 03:53:48.059
She asked.

03:53:48.120 --> 03:53:49.020
He's cute.

03:53:49.079 --> 03:53:50.520
Cuter than this one.

03:53:50.639 --> 03:53:53.459
She waved a talon at Starflight's wounded

03:53:53.459 --> 03:53:53.879
expression.

03:53:53.940 --> 03:53:57.540
Why, hello everyone, said Deathbringer.

03:53:57.600 --> 03:53:59.100
Isn't this a coincidence?

03:53:59.159 --> 03:54:00.780
I was just talking about you all this

03:54:00.780 --> 03:54:00.959
morning.

03:54:01.079 --> 03:54:03.479
He turned to glory and tilted his head at

03:54:03.479 --> 03:54:04.319
her purple scales.

03:54:04.379 --> 03:54:06.360
Mystery dragon.

03:54:06.420 --> 03:54:07.260
Hmm.

03:54:07.319 --> 03:54:08.819
There's something different about you.

03:54:08.879 --> 03:54:10.860
Did you get your clothes trimmed?

03:54:10.979 --> 03:54:14.819
Very funny, she said, burying her teeth

03:54:14.819 --> 03:54:15.120
at him.

03:54:15.180 --> 03:54:17.340
You could have told me you were one of

03:54:17.340 --> 03:54:18.239
the dragonettes.

03:54:18.299 --> 03:54:19.559
Deathbringer said.

03:54:19.620 --> 03:54:21.239
I'd have asked for your autograph.

03:54:21.299 --> 03:54:25.260
I see now that you're uh, rain wings, so

03:54:25.260 --> 03:54:27.420
glory, right.

03:54:27.479 --> 03:54:30.659
That was creepy. that he knew her name

03:54:30.659 --> 03:54:33.059
even if she kind of liked the sound of

03:54:33.059 --> 03:54:35.340
him saying it, but it had to confirm her

03:54:35.340 --> 03:54:36.000
theory about him.

03:54:36.059 --> 03:54:38.340
Otherwise, why would he have bothered to

03:54:38.340 --> 03:54:38.639
learn it?

03:54:38.700 --> 03:54:42.180
Right, the one you were sent here to kill

03:54:42.180 --> 03:54:43.139
Glory said.

03:54:43.200 --> 03:54:45.420
Somehow, I think that would have started

03:54:45.420 --> 03:54:46.739
us off on the wrong talent.

03:54:46.860 --> 03:54:49.620
I'm not necessarily here to kill you.

03:54:49.739 --> 03:54:52.319
Deathbringer objected, and even if I were

03:54:52.319 --> 03:54:54.420
it seems like a much better opportunity

03:54:54.420 --> 03:54:55.799
to kill her.

03:54:55.860 --> 03:54:58.799
He suddenly opened his front talons

03:54:58.799 --> 03:55:00.840
revealing a pair of sharp, silvery

03:55:00.840 --> 03:55:01.260
disks.

03:55:01.319 --> 03:55:03.659
Their edges gleamed like knives as he

03:55:03.659 --> 03:55:06.299
flung them, one after the other, right at

03:55:06.299 --> 03:55:06.840
Blaze.

03:55:06.959 --> 03:55:09.780
The sand wings shrieked and stumbled back

03:55:09.780 --> 03:55:11.879
dropping the blanket, but she didn't move

03:55:11.879 --> 03:55:12.479
fast enough.

03:55:12.540 --> 03:55:15.899
One disc embedded itself in her long neck

03:55:15.899 --> 03:55:17.940
releasing a spurt of bright red blood

03:55:17.940 --> 03:55:20.340
that sprayed all over Sonny, who was

03:55:20.340 --> 03:55:21.059
standing next to her.

03:55:21.120 --> 03:55:23.879
The 2nd disk sliced through the edge of

03:55:23.879 --> 03:55:26.159
one of tsunami's wings as she leaped in

03:55:26.159 --> 03:55:27.420
front of Blaze.

03:55:27.479 --> 03:55:29.219
It ricocheted into one of the rocks with

03:55:29.219 --> 03:55:30.059
a ringing sound.

03:55:30.120 --> 03:55:32.819
Tsunami collapsed, clutching her injured

03:55:32.819 --> 03:55:33.180
wing.

03:55:33.239 --> 03:55:36.299
Sonny screamed, looked down at her blood

03:55:36.299 --> 03:55:38.940
spattered scales, and screamed again.

03:55:39.000 --> 03:55:41.520
Clay jumped forward and clapped both his

03:55:41.520 --> 03:55:43.440
talons over the cut in Blaze's neck.

03:55:43.500 --> 03:55:45.120
Throw me the blanket.

03:55:45.239 --> 03:55:46.920
He yelled to Starflight.

03:55:46.979 --> 03:55:48.719
The night wing looked back at him in

03:55:48.719 --> 03:55:49.680
froze in terror.

03:55:49.739 --> 03:55:52.260
Glory grabbed the blanket and flung it to

03:55:52.260 --> 03:55:54.000
Clay, who started to wrap it around

03:55:54.000 --> 03:55:56.819
Blaze's neck, but then Deathbringer was

03:55:56.819 --> 03:55:59.219
there, landing on Blaze's back, and

03:55:59.219 --> 03:56:01.559
tossing Clay aside as if the hefty mud

03:56:01.559 --> 03:56:03.360
wing weighed no more than a salamander.

03:56:03.420 --> 03:56:05.819
Two more silver disks appeared in

03:56:05.819 --> 03:56:06.840
Deathbringer's talons.

03:56:06.899 --> 03:56:09.780
Glory leaped at the assassin, and knocked

03:56:09.780 --> 03:56:10.799
him backward off blaze.

03:56:10.860 --> 03:56:13.620
They rolled on the frozen ground, his

03:56:13.620 --> 03:56:15.180
black wings tangling with hers.

03:56:15.239 --> 03:56:18.540
He was very strong, and astonishingly

03:56:18.540 --> 03:56:18.899
fast.

03:56:18.959 --> 03:56:21.600
A black pouch around his neck thumped

03:56:21.600 --> 03:56:24.180
against her chest, and she realized that

03:56:24.180 --> 03:56:25.799
must be where he kept his weapons.

03:56:25.860 --> 03:56:29.040
She seized it between her claws, just as

03:56:29.040 --> 03:56:31.079
he pinned her down, his talons on her

03:56:31.079 --> 03:56:31.319
wings.

03:56:31.440 --> 03:56:34.799
Killing Blaze was your assignment, she

03:56:34.799 --> 03:56:35.100
said.

03:56:35.159 --> 03:56:38.520
No, but I like to work outside the box, he

03:56:38.520 --> 03:56:38.940
answered.

03:56:39.000 --> 03:56:41.579
And if I kill her, I figure it'll get me

03:56:41.579 --> 03:56:42.959
out of the trouble I'm in for not killing

03:56:42.959 --> 03:56:43.139
you.

03:56:43.200 --> 03:56:47.639
You can try to kill me, she growled.

03:56:47.700 --> 03:56:49.559
But I doubt it'll be as easy as you

03:56:49.559 --> 03:56:49.860
think.

03:56:49.920 --> 03:56:52.860
She ripped open the pouch and caught a

03:56:52.860 --> 03:56:54.719
few of the silver disks as they spilled

03:56:54.719 --> 03:56:55.799
into her talons.

03:56:55.860 --> 03:56:57.659
Several others clattered to the ground

03:56:57.659 --> 03:56:59.940
around her, but one was all she needed.

03:57:00.000 --> 03:57:02.760
She pressed it to Deathbringer's neck

03:57:02.760 --> 03:57:03.719
before he could jump away.

03:57:03.780 --> 03:57:06.840
You missed the biggest artery on Blaze's

03:57:06.840 --> 03:57:07.799
neck, she said.

03:57:07.860 --> 03:57:11.100
If I remember my dragon anatomy correctly

03:57:11.159 --> 03:57:12.180
right here.

03:57:12.239 --> 03:57:15.719
She applied a little more pressure, and

03:57:15.719 --> 03:57:18.299
Deathbringer flinched as the silver edge

03:57:18.299 --> 03:57:19.979
left a thin trail of blood on his

03:57:19.979 --> 03:57:20.340
scales.

03:57:20.399 --> 03:57:22.799
He lifted his talons from her shoulders

03:57:22.799 --> 03:57:24.840
and carefully backed off her.

03:57:24.899 --> 03:57:28.379
Glory stood up, keeping the disc poised

03:57:28.379 --> 03:57:30.299
at his neck, and glanced over

03:57:30.299 --> 03:57:31.440
Deathbringer's shoulder.

03:57:31.500 --> 03:57:34.139
Clay had the blanket tied firmly around

03:57:34.139 --> 03:57:36.180
Blaze's neck, but blood was already

03:57:36.180 --> 03:57:38.100
seeping through the camel hair fabric.

03:57:38.159 --> 03:57:40.440
The sand wing queen leaned against him

03:57:40.440 --> 03:57:41.520
looking faint.

03:57:41.579 --> 03:57:44.340
Tsunami had also climbed to her feet, and

03:57:44.340 --> 03:57:46.020
was examining the cut on her own wing

03:57:46.020 --> 03:57:46.680
with a scowl.

03:57:46.739 --> 03:57:49.500
Starflight hadn't moved.

03:57:49.559 --> 03:57:51.180
Sunny was still staring at the blood all

03:57:51.180 --> 03:57:52.559
over her talons and wings.

03:57:52.620 --> 03:57:55.500
I did mention the pot about how I don't

03:57:55.500 --> 03:57:56.819
actually want to kill you, right?

03:57:56.879 --> 03:57:59.819
Deathbringer said, eye and glory, and the

03:57:59.819 --> 03:58:01.440
disks she held with a faintly amused

03:58:01.440 --> 03:58:01.860
expression.

03:58:01.920 --> 03:58:04.200
I'm pretty sure I snuck that in there.

03:58:04.260 --> 03:58:07.440
Oh, all right, Glory said.

03:58:07.500 --> 03:58:09.479
I'll just trust you then, shall I?

03:58:09.540 --> 03:58:11.579
If you let me kill her.

03:58:11.639 --> 03:58:13.860
I can let you all go, he said.

03:58:13.979 --> 03:58:15.840
I should give you a fair head start

03:58:15.840 --> 03:58:17.579
before they send someone else after you

03:58:17.579 --> 03:58:19.440
especially since no one knows where

03:58:19.440 --> 03:58:20.219
you'll go next.

03:58:20.280 --> 03:58:22.559
All of us, Glory said.

03:58:22.620 --> 03:58:24.420
You're here to kill all of us?

03:58:24.540 --> 03:58:28.200
No, he said, still smiling.

03:58:28.260 --> 03:58:29.520
Just a couple of you.

03:58:29.639 --> 03:58:33.000
Well, that makes me feel better, she

03:58:33.000 --> 03:58:33.299
said.

03:58:33.360 --> 03:58:35.819
Stop looking so pleased with yourself.

03:58:35.879 --> 03:58:39.000
She poked his neck, and he tried, and

03:58:39.000 --> 03:58:40.200
failed to look serious.

03:58:40.260 --> 03:58:42.600
Which couple of us?

03:58:42.600 --> 03:58:43.739
Sonny asked.

03:58:43.860 --> 03:58:45.000
Who's they?

03:58:45.059 --> 03:58:47.760
Tsunami demanded at the same time, who

03:58:47.760 --> 03:58:48.239
sent you?

03:58:48.299 --> 03:58:52.379
The night wings, Starflight said

03:58:52.379 --> 03:58:52.979
bleakly.

03:58:53.040 --> 03:58:55.139
That's it, isn't it?

03:58:55.200 --> 03:58:57.120
Because of what happened in the kingdom

03:58:57.120 --> 03:58:59.100
of the sea, because we didn't choose

03:58:59.100 --> 03:58:59.760
blister.

03:58:59.819 --> 03:59:02.940
The Night Wings wanted us to choose

03:59:02.940 --> 03:59:03.659
blister?

03:59:03.719 --> 03:59:04.799
Glory said.

03:59:04.860 --> 03:59:07.440
A tsunami world to stare at Starflight.

03:59:07.500 --> 03:59:08.819
Why would they care?

03:59:08.879 --> 03:59:12.299
I don't know, Starflight said.

03:59:12.360 --> 03:59:15.420
That's all Moro Seer told me, that we had

03:59:15.420 --> 03:59:17.819
to pig blister, and I should convince you

03:59:17.819 --> 03:59:18.540
all to agree to it.

03:59:18.600 --> 03:59:21.540
That's so mean.

03:59:21.600 --> 03:59:24.959
Blaise interjected, opening her eyes and

03:59:24.959 --> 03:59:25.920
looking a bit more alive.

03:59:25.979 --> 03:59:28.559
Why should the Nightwings get to decide?

03:59:28.620 --> 03:59:30.120
They've never even met me.

03:59:30.180 --> 03:59:31.500
I'm awesome.

03:59:31.559 --> 03:59:36.479
Oh, that's why you were acting so weird

03:59:36.479 --> 03:59:39.659
around blister, Clay said to Starflight.

03:59:39.719 --> 03:59:42.540
Deathbringer suddenly lunged forward

03:59:42.540 --> 03:59:45.420
faster than a striking snake, and seized

03:59:45.420 --> 03:59:48.120
Glory's front talons, she thwacked his

03:59:48.120 --> 03:59:49.620
head as hard as she could with her wings

03:59:49.620 --> 03:59:51.600
and kicked at his underscales with her

03:59:51.600 --> 03:59:52.379
back claws.

03:59:52.440 --> 03:59:55.139
Now, stop, he cried.

03:59:55.200 --> 03:59:56.760
It's like you want me to kill you.

03:59:56.879 --> 03:59:59.579
Just then the sound of wing beats reached

03:59:59.579 --> 04:00:00.180
their ears.

04:00:00.239 --> 04:00:03.180
Glory and Deathbringer both froze and

04:00:03.180 --> 04:00:04.020
looked up at the sky.

04:00:04.139 --> 04:00:06.239
Queen Glacier.

04:00:06.360 --> 04:00:09.479
Blaze breathed with a relieved sigh.

04:00:09.540 --> 04:00:11.760
I knew she would save me.

04:00:11.819 --> 04:00:14.639
The glitter of diamond wings approaching

04:00:14.639 --> 04:00:16.079
from the north was unmistakable.

04:00:16.139 --> 04:00:18.600
The ice wings were on their way.

04:00:18.659 --> 04:00:23.340
Chapter 17.

04:00:23.579 --> 04:00:27.420
Given a choice between the ice wing queen

04:00:27.420 --> 04:00:29.879
and a night wing assassin, Glory wasn't

04:00:29.879 --> 04:00:31.739
sure she'd actually prefer the ice wing

04:00:31.739 --> 04:00:32.159
queen.

04:00:32.219 --> 04:00:35.159
Imprisonment in the Sky Kingdom, and in

04:00:35.159 --> 04:00:37.559
Queen Coral's Summer Palace, had been bad

04:00:37.559 --> 04:00:38.459
enough.

04:00:38.520 --> 04:00:40.680
If they wound up in glaciers dungeon

04:00:40.680 --> 04:00:42.600
they'd probably all freeze to death by

04:00:42.600 --> 04:00:43.079
the end of the day.

04:00:43.139 --> 04:00:47.760
Let me go right now, she said to

04:00:47.760 --> 04:00:48.360
Deathbringer.

04:00:48.420 --> 04:00:51.180
To her immense surprise, he did.

04:00:51.239 --> 04:00:54.360
He stepped back, his talons raised to

04:00:54.360 --> 04:00:56.940
look harmless, and actually dared to

04:00:56.940 --> 04:00:57.840
smile at her.

04:00:57.899 --> 04:00:59.579
Time to go.

04:00:59.700 --> 04:01:01.500
Tsunami ordered.

04:01:01.559 --> 04:01:02.639
They'll be here in about 2 minutes.

04:01:02.700 --> 04:01:04.500
Oh, no.

04:01:04.620 --> 04:01:07.020
Wait, Blaise said.

04:01:07.079 --> 04:01:09.299
She spread her wings and waved at the

04:01:09.299 --> 04:01:10.559
incoming ice dragons.

04:01:10.620 --> 04:01:12.360
You should meet Glacier.

04:01:12.420 --> 04:01:13.260
You'll like her.

04:01:13.379 --> 04:01:16.139
We can't leave Blaze here with him.

04:01:16.200 --> 04:01:18.719
Clay said, pointing to Death Bringer.

04:01:18.780 --> 04:01:21.360
That's true, Glory said.

04:01:21.420 --> 04:01:23.520
She narrowed her eyes at the assassin.

04:01:23.579 --> 04:01:26.639
You have 10 seconds to take off, or we'll

04:01:26.639 --> 04:01:28.379
knock you out and leave you for the ice

04:01:28.379 --> 04:01:29.100
wings to deal with.

04:01:29.159 --> 04:01:31.559
Shouldn't we do that anyway?

04:01:31.620 --> 04:01:32.879
Blaze asked.

04:01:32.940 --> 04:01:35.639
I mean, he did try to kill me.

04:01:35.700 --> 04:01:37.979
Queen Glacier will be so mad.

04:01:38.040 --> 04:01:41.459
This one time, a Skywing flew all the way

04:01:41.459 --> 04:01:43.799
here and nearly got me, while I was

04:01:43.799 --> 04:01:45.840
getting some sun, and Glacier literally

04:01:45.840 --> 04:01:48.120
ripped off his wings before she killed

04:01:48.120 --> 04:01:48.420
him.

04:01:48.479 --> 04:01:52.020
It was really gross, but also kind of

04:01:52.020 --> 04:01:54.180
sweet, you know, like she really cares

04:01:54.180 --> 04:01:54.600
about me.

04:01:54.659 --> 04:01:58.319
Or she really cares about all the land

04:01:58.319 --> 04:02:01.200
she'll get if you become queen, Glory

04:02:01.200 --> 04:02:01.500
thought.

04:02:01.559 --> 04:02:03.600
Sonny looked faintly sick.

04:02:03.659 --> 04:02:07.139
Guess what, I don't want to see. she

04:02:07.139 --> 04:02:07.379
said.

04:02:07.440 --> 04:02:09.899
One dragon ripping the wings off another

04:02:09.899 --> 04:02:10.620
dragon.

04:02:10.680 --> 04:02:11.520
Not ever.

04:02:11.579 --> 04:02:12.059
Thanks.

04:02:12.120 --> 04:02:16.379
All right, I'm convinced, Deathbringer

04:02:16.379 --> 04:02:17.579
said, backing away.

04:02:17.639 --> 04:02:19.620
But you really should have let me kill

04:02:19.620 --> 04:02:19.799
her.

04:02:19.860 --> 04:02:22.440
He paused with his wings spread and gave

04:02:22.440 --> 04:02:23.579
Glory a cheeky grin.

04:02:23.639 --> 04:02:26.100
So, when can I see you again?

04:02:26.159 --> 04:02:29.879
Get out of here, Glory said.

04:02:29.940 --> 04:02:32.340
Glad that Jambu wasn't there to loudly

04:02:32.340 --> 04:02:34.020
interpret the colors that were trying to

04:02:34.020 --> 04:02:34.979
shift through her scales.

04:02:35.040 --> 04:02:37.559
Death Bringer bolted into the sky.

04:02:37.620 --> 04:02:39.840
Blaise followed him with her eyes for a

04:02:39.840 --> 04:02:42.059
moment, then seemed to lose interest.

04:02:42.120 --> 04:02:44.459
She turned to Clay and tsunami with a

04:02:44.459 --> 04:02:45.180
winning smile.

04:02:45.239 --> 04:02:48.120
Please don't go, Blaise said.

04:02:48.180 --> 04:02:50.459
Queen Glacier will be so grateful to you

04:02:50.459 --> 04:02:51.299
for saving my life.

04:02:51.360 --> 04:02:53.940
Now we can have that party I mentioned.

04:02:54.000 --> 04:02:56.879
Sorry, tsunami said.

04:02:56.940 --> 04:02:58.620
We are not sticking around to become

04:02:58.620 --> 04:02:59.579
captives again.

04:02:59.639 --> 04:03:04.500
We'll uh, we'll be in touch, Clay said.

04:03:04.559 --> 04:03:07.079
Keep applying pressure to this until a

04:03:07.079 --> 04:03:08.159
healer can look at it.

04:03:08.219 --> 04:03:11.159
Blaise rallied herself to stand upright

04:03:11.159 --> 04:03:12.899
and give them all a little nod.

04:03:12.959 --> 04:03:16.319
It was delightful to meet you, she said

04:03:16.319 --> 04:03:19.319
even if you are missing a sky wing, and

04:03:19.319 --> 04:03:20.579
some of you are a little funny looking.

04:03:20.700 --> 04:03:23.579
I promise you'll be pleased if you choose

04:03:23.579 --> 04:03:23.819
me.

04:03:23.879 --> 04:03:26.879
She waved a wing weekly in the direction

04:03:26.879 --> 04:03:27.600
of the desert.

04:03:27.659 --> 04:03:30.360
I can offer you whatever land you want.

04:03:30.420 --> 04:03:32.459
You could each have land enough for a

04:03:32.459 --> 04:03:33.120
palace of your own.

04:03:33.180 --> 04:03:36.360
Quit giving away your territory.

04:03:36.479 --> 04:03:37.620
Glory snapped.

04:03:37.680 --> 04:03:40.319
I know the kingdom of sand is big, but

04:03:40.319 --> 04:03:42.239
life in the desert is tough, and your

04:03:42.239 --> 04:03:44.819
subjects need every oasis, and if you do

04:03:44.819 --> 04:03:47.040
become queen, you'll need to rebuild your

04:03:47.040 --> 04:03:47.819
treasury somehow.

04:03:47.879 --> 04:03:48.959
So remember that too.

04:03:49.020 --> 04:03:52.920
Queenly advice from a rain wing.

04:03:53.040 --> 04:03:55.979
Blaise giggled, as if the pain in her

04:03:55.979 --> 04:03:57.239
neck was making her loopy.

04:03:57.299 --> 04:03:59.040
No, I have heard everything.

04:03:59.100 --> 04:04:02.399
Glory frowned at her, but the sand wing

04:04:02.399 --> 04:04:03.180
didn't seem to notice.

04:04:03.239 --> 04:04:04.680
Come on.

04:04:04.739 --> 04:04:07.860
Clay said gently to Sonny, urging her

04:04:07.860 --> 04:04:08.040
up.

04:04:08.100 --> 04:04:10.920
Sonny held her blood stained talons out

04:04:10.920 --> 04:04:13.020
and Starflight jumped forward to take

04:04:13.020 --> 04:04:13.799
them between his.

04:04:13.920 --> 04:04:16.200
You'll feel better once we're in the

04:04:16.200 --> 04:04:16.500
desert.

04:04:16.559 --> 04:04:17.579
He said.

04:04:17.639 --> 04:04:19.620
Don't let them follow us.

04:04:19.680 --> 04:04:22.440
Tsunami said to Blaze as the others took

04:04:22.440 --> 04:04:22.680
off.

04:04:22.739 --> 04:04:26.760
They'll be too busy rescuing me, Blaise

04:04:26.760 --> 04:04:28.920
said, lying down in a graceful

04:04:28.920 --> 04:04:29.940
melodramatic pose.

04:04:30.000 --> 04:04:33.600
Glory and tsunami exchanged eye rolls and

04:04:33.600 --> 04:04:34.379
lifted into the air.

04:04:34.440 --> 04:04:36.719
The ice wings were almost upon them.

04:04:36.780 --> 04:04:38.760
They had to fly as fast as they could.

04:04:38.819 --> 04:04:41.459
Tsunami faltered for a moment as she went

04:04:41.459 --> 04:04:41.879
aloft.

04:04:41.940 --> 04:04:43.559
Does it hurt?

04:04:43.620 --> 04:04:45.899
Glory asked, flying close to her.

04:04:45.959 --> 04:04:48.059
Will you make it to the passage?

04:04:48.120 --> 04:04:51.299
I'll be fine, tsunami said, through

04:04:51.299 --> 04:04:52.139
gridded teeth.

04:04:52.200 --> 04:04:53.340
It's just a cut.

04:04:53.399 --> 04:04:57.239
After a moment she added, But yes, it

04:04:57.239 --> 04:04:57.540
hurts.

04:04:57.600 --> 04:05:00.540
Gloria stayed alongside her as they flew

04:05:00.540 --> 04:05:02.340
through the cold, pale blue sky.

04:05:02.399 --> 04:05:05.340
She glanced back several times, but saw

04:05:05.340 --> 04:05:07.260
no sign of ice wings in pursuit.

04:05:07.319 --> 04:05:09.239
No sign of a night wing trailing them

04:05:09.239 --> 04:05:09.479
either.

04:05:09.540 --> 04:05:13.079
Glory, tsunami said after a bit.

04:05:13.139 --> 04:05:14.940
Can I ask you something?

04:05:15.000 --> 04:05:17.159
Why didn't you use your venom on that

04:05:17.159 --> 04:05:17.700
assassin?

04:05:17.760 --> 04:05:20.819
Glory felt a tinge of embarrassed pink

04:05:20.819 --> 04:05:23.280
creeping along her scales and fought it

04:05:23.280 --> 04:05:25.079
back until she matched the sky.

04:05:25.139 --> 04:05:28.799
That wasn't an invitation to disappear

04:05:28.799 --> 04:05:30.120
tsunami said.

04:05:30.180 --> 04:05:32.879
I just didn't feel like killing him.

04:05:32.940 --> 04:05:34.319
Glory answered.

04:05:34.379 --> 04:05:36.420
I don't want to kill any more than I have

04:05:36.420 --> 04:05:36.659
to.

04:05:36.719 --> 04:05:40.440
But he is literally on a mission to kill

04:05:40.440 --> 04:05:42.360
you, tsunami said.

04:05:42.420 --> 04:05:44.760
Killing him 1st is kind of the definition

04:05:44.760 --> 04:05:45.899
of self-defense.

04:05:45.959 --> 04:05:48.719
Maybe, Glory said.

04:05:48.780 --> 04:05:52.020
I just, It didn't feel like he was trying

04:05:52.020 --> 04:05:52.559
to kill me.

04:05:52.680 --> 04:05:54.840
Tsunami shook her head.

04:05:54.899 --> 04:05:58.200
All right, but so you know, from where I

04:05:58.200 --> 04:06:01.020
was standing, it certainly looked like

04:06:01.020 --> 04:06:01.139
it.

04:06:01.200 --> 04:06:04.020
Whatever, Glory said.

04:06:04.079 --> 04:06:05.879
We'll probably never see him again.

04:06:05.940 --> 04:06:08.520
The real question is why the night wings

04:06:08.520 --> 04:06:09.420
are getting so involved.

04:06:09.479 --> 04:06:11.639
First, they try to get us to choose

04:06:11.639 --> 04:06:14.340
blister, and then they send an assassin

04:06:14.340 --> 04:06:14.760
to kill us.

04:06:14.819 --> 04:06:17.100
Don't they want their prophecy to come

04:06:17.100 --> 04:06:17.340
true?

04:06:17.399 --> 04:06:20.219
Maybe, like everyone else?

04:06:20.280 --> 04:06:22.440
They only wanted to come true their way.

04:06:22.500 --> 04:06:24.299
Tsunami grumbled.

04:06:24.360 --> 04:06:26.219
What's their way?

04:06:26.340 --> 04:06:27.780
Glory wondered.

04:06:27.840 --> 04:06:29.879
What difference does it make to them who

04:06:29.879 --> 04:06:31.440
the queen of the sand wings is?

04:06:31.500 --> 04:06:35.219
I have no idea, tsunami admitted.

04:06:35.280 --> 04:06:37.620
Well, if they have something to say about

04:06:37.620 --> 04:06:40.440
this war, Glory said, they can come on

04:06:40.440 --> 04:06:42.840
out and fight it, instead of hiding and

04:06:42.840 --> 04:06:44.399
making vague predictions every few

04:06:44.399 --> 04:06:44.700
years.

04:06:44.760 --> 04:06:48.840
And sending assassins, tsunami added

04:06:48.840 --> 04:06:49.860
cowards.

04:06:49.920 --> 04:06:53.100
It wasn't often that tsunami and glory

04:06:53.100 --> 04:06:54.239
agreed about something.

04:06:54.299 --> 04:06:56.040
Glory couldn't remember the last time

04:06:56.040 --> 04:06:57.659
they'd had a conversation this long

04:06:57.659 --> 04:06:58.620
without arguing.

04:06:58.680 --> 04:07:01.139
It wasn't that she disliked tsunami.

04:07:01.200 --> 04:07:02.879
She didn't even really mind her

04:07:02.879 --> 04:07:03.540
bossiness.

04:07:03.600 --> 04:07:06.600
But she did feel like someone needed to

04:07:06.600 --> 04:07:08.700
talk back whenever tsunami started acting

04:07:08.700 --> 04:07:10.920
like the boss of everyone, just to make

04:07:10.920 --> 04:07:12.719
sure tsunami's head didn't get too big

04:07:12.719 --> 04:07:13.979
for the rest of her.

04:07:14.040 --> 04:07:16.680
On the other talent, tsunami had been

04:07:16.680 --> 04:07:18.239
much better since their escape from the

04:07:18.239 --> 04:07:18.840
kingdom of the sea.

04:07:18.899 --> 04:07:21.180
Glory could see that she was trying to

04:07:21.180 --> 04:07:23.340
include the others more, instead of just

04:07:23.340 --> 04:07:24.540
telling them all what to do.

04:07:24.600 --> 04:07:27.059
And tsunami never talked about her future

04:07:27.059 --> 04:07:28.260
as a queen anymore.

04:07:28.319 --> 04:07:30.420
When it used to be her favorite topic of

04:07:30.420 --> 04:07:31.020
conversation.

04:07:31.079 --> 04:07:33.959
Maybe she'd meant it when she said, she

04:07:33.959 --> 04:07:35.520
didn't belong in the kingdom of the sea.

04:07:35.579 --> 04:07:38.100
Maybe she'd really given up on ruling her

04:07:38.100 --> 04:07:38.760
tribe one day.

04:07:38.819 --> 04:07:42.420
It was dark by the time they spotted

04:07:42.420 --> 04:07:44.760
Burns' stronghold in the distance, and

04:07:44.760 --> 04:07:46.440
the semicircle of cacti they were looking

04:07:46.440 --> 04:07:46.680
for.

04:07:46.739 --> 04:07:49.379
Glory and tsunami spiraled down to the

04:07:49.379 --> 04:07:51.959
ground and found Starflight, frantically

04:07:51.959 --> 04:07:52.799
digging in the sand.

04:07:52.860 --> 04:07:55.559
The hole is gone, he cried.

04:07:55.620 --> 04:07:56.579
It's disappeared.

04:07:56.700 --> 04:07:59.159
A bolt of green panic shot through

04:07:59.159 --> 04:08:01.799
glory's scales, trapped between the ice

04:08:01.799 --> 04:08:04.260
wings and burn with an assassin out

04:08:04.260 --> 04:08:06.239
hunting them, was not how she wanted to

04:08:06.239 --> 04:08:06.719
spend the night.

04:08:06.840 --> 04:08:10.440
It's not gone, Clay said firmly.

04:08:10.500 --> 04:08:11.639
Let me dig.

04:08:11.700 --> 04:08:14.879
He muscled Starfly aside, looked up at

04:08:14.879 --> 04:08:16.920
the cacti and started to dig in a

04:08:16.920 --> 04:08:17.639
slightly different spot.

04:08:17.700 --> 04:08:19.680
What are you doing?

04:08:19.739 --> 04:08:22.319
Tsunami called to Sonny, who looked like

04:08:22.319 --> 04:08:24.239
she was trying to tango with a cactus up

04:08:24.239 --> 04:08:24.540
the hill.

04:08:24.600 --> 04:08:28.620
You heard what Blaise said, Sonny

04:08:28.620 --> 04:08:29.040
panted.

04:08:29.100 --> 04:08:32.219
If we take this back, maybe we can heal

04:08:32.219 --> 04:08:33.899
webs out.

04:08:34.020 --> 04:08:37.020
She flinched back from the thorns, shaking

04:08:37.020 --> 04:08:38.219
her front talons.

04:08:38.520 --> 04:08:41.459
We don't need the whole cactus, tsunami

04:08:41.459 --> 04:08:42.659
said amused.

04:08:42.719 --> 04:08:44.639
Break off one of those arm things and

04:08:44.639 --> 04:08:45.360
bring that instead.

04:08:45.420 --> 04:08:48.360
That is what I'm trying to do.

04:08:48.479 --> 04:08:50.639
Sonny said irately.

04:08:50.700 --> 04:08:53.100
Tsunami floundered up the sandy rise to

04:08:53.100 --> 04:08:53.579
help her.

04:08:53.639 --> 04:08:56.459
Glory noticed that Sonny had used sand to

04:08:56.459 --> 04:08:58.559
rub off some of the blood stains, but

04:08:58.559 --> 04:09:00.360
there was still dark dried blood caught

04:09:00.360 --> 04:09:01.860
between her scales and talons.

04:09:01.920 --> 04:09:04.440
There, Clay said.

04:09:04.500 --> 04:09:05.579
Found it.

04:09:05.639 --> 04:09:08.219
He swiped some more sand away from the

04:09:08.219 --> 04:09:09.299
entrance to the tunnel.

04:09:09.360 --> 04:09:11.040
Starflight let out his breath.

04:09:11.100 --> 04:09:13.379
Oh, he said.

04:09:13.440 --> 04:09:15.659
That must be why no one spotted it

04:09:15.659 --> 04:09:15.959
before.

04:09:16.020 --> 04:09:18.479
The wind covers it with new sand every

04:09:18.479 --> 04:09:18.659
day.

04:09:18.780 --> 04:09:21.120
He edged toward the tunnel.

04:09:21.180 --> 04:09:23.579
So, we can go?

04:09:23.639 --> 04:09:26.639
Glory checked the sky again as Sunny and

04:09:26.639 --> 04:09:28.379
Tsunami slid back toward them with a

04:09:28.379 --> 04:09:29.100
chunk of cactus.

04:09:29.159 --> 04:09:31.319
No dragons anywhere that she could see.

04:09:31.440 --> 04:09:34.500
She nodded at the tunnel, and Starflight

04:09:34.500 --> 04:09:36.059
darted gratefully inside.

04:09:36.120 --> 04:09:38.459
The others followed, one by one.

04:09:38.520 --> 04:09:41.879
Glory went last, piling up as much sand

04:09:41.879 --> 04:09:42.959
behind her as she could.

04:09:43.020 --> 04:09:45.540
As she came out of the tunnel into the

04:09:45.540 --> 04:09:48.540
dark forest, a ball of fur exploded from

04:09:48.540 --> 04:09:50.340
the tree above her and landed on her

04:09:50.340 --> 04:09:51.420
neck.

04:09:51.479 --> 04:09:53.100
The sloth wrapped her arms and legs

04:09:53.100 --> 04:09:55.620
around Glory's neck, and began warbling

04:09:55.620 --> 04:09:56.940
and chirruping furiously.

04:09:57.000 --> 04:10:00.840
I think I'm being scolded, Glory said to

04:10:00.840 --> 04:10:01.200
Clay.

04:10:01.319 --> 04:10:03.659
She reached up and smoothed Silver's

04:10:03.659 --> 04:10:03.959
fur.

04:10:04.079 --> 04:10:05.639
Worm.

04:10:05.700 --> 04:10:08.520
The sloth said sternly, snuggling in

04:10:08.520 --> 04:10:08.940
closer.

04:10:09.000 --> 04:10:11.280
Sonny dove into the stream above the

04:10:11.280 --> 04:10:13.920
waterfall, washing Blaze's blood off her

04:10:13.920 --> 04:10:14.459
scales.

04:10:14.520 --> 04:10:17.700
Glory realized that Jambu was gone, but

04:10:17.700 --> 04:10:19.260
Mangrove was sitting beside the stream.

04:10:19.319 --> 04:10:21.840
His wings drooped as he stared into the

04:10:21.840 --> 04:10:22.200
water.

04:10:22.260 --> 04:10:25.440
I assume you didn't see any sign of the

04:10:25.440 --> 04:10:26.459
missing rain wings there?

04:10:26.520 --> 04:10:27.840
Glory said to him.

04:10:27.959 --> 04:10:29.219
He shook his head.

04:10:29.280 --> 04:10:31.860
Nothing anywhere in that fort.

04:10:31.979 --> 04:10:34.979
I slipped in when a patrol of sandwings

04:10:34.979 --> 04:10:35.399
came out.

04:10:35.459 --> 04:10:37.860
I searched the whole place.

04:10:37.920 --> 04:10:40.500
He kicked a clump of reeds.

04:10:40.559 --> 04:10:42.600
Useless waste of time.

04:10:42.659 --> 04:10:47.100
Probably, Glory said, but at least now we

04:10:47.100 --> 04:10:47.340
know.

04:10:47.399 --> 04:10:50.639
How are we going to find Orchid?

04:10:50.639 --> 04:10:51.600
he asked.

04:10:51.659 --> 04:10:54.719
Glory stared at the hole in the boulder.

04:10:54.780 --> 04:10:57.659
In the dark, with only a sliver of

04:10:57.659 --> 04:10:59.879
moonlight slipping through the trees, it

04:10:59.879 --> 04:11:02.879
looked like a mouth, jaws wide open to

04:11:02.879 --> 04:11:04.440
swallow dragon's hole.

04:11:04.500 --> 04:11:07.319
We heard something here a couple of

04:11:07.319 --> 04:11:07.860
nights ago.

04:11:07.920 --> 04:11:08.879
She said.

04:11:08.940 --> 04:11:12.299
Maybe, if we lie in wait, we'll catch it

04:11:12.299 --> 04:11:12.479
again.

04:11:12.540 --> 04:11:15.000
She turned and looked at tsunami.

04:11:15.059 --> 04:11:18.239
All we need is someone who can see in the

04:11:18.239 --> 04:11:18.540
dark.

04:11:18.659 --> 04:11:23.100
Chapter 18.

04:11:23.340 --> 04:11:27.299
Glory shifted on her branch inside.

04:11:27.360 --> 04:11:29.879
The knight clung to her wings like hot

04:11:29.879 --> 04:11:31.079
sticky cobwebs.

04:11:31.079 --> 04:11:34.200
A vine of moon colored flowers nearby

04:11:34.200 --> 04:11:36.420
filled the air with a smell like muskrats

04:11:36.420 --> 04:11:37.379
rolled in lemons.

04:11:37.440 --> 04:11:38.940
It was not pleasant.

04:11:39.000 --> 04:11:41.280
You didn't have to stay.

04:11:41.340 --> 04:11:43.139
Tsunami whispered.

04:11:43.200 --> 04:11:45.659
Yes, I did, Glory said.

04:11:45.719 --> 04:11:46.860
I know you.

04:11:46.979 --> 04:11:49.799
No matter what you see, you'll leap out

04:11:49.799 --> 04:11:51.420
of this tree and attack it if you're here

04:11:51.420 --> 04:11:51.780
by yourself.

04:11:51.840 --> 04:11:55.079
I... tsunami paused.

04:11:55.139 --> 04:11:56.879
Well, I still might do that.

04:11:57.000 --> 04:12:00.420
Then at least I'll be here to help, Lori

04:12:00.420 --> 04:12:02.040
said, grinning in the dark.

04:12:02.100 --> 04:12:04.139
They crouch like that for a while

04:12:04.139 --> 04:12:06.360
listening to the creaking, chirping

04:12:06.360 --> 04:12:07.979
sounds of the rainforest at night.

04:12:08.040 --> 04:12:10.559
Some kind of insect was desperately

04:12:10.559 --> 04:12:12.719
announcing the end of the world in a

04:12:12.719 --> 04:12:14.459
shrill whine from the top of their tree.

04:12:14.520 --> 04:12:17.459
If glory had been able to see it, she

04:12:17.459 --> 04:12:19.260
would have eaten it in a heartbeat, just

04:12:19.260 --> 04:12:19.979
to shut it up.

04:12:20.040 --> 04:12:23.100
They'd spent the rest of last night and

04:12:23.100 --> 04:12:25.680
today in the rain wing village, recovering

04:12:25.680 --> 04:12:26.520
from their long flight.

04:12:26.579 --> 04:12:29.459
Sunny had squeezed the cactus juice into

04:12:29.459 --> 04:12:31.979
Webb's wound, and reported jubilantly

04:12:31.979 --> 04:12:33.000
that she thought it was working.

04:12:33.059 --> 04:12:35.399
The others had stayed there for tonight.

04:12:35.459 --> 04:12:38.100
Glory thought it was unlikely that they'd

04:12:38.100 --> 04:12:39.899
catch the mystery monster on their 1st

04:12:39.899 --> 04:12:41.879
night watching, and they looked pretty

04:12:41.879 --> 04:12:42.479
exhausted.

04:12:42.540 --> 04:12:45.659
She'd also made Mangrove promise not to

04:12:45.659 --> 04:12:48.420
follow them again, and she'd left silver

04:12:48.420 --> 04:12:50.219
with Sonny, because the only thing they

04:12:50.219 --> 04:12:52.200
knew for sure was that the monster ate

04:12:52.200 --> 04:12:52.739
sloths.

04:12:52.799 --> 04:12:55.739
What did you think of Blaze?

04:12:55.799 --> 04:12:57.120
Tsunami asked in a whisper.

04:12:57.239 --> 04:12:58.620
Should we choose her?

04:12:58.680 --> 04:13:02.100
I don't know, Lori whispered back.

04:13:02.159 --> 04:13:04.500
I didn't really like her, did you?

04:13:04.559 --> 04:13:07.920
She really needed to shut up about Sky

04:13:07.920 --> 04:13:09.540
Wings, tsunami said.

04:13:09.600 --> 04:13:12.180
Glory couldn't agree more, but she was

04:13:12.180 --> 04:13:13.979
glad tsunami had said it instead of her.

04:13:14.040 --> 04:13:17.700
She seemed much less sinister than burn

04:13:17.700 --> 04:13:20.819
or blister, Glory said, but also

04:13:20.819 --> 04:13:22.200
completely incompetent.

04:13:22.200 --> 04:13:24.959
Is it fair to give the sand wings a

04:13:24.959 --> 04:13:26.520
totally useless queen like that?

04:13:26.579 --> 04:13:28.860
And she's certainly not going to win the

04:13:28.860 --> 04:13:30.719
war just by us saying she should.

04:13:30.780 --> 04:13:34.079
That's true, tsunami said.

04:13:34.139 --> 04:13:36.180
She'd never survive in actual combat

04:13:36.180 --> 04:13:38.280
especially against one of her sisters.

04:13:38.340 --> 04:13:41.219
Anyway, Glory said.

04:13:41.340 --> 04:13:42.780
It's not up to me.

04:13:42.840 --> 04:13:44.879
You guys decide whatever you want.

04:13:44.940 --> 04:13:47.760
I mean, since I'm not in the prophecy

04:13:47.760 --> 04:13:49.680
anyhow, so I shouldn't get a say.

04:13:49.739 --> 04:13:52.860
Stop talking like that or I will thump

04:13:52.860 --> 04:13:55.739
you, Tsunami said, in a loud hiss.

04:13:55.799 --> 04:13:58.500
Glory could feel her glaring even in the

04:13:58.500 --> 04:14:01.079
dark, and she felt obscurely pleased.

04:14:01.200 --> 04:14:04.860
Shh, Glory said, flicking her tail at

04:14:04.860 --> 04:14:05.579
tsunami's wings.

04:14:05.700 --> 04:14:06.719
What was that?

04:14:06.780 --> 04:14:08.819
Snap.

04:14:08.879 --> 04:14:11.399
Both dragons froze with their heads

04:14:11.399 --> 04:14:12.540
lifted.

04:14:12.600 --> 04:14:13.739
Glory's ears twitched.

04:14:13.799 --> 04:14:17.100
Snap, slither.

04:14:17.159 --> 04:14:18.719
That's it.

04:14:18.780 --> 04:14:20.399
Glory whispered.

04:14:20.459 --> 04:14:22.260
Her heart was pounding again.

04:14:22.319 --> 04:14:24.659
She tried to squint through the darkness

04:14:24.659 --> 04:14:26.399
of the boulder, but she couldn't see

04:14:26.399 --> 04:14:27.000
anything moving.

04:14:27.059 --> 04:14:30.059
The sounds of something large rustled

04:14:30.059 --> 04:14:31.739
through the undergrowth.

04:14:31.799 --> 04:14:34.079
It was breathing heavily, snuffling in

04:14:34.079 --> 04:14:36.540
and out, like a congested rhinoceros.

04:14:36.600 --> 04:14:40.079
It didn't come out of the hole, tsunami

04:14:40.079 --> 04:14:40.559
whispered.

04:14:40.620 --> 04:14:43.079
It's on the other side of the creek, near

04:14:43.079 --> 04:14:43.739
the other tree.

04:14:43.799 --> 04:14:45.059
But I can't.

04:14:45.239 --> 04:14:47.100
I'm not sure.

04:14:47.159 --> 04:14:49.379
She leaned forward, trying to see under

04:14:49.379 --> 04:14:49.979
the branches.

04:14:50.040 --> 04:14:53.819
Suddenly, another noise reached them, as

04:14:53.819 --> 04:14:55.379
if from a long way away.

04:14:55.440 --> 04:14:59.639
It sounded like, Whistling.

04:14:59.700 --> 04:15:02.159
Glory leaned forward, listening

04:15:02.159 --> 04:15:02.819
intently.

04:15:02.879 --> 04:15:05.340
It was the Dragonette's song.

04:15:05.459 --> 04:15:08.100
The ones she'd last heard when the

04:15:08.100 --> 04:15:10.020
prisoners were singing it in the Skywing

04:15:10.020 --> 04:15:10.440
Arena.

04:15:10.500 --> 04:15:12.540
The dragonettes are coming.

04:15:12.600 --> 04:15:14.459
They're coming to save the day.

04:15:14.520 --> 04:15:17.159
They're coming to fight, for they know

04:15:17.159 --> 04:15:17.819
what's right.

04:15:17.879 --> 04:15:19.379
The dragonettes.

04:15:19.500 --> 04:15:22.139
Someone was whistling their song.

04:15:22.200 --> 04:15:26.520
That is coming from the hole, tsunami

04:15:26.520 --> 04:15:27.000
whispered.

04:15:27.059 --> 04:15:29.520
She crouched to peer through the leaves.

04:15:29.579 --> 04:15:31.920
A dark shape appeared at the opening of

04:15:31.920 --> 04:15:32.399
the boulder.

04:15:32.459 --> 04:15:35.219
At the same time, the dragons heard

04:15:35.219 --> 04:15:37.559
thumping and crackling as the mystery

04:15:37.559 --> 04:15:38.819
creature fled back into the forest.

04:15:38.940 --> 04:15:41.700
Glory cursed under her breath and leaped

04:15:41.700 --> 04:15:42.120
to her feet.

04:15:42.180 --> 04:15:43.799
Should we go after it?

04:15:43.920 --> 04:15:46.440
The tsunami had already launched herself

04:15:46.440 --> 04:15:48.780
out of the tree and flung herself at the

04:15:48.780 --> 04:15:49.079
boulder.

04:15:49.139 --> 04:15:51.360
She collided with the shape there, and

04:15:51.360 --> 04:15:53.700
they both yelped with pain, rolling and

04:15:53.700 --> 04:15:54.420
grappling on the ground.

04:15:54.479 --> 04:15:57.959
Glory sprang after her and seized the new

04:15:57.959 --> 04:15:58.860
dragon's tail.

04:15:58.979 --> 04:16:01.079
The 3 of them wrestled until glory and

04:16:01.079 --> 04:16:03.360
tsunami had him pinned down, and glory

04:16:03.360 --> 04:16:04.200
could sit on his chest.

04:16:04.260 --> 04:16:06.719
She was not particularly surprised to

04:16:06.719 --> 04:16:08.579
discover, it was Deathbringer.

04:16:08.639 --> 04:16:11.639
The night wing had sand between his claws

04:16:11.639 --> 04:16:14.040
and an unrepentant expression on his face

04:16:14.040 --> 04:16:16.680
from what she could see in the ripples of

04:16:16.680 --> 04:16:18.659
moonlight that made it through the leaves

04:16:18.659 --> 04:16:19.319
overhead.

04:16:19.379 --> 04:16:23.280
What kind of assassin stalks his prey and

04:16:23.280 --> 04:16:24.659
whistles at the same time.

04:16:24.719 --> 04:16:26.940
Glory asked him.

04:16:27.000 --> 04:16:28.559
We should kill him right now.

04:16:28.680 --> 04:16:30.239
Tsunami hissed.

04:16:30.299 --> 04:16:33.840
You scared our monster away, Glory said

04:16:33.840 --> 04:16:35.040
poking his snout.

04:16:35.100 --> 04:16:36.959
So now we're extra mad at you.

04:16:37.020 --> 04:16:40.559
Yes, that plus the trying to kill us

04:16:40.559 --> 04:16:41.700
tsunami said.

04:16:41.760 --> 04:16:45.659
One monster, Deathbringer said, a little

04:16:45.659 --> 04:16:46.500
too innocently.

04:16:46.559 --> 04:16:48.600
Glory peered at him with growing

04:16:48.600 --> 04:16:49.260
suspicion.

04:16:49.319 --> 04:16:50.459
Did he know something?

04:16:50.520 --> 04:16:53.879
Did you follow us through the tunnel, she

04:16:53.879 --> 04:16:55.559
asked, or did you already know it was

04:16:55.559 --> 04:16:55.799
there?

04:16:55.860 --> 04:16:58.319
How would I know it was there?

04:16:58.379 --> 04:16:59.159
he asked.

04:16:59.280 --> 04:17:02.100
That's what I'd like to know, she said.

04:17:02.159 --> 04:17:04.620
Let's take him back to the village and

04:17:04.620 --> 04:17:06.600
interrogate him, Tsunami said.

04:17:06.659 --> 04:17:09.719
I don't think that's safe, Glory said.

04:17:09.780 --> 04:17:12.600
I mean, for the rain wings or for the

04:17:12.600 --> 04:17:13.020
others.

04:17:13.079 --> 04:17:14.819
We should keep him as far away from

04:17:14.819 --> 04:17:15.600
everyone as possible.

04:17:15.719 --> 04:17:19.079
Tsunami wrinkled her snout, thinking.

04:17:19.200 --> 04:17:23.399
Or, she said, we go back to plan A, kill

04:17:23.399 --> 04:17:24.540
him right now.

04:17:24.600 --> 04:17:27.120
Tsunami, I don't think you want to do

04:17:27.120 --> 04:17:28.139
that any more than I do.

04:17:28.200 --> 04:17:29.159
Glory said.

04:17:29.280 --> 04:17:30.780
That shut her up.

04:17:30.840 --> 04:17:33.479
Glory had noticed tsunami getting

04:17:33.479 --> 04:17:35.280
queasier about killing other dragons

04:17:35.280 --> 04:17:37.860
after her experiences in the Sky Wing

04:17:37.860 --> 04:17:38.340
Arena.

04:17:38.399 --> 04:17:41.100
Self-defense was one thing, but they had

04:17:41.100 --> 04:17:43.739
Deathbringer trapped under their talons.

04:17:43.799 --> 04:17:47.399
All right, tsunami said finally, after a

04:17:47.399 --> 04:17:50.040
long pause, you're right, I don't want

04:17:50.040 --> 04:17:50.340
to.

04:17:50.399 --> 04:17:53.159
But I was hoping he'd think we wanted to

04:17:53.159 --> 04:17:55.260
so good job backing me up on that.

04:17:55.319 --> 04:17:58.319
Sorry, I couldn't read your mind like a

04:17:58.319 --> 04:18:00.239
stupid night wing, Glory said.

04:18:00.299 --> 04:18:03.000
Speaking of which, are you the mind

04:18:03.000 --> 04:18:04.139
reading kind of night wing?

04:18:04.260 --> 04:18:06.780
She narrowed her eyes, a death bringer?

04:18:06.840 --> 04:18:08.760
What am I thinking right now?

04:18:08.819 --> 04:18:13.319
That I'm much too charming, clever, and

04:18:13.319 --> 04:18:14.340
good looking to kill?

04:18:14.399 --> 04:18:15.420
He guessed.

04:18:15.540 --> 04:18:18.120
That was actually a little closer to

04:18:18.120 --> 04:18:19.559
accurate than Glory liked.

04:18:19.620 --> 04:18:21.840
She flared her rough and poked us now

04:18:21.840 --> 04:18:22.260
again.

04:18:22.319 --> 04:18:24.120
Wrong, she said.

04:18:24.180 --> 04:18:26.100
I'm thinking that you're starting to be

04:18:26.100 --> 04:18:27.120
an awful lot of trouble.

04:18:27.180 --> 04:18:29.280
Have you decided to kill me after all?

04:18:29.340 --> 04:18:32.940
The rakish grin faded from Deathbringer's

04:18:32.940 --> 04:18:33.180
face.

04:18:33.239 --> 04:18:35.579
He studied her, as though he were

04:18:35.579 --> 04:18:37.500
seriously considering the question.

04:18:37.559 --> 04:18:40.079
Not sure I like the length of this pause

04:18:40.079 --> 04:18:41.340
Lori said.

04:18:41.399 --> 04:18:43.379
I've been wondering if there's an

04:18:43.379 --> 04:18:45.899
alternative, said Deathbringer, but

04:18:45.899 --> 04:18:46.920
that's not usually my call.

04:18:46.979 --> 04:18:48.719
Whose is it?

04:18:48.780 --> 04:18:50.100
Tsunami demanded.

04:18:50.159 --> 04:18:51.479
The Nightwing Queen?

04:18:51.540 --> 04:18:54.180
Death bringer made a peculiar expression

04:18:54.180 --> 04:18:55.620
which Glory couldn't interpret.

04:18:55.680 --> 04:18:57.299
I can't say.

04:18:57.360 --> 04:19:00.840
I don't understand why any Night Wings

04:19:00.840 --> 04:19:02.579
would want me dead, Glory said.

04:19:02.639 --> 04:19:05.760
That has become ever more mystifying to

04:19:05.760 --> 04:19:08.700
me as well, Deathbringer said, in a

04:19:08.700 --> 04:19:10.860
manner that managed to sound both gallant

04:19:10.860 --> 04:19:12.120
and truthful.

04:19:12.180 --> 04:19:15.479
So you're mystified, Glory said.

04:19:15.600 --> 04:19:17.219
But you'll still probably do it.

04:19:17.280 --> 04:19:20.280
I wouldn't say, probably.

04:19:20.340 --> 04:19:21.959
Deathbringer offered.

04:19:22.020 --> 04:19:24.000
I'd say maybe.

04:19:24.120 --> 04:19:28.200
I wouldn't call that reassuring, glory

04:19:28.200 --> 04:19:28.860
shot back.

04:19:28.920 --> 04:19:31.260
I'd call that the opposite of

04:19:31.260 --> 04:19:31.739
reassuring.

04:19:31.799 --> 04:19:33.540
He grinned at her again.

04:19:33.600 --> 04:19:35.399
He really needed to quit doing that.

04:19:35.459 --> 04:19:37.020
It was very distracting.

04:19:37.079 --> 04:19:39.360
So what do we do with them?

04:19:39.420 --> 04:19:40.680
Tsunami asked her.

04:19:40.739 --> 04:19:42.959
We can't let him go, and we can't take

04:19:42.959 --> 04:19:44.159
him back to the rain wing village.

04:19:44.280 --> 04:19:47.700
We could tie him up, leave him in the

04:19:47.700 --> 04:19:50.040
forest, and hope the monster eats him.

04:19:50.159 --> 04:19:51.059
Glory said.

04:19:51.120 --> 04:19:53.340
She squinted at Deathbringer's face.

04:19:53.399 --> 04:19:55.500
He didn't look even a little bit

04:19:55.500 --> 04:19:55.920
worried.

04:19:55.979 --> 04:19:58.559
Did we mention the monster?

04:19:58.620 --> 04:19:59.459
she asked him.

04:19:59.520 --> 04:20:02.340
It's been abducting or possibly eating

04:20:02.340 --> 04:20:03.540
rain wings around here?

04:20:03.600 --> 04:20:06.719
I bet it'll be pretty excited to find you

04:20:06.719 --> 04:20:07.739
all tied up.

04:20:07.799 --> 04:20:11.879
Oh no, Deathbringer said.

04:20:11.940 --> 04:20:13.920
Please don't leave me alone where a

04:20:13.920 --> 04:20:14.760
monster could get me.

04:20:14.819 --> 04:20:17.700
Glory opened her mouth and then closed

04:20:17.700 --> 04:20:17.940
it.

04:20:18.000 --> 04:20:20.879
She'd just had a possibly brilliant and

04:20:20.879 --> 04:20:22.079
perfectly terrible idea.

04:20:22.139 --> 04:20:24.299
One she'd have to think about for a

04:20:24.299 --> 04:20:24.780
minute.

04:20:24.780 --> 04:20:26.520
She poked him and the snout again.

04:20:26.579 --> 04:20:29.340
Was that sarcasm?

04:20:29.340 --> 04:20:29.879
she asked.

04:20:29.940 --> 04:20:31.440
Tsunami?

04:20:31.500 --> 04:20:33.540
Did that sound weirdly sarcastic to you?

04:20:33.600 --> 04:20:36.719
Like he doesn't believe in monsters?

04:20:36.780 --> 04:20:39.120
Tsunami said, which I'm not sure I do

04:20:39.120 --> 04:20:40.440
either, just for the record.

04:20:40.500 --> 04:20:43.620
Or he's in cahoots with it.

04:20:43.680 --> 04:20:44.879
Glory thought.

04:20:44.940 --> 04:20:47.700
Or at least he knows what it is, and

04:20:47.700 --> 04:20:48.540
isn't afraid of it.

04:20:48.659 --> 04:20:51.239
She decided not to say this out loud.

04:20:51.299 --> 04:20:54.180
Tsunami's enthusiasm for interrogation

04:20:54.180 --> 04:20:56.459
might spring up again, and Glory was

04:20:56.459 --> 04:20:57.899
fairly sure it would be a waste of time.

04:20:57.959 --> 04:21:00.180
They weren't going to get anything useful

04:21:00.180 --> 04:21:02.280
out of Deathbringer by looking fierce and

04:21:02.280 --> 04:21:03.420
demanding answers.

04:21:03.479 --> 04:21:06.600
Besides, now that a plan was forming in

04:21:06.600 --> 04:21:09.180
her mind, she wanted to try it out, which

04:21:09.180 --> 04:21:11.100
meant she had to get rid of tsunami.

04:21:11.159 --> 04:21:13.979
Let's drag him away from the tunnel and

04:21:13.979 --> 04:21:14.639
tie him up.

04:21:14.700 --> 04:21:15.360
She said.

04:21:15.420 --> 04:21:17.700
Then you go tell the others, and we can

04:21:17.700 --> 04:21:19.559
take turns watching him until he decides

04:21:19.559 --> 04:21:21.659
to tell us who wants us dead and why.

04:21:21.719 --> 04:21:24.000
And which of us?

04:21:24.000 --> 04:21:25.440
tsunami suggested.

04:21:25.500 --> 04:21:27.600
He said he was sent to kill a few of us

04:21:27.600 --> 04:21:28.319
not just you.

04:21:28.379 --> 04:21:33.059
And also, you know, how to avoid it, said

04:21:33.059 --> 04:21:33.540
glory.

04:21:33.600 --> 04:21:35.760
You'll have to wait a while.

04:21:35.879 --> 04:21:37.200
Deathbringer said.

04:21:37.260 --> 04:21:39.360
I'm not allowed to tell you anything.

04:21:39.420 --> 04:21:42.239
Tsunami and glory ignored this.

04:21:42.299 --> 04:21:45.059
They ripped vines down from the trees and

04:21:45.059 --> 04:21:46.680
wrapped the strongest ones around his

04:21:46.680 --> 04:21:47.040
wings.

04:21:47.100 --> 04:21:49.860
Tsunami tied his talons together so he

04:21:49.860 --> 04:21:52.200
couldn't run, slid a rope around his neck

04:21:52.200 --> 04:21:54.059
and prodded him ahead of them into the

04:21:54.059 --> 04:21:54.299
forest.

04:21:54.360 --> 04:21:57.360
After a short walk, they found a tree

04:21:57.360 --> 04:21:59.760
that tsunami approved of, and tied him to

04:21:59.760 --> 04:22:01.379
it with a tightest knot they could

04:22:01.379 --> 04:22:01.680
muster.

04:22:01.739 --> 04:22:04.200
He'll burn through these vines the moment

04:22:04.200 --> 04:22:04.860
we walk away.

04:22:04.979 --> 04:22:06.299
Tsunami pointed out.

04:22:06.360 --> 04:22:08.219
So we don't walk away.

04:22:08.280 --> 04:22:09.420
Glory said.

04:22:09.479 --> 04:22:10.799
You go tell the others.

04:22:10.860 --> 04:22:13.200
I'll sit here with my extremely deadly

04:22:13.200 --> 04:22:14.579
secret weapon pointed at him.

04:22:14.639 --> 04:22:16.559
What's that?

04:22:16.680 --> 04:22:18.120
asked Deathbringer.

04:22:18.180 --> 04:22:19.979
Wait, let me guess.

04:22:20.040 --> 04:22:21.479
You'll rape your wit.

04:22:21.540 --> 04:22:24.719
Try to escape, and find out the dead

04:22:24.719 --> 04:22:25.020
way.

04:22:25.139 --> 04:22:26.340
Glory offered.

04:22:26.459 --> 04:22:29.159
He leaned back against the tree, looking

04:22:29.159 --> 04:22:30.840
perfectly comfortable and thoroughly

04:22:30.840 --> 04:22:32.159
uninterested in escaping.

04:22:32.219 --> 04:22:34.440
Peculiar dragon.

04:22:34.500 --> 04:22:35.700
Glory thought.

04:22:35.760 --> 04:22:38.100
Send back clay first.

04:22:38.159 --> 04:22:41.040
Glory suggested to Tsunami, he can take

04:22:41.040 --> 04:22:41.520
the next watch.

04:22:41.639 --> 04:22:44.639
I hope you hear how bossy you're being

04:22:44.639 --> 04:22:45.719
tsunami said.

04:22:45.780 --> 04:22:47.760
I'm letting it slide for now, but I'll

04:22:47.760 --> 04:22:48.120
remember this.

04:22:48.180 --> 04:22:49.979
Oh, go away.

04:22:50.040 --> 04:22:53.219
Glory flapped her wings at her until the

04:22:53.219 --> 04:22:55.079
sea wing lifted off into the darkness.

04:22:55.139 --> 04:22:58.139
As her wing beats faded, the night sounds

04:22:58.139 --> 04:22:59.940
of the rainforest settled over them.

04:23:00.000 --> 04:23:03.000
An orchestra of insects warbled and

04:23:03.000 --> 04:23:04.799
chirped away as the trees rustled.

04:23:04.860 --> 04:23:07.680
Night birds called, and frogs muttered in

04:23:07.680 --> 04:23:09.059
the background like a disgruntled

04:23:09.059 --> 04:23:10.139
audience.

04:23:10.200 --> 04:23:11.879
It's so noisy here.

04:23:11.940 --> 04:23:15.059
Death bringer said after a moment, so

04:23:15.059 --> 04:23:15.540
alive.

04:23:15.659 --> 04:23:18.659
Is it not like that where you come from?

04:23:18.719 --> 04:23:19.920
Glory asked.

04:23:19.979 --> 04:23:22.920
It's a lot quieter than the Ice Kingdom

04:23:22.920 --> 04:23:24.299
he pointed out.

04:23:24.360 --> 04:23:26.219
And the kingdom of sand.

04:23:26.280 --> 04:23:28.200
He didn't say anything about the

04:23:28.200 --> 04:23:30.059
Nightwing Home, but she didn't really

04:23:30.059 --> 04:23:30.659
expect him to.

04:23:30.780 --> 04:23:33.659
She stared into the trees, thinking

04:23:33.659 --> 04:23:34.020
hard.

04:23:34.079 --> 04:23:37.440
Once Clay arrived to take her place, she

04:23:37.440 --> 04:23:37.979
could slip away.

04:23:38.040 --> 04:23:40.440
No one would notice she was missing for a

04:23:40.440 --> 04:23:40.860
while.

04:23:40.920 --> 04:23:42.659
She could go out and look for the monster

04:23:42.659 --> 04:23:45.059
by herself, which was the best way to do

04:23:45.059 --> 04:23:46.079
anything if you asked her.

04:23:46.139 --> 04:23:49.799
Don't do it. said Deathbringer suddenly.

04:23:49.860 --> 04:23:53.159
You better not be reading my mind, she

04:23:53.159 --> 04:23:53.579
snapped.

04:23:53.639 --> 04:23:56.219
I don't have to, he said.

04:23:56.280 --> 04:23:58.620
You have, I'm about to do something

04:23:58.620 --> 04:24:00.360
stupid written all over your face.

04:24:00.420 --> 04:24:03.360
It's not stupid, she said.

04:24:03.420 --> 04:24:05.760
It's quite clever, and it might be the

04:24:05.760 --> 04:24:06.959
only way to catch the monster.

04:24:07.020 --> 04:24:10.200
Maybe you should leave the monster

04:24:10.200 --> 04:24:10.680
alone.

04:24:10.739 --> 04:24:11.819
He said.

04:24:11.879 --> 04:24:12.780
Forget about it.

04:24:12.840 --> 04:24:15.120
Get back to the prophecy fulfilling

04:24:15.120 --> 04:24:15.479
business.

04:24:15.600 --> 04:24:17.579
That stopped her for a moment.

04:24:17.700 --> 04:24:19.260
The prophecy.

04:24:19.319 --> 04:24:22.620
Putting an end to the war was important.

04:24:22.680 --> 04:24:25.319
Finding a few rain wings hardly compared

04:24:25.319 --> 04:24:27.120
but she'd made a promise.

04:24:27.180 --> 04:24:31.319
I'm not even in the stupid prophecy, she

04:24:31.319 --> 04:24:31.559
said.

04:24:31.620 --> 04:24:34.079
I know, he said.

04:24:34.139 --> 04:24:36.479
But I bet you'd still be remarkably good

04:24:36.479 --> 04:24:37.379
at making it come true.

04:24:37.440 --> 04:24:41.579
That doesn't make any sense, she said, and

04:24:41.579 --> 04:24:43.020
the rain wings are my tribe.

04:24:43.079 --> 04:24:44.159
They need my help.

04:24:44.219 --> 04:24:46.799
She felt a burst of certainty in her

04:24:46.799 --> 04:24:49.319
chest, and I have to do this on my own.

04:24:49.379 --> 04:24:53.340
Wait, said Deathbringer, with a

04:24:53.340 --> 04:24:54.780
gratifying note of alarm in his voice.

04:24:54.899 --> 04:24:56.100
Why?

04:24:56.159 --> 04:24:57.659
You have friends.

04:24:57.719 --> 04:24:58.500
Let them help you.

04:24:58.620 --> 04:25:00.120
Glory shook her head.

04:25:00.180 --> 04:25:02.040
They can't help me with this.

04:25:02.100 --> 04:25:05.340
The monster, or whatever is out there

04:25:05.340 --> 04:25:06.540
isn't going to approach a group of

04:25:06.540 --> 04:25:07.260
dragonettes.

04:25:07.319 --> 04:25:09.540
It attacks rain wings who are out in the

04:25:09.540 --> 04:25:10.079
forest alone.

04:25:10.139 --> 04:25:13.139
So you're...

04:25:13.139 --> 04:25:15.120
Gloria smiled at Deathbringer.

04:25:15.180 --> 04:25:18.059
I'm going to use myself as bait.

04:25:18.180 --> 04:25:22.620
Chapter 19.

04:25:22.860 --> 04:25:26.219
Watch him carefully, Glory instructed

04:25:26.219 --> 04:25:26.700
Clay.

04:25:26.760 --> 04:25:27.719
Don't let him talk.

04:25:27.780 --> 04:25:32.340
Deathbringer complained through the vines

04:25:32.340 --> 04:25:33.840
she'd tied around its snout.

04:25:33.899 --> 04:25:35.819
She didn't want him spilling the beans to

04:25:35.819 --> 04:25:37.200
clay before she could get away into the

04:25:37.200 --> 04:25:37.500
forest.

04:25:37.559 --> 04:25:40.319
Also, she'd gotten sick of listening to

04:25:40.319 --> 04:25:42.540
him Yammer all night long, trying to

04:25:42.540 --> 04:25:43.739
derail her plan.

04:25:43.799 --> 04:25:45.780
This way, she'd been able to watch the

04:25:45.780 --> 04:25:47.879
sunrise in relative peace and quiet

04:25:47.879 --> 04:25:50.100
shortly after which Clay had shown up.

04:25:50.159 --> 04:25:53.280
No worries, Play said.

04:25:53.340 --> 04:25:55.680
I'll just sit here and be my usual

04:25:55.680 --> 04:25:56.879
intimidating self.

04:25:56.940 --> 04:25:59.760
He threw back his shoulders and tried to

04:25:59.760 --> 04:26:00.180
scowl.

04:26:00.299 --> 04:26:02.520
Absolutely terrifying.

04:26:02.579 --> 04:26:03.959
Glory assured him.

04:26:04.020 --> 04:26:06.479
Deathbringer managed to look skeptical

04:26:06.479 --> 04:26:08.340
despite the vines obscuring most of his

04:26:08.340 --> 04:26:08.579
face.

04:26:08.639 --> 04:26:11.579
I'll send someone else soon to take the

04:26:11.579 --> 04:26:14.459
next watch, she said, backing away.

04:26:14.520 --> 04:26:17.280
But first, I'm going to catch a monster.

04:26:17.399 --> 04:26:21.719
It wasn't that stupid a plan, no matter

04:26:21.719 --> 04:26:22.799
what Death Bringer said.

04:26:22.860 --> 04:26:25.559
Alone rain wing was exactly the kind of

04:26:25.559 --> 04:26:27.959
target the monster would go after, and

04:26:27.959 --> 04:26:29.819
she couldn't risk enlisting another rain

04:26:29.819 --> 04:26:32.219
wing as bait, they were all too dopey to

04:26:32.219 --> 04:26:34.200
be any use, even mangrove.

04:26:34.260 --> 04:26:37.200
Besides, as far as she could tell, she

04:26:37.200 --> 04:26:39.059
was the only rain wing willing to use her

04:26:39.059 --> 04:26:40.319
venom on other living things.

04:26:40.440 --> 04:26:43.860
It wasn't her favorite thing to do, but

04:26:43.860 --> 04:26:46.079
it was still a weapon, a powerful one

04:26:46.079 --> 04:26:48.479
that few dragons knew about, and she was

04:26:48.479 --> 04:26:49.979
sure she could use it to escape any

04:26:49.979 --> 04:26:51.180
situation if she had to.

04:26:51.239 --> 04:26:53.819
She headed back to the tunnel first.

04:26:53.879 --> 04:26:55.799
She was still certain that it was

04:26:55.799 --> 04:26:57.479
connected to the missing rain wings

04:26:57.479 --> 04:26:59.100
although she couldn't figure out how.

04:26:59.159 --> 04:27:02.760
It started with a question, who had put

04:27:02.760 --> 04:27:05.639
the tunnel in place, and then, what was

04:27:05.639 --> 04:27:06.120
their plan?

04:27:06.239 --> 04:27:08.399
To steal a rain wing here and there?

04:27:08.459 --> 04:27:09.239
Why?

04:27:09.299 --> 04:27:12.360
Glory nosed around the forest near the

04:27:12.360 --> 04:27:14.159
tunnel opening until she found a clearing

04:27:14.159 --> 04:27:15.659
where she could sit and think for a

04:27:15.659 --> 04:27:15.899
moment.

04:27:15.959 --> 04:27:19.799
Burn seemed like an obvious suspect, since

04:27:19.799 --> 04:27:21.239
her stronghold was not far from the

04:27:21.239 --> 04:27:21.600
tunnel.

04:27:21.659 --> 04:27:24.479
But glory had seen the look on Burns' face

04:27:24.479 --> 04:27:26.700
as glory's venom sizzled on Queen

04:27:26.700 --> 04:27:28.020
Scarlet's scales.

04:27:28.079 --> 04:27:30.180
It was pure, shocked terror.

04:27:30.239 --> 04:27:33.059
The sandwing queen had clearly never seen

04:27:33.059 --> 04:27:35.159
anything like glory's venom before.

04:27:35.219 --> 04:27:37.680
If she were the one abducting rain wings

04:27:37.680 --> 04:27:39.780
for the past year, surely she'd have

04:27:39.780 --> 04:27:41.520
heard about their training sessions, and

04:27:41.520 --> 04:27:42.780
she'd know all about it.

04:27:42.840 --> 04:27:45.360
Glory stopped at a small bush, and

04:27:45.360 --> 04:27:46.620
sprayed it with her venom.

04:27:46.680 --> 04:27:49.979
Black goop spattered over the leaves, and

04:27:49.979 --> 04:27:52.319
almost immediately the whole bush wilted

04:27:52.319 --> 04:27:54.180
shriveled up, and died.

04:27:54.299 --> 04:27:56.700
Glory tilted her head at it, feeling

04:27:56.700 --> 04:27:57.899
weirdly guilty.

04:27:57.959 --> 04:28:00.479
Maybe she could practice her aim while

04:28:00.479 --> 04:28:01.920
she waited for the monster to attack

04:28:01.920 --> 04:28:02.159
her.

04:28:02.219 --> 04:28:04.680
She chose another bush with long dragon

04:28:04.680 --> 04:28:07.139
tail leaves, and tried to hit just one of

04:28:07.139 --> 04:28:07.319
them.

04:28:07.379 --> 04:28:11.520
Half the bush went, and melted into the

04:28:11.520 --> 04:28:11.760
grass.

04:28:11.819 --> 04:28:14.520
Hmm, Glory said aloud.

04:28:14.639 --> 04:28:15.899
Not awesome.

04:28:16.020 --> 04:28:19.620
She tried again, and again, the clearing

04:28:19.620 --> 04:28:20.940
was starting to look a bit worse for

04:28:20.940 --> 04:28:21.360
wear.

04:28:21.420 --> 04:28:23.639
Glory stopped and smacked herself with

04:28:23.639 --> 04:28:24.000
her tail.

04:28:24.120 --> 04:28:27.059
Try using your brain for half a moment

04:28:27.059 --> 04:28:27.420
glory.

04:28:27.479 --> 04:28:30.059
If she made a mess like this with her

04:28:30.059 --> 04:28:32.219
venom practice, then surely the other

04:28:32.219 --> 04:28:33.719
training dragonettes would have too.

04:28:33.780 --> 04:28:36.360
So even though Bromeliad wouldn't show

04:28:36.360 --> 04:28:38.760
her where Kinkachu had disappeared, there

04:28:38.760 --> 04:28:40.440
was a chance Glory could find it on her

04:28:40.440 --> 04:28:40.620
own.

04:28:40.680 --> 04:28:43.979
She started at the waterfall and circled

04:28:43.979 --> 04:28:46.020
out from there, walking so she could

04:28:46.020 --> 04:28:48.059
study the bushes as she went past them.

04:28:48.120 --> 04:28:51.420
Fat, spiny frogs stared at her, making

04:28:51.420 --> 04:28:54.059
woo goo woo noises in their throats.

04:28:54.120 --> 04:28:56.459
A pair of red and gold birds with large

04:28:56.459 --> 04:28:59.040
beaks followed her for a while, gossiping

04:28:59.040 --> 04:29:00.899
loudly in what sounded like garbled

04:29:00.899 --> 04:29:04.079
dragon language, but she found nothing, no

04:29:04.079 --> 04:29:05.280
signs of venom anywhere.

04:29:05.340 --> 04:29:08.219
Maybe the training sessions had been in a

04:29:08.219 --> 04:29:10.440
whole different part of the forest, maybe

04:29:10.440 --> 04:29:12.180
the secret tunnel really had nothing to

04:29:12.180 --> 04:29:13.200
do with the abductions.

04:29:13.260 --> 04:29:15.899
Glory stubbornly kept searching.

04:29:15.959 --> 04:29:18.299
What other reason could there be for the

04:29:18.299 --> 04:29:18.840
tunnel?

04:29:18.899 --> 04:29:21.000
Who would need to get quickly between the

04:29:21.000 --> 04:29:22.739
desert and the rainforest?

04:29:22.799 --> 04:29:24.000
No one.

04:29:24.059 --> 04:29:27.239
No one came to the rainforest at all, and

04:29:27.239 --> 04:29:28.799
the rain wings certainly never left.

04:29:28.920 --> 04:29:32.819
But the war is closer than they think, she

04:29:32.819 --> 04:29:33.120
thought.

04:29:33.180 --> 04:29:36.659
It's right on their doorstep, ready to

04:29:36.659 --> 04:29:38.399
fall through into their peaceful world.

04:29:38.459 --> 04:29:42.000
She glared up at the treetops as an image

04:29:42.000 --> 04:29:43.860
of Queen Magnificent flashed through her

04:29:43.860 --> 04:29:44.100
head.

04:29:44.159 --> 04:29:47.100
And what is that useless queen going to

04:29:47.100 --> 04:29:47.579
do about it?

04:29:47.639 --> 04:29:50.459
Blaze is no better than magnificent.

04:29:50.520 --> 04:29:53.760
If we pick her, we leave the sand wings

04:29:53.760 --> 04:29:55.379
as weak and vulnerable as the rain

04:29:55.379 --> 04:29:55.920
wings.

04:29:55.979 --> 04:29:58.319
She looked up at the trees again.

04:29:58.379 --> 04:30:00.000
Was it getting darker?

04:30:00.059 --> 04:30:02.399
The sun had been up for only a couple of

04:30:02.399 --> 04:30:02.760
hours.

04:30:02.819 --> 04:30:05.760
A fat raindrop splattered against her

04:30:05.760 --> 04:30:06.299
snout.

04:30:06.360 --> 04:30:08.940
The leaves above her whoosht like dragon

04:30:08.940 --> 04:30:11.819
wings as the wind rushed through them, and

04:30:11.819 --> 04:30:13.979
more rain came pattering down in scatters

04:30:13.979 --> 04:30:14.700
and sprays.

04:30:14.760 --> 04:30:17.100
Glory drew her wings close to her.

04:30:17.159 --> 04:30:20.700
Rain probably washed away any trace of

04:30:20.700 --> 04:30:21.899
venom training days ago.

04:30:21.959 --> 04:30:25.920
She realized, but she kept going, sodden

04:30:25.920 --> 04:30:28.020
undergrowth squelching below her talons.

04:30:28.079 --> 04:30:31.139
She found herself in a small circle, where

04:30:31.139 --> 04:30:33.120
the trees above bent together to form a

04:30:33.120 --> 04:30:35.579
kind of umbrella canopy, keeping the

04:30:35.579 --> 04:30:36.840
ground below relatively dry.

04:30:36.899 --> 04:30:39.840
She stopped there, stretching and shaking

04:30:39.840 --> 04:30:40.319
her wings.

04:30:40.379 --> 04:30:42.120
This is stupid.

04:30:42.180 --> 04:30:44.940
She told herself, I'm not going to find

04:30:44.940 --> 04:30:47.100
anything, and I'm not going to get caught

04:30:47.100 --> 04:30:48.479
by anything in this weather either.

04:30:48.540 --> 04:30:50.579
What kind of creature would be out

04:30:50.579 --> 04:30:51.479
hunting in the rain?

04:30:51.540 --> 04:30:54.120
She might as well head back to the

04:30:54.120 --> 04:30:55.079
village and dry off.

04:30:55.139 --> 04:30:58.020
But as she turned to fly away, She

04:30:58.020 --> 04:31:00.059
spotted a dark patch on the bush of pink

04:31:00.059 --> 04:31:01.079
flowers beside her.

04:31:01.139 --> 04:31:04.680
Gloria paused, then edged closer and

04:31:04.680 --> 04:31:05.399
peered at it.

04:31:05.459 --> 04:31:07.920
Several of the leaves were withered and

04:31:07.920 --> 04:31:10.620
dead, looking sickly, black and twisted.

04:31:10.680 --> 04:31:13.500
A glossy pattern of dark droplets had

04:31:13.500 --> 04:31:15.059
hardened on the ground under the bush.

04:31:15.120 --> 04:31:19.260
Someone was training here, Glory

04:31:19.260 --> 04:31:19.620
thought.

04:31:19.680 --> 04:31:23.040
Maybe Kinkachu, maybe one of the other

04:31:23.040 --> 04:31:23.940
missing dragons.

04:31:24.000 --> 04:31:26.639
She poked the piles of leaves that

04:31:26.639 --> 04:31:29.040
covered the ground and found half a talon

04:31:29.040 --> 04:31:31.680
print in the dirt, a small one, even

04:31:31.680 --> 04:31:33.180
smaller than Sonny's.

04:31:33.239 --> 04:31:36.059
She leaned down to sniff at it, and that

04:31:36.059 --> 04:31:37.979
was when something bashed her on the back

04:31:37.979 --> 04:31:38.340
of her head.

04:31:38.459 --> 04:31:43.020
Glory started away to the feeling of

04:31:43.020 --> 04:31:45.239
movement, and something uncomfortable

04:31:45.239 --> 04:31:47.520
pressing against her wings, she kept

04:31:47.520 --> 04:31:49.739
still for a moment with her eyes closed

04:31:49.739 --> 04:31:51.479
trying to figure out what was happening.

04:31:51.540 --> 04:31:54.000
It felt like she was being dragged along

04:31:54.000 --> 04:31:54.479
the ground.

04:31:54.540 --> 04:31:57.540
Her left side was unpleasantly damp and

04:31:57.540 --> 04:31:59.639
slimy, as if she were wrapped in

04:31:59.639 --> 04:32:01.260
something that instantly soaked up the

04:32:01.260 --> 04:32:04.440
mud and clung to her scales, rain still

04:32:04.440 --> 04:32:06.899
splattered around her, the sound muffled

04:32:06.899 --> 04:32:09.600
now by whatever she was in, a giant sack

04:32:09.600 --> 04:32:11.040
of some kind, she guessed.

04:32:11.040 --> 04:32:14.100
Her wings were bound to her sides, and

04:32:14.100 --> 04:32:15.719
thick cloth was wrapped around her

04:32:15.719 --> 04:32:16.079
claws.

04:32:16.139 --> 04:32:19.500
More disturbingly, some kind of vine or

04:32:19.500 --> 04:32:21.959
rope was tied around her snout, binding

04:32:21.959 --> 04:32:24.540
her mouth shut, which meant using her

04:32:24.540 --> 04:32:25.799
venom was out of the question.

04:32:25.860 --> 04:32:28.860
It also meant that whatever had called

04:32:28.860 --> 04:32:31.379
her wasn't just a mindless mystery

04:32:31.379 --> 04:32:31.739
beast.

04:32:31.860 --> 04:32:33.959
It was smart enough to tie her up.

04:32:34.020 --> 04:32:37.200
It probably knew about her venom, or it

04:32:37.200 --> 04:32:38.579
might just be wary of her teeth.

04:32:38.639 --> 04:32:41.579
Her tails whacked against something solid

04:32:41.579 --> 04:32:42.659
and she winced.

04:32:42.719 --> 04:32:45.420
She cracked open her eyes and saw only

04:32:45.420 --> 04:32:46.139
darkness.

04:32:46.200 --> 04:32:47.459
No, wait.

04:32:47.520 --> 04:32:51.239
Not total darkness, faint green light

04:32:51.239 --> 04:32:53.040
filtered through the thick canvas around

04:32:53.040 --> 04:32:55.440
her, the sack pressed close to her

04:32:55.440 --> 04:32:55.920
snout.

04:32:55.979 --> 04:32:58.860
It smelled like dead animals and rotten

04:32:58.860 --> 04:33:00.239
eggs and fire.

04:33:00.299 --> 04:33:03.299
Overwhelming the damp, leafy scent of the

04:33:03.299 --> 04:33:04.080
rainforest outside.

04:33:04.200 --> 04:33:07.799
Glory tried to listen for clues, but all

04:33:07.799 --> 04:33:10.080
she could hear was wet slithering, which

04:33:10.080 --> 04:33:12.000
might be just the sack sliding over the

04:33:12.000 --> 04:33:13.020
forest floor.

04:33:13.080 --> 04:33:16.080
Then a shiver ran down her spine, like

04:33:16.080 --> 04:33:18.119
sharp claws scrabbling to escape.

04:33:18.180 --> 04:33:21.119
She recognized the weird prickle under

04:33:21.119 --> 04:33:21.599
her scales.

04:33:21.659 --> 04:33:24.599
It was the feeling she got from the hole

04:33:24.599 --> 04:33:26.159
that led to the kingdom of sand.

04:33:26.220 --> 04:33:28.799
I was right, she thought.

04:33:28.860 --> 04:33:30.720
They're taking me to the tunnel.

04:33:30.779 --> 04:33:34.559
Somehow, without her venom, she didn't

04:33:34.559 --> 04:33:36.239
feel quite as triumphant about being

04:33:36.239 --> 04:33:37.379
right as she'd hoped.

04:33:37.439 --> 04:33:40.379
She heard splashing, and a moment later

04:33:40.379 --> 04:33:42.299
water soaked through the sack as she was

04:33:42.299 --> 04:33:43.739
dragged through the stream.

04:33:43.799 --> 04:33:46.680
A couple of grunts followed, and Glory

04:33:46.680 --> 04:33:49.139
felt herself lifted up into the air, then

04:33:49.139 --> 04:33:50.639
dropped onto cold stone.

04:33:50.700 --> 04:33:53.759
Something shoved at her tail, and she

04:33:53.759 --> 04:33:56.819
started to slide down and down, as if it

04:33:56.819 --> 04:33:57.959
were slick ice below her.

04:33:58.020 --> 04:34:01.139
Wait, she thought with a sickening

04:34:01.139 --> 04:34:01.500
lurch.

04:34:01.560 --> 04:34:03.900
The tunnel to the desert doesn't go

04:34:03.900 --> 04:34:04.200
down.

04:34:04.259 --> 04:34:05.639
Where am I?

04:34:05.700 --> 04:34:08.880
She smacked into a wall and slid around a

04:34:08.880 --> 04:34:10.619
corner, picking up speed again.

04:34:10.680 --> 04:34:13.200
This isn't the hold of the kingdom of

04:34:13.200 --> 04:34:15.599
sand, but it feels like that hole.

04:34:15.720 --> 04:34:18.599
So is this the same kind of passageway?

04:34:18.659 --> 04:34:20.459
ripped into the world where it shouldn't

04:34:20.459 --> 04:34:20.639
be?

04:34:20.759 --> 04:34:22.919
And where does this one end?

04:34:22.979 --> 04:34:26.880
She tumbled suddenly into open space and

04:34:26.880 --> 04:34:29.880
slammed into a pile of thin firs, which

04:34:29.880 --> 04:34:31.680
did not do much to blunt the impact of

04:34:31.680 --> 04:34:32.639
the rocks underneath them.

04:34:32.759 --> 04:34:35.819
Glory lay there for a moment, trying not

04:34:35.819 --> 04:34:36.419
to groan.

04:34:36.479 --> 04:34:38.939
Every bone in her body ached.

04:34:39.060 --> 04:34:41.099
Every scale felt as though it had been

04:34:41.099 --> 04:34:41.819
scraped raw.

04:34:41.880 --> 04:34:44.279
She was pretty sure she'd bent her tongue

04:34:44.279 --> 04:34:45.180
when she landed.

04:34:45.240 --> 04:34:46.799
She could taste blood in her mouth.

04:34:46.860 --> 04:34:49.680
The smell of death and smoke was stronger

04:34:49.680 --> 04:34:52.380
now, and it was no longer raining, but

04:34:52.380 --> 04:34:53.880
there was hardly any light coming through

04:34:53.880 --> 04:34:54.360
the sack.

04:34:54.479 --> 04:34:57.180
This was definitely not the desert.

04:34:57.240 --> 04:35:00.659
It was chilly, instead of blazingly warm

04:35:00.659 --> 04:35:02.939
although the sound of a fire crackled

04:35:02.939 --> 04:35:03.720
somewhere nearby.

04:35:03.779 --> 04:35:06.179
Glory could hear a distant rumble like

04:35:06.179 --> 04:35:08.639
faraway thunderclouds, except that it

04:35:08.639 --> 04:35:10.139
felt like it was coming from below the

04:35:10.139 --> 04:35:12.179
rocks instead of up in the sky.

04:35:12.240 --> 04:35:15.540
Heavy feet thudded down beside her, and

04:35:15.540 --> 04:35:17.459
something snuffled loudly around the

04:35:17.459 --> 04:35:17.759
sack.

04:35:17.819 --> 04:35:20.400
Its breathing sounded the same as

04:35:20.400 --> 04:35:22.439
whatever had eaten the dead sloth in the

04:35:22.439 --> 04:35:22.740
night.

04:35:22.740 --> 04:35:24.779
Glory clenched her talons.

04:35:24.840 --> 04:35:27.479
Was it planning to eat her, because it

04:35:27.479 --> 04:35:29.400
was in for quite a surprise if it...

04:35:29.400 --> 04:35:33.119
Another one, said a disapproving voice.

04:35:33.240 --> 04:35:36.240
The snuffling hitched for a 2nd, as if

04:35:36.240 --> 04:35:38.700
startled, and then a hoarse voice beside

04:35:38.700 --> 04:35:42.299
Gloria's head said, yeah, easy catch.

04:35:42.360 --> 04:35:44.459
She was all alone in the forest.

04:35:44.520 --> 04:35:47.159
Stupid, like all rain wings.

04:35:47.220 --> 04:35:49.860
Dragons, Lori thought.

04:35:49.919 --> 04:35:52.139
Relief warred with fury.

04:35:52.200 --> 04:35:54.299
They're just dragons.

04:35:54.360 --> 04:35:56.639
Nothing mysterious and creepy.

04:35:56.700 --> 04:35:58.979
Apart from the basic mysterious

04:35:58.979 --> 04:36:01.259
creepiness of kidnapping other dragons

04:36:01.259 --> 04:36:04.200
that is, well, I can handle a couple of

04:36:04.200 --> 04:36:06.900
creepy dragons, just as soon as they take

04:36:06.900 --> 04:36:07.919
this sack off me.

04:36:07.979 --> 04:36:11.159
She flexed her claws, wondering if she

04:36:11.159 --> 04:36:12.360
could rip through the cloth around them.

04:36:12.419 --> 04:36:16.259
Didn't you get the message, said the 1st

04:36:16.259 --> 04:36:16.739
dragon.

04:36:16.799 --> 04:36:19.919
Yeah, said the one with a garbled

04:36:19.919 --> 04:36:20.340
breathing.

04:36:20.459 --> 04:36:23.520
But I like the prey in the rainforest, and

04:36:23.520 --> 04:36:26.099
I was hungry, and then this dragon was

04:36:26.099 --> 04:36:27.360
just asking to get caught.

04:36:27.419 --> 04:36:29.519
Besides, I thought his message was

04:36:29.519 --> 04:36:29.879
stupid.

04:36:29.939 --> 04:36:32.279
It's not stupid.

04:36:32.340 --> 04:36:33.779
If it keeps us safe.

04:36:33.840 --> 04:36:35.759
The 1st dragon side.

04:36:35.819 --> 04:36:38.400
Throw her in with the others, but from

04:36:38.400 --> 04:36:40.380
now on, do as you're told.

04:36:40.439 --> 04:36:41.999
Yeah, yeah.

04:36:42.060 --> 04:36:44.099
Grumbled the 2nd dragon.

04:36:44.159 --> 04:36:46.200
All right, I got it.

04:36:46.259 --> 04:36:49.199
No more hunting or grabbing dragons in

04:36:49.199 --> 04:36:51.959
the rainforest until Death Bringer says

04:36:51.959 --> 04:36:52.559
it's all clear.

04:36:52.619 --> 04:36:57.179
Chapter 20.

04:36:57.540 --> 04:37:01.080
Glory had never been so glad that her

04:37:01.080 --> 04:37:01.860
scales were hidden.

04:37:01.919 --> 04:37:03.899
There was no way she could stop the

04:37:03.899 --> 04:37:05.039
colors flooding through them.

04:37:05.099 --> 04:37:07.259
She couldn't even guess what they were

04:37:07.259 --> 04:37:07.979
turning to right now.

04:37:08.040 --> 04:37:10.919
Deathbringer did know who was taking the

04:37:10.919 --> 04:37:11.880
missing rain wings.

04:37:11.939 --> 04:37:15.179
He was connected to them, and somehow he

04:37:15.179 --> 04:37:17.939
had told them to stop, until it's all

04:37:17.939 --> 04:37:18.779
clear.

04:37:18.840 --> 04:37:19.740
What did that mean?

04:37:19.740 --> 04:37:21.779
Until he'd finished killing the

04:37:21.779 --> 04:37:24.180
dragonettes, or until Glory and her

04:37:24.180 --> 04:37:25.740
friends stopped snooping around the

04:37:25.740 --> 04:37:26.459
tunnel.

04:37:26.520 --> 04:37:29.040
And how did he get a message to these

04:37:29.040 --> 04:37:30.299
dragons?

04:37:30.360 --> 04:37:32.700
Glory had left him in the ice kingdom, and

04:37:32.700 --> 04:37:34.319
then caught him coming out of the desert

04:37:34.319 --> 04:37:35.700
tunnel into the rainforest.

04:37:35.759 --> 04:37:38.579
He'd said he followed the dragonettes to

04:37:38.579 --> 04:37:40.619
the hole in the sand, but maybe he'd

04:37:40.619 --> 04:37:41.279
known about it before.

04:37:41.279 --> 04:37:44.159
Maybe he'd gotten there first, gone

04:37:44.159 --> 04:37:46.199
through to this place, warned these

04:37:46.199 --> 04:37:48.479
dragons, and then gone back to the desert

04:37:48.479 --> 04:37:50.579
tunnel after the dragonettes were back in

04:37:50.579 --> 04:37:52.499
the rainforest, but...

04:37:52.499 --> 04:37:55.319
Glory remembered that Deathbringer had

04:37:55.319 --> 04:37:57.539
conveniently appeared just in time to

04:37:57.539 --> 04:37:59.219
stop them from catching the creature in

04:37:59.219 --> 04:37:59.519
the dark.

04:37:59.639 --> 04:38:02.459
He did that on purpose.

04:38:02.520 --> 04:38:05.400
He was warning off the other dragon.

04:38:05.459 --> 04:38:07.380
This one with a weird breathing.

04:38:07.439 --> 04:38:10.079
Deathbringer knew we would catch him.

04:38:10.139 --> 04:38:12.599
Maybe he wanted us to catch him.

04:38:12.659 --> 04:38:16.560
Her tail curled, and my friends are alone

04:38:16.560 --> 04:38:17.520
with Deathbringer.

04:38:17.580 --> 04:38:19.080
I have to get back to them.

04:38:19.200 --> 04:38:21.119
I have to get back right now.

04:38:21.180 --> 04:38:24.419
She flung open her wings and lashed her

04:38:24.419 --> 04:38:26.580
tail, clawing at the sack frantically.

04:38:26.639 --> 04:38:29.520
Whoa, yelled the hoarse voice.

04:38:29.580 --> 04:38:31.139
A little help here.

04:38:31.200 --> 04:38:33.479
Gloria's heart sank at the sound of

04:38:33.479 --> 04:38:34.799
footsteps and wing beats.

04:38:34.860 --> 04:38:37.259
There were a lot more than 2 dragons out

04:38:37.259 --> 04:38:37.500
there.

04:38:37.560 --> 04:38:40.259
She kicked out blindly, fighting as hard

04:38:40.259 --> 04:38:42.659
as she could, but Talons grabbed her from

04:38:42.659 --> 04:38:44.520
all sides, pinning her to the ground.

04:38:44.580 --> 04:38:47.099
You'll never get her there like this

04:38:47.099 --> 04:38:49.080
gasped one of the dragons.

04:38:49.139 --> 04:38:50.939
You'll have to knock her out again.

04:38:51.000 --> 04:38:54.779
My pleasure, said the hoarse voice.

04:38:54.840 --> 04:38:57.540
And once again, something slammed into

04:38:57.540 --> 04:39:00.060
Glory's head, and then all was darkness.

04:39:00.119 --> 04:39:03.059
Hey.

04:39:03.119 --> 04:39:06.299
Something nosed glory in the ribs, and

04:39:06.299 --> 04:39:07.919
she woke up with a small yelp of pain.

04:39:07.979 --> 04:39:09.419
Are you awake?

04:39:09.479 --> 04:39:13.020
Tiny claws lifted glory's eyelids and

04:39:13.020 --> 04:39:14.939
something blurry came way too close to

04:39:14.939 --> 04:39:16.200
her snout to peer at her.

04:39:16.259 --> 04:39:20.219
Oomph, Glory said, through the gag around

04:39:20.219 --> 04:39:20.699
her mouth.

04:39:20.759 --> 04:39:23.579
She tried to push the something away, but

04:39:23.579 --> 04:39:25.619
her talons felt heavy, and she missed.

04:39:25.680 --> 04:39:28.860
Ha ha, don't even try, said the little

04:39:28.860 --> 04:39:29.340
voice.

04:39:29.400 --> 04:39:31.619
I've spent my whole life waking up

04:39:31.619 --> 04:39:33.360
dragons who'd rather be sleeping instead

04:39:33.360 --> 04:39:33.959
of training me.

04:39:34.020 --> 04:39:36.360
I am excellent at dodging when they get

04:39:36.360 --> 04:39:37.319
all mad about it.

04:39:37.380 --> 04:39:40.020
The tiny claws poked at her rough.

04:39:40.080 --> 04:39:41.759
How come I don't know you?

04:39:41.880 --> 04:39:45.240
Glory said again.

04:39:45.299 --> 04:39:46.560
Her head hurt.

04:39:46.680 --> 04:39:48.840
She rested it back on the ground and

04:39:48.840 --> 04:39:51.000
blinked until the world came into focus.

04:39:51.060 --> 04:39:54.720
A small diamond shaped snout hovered only

04:39:54.720 --> 04:39:56.220
a few inches from hers.

04:39:56.279 --> 04:39:59.459
Gigantic dark eyes peered out of gold and

04:39:59.459 --> 04:40:00.360
orange scales.

04:40:00.419 --> 04:40:02.459
The little dragonette couldn't have been

04:40:02.459 --> 04:40:03.479
more than 3 years old.

04:40:03.540 --> 04:40:05.340
She poked Glory's rough again.

04:40:05.400 --> 04:40:07.979
Don't worry, I know you can't talk.

04:40:08.040 --> 04:40:09.959
I'm the only one without a gag.

04:40:10.020 --> 04:40:12.180
They decided my venom wasn't strong

04:40:12.180 --> 04:40:14.580
enough, or I couldn't shoot it far enough

04:40:14.580 --> 04:40:16.680
to be dangerous, or something, I guess

04:40:16.680 --> 04:40:19.380
which is a little unfair because if

04:40:19.380 --> 04:40:23.159
somebody would just train me properly, I

04:40:23.159 --> 04:40:25.319
think I'd be super great at it, and then

04:40:25.319 --> 04:40:27.540
these horrible dragons would be super

04:40:27.540 --> 04:40:30.000
sorry for putting me in a cage.

04:40:30.060 --> 04:40:33.540
A ripple of scarlet fury moved through

04:40:33.540 --> 04:40:34.380
her wings.

04:40:34.439 --> 04:40:36.840
Glory reluctantly sat up so she could

04:40:36.840 --> 04:40:37.319
look around.

04:40:37.380 --> 04:40:40.560
The pain in her head flared viciously, and

04:40:40.560 --> 04:40:42.119
she had to close her eyes until it

04:40:42.119 --> 04:40:43.680
receded into a dull throb.

04:40:43.740 --> 04:40:45.360
When she opened them again.

04:40:45.419 --> 04:40:47.759
She realized that the blurriness around

04:40:47.759 --> 04:40:49.500
her wasn't just her eyes.

04:40:49.500 --> 04:40:51.659
The air was hazy with smoke.

04:40:51.720 --> 04:40:54.779
Pulsing heat wafted over her scales

04:40:54.779 --> 04:40:56.880
although she couldn't see any sign of a

04:40:56.880 --> 04:41:00.180
fire, she glanced up and saw jagged stone

04:41:00.180 --> 04:41:01.799
walls pressing close overhead.

04:41:01.860 --> 04:41:04.200
It seems like the heat was coming from

04:41:04.200 --> 04:41:05.340
the rocks themselves.

04:41:05.400 --> 04:41:08.459
Back in a cave, she thought.

04:41:08.580 --> 04:41:09.840
Awesome.

04:41:09.900 --> 04:41:13.200
The sack was gone, but the bindings

04:41:13.200 --> 04:41:14.880
around her wings and claws were still in

04:41:14.880 --> 04:41:15.180
place.

04:41:15.240 --> 04:41:18.419
Her mouth was still bound as well, but it

04:41:18.419 --> 04:41:19.500
felt different from before.

04:41:19.619 --> 04:41:23.340
Whatever clamped her snout shut now, was

04:41:23.340 --> 04:41:25.139
much heavier than the earlier vines.

04:41:25.200 --> 04:41:27.360
She crossed her eyes trying to get a look

04:41:27.360 --> 04:41:28.380
at it.

04:41:28.439 --> 04:41:31.080
It's a metal band, the little dragonette

04:41:31.080 --> 04:41:32.700
explained, tilting her head

04:41:32.700 --> 04:41:33.419
sympathetically.

04:41:33.479 --> 04:41:36.060
Like this one around my neck?

04:41:36.119 --> 04:41:37.619
It's to keep you from using your venom.

04:41:37.680 --> 04:41:40.139
But it's also so we can't camouflage

04:41:40.139 --> 04:41:41.099
ourselves and disappear.

04:41:41.159 --> 04:41:43.200
They'll always be able to see the metal

04:41:43.200 --> 04:41:43.740
band.

04:41:43.799 --> 04:41:46.380
She pointed to a thick, brassy clamp

04:41:46.380 --> 04:41:47.580
around her own neck.

04:41:47.639 --> 04:41:49.680
Smart but annoying, right?

04:41:49.799 --> 04:41:51.419
She paused.

04:41:51.479 --> 04:41:52.259
Kind of like me.

04:41:52.319 --> 04:41:53.220
Ha ha.

04:41:53.279 --> 04:41:55.680
My name's Kinkaju, by the way, in case

04:41:55.680 --> 04:41:56.220
you were wondering.

04:41:56.279 --> 04:42:00.060
So there's one of the missing rain wings

04:42:00.060 --> 04:42:01.080
Glory thought.

04:42:01.139 --> 04:42:03.000
Where are the others?

04:42:03.060 --> 04:42:06.000
The small cave held only herself and the

04:42:06.000 --> 04:42:06.720
dragonette?

04:42:06.779 --> 04:42:09.060
A half moon of light glowed the cave

04:42:09.060 --> 04:42:10.259
opening not far away.

04:42:10.319 --> 04:42:12.720
Glory took a tentative step toward it

04:42:12.720 --> 04:42:14.639
then another when nothing happened.

04:42:14.700 --> 04:42:16.500
Nothing fell from the roof.

04:42:16.560 --> 04:42:18.000
Nothing attacked her.

04:42:18.060 --> 04:42:19.439
No alarms went off.

04:42:19.500 --> 04:42:21.599
What sort of prison was this?

04:42:21.659 --> 04:42:24.659
Kingachu followed her, still chattering.

04:42:24.720 --> 04:42:27.180
I know what you're thinking, she said.

04:42:27.240 --> 04:42:29.279
I'm super good at that, especially

04:42:29.279 --> 04:42:31.139
nowadays when I'm the only one who can

04:42:31.139 --> 04:42:33.240
talk, and so I have to imagine the other

04:42:33.240 --> 04:42:35.099
side of every conversation I have.

04:42:35.159 --> 04:42:37.860
Maybe telepathy is contagious or

04:42:37.860 --> 04:42:38.099
something.

04:42:38.159 --> 04:42:40.619
But anyway, you're thinking you can walk

04:42:40.619 --> 04:42:42.900
out of this cave, and trust me, you

04:42:42.900 --> 04:42:43.319
can't.

04:42:43.380 --> 04:42:44.939
But you'll have to go see for yourself

04:42:44.939 --> 04:42:47.819
because everybody does, I guess, instead

04:42:47.819 --> 04:42:48.479
of listening to me.

04:42:48.540 --> 04:42:51.060
Gloria reached the entrance and stopped.

04:42:51.180 --> 04:42:52.919
Kinkachu was right.

04:42:52.979 --> 04:42:54.659
There was no walking out this way.

04:42:54.720 --> 04:42:58.619
A wide sluggish river of molten lava load

04:42:58.619 --> 04:43:00.599
passed just outside the cave.

04:43:00.659 --> 04:43:03.599
It glowed gold and orange bright, the

04:43:03.599 --> 04:43:05.639
only splash of color in a barren black

04:43:05.639 --> 04:43:08.880
landscape, with her wings bound, glory

04:43:08.880 --> 04:43:09.720
would never make it across.

04:43:09.779 --> 04:43:12.360
She leaned out to see where the lava

04:43:12.360 --> 04:43:13.020
river started.

04:43:13.080 --> 04:43:16.020
A hulking dark mountain filled the sky

04:43:16.020 --> 04:43:18.299
half hidden by the smoke pouring out the

04:43:18.299 --> 04:43:18.599
top.

04:43:18.659 --> 04:43:21.779
Smaller rivulets of lava dappled the

04:43:21.779 --> 04:43:24.180
slope, and a red glow came from a few

04:43:24.180 --> 04:43:25.080
holes in the rocks.

04:43:25.139 --> 04:43:27.479
It was hard to tell whether it was night

04:43:27.479 --> 04:43:27.959
or day.

04:43:28.020 --> 04:43:30.959
The light was so strange, and the sky was

04:43:30.959 --> 04:43:32.520
swathed in dark clouds.

04:43:32.639 --> 04:43:35.040
Glory guessed that she'd been knocked out

04:43:35.040 --> 04:43:36.180
for a few hours at least.

04:43:36.240 --> 04:43:39.119
The rotten eggs smell was thick in the

04:43:39.119 --> 04:43:39.240
air.

04:43:39.299 --> 04:43:41.639
Sinister, right?

04:43:41.700 --> 04:43:44.340
Kinkachu said in her ear, and glory

04:43:44.340 --> 04:43:44.759
jumped.

04:43:44.819 --> 04:43:46.799
Who would actually want to live here?

04:43:46.860 --> 04:43:47.819
I don't get it.

04:43:47.880 --> 04:43:50.520
Who does live here?

04:43:50.580 --> 04:43:51.840
Glory wondered.

04:43:51.900 --> 04:43:53.639
The talons of peace?

04:43:54.299 --> 04:43:55.139
Is this where they hide?

04:43:55.200 --> 04:43:58.619
And then she realized that parts of the

04:43:58.619 --> 04:44:01.020
landscape were moving, and they weren't

04:44:01.020 --> 04:44:01.979
rocks after all.

04:44:02.040 --> 04:44:05.939
They were dragons, black dragons, with

04:44:05.939 --> 04:44:07.740
silver scales glittering under their

04:44:07.740 --> 04:44:08.099
wings.

04:44:08.220 --> 04:44:10.380
She could see at least a 100 of them

04:44:10.380 --> 04:44:12.180
scattered across the mountain, and

04:44:12.180 --> 04:44:13.619
several more flying above it.

04:44:13.680 --> 04:44:17.400
She inhaled sharply, and regretted it, as

04:44:17.400 --> 04:44:18.540
sulfur filled her nose.

04:44:18.659 --> 04:44:20.459
I know where we are.

04:44:20.520 --> 04:44:23.700
This is the secret home of the night

04:44:23.700 --> 04:44:24.180
wings.

04:44:24.240 --> 04:44:28.860
Chapter 21.

04:44:28.979 --> 04:44:32.819
Glory turned to the dragonette and waved

04:44:32.819 --> 04:44:34.380
her bound claws of the gag around her

04:44:34.380 --> 04:44:34.560
mouth.

04:44:34.619 --> 04:44:38.580
Oh my gosh, said Kinkachu, staring at

04:44:38.580 --> 04:44:40.619
Glory's scales as they changed color.

04:44:40.680 --> 04:44:42.419
You're excited about something.

04:44:42.479 --> 04:44:44.220
I wonder what?

04:44:44.279 --> 04:44:46.259
Ooh, and curious.

04:44:46.319 --> 04:44:48.180
Sure, of course you are.

04:44:48.240 --> 04:44:49.560
You must have lots of questions.

04:44:49.619 --> 04:44:52.200
I sure had lots of questions when I got

04:44:52.200 --> 04:44:52.380
here.

04:44:52.439 --> 04:44:55.740
Hey, now you're...

04:44:55.740 --> 04:44:59.040
Frustrated, super frustrated and getting

04:44:59.040 --> 04:44:59.639
mad.

04:44:59.759 --> 04:45:03.360
Wow, what are you so exasperated.

04:45:03.419 --> 04:45:05.340
Glory shoved her aside and marched back

04:45:05.340 --> 04:45:05.880
into the cave.

04:45:05.939 --> 04:45:10.919
Oh, you're mad at me, said Kinkachu

04:45:10.979 --> 04:45:12.060
trotting along behind her.

04:45:12.119 --> 04:45:13.500
I'm used to that.

04:45:13.560 --> 04:45:16.799
The cave was not very big, ending

04:45:16.799 --> 04:45:18.959
abruptly at a steep drop off at the back

04:45:18.959 --> 04:45:21.180
Glory stared down into a pitch black

04:45:21.180 --> 04:45:21.840
abyss.

04:45:21.900 --> 04:45:25.380
With no fire, and no ability to see in

04:45:25.380 --> 04:45:25.979
the dark.

04:45:26.459 --> 04:45:28.080
No rain wing would get very close to that

04:45:28.080 --> 04:45:30.959
even if her wings were free, glory

04:45:30.959 --> 04:45:31.619
wouldn't go near it.

04:45:31.680 --> 04:45:34.560
That's how I visit the other prisoners

04:45:34.560 --> 04:45:35.759
Kingachu said.

04:45:35.819 --> 04:45:38.400
All their caves, and the one I'm supposed

04:45:38.400 --> 04:45:40.020
to stay in open out onto this.

04:45:40.080 --> 04:45:43.080
Glory looked at the dragonette with new

04:45:43.080 --> 04:45:43.380
respect.

04:45:43.439 --> 04:45:46.439
Kinkachu's wings weren't bound, but they

04:45:46.439 --> 04:45:46.979
were tiny.

04:45:47.040 --> 04:45:49.740
Most 3 year old dragons couldn't fly for

04:45:49.740 --> 04:45:50.819
long without needing a rest.

04:45:50.880 --> 04:45:53.220
She couldn't have known how long she'd

04:45:53.220 --> 04:45:55.080
have to fly when she 1st jumped into the

04:45:55.080 --> 04:45:57.360
darkness, looking for other prisoners.

04:45:57.419 --> 04:45:59.700
That was a special kind of brave.

04:45:59.759 --> 04:46:01.380
And crazy.

04:46:01.439 --> 04:46:03.900
Kinkatu tilted her head at glory.

04:46:03.959 --> 04:46:07.380
I have no idea what that color means, she

04:46:07.380 --> 04:46:07.680
said.

04:46:07.799 --> 04:46:10.380
Wow, you really are different.

04:46:10.439 --> 04:46:13.139
She reached up and tugged on the ropes

04:46:13.139 --> 04:46:14.040
around Glory's wings.

04:46:14.099 --> 04:46:17.459
But this is the same, she sighed.

04:46:17.580 --> 04:46:20.220
I can't get any of them off.

04:46:20.279 --> 04:46:20.639
I' sorry.

04:46:20.700 --> 04:46:23.279
It's some kind of super impossible knot.

04:46:23.400 --> 04:46:25.740
Glory held up her claws.

04:46:25.799 --> 04:46:28.560
Thick canvas covered them, tied together

04:46:28.560 --> 04:46:30.299
with another robe around each forearm.

04:46:30.360 --> 04:46:34.439
Here too, Kikachu said, pointing to the

04:46:34.439 --> 04:46:36.299
knot, see how tight that is?

04:46:36.360 --> 04:46:38.279
Glory squinted at it.

04:46:38.340 --> 04:46:39.959
She didn't know much about knots.

04:46:40.080 --> 04:46:43.380
She nodded to Kingaju's talons, and the

04:46:43.380 --> 04:46:44.520
little dragonette shook her head.

04:46:44.639 --> 04:46:46.680
They're not sharp enough to cut through

04:46:46.680 --> 04:46:47.220
the rope.

04:46:47.279 --> 04:46:48.180
I've tried.

04:46:48.240 --> 04:46:51.479
Kinkachu sliced one tiny claw across the

04:46:51.479 --> 04:46:53.400
rope, but it didn't even look frayed.

04:46:53.400 --> 04:46:55.319
Glory lashed her tail.

04:46:55.380 --> 04:46:57.599
It is frustrating.

04:46:57.659 --> 04:46:59.340
Kinkachu agreed.

04:46:59.400 --> 04:47:00.900
Stupid night wings.

04:47:00.959 --> 04:47:03.240
But if we tried to escape, they'd read

04:47:03.240 --> 04:47:05.400
our minds or foresee it and stop us

04:47:05.400 --> 04:47:06.479
anyway, right?

04:47:06.540 --> 04:47:08.939
Glory discovered that she could still

04:47:08.939 --> 04:47:09.540
growl.

04:47:09.599 --> 04:47:11.880
Does that mean you want to try?

04:47:11.939 --> 04:47:14.459
Kinkaju asked, perking up.

04:47:14.520 --> 04:47:16.319
Her ruff flared around her face.

04:47:16.380 --> 04:47:19.500
Because nobody else wants to try escaping

04:47:19.500 --> 04:47:22.439
but I so do, because, oh my gosh, you

04:47:22.439 --> 04:47:24.659
haven't even seen how awful the food is

04:47:24.659 --> 04:47:25.500
here.

04:47:25.560 --> 04:47:27.419
They keep bringing us horrible dead

04:47:27.419 --> 04:47:28.020
things.

04:47:28.139 --> 04:47:30.720
I mean, things that have been dead for

04:47:30.720 --> 04:47:32.340
weeks, I think.

04:47:32.400 --> 04:47:35.639
It is mega gross and makes us totally

04:47:35.639 --> 04:47:37.020
sick when we eat it.

04:47:37.080 --> 04:47:38.400
There's no fruit at all.

04:47:38.459 --> 04:47:41.340
Taper finally just let himself starve to

04:47:41.340 --> 04:47:41.639
death.

04:47:41.700 --> 04:47:42.540
It's so awful.

04:47:42.599 --> 04:47:44.939
I try to eat as little as I can.

04:47:45.000 --> 04:47:48.299
How am I supposed to make an escape plan

04:47:48.299 --> 04:47:50.099
with a dragonette who won't shut up?

04:47:50.159 --> 04:47:51.540
Glory wondered.

04:47:51.659 --> 04:47:54.119
When I can't even ask her any questions.

04:47:54.240 --> 04:47:57.779
Such as, what did the night wings want

04:47:57.779 --> 04:47:58.919
with the rain wings anyway?

04:47:58.979 --> 04:48:01.740
Why were they kidnapping them and holding

04:48:01.740 --> 04:48:02.340
them prisoner?

04:48:02.400 --> 04:48:04.740
What did Deathbringer have to do with

04:48:04.740 --> 04:48:05.279
this plan?

04:48:05.279 --> 04:48:07.740
And why had he told them to stop?

04:48:07.799 --> 04:48:09.119
Confused?

04:48:09.180 --> 04:48:11.819
Kinkachu guessed, pointing at glory

04:48:11.819 --> 04:48:15.720
scales, and... frustrated again.

04:48:15.779 --> 04:48:19.979
I need a color for stop that, Glory

04:48:19.979 --> 04:48:20.340
thought.

04:48:20.400 --> 04:48:22.680
Something flapped outside the cave

04:48:22.680 --> 04:48:23.340
entrance.

04:48:23.400 --> 04:48:25.919
Kinkachu turned toward the sound, then

04:48:25.919 --> 04:48:27.479
winced, and closed her eyes.

04:48:27.540 --> 04:48:29.700
Glory pushed past her and peered out.

04:48:29.759 --> 04:48:32.520
Three night wings flew over the lava

04:48:32.520 --> 04:48:34.919
river, and disappeared into another cave

04:48:34.919 --> 04:48:36.240
not far from glories.

04:48:36.360 --> 04:48:39.060
A few moments later, they reappeared

04:48:39.060 --> 04:48:41.520
dragging a limp rain wing behind them.

04:48:41.580 --> 04:48:44.819
The rain wings scales were a heavy gray

04:48:44.819 --> 04:48:46.439
like rain clouds.

04:48:46.500 --> 04:48:49.139
It was a color of sadness glory hadn't

04:48:49.139 --> 04:48:50.459
seen on any other rain wing.

04:48:50.520 --> 04:48:53.400
He was conscious, but neither struggled

04:48:53.400 --> 04:48:54.779
nor helped the night wings.

04:48:54.840 --> 04:48:57.479
He just hung between them, like he'd

04:48:57.479 --> 04:48:58.200
given up completely.

04:48:58.259 --> 04:49:01.139
Glory thought of Jamboo's vibrantly

04:49:01.139 --> 04:49:03.659
joyful scales and felt a stab of anger.

04:49:03.720 --> 04:49:06.779
At the night wings, for ripping innocent

04:49:06.779 --> 04:49:09.240
dragons from their homes, and at the

04:49:09.240 --> 04:49:11.220
other rain wings, for letting this happen

04:49:11.220 --> 04:49:13.380
to their friends, without even noticing

04:49:13.380 --> 04:49:14.880
or caring that they were gone.

04:49:14.939 --> 04:49:18.419
The black dragons lifted the rain wing

04:49:18.419 --> 04:49:20.340
over the river and carried him up the

04:49:20.340 --> 04:49:22.380
slope of the mountain, letting his tail

04:49:22.380 --> 04:49:23.520
bump across the rocks.

04:49:23.520 --> 04:49:26.400
Glory watched until they all vanished

04:49:26.400 --> 04:49:28.740
into a sort of fortress halfway up the

04:49:28.740 --> 04:49:29.040
mountain.

04:49:29.099 --> 04:49:32.520
It looked like a jumbled pile of rocks, so

04:49:32.520 --> 04:49:33.900
she hadn't realized it was a building

04:49:33.900 --> 04:49:34.259
before.

04:49:34.319 --> 04:49:38.159
Poor Gibbon, Kinkachu said.

04:49:38.220 --> 04:49:39.959
They take him all the time.

04:49:40.080 --> 04:49:42.779
I guess his venom is way more interesting

04:49:42.779 --> 04:49:43.979
than mine or something.

04:49:44.040 --> 04:49:46.560
Glory whirled to stare at her.

04:49:46.680 --> 04:49:49.080
Oh yeah, Kinkaju said.

04:49:49.139 --> 04:49:51.180
When they take you up there, try

04:49:51.180 --> 04:49:52.919
pretending your venom doesn't work right

04:49:52.919 --> 04:49:53.459
or something.

04:49:53.520 --> 04:49:55.560
That's all they want us to do.

04:49:55.619 --> 04:49:57.000
Melt things.

04:49:57.060 --> 04:49:58.860
It's so weird.

04:49:58.860 --> 04:50:01.200
Like, can't they melt their own things?

04:50:01.259 --> 04:50:04.139
So far, I've melted an orange and a pile

04:50:04.139 --> 04:50:04.680
of leaves.

04:50:04.740 --> 04:50:07.139
They told me to melt this metal claw

04:50:07.139 --> 04:50:09.240
thing too, but of course that's stupid.

04:50:09.299 --> 04:50:11.580
Our venom doesn't work on non-living

04:50:11.580 --> 04:50:11.880
stuff.

04:50:11.939 --> 04:50:14.099
And then they had me spit some venom into

04:50:14.099 --> 04:50:16.020
a bowl, and who knows what they want with

04:50:16.020 --> 04:50:16.259
that?

04:50:16.319 --> 04:50:17.819
I don't get it.

04:50:17.880 --> 04:50:20.520
They're studying us.

04:50:20.580 --> 04:50:24.060
Glory realized, or at least they're

04:50:24.060 --> 04:50:24.959
studying our venom.

04:50:25.020 --> 04:50:28.139
She turned and began pacing the length of

04:50:28.139 --> 04:50:28.680
the cave.

04:50:28.740 --> 04:50:31.080
Are they hoping to use it themselves?

04:50:31.200 --> 04:50:32.639
As a weapon?

04:50:32.700 --> 04:50:34.919
But the night wings don't fight.

04:50:34.979 --> 04:50:36.659
They stay out of the war.

04:50:36.720 --> 04:50:38.759
So who do they need weapons for?

04:50:38.819 --> 04:50:41.580
Are they planning to join the war soon?

04:50:41.700 --> 04:50:43.259
On whose side?

04:50:43.319 --> 04:50:46.979
Blisters, of course, she thought

04:50:46.979 --> 04:50:49.259
immediately, smacking herself in the head

04:50:49.259 --> 04:50:49.740
with her tail.

04:50:49.799 --> 04:50:52.680
That's why they wanted us to choose her

04:50:52.680 --> 04:50:53.459
for the prophecy.

04:50:53.520 --> 04:50:55.740
But why join the war now?

04:50:55.799 --> 04:50:58.200
And why torture rain wings for their

04:50:58.200 --> 04:51:00.299
venom, when night wings have their own

04:51:00.299 --> 04:51:02.939
ever so special powers they never shut up

04:51:02.939 --> 04:51:03.180
about?

04:51:03.240 --> 04:51:07.020
That must be what thinking hard looks

04:51:07.020 --> 04:51:07.319
like.

04:51:07.439 --> 04:51:10.740
Kinkachu said, hopping onto a boulder and

04:51:10.740 --> 04:51:12.299
watching glory with great interest.

04:51:12.360 --> 04:51:15.060
Your scales are all kinds of colors right

04:51:15.060 --> 04:51:15.360
now.

04:51:15.419 --> 04:51:17.819
I've never seen another rain wing do

04:51:17.819 --> 04:51:17.939
that.

04:51:18.000 --> 04:51:20.700
Oh, I wish you could talk to me.

04:51:20.759 --> 04:51:22.439
Me too.

04:51:22.500 --> 04:51:23.880
Glory thought.

04:51:23.939 --> 04:51:26.040
Maybe we could escape together.

04:51:26.099 --> 04:51:28.979
And then you could be my teacher, Kinkaju

04:51:28.979 --> 04:51:29.279
said.

04:51:29.340 --> 04:51:31.799
I swear I'm not as awful as everyone says

04:51:31.799 --> 04:51:34.500
but we'd have to get you across the lava

04:51:34.500 --> 04:51:36.119
and then we'd have to find the tunnel

04:51:36.119 --> 04:51:38.099
back to the rainforest, and then we'd

04:51:38.099 --> 04:51:40.020
have to get past the guards there, and

04:51:40.020 --> 04:51:41.459
then we'd have to get all your bindings

04:51:41.459 --> 04:51:41.759
off.

04:51:41.819 --> 04:51:43.919
Or maybe we'd have to do that first.

04:51:43.979 --> 04:51:46.380
Actually, that would make more sense.

04:51:46.439 --> 04:51:48.479
Because then you could fly and fight and

04:51:48.479 --> 04:51:48.720
stuff.

04:51:48.779 --> 04:51:51.000
But I have no idea how to do any of

04:51:51.000 --> 04:51:51.180
that.

04:51:51.299 --> 04:51:53.220
She stopped.

04:51:53.279 --> 04:51:55.860
Her wings drooping, and suddenly looked

04:51:55.860 --> 04:51:56.400
very young.

04:51:56.459 --> 04:51:59.639
Glory had been wondering why Kinkachu

04:51:59.639 --> 04:52:01.680
didn't escape on her own, but if she

04:52:01.680 --> 04:52:03.479
didn't know where the tunnel was, and

04:52:03.479 --> 04:52:06.119
there were guards to fight along away, it

04:52:06.119 --> 04:52:08.099
was a tall order for a little dragon

04:52:08.099 --> 04:52:10.560
especially when failure would surely mean

04:52:10.560 --> 04:52:12.659
she'd end up bound and gagged like the

04:52:12.659 --> 04:52:13.619
other rain wings.

04:52:13.680 --> 04:52:16.619
Maybe I could find something sharp enough

04:52:16.619 --> 04:52:18.840
to cut the ropes, Kinkaju said

04:52:18.840 --> 04:52:21.599
brightening again, like a really sharp

04:52:21.599 --> 04:52:25.259
rock, or, well, there's not much around

04:52:25.259 --> 04:52:26.159
here except rocks.

04:52:26.220 --> 04:52:29.279
Oh, or I could check one of the really

04:52:29.279 --> 04:52:31.380
disgusting dead things for sharp bones

04:52:31.380 --> 04:52:32.700
when our dinner comes.

04:52:32.759 --> 04:52:34.020
That would be pretty gross, though.

04:52:34.139 --> 04:52:35.639
Maybe you should do that.

04:52:35.700 --> 04:52:38.400
Glory thumbed her tail on the ground to

04:52:38.400 --> 04:52:39.720
get Kinkaju's attention.

04:52:39.779 --> 04:52:41.819
She pointed to her mouth, then her

04:52:41.819 --> 04:52:44.220
stomach, then her mouth again, and tried

04:52:44.220 --> 04:52:45.479
to turn her scales the color of

04:52:45.479 --> 04:52:45.959
curiosity.

04:52:46.020 --> 04:52:50.400
You're asking me a question, Kinkachu

04:52:50.400 --> 04:52:51.779
said, with great delight.

04:52:51.840 --> 04:52:53.459
Wait, let me guess.

04:52:53.520 --> 04:52:55.740
You're...

04:52:55.740 --> 04:52:57.180
Hungry.

04:52:57.240 --> 04:53:00.000
Glory frowned and tabbed the rope around

04:53:00.000 --> 04:53:02.279
her mouth, pointed to the cave opening

04:53:02.279 --> 04:53:04.979
flapped her arms like wings, pointed to

04:53:04.979 --> 04:53:06.900
her stomach, and pointed to the rope

04:53:06.900 --> 04:53:07.319
again.

04:53:07.380 --> 04:53:09.540
Kinkaju furrowed her brow.

04:53:09.599 --> 04:53:12.360
Something about the night wings and

04:53:12.360 --> 04:53:13.080
food.

04:53:13.200 --> 04:53:16.259
Oh, oh, I know.

04:53:16.319 --> 04:53:18.299
You want to know if they take off the

04:53:18.299 --> 04:53:19.619
metal band when they feed us?

04:53:19.680 --> 04:53:20.400
Am I right?

04:53:20.520 --> 04:53:21.000
Am I right?

04:53:21.060 --> 04:53:23.700
She turned toward the cave entrance as

04:53:23.700 --> 04:53:24.419
Glory nodded.

04:53:24.479 --> 04:53:26.639
I guess you're about to find out.

04:53:26.700 --> 04:53:29.400
The little dragonette darted over the

04:53:29.400 --> 04:53:31.619
drop and vanished into one of the gaps in

04:53:31.619 --> 04:53:32.220
the far wall.

04:53:32.340 --> 04:53:35.159
Glory could see her eyes shining in the

04:53:35.159 --> 04:53:36.360
dark, still watching.

04:53:36.479 --> 04:53:40.319
Four night wings ducked into the cave, one

04:53:40.319 --> 04:53:42.419
after the other, crowding the narrow

04:53:42.419 --> 04:53:42.840
space.

04:53:42.900 --> 04:53:45.360
Glory held her ground and glared at

04:53:45.360 --> 04:53:45.659
them.

04:53:45.720 --> 04:53:47.700
At least there was no sign of Morrow

04:53:47.700 --> 04:53:48.119
seer.

04:53:48.180 --> 04:53:51.000
She was safer as an ordinary rain wing

04:53:51.000 --> 04:53:52.979
prisoner than she would be if they found

04:53:52.979 --> 04:53:54.840
out she was the dragonette messing up

04:53:54.840 --> 04:53:55.500
their prophecy.

04:53:55.560 --> 04:53:58.020
The one they'd already tried to kill more

04:53:58.020 --> 04:53:58.439
than once.

04:53:58.500 --> 04:54:02.340
The last dragon who came in had a

04:54:02.340 --> 04:54:04.259
disturbing scar twisted across his

04:54:04.259 --> 04:54:04.919
snout.

04:54:04.979 --> 04:54:07.200
Strange bubbles, a deformed skin

04:54:07.200 --> 04:54:10.080
protruded from his jawline, and one of

04:54:10.080 --> 04:54:12.659
his nostrils was sealed shut, so he

04:54:12.659 --> 04:54:14.400
breathed in a loud, snuffly way.

04:54:14.459 --> 04:54:17.580
When he spoke, Glory recognized the

04:54:17.580 --> 04:54:19.380
hoarse voice of the dragon who'd captured

04:54:19.380 --> 04:54:19.619
her.

04:54:19.680 --> 04:54:23.099
He was the one in the forest, she

04:54:23.099 --> 04:54:25.380
realized, listening to his peculiar

04:54:25.380 --> 04:54:25.799
breathing.

04:54:25.860 --> 04:54:29.159
The creature in the dark, the one who ate

04:54:29.159 --> 04:54:30.119
the dead sloth.

04:54:30.180 --> 04:54:34.619
Looks normal to me, he said gruffly.

04:54:34.680 --> 04:54:36.779
One of the others gave him a scathing

04:54:36.779 --> 04:54:37.080
look.

04:54:37.139 --> 04:54:40.799
On the contrary, she said, there's

04:54:40.799 --> 04:54:42.299
clearly something wrong with this one.

04:54:42.360 --> 04:54:44.759
What do you mean?

04:54:44.759 --> 04:54:46.200
said a 3rd dragon.

04:54:46.259 --> 04:54:48.419
Observe her scales.

04:54:48.479 --> 04:54:50.759
Every other rain wing we've picked up

04:54:50.759 --> 04:54:53.279
turned instantly green, the color that

04:54:53.279 --> 04:54:56.400
seems to indicate fear, but this one, I

04:54:56.400 --> 04:54:58.619
don't know what it indicates, but I am

04:54:58.619 --> 04:55:00.299
seeing shades of red and orange.

04:55:00.360 --> 04:55:03.419
Perhaps a little black here and here.

04:55:03.479 --> 04:55:06.959
The Nightwing used a thin stick to point

04:55:06.959 --> 04:55:09.599
to spots on glory's wings, with clinical

04:55:09.599 --> 04:55:10.259
detachment.

04:55:10.319 --> 04:55:12.060
She could have been describing a

04:55:12.060 --> 04:55:13.860
moderately interesting beetle for all the

04:55:13.860 --> 04:55:14.639
emotion in her voice.

04:55:14.759 --> 04:55:19.020
So she's matching the environment, said

04:55:19.020 --> 04:55:19.799
that they're a dragon.

04:55:19.860 --> 04:55:22.080
That's something they do too, isn't it?

04:55:22.139 --> 04:55:25.319
Glory narrowed her eyes at them and

04:55:25.319 --> 04:55:27.360
turned a deliberate, violent shade of

04:55:27.360 --> 04:55:27.720
purple.

04:55:27.779 --> 04:55:31.740
Oh my, said the unemotional dragon.

04:55:31.799 --> 04:55:34.740
We should take her to the lab immediately

04:55:34.740 --> 04:55:35.939
for closer study.

04:55:36.060 --> 04:55:38.759
I strongly recommend not feeding her and

04:55:38.759 --> 04:55:41.459
not touching that gag until we know more

04:55:41.459 --> 04:55:41.819
about her.

04:55:41.880 --> 04:55:45.900
Bosh. said the scarred Nightwing.

04:55:45.959 --> 04:55:48.599
All rain wings are the same.

04:55:48.659 --> 04:55:50.520
Rotten and useless.

04:55:50.580 --> 04:55:55.259
Besides, Queen Battle Winner doesn't like

04:55:55.259 --> 04:55:56.520
to have her orders questioned.

04:55:56.639 --> 04:55:58.439
The 4th dragon spoke up.

04:55:58.500 --> 04:56:01.439
He stepped forward with something furry

04:56:01.439 --> 04:56:03.479
and horrible smelling in his talons.

04:56:03.479 --> 04:56:05.220
It's feeding time now.

04:56:05.279 --> 04:56:08.159
You can go ask her if this one should go

04:56:08.159 --> 04:56:09.119
to the lab afterward.

04:56:09.180 --> 04:56:13.080
I will. she said stepping back.

04:56:13.139 --> 04:56:15.540
I've registered my concern here.

04:56:15.599 --> 04:56:16.979
You do what you like.

04:56:17.099 --> 04:56:19.680
The Nightwing slid out of the cave and

04:56:19.680 --> 04:56:20.040
flew off.

04:56:20.159 --> 04:56:23.400
Leaving only 3 for me to fight.

04:56:23.459 --> 04:56:24.479
Glory thought.

04:56:24.540 --> 04:56:26.880
You may have studied the venom of

04:56:26.880 --> 04:56:28.979
pacifist, well trained, frightened rain

04:56:28.979 --> 04:56:31.200
wings, but you've never studied me.

04:56:31.259 --> 04:56:34.799
The scarred dragon produced a long spear

04:56:34.799 --> 04:56:35.700
from a sheath on his back.

04:56:35.819 --> 04:56:39.419
The sharp end had 3 twisted claw like

04:56:39.419 --> 04:56:42.060
points, and glinted evilly in the reddish

04:56:42.060 --> 04:56:42.360
light.

04:56:42.419 --> 04:56:45.240
He hefted it in his talons and flicked

04:56:45.240 --> 04:56:47.459
his black tongue at glory, as if he were

04:56:47.459 --> 04:56:49.139
hoping she'd give him an excuse to hurt

04:56:49.139 --> 04:56:49.380
her.

04:56:49.380 --> 04:56:53.580
He hates us, she thought, meeting his

04:56:53.580 --> 04:56:53.880
eyes.

04:56:53.939 --> 04:56:55.799
It's personal for him.

04:56:55.919 --> 04:56:58.560
Her gaze shifted to his scar.

04:56:58.619 --> 04:57:02.040
Ah, that looks like it could have been

04:57:02.040 --> 04:57:03.419
caused by a venom strike.

04:57:03.479 --> 04:57:06.180
I wonder which rain wing was bold enough

04:57:06.180 --> 04:57:06.659
to do that.

04:57:06.779 --> 04:57:08.759
With a shiver.

04:57:08.819 --> 04:57:11.700
She realized he was the 1st dragon she'd

04:57:11.700 --> 04:57:14.459
seen who'd survived a venom attack, which

04:57:14.459 --> 04:57:17.400
meant it was possible to survive a venom

04:57:17.400 --> 04:57:20.099
attack, which meant Queen Scarlet really

04:57:20.099 --> 04:57:21.060
might still be alive.

04:57:21.119 --> 04:57:24.599
The dead pile of fur landed by her feet

04:57:24.599 --> 04:57:26.639
and the other 2 guards pulled out long

04:57:26.639 --> 04:57:27.419
spears of their own.

04:57:27.540 --> 04:57:30.119
Lori stared down at the meal they were

04:57:30.119 --> 04:57:30.419
offering.

04:57:30.479 --> 04:57:32.939
Kinkaju wasn't exaggerating.

04:57:33.000 --> 04:57:36.419
It did smell horrible, and long dead.

04:57:36.479 --> 04:57:38.880
She could barely tell what it had once

04:57:38.880 --> 04:57:43.619
been, a muskrat, perhaps, a nasty bite on

04:57:43.619 --> 04:57:45.659
its side, looked a lot like the one on

04:57:45.659 --> 04:57:47.939
the sloth by the river, black and

04:57:47.939 --> 04:57:48.419
infected.

04:57:48.479 --> 04:57:51.299
One of the guards leaned forward, and

04:57:51.299 --> 04:57:52.619
jabbed his spear toward her face.

04:57:52.680 --> 04:57:55.500
Glory leaped back with a muffled snarl.

04:57:55.560 --> 04:57:58.020
Hold still if you want to eat.

04:57:58.080 --> 04:58:01.560
Growled the scarred dragon, or else

04:58:01.560 --> 04:58:02.279
starve.

04:58:02.279 --> 04:58:04.080
We're fine with that too.

04:58:04.139 --> 04:58:07.680
Glory clenched her talons and eyed the

04:58:07.680 --> 04:58:08.880
spear as it bobbed closer.

04:58:09.000 --> 04:58:11.279
It was hard to see exactly what the guard

04:58:11.279 --> 04:58:13.979
did, but she felt the spear points hook

04:58:13.979 --> 04:58:16.080
into some kind of latch on the metal band

04:58:16.080 --> 04:58:17.520
then twist and pull.

04:58:17.639 --> 04:58:20.759
The clamp slipped open and off, and the

04:58:20.759 --> 04:58:22.259
night wings all jumped back with their

04:58:22.259 --> 04:58:22.740
spears up.

04:58:22.860 --> 04:58:25.020
But not fast enough.

04:58:25.139 --> 04:58:29.939
Chapter 22.

04:58:30.180 --> 04:58:34.200
Glory lunged forward with her fangs bared

04:58:34.200 --> 04:58:36.180
and seized the closest spear in her

04:58:36.180 --> 04:58:38.759
talons, she yanked it toward her, throwing

04:58:38.759 --> 04:58:41.340
the guard off balance, and shot a jet of

04:58:41.340 --> 04:58:43.439
venom that missed his face, but sprayed

04:58:43.439 --> 04:58:45.180
across his wings and back.

04:58:45.240 --> 04:58:47.400
He let go of the spear, and stumbled

04:58:47.400 --> 04:58:49.319
toward the cave entrance with a shriek of

04:58:49.319 --> 04:58:49.500
pain.

04:58:49.560 --> 04:58:52.860
The scarred dragon dropped his spear.

04:58:52.919 --> 04:58:55.200
He shot out of the cave, shoving aside

04:58:55.200 --> 04:58:57.119
his injured tribe made as he went by.

04:58:57.180 --> 04:59:00.060
Glory whipped toward the last guard and

04:59:00.060 --> 04:59:02.159
tried to turn the spear on him, but her

04:59:02.159 --> 04:59:04.080
wrapped talons were clumsy, and she

04:59:04.080 --> 04:59:04.919
fumbled the weapon.

04:59:04.979 --> 04:59:07.560
He darted toward her, stabbing for her

04:59:07.560 --> 04:59:08.040
neck.

04:59:08.040 --> 04:59:11.159
Glory hissed a spray of venom at him, but

04:59:11.159 --> 04:59:13.259
to her surprise, he dodged and rolled

04:59:13.259 --> 04:59:13.680
under it.

04:59:13.740 --> 04:59:16.380
A moment later, he knocked her over and

04:59:16.380 --> 04:59:17.279
pinned her face down.

04:59:17.340 --> 04:59:19.979
He shoved her snout into the rocky floor

04:59:19.979 --> 04:59:22.080
and pressed the points of the spear into

04:59:22.080 --> 04:59:22.500
her neck.

04:59:22.619 --> 04:59:27.299
Nice try, rain wing, he snarled, but it's

04:59:27.299 --> 04:59:30.240
not that easy to fool a...

04:59:30.360 --> 04:59:32.520
His weight suddenly disappeared from her

04:59:32.520 --> 04:59:34.740
back as his howls echoed around the

04:59:34.740 --> 04:59:35.220
cave.

04:59:35.279 --> 04:59:37.619
Glory leaped to her feet and found

04:59:37.619 --> 04:59:40.500
Kinkaju beside her, with her front talons

04:59:40.500 --> 04:59:41.520
pressed over her snout.

04:59:41.639 --> 04:59:43.500
I can't believe I did that.

04:59:43.619 --> 04:59:45.180
Kinkachu yelped.

04:59:45.299 --> 04:59:47.040
Oh my gosh, look at him.

04:59:47.099 --> 04:59:49.799
The night wing staggered into the wall

04:59:49.860 --> 04:59:51.119
clawing at his neck.

04:59:51.180 --> 04:59:53.400
Kinkachu had hit him with only a few

04:59:53.400 --> 04:59:55.619
droplets of venom, but those were smoking

04:59:55.619 --> 04:59:57.119
and bubbling on his scales.

04:59:57.180 --> 04:59:59.819
He turned back to the 2 rain wings with

04:59:59.819 --> 05:00:01.979
pain crazed rage in his eyes.

05:00:02.040 --> 05:00:04.740
I'm sorry, Kinkachu cried.

05:00:04.799 --> 05:00:07.080
Oh, that looks like it hurts so much.

05:00:07.139 --> 05:00:10.139
Glory yanked the spear out of the guard's

05:00:10.139 --> 05:00:12.540
claws and shoved him over the drop off at

05:00:12.540 --> 05:00:13.500
the back of the cave.

05:00:13.560 --> 05:00:15.299
She could hear him flapping and

05:00:15.299 --> 05:00:17.340
blundering around in the dark, still

05:00:17.340 --> 05:00:17.819
yowling.

05:00:17.880 --> 05:00:20.220
But Kinkachu said.

05:00:20.279 --> 05:00:21.779
He'll be fine.

05:00:21.840 --> 05:00:24.360
Once he remembers he has fire, Glory said

05:00:24.360 --> 05:00:25.619
we should be gone by then.

05:00:25.680 --> 05:00:29.400
I didn't realize you meant escape, now

05:00:29.400 --> 05:00:30.540
Kinkachu said.

05:00:30.599 --> 05:00:32.520
I mean, like, right now?

05:00:32.639 --> 05:00:33.840
That is so crazy.

05:00:33.900 --> 05:00:35.279
You're crazy.

05:00:35.340 --> 05:00:38.400
Her voice was edgy and manic, but her

05:00:38.400 --> 05:00:39.659
scales were bright yellow with

05:00:39.659 --> 05:00:40.380
excitement.

05:00:40.439 --> 05:00:42.540
Tone it down a bit, can you?

05:00:42.599 --> 05:00:44.759
Glory said, nodding at the little

05:00:44.759 --> 05:00:45.720
dragonette's wings.

05:00:45.840 --> 05:00:47.639
We don't need to alert the whole mountain

05:00:47.639 --> 05:00:48.360
as we escape.

05:00:48.419 --> 05:00:49.680
Try looking like them.

05:00:49.740 --> 05:00:52.319
She turned her own scales the same

05:00:52.319 --> 05:00:53.939
gleaming black as the night wings

05:00:53.939 --> 05:00:54.299
outside.

05:00:54.360 --> 05:00:56.520
And I'm glory, by the way.

05:00:56.639 --> 05:01:00.299
Got it, Kinkachu said, flipping her

05:01:00.299 --> 05:01:00.599
tail.

05:01:00.659 --> 05:01:03.779
Inky Black spread across her scales, as

05:01:03.779 --> 05:01:05.639
if someone was pouring the night sky onto

05:01:05.639 --> 05:01:05.939
her.

05:01:06.000 --> 05:01:08.459
But how do we get you over the lava

05:01:08.459 --> 05:01:08.880
river?

05:01:08.939 --> 05:01:10.680
Whoops.

05:01:10.740 --> 05:01:12.779
Glory had forgotten about that.

05:01:12.840 --> 05:01:15.000
Or rather, she hadn't thought that far

05:01:15.000 --> 05:01:15.299
ahead.

05:01:15.360 --> 05:01:17.639
She'd seen an opportunity to use her

05:01:17.639 --> 05:01:20.639
venom, and took it without thinking, Who

05:01:20.639 --> 05:01:21.119
am I?

05:01:21.180 --> 05:01:22.259
Tsunami?

05:01:22.319 --> 05:01:23.580
She scolded herself.

05:01:23.639 --> 05:01:26.819
Worse yet, she knew the scarred night

05:01:26.819 --> 05:01:28.259
wing would be back any moment with

05:01:28.259 --> 05:01:29.159
reinforcements.

05:01:29.220 --> 05:01:31.619
She clamped her teeth down on the canvas

05:01:31.619 --> 05:01:33.900
that covered her talons with a violent

05:01:33.900 --> 05:01:34.680
shake of her head.

05:01:34.740 --> 05:01:36.720
She ripped the cloth until it tore

05:01:36.720 --> 05:01:37.979
loose.

05:01:38.040 --> 05:01:39.779
As soon as her claws were free, she

05:01:39.779 --> 05:01:42.180
seized a spear and turned it on the ropes

05:01:42.180 --> 05:01:42.900
wrapped around her body.

05:01:43.020 --> 05:01:45.060
The guards are coming.

05:01:45.240 --> 05:01:46.860
Kinkaju said anxiously.

05:01:46.919 --> 05:01:49.319
Pretend you're a night wing dragonette

05:01:49.319 --> 05:01:51.060
and stall them, Glory said.

05:01:51.180 --> 05:01:53.700
She jabbed the spear point awkwardly at

05:01:53.700 --> 05:01:55.619
one of the ropes, and stabbed herself in

05:01:55.619 --> 05:01:56.459
the underbelly.

05:01:56.459 --> 05:01:58.919
With a hiss, she hefted the weapon and

05:01:58.919 --> 05:01:59.340
tried again.

05:01:59.400 --> 05:02:02.220
Yes, all right, stall them.

05:02:02.279 --> 05:02:04.740
No problem, Kingaju said.

05:02:04.799 --> 05:02:06.659
She darted toward the cave entrance.

05:02:06.720 --> 05:02:09.479
The 1st night when Glory had attacked, was

05:02:09.479 --> 05:02:12.000
lying halfway across the opening, moaning

05:02:12.000 --> 05:02:14.220
softly and writhing, as if he were trying

05:02:14.220 --> 05:02:17.159
to wriggle out of his own skin, Kinkaju

05:02:17.159 --> 05:02:19.200
blinked at him for a moment, then lifted

05:02:19.200 --> 05:02:21.060
one of his wings so it draped across her

05:02:21.060 --> 05:02:23.159
shoulders and back, covering the brass

05:02:23.159 --> 05:02:24.240
band around her neck.

05:02:24.299 --> 05:02:26.220
She leaned a little way out of the cave

05:02:26.220 --> 05:02:26.759
and looked up.

05:02:26.880 --> 05:02:30.599
Quick, she shouted suddenly, making glory

05:02:30.599 --> 05:02:30.959
jump.

05:02:31.020 --> 05:02:33.240
She attacked us and escaped.

05:02:33.299 --> 05:02:34.919
We saw her go that way.

05:02:34.979 --> 05:02:36.659
She pointed down the mountain.

05:02:36.720 --> 05:02:38.400
Hurry, don't stop.

05:02:38.520 --> 05:02:40.080
She was flying super fast.

05:02:40.139 --> 05:02:42.000
No, no, I'll take care of him.

05:02:42.060 --> 05:02:43.080
Go after her.

05:02:43.200 --> 05:02:43.979
She's getting away.

05:02:44.040 --> 05:02:47.279
The whoosh of wings shot by overhead

05:02:47.279 --> 05:02:49.439
sending a blast of hot air back into the

05:02:49.439 --> 05:02:49.799
cave.

05:02:49.919 --> 05:02:52.919
At the same time, Glory finally hooked

05:02:52.919 --> 05:02:54.599
the spear into the knot of the rope.

05:02:54.840 --> 05:02:57.299
With a twist, she managed to saw the

05:02:57.299 --> 05:02:59.340
sharp points across the fibers until they

05:02:59.340 --> 05:02:59.759
split.

05:02:59.819 --> 05:03:02.880
But as that rope slid off, she realized

05:03:02.880 --> 05:03:05.159
there were 4 more separately knotted

05:03:05.159 --> 05:03:05.580
around her.

05:03:05.639 --> 05:03:08.520
I'll never get these all off before they

05:03:08.520 --> 05:03:11.220
realize it was a trick and come back, she

05:03:11.220 --> 05:03:11.520
thought.

05:03:11.580 --> 05:03:13.740
There had to be another way across the

05:03:13.740 --> 05:03:14.040
river.

05:03:14.099 --> 05:03:16.080
Maybe there was something they could use

05:03:16.080 --> 05:03:17.040
as a stepping stone.

05:03:17.099 --> 05:03:19.740
She hurried to the opening and stared out

05:03:19.740 --> 05:03:21.659
looking for large boulders.

05:03:21.720 --> 05:03:23.580
Kingaju watched her trustingly.

05:03:23.639 --> 05:03:27.180
A squadron of 5 night wings was flapping

05:03:27.180 --> 05:03:29.340
away down the mountain toward a black

05:03:29.340 --> 05:03:32.099
sand beach and an expanse of gray, stormy

05:03:32.099 --> 05:03:32.400
water.

05:03:32.459 --> 05:03:35.520
Only 5 night wings to stop me?

05:03:35.580 --> 05:03:36.840
Glory thought.

05:03:37.020 --> 05:03:39.299
She glanced up the mountain, but there

05:03:39.299 --> 05:03:41.880
was no sign of an alarm. or extra forces

05:03:41.880 --> 05:03:42.540
mobilizing.

05:03:42.599 --> 05:03:45.119
I guess they're not really that worried

05:03:45.119 --> 05:03:47.759
about me escaping, she said uneasily.

05:03:47.819 --> 05:03:50.220
I'm getting pretty worried about it

05:03:50.220 --> 05:03:50.400
though.

05:03:50.520 --> 05:03:51.959
Kinkachu offered.

05:03:52.020 --> 05:03:55.319
Hey, Glory said, poking the wounded

05:03:55.319 --> 05:03:56.220
guard.

05:03:56.279 --> 05:03:57.540
You can still fly, can't you?

05:03:57.659 --> 05:03:59.400
He flinched away from her.

05:03:59.459 --> 05:04:01.979
I can't, he moaned.

05:04:02.040 --> 05:04:03.540
Everything hurts.

05:04:03.659 --> 05:04:05.580
It didn't even look that bad.

05:04:05.639 --> 05:04:08.520
He'd avoided the worst of the spray, and

05:04:08.520 --> 05:04:10.259
most of the damage was along one side of

05:04:10.259 --> 05:04:10.619
his back.

05:04:10.680 --> 05:04:13.860
You're going to hurt a lot more unless

05:04:13.860 --> 05:04:16.259
you carry me over this lava, Glory said

05:04:16.259 --> 05:04:18.060
or cut these ropes off for me.

05:04:18.119 --> 05:04:21.119
She bared her fangs at him, and he threw

05:04:21.119 --> 05:04:23.040
his wings over his head, scuttling

05:04:23.040 --> 05:04:23.939
backward into the cave.

05:04:24.000 --> 05:04:28.380
Actually, said a new voice, I have a

05:04:28.380 --> 05:04:28.860
better offer.

05:04:28.919 --> 05:04:32.159
Glory whirled around as a black dragon

05:04:32.159 --> 05:04:34.200
descended from the sky and gave her a

05:04:34.200 --> 05:04:34.979
cheeky grin.

05:04:35.040 --> 05:04:38.279
Hello, Glory, said Death Bringer.

05:04:38.340 --> 05:04:42.599
Chapter 23.

05:04:42.840 --> 05:04:46.319
Don't give me that smug face.

05:04:46.380 --> 05:04:47.340
Glory snapped.

05:04:47.459 --> 05:04:49.740
This isn't my smug face.

05:04:49.799 --> 05:04:52.560
It's my heroic face, Deathbringer said.

05:04:52.619 --> 05:04:54.540
And how funny is this?

05:04:54.599 --> 05:04:57.000
First, I was your prisoner.

05:04:57.060 --> 05:04:58.139
Now you're mine.

05:04:58.200 --> 05:05:01.080
Perhaps you haven't heard what I do to

05:05:01.080 --> 05:05:03.779
dragons who try to keep me prisoner, Glory

05:05:03.779 --> 05:05:04.439
said with a hiss.

05:05:04.560 --> 05:05:08.040
All right, stop it, you two.

05:05:08.099 --> 05:05:10.799
Clay flapped up behind Deathbringer and

05:05:10.799 --> 05:05:11.880
landed beside glory.

05:05:12.000 --> 05:05:14.220
Clay, glory cried.

05:05:14.279 --> 05:05:15.299
What are you doing here?

05:05:15.360 --> 05:05:19.500
We came to rescue you, he said, nudging

05:05:19.500 --> 05:05:20.520
her wing with his.

05:05:20.580 --> 05:05:21.840
Aren't you pleased?

05:05:21.900 --> 05:05:24.479
I'm right in the middle of rescuing

05:05:24.479 --> 05:05:26.040
myself, Glory said.

05:05:26.099 --> 05:05:28.139
She was having a hard time keeping her

05:05:28.139 --> 05:05:30.479
scales black when the side of clay made

05:05:30.479 --> 05:05:32.040
her feel as pink as her ridiculous

05:05:32.040 --> 05:05:32.400
brother.

05:05:32.459 --> 05:05:34.020
Maybe some other time.

05:05:34.080 --> 05:05:35.759
Don't listen to her.

05:05:35.819 --> 05:05:37.259
Kinkaju cried.

05:05:37.319 --> 05:05:38.880
We definitely need rescuing.

05:05:38.939 --> 05:05:40.319
Please, rescue us.

05:05:40.380 --> 05:05:42.479
How did you even get here?

05:05:42.479 --> 05:05:43.680
Gloria asked.

05:05:43.740 --> 05:05:45.659
I mean, how did you know to look for me

05:05:45.659 --> 05:05:45.900
here?

05:05:45.959 --> 05:05:49.919
Clay nodded a death bringer, who flicked

05:05:49.919 --> 05:05:51.779
his tail and managed to look even more

05:05:51.779 --> 05:05:52.380
smug.

05:05:52.500 --> 05:05:54.540
He talked me into it.

05:05:54.599 --> 05:05:57.479
When you didn't come back, he told me he

05:05:57.479 --> 05:05:59.580
knew where you'd gone, and that he'd help

05:05:59.580 --> 05:06:00.959
me find you if I set him free.

05:06:01.020 --> 05:06:05.340
Sounds like a trick, Glory said, eyeing

05:06:05.340 --> 05:06:06.720
Deathbringer suspiciously.

05:06:06.779 --> 05:06:08.700
Why would he work against his fellow

05:06:08.700 --> 05:06:09.419
night wings?

05:06:09.479 --> 05:06:11.880
Was this a way to get clay into their

05:06:11.880 --> 05:06:12.540
clutches as well?

05:06:12.599 --> 05:06:15.900
Let's escape 1st and ask skeptical

05:06:15.900 --> 05:06:18.299
questions later, said Kinkaju.

05:06:18.360 --> 05:06:20.400
She jumped into the air, wings flapping.

05:06:20.459 --> 05:06:23.819
Sensible Dragonette, said Deathbringer.

05:06:23.939 --> 05:06:27.119
He gave glory an unreadable look, teasing

05:06:27.119 --> 05:06:29.880
but worried, and self satisfied, but

05:06:29.880 --> 05:06:30.959
sweet all at once.

05:06:31.020 --> 05:06:34.080
You can express your undying gratitude to

05:06:34.080 --> 05:06:34.380
me later.

05:06:34.439 --> 05:06:35.220
I'll wait.

05:06:35.279 --> 05:06:38.880
Go ahead and hold your breath, Glory

05:06:38.880 --> 05:06:39.360
suggested.

05:06:39.419 --> 05:06:41.159
Up you go.

05:06:41.279 --> 05:06:42.180
Clay said.

05:06:42.240 --> 05:06:44.580
He spread his wings so glory could climb

05:06:44.580 --> 05:06:45.240
onto his back.

05:06:45.299 --> 05:06:46.740
She hesitated for a moment.

05:06:46.799 --> 05:06:49.380
Part of her said, you can do this

05:06:49.380 --> 05:06:49.799
yourself.

05:06:49.860 --> 05:06:51.119
You don't need help.

05:06:51.180 --> 05:06:53.639
Just get your wings free and save your

05:06:53.639 --> 05:06:54.240
own scales.

05:06:54.299 --> 05:06:56.700
But there wasn't time.

05:06:56.759 --> 05:06:57.779
And although she couldn't trust

05:06:57.779 --> 05:07:00.000
Deathbringer, There was no one more

05:07:00.000 --> 05:07:01.259
trustworthy than clay.

05:07:01.319 --> 05:07:03.779
She clambered onto his back, still

05:07:03.779 --> 05:07:05.880
holding the spear and awkwardly adjusting

05:07:05.880 --> 05:07:07.080
her balance without her wings.

05:07:07.139 --> 05:07:09.659
He was in the air almost before she could

05:07:09.659 --> 05:07:10.979
get her talons around his neck.

05:07:11.040 --> 05:07:13.860
She slipped sideways, and nearly knocked

05:07:13.860 --> 05:07:14.880
him into the lava.

05:07:14.880 --> 05:07:17.580
Clay's tail brushed the bubbling red hot

05:07:17.580 --> 05:07:20.040
river below, and he lurched upward with a

05:07:20.040 --> 05:07:20.639
hiss of pain.

05:07:20.700 --> 05:07:24.599
It's all right, he said quickly, it'll

05:07:24.599 --> 05:07:25.200
heal fast.

05:07:25.259 --> 05:07:25.860
Don't worry.

05:07:25.919 --> 05:07:29.939
Fire resistant scales like clays would

05:07:29.939 --> 05:07:32.279
definitely have come in handy here, Glory

05:07:32.279 --> 05:07:34.259
thought, glancing down as he flew

05:07:34.259 --> 05:07:34.560
higher.

05:07:34.619 --> 05:07:37.259
She saw several other caves overlooking

05:07:37.259 --> 05:07:39.659
the lava river, but no snouts sticking

05:07:39.659 --> 05:07:39.840
out.

05:07:39.900 --> 05:07:42.959
We have to get the other rain wings, she

05:07:42.959 --> 05:07:44.099
shouted in clays ear.

05:07:44.159 --> 05:07:45.479
We have to set them all free.

05:07:45.540 --> 05:07:47.220
Now?

05:07:47.220 --> 05:07:48.119
he asked.

05:07:48.180 --> 05:07:50.639
We'll be lucky if we make it out without

05:07:50.639 --> 05:07:51.119
getting caught.

05:07:51.180 --> 05:07:54.659
I can't just leave them here. she cried.

05:07:54.720 --> 05:07:57.360
I promised Mangrove I'd find Orchid.

05:07:57.479 --> 05:08:00.060
And you did, he said.

05:08:00.119 --> 05:08:02.159
Now you know where she is.

05:08:02.220 --> 05:08:04.439
We can come back and get her, with

05:08:04.439 --> 05:08:05.040
backup.

05:08:05.159 --> 05:08:07.799
He glanced over his shoulder and put on a

05:08:07.799 --> 05:08:08.520
burst of speed.

05:08:08.580 --> 05:08:10.979
Lots and lots of backup.

05:08:11.099 --> 05:08:14.220
Glory looked behind them as well, and saw

05:08:14.220 --> 05:08:16.259
a cluster of night wings standing on a

05:08:16.259 --> 05:08:17.459
high rocky ledge.

05:08:17.520 --> 05:08:19.500
Three of them were pointing at clay and

05:08:19.500 --> 05:08:21.180
shouting to the others.

05:08:21.240 --> 05:08:23.099
Black scaled heads were turning toward

05:08:23.099 --> 05:08:25.020
the sky all across the volcano.

05:08:25.080 --> 05:08:27.840
She also saw Kinkachu flapping madly to

05:08:27.840 --> 05:08:28.860
keep up with them.

05:08:28.919 --> 05:08:30.840
What she didn't see was a certain

05:08:30.840 --> 05:08:33.000
dangerous know it all assassin.

05:08:33.060 --> 05:08:35.880
Deathbringer's not with us, she called.

05:08:35.939 --> 05:08:38.759
Of course not, Clay called back.

05:08:38.819 --> 05:08:41.580
He swooped down between 2 curved stone

05:08:41.580 --> 05:08:42.900
columns and banked right.

05:08:43.020 --> 05:08:45.479
His tribe can't know he helped us.

05:08:45.540 --> 05:08:49.200
Glory thought uneasily of the dragon

05:08:49.200 --> 05:08:51.900
she'd wounded back in the prison cave.

05:08:51.959 --> 05:08:54.060
Surely he had seen Deathbringer and

05:08:54.060 --> 05:08:56.700
overheard their conversation, but really

05:08:56.700 --> 05:08:58.319
that was Deathbringer's problem.

05:08:58.380 --> 05:09:00.720
What happened to his mission?

05:09:00.779 --> 05:09:02.819
The one about killing us, remember?

05:09:02.939 --> 05:09:06.599
Maybe he doesn't want to anymore, Clay

05:09:06.599 --> 05:09:07.500
said with a shrug.

05:09:07.560 --> 05:09:10.139
Suspicious glory thought.

05:09:10.200 --> 05:09:13.259
Or as Kinkaju would say, mega

05:09:13.259 --> 05:09:13.860
suspicious.

05:09:13.919 --> 05:09:17.759
And yet she also felt a weird loss, like

05:09:17.759 --> 05:09:19.259
she wished she'd had a chance to say

05:09:19.259 --> 05:09:19.680
goodbye.

05:09:19.740 --> 05:09:22.860
She twisted to look back again, but he

05:09:22.860 --> 05:09:23.400
really wasn't there.

05:09:23.459 --> 05:09:24.959
Oh well.

05:09:25.020 --> 05:09:27.240
Maybe the next time he shows up to kill

05:09:27.240 --> 05:09:27.479
me.

05:09:27.540 --> 05:09:30.360
She realized that Clay was winging

05:09:30.360 --> 05:09:32.279
rapidly toward the black sand beach that

05:09:32.279 --> 05:09:33.900
ringed the island at the base of the

05:09:33.900 --> 05:09:34.439
volcano.

05:09:34.500 --> 05:09:36.959
Twisted, leafless trees grew on the

05:09:36.959 --> 05:09:39.720
volcano's slopes, like bones sticking out

05:09:39.720 --> 05:09:40.139
of the dirt.

05:09:40.259 --> 05:09:43.139
Beyond the beach, the ocean roared and

05:09:43.139 --> 05:09:46.080
churned, gray and unfriendly, and

05:09:46.080 --> 05:09:46.919
speckled with foam.

05:09:47.040 --> 05:09:50.340
Um, clay, Glory said.

05:09:50.400 --> 05:09:52.619
We're not flying back to the rainforest

05:09:52.619 --> 05:09:53.880
across that ocean, are we?

05:09:53.939 --> 05:09:56.580
No way, Clay said.

05:09:56.639 --> 05:09:58.979
I don't even know which way the rest of

05:09:58.979 --> 05:10:01.020
Pyria is, or how far.

05:10:01.080 --> 05:10:01.740
Do you?

05:10:01.799 --> 05:10:05.639
Nope, Glory said, but it makes sense to

05:10:05.639 --> 05:10:07.680
me that the night wings live on an island

05:10:07.680 --> 05:10:09.299
one that's not on any maps.

05:10:09.360 --> 05:10:12.000
I would have thought they'd pick a nicer

05:10:12.000 --> 05:10:12.540
one though.

05:10:12.599 --> 05:10:14.220
This place is ghastly.

05:10:14.279 --> 05:10:17.159
She coughed. wondering if the smell of

05:10:17.159 --> 05:10:18.959
rotten eggs would ever clear out of her

05:10:18.959 --> 05:10:19.380
snout.

05:10:19.500 --> 05:10:22.439
Clay dove toward a cave halfway up a

05:10:22.439 --> 05:10:24.479
small rocky cliff at one end of the

05:10:24.479 --> 05:10:24.779
beach.

05:10:24.840 --> 05:10:28.020
The passage to the rainforest is in there

05:10:28.020 --> 05:10:28.799
he called.

05:10:28.860 --> 05:10:30.119
Get ready to fight.

05:10:30.180 --> 05:10:34.799
Always, ready, panted Kinkaju beside

05:10:34.799 --> 05:10:35.580
them.

05:10:35.639 --> 05:10:37.139
Glory opened her mouth and tasted the

05:10:37.139 --> 05:10:37.799
smoky air.

05:10:37.860 --> 05:10:39.900
She couldn't see any guards on the beach

05:10:39.900 --> 05:10:40.259
below.

05:10:40.319 --> 05:10:42.779
Didn't you have to fight them on your way

05:10:42.779 --> 05:10:43.619
out of the tunnel?

05:10:43.619 --> 05:10:44.220
she asked.

05:10:44.279 --> 05:10:47.939
No, Death Bringer went ahead of me and

05:10:47.939 --> 05:10:49.919
distracted them, but they'll be back by

05:10:49.919 --> 05:10:50.099
now.

05:10:50.220 --> 05:10:53.400
Also, Kinkaju gasped.

05:10:53.459 --> 05:10:55.080
Company, behind.

05:10:55.200 --> 05:10:57.119
Glory didn't have to look back.

05:10:57.180 --> 05:10:59.700
She'd already heard the wing beats, and

05:10:59.700 --> 05:11:01.139
she didn't really want to know exactly

05:11:01.139 --> 05:11:02.700
how many night wings were on their

05:11:02.700 --> 05:11:03.060
tails.

05:11:03.119 --> 05:11:05.580
She gripped the spear in her claws.

05:11:05.639 --> 05:11:07.919
Imagining Morrow's sear on the pointy end

05:11:07.919 --> 05:11:08.159
of it.

05:11:08.220 --> 05:11:10.919
The cave yawned wide in front of them.

05:11:10.979 --> 05:11:13.319
Clay didn't slow down as he shot between

05:11:13.319 --> 05:11:14.340
the rocky walls.

05:11:14.400 --> 05:11:17.040
Glory blinked, her eyes adjusting to the

05:11:17.040 --> 05:11:19.500
darkness, and then she saw the light of a

05:11:19.500 --> 05:11:20.580
fire glowing up ahead.

05:11:20.700 --> 05:11:23.159
Four night wings were gathered around the

05:11:23.159 --> 05:11:25.560
fire, each of them carrying one of the

05:11:25.560 --> 05:11:26.459
wicked looking spears.

05:11:26.580 --> 05:11:29.700
The wrongness, feeling emanated from a

05:11:29.700 --> 05:11:31.680
perfectly circular hole in the rock wall

05:11:31.680 --> 05:11:33.779
behind them, and they were clearly not

05:11:33.779 --> 05:11:35.340
planning on letting anyone get to it.

05:11:35.400 --> 05:11:39.119
We have to get past them fast, Glory

05:11:39.119 --> 05:11:41.220
thought, or else we'll have all the ones

05:11:41.220 --> 05:11:42.659
behind us to deal with as well.

05:11:42.720 --> 05:11:46.619
The 1st guard saw them coming, jumped up

05:11:46.619 --> 05:11:48.540
and slammed into clay.

05:11:48.599 --> 05:11:51.000
Glory catapulted over his head, dropping

05:11:51.000 --> 05:11:53.220
the spear, and just missing the fire as

05:11:53.220 --> 05:11:54.419
she crashed into one of the other

05:11:54.419 --> 05:11:55.200
dragons.

05:11:55.200 --> 05:11:58.319
Talons seized her tail and wings, and

05:11:58.319 --> 05:12:00.959
more talons fumbled for her snout, not

05:12:00.959 --> 05:12:01.439
happening.

05:12:01.500 --> 05:12:02.700
Glory thought.

05:12:02.759 --> 05:12:04.680
No one would muzzle her weapon again.

05:12:04.740 --> 05:12:07.740
Her jaw sprang open, and she swung her

05:12:07.740 --> 05:12:09.959
neck around, spraying venom at the guard

05:12:09.959 --> 05:12:11.580
who was trying to hold her down.

05:12:11.639 --> 05:12:14.220
Black droplets spattered across his chest

05:12:14.220 --> 05:12:16.919
screaming, he leaped back and stumbled

05:12:16.919 --> 05:12:18.959
into the fire, then fled toward the beach

05:12:18.959 --> 05:12:20.700
with smoke rising from his scales.

05:12:20.759 --> 05:12:23.459
The other 2 guards pounced on glory from

05:12:23.459 --> 05:12:25.319
behind, wrestling her back down again.

05:12:25.380 --> 05:12:28.799
They were both huge, the size of Morrow

05:12:28.799 --> 05:12:31.319
Seer, with metal armor buckled over their

05:12:31.319 --> 05:12:33.299
underbellies and strange helmets

05:12:33.299 --> 05:12:34.619
protecting their snouts.

05:12:34.680 --> 05:12:36.599
Glory's face was pressed into the

05:12:36.599 --> 05:12:36.900
ground.

05:12:36.959 --> 05:12:40.080
She lashed her tail furiously, trying to

05:12:40.080 --> 05:12:42.479
smack them the way tsunami would have, but

05:12:42.479 --> 05:12:44.099
one of the guards stepped on it and

05:12:44.099 --> 05:12:44.759
pinned it down.

05:12:44.819 --> 05:12:47.400
Glory struggled against the weight of the

05:12:47.400 --> 05:12:48.240
2 dragons.

05:12:48.299 --> 05:12:50.819
Above her, Clay was battling the 1st

05:12:50.819 --> 05:12:51.419
night wing.

05:12:51.479 --> 05:12:54.240
Their claws clashed, and bouts of fire

05:12:54.240 --> 05:12:55.200
blasted through the air.

05:12:55.259 --> 05:12:57.000
Kinkachoo.

05:12:57.060 --> 05:12:57.900
Glory thought.

05:12:57.959 --> 05:12:59.159
Where had she gone?

05:12:59.220 --> 05:13:00.720
Had she made it into the tunnel?

05:13:00.779 --> 05:13:03.720
The tiny dragonette suddenly popped up

05:13:03.720 --> 05:13:05.759
behind the guards, holding the spear

05:13:05.759 --> 05:13:06.659
Glory had dropped.

05:13:06.779 --> 05:13:09.540
She swung it hard, and smacked one of the

05:13:09.540 --> 05:13:10.860
night wings on the head with a blunt

05:13:10.860 --> 05:13:11.220
end.

05:13:11.279 --> 05:13:14.159
He tottered sideways with a yell, then

05:13:14.159 --> 05:13:16.080
whipped around with a murderous gleam in

05:13:16.080 --> 05:13:16.860
his eyes.

05:13:16.919 --> 05:13:18.180
Kingajou!

05:13:18.240 --> 05:13:19.020
Glory shouted.

05:13:19.080 --> 05:13:20.220
Use your venom.

05:13:20.279 --> 05:13:23.939
But, Kinkaju said, dodging a swipe of the

05:13:23.939 --> 05:13:24.900
night wings claws.

05:13:24.959 --> 05:13:27.119
I don't, or the spear.

05:13:27.180 --> 05:13:28.619
The pointy end this time.

05:13:28.740 --> 05:13:31.200
Kinkaju looked down at the spear with a

05:13:31.200 --> 05:13:32.220
surprised expression.

05:13:32.279 --> 05:13:34.919
She hefted it, and jabbed it at a guard

05:13:34.919 --> 05:13:36.060
as he came at her again.

05:13:36.119 --> 05:13:38.520
He knocked it aside and thrust his own

05:13:38.520 --> 05:13:39.180
spear at her.

05:13:39.240 --> 05:13:42.360
Kinkaju yelped, and Glory saw a streak of

05:13:42.360 --> 05:13:43.799
blood slashed across her neck.

05:13:43.860 --> 05:13:46.439
Glory clenched her talons with rage.

05:13:46.500 --> 05:13:48.240
How dare he?

05:13:48.299 --> 05:13:51.060
Kinkaju was just a tiny dragonette.

05:13:51.119 --> 05:13:54.119
Not only that, she was a rain wing, which

05:13:54.119 --> 05:13:55.619
meant she'd never been trained to fight.

05:13:55.680 --> 05:13:58.439
There was just one guard holding glory

05:13:58.439 --> 05:13:59.159
down at the moment.

05:13:59.220 --> 05:14:01.619
She thought of Sonny's tricks from battle

05:14:01.619 --> 05:14:03.299
training and stopped struggling.

05:14:03.360 --> 05:14:05.880
On top of her, the guard let out a

05:14:05.880 --> 05:14:06.840
pleased hiss.

05:14:06.900 --> 05:14:09.119
Glory let her scales ripple into the

05:14:09.119 --> 05:14:10.319
color of the rocks below her.

05:14:10.380 --> 05:14:13.979
Foolish rain wing, hissed the guard.

05:14:14.099 --> 05:14:16.020
I can still feel you.

05:14:16.139 --> 05:14:18.840
I can still see your wing bindings.

05:14:18.900 --> 05:14:21.840
Glory knew that, but she was hoping the

05:14:21.840 --> 05:14:23.279
strangeness of holding something he

05:14:23.279 --> 05:14:24.659
couldn't see would make him slower.

05:14:24.720 --> 05:14:27.419
Taking a deep breath, she suddenly

05:14:27.419 --> 05:14:29.819
twisted herself into a tight spiral.

05:14:29.880 --> 05:14:31.799
The night wing's talons slipped on her

05:14:31.799 --> 05:14:33.900
scales, and she was able to get her tail

05:14:33.900 --> 05:14:36.240
free for a moment, long enough to swing

05:14:36.240 --> 05:14:38.580
it around and jab him sharply in the

05:14:38.580 --> 05:14:39.119
middle of his back.

05:14:39.180 --> 05:14:43.020
Sonny loved this move, and at 1st none of

05:14:43.020 --> 05:14:43.799
them had understood why.

05:14:43.860 --> 05:14:46.860
If she'd had a poisonous barb on her tail

05:14:46.860 --> 05:14:48.900
like other sand wings, it would have been

05:14:48.900 --> 05:14:51.180
terrifying, but with a harmless tail.

05:14:51.299 --> 05:14:52.080
What was the point?

05:14:52.139 --> 05:14:55.319
Then they'd each experienced it, and

05:14:55.319 --> 05:14:57.240
discovered there was something freaky and

05:14:57.240 --> 05:14:58.139
unsettling about it.

05:14:58.200 --> 05:15:00.779
It felt like being hit by lightning at

05:15:00.779 --> 05:15:01.619
just the wrong spot.

05:15:01.740 --> 05:15:04.799
It was as if their scales knew they could

05:15:04.799 --> 05:15:06.000
have been badly injured.

05:15:06.119 --> 05:15:08.639
If there had been poison at the tip of

05:15:08.639 --> 05:15:10.680
that tail, it would have paralyzed their

05:15:10.680 --> 05:15:12.900
spines instantly and killed them a few

05:15:12.900 --> 05:15:13.380
moments later.

05:15:13.439 --> 05:15:16.740
So it was weirdly chilling, and an

05:15:16.740 --> 05:15:18.299
effective distraction in the middle of a

05:15:18.299 --> 05:15:18.540
fight.

05:15:18.599 --> 05:15:21.959
Glory had no idea if this would work when

05:15:21.959 --> 05:15:24.180
a rain wing did it to a night wing, but

05:15:24.180 --> 05:15:24.779
it was worth a try.

05:15:24.840 --> 05:15:28.139
The guard stiffened, as if he'd just been

05:15:28.139 --> 05:15:30.180
shocked by one of the electric eels in

05:15:30.180 --> 05:15:31.439
Queen Coral's prison.

05:15:31.500 --> 05:15:33.959
It was only for a moment, but in that

05:15:33.959 --> 05:15:36.240
moment, Glory was able to throw him offer

05:15:36.240 --> 05:15:37.500
and free her snout.

05:15:37.560 --> 05:15:40.439
She went straight for Kinkaju's attacker

05:15:40.439 --> 05:15:42.840
shooting venom at all the exposed scales

05:15:42.840 --> 05:15:43.380
she could see.

05:15:43.439 --> 05:15:46.319
He screamed and slammed back into the

05:15:46.319 --> 05:15:46.740
rocks.

05:15:46.799 --> 05:15:49.680
Glory saw another gash along Kinkachu's

05:15:49.680 --> 05:15:51.900
side, the little dragonette was shaking

05:15:51.900 --> 05:15:54.299
and her scales were ripples of pale green

05:15:54.299 --> 05:15:54.659
and white.

05:15:54.720 --> 05:15:57.659
Claws seized Glory's tail before she

05:15:57.659 --> 05:15:58.680
could get to Kinkaju.

05:15:58.740 --> 05:15:59.939
Get out of here.

05:16:00.000 --> 05:16:02.400
Glory shouted, pointing at the hole.

05:16:02.459 --> 05:16:06.299
Go. Kinkaju hesitated, looking beyond

05:16:06.299 --> 05:16:07.680
glory at the night wing guard.

05:16:07.740 --> 05:16:10.080
For a moment, glory was certain that

05:16:10.080 --> 05:16:12.119
she'd disobey and stayed to help fight

05:16:12.119 --> 05:16:15.119
but then, without arguing, Kinkachu

05:16:15.119 --> 05:16:16.919
darted for the tunnel and vanished into

05:16:16.919 --> 05:16:17.520
the darkness.

05:16:17.580 --> 05:16:21.360
Well, good, glory thought, as a spear

05:16:21.360 --> 05:16:23.639
viciously clocked her in the head, someone

05:16:23.639 --> 05:16:25.979
being sensible for once, unlike my

05:16:25.979 --> 05:16:26.279
friends.

05:16:26.340 --> 05:16:29.159
She tried to turn around, but the night

05:16:29.159 --> 05:16:30.240
wing threw her into the wall.

05:16:30.360 --> 05:16:33.479
Stars spun dizzily in Glory's vision.

05:16:33.540 --> 05:16:34.799
Don't pass out.

05:16:34.860 --> 05:16:35.939
Don't pass out.

05:16:36.060 --> 05:16:38.400
If the Nightwings recaptured her.

05:16:38.459 --> 05:16:40.680
She'd never get another chance to use her

05:16:40.680 --> 05:16:41.580
venom and escape.

05:16:41.639 --> 05:16:43.919
They'd probably let her starve to death

05:16:43.919 --> 05:16:44.400
instead.

05:16:44.459 --> 05:16:47.580
Blurrily, she saw clay suddenly drop out

05:16:47.580 --> 05:16:49.740
of the air, and her heart leaped into her

05:16:49.740 --> 05:16:50.040
throat.

05:16:50.099 --> 05:16:51.180
Was he hurt?

05:16:51.299 --> 05:16:54.119
She staggered a step toward him, but a

05:16:54.119 --> 05:16:56.099
sharp pain in her back leg stopped her.

05:16:56.159 --> 05:16:57.840
The guard had stabbed her with his

05:16:57.840 --> 05:16:58.139
spear.

05:16:58.200 --> 05:17:01.560
Glory hissed angrily, and lunged for the

05:17:01.560 --> 05:17:03.240
spear as the guard pulled it back.

05:17:03.419 --> 05:17:05.939
He stabbed it at her again, violent and

05:17:05.939 --> 05:17:08.220
fast, and she felt it scratch her

05:17:08.220 --> 05:17:10.200
underbelly like a sharp line of bee

05:17:10.200 --> 05:17:10.860
stings.

05:17:11.099 --> 05:17:13.680
At the same time, Clay landed right in

05:17:13.680 --> 05:17:14.580
the middle of the fire.

05:17:14.639 --> 05:17:17.639
Flames licked at his underbelly and wings

05:17:17.639 --> 05:17:19.979
and a scorched smell filled the cave.

05:17:20.099 --> 05:17:22.860
Glorious scales hurt just looking at

05:17:22.860 --> 05:17:23.159
him.

05:17:23.220 --> 05:17:25.259
Even if he healed fast.

05:17:25.319 --> 05:17:27.479
She knew his skin was burning right now.

05:17:27.540 --> 05:17:29.459
Clenching his jaw.

05:17:29.520 --> 05:17:32.099
Clay crouched, and picked up smoldering

05:17:32.099 --> 05:17:34.259
coals from the fire in his talons.

05:17:34.319 --> 05:17:36.299
The night wing in the air above him

05:17:36.299 --> 05:17:38.040
didn't have time to figure out what was

05:17:38.040 --> 05:17:38.220
coming.

05:17:38.279 --> 05:17:41.040
Clay flung the coals right in the guard's

05:17:41.040 --> 05:17:43.200
face, and started grabbing and throwing

05:17:43.200 --> 05:17:45.240
more as the guard frantically clawed at

05:17:45.240 --> 05:17:45.840
his snout.

05:17:45.900 --> 05:17:46.919
Clay!

05:17:46.979 --> 05:17:49.979
Glory yelled, as her own opponent flung

05:17:49.979 --> 05:17:52.619
her off balance, Glory fell backward, and

05:17:52.619 --> 05:17:54.299
the night wing was on her in an instant

05:17:54.299 --> 05:17:56.580
wrapping his strong talons around her

05:17:56.580 --> 05:17:57.720
snout to force it shut.

05:17:57.779 --> 05:18:00.360
Red hot coals came flying through the

05:18:00.360 --> 05:18:00.599
air.

05:18:00.659 --> 05:18:03.840
Most bounced off the dragon's armor, and

05:18:03.840 --> 05:18:06.060
one ricocheted painfully against glory's

05:18:06.060 --> 05:18:08.459
bound wings, but a few found the gaps in

05:18:08.459 --> 05:18:09.479
the armor and slid inside.

05:18:09.599 --> 05:18:12.599
The guard let go of glory and started

05:18:12.599 --> 05:18:14.939
clawing at his armor, howling with pain.

05:18:15.000 --> 05:18:17.400
Glory had just made it to her feet again

05:18:17.400 --> 05:18:19.139
when someone grabbed her shoulders.

05:18:19.200 --> 05:18:22.259
She whipped around with a hiss and barely

05:18:22.259 --> 05:18:24.000
managed to stop herself from shooting

05:18:24.000 --> 05:18:25.259
venom and clay's face.

05:18:25.319 --> 05:18:28.619
Quick, he cried, shoving her onto his

05:18:28.619 --> 05:18:28.799
back.

05:18:28.860 --> 05:18:31.319
She grabbed his neck again as he bunched

05:18:31.319 --> 05:18:33.119
his legs and flung himself over the

05:18:33.119 --> 05:18:34.020
guards at the hole.

05:18:34.080 --> 05:18:36.959
One of the injured night wings lunged for

05:18:36.959 --> 05:18:39.060
Clay's tail, but when he saw glory

05:18:39.060 --> 05:18:41.040
opening her mouth, he flinched away.

05:18:41.099 --> 05:18:44.580
Clay dove into the tunnel, which spiraled

05:18:44.580 --> 05:18:45.299
up and around.

05:18:45.360 --> 05:18:48.779
Glory held on tight, burying her head in

05:18:48.779 --> 05:18:50.159
his scales as they flew.

05:18:50.220 --> 05:18:52.439
She could hear rain falling up ahead.

05:18:52.500 --> 05:18:54.119
Almost there.

05:18:54.180 --> 05:18:55.020
She thought.

05:18:55.080 --> 05:18:58.020
Almost safe, for now.

05:18:58.080 --> 05:19:02.580
Chapter 24.

05:19:02.819 --> 05:19:06.360
They emerged into a sun shower.

05:19:06.419 --> 05:19:09.360
Rain dripped down through the leaves, but

05:19:09.360 --> 05:19:11.279
shafts of sunlight still dappled the

05:19:11.279 --> 05:19:13.799
trees, reflecting flashes of light off

05:19:13.799 --> 05:19:16.200
the droplets, and catching rainbows in

05:19:16.200 --> 05:19:17.819
the spider webs and waterfalls.

05:19:17.880 --> 05:19:20.939
Clay tipped Glory off onto the ground, and

05:19:20.939 --> 05:19:22.680
flopped into the nearest mud puddle

05:19:22.680 --> 05:19:23.459
breathing heavily.

05:19:23.520 --> 05:19:26.639
She sat up, shaking herself, and looked

05:19:26.639 --> 05:19:28.080
up at the tunnel to the Nightwing

05:19:28.080 --> 05:19:28.439
Island.

05:19:28.500 --> 05:19:31.200
There was no sound of pursuit, no

05:19:31.200 --> 05:19:33.840
thumping wing beats, no black snout

05:19:33.840 --> 05:19:35.400
crawling out to continue the battle.

05:19:35.459 --> 05:19:38.099
It took her a moment to realize how close

05:19:38.099 --> 05:19:40.500
they were to the other passage, the one

05:19:40.500 --> 05:19:41.400
that went to the desert.

05:19:41.520 --> 05:19:43.919
The 1st tunnel was in a boulder.

05:19:43.979 --> 05:19:46.619
This one went straight into the 2nd dark

05:19:46.619 --> 05:19:48.900
tree, on the other side of the stream.

05:19:48.959 --> 05:19:51.599
She wouldn't have noticed the hole in the

05:19:51.599 --> 05:19:53.400
tree trunk if she hadn't been looking for

05:19:53.400 --> 05:19:53.520
it.

05:19:53.580 --> 05:19:56.700
It was above her eye level, carved into

05:19:56.700 --> 05:19:58.439
the tree at a height where most dragons

05:19:58.439 --> 05:20:00.060
would have to look up to see it.

05:20:00.119 --> 05:20:02.759
It was as dark as the tree itself

05:20:02.759 --> 05:20:06.060
disappearing into the wood, and it pulsed

05:20:06.060 --> 05:20:08.340
with such a feeling of not supposed to be

05:20:08.340 --> 05:20:10.680
there, that she wanted to look away the

05:20:10.680 --> 05:20:12.180
moment her eyes came anywhere near it.

05:20:12.240 --> 05:20:15.659
A 2nd tunnel, she said to Clay.

05:20:15.720 --> 05:20:17.159
That is so weird.

05:20:17.220 --> 05:20:18.900
Do you think there are more?

05:20:18.959 --> 05:20:22.799
Wake me when you figure it out, Clay

05:20:22.799 --> 05:20:23.159
said.

05:20:23.220 --> 05:20:24.659
No, hang on.

05:20:24.720 --> 05:20:27.000
Never wake me up again.

05:20:27.060 --> 05:20:29.819
I'm going to sleep for a few 100 years.

05:20:29.880 --> 05:20:33.779
He scooped up 2 talon fulls of mud and

05:20:33.779 --> 05:20:36.119
poured it onto his head, closing his eyes

05:20:36.119 --> 05:20:36.840
with a sigh.

05:20:36.900 --> 05:20:40.020
Kinkaju shot out of the treetops and

05:20:40.020 --> 05:20:41.220
cannoned into glory.

05:20:41.279 --> 05:20:43.619
I'm so glad you're all right, she

05:20:43.619 --> 05:20:44.159
yelped.

05:20:44.220 --> 05:20:46.380
I didn't want to leave you there, but I

05:20:46.380 --> 05:20:46.799
was so scared.

05:20:46.860 --> 05:20:48.840
You did the right thing.

05:20:48.900 --> 05:20:50.220
Glory said.

05:20:50.279 --> 05:20:52.860
Ducking to avoid the spear, Kinkaju was

05:20:52.860 --> 05:20:53.819
still swinging around.

05:20:53.880 --> 05:20:55.500
Here give me that.

05:20:55.560 --> 05:20:57.779
And go look in that hole to see if

05:20:57.779 --> 05:20:58.560
anyone's following us.

05:20:58.619 --> 05:21:00.959
Kinkaju's eyes went wide.

05:21:01.080 --> 05:21:02.700
But what if they are?

05:21:02.759 --> 05:21:04.139
Then what do I do?

05:21:04.200 --> 05:21:07.439
Scare them back to their hideous island

05:21:07.439 --> 05:21:09.959
Glory said, poking the spear at her

05:21:09.959 --> 05:21:10.439
bindings.

05:21:10.500 --> 05:21:12.779
I'll come help you as soon as I get my

05:21:12.779 --> 05:21:13.380
wings free.

05:21:13.439 --> 05:21:16.020
And if I can figure it out, I'll use this

05:21:16.020 --> 05:21:17.520
thing to get your neck band off too.

05:21:17.639 --> 05:21:20.819
She nodded at the metal ring on Kinkaju.

05:21:20.880 --> 05:21:22.979
The little dragonette shuffled her feet.

05:21:23.040 --> 05:21:27.540
But, um, listen, I...

05:21:27.540 --> 05:21:30.479
I'm not sure I want to use my venom on

05:21:30.479 --> 05:21:33.240
any more dragons, it made me feel really

05:21:33.240 --> 05:21:34.200
really awful.

05:21:34.259 --> 05:21:38.580
Then just pretend you're going to, Glory

05:21:38.580 --> 05:21:38.880
said.

05:21:38.939 --> 05:21:41.099
She nudged the dragonette toward the

05:21:41.099 --> 05:21:41.340
tree.

05:21:41.400 --> 05:21:43.799
Sit in the tunnel entrance with your

05:21:43.799 --> 05:21:45.720
mouth open and try to look sinister, all

05:21:45.720 --> 05:21:45.959
right?

05:21:46.020 --> 05:21:48.060
Kingaju perked up.

05:21:48.119 --> 05:21:51.000
Sure, I bet I can look sinister, super

05:21:51.000 --> 05:21:51.840
sinister.

05:21:51.900 --> 05:21:52.860
Just watch me.

05:21:52.979 --> 05:21:56.040
She flapped up to the hole, curled her

05:21:56.040 --> 05:21:58.439
tail around her talons, opened her mouth

05:21:58.439 --> 05:22:00.479
and squinted fiercely down the tunnel.

05:22:00.540 --> 05:22:03.119
She looked more like a decorative

05:22:03.119 --> 05:22:05.099
doorstop than a guard, but it would have

05:22:05.099 --> 05:22:05.580
to do for now.

05:22:05.639 --> 05:22:08.639
Glory kept one eye on her as she worked

05:22:08.639 --> 05:22:09.479
to free her wings.

05:22:09.540 --> 05:22:11.939
It was a little unsettling that no one

05:22:11.939 --> 05:22:13.259
had chased them through the tunnel.

05:22:13.380 --> 05:22:15.479
Maybe the Nightwing thought there'd be

05:22:15.479 --> 05:22:17.220
more dragons waiting on this end to fight

05:22:17.220 --> 05:22:18.299
them off.

05:22:18.360 --> 05:22:19.619
How long had she been gone?

05:22:19.680 --> 05:22:22.740
She squinted at the angle of the sunbeams

05:22:22.740 --> 05:22:24.479
and realized it must be morning.

05:22:24.540 --> 05:22:26.939
It felt like she'd been trapped in the

05:22:26.939 --> 05:22:29.220
night kingdom for a month, but it had

05:22:29.220 --> 05:22:30.119
been only a day.

05:22:30.180 --> 05:22:33.119
She had one rope left to untie when she

05:22:33.119 --> 05:22:34.380
heard voices approaching through the

05:22:34.380 --> 05:22:34.680
forest.

05:22:34.740 --> 05:22:37.259
This is a terrible idea.

05:22:37.500 --> 05:22:39.299
Can't we discuss it like sensible

05:22:39.299 --> 05:22:39.900
dragons?

05:22:39.959 --> 05:22:41.639
There's no time.

05:22:41.700 --> 05:22:43.860
Clay and Glory have been kidnapped by

05:22:43.860 --> 05:22:45.119
that Nightwing assassin.

05:22:45.180 --> 05:22:46.020
I have to save them.

05:22:46.080 --> 05:22:49.680
But we don't know that he took them, and

05:22:49.680 --> 05:22:51.060
we don't know that he went through the

05:22:51.060 --> 05:22:52.979
tunnel or where they might be in the

05:22:52.979 --> 05:22:55.139
kingdom of sand, and we're over here

05:22:55.139 --> 05:22:56.400
Glory called.

05:22:56.459 --> 05:22:58.860
There was a pause, followed by some

05:22:58.860 --> 05:22:59.880
vigorous flapping.

05:22:59.939 --> 05:23:02.880
Starflight and tsunami burst out of the

05:23:02.880 --> 05:23:05.459
trees, and soared down over the stream to

05:23:05.459 --> 05:23:06.479
land beside clay.

05:23:06.540 --> 05:23:09.180
A few moments later, Sonny caught up to

05:23:09.180 --> 05:23:09.360
them.

05:23:09.419 --> 05:23:12.180
Glory's sloth was sitting on her head

05:23:12.180 --> 05:23:14.340
clutching Sonny's horns with a startled

05:23:14.340 --> 05:23:14.819
expression.

05:23:14.880 --> 05:23:18.959
Oh, I knew you were all right, Sonny said

05:23:18.959 --> 05:23:19.439
brightly.

05:23:19.500 --> 05:23:22.380
She hesitated, squinting at clay and the

05:23:22.380 --> 05:23:23.880
mud dripping over his snout.

05:23:23.939 --> 05:23:26.520
Her eyes took in the wounds slashed along

05:23:26.520 --> 05:23:27.599
glory's scales.

05:23:27.659 --> 05:23:30.119
Um, are you all right?

05:23:30.180 --> 05:23:34.380
Of course, Clay said, squishing himself

05:23:34.380 --> 05:23:35.939
farther down into the mud puddle.

05:23:36.000 --> 05:23:38.880
Silver leaped from Sonny onto Glory's

05:23:38.880 --> 05:23:41.340
neck and started tugging on Glory's ears

05:23:41.340 --> 05:23:43.200
warbling a furry complaint.

05:23:43.259 --> 05:23:45.479
Glory caught her between her claws and

05:23:45.479 --> 05:23:46.380
stroked her head.

05:23:46.380 --> 05:23:49.860
Sorry, she whispered, but it wouldn't

05:23:49.860 --> 05:23:50.639
have been safe for you.

05:23:50.759 --> 05:23:52.740
Irv.

05:23:52.799 --> 05:23:54.299
The soft objected.

05:23:54.360 --> 05:23:55.680
Where were you?

05:23:55.740 --> 05:23:57.060
Tsunami cried.

05:23:57.119 --> 05:23:58.799
Death bringers escaped.

05:23:58.860 --> 05:23:59.700
He could be anywhere.

05:23:59.759 --> 05:24:01.619
He could jump out and try to kill you at

05:24:01.619 --> 05:24:02.040
any time.

05:24:02.159 --> 05:24:04.979
Actually, he's in there.

05:24:05.040 --> 05:24:07.619
Glory said, pointing up at the tree.

05:24:07.680 --> 05:24:10.080
Her friends all crane their necks to

05:24:10.080 --> 05:24:10.680
appear at the hole.

05:24:10.799 --> 05:24:12.599
Another tunnel?

05:24:12.720 --> 05:24:13.619
Sonny said.

05:24:13.680 --> 05:24:15.479
She glanced across the stream and

05:24:15.479 --> 05:24:15.900
shivered.

05:24:16.020 --> 05:24:19.020
I mean, I noticed the weird feeling, but

05:24:19.020 --> 05:24:21.180
I thought it was still coming from that

05:24:21.180 --> 05:24:21.360
one.

05:24:21.419 --> 05:24:23.759
Where does this one go?

05:24:23.819 --> 05:24:25.380
Starflight asked.

05:24:25.439 --> 05:24:27.180
Glory tilted her head at him.

05:24:27.240 --> 05:24:30.599
It goes to the night kingdom, she said.

05:24:30.659 --> 05:24:34.439
Starflight inhaled softly and stared up

05:24:34.439 --> 05:24:34.979
at the tree.

05:24:35.040 --> 05:24:37.799
She saw the anxiety and curiosity

05:24:37.799 --> 05:24:40.500
tingling through him as clearly as if his

05:24:40.500 --> 05:24:41.939
scales could change color too.

05:24:42.000 --> 05:24:45.540
His tribe was through there, and his

05:24:45.540 --> 05:24:46.259
original home.

05:24:46.319 --> 05:24:48.599
She wondered what he would think of the

05:24:48.599 --> 05:24:51.900
island, the smell, the scorched air and

05:24:51.900 --> 05:24:54.540
unfriendly rocks, the horrible smoky

05:24:54.540 --> 05:24:56.880
cloud that hung over everything, and the

05:24:56.880 --> 05:24:58.439
fact that his fellow night wings were

05:24:58.439 --> 05:25:00.299
kidnapping rain wings for their venom.

05:25:00.360 --> 05:25:03.599
All things considered, she thought she'd

05:25:03.599 --> 05:25:06.240
rather have her own tribe of lazy but not

05:25:06.240 --> 05:25:07.619
evil dragons.

05:25:07.740 --> 05:25:09.779
Listen, she said.

05:25:09.840 --> 05:25:11.939
You may want to sit down for this.

05:25:12.060 --> 05:25:16.259
They decided to leave tsunami and clay

05:25:16.259 --> 05:25:17.099
guarding the tunnel.

05:25:17.159 --> 05:25:20.400
Don't let anyone come through there, Glory

05:25:20.400 --> 05:25:21.180
said fiercely.

05:25:21.240 --> 05:25:23.700
If you even see a hint of a snout poke

05:25:23.700 --> 05:25:25.919
out, you jab it with this thing as hard

05:25:25.919 --> 05:25:26.520
as you can.

05:25:26.639 --> 05:25:28.860
She handed the spear to tsunami.

05:25:28.919 --> 05:25:33.000
No problem, Tsunami said with relish.

05:25:33.060 --> 05:25:35.099
She spun the spear between her talons.

05:25:35.159 --> 05:25:38.639
We'll be back soon, Glory said, with an

05:25:38.639 --> 05:25:39.659
army of rain wings.

05:25:39.720 --> 05:25:43.200
Tsunami and Starflight exchanged glances

05:25:43.200 --> 05:25:45.659
and glory flared her rough at them.

05:25:45.720 --> 05:25:48.240
I know what you're thinking, she snapped

05:25:48.240 --> 05:25:49.619
so don't say it.

05:25:49.680 --> 05:25:52.740
It's just Starflight said.

05:25:52.799 --> 05:25:55.139
I mean, is that a good idea?

05:25:55.200 --> 05:25:58.860
Rain wings aren't very army-like.

05:25:58.979 --> 05:26:01.200
The night wings would crush them easily.

05:26:01.259 --> 05:26:04.139
Especially if any of them look into the

05:26:04.139 --> 05:26:06.540
future and see you coming, Sonny said.

05:26:06.599 --> 05:26:10.200
They didn't foresee me escaping, Glory

05:26:10.200 --> 05:26:10.799
pointed out.

05:26:10.860 --> 05:26:12.659
They're not all powerful.

05:26:12.720 --> 05:26:15.299
We can stop them and rescue the others.

05:26:15.360 --> 05:26:19.020
Maybe it's a misunderstanding.

05:26:19.080 --> 05:26:22.139
Starflight said, resting his front talons

05:26:22.139 --> 05:26:22.560
on the tree.

05:26:22.619 --> 05:26:25.500
Maybe if I went through and talked to

05:26:25.500 --> 05:26:28.680
them, Then maybe you'd end up in a lovely

05:26:28.680 --> 05:26:32.159
lava prison too, Glory said, or dead.

05:26:32.220 --> 05:26:34.619
Let's not forget that you might be one of

05:26:34.619 --> 05:26:36.240
the dragon's death bringer was sent to

05:26:36.240 --> 05:26:36.419
kill.

05:26:36.540 --> 05:26:39.479
She spread her wings, letting them

05:26:39.479 --> 05:26:41.340
shimmer into the colors of the cobweb

05:26:41.340 --> 05:26:41.939
rainbows.

05:26:42.000 --> 05:26:44.400
But feel free to stand here worrying

05:26:44.400 --> 05:26:45.000
about it all day.

05:26:45.060 --> 05:26:48.419
I'm going back to get my tribe, with or

05:26:48.419 --> 05:26:48.900
without you.

05:26:48.959 --> 05:26:52.200
She beckoned to Kinkaju and leaped into

05:26:52.200 --> 05:26:52.500
the air.

05:26:52.560 --> 05:26:55.139
It was a relief to use her own wings

05:26:55.139 --> 05:26:55.439
again.

05:26:55.500 --> 05:26:58.319
She stretched them wide as they soared up

05:26:58.319 --> 05:26:59.279
to the highest branches.

05:26:59.340 --> 05:27:02.279
Silver clung to her shoulders, making

05:27:02.279 --> 05:27:03.419
happy furry noises.

05:27:03.479 --> 05:27:06.119
Kinkaju took the lead with an eager flick

05:27:06.119 --> 05:27:06.599
of her tail.

05:27:06.659 --> 05:27:08.939
Glory had figured out how to get the band

05:27:08.939 --> 05:27:10.439
off with a night wing spear.

05:27:10.500 --> 05:27:12.720
It had left a painful looking dent in

05:27:12.720 --> 05:27:15.240
Kinkaju's neck, but the little dragon was

05:27:15.240 --> 05:27:15.900
too happy to mind.

05:27:15.959 --> 05:27:19.020
Bursts of pink and yellow spiraled

05:27:19.020 --> 05:27:21.240
through her scales, getting brighter the

05:27:21.240 --> 05:27:22.200
closer they got to the village.

05:27:22.259 --> 05:27:24.900
Have they been looking for me every day?

05:27:25.020 --> 05:27:27.779
The dragonette asked, looping back to

05:27:27.779 --> 05:27:28.740
circle around glory.

05:27:28.799 --> 05:27:31.259
Did Bromelia just have a heart attack

05:27:31.259 --> 05:27:32.220
when I disappeared?

05:27:32.279 --> 05:27:33.959
I can imagine her face.

05:27:34.080 --> 05:27:37.439
Kinkaju pursed her snout in a hilariously

05:27:37.439 --> 05:27:39.060
accurate impression of Bromeliad.

05:27:39.119 --> 05:27:41.700
That dragonette got herself kidnapped on

05:27:41.700 --> 05:27:42.119
purpose.

05:27:42.180 --> 05:27:44.700
She's always been trouble.

05:27:44.759 --> 05:27:46.020
Kinkaju giggled.

05:27:46.080 --> 05:27:48.299
I hope she wore out her wings looking for

05:27:48.299 --> 05:27:48.599
me.

05:27:48.659 --> 05:27:49.979
Grumpy old cow.

05:27:50.040 --> 05:27:52.860
Gosh, won't everyone be excited when I

05:27:52.860 --> 05:27:53.639
finally turn up?

05:27:53.700 --> 05:27:56.880
Um, Glory said.

05:27:56.939 --> 05:27:59.880
Don't be upset if there's no welcome home

05:27:59.880 --> 05:28:00.299
party.

05:28:00.360 --> 05:28:02.159
There's coconut.

05:28:02.220 --> 05:28:05.040
Kinkaju cried, spotting a small dragon

05:28:05.040 --> 05:28:07.020
lounging in a hammock on the outskirts of

05:28:07.020 --> 05:28:07.740
the village.

05:28:07.799 --> 05:28:10.319
Aw, look how exhausted he is.

05:28:10.380 --> 05:28:12.900
We took gliding lessons together all last

05:28:12.900 --> 05:28:13.139
year.

05:28:13.200 --> 05:28:15.419
I bet he's been helping to search for

05:28:15.419 --> 05:28:15.599
me.

05:28:15.659 --> 05:28:17.159
Coconut, it's me.

05:28:17.220 --> 05:28:17.880
I'm back.

05:28:17.939 --> 05:28:20.639
She swooped up to the hammock and poked

05:28:20.639 --> 05:28:22.740
it vigorously with her tail until the

05:28:22.740 --> 05:28:25.080
emerald green dragon inside sat up

05:28:25.080 --> 05:28:27.119
blinking, hmm?

05:28:27.180 --> 05:28:27.959
He said.

05:28:28.020 --> 05:28:28.740
What?

05:28:28.860 --> 05:28:30.240
I'm back.

05:28:30.360 --> 05:28:32.880
Kinkaju said, wrapping her wings around

05:28:32.880 --> 05:28:34.500
him and nearly knocking him out of the

05:28:34.500 --> 05:28:34.979
hammock.

05:28:35.040 --> 05:28:36.060
I'm all right.

05:28:36.119 --> 05:28:37.080
I made it home.

05:28:37.139 --> 05:28:40.500
Coconut disentangled himself politely.

05:28:40.560 --> 05:28:42.240
Kinkaju?

05:28:42.299 --> 05:28:43.619
He squinted at her.

05:28:43.680 --> 05:28:45.000
You went somewhere?

05:28:45.060 --> 05:28:48.360
I've been gone for almost 3 whole weeks

05:28:48.360 --> 05:28:49.860
Kinkaju said.

05:28:49.919 --> 05:28:52.680
Her smile faded as the other dragon shook

05:28:52.680 --> 05:28:52.979
his head.

05:28:53.040 --> 05:28:55.139
Didn't you miss me?

05:28:55.200 --> 05:28:59.700
Um, he said, I've been very busy.

05:28:59.759 --> 05:29:03.599
I bet, Glory said disgustedly.

05:29:03.659 --> 05:29:07.139
You, be at Magnificence Pavilion in one

05:29:07.139 --> 05:29:09.419
hour, and bring every other rain wing you

05:29:09.419 --> 05:29:09.840
can find.

05:29:09.900 --> 05:29:11.639
We are having a tribe meeting.

05:29:11.700 --> 05:29:13.680
Oh, what?

05:29:13.799 --> 05:29:15.000
Coconut said.

05:29:15.060 --> 05:29:18.299
And if you're not there, I will know, and

05:29:18.299 --> 05:29:20.040
I will personally come tie you into this

05:29:20.040 --> 05:29:22.020
hammock, so you're stuck here forever

05:29:22.020 --> 05:29:23.520
Glory said.

05:29:23.580 --> 05:29:26.459
Go start telling everyone, go.

05:29:26.520 --> 05:29:29.400
Coconut flailed out of the hammock and

05:29:29.400 --> 05:29:31.259
flapped away, looking confused.

05:29:31.319 --> 05:29:33.959
Glory steered Kinkaju toward the center

05:29:33.959 --> 05:29:34.560
of the village.

05:29:34.619 --> 05:29:37.080
The dragonette's wings were drooping and

05:29:37.080 --> 05:29:38.400
speckled with a blue gray.

05:29:38.459 --> 05:29:41.939
Disappointing young dragons who count on

05:29:41.939 --> 05:29:44.939
them, Glory said. seems to be a rain wing

05:29:44.939 --> 05:29:45.419
specialty.

05:29:45.479 --> 05:29:48.299
Someone must have looked for me?

05:29:48.299 --> 05:29:49.799
said Kinkachu.

05:29:49.860 --> 05:29:53.520
Yes, I did, Glory pointed out.

05:29:53.580 --> 05:29:56.099
She saw the Queen's tree house up ahead

05:29:56.099 --> 05:29:57.299
and veered that way.

05:29:57.360 --> 05:29:59.639
Starfight and Sunny hadn't caught up

05:29:59.639 --> 05:29:59.819
yet.

05:29:59.880 --> 05:30:02.279
Maybe they were busy talking about how

05:30:02.279 --> 05:30:03.900
this plan of glories would fail.

05:30:03.959 --> 05:30:06.900
Or maybe they were checking on webs again

05:30:06.900 --> 05:30:09.240
as if that was at all important compared

05:30:09.240 --> 05:30:10.619
to saving the rain wings.

05:30:10.680 --> 05:30:13.200
The line to see magnificent was shorter

05:30:13.200 --> 05:30:13.439
today.

05:30:13.500 --> 05:30:15.900
Only 2 dragons sat on the waiting

05:30:15.900 --> 05:30:17.939
platform, and neither of them looked

05:30:17.939 --> 05:30:18.900
particularly upset.

05:30:18.959 --> 05:30:21.720
Glory swooped right past them and dove

05:30:21.720 --> 05:30:23.819
through the vine curtain, skidding to a

05:30:23.819 --> 05:30:24.599
stop on the wood floor.

05:30:24.659 --> 05:30:27.900
The rain wing queen jumped, and her sloth

05:30:27.900 --> 05:30:30.060
leaped onto her head, looking startled.

05:30:30.119 --> 05:30:32.759
I found them, Gloria announced.

05:30:32.819 --> 05:30:35.340
She glanced at the dragons magnificent

05:30:35.340 --> 05:30:36.000
was meeting with.

05:30:36.060 --> 05:30:38.819
A young rain wing whose blue green scales

05:30:38.819 --> 05:30:40.319
looked like he was trying to match

05:30:40.319 --> 05:30:42.959
tsunamis, complete with white dots to

05:30:42.959 --> 05:30:45.659
mimic her pearls, and a shrunken old

05:30:45.659 --> 05:30:47.759
dragon with a silvery tinge to his ruff.

05:30:47.880 --> 05:30:50.340
I found the missing rain wings, Your

05:30:50.340 --> 05:30:50.759
Majesty.

05:30:50.819 --> 05:30:54.959
Oh, call me Maggie, said the queen.

05:30:55.020 --> 05:30:57.060
What missing rain wings?

05:30:57.119 --> 05:30:59.520
The ones you sent me to find?

05:30:59.639 --> 05:31:02.819
Glory said impatiently, like Orchid, and

05:31:02.819 --> 05:31:05.220
Queen Splendor, and Kinkajou here?

05:31:05.279 --> 05:31:08.279
Oh, said magnificent.

05:31:08.340 --> 05:31:10.740
A shimmer of dark purple rippled through

05:31:10.740 --> 05:31:11.159
her scales.

05:31:11.279 --> 05:31:13.860
Marvelous, I'm so pleased.

05:31:13.919 --> 05:31:15.900
Do go tell mangrove.

05:31:15.959 --> 05:31:17.639
It'll be so nice not to have to deal with

05:31:17.639 --> 05:31:18.720
that headache anymore.

05:31:18.779 --> 05:31:21.360
She turned back to the other rain wings.

05:31:21.419 --> 05:31:24.479
No, no, listen, Glory said.

05:31:24.540 --> 05:31:25.799
They were abducted.

05:31:25.860 --> 05:31:27.479
We have to go rescue them.

05:31:27.540 --> 05:31:30.540
Magnificent, blinked at Kinkaju.

05:31:30.599 --> 05:31:33.119
Except her, Glory said.

05:31:33.180 --> 05:31:35.700
I mean, we got her out, but the others

05:31:35.700 --> 05:31:36.299
are still there.

05:31:36.360 --> 05:31:38.700
We need to get the tribe together and

05:31:38.700 --> 05:31:40.439
organize an expedition to save them.

05:31:40.500 --> 05:31:42.840
An expedition?

05:31:42.959 --> 05:31:44.580
Magnificent echoed.

05:31:44.639 --> 05:31:47.220
Her eyes wandered to a lizard that was

05:31:47.220 --> 05:31:48.540
crawling slowly through the window.

05:31:48.599 --> 05:31:51.299
Save them from what?

05:31:51.360 --> 05:31:53.700
Asked the blue green rain wing.

05:31:53.759 --> 05:31:56.819
From the night wings, said glory.

05:31:56.880 --> 05:31:59.400
They've been kidnapping rain wings and

05:31:59.400 --> 05:32:02.159
holding them prisoner, she hissed

05:32:02.159 --> 05:32:04.259
remembering the gray dragon's tail

05:32:04.259 --> 05:32:06.840
thumping sadly along the ground as the

05:32:06.840 --> 05:32:07.919
night wings carried him off.

05:32:07.979 --> 05:32:12.840
You want us to fight other dragons?

05:32:12.840 --> 05:32:13.799
said the queen.

05:32:13.860 --> 05:32:15.360
How would we do that?

05:32:15.419 --> 05:32:17.759
Glory clutched her head.

05:32:17.819 --> 05:32:20.459
She knew her scales were vibrating with

05:32:20.459 --> 05:32:23.400
furious sunset colors, but she needed all

05:32:23.400 --> 05:32:25.200
her energy for arguing with a queen.

05:32:25.319 --> 05:32:28.619
With your venom, she said slowly.

05:32:28.680 --> 05:32:32.040
With your camouflage, with your claws and

05:32:32.040 --> 05:32:34.439
teeth, with anything that will save your

05:32:34.439 --> 05:32:35.459
fellow tribe mates.

05:32:35.580 --> 05:32:40.020
We are not fighters, the queen said, as

05:32:40.020 --> 05:32:42.180
if she were explaining the 3 moons to a

05:32:42.180 --> 05:32:43.680
very small dragonette.

05:32:43.740 --> 05:32:46.080
Rain wings aren't built for it.

05:32:46.139 --> 05:32:48.240
We are a peaceful tribe.

05:32:48.299 --> 05:32:50.400
So what do you suggest?

05:32:50.520 --> 05:32:51.840
Glory snapped.

05:32:51.900 --> 05:32:54.360
Ask the night wings nicely to give back

05:32:54.360 --> 05:32:55.740
the dragons they stole?

05:32:55.799 --> 05:32:58.259
Because kidnapping dragons certainly

05:32:58.259 --> 05:33:00.180
makes them seem like a pretty reasonable

05:33:00.180 --> 05:33:02.759
tribe, open to negotiations and all

05:33:02.759 --> 05:33:03.000
that.

05:33:03.000 --> 05:33:06.240
Queen Magnificent examined her claws for

05:33:06.240 --> 05:33:09.000
a moment, then picked up her sloth and

05:33:09.000 --> 05:33:10.380
scratched it under its chin.

05:33:10.380 --> 05:33:13.799
Well, let's think about this sensibly.

05:33:13.860 --> 05:33:16.080
Do we really need to get them back?

05:33:16.139 --> 05:33:19.439
Glory felt as if she'd just been dropped

05:33:19.439 --> 05:33:20.939
in the Night Wings volcano.

05:33:21.000 --> 05:33:22.799
She stared at the queen.

05:33:22.860 --> 05:33:26.580
You mean, you would leave them there?

05:33:26.700 --> 05:33:31.680
Whoa, said the blue dragon, staring at

05:33:31.680 --> 05:33:32.700
Glory's scales.

05:33:32.759 --> 05:33:35.459
I've never seen anyone turn that color

05:33:35.459 --> 05:33:36.119
red before.

05:33:36.180 --> 05:33:40.919
It's only a few dragons, said the queen

05:33:40.919 --> 05:33:42.419
with a wave of one talon.

05:33:42.479 --> 05:33:43.500
Right?

05:33:43.560 --> 05:33:48.180
Five or six. 14, said Kinkaju.

05:33:48.299 --> 05:33:50.459
Not counting the 3 who already died

05:33:50.459 --> 05:33:50.819
there.

05:33:50.880 --> 05:33:54.119
Even mangrove didn't realize how many

05:33:54.119 --> 05:33:56.040
were missing, Glory thought.

05:33:56.099 --> 05:33:58.200
She felt another wave of anger.

05:33:58.259 --> 05:34:01.020
Three dead before anyone even went

05:34:01.020 --> 05:34:01.560
looking for them.

05:34:01.619 --> 05:34:03.840
Were they waiting to be rescued?

05:34:03.900 --> 05:34:06.060
Did they believe someone would come for

05:34:06.060 --> 05:34:06.299
them?

05:34:06.360 --> 05:34:08.759
Or did they know there was no hope?

05:34:08.819 --> 05:34:10.860
See?

05:34:10.919 --> 05:34:14.040
Only 14 said magnificent.

05:34:14.099 --> 05:34:16.139
It doesn't really make that much

05:34:16.139 --> 05:34:16.860
difference, does it?

05:34:16.919 --> 05:34:19.200
There are plenty of other dragons in the

05:34:19.200 --> 05:34:19.560
tribe.

05:34:19.680 --> 05:34:22.919
For a moment, glory was speechless.

05:34:22.979 --> 05:34:27.180
She had never, ever, not once in a

05:34:27.180 --> 05:34:30.000
1000000 years, imagined there could be a

05:34:30.000 --> 05:34:32.220
queen who would let her subjects die

05:34:32.220 --> 05:34:33.900
without lifting a claw to save them.

05:34:34.020 --> 05:34:37.020
If the queen didn't even care, what

05:34:37.020 --> 05:34:40.020
chance did any rain wing have, and there

05:34:40.020 --> 05:34:41.099
was nothing glory could do.

05:34:41.159 --> 05:34:44.220
She wasn't part of the prophecy, she

05:34:44.220 --> 05:34:46.439
wasn't a normal rain wing, and she

05:34:46.439 --> 05:34:48.180
couldn't save the rain wings on her own

05:34:48.180 --> 05:34:50.159
no matter how much she wanted to.

05:34:50.279 --> 05:34:54.240
Without the queen, with no army, she was

05:34:54.240 --> 05:34:55.619
as useless as a sloth.

05:34:55.680 --> 05:34:58.680
She wanted to scream a 1000000 things at

05:34:58.680 --> 05:34:59.040
the queen.

05:34:59.099 --> 05:35:00.720
What is wrong with all of you?

05:35:00.779 --> 05:35:03.540
Don't you have any loyalty or empathy?

05:35:03.599 --> 05:35:06.720
Someone should care when a dragon

05:35:06.720 --> 05:35:07.259
disappears.

05:35:07.380 --> 05:35:10.560
And then she realized exactly what she

05:35:10.560 --> 05:35:11.099
wanted to say.

05:35:11.159 --> 05:35:14.040
She spread her wings and pointed at the

05:35:14.040 --> 05:35:14.700
larger dragon.

05:35:14.759 --> 05:35:16.680
Queen Magnificent?

05:35:16.740 --> 05:35:19.259
I challenge you for the throne of the

05:35:19.259 --> 05:35:19.979
rain wings.

05:35:20.040 --> 05:35:24.599
Chapter 25.

05:35:24.900 --> 05:35:29.340
You mean you want to turn it being queen

05:35:29.340 --> 05:35:31.619
said magnificent, tilting her head in a

05:35:31.619 --> 05:35:32.279
puzzled way.

05:35:32.340 --> 05:35:35.340
I'm sure that could be arranged, if you

05:35:35.340 --> 05:35:37.919
insist, I can talk to the others and try

05:35:37.919 --> 05:35:39.779
to fit you in between grandeur and

05:35:39.779 --> 05:35:41.040
exquisite next year.

05:35:41.099 --> 05:35:46.200
No, I need to be queen now, said Glory.

05:35:46.259 --> 05:35:48.540
She tried not to think about how much

05:35:48.540 --> 05:35:51.299
bigger than her magnificent was or how

05:35:51.299 --> 05:35:52.619
many years older she must be.

05:35:52.680 --> 05:35:56.220
Then again, I'm sure she's never had any

05:35:56.220 --> 05:35:59.340
battle training or faced a Skywings claws

05:35:59.340 --> 05:36:00.599
every morning for 6 years.

05:36:00.659 --> 05:36:03.900
Because if you won't rescue those rain

05:36:03.900 --> 05:36:07.500
wings, I will, whatever it takes, even if

05:36:07.500 --> 05:36:08.939
it means taking the throne from you.

05:36:09.000 --> 05:36:12.659
Oh, wow.

05:36:12.720 --> 05:36:14.459
Kinkachu breathed.

05:36:14.580 --> 05:36:17.220
I don't see how you could possibly do

05:36:17.220 --> 05:36:19.680
that, said Queen Magnificent.

05:36:19.740 --> 05:36:22.200
She looked down and started rearranging

05:36:22.200 --> 05:36:23.520
one of her flower necklaces.

05:36:23.580 --> 05:36:27.060
It's not very complicated, Glory said.

05:36:27.119 --> 05:36:28.139
We fight.

05:36:28.200 --> 05:36:30.479
Whoever survives gets to be queen.

05:36:30.540 --> 05:36:32.939
The other rain wings in the room all

05:36:32.939 --> 05:36:33.479
gasped.

05:36:33.540 --> 05:36:36.419
The queen's scales shimmered white and

05:36:36.419 --> 05:36:36.720
green.

05:36:36.779 --> 05:36:38.639
She stared at Glory.

05:36:38.700 --> 05:36:42.540
You would kill another dragon, just so

05:36:42.540 --> 05:36:43.319
you could be queen.

05:36:43.380 --> 05:36:46.500
That's how it works in every other tribe

05:36:46.500 --> 05:36:47.880
Glory pointed out.

05:36:47.939 --> 05:36:51.180
Not here, said Magnificent.

05:36:51.240 --> 05:36:53.159
That's barbaric.

05:36:53.220 --> 05:36:55.139
What's barbaric?

05:36:55.139 --> 05:36:57.419
is abandoning dragons of your tribe when

05:36:57.419 --> 05:36:59.220
you could save them, said glory

05:36:59.220 --> 05:36:59.759
fiercely.

05:36:59.819 --> 05:37:02.639
Queen Magnificent waved her front claws

05:37:02.639 --> 05:37:05.159
airily, and addressed herself to Kinkaju

05:37:05.159 --> 05:37:06.299
and the blue green dragon.

05:37:06.360 --> 05:37:09.360
I'm sure no rain wing would follow a

05:37:09.360 --> 05:37:11.040
queen who got her thrown by violence.

05:37:11.159 --> 05:37:12.479
Agreed.

05:37:12.479 --> 05:37:15.419
The blue green dragon shrugged, but

05:37:15.419 --> 05:37:17.340
Kinkachu puffed out her chest and glared

05:37:17.340 --> 05:37:17.819
at the queen.

05:37:17.880 --> 05:37:21.540
I'd follow glory anywhere, she said.

05:37:21.659 --> 05:37:24.299
It's not the rain wing way.

05:37:24.360 --> 05:37:26.099
Magnificent protested.

05:37:26.159 --> 05:37:29.639
As far as I can tell, the rain wing way

05:37:29.639 --> 05:37:32.220
is to lie around and do nothing.

05:37:32.340 --> 05:37:33.599
Glory snapped.

05:37:33.659 --> 05:37:35.159
So why don't you do that?

05:37:35.220 --> 05:37:37.200
And I'll just go ahead and be Queen.

05:37:37.259 --> 05:37:40.080
After all, no one really wants the job

05:37:40.080 --> 05:37:40.259
right?

05:37:40.380 --> 05:37:45.000
Maybe, I don't want you to have it, said

05:37:45.000 --> 05:37:45.900
the queen with a growl.

05:37:46.020 --> 05:37:51.180
There is an old tradition, interjected

05:37:51.180 --> 05:37:52.680
the ancient dragon suddenly.

05:37:52.740 --> 05:37:55.259
If anyone wants to hear about it.

05:37:55.319 --> 05:37:58.259
The old rain wing chuckled, as they all

05:37:58.259 --> 05:37:59.099
turned to him.

05:37:59.159 --> 05:38:01.979
Don't look at me like that, Maggie.

05:38:02.040 --> 05:38:05.159
It's the fair thing to do, and it gives

05:38:05.159 --> 05:38:07.979
you as much chance, if not more, of

05:38:07.979 --> 05:38:08.880
keeping the throne.

05:38:08.939 --> 05:38:11.040
What is it?

05:38:11.099 --> 05:38:12.000
Glory asked.

05:38:12.060 --> 05:38:15.180
A contest. he said.

05:38:15.240 --> 05:38:19.080
Legend has it the dragons once vied for

05:38:19.080 --> 05:38:22.319
our throne like any other, but over time

05:38:22.319 --> 05:38:25.139
the rain wings devised a new method that

05:38:25.139 --> 05:38:26.279
did not end in death.

05:38:26.340 --> 05:38:29.819
If a challenger wished to take the throne

05:38:29.819 --> 05:38:32.340
she had to defeat the present queen in a

05:38:32.340 --> 05:38:33.119
competition.

05:38:33.180 --> 05:38:36.000
And the queen had the right to choose the

05:38:36.000 --> 05:38:37.139
nature of the contest.

05:38:37.200 --> 05:38:40.139
That sounds exhausting.

05:38:40.259 --> 05:38:43.200
Magnificent said peevishly.

05:38:43.259 --> 05:38:46.500
It sounds fair to me, said Glory.

05:38:46.560 --> 05:38:49.380
Typical rain wing nonsense, but honestly

05:38:49.380 --> 05:38:51.659
becoming queen without any killing would

05:38:51.659 --> 05:38:52.380
be fine by her.

05:38:52.439 --> 05:38:55.439
What kinds of contests did they have?

05:38:55.500 --> 05:38:58.259
The old dragon squinted into the air.

05:38:58.319 --> 05:39:02.700
Let me think, he said, counting on his

05:39:02.700 --> 05:39:03.240
claws.

05:39:03.299 --> 05:39:06.299
Once there was a gliding race through the

05:39:06.299 --> 05:39:09.299
treetops, and when I was a very young

05:39:09.299 --> 05:39:12.720
dragonette, I saw a camouflage contest.

05:39:12.779 --> 05:39:15.419
One would hide while the other tried to

05:39:15.419 --> 05:39:17.340
find her, and then vice versa.

05:39:17.400 --> 05:39:20.099
The winner was the one who found the

05:39:20.099 --> 05:39:21.000
other fastest.

05:39:21.060 --> 05:39:24.419
A game of hide and seek to become queen

05:39:24.419 --> 05:39:25.619
Glory said.

05:39:25.680 --> 05:39:27.419
Why not?

05:39:27.479 --> 05:39:29.880
She hoped no one could tell that she was

05:39:29.880 --> 05:39:30.720
a bit shaken.

05:39:30.779 --> 05:39:33.479
She was pretty sure she'd be better at a

05:39:33.479 --> 05:39:35.700
fight to the death, than she would be at

05:39:35.700 --> 05:39:38.639
tree gliding, or flower picking, or

05:39:38.639 --> 05:39:39.959
whatever a magnificent would come up

05:39:39.959 --> 05:39:40.200
with.

05:39:40.259 --> 05:39:42.419
But if she wanted to be queen of the rain

05:39:42.419 --> 05:39:44.520
wings, she'd have to start acting like

05:39:44.520 --> 05:39:44.759
one.

05:39:44.880 --> 05:39:48.360
Keeping her scales evenly red, she turned

05:39:48.360 --> 05:39:49.259
to magnificent.

05:39:49.319 --> 05:39:52.860
Go ahead and name your contest, your

05:39:52.860 --> 05:39:53.400
majesty.

05:39:53.459 --> 05:39:56.279
Magnificent narrowed her eyes.

05:39:56.340 --> 05:39:59.520
I want a day to think about it, she

05:39:59.520 --> 05:39:59.759
said.

05:39:59.880 --> 05:40:03.599
That is customary, agreed the old

05:40:03.599 --> 05:40:04.080
dragon.

05:40:04.139 --> 05:40:06.060
Glory lashed her tail.

05:40:06.119 --> 05:40:08.700
The kidnapped rain wings might not have a

05:40:08.700 --> 05:40:09.180
day.

05:40:09.240 --> 05:40:11.159
Who knew what the night wings would do

05:40:11.159 --> 05:40:12.360
now that they'd been found out?

05:40:12.419 --> 05:40:14.520
What if they killed all their prisoners

05:40:14.520 --> 05:40:15.479
to hide the evidence?

05:40:15.540 --> 05:40:17.880
Or what if they were gathering an army

05:40:17.880 --> 05:40:19.860
and shoring up their defenses right now?

05:40:19.919 --> 05:40:23.340
A quick, overwhelming attack before the

05:40:23.340 --> 05:40:25.020
night wings could prepare?

05:40:25.080 --> 05:40:26.159
That what glory had been planning.

05:40:26.220 --> 05:40:30.060
Maybe I could go back tonight by myself

05:40:30.060 --> 05:40:30.840
she thought.

05:40:30.959 --> 05:40:33.299
Maybe I could sneak through the tunnel

05:40:33.299 --> 05:40:35.459
and free them all and melt any night

05:40:35.459 --> 05:40:37.439
wings who tried to stop me and bring

05:40:37.439 --> 05:40:38.099
everyone home.

05:40:38.159 --> 05:40:41.099
But she remembered the feeling of

05:40:41.099 --> 05:40:42.959
nightwing claws pressing her into the

05:40:42.959 --> 05:40:45.599
stone, and the cold band of metal around

05:40:45.599 --> 05:40:46.200
her jaws.

05:40:46.259 --> 05:40:49.020
If she went back alone and got caught

05:40:49.020 --> 05:40:51.180
there wouldn't be time for anyone to come

05:40:51.180 --> 05:40:53.340
after her, the night wings would kill her

05:40:53.340 --> 05:40:55.860
on sight, and then there would be no hope

05:40:55.860 --> 05:40:57.900
for the imprisoned rain wings at all.

05:40:57.959 --> 05:41:01.259
No, she couldn't rescue anyone without an

05:41:01.259 --> 05:41:03.720
army, which meant she needed the power of

05:41:03.720 --> 05:41:05.880
the throne behind her, and to get that

05:41:05.880 --> 05:41:07.619
she had to win this contest.

05:41:07.680 --> 05:41:10.799
And with a day, she might at least have a

05:41:10.799 --> 05:41:11.639
chance of preparing.

05:41:11.700 --> 05:41:14.939
Maybe Jambu could teach her tree gliding

05:41:14.939 --> 05:41:15.720
like he'd promised.

05:41:15.779 --> 05:41:19.919
All right, she said. meeting the queen's

05:41:19.919 --> 05:41:20.220
eyes.

05:41:20.279 --> 05:41:21.840
Sunrise tomorrow.

05:41:21.900 --> 05:41:26.580
At the arboretum, said magnificent, with

05:41:26.580 --> 05:41:28.979
a sly smile, as if she knew perfectly

05:41:28.979 --> 05:41:30.720
well that Glory had no idea where that

05:41:30.720 --> 05:41:30.959
was.

05:41:31.020 --> 05:41:34.860
Also memorize the layout of the rain wing

05:41:34.860 --> 05:41:35.220
village.

05:41:35.279 --> 05:41:37.020
Glory noted to herself.

05:41:37.080 --> 05:41:40.979
Just in case she chooses like a scavenger

05:41:40.979 --> 05:41:41.880
hunt or something.

05:41:41.939 --> 05:41:44.700
Magnificent nodded toward the old

05:41:44.700 --> 05:41:45.419
dragon.

05:41:45.479 --> 05:41:47.340
What was your name again?

05:41:47.400 --> 05:41:50.520
Handsome, he said.

05:41:50.580 --> 05:41:52.200
He winked at glory.

05:41:52.259 --> 05:41:54.959
Our names don't always end up suiting

05:41:54.959 --> 05:41:55.200
us.

05:41:55.259 --> 05:41:59.040
Handsome can oversee the contest, since

05:41:59.040 --> 05:42:01.200
this was his stupid suggestion

05:42:01.200 --> 05:42:02.459
Magnificent said.

05:42:02.520 --> 05:42:05.220
If that's all right with you, Pipsqueak.

05:42:05.279 --> 05:42:08.040
Sounds perfect, Glory said.

05:42:08.159 --> 05:42:10.259
Enjoy your last day as queen.

05:42:10.380 --> 05:42:13.080
She ducked out through the vine curtain

05:42:13.080 --> 05:42:14.580
and stood on the bridge for a moment

05:42:14.580 --> 05:42:16.380
breathing deeply.

05:42:16.439 --> 05:42:18.900
The full impact of what she'd just done

05:42:18.900 --> 05:42:20.580
was finally starting to hit her.

05:42:20.639 --> 05:42:22.560
Am I crazy?

05:42:22.619 --> 05:42:26.040
Do I even want to be queen of the rain

05:42:26.040 --> 05:42:28.380
wings and be stuck here forever?

05:42:28.439 --> 05:42:30.599
Trying to organize these hopeless

05:42:30.599 --> 05:42:31.740
dragons?

05:42:31.799 --> 05:42:34.020
She could just imagine what her friends

05:42:34.020 --> 05:42:35.580
were going to say about this.

05:42:35.639 --> 05:42:39.540
She looked up and saw about 25 rain wings

05:42:39.540 --> 05:42:41.340
all crowded onto the waiting platform

05:42:41.340 --> 05:42:42.419
staring at her.

05:42:42.479 --> 05:42:44.279
One of them was coconut.

05:42:44.340 --> 05:42:46.740
Apparently, this was the best he could

05:42:46.740 --> 05:42:48.419
muster when asked to gather the whole

05:42:48.419 --> 05:42:48.840
village.

05:42:48.900 --> 05:42:51.959
But judging from their expressions, they'd

05:42:51.959 --> 05:42:53.340
heard Glory's conversation with

05:42:53.340 --> 05:42:54.000
magnificent.

05:42:54.060 --> 05:42:56.520
And from what she knew about rain wings

05:42:56.520 --> 05:42:58.439
this was the kind of news that would

05:42:58.439 --> 05:43:00.900
spread quickly, mainly because it meant

05:43:00.900 --> 05:43:02.939
they'd have some entertainment at sunrise

05:43:02.939 --> 05:43:03.299
tomorrow.

05:43:03.360 --> 05:43:05.880
Kingachu bounced out of the tree house

05:43:05.880 --> 05:43:07.799
behind her, and solve the dragons as

05:43:07.799 --> 05:43:07.979
well.

05:43:08.040 --> 05:43:10.439
Coconut, she cried.

05:43:10.500 --> 05:43:11.340
Did you hear that?

05:43:11.400 --> 05:43:14.459
The other dragonette scuffed one talon

05:43:14.459 --> 05:43:15.599
across the wooden platform.

05:43:15.659 --> 05:43:18.060
Sure, he said.

05:43:18.119 --> 05:43:20.400
We're going to have a proper queen for

05:43:20.400 --> 05:43:20.759
once.

05:43:20.819 --> 05:43:22.560
Kinkaju said proudly.

05:43:22.619 --> 05:43:25.799
A few of the rain wings exchanged glances

05:43:25.799 --> 05:43:28.439
turning an odd shade of light, purplish

05:43:28.439 --> 05:43:29.340
orange.

05:43:29.400 --> 05:43:31.380
Glory guessed it meant puzzled or

05:43:31.380 --> 05:43:31.860
confused.

05:43:31.919 --> 05:43:34.799
It wasn't a color she wore, or let

05:43:34.799 --> 05:43:37.020
herself wear, very often.

05:43:37.080 --> 05:43:40.860
A proper queen, echoed another of the

05:43:40.860 --> 05:43:44.220
rain wings, is, uh, is that something we

05:43:44.220 --> 05:43:44.700
need?

05:43:44.759 --> 05:43:47.400
What's wrong with the ones we've got?

05:43:47.520 --> 05:43:48.840
asked another.

05:43:48.959 --> 05:43:52.259
Why don't you ask Gibbon that question?

05:43:52.439 --> 05:43:53.580
Kingaju shot back.

05:43:53.639 --> 05:43:57.479
Or Orchid, or Splendor, or Tulong, or

05:43:57.479 --> 05:43:58.020
Loris?

05:43:58.139 --> 05:44:00.779
All of the dragons were frowning now.

05:44:00.840 --> 05:44:03.119
Several of them glanced around at the

05:44:03.119 --> 05:44:05.400
trees, as if they expected orchid and

05:44:05.400 --> 05:44:07.200
splendor to come sauntering out to be

05:44:07.200 --> 05:44:07.799
interviewed.

05:44:07.860 --> 05:44:11.520
Hmm, that's right, Kinkachu said.

05:44:11.580 --> 05:44:13.319
Haven't seen them in a while, have you?

05:44:13.439 --> 05:44:15.840
That's because they've been kidnapped

05:44:15.840 --> 05:44:18.240
like I was, and they're still trapped

05:44:18.240 --> 05:44:18.599
there.

05:44:18.659 --> 05:44:22.799
Except for taper and bright, and

05:44:22.799 --> 05:44:26.159
orangutan, who died of awful deaths, alone

05:44:26.159 --> 05:44:28.680
and far away from everything and everyone

05:44:28.680 --> 05:44:29.340
they loved.

05:44:29.400 --> 05:44:31.860
And the only dragon who's willing to do

05:44:31.860 --> 05:44:34.619
anything about it is glory.

05:44:34.680 --> 05:44:36.360
That's why she should be our queen.

05:44:36.419 --> 05:44:39.959
Glory did not enjoy the awkward pause

05:44:39.959 --> 05:44:40.680
that followed.

05:44:40.740 --> 05:44:43.319
A number of the rain wings wrinkled up

05:44:43.319 --> 05:44:45.180
their snouts, as if they were trying to

05:44:45.180 --> 05:44:47.220
figure out who this glory character was.

05:44:47.279 --> 05:44:49.740
Don't listen to her.

05:44:49.799 --> 05:44:52.080
From Iliad shouldered her way to the

05:44:52.080 --> 05:44:54.599
other dragons and glared at Kinkaju.

05:44:54.659 --> 05:44:56.520
Her tongue flicked in and out of her

05:44:56.520 --> 05:44:56.639
mouth.

05:44:56.759 --> 05:44:59.040
This dragonette is trouble.

05:44:59.099 --> 05:45:01.560
She's been hiding in the forest for 3

05:45:01.560 --> 05:45:04.380
weeks to spite me, and now she's made up

05:45:04.380 --> 05:45:06.060
a ridiculous tale just for the

05:45:06.060 --> 05:45:06.419
attention.

05:45:06.540 --> 05:45:10.200
Violent orange shot through Kinkaju's

05:45:10.200 --> 05:45:12.119
wings, and she bared her fangs of

05:45:12.119 --> 05:45:13.259
Bromeliad with a hiss.

05:45:13.319 --> 05:45:15.779
Put a sheep in it, Bromeliad.

05:45:15.840 --> 05:45:18.299
Gloria said, pulling Kinkaju back behind

05:45:18.299 --> 05:45:18.599
her.

05:45:18.659 --> 05:45:19.860
It's all true.

05:45:19.919 --> 05:45:21.180
I was there too.

05:45:21.240 --> 05:45:23.580
She turned her attention to the other

05:45:23.580 --> 05:45:26.159
dragons on the platform, and the ones who

05:45:26.159 --> 05:45:27.599
are starting to gather in the trees as

05:45:27.599 --> 05:45:27.779
well.

05:45:27.840 --> 05:45:29.580
Listen to me.

05:45:29.639 --> 05:45:31.860
Your friends are suffering.

05:45:31.919 --> 05:45:35.220
They're tortured and trapped in caves in

05:45:35.220 --> 05:45:37.619
a horrible place that smells of smoke and

05:45:37.619 --> 05:45:37.979
death.

05:45:38.040 --> 05:45:39.900
There's no fruit.

05:45:39.959 --> 05:45:41.340
There's no sun time.

05:45:41.400 --> 05:45:44.279
Horrified murmurs swept through the

05:45:44.279 --> 05:45:45.000
branches overhead.

05:45:45.060 --> 05:45:47.580
No sun time?

05:45:47.639 --> 05:45:48.900
Somebody squeaked.

05:45:48.959 --> 05:45:51.900
Glory took a step along the bridge, and

05:45:51.900 --> 05:45:53.759
several of the rain wings quailed back.

05:45:53.880 --> 05:45:57.240
This could have happened, could still

05:45:57.240 --> 05:45:59.159
happen, to any of you.

05:45:59.220 --> 05:46:02.759
If you won't go rescue them, who will?

05:46:02.759 --> 05:46:04.439
They'll be lost there forever.

05:46:04.500 --> 05:46:06.900
Glory lashed her tail.

05:46:06.959 --> 05:46:09.479
I know you'd rather sleep than deal with

05:46:09.479 --> 05:46:11.819
problems, but these dragons are from your

05:46:11.819 --> 05:46:13.740
tribe, and they need you.

05:46:13.799 --> 05:46:16.439
She glanced back at the treehouse behind

05:46:16.439 --> 05:46:18.299
her and raised her voice.

05:46:18.360 --> 05:46:20.700
That's why I'm going to take the throne

05:46:20.700 --> 05:46:21.119
tomorrow.

05:46:21.180 --> 05:46:23.340
It's not because I want the biggest

05:46:23.340 --> 05:46:25.979
pieces of fruit or the highest sun

05:46:25.979 --> 05:46:26.459
platform.

05:46:26.520 --> 05:46:29.819
I'm doing this for the missing rain wings

05:46:29.819 --> 05:46:31.799
and for you, so that you don't have to

05:46:31.799 --> 05:46:33.779
spend the rest of your lives, looking

05:46:33.779 --> 05:46:36.240
over your shoulders and thinking, our

05:46:36.240 --> 05:46:37.560
friends are still lost.

05:46:37.680 --> 05:46:39.720
And we could have saved them.

05:46:39.779 --> 05:46:44.400
Chapter 26.

05:46:44.639 --> 05:46:48.959
Glory took a deep breath and studied her

05:46:48.959 --> 05:46:49.259
audience.

05:46:49.319 --> 05:46:51.779
Most of the dragons looked confused.

05:46:51.900 --> 05:46:54.240
But if you had dark purple stripes

05:46:54.240 --> 05:46:57.119
rippling over their scales, guilt and

05:46:57.119 --> 05:46:59.759
shame, living right next to pride on the

05:46:59.759 --> 05:47:00.720
color spectrum.

05:47:00.779 --> 05:47:02.939
Hmm, glory thought.

05:47:03.000 --> 05:47:06.180
That's about all the noble speechifying

05:47:06.180 --> 05:47:06.900
I've got in me.

05:47:06.959 --> 05:47:09.419
Somehow it had always seemed more

05:47:09.419 --> 05:47:11.459
believable and less awkward in the

05:47:11.459 --> 05:47:12.419
scrolls she read.

05:47:12.479 --> 05:47:14.700
The stirring speech was always where

05:47:14.700 --> 05:47:15.900
chapters ended.

05:47:15.959 --> 05:47:18.659
But right now, a host of dragons were

05:47:18.659 --> 05:47:20.819
just staring at her, and she couldn't

05:47:20.819 --> 05:47:22.439
remember anything from the stories about

05:47:22.439 --> 05:47:24.779
what you did at the end of a noble speech

05:47:24.779 --> 05:47:26.639
or how to slink away gracefully

05:47:26.639 --> 05:47:27.419
afterward.

05:47:27.479 --> 05:47:31.740
So there, said Kinkachu. sticking out her

05:47:31.740 --> 05:47:32.819
tongue at Bromeliad.

05:47:32.880 --> 05:47:35.880
Glory was pretty sure that wasn't it.

05:47:35.939 --> 05:47:37.979
What do we do now?

05:47:38.040 --> 05:47:40.380
Kinkaju asked Glory brightly.

05:47:40.439 --> 05:47:43.139
The blue gray was gone from her scales

05:47:43.139 --> 05:47:45.060
and all her energy had returned.

05:47:45.119 --> 05:47:46.500
Never mind.

05:47:46.560 --> 05:47:48.240
I know exactly what we're doing first.

05:47:48.299 --> 05:47:50.700
Finding something decent to eat.

05:47:50.759 --> 05:47:53.819
Glory turned her back on her wide-eyed

05:47:53.819 --> 05:47:55.979
audience and focused on Kinkaju.

05:47:56.040 --> 05:47:57.240
You go ahead.

05:47:57.299 --> 05:47:59.159
I have to tell my friends what just

05:47:59.159 --> 05:48:01.740
happened, and also find someone to teach

05:48:01.740 --> 05:48:04.259
me everything about rain wing skills in

05:48:04.259 --> 05:48:04.860
the next day.

05:48:04.919 --> 05:48:08.099
I can do that, Kingachu said.

05:48:08.159 --> 05:48:11.040
After I eat, I'm going to eat every piece

05:48:11.040 --> 05:48:12.419
of fruit in the rainforest.

05:48:12.479 --> 05:48:13.799
Where should I meet you?

05:48:13.860 --> 05:48:16.439
Try the healer's hut.

05:48:16.560 --> 05:48:17.939
Glory said with a sigh.

05:48:18.060 --> 05:48:19.619
Bring mangrove too.

05:48:19.680 --> 05:48:22.380
Kingajoo shot off into the trees.

05:48:22.439 --> 05:48:24.599
Glory swiveled her head around and

05:48:24.599 --> 05:48:26.340
checked that silver was still asleep on

05:48:26.340 --> 05:48:28.860
her shoulder, ignoring the crowd.

05:48:28.919 --> 05:48:30.479
She spread her wings and flew away.

05:48:30.540 --> 05:48:33.299
If she remembered magnificent directions

05:48:33.299 --> 05:48:35.819
correctly, the healer's tree house was

05:48:35.819 --> 05:48:36.540
not far.

05:48:36.599 --> 05:48:39.119
She spotted the red berries growing on

05:48:39.119 --> 05:48:41.220
the balcony, and swooped down to a tree

05:48:41.220 --> 05:48:43.619
house, whose leafy roof was dotted with

05:48:43.619 --> 05:48:44.580
skylight holes.

05:48:44.639 --> 05:48:48.360
Inside, only 2 of the beds were taken, one

05:48:48.360 --> 05:48:50.520
by Webbs, and the other by a sleeping

05:48:50.520 --> 05:48:53.400
rain wing with a bandage on his snout, as

05:48:53.400 --> 05:48:55.200
if he had bumped into a tree while flying

05:48:55.200 --> 05:48:55.740
around.

05:48:55.799 --> 05:48:58.500
Three rain wings and shades of white and

05:48:58.500 --> 05:49:00.479
soothing blue were gathered in a corner

05:49:00.479 --> 05:49:02.880
eating bananas, and talking in low

05:49:02.880 --> 05:49:03.479
voices.

05:49:03.540 --> 05:49:06.419
Sure enough, Sonny and Starflight were

05:49:06.419 --> 05:49:08.340
crouched beside Webbs, watching him

05:49:08.340 --> 05:49:08.819
anxiously.

05:49:08.880 --> 05:49:11.639
Well, Sonny was watching webs.

05:49:11.759 --> 05:49:14.939
As usual, Starflight was watching Sonny.

05:49:15.000 --> 05:49:17.220
Webbs was sprawled across a nest of

05:49:17.220 --> 05:49:19.139
spider shaped leaves in the sunlight.

05:49:19.200 --> 05:49:22.319
He was asleep, breathing peacefully for

05:49:22.319 --> 05:49:24.240
the 1st time since blister had attacked

05:49:24.240 --> 05:49:24.419
him.

05:49:24.479 --> 05:49:25.979
Sonny was right.

05:49:26.040 --> 05:49:28.380
The cactus juice clearly was working.

05:49:28.439 --> 05:49:30.959
The scratch on his tail wasn't completely

05:49:30.959 --> 05:49:33.479
healed, but the edges looked much less

05:49:33.479 --> 05:49:36.659
raw, and the black had faded instead of

05:49:36.659 --> 05:49:37.319
spreading further.

05:49:37.380 --> 05:49:41.040
I guess you saved him, Glory remarked

05:49:41.040 --> 05:49:42.299
sliding up beside them.

05:49:42.360 --> 05:49:45.299
I hope so, Sonny said.

05:49:45.360 --> 05:49:47.220
But he's still really sad.

05:49:47.279 --> 05:49:49.860
He keeps mumbling in his sleep about how

05:49:49.860 --> 05:49:52.259
it's his fault the skywings found and

05:49:52.259 --> 05:49:53.639
destroyed the summer palace.

05:49:53.700 --> 05:49:56.639
Well, it is.

05:49:56.759 --> 05:49:57.720
Glory said.

05:49:57.779 --> 05:50:02.159
Oh, very sympathetic, Starflight said.

05:50:02.220 --> 05:50:03.180
Come on.

05:50:03.240 --> 05:50:05.520
Webbs didn't know crocodile was following

05:50:05.520 --> 05:50:05.880
him.

05:50:05.939 --> 05:50:07.619
Crocodile.

05:50:07.680 --> 05:50:10.619
The last dragon, Glory had used her venom

05:50:10.619 --> 05:50:11.759
on before the night kingdom.

05:50:11.819 --> 05:50:14.040
She saw a flash of the mud wings

05:50:14.040 --> 05:50:16.380
terrified face, and shoved the thought

05:50:16.380 --> 05:50:16.619
away.

05:50:16.680 --> 05:50:18.240
That was self-defense.

05:50:18.360 --> 05:50:20.580
It was always self-defense.

05:50:20.639 --> 05:50:23.159
The kind of self-defense her fellow rain

05:50:23.159 --> 05:50:24.599
wings really needed to learn.

05:50:24.659 --> 05:50:27.659
Sunny brushed Glory's shoulder with her

05:50:27.659 --> 05:50:29.459
wing, and Glory flinched back.

05:50:29.520 --> 05:50:31.740
You should put something on your

05:50:31.740 --> 05:50:33.419
scratches, Sonny said.

05:50:33.479 --> 05:50:35.819
This isn't a scratch.

05:50:35.880 --> 05:50:38.759
Gloria informed her, pointing to the

05:50:38.759 --> 05:50:41.099
bleeding slash on her back leg, which had

05:50:41.099 --> 05:50:43.139
started to throb in a fiercely painful

05:50:43.139 --> 05:50:43.439
way.

05:50:43.500 --> 05:50:45.060
It's a battle wound.

05:50:45.180 --> 05:50:49.680
Yes, you're very tough and scary, Sonny

05:50:49.680 --> 05:50:49.979
said.

05:50:50.040 --> 05:50:52.200
She beckoned to the white and blue rain

05:50:52.200 --> 05:50:54.299
wings, while Glory wondered if that was

05:50:54.299 --> 05:50:55.080
sarcasm.

05:50:55.139 --> 05:50:56.759
Sarcasm from Sonny?

05:50:56.880 --> 05:50:58.680
It didn't seem likely.

05:50:58.740 --> 05:51:01.500
She twisted to watch as the rain wing

05:51:01.500 --> 05:51:03.060
stabbed some kind of paste on her

05:51:03.060 --> 05:51:03.479
injuries.

05:51:03.540 --> 05:51:05.099
Watch it.

05:51:05.159 --> 05:51:06.599
She hissed.

05:51:06.659 --> 05:51:09.419
But after a moment, the stinging faded

05:51:09.419 --> 05:51:10.979
and all she could feel was cool

05:51:10.979 --> 05:51:11.639
numbness.

05:51:11.759 --> 05:51:14.639
Lori studied the wounds and sniffed the

05:51:14.639 --> 05:51:16.740
paste, which smelled a bit like mint.

05:51:16.799 --> 05:51:19.380
Hmm, she said finally.

05:51:19.439 --> 05:51:22.380
A dragonette named Kinkaju is on her way

05:51:22.380 --> 05:51:22.619
here.

05:51:22.680 --> 05:51:24.180
She needs some of that too.

05:51:24.240 --> 05:51:27.599
She caught Sonny's significant look and

05:51:27.599 --> 05:51:28.860
gave the healers a nod.

05:51:28.919 --> 05:51:29.880
Thanks.

05:51:29.939 --> 05:51:32.340
Where's your army?

05:51:32.400 --> 05:51:34.919
Starflight asked Glory, only a little

05:51:34.919 --> 05:51:35.700
Snidely.

05:51:35.759 --> 05:51:40.319
They're a work in progress, said Glory.

05:51:40.380 --> 05:51:43.259
Sonny leaned over Webbs, adjusting the

05:51:43.259 --> 05:51:44.459
dressing on his injury.

05:51:44.520 --> 05:51:49.319
So, by the way, Glory went on, I've

05:51:49.319 --> 05:51:50.939
decided to be queen of the rain wings.

05:51:51.000 --> 05:51:54.540
Sonny tripped, and Webbs let out an oof

05:51:54.540 --> 05:51:56.880
as she landed on him, but he didn't wake

05:51:56.880 --> 05:51:57.060
up.

05:51:57.119 --> 05:51:59.400
Starflight turned to stare at glory

05:51:59.400 --> 05:52:00.240
incredulously.

05:52:00.299 --> 05:52:02.040
But why?

05:52:02.099 --> 05:52:05.459
You've never wanted to be a queen, he

05:52:05.459 --> 05:52:05.759
said.

05:52:05.819 --> 05:52:08.580
You don't know that, said Glory.

05:52:08.639 --> 05:52:11.159
She was aware of the healers hovering

05:52:11.159 --> 05:52:13.680
just within earshot, trying to look busy

05:52:13.680 --> 05:52:15.479
but obviously eavesdropping.

05:52:15.540 --> 05:52:17.939
It just didn't come up because we were

05:52:17.939 --> 05:52:20.159
too busy hearing about how much tsunami

05:52:20.159 --> 05:52:21.000
wanted to be queen.

05:52:21.119 --> 05:52:24.659
Anyway, I have to if I want to lead them

05:52:24.659 --> 05:52:26.220
into battle against the night wings.

05:52:26.279 --> 05:52:28.200
Battle?

05:52:28.259 --> 05:52:29.939
Starflight said anxiously.

05:52:30.000 --> 05:52:33.540
I think you'll be a great queen, said

05:52:33.540 --> 05:52:35.580
Sonny, with a flutter of her golden

05:52:35.580 --> 05:52:36.000
wings.

05:52:36.060 --> 05:52:40.500
Rule. agreed the sloth, waking up and

05:52:40.500 --> 05:52:42.119
leaning around glory's neck.

05:52:42.360 --> 05:52:45.240
Maybe we don't have to fight the night

05:52:45.240 --> 05:52:45.959
wings.

05:52:46.020 --> 05:52:48.540
Starflight said, in a plaintive voice.

05:52:48.599 --> 05:52:50.400
Let me talk to them.

05:52:50.459 --> 05:52:52.979
Maybe I can find out why they've been

05:52:52.979 --> 05:52:54.540
taking rain wings in the 1st place.

05:52:54.599 --> 05:52:57.840
They still need rescuing.

05:52:57.959 --> 05:52:58.979
Glory snapped.

05:52:59.040 --> 05:53:01.799
Maybe the Nightwings will let them go

05:53:01.799 --> 05:53:03.180
Starflight said.

05:53:03.240 --> 05:53:06.659
Maybe if I explain to them, that keeping

05:53:06.659 --> 05:53:09.599
dragons tied up in caves is wrong, Glory

05:53:09.599 --> 05:53:09.900
said.

05:53:09.959 --> 05:53:10.740
Sure.

05:53:10.799 --> 05:53:12.840
That's probably never occurred to them.

05:53:12.959 --> 05:53:15.540
Or that they should have asked politely

05:53:15.540 --> 05:53:17.520
before stealing rainwing venom?

05:53:17.639 --> 05:53:21.000
And don't forget the med wings, Sonny

05:53:21.000 --> 05:53:21.240
added.

05:53:21.299 --> 05:53:23.520
Why did they kill those 2 soldiers?

05:53:23.580 --> 05:53:26.880
Glory had forgotten about the dead mud

05:53:26.880 --> 05:53:27.299
wings.

05:53:27.360 --> 05:53:30.119
If that had been the night wings too, then

05:53:30.119 --> 05:53:32.220
what on pyria were they up to?

05:53:32.279 --> 05:53:35.220
Listen, she said to Starflight.

05:53:35.279 --> 05:53:37.619
I know you don't want to meet your tribe

05:53:37.619 --> 05:53:39.659
for the 1st time on the opposite side of

05:53:39.659 --> 05:53:41.520
a battlefield, but they can't be

05:53:41.520 --> 05:53:41.880
trusted.

05:53:41.939 --> 05:53:43.919
It's not even safe for you.

05:53:43.979 --> 05:53:46.560
We have no idea whether Deathbringer was

05:53:46.560 --> 05:53:47.759
supposed to kill you as well.

05:53:47.819 --> 05:53:50.340
They would never kill me.

05:53:50.400 --> 05:53:52.139
Starflight protested.

05:53:52.200 --> 05:53:53.279
I'm one of them.

05:53:53.340 --> 05:53:56.459
Barely, said Glory.

05:53:56.520 --> 05:53:59.340
Anyway, I'd rather find out the truth

05:53:59.340 --> 05:54:01.319
with a whole lot of venomous backup

05:54:01.319 --> 05:54:02.040
wouldn't you?

05:54:02.159 --> 05:54:05.159
Starflight twisted his talons together.

05:54:05.220 --> 05:54:08.040
Glory glanced out the nearest window and

05:54:08.040 --> 05:54:10.200
saw a pair of dragons shift quickly to

05:54:10.200 --> 05:54:11.639
camouflage on the branch outside.

05:54:11.700 --> 05:54:14.459
She squinted, and thought she could see

05:54:14.459 --> 05:54:16.080
shimmers of movement on several other

05:54:16.080 --> 05:54:16.979
branches as well.

05:54:17.040 --> 05:54:19.979
Apparently, her tribe was finally

05:54:19.979 --> 05:54:21.000
interested in her.

05:54:21.060 --> 05:54:25.500
Wait, said Sonny, sitting up and flaring

05:54:25.500 --> 05:54:26.040
her wings.

05:54:26.099 --> 05:54:29.099
If you want to be queen, don't you have

05:54:29.099 --> 05:54:30.060
to kill magnificent?

05:54:30.119 --> 05:54:33.299
They have this whole no killing way of

05:54:33.299 --> 05:54:34.200
taking the throne?

05:54:34.259 --> 05:54:35.099
Glory said.

05:54:35.159 --> 05:54:36.659
They're rain wings.

05:54:36.720 --> 05:54:37.619
Of course, they do.

05:54:37.680 --> 05:54:39.060
They do?

05:54:39.119 --> 05:54:43.020
That's fantastic, Sonny said, with

05:54:43.020 --> 05:54:44.099
unexpected intensity.

05:54:44.220 --> 05:54:46.619
That's how all the tribes should do it.

05:54:46.680 --> 05:54:49.560
Maybe after we stop the war, we can teach

05:54:49.560 --> 05:54:51.720
everyone the rain wing way of changing

05:54:51.720 --> 05:54:52.259
queens.

05:54:52.319 --> 05:54:54.959
Glory gave her a quizzical look.

05:54:55.020 --> 05:54:58.020
That was a lot of enthusiasm for a rain

05:54:58.020 --> 05:54:59.220
wing way of doing things.

05:54:59.279 --> 05:55:02.279
She was pretty sure most dragons wouldn't

05:55:02.279 --> 05:55:02.700
feel that way.

05:55:02.759 --> 05:55:06.240
Why don't we take our revolution one step

05:55:06.240 --> 05:55:09.000
at a time, she said. flicking her tail at

05:55:09.000 --> 05:55:09.419
Sonny.

05:55:09.479 --> 05:55:11.340
The other tribes have been doing things

05:55:11.340 --> 05:55:12.779
their way for 100s of years.

05:55:12.840 --> 05:55:16.860
So, Sonny said, things can change.

05:55:16.979 --> 05:55:20.639
If queens didn't kill their challengers

05:55:20.639 --> 05:55:23.639
Starflight interjected, what would stop

05:55:23.639 --> 05:55:25.439
the challengers from trying again the

05:55:25.439 --> 05:55:25.919
next day?

05:55:25.919 --> 05:55:26.819
and the next?

05:55:26.939 --> 05:55:29.880
Or if the challenger won, the queen could

05:55:29.880 --> 05:55:31.439
just come try to take it back.

05:55:31.500 --> 05:55:34.439
Instead of ruling her kingdom, a queen

05:55:34.439 --> 05:55:36.360
would have to spend all her time simply

05:55:36.360 --> 05:55:37.380
trying to keep her thrown.

05:55:37.500 --> 05:55:41.759
Then we make new rules, Sonny said

05:55:41.759 --> 05:55:42.599
stubbornly.

05:55:42.659 --> 05:55:45.299
Like, she can only be challenged at

05:55:45.299 --> 05:55:47.700
certain times of the year, or each

05:55:47.700 --> 05:55:50.459
challenger can try twice before giving up

05:55:50.459 --> 05:55:51.240
or something like that.

05:55:51.299 --> 05:55:54.720
We're dragons, not caterpillars.

05:55:54.779 --> 05:55:56.639
We can do things differently if we choose

05:55:56.639 --> 05:55:56.939
to.

05:55:57.000 --> 05:56:02.279
Dragons are dragons, Sonny, Glory said.

05:56:02.340 --> 05:56:04.020
Fighting is part of our nature.

05:56:04.080 --> 05:56:08.459
Not for the rain wings, Sonny said, and

05:56:08.459 --> 05:56:09.659
their dragons too.

05:56:09.720 --> 05:56:13.380
But, but there's something wrong with

05:56:13.380 --> 05:56:13.619
them.

05:56:13.680 --> 05:56:14.880
Glory thought.

05:56:14.939 --> 05:56:17.639
She didn't want to say that out loud with

05:56:17.639 --> 05:56:19.799
a healer is listening, and however many

05:56:19.799 --> 05:56:22.560
dragons were just outside the window, but

05:56:22.560 --> 05:56:24.360
she knew Starflight must be thinking it

05:56:24.360 --> 05:56:24.720
too.

05:56:24.840 --> 05:56:28.439
Maybe rain wings are more evolved than

05:56:28.439 --> 05:56:30.180
the rest of us, Sonny said.

05:56:30.240 --> 05:56:32.939
Maybe all dragons should try to be more

05:56:32.939 --> 05:56:33.299
like them.

05:56:33.360 --> 05:56:35.520
They're happy, aren't they?

05:56:35.580 --> 05:56:38.400
True, Glory thought.

05:56:38.459 --> 05:56:40.979
But maybe I could have been happy as

05:56:40.979 --> 05:56:43.619
Queen Scarlet's prisoner, as long as I

05:56:43.619 --> 05:56:46.020
got to lie in the sun and eat pineapple

05:56:46.020 --> 05:56:46.319
all day.

05:56:46.380 --> 05:56:48.540
And then where would my friends be?

05:56:48.659 --> 05:56:52.080
I don't think it's enough to just be

05:56:52.080 --> 05:56:54.240
happy, Glory said slowly.

05:56:54.299 --> 05:56:56.639
I think you have to care about something

05:56:56.639 --> 05:56:57.060
too.

05:56:57.119 --> 05:56:59.939
Like other dragons who need you, for

05:56:59.939 --> 05:57:02.099
instance, and you still have to be ready

05:57:02.099 --> 05:57:05.459
to fight, just in case some creepy, less

05:57:05.459 --> 05:57:07.979
evolved dragons decide to invade your

05:57:07.979 --> 05:57:10.080
territory and kidnap a bunch of you.

05:57:10.139 --> 05:57:14.400
I don't believe anyone can be truly happy

05:57:14.400 --> 05:57:17.279
without scrolls, Starflight said

05:57:17.279 --> 05:57:17.819
wistfully.

05:57:17.880 --> 05:57:21.419
I haven't seen a scroll in weeks, and I'm

05:57:21.419 --> 05:57:22.619
perfectly miserable.

05:57:22.680 --> 05:57:27.299
Poor Starflight, Sonny said. with genuine

05:57:27.299 --> 05:57:30.299
sympathy, brushing his wings with hers.

05:57:30.360 --> 05:57:32.819
Well, when Gloria is queen, she can fix

05:57:32.819 --> 05:57:33.240
all that.

05:57:33.360 --> 05:57:36.540
Starflight can teach everyone to read, and

05:57:36.540 --> 05:57:38.220
tsunami can teach them to defend

05:57:38.220 --> 05:57:40.919
themselves, and will make a list of all

05:57:40.919 --> 05:57:43.439
the eggs and all the dragons in the tribe

05:57:43.439 --> 05:57:46.380
so no one will ever get lost again, plus

05:57:46.380 --> 05:57:49.500
save the missing rain wings, and choose a

05:57:49.500 --> 05:57:51.119
sand wing queen, and stop the war.

05:57:51.180 --> 05:57:52.139
Glory said.

05:57:52.200 --> 05:57:53.400
No problem.

05:57:53.459 --> 05:57:54.299
Give me a week.

05:57:54.419 --> 05:57:57.659
Sonny beamed, as if this sounded like a

05:57:57.659 --> 05:57:58.979
perfectly reasonable plan to her.

05:57:59.040 --> 05:58:03.779
When I'm queen, glory thought, I like the

05:58:03.779 --> 05:58:04.319
sound of that.

05:58:04.380 --> 05:58:07.919
Through one of the windows, Glory saw

05:58:07.919 --> 05:58:09.779
Kinkachu and Mangrove approaching.

05:58:09.840 --> 05:58:12.720
A few more curious dragons were tailing

05:58:12.720 --> 05:58:15.000
them through the trees, and Glory spotted

05:58:15.000 --> 05:58:16.560
more eyes watching from the leaves.

05:58:16.619 --> 05:58:19.560
Mangrove was an unexpected, dappled

05:58:19.560 --> 05:58:21.540
mixture of bright yellow and lime green

05:58:21.599 --> 05:58:25.080
excited and terrified, she thought.

05:58:25.139 --> 05:58:26.819
But more complicated.

05:58:26.880 --> 05:58:30.360
With the return of Kinkaju, now he knew

05:58:30.360 --> 05:58:32.939
that Orchid was alive, but he also knew

05:58:32.939 --> 05:58:35.340
what an awful place she was in and how

05:58:35.340 --> 05:58:36.479
hard it would be to get her back.

05:58:36.540 --> 05:58:39.479
Glory hoped Clay and tsunami were ready

05:58:39.479 --> 05:58:41.220
to stop him if he tried to dash through

05:58:41.220 --> 05:58:42.959
the tunnel and do any rescuing by

05:58:42.959 --> 05:58:43.380
himself.

05:58:43.439 --> 05:58:46.799
Well, before we change the fundamental

05:58:46.799 --> 05:58:49.560
essence of dragons and revamp the rain

05:58:49.560 --> 05:58:52.919
wing tribe, First, I have to win, she

05:58:52.919 --> 05:58:53.220
said.

05:58:53.279 --> 05:58:55.860
So right now, I have to go train for this

05:58:55.860 --> 05:58:56.939
contest thing tomorrow.

05:58:57.000 --> 05:58:59.279
If anyone wants to come watch while the

05:58:59.279 --> 05:59:01.139
others guard the tunnel, it's in the

05:59:01.139 --> 05:59:02.459
arboretum at sunrise.

05:59:02.580 --> 05:59:05.040
I'll be there, Sonny said.

05:59:05.099 --> 05:59:07.319
It'll be nice to know a queen we actually

05:59:07.319 --> 05:59:07.680
like.

05:59:07.740 --> 05:59:12.299
If you win, Starflight added gloomily.

05:59:12.360 --> 05:59:15.240
I will win, Glory said.

05:59:15.299 --> 05:59:18.119
Glancing again at Mangroves Scales.

05:59:18.180 --> 05:59:20.580
She thought of orchid, and the other

05:59:20.580 --> 05:59:23.939
rainforest dragons, chained and muzzled

05:59:23.939 --> 05:59:26.880
and fed rotting prey, imprisoned away

05:59:26.880 --> 05:59:28.979
from the sun and their own tribe.

05:59:29.400 --> 05:59:30.360
I have to.

05:59:30.419 --> 05:59:34.979
Chapter 27.

05:59:35.220 --> 05:59:38.520
Papaya, Glory said.

05:59:38.580 --> 05:59:44.759
Starfruit, Tangelo, Clementine, Kumbu

05:59:44.759 --> 05:59:50.400
Dragonberry, Mango, Fire Pair, and that

05:59:50.400 --> 05:59:51.900
one's a trick that only looks like a

05:59:51.900 --> 05:59:54.000
fruit, but is actually a poorly designed

05:59:54.000 --> 05:59:54.419
snail.

05:59:54.540 --> 05:59:57.779
She poked the purple snail's shell with

05:59:57.779 --> 06:00:00.180
one claw, and its nervous antennae

06:00:00.180 --> 06:00:00.659
vanished again.

06:00:00.720 --> 06:00:03.479
The sun was high above them, and the

06:00:03.479 --> 06:00:05.880
morning rain had stopped, although the

06:00:05.880 --> 06:00:08.040
leaves kept showering the dragons every

06:00:08.040 --> 06:00:09.599
time someone bounced through and shook

06:00:09.599 --> 06:00:10.020
the trees.

06:00:10.139 --> 06:00:12.840
All the toucans and parrots and

06:00:12.840 --> 06:00:15.000
lowerkeets that had disappeared during

06:00:15.000 --> 06:00:17.400
the rainfall were back, perched on the

06:00:17.400 --> 06:00:19.740
highest branches, and hollering joyfully

06:00:19.740 --> 06:00:22.020
at the sun as if they'd never expected to

06:00:22.020 --> 06:00:23.099
see it again.

06:00:23.159 --> 06:00:25.919
And now glory could identify all the

06:00:25.919 --> 06:00:28.259
birds in sight, after studying with

06:00:28.259 --> 06:00:30.180
mangrove and kinkaju all morning.

06:00:30.240 --> 06:00:34.259
Birds, insects, flowers, fruit, anything

06:00:34.259 --> 06:00:36.299
magnificent might tester on she would

06:00:36.299 --> 06:00:36.900
memorize.

06:00:36.959 --> 06:00:39.240
Whenever she felt her brain getting tired

06:00:39.240 --> 06:00:41.880
she'd think of the smoky air choking the

06:00:41.880 --> 06:00:44.459
caves of the rain wings, and that would

06:00:44.459 --> 06:00:45.959
snap her back into focus.

06:00:46.139 --> 06:00:49.139
Wow, said Kinkaju.

06:00:49.200 --> 06:00:51.599
She blinked large dark eyes at glory.

06:00:51.720 --> 06:00:54.000
How did you learn all of that so fast?

06:00:54.060 --> 06:00:57.299
You really never had any of these

06:00:57.299 --> 06:00:57.779
before?

06:00:57.840 --> 06:01:01.139
Mangrove asked, surveying the 40 or so

06:01:01.139 --> 06:01:02.700
fruits arranged around the platform.

06:01:02.759 --> 06:01:05.819
One or 2 maybe, said Glory.

06:01:05.880 --> 06:01:07.740
I should taste them all too, right?

06:01:07.799 --> 06:01:10.139
Just in case she chooses a blind taste

06:01:10.139 --> 06:01:10.439
test?

06:01:10.560 --> 06:01:13.500
I don't think anyone's ever thought of

06:01:13.500 --> 06:01:15.599
that before, said Mangrove.

06:01:15.659 --> 06:01:17.220
But you never know.

06:01:17.279 --> 06:01:20.099
He peeled the banana with a few swipes of

06:01:20.099 --> 06:01:21.419
his claws and tossed it to her.

06:01:21.479 --> 06:01:24.720
Clay would dominate a blind taste test

06:01:24.720 --> 06:01:27.000
Sonny offered, from her perch in the

06:01:27.000 --> 06:01:27.659
trees above them.

06:01:27.720 --> 06:01:30.479
Sunlight danced on her golden scales.

06:01:30.540 --> 06:01:33.119
A small orange monkey with a black face

06:01:33.119 --> 06:01:35.340
was playing with her tail, but Sonny

06:01:35.340 --> 06:01:36.900
either didn't notice or didn't mind.

06:01:36.959 --> 06:01:39.000
I would.

06:01:39.060 --> 06:01:40.560
Clay said wistfully.

06:01:40.619 --> 06:01:43.319
Are you going to eat that whole thing?

06:01:43.380 --> 06:01:46.619
Glory took another bite, and then lobbed

06:01:46.619 --> 06:01:47.639
the rest of it, Adam.

06:01:47.700 --> 06:01:49.740
Clay fumbled to catch it and ended up

06:01:49.740 --> 06:01:51.419
with bananas smeared all over his

06:01:51.419 --> 06:01:51.720
talons.

06:01:51.779 --> 06:01:54.000
He licked it off with a contented

06:01:54.000 --> 06:01:54.419
expression.

06:01:54.479 --> 06:01:58.259
You can practice your camouflage at the

06:01:58.259 --> 06:01:58.740
same time.

06:01:58.799 --> 06:02:00.240
Mangrove said.

06:02:00.299 --> 06:02:03.000
See if you can match this mango.

06:02:03.060 --> 06:02:04.919
He rolled it to her with his nose.

06:02:04.979 --> 06:02:08.159
Glory studied the outside of the mango

06:02:08.159 --> 06:02:10.680
and let her scales slowly turn a dull

06:02:10.680 --> 06:02:13.080
green with black speckles, shading to

06:02:13.080 --> 06:02:14.939
warm red around her wings and tail.

06:02:15.000 --> 06:02:18.540
So cool, said Sonny.

06:02:18.599 --> 06:02:22.380
Are you going to eat that whole thing?

06:02:22.500 --> 06:02:23.580
Clay asked.

06:02:23.639 --> 06:02:24.900
Glory laughed.

06:02:24.959 --> 06:02:25.979
Clay.

06:02:26.040 --> 06:02:26.939
Let me at least try it.

06:02:27.000 --> 06:02:30.060
She tried slicing it open as neatly as

06:02:30.060 --> 06:02:32.340
mangrove had opened the banana and made a

06:02:32.340 --> 06:02:32.880
terrific mess.

06:02:33.000 --> 06:02:36.060
Cheerful orange yellow pulp squirted all

06:02:36.060 --> 06:02:38.759
over her scales, and Silver scrambled

06:02:38.759 --> 06:02:40.139
down Glory's arm to lick it up.

06:02:40.259 --> 06:02:42.240
Stop wasting time.

06:02:42.360 --> 06:02:45.000
She scolded herself as she helped the

06:02:45.000 --> 06:02:45.779
sloth balance.

06:02:45.840 --> 06:02:48.720
The days half gone, and you still need to

06:02:48.720 --> 06:02:51.419
practice venom targeting and tree gliding

06:02:51.419 --> 06:02:52.860
and camouflage.

06:02:52.919 --> 06:02:55.619
I'm not sure this is the right time to

06:02:55.619 --> 06:02:56.459
tell you this?

06:02:56.520 --> 06:02:58.799
Sonny said, but you're being watched.

06:02:58.860 --> 06:03:01.979
Glory and Mangrove looked up sharply.

06:03:02.040 --> 06:03:04.380
She'd asked him to choose a spot where

06:03:04.380 --> 06:03:05.700
they could practice without attracting

06:03:05.700 --> 06:03:06.419
too much attention.

06:03:06.540 --> 06:03:09.419
It was unsettling to keep finding rain

06:03:09.419 --> 06:03:11.220
wing eyes on her every time she turned

06:03:11.220 --> 06:03:12.060
around.

06:03:12.119 --> 06:03:14.279
The whole tribe must know she wasn't a

06:03:14.279 --> 06:03:16.500
normal rain wing, but they didn't need to

06:03:16.500 --> 06:03:18.060
see all of her mistakes the day before

06:03:18.060 --> 06:03:19.740
she tried to become their queen.

06:03:19.799 --> 06:03:22.439
But Sonny was right, even though they

06:03:22.439 --> 06:03:23.880
were in a secluded corner of the

06:03:23.880 --> 06:03:24.180
village.

06:03:24.240 --> 06:03:26.639
Glory could see dragon heads peering

06:03:26.639 --> 06:03:28.680
around tree trunks and poking out of

06:03:28.680 --> 06:03:30.419
hammocks, staring her away.

06:03:30.479 --> 06:03:32.939
As she whipped her head around to look at

06:03:32.939 --> 06:03:35.400
them, most of them quickly changed color

06:03:35.400 --> 06:03:36.060
and disappeared.

06:03:36.180 --> 06:03:39.360
But if she'd spotted those few, she could

06:03:39.360 --> 06:03:40.860
imagine how many more might be out

06:03:40.860 --> 06:03:41.099
there.

06:03:41.159 --> 06:03:43.619
Camouflaged and curious about the

06:03:43.619 --> 06:03:44.700
challenger for the throne.

06:03:44.759 --> 06:03:49.380
Well, take me or leave me, Glory

06:03:49.380 --> 06:03:49.740
thought.

06:03:49.799 --> 06:03:53.340
I'm not a typical rain wing, but maybe

06:03:53.340 --> 06:03:54.779
that's what you need for a queen.

06:03:54.840 --> 06:03:56.759
All right.

06:03:56.819 --> 06:03:58.139
What can we do next?

06:03:58.259 --> 06:04:00.720
she asked, popping berries in her mouth.

06:04:00.779 --> 06:04:03.599
Raspberries are sharper than cloud

06:04:03.599 --> 06:04:04.139
berries.

06:04:04.200 --> 06:04:06.240
Figs taste like desert winds.

06:04:06.299 --> 06:04:09.060
Guavas are the ones I could eat every day

06:04:09.060 --> 06:04:10.139
for the rest of time.

06:04:10.200 --> 06:04:12.299
Venom practice?

06:04:12.360 --> 06:04:16.380
Next to suntime, Kingachoo said, and

06:04:16.380 --> 06:04:17.939
Mangrove nodded with a glance at the

06:04:17.939 --> 06:04:18.240
sky.

06:04:18.299 --> 06:04:19.979
Are you crazy?

06:04:20.099 --> 06:04:21.180
Glory said.

06:04:21.240 --> 06:04:23.700
She seized a papaya and accidentally

06:04:23.700 --> 06:04:25.319
crushed it between her front talons.

06:04:25.380 --> 06:04:27.599
I have one day to prepare for this.

06:04:27.659 --> 06:04:30.119
I'm not going to spend it snoozing like a

06:04:30.119 --> 06:04:30.479
slug.

06:04:30.540 --> 06:04:35.639
Sun time isn't about snoozing, Mangrove

06:04:35.639 --> 06:04:36.599
said sternly.

06:04:36.659 --> 06:04:38.459
It's about recharging.

06:04:38.580 --> 06:04:43.319
Terrible, furable, agreed Glory Sloth

06:04:43.319 --> 06:04:45.299
climbing up to tug on Glory's ears.

06:04:45.360 --> 06:04:47.400
I'd rather study.

06:04:47.459 --> 06:04:48.419
Glory said.

06:04:48.479 --> 06:04:51.240
She saw Kinkaju's crestfallen face and

06:04:51.240 --> 06:04:52.979
added, you 2 can go ahead.

06:04:53.040 --> 06:04:54.299
I'll practice on my own.

06:04:54.360 --> 06:04:58.020
You will not, said Mangrove.

06:04:58.080 --> 06:05:00.180
You need this energy to win.

06:05:00.240 --> 06:05:03.540
You will sleep if we all have to sit on

06:05:03.540 --> 06:05:04.319
you to make it happen.

06:05:04.380 --> 06:05:07.799
I volunteer, Clay said.

06:05:07.860 --> 06:05:10.319
I'm a world champion at sitting on my

06:05:10.319 --> 06:05:10.919
friends.

06:05:10.979 --> 06:05:15.299
Clay, Glory said, over Sunny's giggling

06:05:15.299 --> 06:05:16.380
this isn't a joke.

06:05:16.439 --> 06:05:18.180
I don't have time to be lazy.

06:05:18.240 --> 06:05:21.779
Glory has some issues with the word lazy

06:05:21.779 --> 06:05:23.040
Sonny announced.

06:05:23.099 --> 06:05:25.139
Our guardians used to call her that all

06:05:25.139 --> 06:05:27.479
the time, so she feels like she needs to

06:05:27.479 --> 06:05:29.340
prove something by showing she doesn't

06:05:29.340 --> 06:05:30.299
need to sleep.

06:05:30.360 --> 06:05:33.000
Glory flared her rough and glared at

06:05:33.000 --> 06:05:33.360
Sonny.

06:05:33.419 --> 06:05:36.540
Excuse me, are you explaining me?

06:05:36.599 --> 06:05:39.180
Sonny shifted her wings in a friendly

06:05:39.180 --> 06:05:39.659
shrug.

06:05:39.720 --> 06:05:42.779
Well, that's what Starflight said, she

06:05:42.779 --> 06:05:44.580
offered, but it makes sense to me.

06:05:44.639 --> 06:05:49.080
Sleeping when you need to is not lazy

06:05:49.139 --> 06:05:50.520
said Mangrove.

06:05:50.580 --> 06:05:53.459
That is a crazy dragon's way of

06:05:53.459 --> 06:05:53.759
thinking.

06:05:53.819 --> 06:05:57.060
Sleeping is as important as breathing.

06:05:57.119 --> 06:05:59.700
You wouldn't skip that because there's no

06:05:59.700 --> 06:06:00.779
time for it.

06:06:00.840 --> 06:06:03.959
Or food, Clay agreed.

06:06:04.020 --> 06:06:06.900
You can't skip sleeping or food.

06:06:06.959 --> 06:06:10.020
The mudwing dragonette hopped off his

06:06:10.020 --> 06:06:12.000
branch and thudded down next to her

06:06:12.000 --> 06:06:14.400
squashing a mango under his big claws.

06:06:14.459 --> 06:06:17.099
He crouched so his brown eyes were

06:06:17.099 --> 06:06:18.360
directly even with glories.

06:06:18.419 --> 06:06:20.759
Silver leaned over Gloria's head and

06:06:20.759 --> 06:06:21.779
tried to poke at his horns.

06:06:21.900 --> 06:06:23.340
Glory.

06:06:23.400 --> 06:06:24.299
He said.

06:06:24.419 --> 06:06:27.659
Stop panicking for one moment, and think

06:06:27.659 --> 06:06:29.099
about how you feel right now.

06:06:29.159 --> 06:06:31.560
And I don't mean mad.

06:06:31.740 --> 06:06:32.700
I mean physically.

06:06:32.759 --> 06:06:37.080
I'm not panicking, Glory said, ruffled.

06:06:37.200 --> 06:06:39.419
I am pretty close to mad though.

06:06:39.479 --> 06:06:42.000
And he prompted.

06:06:42.119 --> 06:06:45.240
And getting closer, she shot back.

06:06:45.299 --> 06:06:47.220
He gave her a patient look.

06:06:47.279 --> 06:06:49.259
And...

06:06:49.259 --> 06:06:51.000
Exhausted.

06:06:51.060 --> 06:06:53.639
Glory realized, as she took a deep

06:06:53.639 --> 06:06:54.119
breath.

06:06:54.180 --> 06:06:58.080
She hadn't really slept in a, well, in a

06:06:58.080 --> 06:07:00.119
really long time, not properly.

06:07:00.180 --> 06:07:02.520
She thought about the brush of sunlight

06:07:02.520 --> 06:07:03.180
on her scales.

06:07:03.240 --> 06:07:07.259
Fine, she snapped, but wake me up in one

06:07:07.259 --> 06:07:07.799
hour.

06:07:07.860 --> 06:07:08.759
Understand?

06:07:08.819 --> 06:07:12.419
We'll see, Clay said.

06:07:12.479 --> 06:07:15.599
Cheered the sloth.

06:07:15.659 --> 06:07:17.040
Come on.

06:07:17.099 --> 06:07:18.779
Kinkaju said excitedly.

06:07:18.840 --> 06:07:19.979
I know the best spot.

06:07:20.099 --> 06:07:24.000
As Glory, Kinkaju, and Mangrove took off

06:07:24.000 --> 06:07:25.740
there was a flurry of wing beat

06:07:25.740 --> 06:07:27.599
throughout the trees around them, as

06:07:27.599 --> 06:07:30.000
camouflaged rain wings none too subtly

06:07:30.000 --> 06:07:30.479
followed them.

06:07:30.540 --> 06:07:33.180
Kinkachu led the way to a platform that

06:07:33.180 --> 06:07:35.159
was built right above the treetops with

06:07:35.159 --> 06:07:37.740
no leaves between it and the blue arc of

06:07:37.740 --> 06:07:38.040
the sky.

06:07:38.099 --> 06:07:41.220
The surface dipped in the center. and was

06:07:41.220 --> 06:07:43.680
lined with cloud soft pink blossoms

06:07:43.680 --> 06:07:45.959
growing along the vines that were woven

06:07:45.959 --> 06:07:46.439
around the wood.

06:07:46.500 --> 06:07:49.919
You take this spot, Kinkachu said

06:07:49.919 --> 06:07:51.479
pointing to the hollow in the middle.

06:07:51.540 --> 06:07:54.240
Glory reluctantly curled up in the vines

06:07:54.240 --> 06:07:56.819
and immediately felt warmth soaking into

06:07:56.819 --> 06:07:57.299
her bones.

06:07:57.360 --> 06:08:00.119
Silver flopped happily into a spot on

06:08:00.119 --> 06:08:01.740
Glory's shoulder and snuggled in.

06:08:01.799 --> 06:08:05.099
Glory jumped, as Kinkaju nestled on one

06:08:05.099 --> 06:08:07.680
side of her, and Mangrove settled on the

06:08:07.680 --> 06:08:07.860
other.

06:08:07.919 --> 06:08:09.900
That answered that question.

06:08:09.959 --> 06:08:12.720
Other rain wings didn't mind touching one

06:08:12.720 --> 06:08:13.020
another.

06:08:13.080 --> 06:08:15.720
So it was just her who had a problem with

06:08:15.720 --> 06:08:15.900
it.

06:08:15.959 --> 06:08:20.459
Um, she started to say, but the 2 rain

06:08:20.459 --> 06:08:22.139
wings were already breathing deeply.

06:08:22.200 --> 06:08:25.439
Glory closed her eyes, certain she'd

06:08:25.439 --> 06:08:26.580
never fall asleep like this.

06:08:26.639 --> 06:08:30.180
A moment later, she opened them, and

06:08:30.180 --> 06:08:32.220
found herself looking into the amber eyes

06:08:32.220 --> 06:08:33.779
of Queen Scarlet.

06:08:33.840 --> 06:08:38.340
Chapter 28.

06:08:38.580 --> 06:08:42.479
Glory leaped back with a hiss and opened

06:08:42.479 --> 06:08:42.900
her mouth.

06:08:42.959 --> 06:08:46.680
Don't you dare, snarled the queen.

06:08:46.740 --> 06:08:48.659
Haven't you done enough already?

06:08:48.720 --> 06:08:52.500
Glory paused, studying the Skywing's

06:08:52.500 --> 06:08:52.740
face.

06:08:52.799 --> 06:08:55.979
It was perfect, as perfect as it had ever

06:08:55.979 --> 06:08:56.279
been.

06:08:56.340 --> 06:08:59.220
A shimmering orange like the orchid

06:08:59.220 --> 06:09:01.500
growing from the moss behind her, with

06:09:01.500 --> 06:09:02.939
the small rubies above her eyes

06:09:02.939 --> 06:09:05.340
glittering in the bright sunlight.

06:09:05.400 --> 06:09:08.400
And then Scarlet's whole body flickered

06:09:08.400 --> 06:09:09.180
somehow.

06:09:09.240 --> 06:09:12.599
And under the perfect scales, Glory saw

06:09:12.599 --> 06:09:15.180
something dark and melted, a horrible

06:09:15.180 --> 06:09:17.279
smeared mess where a face used to be.

06:09:17.340 --> 06:09:19.200
Behind Scarlet.

06:09:19.259 --> 06:09:21.900
She caught a glimpse of a dim room with

06:09:21.900 --> 06:09:23.700
glass jars hanging from the ceiling.

06:09:23.759 --> 06:09:25.740
Some of them glowing strangely.

06:09:25.860 --> 06:09:27.540
Oh.

06:09:27.599 --> 06:09:31.259
You're not really here, Glory said, as

06:09:31.259 --> 06:09:34.020
the rainforest reappeared, and Scarlet's

06:09:34.020 --> 06:09:35.880
scales smoothed back to perfect.

06:09:36.060 --> 06:09:38.040
The queen was perched on the edge of

06:09:38.040 --> 06:09:40.500
Glory's sleeping platform, but now that

06:09:40.500 --> 06:09:42.599
Glory looked closely, she could see that

06:09:42.599 --> 06:09:44.639
the sky wings claws didn't sink into the

06:09:44.639 --> 06:09:45.240
leaves below her.

06:09:45.299 --> 06:09:48.659
Glory sat down and curled her tail around

06:09:48.659 --> 06:09:49.319
her talons.

06:09:49.380 --> 06:09:52.500
Kinkachu and mangrove were fast asleep on

06:09:52.500 --> 06:09:53.400
either side of her.

06:09:53.459 --> 06:09:56.459
The sloth was snoring on her shoulder, and

06:09:56.459 --> 06:09:58.020
the sun had climbed higher in the sky.

06:09:58.080 --> 06:10:00.659
Am I even awake?

06:10:00.720 --> 06:10:01.919
Glory asked.

06:10:01.979 --> 06:10:04.799
No, said Scarlet.

06:10:04.860 --> 06:10:07.080
I've been trying to catch you asleep for

06:10:07.080 --> 06:10:07.319
days.

06:10:07.380 --> 06:10:10.919
She held up a small star shaped sapphire

06:10:10.919 --> 06:10:13.080
that glowed an eerie blue light through

06:10:13.080 --> 06:10:13.680
her claws.

06:10:13.799 --> 06:10:16.860
Once I realized what this was.

06:10:16.919 --> 06:10:22.080
A dream visitor, Glory said, recognizing

06:10:22.080 --> 06:10:23.279
the shape from her scrolls.

06:10:23.340 --> 06:10:25.979
I read about those.

06:10:26.040 --> 06:10:28.259
An animus dragon made 3 of them 100s of

06:10:28.259 --> 06:10:28.919
years ago, right?

06:10:28.979 --> 06:10:31.799
I thought the last one in existence was

06:10:31.799 --> 06:10:34.139
lost with the sandwing treasure, when the

06:10:34.139 --> 06:10:36.240
scavenger killed Queen Oasis and stole it

06:10:36.240 --> 06:10:36.479
all.

06:10:36.599 --> 06:10:41.400
Apparently not, Scarlett said. opening

06:10:41.400 --> 06:10:42.959
her claws to glance down at it.

06:10:43.020 --> 06:10:46.799
So you're really alive, Glory said.

06:10:46.919 --> 06:10:49.799
You don't sound as disappointed as I

06:10:49.799 --> 06:10:51.959
thought you would be, Scarlett said.

06:10:52.020 --> 06:10:53.939
Glory flicked her tail.

06:10:54.000 --> 06:10:56.220
It's not that I want you dead.

06:10:56.279 --> 06:10:58.380
I just want you not trying to kill us.

06:10:58.439 --> 06:11:03.060
I never tried to kill you, Scarlett

06:11:03.060 --> 06:11:03.540
pointed out.

06:11:03.599 --> 06:11:05.279
I quite liked you.

06:11:05.340 --> 06:11:07.919
We could have had a thrilling time

06:11:07.919 --> 06:11:08.400
together.

06:11:08.459 --> 06:11:12.240
She stood up and paced toward glory until

06:11:12.240 --> 06:11:14.340
their snouts were almost nose to nose.

06:11:14.400 --> 06:11:18.119
Which reminds me, I wanted to try

06:11:18.119 --> 06:11:18.659
something.

06:11:18.779 --> 06:11:22.139
Abruptly, she lashed out with her free

06:11:22.139 --> 06:11:25.319
talent, slashing at glory's face, her

06:11:25.319 --> 06:11:27.840
claws sliced right through glory's scales

06:11:27.840 --> 06:11:30.959
like raindrops splashing icy water over

06:11:30.959 --> 06:11:31.319
her.

06:11:31.380 --> 06:11:34.020
It was cold, but it didn't hurt.

06:11:34.080 --> 06:11:36.599
Scarlet's claws weren't really there.

06:11:36.659 --> 06:11:39.779
Glory fixed that thought in her head as

06:11:39.779 --> 06:11:40.919
Scarlet lunged again.

06:11:40.979 --> 06:11:43.919
She closed her eyes and sat perfectly

06:11:43.919 --> 06:11:44.159
still.

06:11:44.220 --> 06:11:47.400
There was nothing the Skywing queen could

06:11:47.400 --> 06:11:48.060
do to her right now.

06:11:48.119 --> 06:11:50.580
She was no more dangerous than any

06:11:50.580 --> 06:11:50.819
dream.

06:11:50.880 --> 06:11:52.860
After a few moments.

06:11:52.919 --> 06:11:55.979
Glory opened her eyes again, and Scarlet

06:11:55.979 --> 06:11:57.540
stepped back, hissing.

06:11:57.599 --> 06:12:00.959
Smoke rose up from her nose, winding

06:12:00.959 --> 06:12:03.599
around her horns, and the dark, misshapen

06:12:03.599 --> 06:12:05.580
snout underneath flickered through again

06:12:05.580 --> 06:12:07.380
for a moment, along with the room

06:12:07.380 --> 06:12:07.740
beyond.

06:12:07.799 --> 06:12:09.959
Where are you?

06:12:10.080 --> 06:12:11.040
Glory asked.

06:12:11.099 --> 06:12:13.020
If I tell you.

06:12:13.080 --> 06:12:15.119
Will you find me and free me?

06:12:15.180 --> 06:12:16.380
Scarlett asked.

06:12:16.439 --> 06:12:19.200
Not likely, Glory said.

06:12:19.259 --> 06:12:21.180
Wait, let me think.

06:12:21.299 --> 06:12:24.540
Absolutely, definitely not.

06:12:24.599 --> 06:12:29.520
But you owe me, Scarlett said, stamping

06:12:29.520 --> 06:12:29.939
one foot.

06:12:30.000 --> 06:12:32.700
Glory tilted her head sideways.

06:12:32.759 --> 06:12:35.639
How exactly do you figure that?

06:12:35.700 --> 06:12:38.220
For what you did to me.

06:12:38.279 --> 06:12:40.259
Scarlet seethed.

06:12:40.319 --> 06:12:42.000
I was beautiful before.

06:12:42.119 --> 06:12:43.919
I had everything.

06:12:43.979 --> 06:12:47.340
Including a pretty rainbow dragon on a

06:12:47.340 --> 06:12:47.520
tree.

06:12:47.639 --> 06:12:48.840
Glory said.

06:12:48.959 --> 06:12:50.099
I remember.

06:12:50.159 --> 06:12:55.080
If you don't free me, Scarlett said, I

06:12:55.080 --> 06:12:57.479
will find a way out of here myself, and

06:12:57.479 --> 06:13:00.000
then when I find you, I will kill you.

06:13:00.119 --> 06:13:02.220
You know?

06:13:02.340 --> 06:13:04.799
Something tells me that's on your agenda

06:13:04.799 --> 06:13:06.720
either way, Glory said.

06:13:06.779 --> 06:13:09.900
Scarlet hissed deep in her throat, and

06:13:09.900 --> 06:13:12.000
then shot a blast of flame at glory's

06:13:12.000 --> 06:13:12.299
face.

06:13:12.360 --> 06:13:14.340
Calm and blue.

06:13:14.400 --> 06:13:15.599
Glory thought.

06:13:15.659 --> 06:13:17.759
Stay calm and blue.

06:13:17.819 --> 06:13:20.639
Is someone keeping you prisoner?

06:13:20.700 --> 06:13:21.779
Glory asked.

06:13:21.840 --> 06:13:23.340
A thought occurred to her.

06:13:23.400 --> 06:13:25.200
Is it the night wings?

06:13:25.259 --> 06:13:29.220
If you're not going to help me, Scarlett

06:13:29.220 --> 06:13:29.700
growled.

06:13:29.759 --> 06:13:31.979
I'll find someone else who will.

06:13:32.099 --> 06:13:35.700
And suddenly she was gone, leaving only a

06:13:35.700 --> 06:13:36.900
curl of smoke in the air.

06:13:36.959 --> 06:13:39.360
So there's my answer.

06:13:39.419 --> 06:13:41.819
Scarlet is alive.

06:13:41.880 --> 06:13:45.360
Glory noticed that the leaves below her

06:13:45.360 --> 06:13:45.959
were shaking.

06:13:46.020 --> 06:13:47.939
Oh, wait.

06:13:48.000 --> 06:13:49.500
That's me.

06:13:49.560 --> 06:13:53.580
Kinkaju stirred, as if she felt glory

06:13:53.580 --> 06:13:54.119
shaking too.

06:13:54.180 --> 06:13:57.659
She nestled closer, and glory felt sun

06:13:57.659 --> 06:13:59.400
drenched warmth along her scales.

06:13:59.459 --> 06:14:03.000
Slowly she closed her eyes, breathing

06:14:03.000 --> 06:14:05.279
deeply, and drifted out of the dream.

06:14:05.340 --> 06:14:09.900
When she woke up, she knew right away it

06:14:09.900 --> 06:14:11.159
had been longer than an hour.

06:14:11.220 --> 06:14:13.680
Silver was crouched in front of her

06:14:13.680 --> 06:14:15.840
stroking Glory's nose with a worried

06:14:15.840 --> 06:14:16.439
expression.

06:14:16.500 --> 06:14:19.020
The other 2 were awake, and stretching

06:14:19.020 --> 06:14:19.740
contentedly.

06:14:19.799 --> 06:14:21.659
Don't you feel better?

06:14:21.720 --> 06:14:23.099
Kinkaju asked.

06:14:23.159 --> 06:14:26.159
Yes, Glory admitted.

06:14:26.220 --> 06:14:27.900
And no.

06:14:27.959 --> 06:14:30.419
Then let's do tree gliding next.

06:14:30.479 --> 06:14:32.279
Kinkaju said cheerfully.

06:14:32.340 --> 06:14:36.599
Fine by me, said Mangrove, and Glory

06:14:36.599 --> 06:14:37.080
nodded.

06:14:37.139 --> 06:14:39.000
She was too shaken to argue.

06:14:39.060 --> 06:14:41.400
She wondered what Scarlet would think of

06:14:41.400 --> 06:14:43.439
glory becoming queen of the rain wings.

06:14:43.500 --> 06:14:45.900
She wondered if being a queen would make

06:14:45.900 --> 06:14:46.680
her any safer.

06:14:46.740 --> 06:14:49.500
Sonny and Clay waved from their branch

06:14:49.500 --> 06:14:50.040
down below.

06:14:50.099 --> 06:14:51.840
Should I tell them?

06:14:51.900 --> 06:14:53.400
I should tell them.

06:14:53.459 --> 06:14:56.220
I will tell them, but not yet.

06:14:56.279 --> 06:15:00.360
Glory wanted to talk to Starflight 1st to

06:15:00.360 --> 06:15:01.860
see what he could remember about dream

06:15:01.860 --> 06:15:04.080
visitors, and if he could guess anything

06:15:04.080 --> 06:15:05.939
about the room she'd seen behind

06:15:05.939 --> 06:15:06.720
Scarlet.

06:15:06.779 --> 06:15:09.479
His giant brain was what she needed for a

06:15:09.479 --> 06:15:10.259
puzzle like this.

06:15:10.319 --> 06:15:13.560
As glory lifted into the sky, setting off

06:15:13.560 --> 06:15:14.880
a commotion of hidden wings.

06:15:14.939 --> 06:15:17.819
She wondered where the sky wing queen was

06:15:17.819 --> 06:15:19.619
and when she would see her again.

06:15:19.680 --> 06:15:24.240
Chapter 29.

06:15:24.479 --> 06:15:28.500
The arboretum, it turned out, was the

06:15:28.500 --> 06:15:29.939
heart of the rain wing village.

06:15:30.000 --> 06:15:32.340
Vines and branches were woven tightly

06:15:32.340 --> 06:15:34.860
together to form a wide field high above

06:15:34.860 --> 06:15:37.319
the ground, open to the sky, and

06:15:37.319 --> 06:15:40.020
surrounded by tree houses, walkways, and

06:15:40.020 --> 06:15:40.860
hammocks.

06:15:40.919 --> 06:15:42.779
Several of the tree houses around the

06:15:42.779 --> 06:15:45.119
edge appeared to be set up for trading

06:15:45.119 --> 06:15:48.060
fruits and flower garlands, brilliant

06:15:48.060 --> 06:15:50.880
blue and coppery orange birds, darted

06:15:50.880 --> 06:15:52.860
through the leaves, chattering, and

06:15:52.860 --> 06:15:54.900
calling to one another, like an audience

06:15:54.900 --> 06:15:56.279
gathering for a performance.

06:15:56.340 --> 06:15:58.380
There seemed to be room for the entire

06:15:58.380 --> 06:16:00.360
village to gather around the edges of the

06:16:00.360 --> 06:16:02.759
circle, and it looked like the entire

06:16:02.759 --> 06:16:04.080
village had shown up.

06:16:04.139 --> 06:16:06.840
The rumble of dragon voices mixed with

06:16:06.840 --> 06:16:08.759
the chirruping of sloths, and sent

06:16:08.759 --> 06:16:10.740
shivers through the wooden walkway where

06:16:10.740 --> 06:16:13.380
Glory stood, studying the green stadium

06:16:13.380 --> 06:16:13.919
in front of her.

06:16:13.979 --> 06:16:18.000
Glory was reminded, uncomfortably, of the

06:16:18.000 --> 06:16:20.159
Sky Wing Arena, where her friends had

06:16:20.159 --> 06:16:23.099
battled for Queen Scarlet's amusement.

06:16:23.159 --> 06:16:24.900
From the way Tsunami's tail was twitching

06:16:24.900 --> 06:16:27.000
Glory guessed she felt the same way.

06:16:27.060 --> 06:16:29.220
This is unfair.

06:16:29.340 --> 06:16:30.840
Tsunami grumbled.

06:16:30.900 --> 06:16:33.959
If you win, you'll have to call me your

06:16:33.959 --> 06:16:36.419
majesty, Glory said, grinning.

06:16:36.479 --> 06:16:37.500
I know.

06:16:37.560 --> 06:16:39.000
Won't that be hilarious?

06:16:39.119 --> 06:16:42.959
And your face will look like that all the

06:16:42.959 --> 06:16:44.819
time, tsunami said.

06:16:44.880 --> 06:16:47.040
It's going to be so hard not to bite

06:16:47.040 --> 06:16:47.220
you.

06:16:47.279 --> 06:16:50.759
But if you do, my guards will throw you

06:16:50.759 --> 06:16:53.580
in my dungeons, Glory said, with an

06:16:53.580 --> 06:16:54.900
imperious wave of her talons.

06:16:54.959 --> 06:16:57.659
Rain wings don't have dungeons.

06:16:57.720 --> 06:16:59.159
Kinkaju pointed out.

06:16:59.220 --> 06:17:01.500
There's a surprise.

06:17:01.560 --> 06:17:04.200
Well, I'll make one, just for tsunami

06:17:04.200 --> 06:17:05.340
Glory said.

06:17:05.400 --> 06:17:07.979
Maybe I should have let Starfly come to

06:17:07.979 --> 06:17:09.900
this instead, tsunami said.

06:17:09.959 --> 06:17:12.119
Postpone my agony a little bit.

06:17:12.180 --> 06:17:15.060
Starflight and Clay were taking a shift

06:17:15.060 --> 06:17:16.680
watching the Nightwing Tunnel.

06:17:16.919 --> 06:17:18.779
They'd seen nothing come out of it yet

06:17:18.779 --> 06:17:20.880
not so much as a puff of smoke.

06:17:20.939 --> 06:17:24.240
Glory found that both alarming and

06:17:24.240 --> 06:17:24.959
reassuring.

06:17:25.020 --> 06:17:27.240
Maybe the night wings were afraid to

06:17:27.240 --> 06:17:28.319
fight rain wings.

06:17:28.439 --> 06:17:29.819
That would make attacking them a bit

06:17:29.819 --> 06:17:30.060
easier.

06:17:30.119 --> 06:17:32.639
She hadn't had a chance to talk to

06:17:32.639 --> 06:17:33.419
Starflight yet.

06:17:33.479 --> 06:17:36.060
He'd stayed out by the tunnel all night.

06:17:36.119 --> 06:17:38.580
I'll talk to him right after the contest

06:17:38.580 --> 06:17:39.419
she thought.

06:17:39.540 --> 06:17:42.540
Telling him about Queen Scarlet ought to

06:17:42.540 --> 06:17:44.340
distract him from fretting about fighting

06:17:44.340 --> 06:17:44.939
night wings.

06:17:45.000 --> 06:17:48.299
And I cannot think about Queen Scarlet

06:17:48.299 --> 06:17:48.599
right now.

06:17:48.659 --> 06:17:52.619
I could have watched the tunnel, Sonny

06:17:52.619 --> 06:17:52.919
said.

06:17:52.979 --> 06:17:55.500
I don't understand why no one will let me

06:17:55.500 --> 06:17:56.400
take a turn on guard.

06:17:56.459 --> 06:18:00.299
Well, for one thing, I need you here to

06:18:00.299 --> 06:18:03.180
cheer me on, Glory said, who could do

06:18:03.180 --> 06:18:03.720
that better than you?

06:18:03.779 --> 06:18:07.619
I think I'm being patronized, Sonny

06:18:07.619 --> 06:18:07.860
said.

06:18:07.919 --> 06:18:10.139
She poked at the wooden platform below

06:18:10.139 --> 06:18:11.700
them with a harmless point of her tail.

06:18:11.819 --> 06:18:13.979
But I'll cheer for you anyway.

06:18:14.040 --> 06:18:15.840
You're definitely going to win.

06:18:15.900 --> 06:18:17.099
I'm not worried.

06:18:17.159 --> 06:18:19.740
Glory was a little worried.

06:18:19.799 --> 06:18:22.439
For one thing, her opponent had

06:18:22.439 --> 06:18:24.000
apparently multiplied overnight.

06:18:24.060 --> 06:18:27.240
Queen Magnificent was waiting in the

06:18:27.240 --> 06:18:28.319
center of the canopy.

06:18:28.380 --> 06:18:31.500
Her scales were resplendently purple, with

06:18:31.500 --> 06:18:33.900
scalloped gold edging on each individual

06:18:33.900 --> 06:18:36.540
scale, which was a color trick Glory had

06:18:36.540 --> 06:18:37.500
never tried.

06:18:37.560 --> 06:18:39.360
She had taken off most of her flower

06:18:39.360 --> 06:18:39.959
necklaces.

06:18:40.020 --> 06:18:43.080
Replacing them with one small wreath of

06:18:43.080 --> 06:18:45.299
lilies on her ruff, which had the effect

06:18:45.299 --> 06:18:47.159
of looking like a lacy white crown.

06:18:47.220 --> 06:18:50.759
Arrayed behind her were 4 more rain wings

06:18:50.759 --> 06:18:53.880
all quite large, quite beautiful, and

06:18:53.880 --> 06:18:56.220
quite outraged, judging from their

06:18:56.220 --> 06:18:57.360
expressions and coloring.

06:18:57.419 --> 06:18:59.159
Who are they?

06:18:59.220 --> 06:19:01.319
Glory asked Kinkaju.

06:19:01.380 --> 06:19:04.799
The other queens, Kingajoo whispered.

06:19:04.860 --> 06:19:07.979
I mean, you know, the ones who take turns

06:19:07.979 --> 06:19:08.580
being queen.

06:19:08.639 --> 06:19:10.740
I guess they don't particularly want you

06:19:10.740 --> 06:19:12.119
to take their job either.

06:19:12.180 --> 06:19:15.540
Are any of them better than magnificent?

06:19:15.599 --> 06:19:16.740
Glory asked.

06:19:16.799 --> 06:19:18.840
Maybe there was another option.

06:19:18.900 --> 06:19:20.580
It didn't have to be her.

06:19:20.580 --> 06:19:22.979
As long as the rain wings had a queen who

06:19:22.979 --> 06:19:23.759
would take care of them.

06:19:23.819 --> 06:19:25.979
But Kinkaju was shaking her head.

06:19:26.040 --> 06:19:29.040
They're all pretty much the same, she

06:19:29.040 --> 06:19:29.340
said.

06:19:29.400 --> 06:19:32.099
She pointed to one of the queens, who

06:19:32.099 --> 06:19:33.959
looked like she'd eaten a few too many

06:19:33.959 --> 06:19:36.180
avocados and papayas during her reign.

06:19:36.299 --> 06:19:38.400
That one's dazzling.

06:19:38.459 --> 06:19:40.979
She'll grant anyone anything they ask if

06:19:40.979 --> 06:19:42.060
they bring her enough tribute.

06:19:42.119 --> 06:19:44.639
She has the throne before magnificent.

06:19:44.700 --> 06:19:47.340
After magnificent, it passes to

06:19:47.340 --> 06:19:47.759
grandeur.

06:19:47.819 --> 06:19:51.540
Grandeur was a stately older dragon with

06:19:51.540 --> 06:19:54.299
half asleep eyes and a sour expression.

06:19:54.360 --> 06:19:56.939
Her ruff was indignantly pale orange at

06:19:56.939 --> 06:19:58.919
the moment, but the rest of her scales

06:19:58.919 --> 06:20:01.139
were pale lavender, and seemed to glitter

06:20:01.139 --> 06:20:02.400
with tiny dewdrops.

06:20:02.459 --> 06:20:05.279
During her reign, Kinkachu said.

06:20:05.340 --> 06:20:07.439
She'll only see petitioners once a week

06:20:07.439 --> 06:20:08.279
for an hour.

06:20:08.340 --> 06:20:11.400
First come, 1st served, and if you don't

06:20:11.400 --> 06:20:13.080
get in during that hour, you have to wait

06:20:13.080 --> 06:20:13.860
until the next week.

06:20:13.919 --> 06:20:16.439
The lines practically stretch around the

06:20:16.439 --> 06:20:17.340
jungle.

06:20:17.400 --> 06:20:19.200
And then she says no to pretty much

06:20:19.200 --> 06:20:19.680
everything.

06:20:19.740 --> 06:20:22.439
She's really, really old.

06:20:22.500 --> 06:20:25.139
She's been one of the queens for as long

06:20:25.139 --> 06:20:26.099
as anyone can remember.

06:20:26.220 --> 06:20:29.880
Kingaju pointed to the next dragon, who

06:20:29.880 --> 06:20:32.819
had 2 sloths flopped on her back, and one

06:20:32.819 --> 06:20:34.200
more perched in the curve of her tail.

06:20:34.259 --> 06:20:37.319
This queen had scales the same silvery

06:20:37.319 --> 06:20:40.080
color as the sloths, with a soft shimmer

06:20:40.080 --> 06:20:42.360
to them that looked like wind brushing

06:20:42.360 --> 06:20:42.840
through fur.

06:20:42.900 --> 06:20:46.619
That's exquisite, said Kinkaju.

06:20:46.680 --> 06:20:48.659
Obsessed with sloths.

06:20:48.720 --> 06:20:50.700
She has about 20 more at home.

06:20:50.759 --> 06:20:53.639
Talks about them constantly, feeds them

06:20:53.639 --> 06:20:56.159
the best fruits, grooms them with their

06:20:56.159 --> 06:20:56.880
own claws.

06:20:57.000 --> 06:20:59.400
And whenever she's queen, she has

06:20:59.400 --> 06:21:01.380
everyone build tiny hammocks for the

06:21:01.380 --> 06:21:03.900
sloths to sleep in, and weave them tiny

06:21:03.900 --> 06:21:04.740
flower necklaces.

06:21:04.799 --> 06:21:07.380
No dragon is as important to her as those

06:21:07.380 --> 06:21:07.799
sloths.

06:21:07.919 --> 06:21:12.540
Dazzling, grandeur, exquisite.

06:21:12.599 --> 06:21:13.979
Glory muttered.

06:21:14.040 --> 06:21:16.619
Adding those to the list of things she'd

06:21:16.619 --> 06:21:17.819
memorized in the last day.

06:21:17.939 --> 06:21:19.799
And the last one?

06:21:19.860 --> 06:21:21.000
Let me guess.

06:21:21.060 --> 06:21:24.419
Splendiferous, astonishing, too beautiful

06:21:24.419 --> 06:21:26.040
for dragon eyes to bear?

06:21:26.040 --> 06:21:29.340
That's Fruit Bat, said Kinkaju.

06:21:29.400 --> 06:21:31.919
All right, said Glory.

06:21:31.979 --> 06:21:33.119
Didn't see that coming.

06:21:33.180 --> 06:21:35.700
Who picks the names for newly hatched

06:21:35.700 --> 06:21:37.979
dragonettes if no one has any parents

06:21:37.979 --> 06:21:38.220
here?

06:21:38.279 --> 06:21:40.680
There's a list we cycle through.

06:21:40.740 --> 06:21:42.299
Kingachu said.

06:21:42.360 --> 06:21:44.580
Usually the ones with shiny names are

06:21:44.580 --> 06:21:45.900
more likely to want to be queen.

06:21:45.959 --> 06:21:47.819
Fruit bat is an exception.

06:21:47.880 --> 06:21:50.279
She's working on this experiment to see

06:21:50.279 --> 06:21:52.080
if she can take this sense out of flowers

06:21:52.080 --> 06:21:54.599
and make herself smell like them all the

06:21:54.599 --> 06:21:54.900
time.

06:21:54.959 --> 06:21:57.479
Glory wrinkled her nose.

06:21:57.599 --> 06:22:01.020
Weird, but interesting at least.

06:22:01.080 --> 06:22:02.580
What in the world does that have to do

06:22:02.580 --> 06:22:03.299
with being queen?

06:22:03.360 --> 06:22:05.520
Kinkaju shrugged.

06:22:05.580 --> 06:22:06.840
It's not going very well.

06:22:06.900 --> 06:22:08.819
She's been working on it for something

06:22:08.819 --> 06:22:09.720
like 30 years.

06:22:09.779 --> 06:22:12.900
She started taking a turn as queen so

06:22:12.900 --> 06:22:14.520
that she could have access to the Royal

06:22:14.520 --> 06:22:16.979
Gardens, and by the end of her month, the

06:22:16.979 --> 06:22:18.240
gardens are always a wreck.

06:22:18.299 --> 06:22:21.060
My friend Tamarin is one of the flower

06:22:21.060 --> 06:22:23.340
caretakers, and it drives her crazy.

06:22:23.400 --> 06:22:26.639
Sounds like magnificent might be the best

06:22:26.639 --> 06:22:27.299
of all of them.

06:22:27.360 --> 06:22:30.360
Glory said, twisting one claw through a

06:22:30.360 --> 06:22:30.900
hole in the wood.

06:22:31.020 --> 06:22:34.259
Magnificent's main problem is that she's

06:22:34.259 --> 06:22:34.740
forgetful.

06:22:34.860 --> 06:22:36.540
Kinkachu pointed out.

06:22:36.599 --> 06:22:38.819
She can never remember what she's agreed

06:22:38.819 --> 06:22:41.520
to do, or what's going on in the tribe, or

06:22:41.520 --> 06:22:43.919
who asked her for what, and she doesn't

06:22:43.919 --> 06:22:44.220
really care.

06:22:44.279 --> 06:22:47.099
We're all pretty used to it by now.

06:22:47.159 --> 06:22:49.740
She turned her dark, shining eyes to

06:22:49.740 --> 06:22:50.099
glory.

06:22:50.159 --> 06:22:53.159
But if we had you as our queen instead

06:22:53.159 --> 06:22:55.319
then everything would be different.

06:22:55.380 --> 06:22:58.979
I hope so, Glory thought.

06:22:59.040 --> 06:23:01.080
I hope different in a good way.

06:23:01.139 --> 06:23:03.299
But what if I'm no better than they are?

06:23:03.360 --> 06:23:06.900
She glanced across at Fruit Bat, who had

06:23:06.900 --> 06:23:08.880
her nose buried in a massive orchid

06:23:08.880 --> 06:23:10.319
necklace hung around her neck.

06:23:10.380 --> 06:23:13.740
All right, I'm pretty sure I'll be better

06:23:13.740 --> 06:23:14.459
than some of them.

06:23:14.580 --> 06:23:17.340
The old dragon who had been in the

06:23:17.340 --> 06:23:19.560
Queen's tree house slithered out to stand

06:23:19.560 --> 06:23:20.700
next to magnificent.

06:23:20.759 --> 06:23:23.099
He squinted around and beckoned to

06:23:23.099 --> 06:23:23.400
glory.

06:23:23.520 --> 06:23:25.319
Wish me luck.

06:23:25.380 --> 06:23:27.900
Glory muttered, handing her sloth to

06:23:27.900 --> 06:23:28.319
Sonny.

06:23:28.380 --> 06:23:31.439
Silver burbled something anxious sounding

06:23:31.439 --> 06:23:34.080
and clambered immediately up onto Sonny's

06:23:34.080 --> 06:23:34.680
head for the best view.

06:23:34.799 --> 06:23:38.099
Magnificent, flattened her ruff, and

06:23:38.099 --> 06:23:40.259
looked down her nose as Glory landed in

06:23:40.259 --> 06:23:40.860
front of her.

06:23:40.919 --> 06:23:43.380
The other 4 queens lashed their tails.

06:23:43.439 --> 06:23:45.840
So what's the plan?

06:23:45.959 --> 06:23:48.419
Glory said, shaking out her wings.

06:23:48.479 --> 06:23:50.279
I have to defeat all 5 of you.

06:23:50.340 --> 06:23:53.759
She'd chosen a summary gold color for her

06:23:53.759 --> 06:23:56.400
scales that matched the dragonflies

06:23:56.400 --> 06:23:57.659
darting through the treetops.

06:23:57.720 --> 06:24:00.299
She was determined to stay that color

06:24:00.299 --> 06:24:02.459
throughout the contest, no matter what

06:24:02.459 --> 06:24:03.900
magnificent through adder.

06:24:03.959 --> 06:24:05.340
Glory's 1st goal?

06:24:05.400 --> 06:24:08.459
Don't let anyone see that you're upset or

06:24:08.459 --> 06:24:11.220
angry, or worst of all, scared.

06:24:11.279 --> 06:24:13.259
No.

06:24:13.319 --> 06:24:16.439
Handsome interjected. before magnificent

06:24:16.439 --> 06:24:16.860
could answer.

06:24:16.919 --> 06:24:19.259
That is not the tradition.

06:24:19.319 --> 06:24:22.319
The challenger competes only against the

06:24:22.319 --> 06:24:23.220
current queen.

06:24:23.279 --> 06:24:27.299
But my fellow royalty didn't want to be

06:24:27.299 --> 06:24:30.419
left out, said Magnificent, so I worked

06:24:30.419 --> 06:24:31.380
them into the competition.

06:24:31.439 --> 06:24:34.500
She smiled in a way that made glory want

06:24:34.500 --> 06:24:36.900
to strangle her with a hammock, which

06:24:36.900 --> 06:24:38.220
means you're going to need a team as

06:24:38.220 --> 06:24:38.520
well.

06:24:38.580 --> 06:24:40.740
I don't have a team.

06:24:40.799 --> 06:24:43.680
Glory started, and then stopped herself.

06:24:43.740 --> 06:24:45.240
Well?

06:24:45.360 --> 06:24:47.040
I kind of do.

06:24:47.159 --> 06:24:50.220
She turned and glanced back at Sunny and

06:24:50.220 --> 06:24:52.139
Tsunami, who were watching with round

06:24:52.139 --> 06:24:53.819
eyes from the platform.

06:24:53.880 --> 06:24:56.220
I don't need to drag the others into

06:24:56.220 --> 06:24:56.459
this.

06:24:56.580 --> 06:24:59.279
Surely I can defeat the queens myself.

06:24:59.340 --> 06:25:02.459
What can 5 rain wings do that I can't?

06:25:02.580 --> 06:25:05.700
And wouldn't everyone be impressed if I

06:25:05.700 --> 06:25:06.599
beat all of them?

06:25:06.599 --> 06:25:08.159
All by myself?

06:25:08.159 --> 06:25:09.840
With no help whatsoever?

06:25:09.900 --> 06:25:13.020
She flexed her wings, which were still

06:25:13.020 --> 06:25:14.759
sore from the robes that abound them

06:25:14.759 --> 06:25:16.200
tightly just one day earlier?

06:25:16.259 --> 06:25:18.959
This line of thinking felt familiar.

06:25:19.020 --> 06:25:21.419
It was how she had convinced herself to

06:25:21.419 --> 06:25:22.560
go out alone as bait.

06:25:22.680 --> 06:25:25.080
And I made it back, didn't I?

06:25:25.139 --> 06:25:27.599
I could have handled that situation fine

06:25:27.599 --> 06:25:28.380
on my own.

06:25:28.439 --> 06:25:30.779
But she knew it wasn't true.

06:25:30.900 --> 06:25:34.799
Without Kinkachu, Clay, and Deathbringer

06:25:34.799 --> 06:25:36.840
she'd still be stuck in a night wing

06:25:36.840 --> 06:25:40.080
prison, or perhaps even dead, if the

06:25:40.080 --> 06:25:41.340
night wings had had time to figure out

06:25:41.340 --> 06:25:41.939
who she was.

06:25:42.000 --> 06:25:44.400
So don't be an idiot.

06:25:44.459 --> 06:25:47.040
Winning the throne with help won't make

06:25:47.040 --> 06:25:48.180
you any less of a queen.

06:25:48.240 --> 06:25:51.959
You get to choose your dragons, said

06:25:51.959 --> 06:25:54.060
Magnificent, any 4 you wish.

06:25:54.119 --> 06:25:58.080
That makes it easy for me, Glory

06:25:58.080 --> 06:25:58.380
thought.

06:25:58.439 --> 06:26:01.020
She had exactly 4 friends in the world

06:26:01.020 --> 06:26:01.560
after all.

06:26:01.619 --> 06:26:04.139
She could ask mangrove to go guard the

06:26:04.139 --> 06:26:06.779
tunnel and send back Starflight and

06:26:06.779 --> 06:26:07.020
clay.

06:26:07.080 --> 06:26:09.720
She opened her mouth to call him, and

06:26:09.720 --> 06:26:10.500
hesitated.

06:26:10.560 --> 06:26:13.380
Maybe, a little too easy.

06:26:13.500 --> 06:26:18.299
She studied dazzling, grandeur, exquisite

06:26:18.299 --> 06:26:19.259
and fruit bat.

06:26:19.319 --> 06:26:22.680
They looked ready, alert, and eager to

06:26:22.680 --> 06:26:22.979
compete.

06:26:23.099 --> 06:26:25.740
Not a look she'd seen on many rain wings

06:26:25.740 --> 06:26:26.099
before.

06:26:26.159 --> 06:26:28.860
They're convinced they're going to win.

06:26:28.919 --> 06:26:31.979
Go ahead, said the Queen.

06:26:32.040 --> 06:26:34.259
Call them out here, anyone you like.

06:26:34.380 --> 06:26:37.020
Glory tilted her head at magnificent.

06:26:37.080 --> 06:26:39.299
This is a trick.

06:26:39.360 --> 06:26:41.819
She wants me to pick my friends.

06:26:41.939 --> 06:26:44.400
And then the contest will involve

06:26:44.400 --> 06:26:47.220
camouflage, or venom, or something that

06:26:47.220 --> 06:26:49.020
only rain wings can do.

06:26:49.080 --> 06:26:52.200
Not only that, but my future subjects

06:26:52.200 --> 06:26:54.360
will think I trust outsiders more than I

06:26:54.360 --> 06:26:54.900
trust them.

06:26:54.959 --> 06:26:58.380
Which, frankly, I do, because most rain

06:26:58.380 --> 06:26:59.939
wings are hopelessly incompetent.

06:27:00.000 --> 06:27:02.700
But right now, I need their help.

06:27:02.759 --> 06:27:07.860
I choose Kinkaju, Glory said.

06:27:07.979 --> 06:27:10.319
She heard a loud squeak of surprise

06:27:10.319 --> 06:27:12.659
behind her, and a murmur ran through the

06:27:12.659 --> 06:27:13.500
watching dragons.

06:27:13.619 --> 06:27:16.380
A three-year-old dragonette?

06:27:16.380 --> 06:27:18.360
said magnificent archly.

06:27:18.419 --> 06:27:19.799
This should be funny.

06:27:19.860 --> 06:27:23.639
And I choose mangrove, Glory went on

06:27:23.639 --> 06:27:24.540
ignoring her.

06:27:24.659 --> 06:27:27.000
Mangrove stepped out of the crowd

06:27:27.000 --> 06:27:28.979
opposite her and gave her a small bow.

06:27:29.040 --> 06:27:31.380
Orchid was still out there.

06:27:31.439 --> 06:27:33.240
He'd do anything to save her.

06:27:33.299 --> 06:27:35.159
Glory could count on that.

06:27:35.220 --> 06:27:37.680
Now it got a little harder.

06:27:37.740 --> 06:27:40.319
Glory closed her eyes and side.

06:27:40.439 --> 06:27:42.720
I choose Jambu.

06:27:42.779 --> 06:27:44.099
Yes!

06:27:44.159 --> 06:27:46.680
Her brother shouted, leaping into the

06:27:46.680 --> 06:27:46.860
air.

06:27:46.919 --> 06:27:48.119
That's me.

06:27:48.180 --> 06:27:51.240
He bounced across the vines toward her

06:27:51.240 --> 06:27:54.060
grinning all over his goofy pink face.

06:27:54.360 --> 06:27:55.500
Who else?

06:27:55.619 --> 06:27:58.560
Glory ran through the dragons she'd met

06:27:58.560 --> 06:27:59.279
in the rainforest.

06:27:59.400 --> 06:28:00.840
Liana?

06:28:00.900 --> 06:28:02.400
Vermiliad?

06:28:02.400 --> 06:28:03.720
Coconut.

06:28:03.779 --> 06:28:06.000
Not a promising set.

06:28:06.060 --> 06:28:07.860
She didn't know much about any of them

06:28:07.860 --> 06:28:09.900
but none of them had impressed her as

06:28:09.900 --> 06:28:10.500
team players.

06:28:10.619 --> 06:28:14.040
Kinkachu came up beside her, fidgeting

06:28:14.040 --> 06:28:16.319
excitedly and spilling deep purple blue

06:28:16.319 --> 06:28:17.759
bubbles through her green scales.

06:28:17.880 --> 06:28:20.220
Glory remembered someone the little

06:28:20.220 --> 06:28:21.779
dragonette had mentioned when she was

06:28:21.779 --> 06:28:22.799
describing the queens.

06:28:22.860 --> 06:28:25.919
It was a risk, choosing a dragon she'd

06:28:25.919 --> 06:28:27.900
never met, but she couldn't be worse than

06:28:27.900 --> 06:28:29.040
any other rain wing.

06:28:29.099 --> 06:28:32.700
And I choose Tamarin, she said.

06:28:32.759 --> 06:28:35.279
All glory knew about her was that she was

06:28:35.279 --> 06:28:36.479
friends with Kingaju.

06:28:36.540 --> 06:28:38.520
She cared about her work with the flowers

06:28:38.520 --> 06:28:40.919
and she wasn't the biggest fan of Fruit

06:28:40.919 --> 06:28:43.259
Bat, which sounded like 3 good features

06:28:43.259 --> 06:28:44.220
to glory.

06:28:44.279 --> 06:28:46.979
The crowd murmured again, sounding like

06:28:46.979 --> 06:28:49.380
waves rushing in from the ocean, and

06:28:49.380 --> 06:28:51.599
Queen Magnificent barked a startled

06:28:51.599 --> 06:28:51.959
laugh.

06:28:52.020 --> 06:28:54.119
Tamarin?

06:28:54.240 --> 06:28:55.380
Kinkachu cried.

06:28:55.439 --> 06:28:57.180
But are you sure?

06:28:57.240 --> 06:29:00.360
Too late, said Magnificent.

06:29:00.419 --> 06:29:01.799
That's who she chose.

06:29:01.919 --> 06:29:04.380
Someone give Tamaron a shove in the right

06:29:04.380 --> 06:29:04.680
direction.

06:29:04.740 --> 06:29:08.220
A small dragon popped out of the crowd

06:29:08.220 --> 06:29:10.799
and stumbled forward a few steps, then

06:29:10.799 --> 06:29:11.220
stopped.

06:29:11.340 --> 06:29:14.939
She stood very still, with waves of pale

06:29:14.939 --> 06:29:16.619
green rippling across her scales.

06:29:16.680 --> 06:29:19.740
Her eyes were an odd light shade of blue

06:29:19.740 --> 06:29:22.259
and stared blankly past glory at the

06:29:22.259 --> 06:29:22.740
trees.

06:29:22.799 --> 06:29:24.360
What is it?

06:29:24.479 --> 06:29:27.180
Glory asked, glancing at Kinkajoo.

06:29:27.240 --> 06:29:28.619
Why shouldn't I pick her?

06:29:28.680 --> 06:29:31.979
You can, said Kinkachu.

06:29:32.040 --> 06:29:33.000
It's just that.

06:29:33.299 --> 06:29:35.340
Tamarin is blind.

06:29:35.459 --> 06:29:39.659
Chapter 30.

06:29:40.020 --> 06:29:43.680
Kinkachu hurried forward and whispered in

06:29:43.680 --> 06:29:46.020
her friend's ear, then led Tamarin over

06:29:46.020 --> 06:29:46.439
to glory.

06:29:46.500 --> 06:29:49.259
The blind rain wing moved confidently

06:29:49.259 --> 06:29:51.840
across the unsteady vine surface, as if

06:29:51.840 --> 06:29:53.639
she knew where every leaf and every gap

06:29:53.639 --> 06:29:54.000
would be.

06:29:54.060 --> 06:29:57.419
She kept her wings up and out, like an

06:29:57.419 --> 06:29:58.380
insect's antennae.

06:29:58.439 --> 06:30:01.619
This is glory, Kinkaju said.

06:30:01.680 --> 06:30:03.180
Our next queen.

06:30:03.299 --> 06:30:06.419
She held out Tameron's front talons to

06:30:06.419 --> 06:30:07.919
feel glory's face and wings.

06:30:07.979 --> 06:30:10.259
Why would you pick me?

06:30:10.319 --> 06:30:12.000
Tameron blurted.

06:30:12.060 --> 06:30:14.279
She wore only one garland of flowers

06:30:14.279 --> 06:30:15.240
around her shoulders.

06:30:15.299 --> 06:30:17.759
The shades of red and pink and purple

06:30:17.759 --> 06:30:19.919
didn't match at all, but they smelled

06:30:19.919 --> 06:30:20.459
amazing.

06:30:20.520 --> 06:30:23.580
It made Glory think of coconuts and honey

06:30:23.580 --> 06:30:24.599
without making her hungry.

06:30:24.659 --> 06:30:26.819
I told her about you.

06:30:26.880 --> 06:30:28.799
Said Kinkaju.

06:30:28.860 --> 06:30:31.560
Her voice faltered a little, giving away

06:30:31.560 --> 06:30:32.880
that she hadn't quite mentioned

06:30:32.880 --> 06:30:33.299
everything.

06:30:33.360 --> 06:30:36.840
I had no idea there were any blind

06:30:36.840 --> 06:30:40.020
dragons, except an old scroll stories

06:30:40.020 --> 06:30:40.919
Glory said.

06:30:40.979 --> 06:30:43.020
She fluttered a wing in front of

06:30:43.020 --> 06:30:45.419
Tamaron's eyes, but the rain wing didn't

06:30:45.419 --> 06:30:45.720
blink.

06:30:45.779 --> 06:30:48.060
How do you fly between the trees?

06:30:48.119 --> 06:30:49.500
How do you land?

06:30:49.560 --> 06:30:52.619
Don't you accidentally walk off platforms

06:30:52.619 --> 06:30:54.779
and fall out of hammocks all the time?

06:30:54.840 --> 06:30:56.580
Not anymore.

06:30:56.639 --> 06:30:58.619
Tameron answered.

06:30:58.680 --> 06:31:00.599
The green was starting to fade from her

06:31:00.599 --> 06:31:02.459
scales as she relaxed.

06:31:02.520 --> 06:31:05.340
The 1st year, yes, all the time.

06:31:05.459 --> 06:31:08.459
She lifted her wings higher to reveal an

06:31:08.459 --> 06:31:10.740
old scar twisting across her underbelly.

06:31:10.799 --> 06:31:13.740
Glory spotted a few others on Tameron's

06:31:13.740 --> 06:31:14.400
wings and neck.

06:31:14.459 --> 06:31:16.860
These weren't like the battle scars the

06:31:16.860 --> 06:31:18.479
war had given to so many dragons.

06:31:18.540 --> 06:31:21.659
These told the story of a tiny dragonette

06:31:21.659 --> 06:31:23.759
crashing into trees, plummeting off

06:31:23.759 --> 06:31:26.279
walkways, and impaling herself on stray

06:31:26.279 --> 06:31:28.319
branches as she tried to learn to fly in

06:31:28.319 --> 06:31:29.340
total darkness.

06:31:29.400 --> 06:31:31.500
But everyone took care of me.

06:31:31.560 --> 06:31:33.180
Tamaron said.

06:31:33.240 --> 06:31:35.580
There was always a dragon watching me

06:31:35.580 --> 06:31:37.380
helping me, and teaching me.

06:31:37.439 --> 06:31:40.200
Glory glanced at the watching tribe.

06:31:40.259 --> 06:31:42.599
She would have guessed that no one would

06:31:42.599 --> 06:31:44.340
take responsibility for a little blind

06:31:44.340 --> 06:31:45.419
dragonette.

06:31:45.479 --> 06:31:48.720
Instead, everyone had, which gave her

06:31:48.720 --> 06:31:48.959
hope.

06:31:49.020 --> 06:31:51.659
And now I have the village memorized.

06:31:51.720 --> 06:31:53.580
So I know all the distances and

06:31:53.580 --> 06:31:54.180
obstacles.

06:31:54.299 --> 06:31:58.020
Tamron's ruff folded down and then opened

06:31:58.020 --> 06:32:00.419
again, as if she was sensing the shifting

06:32:00.419 --> 06:32:01.139
wind currents.

06:32:01.200 --> 06:32:04.259
Queen magnificent, unfurled her purple

06:32:04.259 --> 06:32:06.540
wings and stood up on her back talons.

06:32:06.599 --> 06:32:09.360
Let's begin, she called.

06:32:09.419 --> 06:32:11.580
Unless you've changed your mind.

06:32:11.639 --> 06:32:14.099
We're ready, Glory said.

06:32:14.159 --> 06:32:17.220
No inspiring speech?

06:32:17.279 --> 06:32:18.720
John Boo said.

06:32:18.779 --> 06:32:19.979
Sounding disappointed.

06:32:20.040 --> 06:32:23.099
Kinkachoo and Mangrove tilted their

06:32:23.099 --> 06:32:24.419
snouts toward her expectantly.

06:32:24.479 --> 06:32:26.580
Tamron's ears twitched.

06:32:26.639 --> 06:32:28.740
I gave one yesterday.

06:32:28.799 --> 06:32:30.479
Glory protested.

06:32:30.540 --> 06:32:32.639
So now do one just for us.

06:32:32.759 --> 06:32:34.319
Kinkaju said.

06:32:34.380 --> 06:32:36.599
Her scales kept shifting to match the

06:32:36.599 --> 06:32:39.180
dark green leaves below them, as if she

06:32:39.180 --> 06:32:40.500
was trying to hide whatever she was

06:32:40.500 --> 06:32:41.040
really feeling.

06:32:41.099 --> 06:32:44.040
Mangrove, on the other hand, was a

06:32:44.040 --> 06:32:45.360
resigned sky blue.

06:32:45.419 --> 06:32:48.000
Um, all right.

06:32:48.119 --> 06:32:49.619
Do your best.

06:32:49.680 --> 06:32:50.759
Glory said.

06:32:50.819 --> 06:32:52.740
And thanks and stuff.

06:32:52.799 --> 06:32:55.380
Kinkaju stifled a laugh.

06:32:55.500 --> 06:32:58.619
Wow. said Mangrove.

06:32:58.680 --> 06:33:00.659
I feel so moved.

06:33:00.720 --> 06:33:04.200
Queen Magnificent beckoned imperiously

06:33:04.200 --> 06:33:06.840
and 2 portly rain wings flew up beside

06:33:06.840 --> 06:33:09.479
her, carrying a low table carved from a

06:33:09.479 --> 06:33:12.479
single log of mahogany, arranged neatly

06:33:12.479 --> 06:33:15.959
on top were 5 nuts, each polished brown

06:33:15.959 --> 06:33:17.880
and about the size of a dragon eye.

06:33:17.939 --> 06:33:22.500
This contest has 5 parts, each related to

06:33:22.500 --> 06:33:25.020
the special talents of our tribe. said

06:33:25.020 --> 06:33:26.099
Queen Magnificent.

06:33:26.159 --> 06:33:29.459
You assign one team member per part, and

06:33:29.459 --> 06:33:31.560
whichever team wins 3 out of the 5

06:33:31.560 --> 06:33:33.779
contests wins the crown.

06:33:33.900 --> 06:33:37.200
She pointed a sharp claw at the 1st nut.

06:33:37.319 --> 06:33:39.119
Venom targeting.

06:33:39.180 --> 06:33:41.040
She pointed to the second.

06:33:41.040 --> 06:33:42.840
A flower hunt?

06:33:42.900 --> 06:33:45.900
The 3rd Treetop Race.

06:33:46.020 --> 06:33:48.779
The 4th, fruit gathering.

06:33:48.900 --> 06:33:51.779
The last nut she picked up and turned

06:33:51.779 --> 06:33:53.279
over in her front talons.

06:33:53.340 --> 06:33:56.159
And naturally there must be a camouflage

06:33:56.159 --> 06:33:56.819
competition.

06:33:56.880 --> 06:33:59.099
We are rain wings after all.

06:33:59.159 --> 06:34:01.500
She set it down again with a toothy

06:34:01.500 --> 06:34:01.799
smile.

06:34:01.919 --> 06:34:04.139
Let's start with fruit gathering.

06:34:04.200 --> 06:34:06.360
So the competitors can work on it while

06:34:06.360 --> 06:34:07.560
we finish the other contests.

06:34:07.619 --> 06:34:11.099
Certainly, said handsome.

06:34:11.159 --> 06:34:12.419
Quite logical.

06:34:12.479 --> 06:34:15.180
It's a very straightforward contest.

06:34:15.240 --> 06:34:18.360
Each dragon has an hour to collect as

06:34:18.360 --> 06:34:20.700
many different types of fruit as he or

06:34:20.700 --> 06:34:24.060
she can find, the one who comes back with

06:34:24.060 --> 06:34:26.520
the most variety wins.

06:34:26.580 --> 06:34:29.939
Dazzling will compete for our side

06:34:29.939 --> 06:34:32.880
Magnificent said, sweeping one wing

06:34:32.880 --> 06:34:34.259
toward the portly queen.

06:34:34.319 --> 06:34:35.639
And for yours.

06:34:35.700 --> 06:34:39.479
Glory studied her own dragons, beating

06:34:39.479 --> 06:34:41.459
back the anxiety that threatened to climb

06:34:41.459 --> 06:34:41.939
up her scales.

06:34:42.000 --> 06:34:45.240
The contests all featured rain wing

06:34:45.240 --> 06:34:45.599
skills.

06:34:45.659 --> 06:34:49.080
So on the one talon, she had outwitted

06:34:49.080 --> 06:34:50.819
magnificent by choosing rain wings

06:34:50.819 --> 06:34:53.099
instead of her friends, but on the other

06:34:53.099 --> 06:34:55.439
talent, she barely knew her teammates.

06:34:55.500 --> 06:34:57.479
She had no idea what they were good at.

06:34:57.540 --> 06:35:01.439
All right, Glory said to them, keeping

06:35:01.439 --> 06:35:02.220
her voice low.

06:35:02.279 --> 06:35:04.020
Who should do what?

06:35:04.080 --> 06:35:06.779
Jambu, you teach tree gliding.

06:35:06.840 --> 06:35:08.159
Are you fast?

06:35:08.279 --> 06:35:09.419
Can you do the treetop race?

06:35:09.540 --> 06:35:11.159
Well, of course.

06:35:11.220 --> 06:35:13.799
Her brother said, glowing with bright

06:35:13.799 --> 06:35:15.000
pink enthusiasm.

06:35:15.119 --> 06:35:18.659
Give me the flower one, said Tamaron.

06:35:18.720 --> 06:35:21.180
If it's about flowers, I can do it.

06:35:21.240 --> 06:35:23.400
Glory hesitated.

06:35:23.580 --> 06:35:26.400
She said flower hunt, though.

06:35:26.459 --> 06:35:31.259
I know, flowers, Tameron insisted.

06:35:31.319 --> 06:35:34.020
Give her a chance, said a voice in

06:35:34.020 --> 06:35:36.360
glory's head, it's what a good queen

06:35:36.360 --> 06:35:36.779
would do.

06:35:36.840 --> 06:35:40.680
All right, glory glanced to the row of

06:35:40.680 --> 06:35:42.659
nuts on the table, thinking through the

06:35:42.659 --> 06:35:43.380
other contests.

06:35:43.439 --> 06:35:45.959
Her day of training hadn't exactly left

06:35:45.959 --> 06:35:47.459
her feeling confident about most of

06:35:47.459 --> 06:35:47.700
these.

06:35:47.759 --> 06:35:50.939
I guess I should do the camouflage

06:35:50.939 --> 06:35:52.139
contest, she said.

06:35:52.200 --> 06:35:54.900
I have no idea where to find fruits in

06:35:54.900 --> 06:35:57.119
the rainforest, and I'm not exactly a

06:35:57.119 --> 06:35:58.139
venom expert.

06:35:58.200 --> 06:36:00.659
She thought of the mess she'd made of

06:36:00.659 --> 06:36:02.040
everything they'd put in front of her

06:36:02.040 --> 06:36:02.340
yesterday.

06:36:02.400 --> 06:36:04.139
Mangrove.

06:36:04.200 --> 06:36:05.759
I know you're a fruit gatherer.

06:36:05.819 --> 06:36:07.319
But Kingaju.

06:36:07.380 --> 06:36:09.659
Sorry, but I got the impression from

06:36:09.659 --> 06:36:11.459
Bromeliad that venom practice wasn't

06:36:11.459 --> 06:36:12.000
going well with you.

06:36:12.060 --> 06:36:15.360
That's because Bromeliad is a slow old

06:36:15.360 --> 06:36:16.200
baboon.

06:36:16.319 --> 06:36:17.939
Kingaju said hotly.

06:36:18.000 --> 06:36:20.279
I'm super great at venom shooting.

06:36:20.340 --> 06:36:21.180
I swear.

06:36:21.240 --> 06:36:23.279
Plus, mangrove can carry more fruit than

06:36:23.279 --> 06:36:23.580
I can.

06:36:23.700 --> 06:36:26.040
Glory rubbed her forehead.

06:36:26.159 --> 06:36:29.099
She only had to win 3 of the 5 contests

06:36:29.099 --> 06:36:29.520
after all.

06:36:29.580 --> 06:36:32.040
All right, she said.

06:36:32.099 --> 06:36:34.200
Turning back to the waiting queens.

06:36:34.259 --> 06:36:36.720
Mangrove will do the fruit gathering for

06:36:36.720 --> 06:36:36.900
us.

06:36:36.959 --> 06:36:39.900
Mangrove spread his wings and bowed to

06:36:39.900 --> 06:36:40.619
dazzling.

06:36:40.740 --> 06:36:42.299
At a signal from handsome.

06:36:42.360 --> 06:36:45.180
They both flew off into the trees, heading

06:36:45.180 --> 06:36:47.520
in opposite directions, and sending up

06:36:47.520 --> 06:36:50.099
tornadoes of tiny crimson butterflies as

06:36:50.099 --> 06:36:50.400
they went.

06:36:50.520 --> 06:36:55.139
Now, said Handsome, he glanced up at the

06:36:55.139 --> 06:36:58.080
sky and turned in a slow circle, so that

06:36:58.080 --> 06:36:59.939
all the watching dragons could hear him.

06:37:00.000 --> 06:37:04.200
Next, the treetop race, a test of speed

06:37:04.200 --> 06:37:05.220
and agility.

06:37:05.279 --> 06:37:08.400
Magnificent spun one of the nuts on the

06:37:08.400 --> 06:37:08.700
table.

06:37:08.759 --> 06:37:11.520
Exquisite. that means you.

06:37:11.639 --> 06:37:13.619
And me.

06:37:13.680 --> 06:37:15.659
Jambu said delightedly.

06:37:15.720 --> 06:37:16.979
Handsome grand.

06:37:17.040 --> 06:37:20.400
I'll never forget the last treetop race I

06:37:20.400 --> 06:37:20.700
saw.

06:37:20.759 --> 06:37:22.319
Weren't you in that?

06:37:22.439 --> 06:37:24.000
He asked grandeur.

06:37:24.060 --> 06:37:25.919
Who was your challenger?

06:37:26.040 --> 06:37:28.680
No one worth mentioning.

06:37:28.740 --> 06:37:31.020
Grandeur said frostily.

06:37:31.080 --> 06:37:32.939
Naturally, I won.

06:37:33.000 --> 06:37:35.939
But you're too old for racing now.

06:37:36.060 --> 06:37:38.400
Magnificent said dismissively.

06:37:38.459 --> 06:37:41.099
Grandeur gave her a wholehearted glare

06:37:41.099 --> 06:37:43.439
that magnificent completely missed.

06:37:43.560 --> 06:37:46.860
The sloth on exquisite tail clambered up

06:37:46.860 --> 06:37:49.080
to her neck as the silver queen stepped

06:37:49.080 --> 06:37:49.500
forward.

06:37:49.560 --> 06:37:51.779
She dipped her wings so the other 2

06:37:51.779 --> 06:37:53.819
sloths could slide off onto the vines

06:37:53.880 --> 06:37:55.680
strong shoulders.

06:37:55.799 --> 06:37:58.439
Glory noticed, big wings.

06:37:58.500 --> 06:37:59.759
I bet she's fast.

06:37:59.819 --> 06:38:02.939
Jambu looked like a bright pink monkey

06:38:02.939 --> 06:38:05.220
next to the sleek silver dragoness.

06:38:05.340 --> 06:38:07.500
Hansom pointed up at the treetops

06:38:07.500 --> 06:38:09.900
surrounding the arboretum, a small

06:38:09.900 --> 06:38:12.959
platform, about 3 dragons wide, was set

06:38:12.959 --> 06:38:13.860
in the high branches.

06:38:13.979 --> 06:38:16.860
Peach colored flowers studded the dark

06:38:16.860 --> 06:38:19.619
wood planks, tied in bunches with strands

06:38:19.619 --> 06:38:20.939
of silver sloth fur.

06:38:21.000 --> 06:38:25.139
That is the start and end of the race, he

06:38:25.139 --> 06:38:25.380
said.

06:38:25.439 --> 06:38:28.979
You will fly 3 times around the arboretum

06:38:28.979 --> 06:38:31.740
staying outside the ring of trees.

06:38:31.799 --> 06:38:35.159
If you fly inside the ring, you will be

06:38:35.159 --> 06:38:36.240
disqualified.

06:38:36.299 --> 06:38:39.419
If you touch your opponent.

06:38:39.479 --> 06:38:41.220
You will be disqualified.

06:38:41.279 --> 06:38:45.180
As long as you stay outside the ring, you

06:38:45.180 --> 06:38:48.659
may take any path around, but you must

06:38:48.659 --> 06:38:51.540
touch down on the platform as you

06:38:51.540 --> 06:38:53.580
complete each circuit.

06:38:53.639 --> 06:38:55.139
Understood?

06:38:55.200 --> 06:38:59.220
Got it, Jambu said, flexing his wings.

06:38:59.279 --> 06:39:01.200
Exquisite didn't answer.

06:39:01.259 --> 06:39:03.659
She had her front talons curled around

06:39:03.659 --> 06:39:06.299
her 2 sloths, and was cooing at them as

06:39:06.299 --> 06:39:07.500
they clambered over her claws.

06:39:07.619 --> 06:39:09.840
Your majesty?

06:39:09.900 --> 06:39:12.299
said Handsome, and then caught himself.

06:39:12.360 --> 06:39:15.779
That is, I mean, exquisite.

06:39:15.840 --> 06:39:18.360
Do you understand the rules?

06:39:18.419 --> 06:39:20.520
Of course.

06:39:20.580 --> 06:39:23.520
She said, disentangling her pets.

06:39:23.580 --> 06:39:26.279
She set the 3rd one down next to them and

06:39:26.279 --> 06:39:27.119
stroked their heads.

06:39:27.180 --> 06:39:30.000
I'll be back in a moment, darlings.

06:39:30.060 --> 06:39:32.459
I just have to win this race for Auntie

06:39:32.459 --> 06:39:33.119
Maggie.

06:39:33.240 --> 06:39:35.040
Stop calling me that.

06:39:35.159 --> 06:39:37.380
Magnificent said crossly.

06:39:37.439 --> 06:39:39.180
I'm nobody's auntie.

06:39:39.240 --> 06:39:41.700
Certainly not a bunch of sloths, and this

06:39:41.700 --> 06:39:43.979
isn't just for me, you big fur head.

06:39:44.040 --> 06:39:45.540
It's your throne too.

06:39:45.599 --> 06:39:47.759
There, there.

06:39:47.819 --> 06:39:51.119
Exquisite said to the sloths, who had

06:39:51.119 --> 06:39:53.159
curled up into a sleepy pile of fur.

06:39:53.220 --> 06:39:56.220
Auntie Maggie isn't mad at you.

06:39:56.279 --> 06:39:58.919
She's just in a bad temper because she

06:39:58.919 --> 06:40:00.900
has to actually do something today.

06:40:00.959 --> 06:40:04.319
In a loud whisper that absolutely

06:40:04.319 --> 06:40:05.639
everyone could hear.

06:40:05.700 --> 06:40:10.139
She added, besides, she's jealous that

06:40:10.139 --> 06:40:13.259
you all are so much prettier than her

06:40:13.259 --> 06:40:14.220
sloth.

06:40:14.279 --> 06:40:19.200
Magnificent snarled in a very unqueenly

06:40:19.200 --> 06:40:22.139
way, and shot a dark look at the 3 sloths

06:40:22.139 --> 06:40:23.939
as if she might throw them off the

06:40:23.939 --> 06:40:25.799
arboretum while exquisite was racing.

06:40:25.919 --> 06:40:29.819
Good luck, Glory said to Jambu.

06:40:29.880 --> 06:40:31.020
Please win.

06:40:31.139 --> 06:40:34.259
That's the plan, he said cheerfully.

06:40:34.319 --> 06:40:36.779
He followed handsome and exquisite up to

06:40:36.779 --> 06:40:39.119
the platform, then leaned over the edge

06:40:39.119 --> 06:40:41.400
and waved the crowd of dragons around the

06:40:41.400 --> 06:40:42.779
edges of the arboretum.

06:40:42.900 --> 06:40:45.599
Sonny and several other dragons waved

06:40:45.599 --> 06:40:46.139
back.

06:40:46.200 --> 06:40:48.060
It occurred to Glory to wonder who

06:40:48.060 --> 06:40:49.200
everyone was rooting for.

06:40:49.259 --> 06:40:51.299
Did anyone want her to win?

06:40:51.360 --> 06:40:53.400
Did they know what that would mean?

06:40:53.459 --> 06:40:55.799
Or about all the things she wanted to

06:40:55.799 --> 06:40:57.240
change about their world?

06:40:57.299 --> 06:41:00.720
Her gaze swept across the rain wings, the

06:41:00.720 --> 06:41:02.580
tribe that might soon be hers.

06:41:02.639 --> 06:41:05.700
She tried to read their scales, but as

06:41:05.700 --> 06:41:07.680
far as she could tell, today most of them

06:41:07.680 --> 06:41:09.659
had chosen their colors for their looks

06:41:09.659 --> 06:41:11.459
as though they were showing off at a

06:41:11.459 --> 06:41:11.700
party.

06:41:11.819 --> 06:41:14.759
The only emotions she spotted were bright

06:41:14.759 --> 06:41:16.860
yellow bursts of excitement in their

06:41:16.860 --> 06:41:18.900
scales here and there, and she had a

06:41:18.900 --> 06:41:20.159
feeling they'd be like that about

06:41:20.159 --> 06:41:21.360
anything new that happened.

06:41:21.419 --> 06:41:24.419
Handsome stepped onto a branch shaped

06:41:24.419 --> 06:41:26.700
like a coiling dragon tail and spread his

06:41:26.700 --> 06:41:27.060
wings.

06:41:27.119 --> 06:41:31.139
Start when you hear the toucan call, he

06:41:31.139 --> 06:41:32.759
said to Jambu and exquisite.

06:41:32.819 --> 06:41:34.259
Don't forget the rules.

06:41:34.319 --> 06:41:35.520
Ready?

06:41:35.580 --> 06:41:37.259
And...

06:41:37.259 --> 06:41:38.880
Call.

06:41:38.939 --> 06:41:41.700
Glory was so startled by the sound that

06:41:41.700 --> 06:41:43.500
came out of his throat that she missed

06:41:43.500 --> 06:41:44.639
the beginning of the race.

06:41:44.700 --> 06:41:47.340
Handsome had perfectly imitated the

06:41:47.340 --> 06:41:49.200
noises she'd been hearing from the big

06:41:49.200 --> 06:41:50.040
beaked birds.

06:41:50.099 --> 06:41:53.040
If that was another rain wing talent, it

06:41:53.040 --> 06:41:54.479
was one she'd never even thought of

06:41:54.479 --> 06:41:55.259
trying before.

06:41:55.319 --> 06:41:59.220
Exquisite shot ahead of Jambu, swinging

06:41:59.220 --> 06:42:01.919
smoothly from branch to vine to branch

06:42:01.919 --> 06:42:04.919
her tail was longer than Jambu's, giving

06:42:04.919 --> 06:42:07.860
her a wider swing and farther reach, but

06:42:07.860 --> 06:42:10.139
his narrower wings helped him dive

06:42:10.139 --> 06:42:12.479
between some tangles of branches that she

06:42:12.479 --> 06:42:14.759
had to maneuver around, and by the time

06:42:14.759 --> 06:42:16.439
they got back to the platform for the 1st

06:42:16.439 --> 06:42:19.259
time, his snout was almost brushing her

06:42:19.259 --> 06:42:19.560
tail.

06:42:19.619 --> 06:42:22.139
Go, Jamboo.

06:42:22.200 --> 06:42:23.580
Sunny yelled from her spot on the

06:42:23.580 --> 06:42:24.060
walkway.

06:42:24.119 --> 06:42:25.919
You're going to win.

06:42:25.979 --> 06:42:27.779
You're the fastest dragon in the forest.

06:42:27.840 --> 06:42:28.919
Woohoo.

06:42:28.979 --> 06:42:31.979
Kingaju nudged Tamarin, and they both

06:42:31.979 --> 06:42:33.779
started hooting and shouting as well.

06:42:33.840 --> 06:42:36.240
Personally, glory thought that much noise

06:42:36.240 --> 06:42:38.759
would have been an annoying distraction

06:42:38.759 --> 06:42:41.520
but it seemed to add wind to Jambu's

06:42:41.520 --> 06:42:41.759
wings.

06:42:41.819 --> 06:42:44.939
He banked around a trunk, dodged a loop

06:42:44.939 --> 06:42:47.580
of hibiscus covered vines, and shot past

06:42:47.580 --> 06:42:49.020
exquisite on the outside.

06:42:49.080 --> 06:42:52.319
Well, if it works, Glory thought.

06:42:52.439 --> 06:42:54.840
Yay, she hollered.

06:42:54.900 --> 06:42:56.700
Jambu is the best.

06:42:56.759 --> 06:42:59.220
Uh, you're an awesome glider.

06:42:59.279 --> 06:43:01.740
Good, uh, flying.

06:43:01.799 --> 06:43:02.580
Yay.

06:43:02.700 --> 06:43:05.159
She called it tsunami, giving her an

06:43:05.159 --> 06:43:07.259
amused look, and stuck out her tongue at

06:43:07.259 --> 06:43:08.040
the sea wing.

06:43:08.099 --> 06:43:10.439
Jambu brushed the platform a 2nd time

06:43:10.439 --> 06:43:12.240
with his claws and took off again.

06:43:12.299 --> 06:43:15.659
A few moments later, exquisite, thudded

06:43:15.659 --> 06:43:18.299
down in the same spot and gave chase, her

06:43:18.299 --> 06:43:20.580
wings pumped, and her brow was furrowed

06:43:20.580 --> 06:43:21.060
angrily.

06:43:21.119 --> 06:43:23.819
Glory's heart pounded as she watched them

06:43:23.819 --> 06:43:24.779
swerve through the trees.

06:43:24.840 --> 06:43:26.279
One more circuit.

06:43:26.340 --> 06:43:28.560
If John Boo could stay ahead just a bit

06:43:28.560 --> 06:43:29.880
longer, he'd win.

06:43:29.880 --> 06:43:31.500
Hang in there.

06:43:31.560 --> 06:43:34.200
She dug her claws into the vines below

06:43:34.200 --> 06:43:36.720
her. wishing she could be up there, giving

06:43:36.720 --> 06:43:38.099
him her speed somehow.

06:43:38.159 --> 06:43:41.400
Jambu ricocheted off a tree, and dipped

06:43:41.400 --> 06:43:43.740
through a hole in the branches, he veered

06:43:43.740 --> 06:43:46.860
around the last curve, and suddenly flung

06:43:46.860 --> 06:43:48.540
his wings up to stop his momentum.

06:43:48.599 --> 06:43:51.540
He thrashed in place for a moment, and

06:43:51.540 --> 06:43:54.299
glory saw a vine wound around his neck.

06:43:54.360 --> 06:43:57.599
He twisted backward, gasping for air, and

06:43:57.599 --> 06:43:58.799
flailed to the side.

06:43:58.860 --> 06:44:01.319
With a horrible lurch in her stomach

06:44:01.319 --> 06:44:04.560
Glory watched Jambu tip over, crossing

06:44:04.560 --> 06:44:05.819
into the ring of trees.

06:44:05.880 --> 06:44:09.000
At the same time, exquisite whisked past

06:44:09.000 --> 06:44:10.919
him and landed neatly on the platform.

06:44:10.979 --> 06:44:14.040
She lifted her wings, and turned in a

06:44:14.040 --> 06:44:16.860
triumphant circle, as deep blue purple

06:44:16.860 --> 06:44:18.659
waves whished through her scales.

06:44:18.720 --> 06:44:21.360
But glory had seen something else too.

06:44:21.419 --> 06:44:23.759
That vine hadn't appeared out of

06:44:23.759 --> 06:44:24.119
nowhere.

06:44:24.180 --> 06:44:26.700
Something was scurrying away from the

06:44:26.700 --> 06:44:28.860
spot where Jambu had nearly strangled

06:44:28.860 --> 06:44:29.279
himself.

06:44:29.340 --> 06:44:32.880
Several somethings, in fact, with shaggy

06:44:32.880 --> 06:44:33.540
silver fur.

06:44:33.599 --> 06:44:38.159
Chapter 31.

06:44:38.340 --> 06:44:42.119
How dare you accuse us of cheating?

06:44:42.240 --> 06:44:44.220
Magnificent demanded.

06:44:44.279 --> 06:44:46.919
The better question is, how dare you

06:44:46.919 --> 06:44:47.639
cheat?

06:44:47.700 --> 06:44:49.319
Glory demanded right back.

06:44:49.380 --> 06:44:52.500
My teammates' sloths were right here in

06:44:52.500 --> 06:44:54.419
front of us the whole time, said the

06:44:54.419 --> 06:44:54.720
queen.

06:44:54.779 --> 06:44:58.860
These 3 were, said Glory, pointing to the

06:44:58.860 --> 06:45:00.479
fur balls that were clambering up to

06:45:00.479 --> 06:45:01.500
exquisite's shoulders.

06:45:01.560 --> 06:45:04.500
We know exquisite has several others who

06:45:04.500 --> 06:45:05.880
could have been planted out there in the

06:45:05.880 --> 06:45:08.700
trees, just waiting to get in the way if

06:45:08.700 --> 06:45:10.560
it looked like she wasn't going to win.

06:45:11.159 --> 06:45:15.419
Hmm, said grandeur, narrowing her eyes.

06:45:15.479 --> 06:45:17.700
She'd been sitting in the same position

06:45:17.700 --> 06:45:20.099
looking bored and regal throughout the

06:45:20.099 --> 06:45:20.400
race.

06:45:20.459 --> 06:45:24.240
Ridiculous, scoffed exquisite.

06:45:24.299 --> 06:45:27.119
Her sloths aren't nearly smart enough for

06:45:27.119 --> 06:45:28.740
that, said magnificent.

06:45:28.860 --> 06:45:32.400
They most certainly are, exquisite

06:45:32.400 --> 06:45:34.259
snapped, flaring her rough.

06:45:34.319 --> 06:45:36.180
She glanced at Glory and carefully

06:45:36.180 --> 06:45:36.959
settled it again.

06:45:37.020 --> 06:45:39.599
But they would never do such a thing.

06:45:39.659 --> 06:45:42.720
They do anything you told them to.

06:45:42.840 --> 06:45:45.720
Kingachu cried, as a surge of orange

06:45:45.720 --> 06:45:48.419
outrage rippled down her tail, she

06:45:48.419 --> 06:45:50.459
snapped her teeth at the nearest sloth

06:45:50.459 --> 06:45:52.080
and it chirped fiercely at her.

06:45:52.139 --> 06:45:54.779
Enough, said Handsome.

06:45:54.900 --> 06:45:57.299
Jambu, what did you see?

06:45:57.360 --> 06:46:00.720
Glory barely recognized her brother with

06:46:00.720 --> 06:46:03.299
his scales, this dismal blue gray color?

06:46:03.360 --> 06:46:05.639
He lifted his shoulders despondently.

06:46:05.700 --> 06:46:07.259
I don't know.

06:46:07.319 --> 06:46:09.119
It all happened so fast.

06:46:09.240 --> 06:46:12.119
One moment I was flying, and the next I

06:46:12.119 --> 06:46:12.779
was choking.

06:46:12.840 --> 06:46:16.380
I saw sloths in the trees, but.

06:46:16.439 --> 06:46:18.360
But you can't be sure they were

06:46:18.360 --> 06:46:20.580
exquisites, or that they had anything to

06:46:20.580 --> 06:46:21.959
do with the vine in your way.

06:46:22.020 --> 06:46:24.060
Magnificent finished.

06:46:24.119 --> 06:46:26.700
Jambu gave Glory a mournful look.

06:46:26.759 --> 06:46:29.700
It's all right, Jambu, she said.

06:46:29.759 --> 06:46:32.520
I know you would have won in a fair

06:46:32.520 --> 06:46:33.000
race.

06:46:33.060 --> 06:46:35.759
She made sure her voice was loud enough

06:46:35.759 --> 06:46:37.560
to carry to the crowd of watching rain

06:46:37.560 --> 06:46:40.979
wings, magnificent hissed softly, and

06:46:40.979 --> 06:46:43.259
snatched up the treetop race nut from the

06:46:43.259 --> 06:46:45.360
low table, lashing her tail.

06:46:45.419 --> 06:46:47.939
She dropped it in a hollowed out coconut

06:46:47.939 --> 06:46:49.500
on her side of the arboretum.

06:46:49.560 --> 06:46:53.520
Let's move on, Handsome said, clearing

06:46:53.520 --> 06:46:53.939
his throat.

06:46:54.000 --> 06:46:56.880
Perhaps the flower hunt next.

06:46:57.000 --> 06:46:59.459
Tamarin stepped forward.

06:46:59.520 --> 06:47:02.580
Her wings trembled, and her scales were

06:47:02.580 --> 06:47:03.959
rippling with pale green again.

06:47:04.020 --> 06:47:06.299
Glory wondered whether she could tell

06:47:06.299 --> 06:47:07.619
that her emotions were on display.

06:47:07.680 --> 06:47:10.139
Another question occurred to her.

06:47:10.200 --> 06:47:13.200
Can you use camouflage?

06:47:13.259 --> 06:47:14.819
She asked Tamarin.

06:47:14.880 --> 06:47:17.099
I mean, since you can't see what you're

06:47:17.099 --> 06:47:17.819
trying to match?

06:47:17.880 --> 06:47:20.700
Yes, it works anyway.

06:47:20.759 --> 06:47:22.319
Tamaron said.

06:47:22.380 --> 06:47:24.119
Don't ask me exactly how.

06:47:24.180 --> 06:47:27.360
She took a few deep breaths, closing her

06:47:27.360 --> 06:47:27.720
eyes.

06:47:27.779 --> 06:47:30.900
Dark green, dappled with sunlight and

06:47:30.900 --> 06:47:33.180
shadows, spread across her whole body

06:47:33.180 --> 06:47:35.400
until she matched the vines below her.

06:47:35.459 --> 06:47:39.599
I can't choose what color I am, Cameron

06:47:39.599 --> 06:47:40.560
explained.

06:47:40.619 --> 06:47:43.200
So if you asked me to make my scales red

06:47:43.200 --> 06:47:46.200
for instance, I couldn't do that, but if

06:47:46.200 --> 06:47:48.540
I relax, they automatically switched to

06:47:48.540 --> 06:47:49.080
whatever's around me.

06:47:49.139 --> 06:47:51.419
Fascinating.

06:47:51.479 --> 06:47:52.740
Glory said.

06:47:52.799 --> 06:47:55.680
More important, Tameron didn't look quite

06:47:55.680 --> 06:47:56.819
so terrified anymore.

06:47:56.880 --> 06:48:00.720
Fruit bat shuffled forward, swinging her

06:48:00.720 --> 06:48:02.819
bulky orchid necklace around so most of

06:48:02.819 --> 06:48:03.900
it hung down her back.

06:48:03.959 --> 06:48:07.799
An odd smell wafted forward with her, of

06:48:07.799 --> 06:48:09.479
decaying leaves underneath something

06:48:09.479 --> 06:48:10.439
sickly sweet.

06:48:10.500 --> 06:48:13.319
It wasn't as bad as the smell in the

06:48:13.319 --> 06:48:15.479
nightwing kingdom, but it wasn't pleasant

06:48:15.479 --> 06:48:15.659
either.

06:48:15.779 --> 06:48:18.419
So how does this contest work?

06:48:18.540 --> 06:48:19.799
Glory asked.

06:48:19.860 --> 06:48:21.900
And how can we be sure there's no

06:48:21.900 --> 06:48:23.099
cheating this time?

06:48:23.159 --> 06:48:26.159
She was gratified to see that Magnificent

06:48:26.159 --> 06:48:28.439
couldn't keep her scales from turning red

06:48:28.439 --> 06:48:31.979
making other dragons angry, was one skill

06:48:31.979 --> 06:48:33.599
glory already knew she was good at.

06:48:33.659 --> 06:48:36.840
She glanced over her shoulder at tsunami

06:48:36.840 --> 06:48:38.580
who had her fierce face on.

06:48:38.639 --> 06:48:40.619
She looked ready to charge into the

06:48:40.619 --> 06:48:42.779
arboretum and take on all 5 queens

06:48:42.779 --> 06:48:43.200
herself.

06:48:43.259 --> 06:48:45.180
Ahem.

06:48:45.240 --> 06:48:48.060
Handsome said hastily, clearing his

06:48:48.060 --> 06:48:48.900
throat a few times.

06:48:48.959 --> 06:48:51.119
Yes, the contest.

06:48:51.180 --> 06:48:54.479
For this member of the team, the queen

06:48:54.479 --> 06:48:56.340
has requested a flower hunt.

06:48:56.459 --> 06:49:00.900
Therefore early this morning, I hid a

06:49:00.900 --> 06:49:03.060
particular flower somewhere in this

06:49:03.060 --> 06:49:04.020
arboretum.

06:49:04.080 --> 06:49:08.459
The rare, majestic cinnamon orchid.

06:49:08.520 --> 06:49:12.360
Not the more common yellow variant, but

06:49:12.360 --> 06:49:14.700
the elusive red variety.

06:49:14.759 --> 06:49:19.740
Ooh, went all the watching rain wings.

06:49:19.799 --> 06:49:24.900
Whoever finds it 1st, naturally, will win

06:49:24.900 --> 06:49:26.040
said handsome.

06:49:26.099 --> 06:49:28.380
One flower?

06:49:28.439 --> 06:49:29.099
Glory thought.

06:49:29.159 --> 06:49:31.259
In this whole giant place.

06:49:31.319 --> 06:49:34.439
It could be anywhere, and she can't see.

06:49:34.500 --> 06:49:37.799
How can Tamarin even begin to look for

06:49:37.799 --> 06:49:38.040
it?

06:49:38.099 --> 06:49:40.799
Even if she could feel the difference

06:49:40.799 --> 06:49:43.259
between flowers, how will she know

06:49:43.259 --> 06:49:44.580
whether it's red or yellow?

06:49:44.639 --> 06:49:48.779
For the 1st time, Glory thought maybe she

06:49:48.779 --> 06:49:50.459
was going to lose this contest after

06:49:50.459 --> 06:49:50.759
all.

06:49:50.759 --> 06:49:53.159
Maybe she wouldn't be queen.

06:49:53.220 --> 06:49:55.979
She narrowed her eyes at magnificent and

06:49:55.979 --> 06:49:56.700
lashed her tail.

06:49:56.759 --> 06:49:58.139
Fine.

06:49:58.200 --> 06:50:00.659
I'll think of another way to rescue the

06:50:00.659 --> 06:50:02.580
rain wings from the night kingdom if I

06:50:02.580 --> 06:50:03.000
have to.

06:50:03.060 --> 06:50:05.340
Handsome spread his wings.

06:50:05.400 --> 06:50:07.139
You may begin.

06:50:07.259 --> 06:50:10.560
Fruit Bat leaped into action.

06:50:10.619 --> 06:50:12.360
Faster than glory would have expected

06:50:12.360 --> 06:50:13.259
from looking at her.

06:50:13.319 --> 06:50:15.540
Fruit bat started dashing around the

06:50:15.540 --> 06:50:17.639
circle, poking her nose into every

06:50:17.639 --> 06:50:18.659
crevice and pocket.

06:50:18.720 --> 06:50:21.360
She scrabbled up drifted piles of leaves

06:50:21.360 --> 06:50:23.400
and lifted bundles of vines.

06:50:23.459 --> 06:50:26.159
She nudged aside dragon tails that were

06:50:26.159 --> 06:50:27.959
draping over the edge of the platforms.

06:50:28.020 --> 06:50:30.659
She pounced on every glimmer of orangey

06:50:30.659 --> 06:50:33.240
red, startling quite a number of innocent

06:50:33.240 --> 06:50:34.139
birds and beetles.

06:50:34.200 --> 06:50:38.159
Meanwhile, Tamarin stood very still, right

06:50:38.159 --> 06:50:38.880
where she was.

06:50:38.939 --> 06:50:41.400
Her nostrils twitched.

06:50:41.459 --> 06:50:44.459
Her wings went up and down as she

06:50:44.459 --> 06:50:45.419
breathed deeply.

06:50:45.479 --> 06:50:49.200
After a few moments of this, Glory said

06:50:49.200 --> 06:50:54.299
um, shh, Kingachu said, she's busy.

06:50:54.360 --> 06:50:58.560
Could she be busy in a more busy looking

06:50:58.560 --> 06:50:58.979
way?

06:50:59.040 --> 06:51:00.540
Glory asked.

06:51:00.599 --> 06:51:03.299
Tamarin inhaled again and lifted her

06:51:03.299 --> 06:51:04.319
snout.

06:51:04.380 --> 06:51:06.659
Small feathers of flame flickered along

06:51:06.659 --> 06:51:09.479
her ruff, shaped like the flower she was

06:51:09.479 --> 06:51:09.840
looking for.

06:51:09.900 --> 06:51:12.240
She can smell it?

06:51:12.299 --> 06:51:14.279
Lori whispered to Kinkachu.

06:51:14.340 --> 06:51:16.080
Is that what she's trying to do?

06:51:16.139 --> 06:51:18.240
She will do it.

06:51:18.360 --> 06:51:20.520
Kinkaju promised fiercely.

06:51:20.580 --> 06:51:22.319
Her nose is amazing.

06:51:22.380 --> 06:51:26.759
I believe you, Lori said, but there have

06:51:26.759 --> 06:51:28.500
to be a 1000000 flowers within smelling

06:51:28.500 --> 06:51:30.900
distance right now, not to mention all

06:51:30.900 --> 06:51:33.180
these dragons and monkeys, and other

06:51:33.180 --> 06:51:35.459
things that smell much stronger than any

06:51:35.459 --> 06:51:36.060
one flower.

06:51:36.119 --> 06:51:37.979
There's no way she'll find it.

06:51:38.040 --> 06:51:42.000
You don't know Tamarind's nose, Kingichu

06:51:42.000 --> 06:51:42.240
said.

06:51:42.299 --> 06:51:43.439
Now shh.

06:51:43.500 --> 06:51:45.900
Gloria sat back and crawled her tail

06:51:45.900 --> 06:51:46.919
around her talons.

06:51:46.979 --> 06:51:48.779
There wasn't anything she could do now

06:51:48.779 --> 06:51:49.200
anyway.

06:51:49.259 --> 06:51:52.080
She badly wanted to start tearing up the

06:51:52.080 --> 06:51:54.360
arboretum, the way Fruit Bat was doing

06:51:54.360 --> 06:51:56.099
but she wasn't allowed to help.

06:51:56.159 --> 06:51:59.220
Is this what being queen would be like?

06:51:59.279 --> 06:52:01.979
Issuing orders and then sitting around

06:52:01.979 --> 06:52:03.840
waiting for dragons to carry them out?

06:52:03.900 --> 06:52:07.319
She thought of the other queens she'd met

06:52:07.319 --> 06:52:10.860
Queen Scarlet and Queen Coral preferred

06:52:10.860 --> 06:52:12.599
to have their minions do their dirty work

06:52:12.599 --> 06:52:15.360
but burn and blister both seemed rather

06:52:15.360 --> 06:52:16.319
claws on.

06:52:16.380 --> 06:52:18.240
Perhaps because they weren't really

06:52:18.240 --> 06:52:21.180
queens yet, or because they'd learned

06:52:21.180 --> 06:52:23.400
after years of war, that the only dragon

06:52:23.400 --> 06:52:25.319
you could really trust was yourself.

06:52:25.380 --> 06:52:28.259
Glory glanced at Sonny and Tsunami

06:52:28.259 --> 06:52:28.680
again.

06:52:28.740 --> 06:52:31.740
She did trust the other dragonettes, a

06:52:31.740 --> 06:52:33.060
little, in different ways.

06:52:33.119 --> 06:52:35.939
She trusted Sonny to at least try to do

06:52:35.939 --> 06:52:38.639
whatever was brave and right, even if she

06:52:38.639 --> 06:52:40.380
was too small to do it effectively.

06:52:40.439 --> 06:52:43.259
Starflight had neither courage nor

06:52:43.259 --> 06:52:45.599
fighting skills, but if glory ever needed

06:52:45.599 --> 06:52:47.819
to figure out something, she'd trust

06:52:47.819 --> 06:52:49.439
Starflight's brain in a second.

06:52:49.500 --> 06:52:51.659
That's why she wanted to talk to him

06:52:51.659 --> 06:52:53.220
about Scarlet before anyone else.

06:52:53.279 --> 06:52:56.520
She could trust tsunami to fight, tooth

06:52:56.520 --> 06:52:57.060
and claw.

06:52:57.119 --> 06:53:00.779
Really in almost any situation, including

06:53:00.779 --> 06:53:01.919
several where it would be quite

06:53:01.919 --> 06:53:02.700
inappropriate.

06:53:02.700 --> 06:53:06.840
And, of course, there was Clay, who would

06:53:06.840 --> 06:53:08.159
do anything to save his friends.

06:53:08.220 --> 06:53:11.819
She wished they were her team, instead of

06:53:11.819 --> 06:53:13.439
these rain wings she barely knew.

06:53:13.500 --> 06:53:16.799
As much as she liked Kinkachu, it was

06:53:16.799 --> 06:53:18.900
agonizing to feel this powerless over her

06:53:18.900 --> 06:53:19.560
own destiny.

06:53:19.619 --> 06:53:23.220
I'm the one who wants to be queen, I

06:53:23.220 --> 06:53:24.540
should be the only one who has to fight

06:53:24.540 --> 06:53:24.959
for it.

06:53:25.020 --> 06:53:28.500
Magnificent's eyes darted back and forth

06:53:28.500 --> 06:53:30.599
between Tamarin and Fruit Bat.

06:53:30.659 --> 06:53:33.119
When Tameron finally took a step forward

06:53:33.119 --> 06:53:36.060
the queen let out a hiss, and Fruit Bat

06:53:36.060 --> 06:53:38.099
whirled around to see what her competitor

06:53:38.099 --> 06:53:38.340
was doing.

06:53:38.400 --> 06:53:41.819
Tamarin, Gloria said quietly.

06:53:41.880 --> 06:53:44.880
If you know where it is, move fast

06:53:44.880 --> 06:53:47.340
because Fruit Bat is watching, and I

06:53:47.340 --> 06:53:48.659
think she'll try to beat you to it.

06:53:48.779 --> 06:53:51.659
The blind rain wing took another deep

06:53:51.659 --> 06:53:52.200
breath.

06:53:52.259 --> 06:53:54.900
Crouched, and launched herself into the

06:53:54.900 --> 06:53:55.139
air.

06:53:55.200 --> 06:53:58.259
She nearly overshot the platform she was

06:53:58.259 --> 06:54:01.020
aiming for, but her tail brushed it, and

06:54:01.020 --> 06:54:02.639
she swung back to land on it in a

06:54:02.639 --> 06:54:03.299
graceful motion.

06:54:03.360 --> 06:54:05.759
It was the start and finish racing

06:54:05.759 --> 06:54:08.759
platform used by Jambu and Exquisite, the

06:54:08.759 --> 06:54:10.619
one littered with bouquets of peach

06:54:10.619 --> 06:54:12.840
colored, star shaped blossoms.

06:54:12.900 --> 06:54:14.700
Fruit bat bolted after her.

06:54:14.759 --> 06:54:17.040
Tamarin quickly bowed her head and

06:54:17.040 --> 06:54:19.619
sniffed the bouquets, just as Fruit Bat

06:54:19.619 --> 06:54:21.959
landed heavily beside her, Tamarin

06:54:21.959 --> 06:54:23.819
snatched up one of the bundles, and

06:54:23.819 --> 06:54:25.680
pulled off the sloth for a ribbon that

06:54:25.680 --> 06:54:26.220
bound it together.

06:54:26.279 --> 06:54:30.060
The pale pink flowers fell away, revealing

06:54:30.060 --> 06:54:31.740
a flower hidden inside.

06:54:31.799 --> 06:54:33.959
It was shaped like a cluster of dragon

06:54:33.959 --> 06:54:36.419
claws, each glowing like a tongue of

06:54:36.419 --> 06:54:36.720
fire.

06:54:36.779 --> 06:54:40.080
Magnificent and fruit bat let out

06:54:40.080 --> 06:54:41.340
matching cries of rage.

06:54:41.400 --> 06:54:45.540
That sounds promising, Tamaron said with

06:54:45.540 --> 06:54:45.840
a smile.

06:54:45.959 --> 06:54:47.279
You did it!

06:54:47.340 --> 06:54:48.659
Kinkaju shouted.

06:54:48.720 --> 06:54:49.560
You found it.

06:54:49.619 --> 06:54:52.560
She poked Glory with her tail, beaming

06:54:52.560 --> 06:54:54.119
told you she could do it.

06:54:54.180 --> 06:54:56.520
If rain wings had fire.

06:54:56.580 --> 06:54:59.459
Glory was pretty sure magnificent would

06:54:59.459 --> 06:55:01.619
have had smoke coming out of her ears and

06:55:01.619 --> 06:55:02.459
nose.

06:55:02.520 --> 06:55:06.720
Nicely done, Glory said, as Tamron landed

06:55:06.720 --> 06:55:08.700
beside them again, clutching the flower

06:55:08.700 --> 06:55:11.220
in her claws, I'm really impressed.

06:55:11.340 --> 06:55:15.000
Glory sauntered over to the table and

06:55:15.000 --> 06:55:17.700
took the flower hunt nut, with an arch

06:55:17.700 --> 06:55:19.740
look at magnificent, she dropped it in

06:55:19.740 --> 06:55:23.639
her own coconut bowl, one to one, 3 more

06:55:23.639 --> 06:55:24.779
contests to go.

06:55:24.840 --> 06:55:27.240
And then she'd be queen.

06:55:27.360 --> 06:55:29.759
What should we do next?

06:55:29.819 --> 06:55:31.500
Glory asked magnificent.

06:55:31.560 --> 06:55:33.540
She was feeling a lot more confident

06:55:33.540 --> 06:55:33.779
now.

06:55:33.840 --> 06:55:36.299
How about the camouflage one?

06:55:36.360 --> 06:55:38.580
Magnificent bared her teeth.

06:55:38.639 --> 06:55:40.200
Sounds perfect.

06:55:40.259 --> 06:55:43.680
Have you ever been in a camouflage

06:55:43.680 --> 06:55:44.759
contest before?

06:55:44.880 --> 06:55:46.500
Handsome asked glory.

06:55:46.619 --> 06:55:50.759
Not precisely, Glory said, but I have had

06:55:50.759 --> 06:55:52.860
to use my camouflage to avoid dragons who

06:55:52.860 --> 06:55:53.400
want to kill me.

06:55:53.459 --> 06:55:55.439
So if you're asking whether I can handle

06:55:55.439 --> 06:55:57.360
the pressure, I'm going to go with yes.

06:55:57.419 --> 06:56:01.139
Actually, I was wondering if you knew the

06:56:01.139 --> 06:56:04.200
rules, Hansom said, hiding a smile.

06:56:04.259 --> 06:56:06.180
But they're not complicated.

06:56:06.240 --> 06:56:09.720
One of you hides first, somewhere within

06:56:09.720 --> 06:56:12.479
eyesight of this spot, then the other

06:56:12.479 --> 06:56:14.759
will search for you, and then you'll

06:56:14.759 --> 06:56:15.599
switch roles.

06:56:15.659 --> 06:56:18.119
I will judge who finds the other

06:56:18.119 --> 06:56:18.840
fastest.

06:56:18.959 --> 06:56:22.020
If it is too close to tell, we will try

06:56:22.020 --> 06:56:22.319
again.

06:56:22.439 --> 06:56:25.020
Got it, Glory said.

06:56:25.139 --> 06:56:29.400
Do you remember, Hanson began, turning to

06:56:29.400 --> 06:56:29.939
grandeur?

06:56:30.000 --> 06:56:32.340
Glory wondered which of them was older.

06:56:32.400 --> 06:56:35.099
They both seemed as ancient as the claws

06:56:35.099 --> 06:56:36.119
of the clouds mountains.

06:56:36.180 --> 06:56:38.819
Of course, I remember.

06:56:38.939 --> 06:56:40.500
Grandeur snapped.

06:56:40.560 --> 06:56:42.720
She drew herself up and hissed at the

06:56:42.720 --> 06:56:44.880
gathered crowd until they were all quiet

06:56:44.880 --> 06:56:46.139
listening.

06:56:46.200 --> 06:56:47.880
I remember everything.

06:56:47.939 --> 06:56:51.840
I remember when we actually needed our

06:56:51.840 --> 06:56:54.779
camouflage to protect ourselves from

06:56:54.779 --> 06:56:56.040
invading dragons.

06:56:56.099 --> 06:56:58.259
It wasn't a game back then.

06:56:58.319 --> 06:57:00.840
It was what we had to do to survive.

06:57:00.900 --> 06:57:04.020
Enough boring stories.

06:57:04.080 --> 06:57:07.200
Magnificent commanded, earning herself

06:57:07.200 --> 06:57:08.099
another glare.

06:57:08.159 --> 06:57:10.680
Grandeur, hush up until it's your

06:57:10.680 --> 06:57:11.279
contest.

06:57:11.340 --> 06:57:12.900
I'll hide first.

06:57:13.020 --> 06:57:15.900
Handsome tied a long, fat leaf around

06:57:15.900 --> 06:57:16.919
glory's eyes.

06:57:16.979 --> 06:57:19.139
As darkness settled around her.

06:57:19.200 --> 06:57:21.240
She thought that this must be what it was

06:57:21.240 --> 06:57:22.799
like for Tamarind all the time.

06:57:22.860 --> 06:57:26.040
She could remember only one story about a

06:57:26.040 --> 06:57:28.560
blind dragon in the scrolls, and it was

06:57:28.560 --> 06:57:30.900
from long ago, before the scorching.

06:57:30.959 --> 06:57:34.200
A moment later, the blindfold was lifted

06:57:34.200 --> 06:57:34.500
away.

06:57:34.560 --> 06:57:37.560
The curious faces of 100s of rain wings

06:57:37.560 --> 06:57:38.279
filled her vision.

06:57:38.400 --> 06:57:42.840
You may begin, said the old dragon with a

06:57:42.840 --> 06:57:43.740
nod.

06:57:43.799 --> 06:57:45.779
Glory blinked and turned in a circle

06:57:45.779 --> 06:57:47.279
searching for clues.

06:57:47.340 --> 06:57:49.500
Magnificent had vanished very

06:57:49.500 --> 06:57:50.099
thoroughly.

06:57:50.159 --> 06:57:53.220
Her small crown of white flowers lay

06:57:53.220 --> 06:57:55.259
abandoned on the vines.

06:57:55.319 --> 06:57:57.119
There was no sign of her gold tipped

06:57:57.119 --> 06:57:59.580
purple scales, and none of the hammocks

06:57:59.580 --> 06:58:01.380
around the arena had a sudden unusual

06:58:01.380 --> 06:58:02.220
bulge in them.

06:58:02.279 --> 06:58:04.319
Where could she be?

06:58:04.380 --> 06:58:07.979
Where would I hide if I were a

06:58:07.979 --> 06:58:10.560
particularly forgetful, spectacularly

06:58:10.560 --> 06:58:11.759
lazy rain wing?

06:58:11.819 --> 06:58:14.520
She didn't think magnificent was the type

06:58:14.520 --> 06:58:17.459
to climb trees, or hang by her tail if

06:58:17.459 --> 06:58:18.779
there was somewhere she could lie down

06:58:18.779 --> 06:58:19.619
comfortably instead.

06:58:19.680 --> 06:58:22.439
And most of the platforms and walkways

06:58:22.439 --> 06:58:24.840
were too crowded with dragons for her to

06:58:24.840 --> 06:58:27.599
squeeze in their easily, which gave glory

06:58:27.599 --> 06:58:27.959
an idea.

06:58:28.020 --> 06:58:30.659
She turned to study the watching rain

06:58:30.659 --> 06:58:31.200
wings.

06:58:31.259 --> 06:58:33.360
Some of them might have seen where

06:58:33.360 --> 06:58:36.180
magnificent hid, and all of them had been

06:58:36.180 --> 06:58:37.919
playing this kind of hide and seek their

06:58:37.919 --> 06:58:38.279
whole lives.

06:58:38.340 --> 06:58:41.819
They must be scanning the area too, trying

06:58:41.819 --> 06:58:42.479
to find her first.

06:58:42.540 --> 06:58:45.779
She noticed that exquisite and fruit bat

06:58:45.779 --> 06:58:48.240
were staring straight up at a nearby tree

06:58:48.240 --> 06:58:50.099
swathed in fuzzy moss.

06:58:50.159 --> 06:58:52.919
They were staring at it a little too hard

06:58:52.919 --> 06:58:54.959
as if they were hoping glory would notice

06:58:54.959 --> 06:58:55.380
that they were.

06:58:55.439 --> 06:58:58.860
Fruit bat nudged grandeur, and the

06:58:58.860 --> 06:59:00.659
stately old dragon gave her a look of

06:59:00.659 --> 06:59:01.020
disgust.

06:59:01.139 --> 06:59:03.959
Then Glory caught a couple of rain wings

06:59:03.959 --> 06:59:05.639
glancing in the direction of a fruit

06:59:05.639 --> 06:59:08.220
stand on the far side of the arena.

06:59:08.279 --> 06:59:10.979
They narrowed their eyes at it, then

06:59:10.979 --> 06:59:12.419
leaned in to whisper to each other.

06:59:12.479 --> 06:59:15.540
Worth a look, Glory thought.

06:59:15.599 --> 06:59:17.939
She flew across the arena to the fruit

06:59:17.939 --> 06:59:18.419
stand.

06:59:18.479 --> 06:59:21.720
It was a wooden platform, with low walls

06:59:21.720 --> 06:59:24.360
that were built to also be tables, most

06:59:24.360 --> 06:59:26.880
of them covered with mangoes, pineapples

06:59:26.939 --> 06:59:29.400
the red sticky spheres, and the star

06:59:29.400 --> 06:59:30.599
shaped green fruits.

06:59:30.659 --> 06:59:33.360
Crowded bunches of bananas hung from the

06:59:33.360 --> 06:59:34.080
branches overhead.

06:59:34.139 --> 06:59:36.720
She swept her tail across the floor of

06:59:36.720 --> 06:59:39.840
the platform, then studied the tables, but

06:59:39.840 --> 06:59:41.279
she couldn't see any sign of a dragon

06:59:41.279 --> 06:59:42.060
hiding anywhere.

06:59:42.119 --> 06:59:44.939
She looked up and poked the dangling

06:59:44.939 --> 06:59:45.840
banana bunches.

06:59:45.900 --> 06:59:48.720
Finally, she jumped over one of the walls

06:59:48.720 --> 06:59:50.819
and flew up above the bananas.

06:59:50.880 --> 06:59:52.919
There was something a little odd about

06:59:52.919 --> 06:59:55.380
the way some of them were hanging, as if

06:59:55.380 --> 06:59:56.939
something heavy were lying on top of

06:59:56.939 --> 06:59:57.119
them.

06:59:57.180 --> 06:59:59.340
It was eerie.

06:59:59.459 --> 07:00:02.279
All she could see were shadows and light

07:00:02.279 --> 07:00:04.860
green leaves and bright yellow bananas

07:00:04.860 --> 07:00:07.560
but when she reached out, her claws

07:00:07.560 --> 07:00:10.139
brushed against dragon scales, and the

07:00:10.139 --> 07:00:12.360
indignant hiss that came from them, told

07:00:12.360 --> 07:00:13.799
her she'd found what she was looking

07:00:13.799 --> 07:00:13.979
for.

07:00:14.099 --> 07:00:18.240
Your majesty, Glory said, with a polite

07:00:18.240 --> 07:00:18.599
bow.

07:00:18.659 --> 07:00:21.900
Very impressive camouflage, she added

07:00:21.900 --> 07:00:22.380
honestly.

07:00:22.500 --> 07:00:25.080
Let's see what you can do.

07:00:25.200 --> 07:00:26.700
Magnificent grumbled.

07:00:26.759 --> 07:00:28.860
Her scales shifting back to purple.

07:00:28.919 --> 07:00:31.380
They returned to the center of the arena

07:00:31.380 --> 07:00:33.659
as the rain wings all applauded.

07:00:33.720 --> 07:00:36.360
It took glory a moment to realize they

07:00:36.360 --> 07:00:37.259
were applauding for her.

07:00:37.319 --> 07:00:39.900
She hoped that meant she had found the

07:00:39.900 --> 07:00:40.799
queen fairly quickly.

07:00:40.860 --> 07:00:43.500
Now she just had to hide even better than

07:00:43.500 --> 07:00:44.400
magnificent had.

07:00:44.459 --> 07:00:47.759
Handsome stepped up to tie the blindfold

07:00:47.759 --> 07:00:48.959
around magnificent's eyes.

07:00:49.080 --> 07:00:51.659
Glory let her scales shift into the

07:00:51.659 --> 07:00:52.860
greens of the vines below her.

07:00:52.919 --> 07:00:55.020
She didn't want anyone to see where she

07:00:55.020 --> 07:00:57.240
went. especially the other queens.

07:00:57.299 --> 07:01:00.180
Her 1st idea had been to go straight up

07:01:00.180 --> 07:01:02.819
and blend into the sky overhead, but to

07:01:02.819 --> 07:01:04.619
stay aloft, she would have had to keep

07:01:04.619 --> 07:01:06.659
her wings moving, and she was worried

07:01:06.659 --> 07:01:08.520
that Magnificent might feel the breeze.

07:01:08.639 --> 07:01:11.099
So instead, she headed for the tree

07:01:11.099 --> 07:01:13.259
exquisite and fruit bat had been staring

07:01:13.259 --> 07:01:13.500
at.

07:01:13.560 --> 07:01:16.500
She swarmed up the side of it, feeling

07:01:16.500 --> 07:01:19.020
the shaggy moss squish below her talons.

07:01:19.080 --> 07:01:21.720
Her scales had changed instantly into the

07:01:21.720 --> 07:01:23.639
dark brown and yellowish green of the

07:01:23.639 --> 07:01:24.479
moss covered tree.

07:01:24.599 --> 07:01:27.360
Once she thought she was high enough, she

07:01:27.360 --> 07:01:29.159
twisted around so she could see

07:01:29.159 --> 07:01:30.299
everything below her.

07:01:30.360 --> 07:01:32.279
Then she flattened herself against the

07:01:32.279 --> 07:01:35.340
trunk and concentrated, adding the shape

07:01:35.340 --> 07:01:37.619
of a tiny blue tree frog on her back for

07:01:37.619 --> 07:01:39.900
extra camouflage, which was a trick

07:01:39.900 --> 07:01:41.220
mangrove had taught her.

07:01:41.279 --> 07:01:44.040
Down below, she heard handsome tail

07:01:44.040 --> 07:01:45.659
magnificent that she could start

07:01:45.659 --> 07:01:45.900
looking.

07:01:46.020 --> 07:01:48.900
The queen's eyes popped open, and she

07:01:48.900 --> 07:01:50.939
turned immediately to the other queens.

07:01:50.939 --> 07:01:53.819
Exquisite and fruit bat lifted their

07:01:53.819 --> 07:01:54.840
wings in the fuddlement.

07:01:54.959 --> 07:01:57.360
Grandeur yawned coldly.

07:01:57.419 --> 07:02:00.840
Magnificent spun in a circle, peering at

07:02:00.840 --> 07:02:01.139
everything.

07:02:01.200 --> 07:02:03.720
She let out a small hiss of frustration

07:02:03.720 --> 07:02:05.279
then gathered her wings.

07:02:05.340 --> 07:02:09.119
Suddenly, she bared her fangs and charged

07:02:09.119 --> 07:02:11.279
toward the edge of the circle where Sonny

07:02:11.279 --> 07:02:11.700
was standing.

07:02:11.759 --> 07:02:14.340
She wouldn't dare hurt my friends.

07:02:14.400 --> 07:02:17.520
But glory felt herself flinch as Sunny

07:02:17.520 --> 07:02:18.180
jumped back.

07:02:18.240 --> 07:02:21.240
At the same moment, Silver leaped off

07:02:21.240 --> 07:02:24.060
Sonny's back with a yelp of alarm, and

07:02:24.060 --> 07:02:25.680
bolted toward the tree where Glory was

07:02:25.680 --> 07:02:26.040
hiding.

07:02:26.099 --> 07:02:29.159
Magnificent saw where the sloth was going

07:02:29.159 --> 07:02:31.919
shot past her, and slammed into the tree

07:02:31.919 --> 07:02:34.200
trunk, nearly jarring glory loose.

07:02:34.259 --> 07:02:36.900
The queen scrambled up the tree so fast

07:02:36.900 --> 07:02:39.000
she stepped on Glory's wings before

07:02:39.000 --> 07:02:40.319
realizing she'd found her.

07:02:40.380 --> 07:02:42.419
With a triumphant yell.

07:02:42.479 --> 07:02:44.819
She backed up and poked glory in the

07:02:44.819 --> 07:02:45.240
snout.

07:02:45.299 --> 07:02:46.619
Found you.

07:02:46.680 --> 07:02:48.299
Magnificent crowed.

07:02:48.360 --> 07:02:50.700
Silver caught up and flung herself into

07:02:50.700 --> 07:02:52.319
Glory's arms, shivering.

07:02:52.439 --> 07:02:55.740
Glory swung onto a branch, so she could

07:02:55.740 --> 07:02:57.900
hold the sloth to her chest and stroke

07:02:57.900 --> 07:02:58.619
its fur.

07:02:58.680 --> 07:03:00.360
Did you think that was funny?

07:03:00.419 --> 07:03:03.900
Glory asked magnificent, scaring a

07:03:03.900 --> 07:03:04.979
harmless sloth like that.

07:03:05.040 --> 07:03:07.979
From the murmurs and shocked expressions

07:03:07.979 --> 07:03:10.560
on the faces below them, she guessed this

07:03:10.560 --> 07:03:12.720
wasn't a very popular way to treat one of

07:03:12.720 --> 07:03:13.740
the rain wing pets.

07:03:13.799 --> 07:03:17.819
She'll survive, magnificent said, and

07:03:17.819 --> 07:03:18.659
here's the important part.

07:03:18.779 --> 07:03:20.099
I won.

07:03:20.220 --> 07:03:22.919
Glory looked down at handsome with a

07:03:22.919 --> 07:03:23.639
sinking feeling.

07:03:23.700 --> 07:03:26.759
He spread his talons in a, What can I

07:03:26.759 --> 07:03:27.060
do?

07:03:27.060 --> 07:03:27.779
gesture.

07:03:27.840 --> 07:03:31.380
The Queen is correct, he said.

07:03:31.439 --> 07:03:33.779
Magnificent wins this round.

07:03:33.900 --> 07:03:38.639
Chapter 32.

07:03:38.819 --> 07:03:43.799
Oh, look, Magnificent said cheerfully

07:03:43.799 --> 07:03:46.080
pointing to the glint of sunlight on

07:03:46.080 --> 07:03:47.580
wings flapping through the trees.

07:03:47.639 --> 07:03:49.799
The fruit gatherers are coming back.

07:03:49.860 --> 07:03:52.139
She flew back to the center of the

07:03:52.139 --> 07:03:54.479
arboretum and snatched one of the nuts

07:03:54.479 --> 07:03:57.360
off the mahogany table, 2 to one.

07:03:57.419 --> 07:03:59.939
Wasn't that cheating?

07:03:59.939 --> 07:04:02.639
Sonny called, as Glory glided back down

07:04:02.639 --> 07:04:03.540
to her team.

07:04:03.599 --> 07:04:06.779
Kinkaju had furious red stripes marching

07:04:06.779 --> 07:04:09.299
along her scales, and Jambu was back to

07:04:09.299 --> 07:04:10.080
blue gray again.

07:04:10.139 --> 07:04:12.779
Glory wondered if her brother had more

07:04:12.779 --> 07:04:13.619
than 2 moods.

07:04:13.740 --> 07:04:17.639
That was totally cheating, tsunami

07:04:17.639 --> 07:04:18.119
shouted.

07:04:18.180 --> 07:04:19.919
You can't let her get away with that.

07:04:19.979 --> 07:04:21.720
Boo, hiss.

07:04:21.779 --> 07:04:25.619
Silence them, Magnificent said to Hanson

07:04:25.619 --> 07:04:26.279
with a frown.

07:04:26.340 --> 07:04:28.259
He spread his wings and cleared his

07:04:28.259 --> 07:04:28.560
throat.

07:04:28.619 --> 07:04:32.400
Nothing in the rules forbids what the

07:04:32.400 --> 07:04:34.439
queen did, he announced.

07:04:34.500 --> 07:04:37.740
She is the winner. officially.

07:04:37.799 --> 07:04:39.959
If not in spirit.

07:04:40.020 --> 07:04:44.159
Magnificent glared at him, while Mangrove

07:04:44.159 --> 07:04:45.900
and Dazzling swooped down from the

07:04:45.900 --> 07:04:46.319
trees.

07:04:46.439 --> 07:04:49.380
Glory was too dazed to chime in.

07:04:49.439 --> 07:04:52.020
The others might call it cheating, but as

07:04:52.020 --> 07:04:54.540
far as she was concerned, Magnificent had

07:04:54.540 --> 07:04:56.580
only found a trick to reveal Glory's

07:04:56.580 --> 07:04:59.040
hiding place, the same way Glory had used

07:04:59.040 --> 07:05:01.500
the rain wing audience for clues.

07:05:01.560 --> 07:05:03.419
So glory had really lost.

07:05:03.479 --> 07:05:05.759
She'd lost.

07:05:05.819 --> 07:05:08.639
She couldn't pay attention to the sorting

07:05:08.639 --> 07:05:11.279
and counting going on, as mangrove and

07:05:11.279 --> 07:05:13.500
dazzling spilled fruits of all shapes and

07:05:13.500 --> 07:05:14.819
sizes across the greenery.

07:05:14.880 --> 07:05:17.759
Hanson picked each one up, muttered over

07:05:17.759 --> 07:05:19.680
it for a moment, and set it in a pile.

07:05:19.799 --> 07:05:23.580
If I were competing alone, it would be

07:05:23.580 --> 07:05:24.479
over by now.

07:05:24.599 --> 07:05:26.159
Glory realized.

07:05:26.220 --> 07:05:28.979
She would have lost the throne in a

07:05:28.979 --> 07:05:30.659
direct contest with magnificent.

07:05:30.720 --> 07:05:34.080
If she won it now, it would be only

07:05:34.080 --> 07:05:36.119
because the other rain wings made it

07:05:36.119 --> 07:05:38.880
happen, Tamarin, who didn't know her at

07:05:38.880 --> 07:05:41.580
all, Mangrove and Kinkaju.

07:05:41.580 --> 07:05:45.119
If they could do it, Kinkaju's eyes were

07:05:45.119 --> 07:05:47.580
fixed on mangrove's fruit pile, she

07:05:47.580 --> 07:05:49.380
fidgeted with her tail and counted along

07:05:49.380 --> 07:05:49.979
under her breath.

07:05:50.099 --> 07:05:53.880
Handsome examined the last fruit, a dark

07:05:53.880 --> 07:05:56.159
blue prickled ball that oozed bright

07:05:56.159 --> 07:05:57.479
green juice when he poked it.

07:05:57.540 --> 07:06:00.419
He nodded, and placed it on mangroves

07:06:00.419 --> 07:06:00.840
pile.

07:06:00.900 --> 07:06:05.279
Kinkajoo shot Glory a delighted look. 17

07:06:05.279 --> 07:06:07.979
to 16, said handsome.

07:06:08.040 --> 07:06:10.680
The winner is mangrove.

07:06:10.740 --> 07:06:12.060
What?

07:06:12.180 --> 07:06:14.159
Shrilled magnificent.

07:06:14.220 --> 07:06:16.860
She whipped around to glare at Dazzling

07:06:16.860 --> 07:06:19.380
who had yellow speckles around her mouth

07:06:19.380 --> 07:06:22.020
and a trail of green splatters down her

07:06:22.020 --> 07:06:22.319
chest.

07:06:22.380 --> 07:06:25.080
You ate some of them?

07:06:25.139 --> 07:06:29.040
I know there were 19 there when I. She

07:06:29.040 --> 07:06:30.000
stopped abruptly.

07:06:30.060 --> 07:06:33.060
Sorry, dazzling muttered.

07:06:33.119 --> 07:06:34.979
I thought 16 would be enough.

07:06:35.040 --> 07:06:38.340
Well, you thought wrong.

07:06:38.459 --> 07:06:40.259
Magnificent growled.

07:06:40.319 --> 07:06:43.319
Excuse me, said Handsome.

07:06:43.380 --> 07:06:47.099
Did you say there were 19 there?

07:06:47.159 --> 07:06:50.880
There was an awkward pause as the 2

07:06:50.880 --> 07:06:52.860
queens glared at each other.

07:06:52.919 --> 07:06:55.020
Magnificent flicked her tail and looked

07:06:55.020 --> 07:06:56.400
down her nose at handsome.

07:06:56.400 --> 07:06:58.860
Are you accusing me of something?

07:06:58.919 --> 07:07:01.020
She asked coldly.

07:07:01.080 --> 07:07:02.639
I am?

07:07:02.700 --> 07:07:04.080
Kingaju blurted.

07:07:04.139 --> 07:07:06.240
You collected fruits and stashed them

07:07:06.240 --> 07:07:07.080
somewhere ahead of time.

07:07:07.200 --> 07:07:10.740
Ludicrous, said the queen.

07:07:10.799 --> 07:07:13.380
The red flickers along her wings vanished

07:07:13.380 --> 07:07:13.919
abruptly.

07:07:13.979 --> 07:07:16.200
And impossible to prove.

07:07:16.319 --> 07:07:20.040
It occurred to glory that magnificent

07:07:20.040 --> 07:07:22.500
might have chosen to be purple today, so

07:07:22.500 --> 07:07:24.479
that no one would spot any shimmers of

07:07:24.479 --> 07:07:25.439
guilt in her scales.

07:07:25.500 --> 07:07:29.580
Clever, she thought, glancing down at her

07:07:29.580 --> 07:07:29.819
own.

07:07:29.939 --> 07:07:33.000
The yellow had faded a little, and small

07:07:33.000 --> 07:07:34.919
gray clouds were gathering around her

07:07:34.919 --> 07:07:36.479
shoulder blades and wing tips.

07:07:36.599 --> 07:07:40.139
Doesn't matter anyway, Dazzling pointed

07:07:40.139 --> 07:07:41.040
out to Kinkachu.

07:07:41.099 --> 07:07:42.240
You won.

07:07:42.299 --> 07:07:45.419
Kinkatu jabbed Glory with her tail, and

07:07:45.419 --> 07:07:46.919
Glory snapped back into focus.

07:07:46.979 --> 07:07:48.479
There was still a chance.

07:07:48.540 --> 07:07:51.180
Now they were tied, and there was one

07:07:51.180 --> 07:07:52.080
contest left.

07:07:52.139 --> 07:07:55.560
It matters if you're planning to cheat

07:07:55.560 --> 07:07:57.599
again, she said sharply.

07:07:57.659 --> 07:08:00.419
That won't be necessary.

07:08:00.479 --> 07:08:04.020
Wind rustled through the leaves as

07:08:04.020 --> 07:08:06.479
grandeur slid majestically between glory

07:08:06.479 --> 07:08:07.319
and magnificent.

07:08:07.380 --> 07:08:10.799
Her bones creaked like ancient forests

07:08:10.799 --> 07:08:13.380
and the silver cast of her scales made

07:08:13.380 --> 07:08:14.819
her look as if she were reflecting

07:08:14.819 --> 07:08:16.560
moonlight instead of sunlight.

07:08:16.619 --> 07:08:19.020
She wasn't like the other queens.

07:08:19.080 --> 07:08:22.139
In fact, she wasn't like any other dragon

07:08:22.139 --> 07:08:22.799
in the village.

07:08:22.919 --> 07:08:25.560
Glory thought grandeur might be the only

07:08:25.560 --> 07:08:28.860
rain wing who actually looked, moved, and

07:08:28.860 --> 07:08:30.180
sounded like a real queen.

07:08:30.240 --> 07:08:33.299
She arched her neck and peered down at

07:08:33.299 --> 07:08:33.959
Kinkaju.

07:08:34.020 --> 07:08:37.799
I can crush this little creature easily

07:08:37.799 --> 07:08:38.459
on my own.

07:08:38.520 --> 07:08:44.040
We'll see, Kinkaju said bravely, but

07:08:44.040 --> 07:08:46.020
anxious streaks of green flickered in her

07:08:46.020 --> 07:08:46.380
rough.

07:08:46.439 --> 07:08:49.080
This is asking too much of her.

07:08:49.200 --> 07:08:50.700
Glory worried.

07:08:50.759 --> 07:08:53.880
Kinkaju was barely half grandeur's size

07:08:53.880 --> 07:08:55.799
with hardly any training.

07:08:55.860 --> 07:08:58.380
The night wings had been so underwhelmed

07:08:58.380 --> 07:09:00.299
by her venom, that they hadn't even

07:09:00.299 --> 07:09:01.380
bothered binding her mouth.

07:09:01.439 --> 07:09:03.479
How could she possibly win?

07:09:03.540 --> 07:09:06.540
Handsome beckoned the 2 dragons into the

07:09:06.540 --> 07:09:07.740
center of the arboretum?

07:09:07.799 --> 07:09:11.340
Standard venom practice rules apply?

07:09:11.400 --> 07:09:12.240
He said.

07:09:12.360 --> 07:09:15.479
Take the utmost caution to hit no living

07:09:15.479 --> 07:09:18.840
creature. will be testing distance and

07:09:18.840 --> 07:09:19.439
targeting.

07:09:19.500 --> 07:09:21.659
Who'd like to go first?

07:09:21.720 --> 07:09:25.319
I, said grandeur.

07:09:25.380 --> 07:09:28.860
She eyed handsome and his 2 helpers as

07:09:28.860 --> 07:09:31.080
they rolled a long polished plank of wood

07:09:31.080 --> 07:09:31.979
across the vines.

07:09:32.040 --> 07:09:35.520
It was as wide as 5 talon prints and 4

07:09:35.520 --> 07:09:38.099
times as long, with small measurement

07:09:38.099 --> 07:09:39.360
marks all the way along it.

07:09:39.419 --> 07:09:42.180
One end stopped at grandeur's front

07:09:42.180 --> 07:09:42.659
talons.

07:09:42.720 --> 07:09:45.659
She stretched her neck and jaw, while the

07:09:45.659 --> 07:09:47.340
rain wings scurried out of the way

07:09:47.340 --> 07:09:49.619
leaving the plank laid out in front of

07:09:49.619 --> 07:09:50.759
her like a welcoming carpet.

07:09:50.819 --> 07:09:54.659
Whenever your hansom started.

07:09:54.720 --> 07:09:57.840
Grandeur's mouth snapped open, and a

07:09:57.840 --> 07:10:00.360
spray of black venom shot out, the

07:10:00.360 --> 07:10:02.220
droplets spattered on the wood near the

07:10:02.220 --> 07:10:04.439
far end of the plank, sizzling and

07:10:04.439 --> 07:10:06.180
burning small holes where they fell.

07:10:06.240 --> 07:10:09.180
The watching dragons all ooed

07:10:09.180 --> 07:10:09.840
admiringly.

07:10:09.900 --> 07:10:13.139
I'm guessing that's pretty impressive

07:10:13.139 --> 07:10:15.000
Glory said to Mangrove.

07:10:15.119 --> 07:10:17.279
His sigh answered her question.

07:10:17.340 --> 07:10:20.040
Grandeur stepped aside with a polite

07:10:20.040 --> 07:10:21.360
gesture at Kinkaju.

07:10:21.419 --> 07:10:23.279
The little dragonette stepped up

07:10:23.279 --> 07:10:25.680
nervously, opened her mouth as wide as

07:10:25.680 --> 07:10:28.380
she could, and shot a tiny jet of venom

07:10:28.380 --> 07:10:28.860
at the plank.

07:10:28.979 --> 07:10:31.740
It landed barely a quarter of the way

07:10:31.740 --> 07:10:34.259
between her claws and grandeur's drops.

07:10:34.319 --> 07:10:36.060
Glory's heart sank.

07:10:36.119 --> 07:10:38.459
Mangrove dropped his head into his front

07:10:38.459 --> 07:10:39.720
talons with a groan.

07:10:39.840 --> 07:10:42.959
Kinkaju turned to glory with a

07:10:42.959 --> 07:10:43.919
heartbroken expression.

07:10:43.979 --> 07:10:46.799
There's still the targeting part.

07:10:46.919 --> 07:10:48.659
Jambu said, hopefully.

07:10:48.720 --> 07:10:51.240
He patted the little dragonette on the

07:10:51.240 --> 07:10:51.419
back.

07:10:51.479 --> 07:10:53.819
The helpers were already dragging out a

07:10:53.819 --> 07:10:56.459
kind of easel, painted with 3 yellow and

07:10:56.459 --> 07:10:57.119
white circles.

07:10:57.240 --> 07:10:59.400
What if I fail?

07:10:59.459 --> 07:11:01.200
Kinkachu said to Glory.

07:11:01.319 --> 07:11:03.119
All those dragons.

07:11:03.180 --> 07:11:05.279
It'll be my fault if we never see them

07:11:05.279 --> 07:11:06.299
again.

07:11:06.360 --> 07:11:08.159
It'll be my fault that you're not queen.

07:11:08.220 --> 07:11:12.959
Stop that, Lori said, placing one talent

07:11:12.959 --> 07:11:14.040
over kinkachoos.

07:11:14.099 --> 07:11:16.619
I lost my own contest, remember?

07:11:16.680 --> 07:11:19.799
It's my fault more than anyone's, but I

07:11:19.799 --> 07:11:20.819
will be queen one day.

07:11:20.880 --> 07:11:23.819
And in the meanwhile, She caught

07:11:23.819 --> 07:11:25.560
Mangrove's eye to make sure he was

07:11:25.560 --> 07:11:25.799
listening.

07:11:25.860 --> 07:11:29.220
We'll get orchid and the other rain wings

07:11:29.220 --> 07:11:30.779
back, no matter what it takes.

07:11:30.840 --> 07:11:33.959
Maybe I won't have an army, but we'll

07:11:33.959 --> 07:11:35.580
make a rescue mission out of my friends

07:11:35.580 --> 07:11:37.500
and anyone else who's willing to go.

07:11:37.560 --> 07:11:39.900
So don't think about that right now.

07:11:39.959 --> 07:11:43.380
All I can ask is that you try your best.

07:11:43.439 --> 07:11:46.259
And I know I don't even have to ask

07:11:46.259 --> 07:11:48.299
because you're the kind of dragon who

07:11:48.299 --> 07:11:48.840
always does.

07:11:48.900 --> 07:11:50.939
That's true.

07:11:51.000 --> 07:11:52.560
Kinkachu said.

07:11:52.680 --> 07:11:54.840
I am that kind of dragon.

07:11:54.900 --> 07:11:57.000
She squared her shoulders.

07:11:57.060 --> 07:11:58.319
I will.

07:11:58.380 --> 07:12:00.060
That's what I'm going to do.

07:12:00.119 --> 07:12:03.659
Glory glanced up, and realized that

07:12:03.659 --> 07:12:04.919
grandeur had been listening to.

07:12:05.040 --> 07:12:08.700
The old queen turned around and casually

07:12:08.700 --> 07:12:10.680
shot a spray of her venom at the painted

07:12:10.680 --> 07:12:11.580
board.

07:12:11.639 --> 07:12:13.979
It landed precisely in the center of the

07:12:13.979 --> 07:12:14.759
1st circle.

07:12:14.819 --> 07:12:17.939
Magnificent gave glory a triumphant

07:12:17.939 --> 07:12:18.299
smile.

07:12:18.360 --> 07:12:21.479
It would have been really nice to wipe

07:12:21.479 --> 07:12:23.099
that smile off her face.

07:12:23.159 --> 07:12:25.439
And one day, I will.

07:12:25.500 --> 07:12:28.139
I will be queen of this tribe.

07:12:28.259 --> 07:12:29.819
That's what I'm meant for.

07:12:29.880 --> 07:12:31.139
I'm sure of it.

07:12:31.200 --> 07:12:35.340
Kinkaju stepped up beside grandeur, opened

07:12:35.340 --> 07:12:37.619
her mouth, and sprayed her venom at the

07:12:37.619 --> 07:12:38.220
circles.

07:12:38.520 --> 07:12:40.680
The drops splashed right on top of

07:12:40.680 --> 07:12:43.439
grandeurs, and a hissing sound came from

07:12:43.439 --> 07:12:45.360
the board as the wood melted a little

07:12:45.360 --> 07:12:45.959
more.

07:12:46.139 --> 07:12:48.299
The older rain wing made a sound of

07:12:48.299 --> 07:12:50.819
approval and padded Kinkaju's head.

07:12:50.880 --> 07:12:53.880
Then she tilted her head just a little

07:12:53.880 --> 07:12:56.880
and shot a black jet directly into the

07:12:56.880 --> 07:12:58.139
center of the 2nd circle.

07:12:58.259 --> 07:13:02.279
Kingaju took a deep breath and did the

07:13:02.279 --> 07:13:02.459
same.

07:13:02.520 --> 07:13:05.580
More sizzling and smoking came from the

07:13:05.580 --> 07:13:05.759
wood.

07:13:05.819 --> 07:13:07.680
Don't get excited.

07:13:07.740 --> 07:13:09.540
Glory told herself.

07:13:09.659 --> 07:13:11.159
Although she couldn't help feeling

07:13:11.159 --> 07:13:12.659
impressed with Kinkaju.

07:13:12.720 --> 07:13:15.060
She knew for a fact that she wouldn't

07:13:15.060 --> 07:13:17.520
have been able to aim that precisely, but

07:13:17.520 --> 07:13:19.560
if the 2 dragons tied on this part of the

07:13:19.560 --> 07:13:21.720
challenge, grandeur would still win

07:13:21.720 --> 07:13:23.639
because of the distance part.

07:13:23.700 --> 07:13:28.080
Practice a gracious in defeat face, and

07:13:28.080 --> 07:13:30.180
then get ready to study like life depends

07:13:30.180 --> 07:13:32.220
on it so I can try this again.

07:13:32.279 --> 07:13:34.380
I wonder how long I have to wait between

07:13:34.380 --> 07:13:35.040
challenges.

07:13:35.099 --> 07:13:39.119
Grandeur opened her mouth, and then a

07:13:39.119 --> 07:13:41.759
sloth tumbled out of the trees, landing

07:13:41.759 --> 07:13:42.599
in front of the board.

07:13:42.720 --> 07:13:45.840
Kingaju leaped to shove it out of the way

07:13:45.840 --> 07:13:49.919
and time seemed to slow down, so glory

07:13:49.919 --> 07:13:53.279
could watch, each drop of venom sail in

07:13:53.279 --> 07:13:57.959
an unhurried arc to land, splash, splash

07:13:57.959 --> 07:14:02.159
right, on Kingaju's wing.

07:14:02.279 --> 07:14:06.599
Chapter 33.

07:14:06.840 --> 07:14:10.799
All around the arboretum, rain wings

07:14:10.799 --> 07:14:11.880
started screaming.

07:14:11.939 --> 07:14:14.700
Kinkachu collapsed in a ball of scales

07:14:14.700 --> 07:14:18.299
that went instantly white with pain

07:14:18.299 --> 07:14:20.880
except for the 3 spots where black venom

07:14:20.880 --> 07:14:22.259
was eating through her wing.

07:14:22.319 --> 07:14:25.139
Glory rushed to her side and found

07:14:25.139 --> 07:14:28.200
grandeur opposite her, grabbing Kingaju's

07:14:28.200 --> 07:14:28.619
talons.

07:14:28.619 --> 07:14:30.659
Grandeur's face was horrified.

07:14:30.720 --> 07:14:32.220
Help her.

07:14:32.279 --> 07:14:33.419
Glory yelled.

07:14:33.479 --> 07:14:35.639
She remembered what Jambu had told her

07:14:35.639 --> 07:14:37.799
about how a relative's venom would

07:14:37.799 --> 07:14:38.759
counteract your own.

07:14:38.819 --> 07:14:40.740
Who's related to you?

07:14:40.740 --> 07:14:41.700
Get them over here.

07:14:41.819 --> 07:14:43.740
I don't know.

07:14:43.799 --> 07:14:45.659
Grandeur said hopelessly.

07:14:45.720 --> 07:14:48.180
I haven't had any eggs in decades.

07:14:48.240 --> 07:14:50.819
I haven't tried matching venom with

07:14:50.819 --> 07:14:51.840
anyone in so long.

07:14:51.900 --> 07:14:54.419
I don't think there's anyone related to

07:14:54.419 --> 07:14:54.840
me anymore.

07:14:54.900 --> 07:14:58.319
That's insane, Glory shouted.

07:14:58.380 --> 07:15:00.779
Why can't you dragons keep track of these

07:15:00.779 --> 07:15:01.020
things?

07:15:01.080 --> 07:15:03.180
You must have had dragonettes at some

07:15:03.180 --> 07:15:05.340
point, and they must have had dragonettes

07:15:05.340 --> 07:15:05.520
too.

07:15:05.580 --> 07:15:08.459
Maybe, but no one has.

07:15:08.700 --> 07:15:12.720
Kinkaju shrieked, a high wailing sound of

07:15:12.720 --> 07:15:13.259
agony.

07:15:13.319 --> 07:15:15.060
Start trying.

07:15:15.060 --> 07:15:16.259
Glory cried.

07:15:16.319 --> 07:15:17.279
Try everyone.

07:15:17.340 --> 07:15:18.000
Try me.

07:15:18.060 --> 07:15:21.119
She grabbed the easel and spat a messy

07:15:21.119 --> 07:15:22.500
puddle of venom on the corner.

07:15:22.560 --> 07:15:25.139
The wood hissed and melted, as if it were

07:15:25.139 --> 07:15:26.520
burning from the inside.

07:15:26.520 --> 07:15:28.319
Grandeur didn't hesitate.

07:15:28.380 --> 07:15:30.599
She sprayed her venom right on top of

07:15:30.599 --> 07:15:31.259
glories.

07:15:31.319 --> 07:15:33.299
And the melting stopped.

07:15:33.360 --> 07:15:36.720
Glory didn't have time for the shocked

07:15:36.720 --> 07:15:38.939
expression on grandeur's face.

07:15:39.000 --> 07:15:41.340
She couldn't risk trying to aim neatly

07:15:41.340 --> 07:15:43.740
for the same 3 spots where Grandeur's

07:15:43.740 --> 07:15:45.240
venom had hit Kinkaju.

07:15:45.360 --> 07:15:47.159
She might end up causing far more

07:15:47.159 --> 07:15:47.639
damage.

07:15:47.700 --> 07:15:51.000
Quickly, she ripped 3 leaves off the vine

07:15:51.000 --> 07:15:53.340
below her, dipped them in the puddle of

07:15:53.340 --> 07:15:55.139
her own venom, and stuck them to

07:15:55.139 --> 07:15:56.159
Kinkaju's wounds.

07:15:56.220 --> 07:15:59.400
The sizzling sound faded, and the black

07:15:59.400 --> 07:16:00.900
acid stopped spreading.

07:16:00.959 --> 07:16:03.119
You're all right.

07:16:03.180 --> 07:16:05.099
You're going to be all right.

07:16:05.159 --> 07:16:08.279
Glory said to Kinkachu, lifting the

07:16:08.279 --> 07:16:09.900
dragonette's head in her talons.

07:16:10.020 --> 07:16:12.659
She realized the little dragon had

07:16:12.659 --> 07:16:13.319
fainted.

07:16:13.560 --> 07:16:17.220
Also, grandeur was staring at her, as if

07:16:17.220 --> 07:16:19.319
sloths were parading out of glory's

07:16:19.319 --> 07:16:19.560
ears.

07:16:19.619 --> 07:16:22.020
What, Glory said.

07:16:22.080 --> 07:16:24.599
So I'm your granddaughter, or great

07:16:24.599 --> 07:16:25.680
grandniece or something?

07:16:25.740 --> 07:16:27.779
It's not like anyone around here really

07:16:27.779 --> 07:16:28.560
cares, right?

07:16:28.619 --> 07:16:32.159
I do, said grandeur.

07:16:32.220 --> 07:16:35.279
Because it means that you are descended

07:16:35.279 --> 07:16:38.340
from the original line of Rain Wing

07:16:38.340 --> 07:16:38.939
Queens.

07:16:39.000 --> 07:16:42.360
And so I am not the last one worthy of

07:16:42.360 --> 07:16:43.619
the throne after all.

07:16:43.619 --> 07:16:46.020
Glory blinked at her.

07:16:46.080 --> 07:16:49.200
I didn't think anyone cared about royal

07:16:49.200 --> 07:16:49.619
blood here.

07:16:49.680 --> 07:16:53.520
Nobody but me, said grandeur.

07:16:53.580 --> 07:16:56.819
We used to keep track of the royal eggs

07:16:56.819 --> 07:17:00.299
but my daughters were useless, so we

07:17:00.299 --> 07:17:03.240
merged our eggs with the tribes, hoping

07:17:03.240 --> 07:17:05.580
to find successors who were queens in

07:17:05.580 --> 07:17:07.560
spirit, if not blood.

07:17:07.619 --> 07:17:10.380
There were a few who might have been

07:17:10.380 --> 07:17:12.479
great if they'd ever tried for the

07:17:12.479 --> 07:17:12.840
throne.

07:17:12.959 --> 07:17:16.380
But the truth is, I've never found a

07:17:16.380 --> 07:17:18.840
dragonette who both wanted to be queen

07:17:18.840 --> 07:17:20.159
and deserved to be.

07:17:20.279 --> 07:17:25.139
Until now, She stood up, and faced

07:17:25.139 --> 07:17:27.479
magnificent, like an enormous storm

07:17:27.479 --> 07:17:27.900
cloud.

07:17:27.959 --> 07:17:30.360
I forfeit.

07:17:30.419 --> 07:17:32.340
Kinkaju wins.

07:17:32.400 --> 07:17:33.720
What?

07:17:33.840 --> 07:17:35.639
Magnificent shrieked.

07:17:35.700 --> 07:17:37.380
Did you hear that?

07:17:37.439 --> 07:17:39.479
Glory said to Kingaju.

07:17:39.540 --> 07:17:40.740
You won.

07:17:40.799 --> 07:17:44.099
The dragonette's eyes fluttered open, and

07:17:44.099 --> 07:17:45.419
she managed a smile.

07:17:45.479 --> 07:17:47.340
That is.

07:17:47.759 --> 07:17:51.299
Super cool, she whispered.

07:17:51.419 --> 07:17:55.200
Tamarin came up behind them and slid her

07:17:55.200 --> 07:17:57.959
wing under Kingaju's head, so glory could

07:17:57.959 --> 07:17:59.340
stand up next to grandeur.

07:17:59.400 --> 07:18:01.500
She felt dizzy with disbelief.

07:18:01.619 --> 07:18:04.860
It's my throne anyway.

07:18:04.919 --> 07:18:06.720
Grandeur said to Magnificent.

07:18:06.779 --> 07:18:09.959
I have merely tolerated all of you on it

07:18:09.959 --> 07:18:12.599
because I thought experience might

07:18:12.599 --> 07:18:14.700
transform you into worthy queens.

07:18:14.759 --> 07:18:18.360
She shot a disgusted look at dazzling

07:18:18.360 --> 07:18:20.639
exquisite, and fruit bat.

07:18:20.700 --> 07:18:24.240
That theory turned out to be quite

07:18:24.240 --> 07:18:24.599
wrong.

07:18:24.659 --> 07:18:28.259
You don't know anything about this dragon

07:18:28.259 --> 07:18:30.900
magnificent complained, pointing at

07:18:30.900 --> 07:18:31.319
glory.

07:18:31.380 --> 07:18:34.860
I know she'll be a better queen than you

07:18:34.919 --> 07:18:36.299
said grandeur.

07:18:36.360 --> 07:18:39.479
She turned to the assembled tribe with a

07:18:39.479 --> 07:18:40.139
sweeping gesture.

07:18:40.200 --> 07:18:46.319
Behold, your new queen, queen glory of

07:18:46.319 --> 07:18:47.400
the rain wings.

07:18:47.520 --> 07:18:49.560
And they cheered.

07:18:49.619 --> 07:18:54.299
Glory stepped back, dazzled, as what

07:18:54.299 --> 07:18:56.819
looked like the whole tribe rose into the

07:18:56.819 --> 07:18:59.340
air, beating their wings and singing out

07:18:59.340 --> 07:19:00.000
joyfully.

07:19:00.060 --> 07:19:03.659
The rainbow of different colors was swept

07:19:03.659 --> 07:19:06.060
away on a tide of sunflower gold

07:19:06.060 --> 07:19:08.279
excitement, and Glory thought to

07:19:08.279 --> 07:19:08.700
herself.

07:19:08.759 --> 07:19:10.439
Wow.

07:19:10.500 --> 07:19:12.599
I'm a queen.

07:19:12.659 --> 07:19:15.479
Queen Glory of the Rain Wings.

07:19:15.540 --> 07:19:18.119
That'll be my name in the history

07:19:18.119 --> 07:19:18.840
scrolls.

07:19:18.959 --> 07:19:20.759
Not glory the mistake.

07:19:20.880 --> 07:19:25.020
Or glory the lazy rain wing, or glory you

07:19:25.020 --> 07:19:27.180
could never be as good as some nameless

07:19:27.180 --> 07:19:29.459
sky wing who died 6 years ago.

07:19:29.520 --> 07:19:32.939
I'm responsible for all these dragons

07:19:32.939 --> 07:19:33.299
now.

07:19:33.360 --> 07:19:36.659
We can rescue the missing rain wings, and

07:19:36.659 --> 07:19:39.000
make sure no more dragonets ever get lost

07:19:39.000 --> 07:19:39.360
again.

07:19:39.419 --> 07:19:42.540
Starfly can help me teach them all how to

07:19:42.540 --> 07:19:43.200
read and write.

07:19:43.259 --> 07:19:44.939
I'll protect them.

07:19:45.000 --> 07:19:46.619
I'll lead them.

07:19:46.680 --> 07:19:51.659
I'll make them, us, a tribe we can be

07:19:51.659 --> 07:19:52.319
proud of.

07:19:52.439 --> 07:19:56.220
Glory, the queen who chose her own

07:19:56.220 --> 07:19:59.279
destiny, saved her subjects, and turned

07:19:59.279 --> 07:20:01.740
her tribe into the greatest dragons in

07:20:01.740 --> 07:20:02.880
all of Pyria.

07:20:02.939 --> 07:20:05.040
Speech!

07:20:05.159 --> 07:20:07.799
Jambu demanded, barreling into her.

07:20:07.860 --> 07:20:10.680
His scales were a pink so vibrant.

07:20:10.799 --> 07:20:12.720
It almost hurt her eyes to look at him.

07:20:12.779 --> 07:20:15.419
Don't you start.

07:20:15.479 --> 07:20:17.340
Luckily, no one would hear me over all

07:20:17.340 --> 07:20:20.340
this noise, Glory said, with a wave at

07:20:20.340 --> 07:20:21.540
her jubilant subjects.

07:20:21.599 --> 07:20:23.700
She gave her brother an affectionate

07:20:23.700 --> 07:20:26.279
shove, and he wound his tail around hers

07:20:26.279 --> 07:20:28.319
for a moment, and she didn't even mind.

07:20:28.380 --> 07:20:31.319
As he bounded off to assault someone

07:20:31.319 --> 07:20:33.779
else's eyes, she felt movement at her

07:20:33.779 --> 07:20:35.700
wing and turned, thinking it was

07:20:35.700 --> 07:20:36.419
Kinkachu.

07:20:36.479 --> 07:20:37.500
But it was sunny.

07:20:37.560 --> 07:20:41.340
Sunbeams danced on her gold scales as the

07:20:41.340 --> 07:20:42.779
little sandwing beamed at her.

07:20:42.840 --> 07:20:45.000
You did it, she said.

07:20:45.060 --> 07:20:48.060
Not by myself, said Glory.

07:20:48.119 --> 07:20:50.400
I needed these dragons to make it

07:20:50.400 --> 07:20:50.639
happen.

07:20:50.700 --> 07:20:53.759
She spread her wings to encompass Jambu

07:20:53.759 --> 07:20:56.220
and Mangrove, but they were bouncing

07:20:56.220 --> 07:20:57.659
around in excitement.

07:20:57.720 --> 07:21:00.900
Tamaron was hugging Kinkaju, and even the

07:21:00.900 --> 07:21:02.880
wounded dragonette was pale pink with

07:21:02.880 --> 07:21:03.119
joy.

07:21:03.180 --> 07:21:08.520
This is so unfair, tsunami said, landing

07:21:08.520 --> 07:21:09.240
beside them.

07:21:09.299 --> 07:21:10.740
She sighed dramatically.

07:21:10.799 --> 07:21:13.619
This was supposed to be my story.

07:21:13.740 --> 07:21:16.979
Stupid sea wings, already having a decent

07:21:16.979 --> 07:21:17.220
queen.

07:21:17.279 --> 07:21:20.759
Maybe you'll still be the sea wing queen

07:21:20.759 --> 07:21:22.080
one day, Glory said.

07:21:22.139 --> 07:21:24.599
And then I can give you tips on how to be

07:21:24.599 --> 07:21:25.740
majestic and brilliant.

07:21:25.799 --> 07:21:27.540
They grinned at each other.

07:21:27.599 --> 07:21:30.540
This just proves what I've always said

07:21:30.540 --> 07:21:32.220
tsunami observed.

07:21:32.279 --> 07:21:34.799
Who needs a prophecy to tell you how to

07:21:34.799 --> 07:21:36.299
make an awesome destiny?

07:21:36.360 --> 07:21:39.000
True, Glory said.

07:21:39.060 --> 07:21:40.799
Take that prophecy.

07:21:40.860 --> 07:21:42.060
You're not about me?

07:21:42.119 --> 07:21:44.099
Well, I'm not all about you either.

07:21:44.159 --> 07:21:47.279
Sunny fluttered her wings like a settling

07:21:47.279 --> 07:21:47.880
butterfly.

07:21:47.939 --> 07:21:50.819
We still need you though, she said.

07:21:50.880 --> 07:21:53.639
You're still one of us, and no one will

07:21:53.639 --> 07:21:55.259
ever convince me otherwise.

07:21:55.319 --> 07:21:58.200
Glory brushed Sonny's wing with hers.

07:21:58.319 --> 07:22:00.840
Feeling a warmth that wasn't coming from

07:22:00.840 --> 07:22:02.159
the sand wings scales.

07:22:02.220 --> 07:22:05.819
The 1st thing we have to do is rescue the

07:22:05.819 --> 07:22:07.979
rain wings from the night kingdom, she

07:22:07.979 --> 07:22:10.619
said, which means turning these dragons

07:22:10.619 --> 07:22:12.180
into an army as fast as possible.

07:22:12.240 --> 07:22:13.979
Tsunami can help with that.

07:22:14.040 --> 07:22:18.479
Yes, I can, tsunami said, flexing her

07:22:18.479 --> 07:22:18.840
claws.

07:22:18.900 --> 07:22:22.560
Well, actually, Sonny said, I was

07:22:22.560 --> 07:22:23.639
thinking maybe there's another.

07:22:23.939 --> 07:22:26.700
The sound of branches thrashing overhead

07:22:26.700 --> 07:22:28.020
made glory spin around.

07:22:28.139 --> 07:22:30.659
Clay came barreling through the trees

07:22:30.659 --> 07:22:33.360
trailing broken twigs and wrestling loops

07:22:33.360 --> 07:22:34.319
of vines out of his way.

07:22:34.380 --> 07:22:37.560
He stared around wildly at the rejoicing

07:22:37.560 --> 07:22:40.319
rain wings, spotted glory, and crashed

07:22:40.319 --> 07:22:41.340
down in front of her.

07:22:41.400 --> 07:22:42.599
Clay!

07:22:42.659 --> 07:22:43.680
Sonny cried.

07:22:43.740 --> 07:22:44.639
What is it?

07:22:44.700 --> 07:22:45.419
What's wrong?

07:22:45.540 --> 07:22:48.299
Horrible images popped into Glory's head

07:22:48.299 --> 07:22:51.119
of her friend's hurt, of a night wing

07:22:51.119 --> 07:22:53.159
army, marching through the tunnel to

07:22:53.159 --> 07:22:54.180
invade the rainforest.

07:22:54.240 --> 07:22:57.540
It's Starflight, Clay said.

07:22:57.599 --> 07:22:58.860
He's disappeared.

07:22:58.919 --> 07:23:02.340
He shot an anxious look at glory, and she

07:23:02.340 --> 07:23:04.139
remembered the argument she'd had with

07:23:04.139 --> 07:23:05.939
Starflight the last time she'd seen him.

07:23:06.000 --> 07:23:08.880
Surely he hadn't...

07:23:08.880 --> 07:23:09.540
Glory.

07:23:09.599 --> 07:23:11.880
I'm sorry, said Clay.

07:23:11.939 --> 07:23:14.279
But I think he's gone to warn the night

07:23:14.279 --> 07:23:14.759
wings.

07:23:14.819 --> 07:23:19.139
Epilogue.

07:23:19.259 --> 07:23:24.419
I hate this place, Flame said, glowering

07:23:24.419 --> 07:23:26.279
at the dark rock dust caught between his

07:23:26.279 --> 07:23:29.159
claws. hate, hate, hate it.

07:23:29.220 --> 07:23:32.759
I hate it more, Squid moaned.

07:23:32.819 --> 07:23:34.200
He coughed gloomily.

07:23:34.259 --> 07:23:38.279
My scales feel so dry, my talons hurt, and

07:23:38.279 --> 07:23:39.119
I'm hungry.

07:23:39.180 --> 07:23:42.779
I hate that big old stupid, horrible

07:23:42.779 --> 07:23:43.560
night wing.

07:23:43.619 --> 07:23:45.000
Viper hissed.

07:23:45.060 --> 07:23:47.939
I can't believe my dad let him take me.

07:23:48.000 --> 07:23:51.119
Squid edged to the mouth of the cave and

07:23:51.119 --> 07:23:53.520
stared at the smoky sky, as if hoping

07:23:53.520 --> 07:23:55.860
Nautilus would appear suddenly, winging

07:23:55.860 --> 07:23:56.340
to his rescue.

07:23:56.400 --> 07:24:00.659
Oh, stop, fate speaker said, flicking her

07:24:00.659 --> 07:24:00.959
tail.

07:24:01.020 --> 07:24:02.340
It's not that bad.

07:24:02.400 --> 07:24:06.779
Actually, it really was that bad, but she

07:24:06.779 --> 07:24:08.159
certainly wasn't going to admit it to

07:24:08.159 --> 07:24:08.580
these four.

07:24:08.639 --> 07:24:12.299
She had never, ever imagined that the

07:24:12.299 --> 07:24:15.720
Knight Kingdom, her kingdom, would be so

07:24:15.720 --> 07:24:19.259
dark and smelly, and that all the dragons

07:24:19.259 --> 07:24:21.900
here would be so incredibly cranky.

07:24:21.959 --> 07:24:24.540
It was as if being the most awesome

07:24:24.540 --> 07:24:27.000
dragons in the world didn't even make

07:24:27.000 --> 07:24:27.659
them happy at all.

07:24:27.720 --> 07:24:30.419
But hey, she was home.

07:24:30.479 --> 07:24:32.939
And Maro Sear said she was part of a

07:24:32.939 --> 07:24:35.340
prophecy, which was even more awesome

07:24:35.340 --> 07:24:36.779
than being a night wing.

07:24:36.840 --> 07:24:38.639
So what was there to complain about

07:24:38.639 --> 07:24:39.180
really?

07:24:39.240 --> 07:24:42.060
I want to die.

07:24:42.180 --> 07:24:43.979
Ochre groaned.

07:24:44.040 --> 07:24:46.200
The mudwing dragonette had been lying on

07:24:46.200 --> 07:24:48.419
the floor of the cave for practically the

07:24:48.419 --> 07:24:50.400
entire day since they'd been dumped here

07:24:50.400 --> 07:24:51.299
by Morrow's year.

07:24:51.419 --> 07:24:54.479
I want you to die too, Flame

07:24:54.479 --> 07:24:55.740
volunteered.

07:24:55.799 --> 07:24:57.180
You smell ghastly.

07:24:57.299 --> 07:24:58.560
Viper agreed.

07:24:58.619 --> 07:25:01.200
I don't think I should have eaten that

07:25:01.200 --> 07:25:01.919
dead thing.

07:25:01.979 --> 07:25:03.599
Okra mumbled.

07:25:03.659 --> 07:25:07.680
He paused, then added, Or all of your

07:25:07.680 --> 07:25:08.400
dead things.

07:25:08.459 --> 07:25:12.659
Well, I wasn't going to eat it, Squid

07:25:12.659 --> 07:25:13.619
said snootily.

07:25:13.680 --> 07:25:15.419
We are on an island.

07:25:15.479 --> 07:25:18.119
I think someone should be able to bring

07:25:18.119 --> 07:25:20.700
me a fresh fish, considering who my

07:25:20.700 --> 07:25:23.099
father is, and the fact that I'm a

07:25:23.099 --> 07:25:24.360
dragonette of destiny.

07:25:24.419 --> 07:25:25.799
I mean really.

07:25:25.799 --> 07:25:28.860
Fate speakers shifted on her talons

07:25:28.860 --> 07:25:29.700
uncomfortably.

07:25:29.759 --> 07:25:32.279
She hadn't really liked the look of what

07:25:32.279 --> 07:25:34.139
the grumpy Nightwings had brought them to

07:25:34.139 --> 07:25:34.500
eat either.

07:25:34.560 --> 07:25:37.619
Why was everything so decayed and

07:25:37.619 --> 07:25:38.520
horrible smelling?

07:25:38.580 --> 07:25:42.060
Have a vision, she told herself.

07:25:42.119 --> 07:25:43.560
That'll make you feel better.

07:25:43.619 --> 07:25:46.799
She closed her eyes and scrunched up her

07:25:46.799 --> 07:25:49.500
forehead and concentrated as hard as she

07:25:49.500 --> 07:25:49.680
could.

07:25:49.740 --> 07:25:52.259
I foresee.

07:25:52.319 --> 07:25:55.080
She said, in a portentous tone.

07:25:55.139 --> 07:26:00.240
No, shouted Viper, spare us, squid

07:26:00.240 --> 07:26:00.840
cried.

07:26:00.900 --> 07:26:04.020
Okra moaned.

07:26:04.080 --> 07:26:07.860
Now, I want you both to die, said Flame.

07:26:07.919 --> 07:26:11.819
Oh, shush, fate speaker said, with her

07:26:11.819 --> 07:26:12.779
eyes still closed.

07:26:12.900 --> 07:26:15.240
I'm using my powers.

07:26:15.299 --> 07:26:22.860
Behold, I foresee, uh, Walrus, a walrus

07:26:22.860 --> 07:26:25.619
in our future, an entire walrus for us to

07:26:25.619 --> 07:26:25.919
eat.

07:26:25.979 --> 07:26:29.520
Why are you torturing me?

07:26:29.580 --> 07:26:31.080
Ogre wailed.

07:26:31.139 --> 07:26:34.619
We hardly ever had walrus even when we

07:26:34.619 --> 07:26:37.259
live next to the sea, Squid pointed out.

07:26:37.319 --> 07:26:40.200
Despite the fact that you predicted we

07:26:40.200 --> 07:26:43.619
would just about every week, Viper added

07:26:43.619 --> 07:26:44.220
sourly.

07:26:44.279 --> 07:26:48.779
My visions are not always precise, fate

07:26:48.779 --> 07:26:49.860
speaker said breezily.

07:26:49.919 --> 07:26:53.099
It does not say when this walrus will

07:26:53.099 --> 07:26:55.979
arrive, only that it will, and then we

07:26:55.979 --> 07:26:58.259
shall feast, and everything will be

07:26:58.259 --> 07:26:58.919
wonderful again.

07:26:59.040 --> 07:27:01.860
When has it ever been wonderful before?

07:27:01.919 --> 07:27:03.540
Flame snarled.

07:27:03.599 --> 07:27:06.599
Do us a favor and stop sharing your

07:27:06.599 --> 07:27:07.740
stupid powers with us.

07:27:07.799 --> 07:27:09.360
Viper snapped.

07:27:09.479 --> 07:27:12.060
Grumpy, ungrateful lizards.

07:27:12.119 --> 07:27:15.119
Fate speaker sat down in the mouth of the

07:27:15.119 --> 07:27:17.580
cave and turned up her snout, ignoring

07:27:17.580 --> 07:27:18.000
everyone.

07:27:18.060 --> 07:27:20.520
If they couldn't appreciate the gifts she

07:27:20.520 --> 07:27:22.979
bestowed upon them, well, then, fine.

07:27:23.040 --> 07:27:25.500
She would just keep her visions to

07:27:25.500 --> 07:27:28.080
herself, until she had another great one

07:27:28.080 --> 07:27:28.500
anyway.

07:27:28.560 --> 07:27:32.220
The night kingdom volcanoes stretched

07:27:32.220 --> 07:27:35.639
below her. dark and craggy, and swarming

07:27:35.639 --> 07:27:37.020
with black dragons.

07:27:37.080 --> 07:27:39.060
There weren't nearly as many night wings

07:27:39.060 --> 07:27:39.840
as she'd expected.

07:27:39.900 --> 07:27:42.360
It felt more like the talons of peace

07:27:42.360 --> 07:27:43.680
camp than a whole kingdom.

07:27:43.740 --> 07:27:46.080
But the dragonettes hadn't exactly been

07:27:46.080 --> 07:27:46.680
given a tour.

07:27:46.740 --> 07:27:48.840
They hadn't even been taken to the big

07:27:48.840 --> 07:27:51.659
fortress, which fate speaker assumed was

07:27:51.659 --> 07:27:52.619
where the Queen lived.

07:27:52.680 --> 07:27:55.259
Nor had they been introduced to the night

07:27:55.259 --> 07:27:57.900
wing queen, or anyone, actually.

07:27:57.959 --> 07:28:00.720
Maru Sier had stuffed them in this high

07:28:00.720 --> 07:28:02.340
cave and stomped away again.

07:28:02.400 --> 07:28:05.400
Fate speaker squinted down at the black

07:28:05.400 --> 07:28:06.959
sand beach in the distance.

07:28:07.020 --> 07:28:10.259
A cave was set into the cliff there, and

07:28:10.259 --> 07:28:13.200
earlier, she'd seen several dragons swoop

07:28:13.200 --> 07:28:13.619
into it.

07:28:13.680 --> 07:28:16.919
Now they were coming out again, and they

07:28:16.919 --> 07:28:18.659
had a night wing dragonette in their

07:28:18.659 --> 07:28:19.319
talons.

07:28:19.380 --> 07:28:21.840
He looked about the same age as fate

07:28:21.840 --> 07:28:23.939
speaker, and he was unconscious.

07:28:24.000 --> 07:28:27.299
His wings drooped, and his claws dragged

07:28:27.299 --> 07:28:27.720
in the sand.

07:28:27.779 --> 07:28:30.479
Her scales began to tingle in that way

07:28:30.479 --> 07:28:32.520
that she was sure meant a sign from the

07:28:32.520 --> 07:28:32.939
universe.

07:28:33.000 --> 07:28:35.400
There was something important about that

07:28:35.400 --> 07:28:36.180
dragonette.

07:28:36.240 --> 07:28:40.799
I'm having another vision, she

07:28:40.799 --> 07:28:41.279
announced.

07:28:41.340 --> 07:28:43.979
The bones left over from Ogre's dinner

07:28:43.979 --> 07:28:45.779
splatted on the ledge beside her.

07:28:45.840 --> 07:28:47.939
She was lucky that Squid didn't have very

07:28:47.939 --> 07:28:48.419
good aim.

07:28:48.479 --> 07:28:52.200
I'm just letting you know that I'm not

07:28:52.200 --> 07:28:55.680
telling you about it, she said, even

07:28:55.680 --> 07:28:58.500
though I'm sure it's very significant.

07:28:58.560 --> 07:29:00.840
The others ignored her.

07:29:00.900 --> 07:29:02.819
Which they did way too often.

07:29:02.880 --> 07:29:05.580
Well, it didn't matter.

07:29:05.639 --> 07:29:08.340
She was home with her own kind now.

07:29:08.459 --> 07:29:10.919
She had a destiny to follow.

07:29:10.979 --> 07:29:13.740
And she was sure the unconscious

07:29:13.740 --> 07:29:16.080
dragonette, who was now being carried

07:29:16.080 --> 07:29:18.299
into the fortress, would be part of it.

